P_HTM[336]="*hīnena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti …pe…**… says what is low to one who is high …*";
P_HTM[337]="*ukkaṭṭhena hīnaṃ vadeti …pe…**… says what is high to one who is low …*";
P_HTM[338]="*ukkaṭṭhena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, paṇḍitaṃ byattaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ—**… says what is high to one who is high—one who is wise, one who is competent, one who is intelligent, one who is learned, one who is an expounder of the Teaching—*";
P_HTM[339]="*“paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi dhammakathikosi, natthi tuyhaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa.**saying, “You’re wise,” “You’re competent,” “You’re intelligent,” “You’re learned,” “You’re an expounder of the Teaching,” “You’re not going to a bad destination,” “You can only expect a good destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[340]="*Upasampanno anupasampannaṃ na khuṃsetukāmo na vambhetukāmo na maṅkukattukāmo, davakamyatā evaṃ vadeti, “santi idhekacce caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati …pe….**If one who is fully ordained, not wishing to revile, not wishing to insult, not wishing to humiliate someone who is not fully ordained, but wanting to have fun, says this, “There are outcasts right here,” “There are bamboo workers right here,” “There are hunters right here,” “There are carriage makers right here,” “There are waste removers right here” …*";
P_HTM[341]="*“Santi idhekacce paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā, natthi tesaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tesaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa.**… “There are wise ones right here,” “There are competent ones right here,” “There are intelligent ones right here,” “There are learned ones right here,” “There are expounders of the Teaching right here,” “There are those not going to a bad destination right here,” “There are those who can only expect a good destination right here,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[342]="*Upasampanno anupasampannaṃ na khuṃsetukāmo na vambhetukāmo na maṅkukattukāmo, davakamyatā evaṃ vadeti, “ye nūna caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati …pe….**If one who is fully ordained, not wishing to revile, not wishing to insult, not wishing to humiliate someone who is not fully ordained, but wanting to have fun, says this, “Perhaps these are outcasts,” “Perhaps these are bamboo workers,” “Perhaps these are hunters,” “Perhaps these are carriage makers,” “Perhaps these are waste removers” …*";
P_HTM[343]="*“Ye nūna paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa.**… “Perhaps these are wise ones,” “Perhaps these are competent ones,” “Perhaps these are intelligent ones,” “Perhaps these are learned ones,” “Perhaps these are expounders of the Teaching,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[344]="*Upasampanno anupasampannaṃ na khuṃsetukāmo na vambhetukāmo na maṅkukattukāmo, davakamyatā evaṃ vadeti, “na mayaṃ caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati …pe….**If one who is fully ordained, not wishing to revile, not wishing to insult, not wishing to humiliate someone who is not fully ordained, but wanting to have fun, says this, “We’re not outcasts,” “We’re not bamboo workers,” “We’re not hunters,” “We’re not carriage makers,” “We’re not waste removers” …*";
P_HTM[345]="*“Na mayaṃ paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā, natthamhākaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva amhākaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dubbhāsitassa.**… “We’re not wise ones,” “We’re not competent ones,” “We’re not intelligent ones,” “We’re not learned ones,” “We’re not expounders of the Teaching,” “We’re not going to a bad destination,” “We can only expect a good destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong speech.*";
P_HTM[346]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[347]="*atthapurekkhārassa,**if he is aiming at what is beneficial;*";
P_HTM[348]="*dhammapurekkhārassa,**if he is aiming at giving a teaching;*";
P_HTM[349]="*anusāsanipurekkhārassa,**if he is aiming at giving an instruction;*";
P_HTM[350]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[351]="*khittacittassa,**if he is deranged;*";
P_HTM[352]="*vedanāṭṭassa,**if he is overwhelmed by pain;*";
P_HTM[353]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[354]="*Omasavādasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on abusive speech, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[355]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[356]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[357]="*3. Pesuññasikkhāpada**3. The training rule on malicious talebearing*";
P_HTM[358]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[359]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharanti;**the monks from the group of six were engaged in malicious talebearing between monks who were arguing.*";
P_HTM[360]="*imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyanti, imassa bhedāya; amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyanti, amussa bhedāya.**After hearing something on one side they reported it to the other side, and vice versa, in order to create division between them.*";
P_HTM[361]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti.**In this way they started new quarrels and made existing quarrels worse.*";
P_HTM[362]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[363]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharissanti, imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyissanti, imassa bhedāya;**“How can the monks from the group of six engage in malicious talebearing between monks who are arguing?*";
P_HTM[364]="*amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyissanti, amussa bhedāya.**How can they report to one side what they have heard on the other side, and vice versa, in order to create division,*";
P_HTM[365]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti.**and in this way start new quarrels and make existing quarrels worse?”*";
P_HTM[366]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned those monks:*";
P_HTM[367]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharatha, imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyatha, imassa bhedāya, amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyatha, amussa bhedāya?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[368]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattantī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[369]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[370]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[371]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ pesuññaṃ upasaṃharissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[372]="*Imassa sutvā amussa akkhāyissatha, imassa bhedāya. Amussa sutvā imassa akkhāyissatha, amussa bhedāya.* **";
P_HTM[373]="*Tena anuppannāni ceva bhaṇḍanāni uppajjanti, uppannāni ca bhaṇḍanāni bhiyyobhāvāya vepullāya saṃvattanti.* **";
P_HTM[374]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya.**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[375]="*Pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya …pe…* **";
P_HTM[376]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[377]="*“Bhikkhupesuññe pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk engages in malicious talebearing between monks, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[378]="*Pesuññaṃ nāma**Malicious talebearing:*";
P_HTM[379]="*dvīhākārehi pesuññaṃ hoti— piyakamyassa vā bhedādhippāyassa vā.**there is malicious talebearing in two ways: for one wanting to endear himself and for one aiming at division.*";
P_HTM[380]="*Dasahākārehi pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— jātitopi, nāmatopi, gottatopi, kammatopi, sippatopi, ābādhatopi, liṅgatopi, kilesatopi, āpattitopi, akkosatopi.**One engages in malicious talebearing in ten ways: about caste, about name, about family, about occupation, about profession, about illnesses, about physical traits, about defilements, about offenses, and by name-calling.*";
P_HTM[381]="*Jāti nāma**Caste:*";
P_HTM[382]="*dve jātiyo— hīnā ca jāti ukkaṭṭhā ca jāti.**there are two kinds of castes: low castes and high castes.*";
P_HTM[383]="*Hīnā nāma jāti—**Low castes:*";
P_HTM[384]="*caṇḍālajāti venajāti nesādajāti rathakārajāti pukkusajāti. Esā hīnā nāma jāti.**outcasts, bamboo workers, hunters, carriage makers, waste removers—these are called “low castes”.*";
P_HTM[385]="*Ukkaṭṭhā nāma jāti—**High castes:*";
P_HTM[386]="*khattiyajāti brāhmaṇajāti. Esā ukkaṭṭhā nāma jāti.**aristocrats and brahmins—these are called “high castes”.*";
P_HTM[387]="*…pe….**(To be expanded as in previous rule.)*";
P_HTM[388]="*Akkoso nāma**Name-calling:*";
P_HTM[389]="*dve akkosā— hīno ca akkoso ukkaṭṭho ca akkoso.**there are two kinds of name-calling: low name-calling and high name-calling.*";
P_HTM[390]="*Hīno nāma akkoso—**Low name-calling:*";
P_HTM[391]="*“oṭṭhosi, meṇḍosi, goṇosi, gadrabhosi, tiracchānagatosi, nerayikosi; natthi tuyhaṃ sugati; duggatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti, yakārena vā bhakārena vā kāṭakoṭacikāya vā. Eso hīno nāma akkoso.**“You’re a camel,” “You’re a ram,” “You’re an ox,” “You’re a donkey,” “You’re an animal,” “You’re bound for hell,” “You’re not going to a good destination,” “You can only expect a bad destination,” or adding disparaging endings to someone’s name, or calling someone words for the male and female genitals—this is called “low name-calling”.*";
P_HTM[392]="*Ukkaṭṭho nāma akkoso—**High name-calling:*";
P_HTM[393]="*“paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi, dhammakathikosi; natthi tuyhaṃ duggati; sugatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti. Eso ukkaṭṭho nāma akkoso.**“You’re wise,” “You’re competent,” “You’re intelligent,” “You’re learned,” “You’re an expounder of the Teaching,” “You’re not going to a bad destination,” “You can only expect a good destination”—this is called “high name-calling”.*";
P_HTM[394]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘caṇḍālo veno nesādo rathakāro pukkuso’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an outcast,’ ‘He’s a bamboo worker,’ ‘He’s a hunter,’ ‘He’s a carriage maker,’ ‘He’s a waste remover,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[395]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘khattiyo brāhmaṇo’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an aristocrat,’ ‘He’s a brahmin,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[396]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘avakaṇṇako javakaṇṇako dhaniṭṭhako saviṭṭhako kulavaḍḍhako’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an Avakaṇṇaka,’ ‘He’s a Javakaṇṇaka,’ ‘He’s a Dhaniṭṭhaka,’ ‘He’s a Saviṭṭhaka,’ ‘He’s a Kulavaḍḍhaka,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[397]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘buddharakkhito dhammarakkhito saṅgharakkhito’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a Buddharakkhita,’ ‘He’s a Dhammarakkhita,’ ‘He’s a Sangharakkhita,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[398]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘kosiyo bhāradvājo’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a Kosiya,’ ‘He’s a Bhāradvāja,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[399]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘gotamo moggallāno kaccāno vāsiṭṭho’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a Gotama,’ ‘He’s a Moggallāna,’ ‘He’s a Kaccāna,’ ‘He’s a Vāsiṭṭha,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[400]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘koṭṭhako pupphachaḍḍako’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a carpenter,’ ‘He’s a waste remover,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[401]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘kassako vāṇijo gorakkho’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a farmer,’ ‘He’s a trader,’ ‘He’s a cattle keeper,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[402]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘naḷakāro kumbhakāro pesakāro cammakāro nahāpito’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a reed worker,’ ‘He’s a potter,’ ‘He’s a weaver,’ ‘He’s a leather worker,’ ‘He’s a hairdresser,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[403]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘muddiko gaṇako lekhako’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s an arithmetician,’ ‘He’s an accountant,’ ‘He’s a clerk,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[404]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘kuṭṭhiko gaṇḍiko kilāsiko sosiko apamāriko’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a leper,’ ‘He has abscesses,’ ‘He has mild leprosy,’ ‘He has tuberculosis,’ ‘He’s an epileptic,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[405]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘madhumehiko’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a diabetic,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[406]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘atidīgho atirasso atikaṇho accodāto’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s too tall,’ ‘He’s too short,’ ‘He’s too dark,’ ‘He’s too fair,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[407]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘nātidīgho nātirasso nātikaṇho nāccodāto’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s not too tall,’ ‘He’s not too short,’ ‘He’s not too dark,’ ‘He’s not too fair,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[408]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘rāgapariyuṭṭhito dosapariyuṭṭhito mohapariyuṭṭhito’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s full of sensual desire,’ ‘He’s full of ill will,’ ‘He’s full of confusion,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[409]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘vītarāgo vītadoso vītamoho’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s without sensual desire,’ ‘He’s without ill will,’ ‘He’s without confusion,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[410]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘pārājikaṃ ajjhāpanno, saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpanno, thullaccayaṃ ajjhāpanno, pācittiyaṃ ajjhāpanno, pāṭidesanīyaṃ ajjhāpanno, dukkaṭaṃ ajjhāpanno, dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpanno’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He has committed an offense entailing expulsion,’ ‘He has committed an offense entailing suspension,’ ‘He has committed a serious offense,’ ‘He has committed an offense entailing confession,’ ‘He has committed an offense entailing acknowledgment,’ ‘He has committed an offense of wrong conduct,’ ‘He has committed an offense of wrong speech,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[411]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘sotāpanno’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a stream-enterer,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[412]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘oṭṭho meṇḍo goṇo gadrabho tiracchānagato nerayiko, natthi tassa sugati, duggatiyeva tassa pāṭikaṅkhā’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s a camel,’ ‘He’s a ram,’ ‘He’s an ox,’ ‘He’s a donkey,’ ‘He’s an animal,’ ‘He’s bound for hell,’ ‘He’s not going to a good destination,’ ‘He can only expect a bad destination,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[413]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo taṃ ‘paṇḍito byatto medhāvī bahussuto dhammakathiko, natthi tassa duggati, sugatiyeva tassa pāṭikaṅkhā’ti bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says this about you, ‘He’s wise,’ ‘He’s competent,’ ‘He’s intelligent,’ ‘He’s learned,’ ‘He’s an expounder of the Teaching,’ ‘He’s not going to a bad destination,’ ‘He can only expect a good destination,’” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[414]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘santi idhekacce caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā, pukkusā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘There are outcasts right here,’ ‘There are bamboo workers right here,’ ‘There are hunters right here,’ ‘There are carriage makers right here,’ ‘There are waste removers right here,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[415]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘santi idhekacce khattiyā brāhmaṇā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa …pe….**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘There are aristocrats right here,’ ‘There are brahmins right here,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[416]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘santi idhekacce paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā, natthi tesaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tesaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘There are wise ones right here,’ ‘There are competent ones right here,’ ‘There are intelligent ones right here,’ ‘There are learned ones right here,’ ‘There are expounders of the Teaching right here,’ ‘There are those not going to a bad destination right here,’ ‘There are those who can only expect a good destination right here,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[417]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘ye nūna caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘Perhaps these are outcasts,’ ‘Perhaps these are bamboo workers,’ ‘Perhaps these are hunters,’ ‘Perhaps these are carriage makers,’ ‘Perhaps these are waste removers,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[418]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘ye nūna paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘Perhaps these are wise ones,’ ‘Perhaps these are competent ones,’ ‘Perhaps these are intelligent ones,’ ‘Perhaps these are learned ones,’ ‘Perhaps these are expounders of the Teaching,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[419]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘na mayaṃ caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘We’re not outcasts,’ ‘We’re not bamboo workers,’ ‘We’re not hunters,’ ‘We’re not carriage makers,’ ‘We’re not waste removers,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[420]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati— “itthannāmo ‘na mayaṃ paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā, natthamhākaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva amhākaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā’ti bhaṇati, na so aññaṃ bhaṇati, taññeva bhaṇatī”ti. Āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing by saying to yet another who is fully ordained, “So-and-so says, ‘We’re not wise ones,’ ‘We’re not competent ones,’ ‘We’re not intelligent ones,’ ‘We’re not learned ones,’ ‘We’re not expounders of the Teaching,’ ‘We’re not going to a bad destination,’ ‘We can only expect a good destination,’ and he’s not speaking about someone else, he’s speaking about you,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[421]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati; āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to yet another who is fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[422]="*Upasampanno upasampannassa sutvā anupasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from another who is fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to one who is not fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[423]="*Upasampanno anupasampannassa sutvā upasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from one who is not fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to another who is fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[424]="*Upasampanno anupasampannassa sutvā anupasampannassa pesuññaṃ upasaṃharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If one who is fully ordained, after hearing it from one who is not fully ordained, engages in malicious talebearing to another who is not fully ordained, then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[425]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[426]="*napiyakamyassa,**if he does not want to endear himself*";
P_HTM[427]="*nabhedādhippāyassa,**and he is not aiming at division;*";
P_HTM[428]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[429]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[430]="*Pesuññasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on malicious talebearing, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[431]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[432]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[433]="*4. Padasodhammasikkhāpada**4. The training rule on memorizing the Teaching*";
P_HTM[434]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[435]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācenti.**the monks from the group of six were instructing lay followers to memorize the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[436]="*Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti.**Those lay followers became disrespectful, undeferential, and rude toward the monks.*";
P_HTM[437]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[438]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācessanti.**“How can the monks from the group of six instruct lay followers to memorize the Teaching?”*";
P_HTM[439]="*Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharantī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[440]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[441]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācetha;**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[442]="*upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharantī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[443]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[444]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[445]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, upāsake padaso dhammaṃ vācessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?”*";
P_HTM[446]="*Upāsakā bhikkhūsu agāravā appatissā asabhāgavuttikā viharanti.* **";
P_HTM[447]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[448]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[449]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannaṃ padaso dhammaṃ vāceyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk instructs a person who is not fully ordained to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[450]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[451]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[452]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[453]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[454]="*Anupasampanno nāma**A person who is not fully ordained:*";
P_HTM[455]="*bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma.**anyone except a fully ordained monk or a fully ordained nun.*";
P_HTM[456]="*Padaso nāma**To memorize:*";
P_HTM[457]="*padaṃ, anupadaṃ, anvakkharaṃ, anubyañjanaṃ.**a line, the next line, syllable by syllable, the next phrase.*";
P_HTM[458]="*Padaṃ nāma**A line:*";
P_HTM[459]="*ekato paṭṭhapetvā ekato osāpenti.**they start together and finish together.*";
P_HTM[460]="*Anupadaṃ nāma**The next line:*";
P_HTM[461]="*pāṭekkaṃ paṭṭhapetvā ekato osāpenti.**one of them starts, but they finish together.*";
P_HTM[462]="*Anvakkharaṃ nāma**Syllable by syllable:*";
P_HTM[463]="*“rūpaṃ aniccan”ti vuccamāno, “run”ti opāteti.**when ‘_Rūpaṃ aniccaṃ_’ is being said, he prompts him, saying, ‘_rū_’.*";
P_HTM[464]="*Anubyañjanaṃ nāma**The next phrase:*";
P_HTM[465]="*“rūpaṃ aniccan”ti vuccamāno, “vedanā aniccā”ti saddaṃ nicchāreti.**when ‘_Rūpaṃ aniccaṃ_,’ is being said, the other says, ‘_Vedanā aniccā_.’*";
P_HTM[466]="*Yañca padaṃ, yañca anupadaṃ, yañca anvakkharaṃ, yañca anubyañjanaṃ—**And whatever line there is, whatever next line, whatever syllable by syllable, whatever next phrase—*";
P_HTM[467]="*sabbametaṃ padaso nāma.**this is all called “to memorize”.*";
P_HTM[468]="*Dhammo nāma**The Teaching:*";
P_HTM[469]="*buddhabhāsito, sāvakabhāsito, isibhāsito, devatābhāsito, atthūpasañhito, dhammūpasañhito.**what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[470]="*Vāceyyāti**Instructs:*";
P_HTM[471]="*padena vāceti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he instructs by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[472]="*Akkharāya vāceti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he instructs by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[473]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the person is not fully ordained, and the monk does not perceive them as such, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[474]="*Anupasampanne vematiko padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the person is not fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[475]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī padaso dhammaṃ vāceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the person is not fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as such, and he instructs them to memorize the Teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[476]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the person is fully ordained, but the monk does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[477]="*Upasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the person is fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[478]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī, anāpatti.**If the person is fully ordained, and the monk perceives them such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[479]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[480]="*ekato uddisāpento,**if they recite together;*";
P_HTM[481]="*ekato sajjhāyaṃ karonto,**if they practice together;*";
P_HTM[482]="*yebhuyyena paguṇaṃ ganthaṃ bhaṇantaṃ opāteti,**if he prompts one who is speaking a mostly familiar text;*";
P_HTM[483]="*osārentaṃ opāteti,**if he prompts one who is reciting;*";
P_HTM[484]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[485]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[486]="*Padasodhammasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on memorizing the Teaching, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[487]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[488]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[489]="*5. Sahaseyyasikkhāpada**5. The training rule on the same sleeping place*";
P_HTM[490]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine.*";
P_HTM[491]="*Tena kho pana samayena upāsakā ārāmaṃ āgacchanti dhammassavanāya.**At that time the lay followers were coming to the monastery to listen to the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[492]="*Dhamme bhāsite therā bhikkhū yathāvihāraṃ gacchanti.**When the instruction was over, the senior monks went to their own dwellings,*";
P_HTM[493]="*Navakā bhikkhū tattheva upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ upāsakehi saddhiṃ muṭṭhassatī, asampajānā, naggā, vikūjamānā, kākacchamānā seyyaṃ kappenti.**but the newly ordained monks lay down right there in the assembly hall together with the lay followers—absentminded, heedless, naked, muttering, and snoring.*";
P_HTM[494]="*Upāsakā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The lay followers complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[495]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā muṭṭhassatī asampajānā naggā vikūjamānā kākacchamānā seyyaṃ kappessantī”ti.**“How can the venerables lie down absentminded, heedless, naked, muttering, and snoring?”*";
P_HTM[496]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ upāsakānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those lay followers,*";
P_HTM[497]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[498]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū anupasampannena sahaseyyaṃ kappessantī”ti.**“How can monks lie down in the same sleeping place as people who are not fully ordained?”*";
P_HTM[499]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū te navake bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those newly ordained monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[500]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū anupasampannena sahaseyyaṃ kappentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”*";
P_HTM[501]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[502]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[503]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā anupasampannena sahaseyyaṃ kappessanti.**“How could those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[504]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[505]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[506]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannena sahaseyyaṃ kappeyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk lies down in the same sleeping place as a person who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[507]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[508]="*Atha kho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena kosambī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**After staying at Āḷavī for as long as he wanted, the Buddha set out wandering toward Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[509]="*Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena kosambī tadavasari. Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati badarikārāme.**When he eventually arrived, he stayed at the Badarikā Monastery.*";
P_HTM[510]="*Bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ rāhulaṃ etadavocuṃ—**Just then the monks there said to Venerable Rāhula,*";
P_HTM[511]="*“bhagavatā, āvuso rāhula, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—‘na anupasampannena sahaseyyā kappetabbā’ti.**“Rāhula, the Buddha has laid down a training rule that we can’t lie down in the same sleeping place as a person who’s not fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[512]="*Seyyaṃ, āvuso rāhula, jānāhī”ti.**Please find another sleeping place.”*";
P_HTM[513]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo seyyaṃ alabhamāno vaccakuṭiyā seyyaṃ kappesi.**Since Rāhula was not able to find a sleeping place, he lay down in the restroom.*";
P_HTM[514]="*Atha kho bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya yena vaccakuṭi tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ukkāsi.**Then, after rising early in the morning, the Buddha went to the restroom, where he cleared his throat.*";
P_HTM[515]="*Āyasmāpi rāhulo ukkāsi.**Rāhula, too, cleared his throat.*";
P_HTM[516]="*“Ko etthā”ti?**“Who’s there?”*";
P_HTM[517]="*“Ahaṃ, bhagavā, rāhulo”ti.**“It’s me, Sir, Rāhula.”*";
P_HTM[518]="*“Kissa tvaṃ, rāhula, idha nisinnosī”ti?**“Why are you sitting here, Rāhula?”*";
P_HTM[519]="*Atha kho āyasmā rāhulo bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Rāhula told the Buddha what had happened.*";
P_HTM[520]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[521]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, anupasampannena dirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ kappetuṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to lie down in the same sleeping place as a person who isn’t fully ordained for two or three nights.*";
P_HTM[522]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[523]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannena uttaridirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk lies down more than two or three nights in the same sleeping place as a person who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[524]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[525]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[526]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[527]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[528]="*Anupasampanno nāma**A person who is not fully ordained:*";
P_HTM[529]="*bhikkhuṃ ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma.**anyone except a fully ordained monk.*";
P_HTM[530]="*Uttaridirattatirattanti**more than two or three nights:*";
P_HTM[531]="*atirekadirattatirattaṃ.**in excess of two or three nights.*";
P_HTM[532]="*Sahāti**Same:*";
P_HTM[533]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[534]="*Seyyā nāma**Sleeping place:*";
P_HTM[535]="*sabbacchannā, sabbaparicchannā, yebhuyyenacchannā, yebhuyyena paricchannā.**fully roofed, fully walled; mostly roofed, mostly walled.*";
P_HTM[536]="*Seyyaṃ kappeyyāti**Lies down in the same sleeping place:*";
P_HTM[537]="*catutthe divase atthaṅgate sūriye, anupasampanne nipanne, bhikkhu nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**at dawn on the fourth day: if he lies down when the person who is not fully ordained is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[538]="*Bhikkhu nipanne, anupasampanno nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the person who is not fully ordained lies down when he is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[539]="*Ubho vā nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[540]="*Uṭṭhahitvā punappunaṃ nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[541]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī uttaridirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they are not fully ordained, and the monk does not perceive them as such, and he lies down more than two or three nights in the same sleeping place as them, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[542]="*Anupasampanne vematiko uttaridirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they are not fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, and he lies down more than two or three nights in the same sleeping place as them, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[543]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī uttaridirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they are is not fully ordained, but the monk perceives them as such, and he lies down more than two or three nights in the same sleeping place as them, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[544]="*Upaḍḍhacchanne upaḍḍhaparicchanne, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is half-roofed and half-walled, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[545]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they are fully ordained, but the monk does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[546]="*Upasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they are fully ordained, but the monk is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[547]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī, anāpatti.**If they are fully ordained, and the monk perceives them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[548]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[549]="*dvetisso rattiyo vasati,**if he stays together with them for two or three nights;*";
P_HTM[550]="*ūnakadvetisso rattiyo vasati,**if he stays together with them for less than two or three nights;*";
P_HTM[551]="*dve rattiyo vasitvā tatiyāya rattiyā purāruṇā nikkhamitvā puna vasati,**if, after staying together for two nights, he leaves before dawn on the third night and then stays together again;*";
P_HTM[552]="*sabbacchanne sabbaaparicchanne,**if it is fully roofed, but not walled;*";
P_HTM[553]="*sabbaparicchanne sabbaacchanne,**if it is fully walled, but not roofed;*";
P_HTM[554]="*yebhuyyena acchanne,**if it is mostly not roofed;*";
P_HTM[555]="*yebhuyyena aparicchanne,**if it is mostly not walled;*";
P_HTM[556]="*anupasampanne nipanne bhikkhu nisīdati,**if the monk sits when the person who is not fully ordained is lying down;*";
P_HTM[557]="*bhikkhu nipanne anupasampanno nisīdati,**if the person who is not fully ordained sits when the monk is lying down;*";
P_HTM[558]="*ubho vā nisīdanti,**if they both sit;*";
P_HTM[559]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[560]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[561]="*Sahaseyyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on the same sleeping place, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[562]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[563]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[564]="*6. Dutiyasahaseyyasikkhāpada**6. The second training rule on the same sleeping place*";
P_HTM[565]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[566]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā anuruddho kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchanto sāyaṃ aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upagacchi.**Venerable Anuruddha was walking through the Kosalan country on his way to Sāvatthī, when one evening he arrived at a certain village.*";
P_HTM[567]="*Tena kho pana samayena tasmiṃ gāme aññatarissā itthiyā āvasathāgāraṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**Just then a woman in that village had prepared her guesthouse.*";
P_HTM[568]="*Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ etadavoca—“sace te, bhagini, agaru, vaseyyāma ekarattaṃ āvasathāgāre”ti.**Anuruddha went to that woman and said, “If it’s not inconvenient for you, I’d like to stay in your guesthouse for one night.”*";
P_HTM[569]="*“Vaseyyātha, bhante”ti.**“Please stay, Venerable.”*";
P_HTM[570]="*Aññepi addhikā yena sā itthī tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ itthiṃ etadavocuṃ—“sace te, ayye, agaru vaseyyāma ekarattaṃ āvasathāgāre”ti.**Other travelers also went to that woman and said, “Madam, if it’s not troublesome for you, we’d like to stay in your guesthouse for one night.”*";
P_HTM[571]="*“Eso kho ayyo samaṇo paṭhamaṃ upagato; sace so anujānāti, vaseyyāthā”ti.**“Sirs, a monastic is already staying there. If he agrees, you may stay.”*";
P_HTM[572]="*Atha kho te addhikā yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavocuṃ—“sace te, bhante, agaru, vaseyyāma ekarattaṃ āvasathāgāre”ti.**Those travelers then approached Anuruddha and said, “If you don’t mind, Venerable, we’d like to stay one night in the guesthouse.”*";
P_HTM[573]="*“Vaseyyātha, āvuso”ti.**“No problem.”*";
P_HTM[574]="*Atha kho sā itthī āyasmante anuruddhe saha dassanena paṭibaddhacittā ahosi.**Now as soon as that woman had seen Anuruddha, she had fallen in love with him.*";
P_HTM[575]="*Atha kho sā itthī yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—“ayyo, bhante, imehi manussehi ākiṇṇo na phāsu viharissati.**She now went to him and said, “Sir, you won’t be comfortable surrounded by these people.*";
P_HTM[576]="*Sādhāhaṃ, bhante, ayyassa mañcakaṃ abbhantaraṃ paññapeyyan”ti.**Why don’t I prepare a bed for you in the main house?”*";
P_HTM[577]="*Adhivāsesi kho āyasmā anuruddho tuṇhībhāvena.**Anuruddha consented by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[578]="*Atha kho sā itthī āyasmato anuruddhassa mañcakaṃ abbhantaraṃ paññapetvā alaṅkatappaṭiyattā gandhagandhinī yenāyasmā anuruddho tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—**After preparing a bed in the main house, she put on jewelery and perfume, and she went to Anuruddha and said,*";
P_HTM[579]="*“ayyo, bhante, abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko, ahañcamhi abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā.**“You’re attractive, Sir, and so am I.*";
P_HTM[580]="*Sādhāhaṃ, bhante, ayyassa pajāpati bhaveyyan”ti.**Why don’t you take me as your wife?”*";
P_HTM[581]="*Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā anuruddho tuṇhī ahosi.**But Anuruddha remained silent.*";
P_HTM[582]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**She said the same thing a second time, but again got no response.*";
P_HTM[583]="*tatiyampi kho sā itthī āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—**And a third time she said,*";
P_HTM[584]="*“ayyo, bhante, abhirūpo dassanīyo pāsādiko, ahañcamhi abhirūpā dassanīyā pāsādikā.**“You’re attractive, Sir, and so am I.*";
P_HTM[585]="*Sādhu, bhante, ayyo mañceva paṭicchatu sabbañca sāpateyyan”ti.**Why don’t you take me and all this property?”*";
P_HTM[586]="*Tatiyampi kho āyasmā anuruddho tuṇhī ahosi.**Once again Anuruddha remained silent.*";
P_HTM[587]="*Atha kho sā itthī sāṭakaṃ nikkhipitvā āyasmato anuruddhassa purato caṅkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi seyyampi kappeti.**She then threw off her wrap, and she walked back and forth, stood, sat down, and lay down in front of him.*";
P_HTM[588]="*Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho indriyāni okkhipitvā taṃ itthiṃ neva olokesi napi ālapi.**But Anuruddha controlled his senses and neither looked at nor spoke to her.*";
P_HTM[589]="*Atha kho sā itthī—“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**Then that woman said, “It’s astonishing and amazing.*";
P_HTM[590]="*Bahū me manussā satenapi sahassenapi pahiṇanti.**Many people pay a hundred or a thousand coins to be with me.*";
P_HTM[591]="*Ayaṃ pana samaṇo—mayā sāmaṃ yāciyamāno—na icchati mañceva paṭicchituṃ sabbañca sāpateyyan”ti**But this monastic doesn’t want me and all this property, even when I beg him!”*";
P_HTM[592]="*sāṭakaṃ nivāsetvā āyasmato anuruddhassa pādesu sirasā nipatitvā āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—**After dressing, she bowed down with her head at Anuruddha’s feet and said,*";
P_HTM[593]="*“accayo maṃ, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ yāhaṃ evamakāsiṃ.**“Sir, I’ve made a mistake. I’ve been foolish, confused, and unskillful.*";
P_HTM[594]="*Tassā me, bhante, ayyo accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti.**Please forgive me so that I may restrain myself in the future.”*";
P_HTM[595]="*“Taggha tvaṃ, bhagini, accayo accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ yā tvaṃ evamakāsi.**“You have certainly made a mistake. You’ve been foolish, confused, and unskillful.*";
P_HTM[596]="*Yato ca kho tvaṃ, bhagini, accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikarosi, taṃ te mayaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**But since you acknowledge your mistake and make proper amends, I forgive you.*";
P_HTM[597]="*Vuddhi hesā, bhagini, ariyassa vinaye yo accayaṃ accayato disvā yathādhammaṃ paṭikaroti āyatiñca saṃvaraṃ āpajjatī”ti.**For this is called growth in the training of the noble ones: acknowledging a mistake, making proper amends, and undertaking restraint for the future.”*";
P_HTM[598]="*Atha kho sā itthī tassā rattiyā accayena āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappetvā sampavāretvā, āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**The following morning that woman personally served and satisfied Anuruddha with various kinds of fine food. When he had finished his meal, she bowed and sat down to one side.*";
P_HTM[599]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho taṃ itthiṃ āyasmā anuruddho dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**And Anuruddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching.*";
P_HTM[600]="*Atha kho sā itthī—āyasmatā anuruddhena dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā—āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ etadavoca—**She then said to him,*";
P_HTM[601]="*“abhikkantaṃ, bhante, abhikkantaṃ, bhante.**“Wonderful, Sir, wonderful!*";
P_HTM[602]="*Seyyathāpi, bhante, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya—‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti;**Just as one might set upright what had been overturned, or reveal what had been hidden, or show the way to one who was lost, or bring a lamp into the darkness so that one with eyes might see what is there—*";
P_HTM[603]="*evamevaṃ ayyena anuruddhena anekapariyāyena dhammo pakāsito.**even so have you made the Teaching clear in many ways.*";
P_HTM[604]="*Esāhaṃ, bhante, taṃ bhagavantaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca.**I go for refuge to the Buddha, the Teaching, and the Sangha of monks.*";
P_HTM[605]="*Upāsikaṃ maṃ ayyo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti.**Please accept me as a lay follower who from today has gone for refuge for life.”*";
P_HTM[606]="*Atha kho āyasmā anuruddho sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Soon afterwards, after arriving at Sāvatthī, Anuruddha told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[607]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[608]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā anuruddho mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappessatī”ti.**“How can Venerable Anuruddha lie down in the same sleeping place as a woman?”*";
P_HTM[609]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ anuruddhaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking him in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned Anuruddha:*";
P_HTM[610]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, anuruddha, mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappesī”ti?**“Is it true, Anuruddha, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[611]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[612]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe… kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, anuruddha, mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappessasi.**The Buddha rebuked him … “Anuruddha, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[613]="*Netaṃ, anuruddha, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[614]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[615]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena sahaseyyaṃ kappeyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk lies down in the same sleeping place as a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[616]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[617]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[618]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[619]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[620]="*Mātugāmo nāma**A woman:*";
P_HTM[621]="*manussitthī, na yakkhī, na petī, na tiracchānagatā; antamaso tadahujātāpi dārikā, pageva mahattarī.**a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal; even a girl born on that very day, let alone an older one.*";
P_HTM[622]="*Sahāti**Same:*";
P_HTM[623]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[624]="*Seyyā nāma**Sleeping place:*";
P_HTM[625]="*sabbacchannā, sabbaparicchannā, yebhuyyenacchannā, yebhuyyena paricchannā.**fully roofed, fully walled; mostly roofed, mostly walled.*";
P_HTM[626]="*Seyyaṃ kappeyyāti**Lies down in the same sleeping place:*";
P_HTM[627]="*atthaṅgate sūriye—**when the sun has set—*";
P_HTM[628]="*Mātugāme nipanne bhikkhu nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the monk lies down when the woman is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[629]="*Bhikkhu nipanne mātugāmo nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the woman lies down when the monk is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[630]="*Ubho vā nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[631]="*Uṭṭhahitvā punappunaṃ nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[632]="*Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, and he perceives her as such, and he lies down in the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[633]="*Mātugāme vematiko sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he is unsure of it, and he lies down in the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[634]="*Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as such, and he lies down in the same sleeping place as her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[635]="*Upaḍḍhacchanne upaḍḍhaparicchanne, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is half-roofed and half-walled, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[636]="*Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatitthiyā vā sahaseyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he lies down in the same sleeping place as a female spirit, a female ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a female animal, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[637]="*Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[638]="*Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[639]="*Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[640]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[641]="*sabbacchanne sabbaaparicchanne,**if it is fully roofed, but not walled;*";
P_HTM[642]="*sabbaparicchanne sabbaacchanne,**if it is fully walled, but not roofed;*";
P_HTM[643]="*yebhuyyena acchanne,**if it is mostly not roofed;*";
P_HTM[644]="*yebhuyyena aparicchanne,**if it is mostly not walled;*";
P_HTM[645]="*mātugāme nipanne bhikkhu nisīdati,**if the monk sits when the woman is lying down;*";
P_HTM[646]="*bhikkhu nipanne mātugāmo nisīdati,**if the woman sits when the monk is lying down;*";
P_HTM[647]="*ubho vā nisīdanti,**if they both sit down together;*";
P_HTM[648]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[649]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[650]="*Dutiyasahaseyyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The second training rule on the same sleeping place, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[651]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[652]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[653]="*7. Dhammadesanāsikkhāpada**7. The training rule on teaching*";
P_HTM[654]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[655]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī sāvatthiyaṃ kulūpako hoti, bahukāni kulāni upasaṅkamati.**At that time Venerable Udāyī was associating with and visiting a number of families in Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[656]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**After robing up one morning, he took his bowl and robe and went to a certain family.*";
P_HTM[657]="*Tena kho pana samayena gharaṇī nivesanadvāre nisinnā hoti, gharasuṇhā āvasathadvāre nisinnā hoti.**Just then the housewife was sitting at the entrance door and the daughter-in-law at the door to one of the rooms.*";
P_HTM[658]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena gharaṇī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā gharaṇiyā upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desesi.**Udāyī went up to the housewife and gave her a teaching, whispering in her ear.*";
P_HTM[659]="*Atha kho gharasuṇhāya etadahosi—**And the daughter-in-law thought,*";
P_HTM[660]="*“kiṃ nu kho so samaṇo sassuyā jāro udāhu obhāsatī”ti?**“Is this monastic my mother-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking indecently?”*";
P_HTM[661]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī gharaṇiyā upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desetvā yena gharasuṇhā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā gharasuṇhāya upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desesi.**After teaching the housewife in this way, Udāyī went up to the daughter-in-law and gave her a teaching in the same way.*";
P_HTM[662]="*Atha kho gharaṇiyā etadahosi—**Then the housewife thought,*";
P_HTM[663]="*“kiṃ nu kho so samaṇo gharasuṇhāya jāro udāhu obhāsatī”ti?**“Is this monastic my daughter-in-law’s lover, or is he speaking indecently?”*";
P_HTM[664]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī gharasuṇhāya upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desetvā pakkāmi.**When Udāyī had left,*";
P_HTM[665]="*Atha kho gharaṇī gharasuṇhaṃ etadavoca—**the housewife said to her daughter-in-law,*";
P_HTM[666]="*“he je, kiṃ te eso samaṇo avocā”ti?**“Hey, what did that monastic say to you?”*";
P_HTM[667]="*“Dhammaṃ me, ayye, desesi”.**“He gave me a teaching, madam.*";
P_HTM[668]="*“Ayyāya pana kiṃ avocā”ti?**But what did he say to you?”*";
P_HTM[669]="*“Mayhampi dhammaṃ desesī”ti.**“He gave me a teaching, too.”*";
P_HTM[670]="*Tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**And they complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[671]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyo udāyī upakaṇṇake dhammaṃ desessati.**“How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings by whispering in the ear?*";
P_HTM[672]="*Nanu nāma vissaṭṭhena vivaṭena dhammo desetabbo”ti?**Should not teachings be given audibly and openly?”*";
P_HTM[673]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ itthīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those women,*";
P_HTM[674]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized Udāyī,*";
P_HTM[675]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desessatī”ti.**“How can Venerable Udāyī give teachings to women?”*";
P_HTM[676]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking him in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned Udāyī:*";
P_HTM[677]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desesī”ti?**“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[678]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[679]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[680]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desessasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[681]="*Netaṃ moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[682]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[683]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmassa dhammaṃ deseyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives a teaching to a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[684]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[685]="*Tena kho pana samayena upāsikā bhikkhū passitvā etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards some female lay followers saw some monks and said to them,*";
P_HTM[686]="*“iṅghāyyā, dhammaṃ desethā”ti.**“Venerables, please give a teaching.”*";
P_HTM[687]="*“Na, bhaginī, kappati mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desetun”ti.**“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”*";
P_HTM[688]="*“Iṅghāyyā, chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetha, sakkā ettakenapi dhammo aññātun”ti.**“Just teach five or six sentences. That might be enough for us to understand.”*";
P_HTM[689]="*“Na, bhaginī, kappati mātugāmassa dhammaṃ desetun”ti.**“It’s not allowable for us to teach women.”*";
P_HTM[690]="*Kukkuccāyantā na desesuṃ.**And being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach them.*";
P_HTM[691]="*Upāsikā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**Those female lay followers complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[692]="*“kathañhi nāma, ayyā, amhehi yācīyamānā dhammaṃ na desessantī”ti.**“How can they not teach us when asked?”*";
P_HTM[693]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ upāsikānaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those female lay followers,*";
P_HTM[694]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[695]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[696]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mātugāmassa chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetuṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to teach five or six sentences to a woman.*";
P_HTM[697]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[698]="*“Yo pana bhikkhū mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[699]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[700]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—“bhagavatā anuññātaṃ mātugāmassa chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desetun”ti te aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desenti.**When the monks from the group of six knew that the Buddha had made this allowance, they taught women more than five or six sentences with a man who did not understand sitting nearby.*";
P_HTM[701]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[702]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desessantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six teach women more than five or six sentences with a man who doesn’t understand sitting nearby?”*";
P_HTM[703]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[704]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[705]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[706]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[707]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, aviññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ upanisīdāpetvā mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ desessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[708]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[709]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[710]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmassa uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseyya, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives a teaching of more than five or six sentences to a woman, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[711]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[712]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[713]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[714]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[715]="*Mātugāmo nāma**A woman:*";
P_HTM[716]="*manussitthī; na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā; viññū, paṭibalā subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ.**a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal; one who understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is indecent and what is decent.*";
P_HTM[717]="*Uttarichappañcavācāhīti**More than five or six sentences:*";
P_HTM[718]="*atirekachappañcavācāhi.**in excess of five or six sentences.*";
P_HTM[719]="*Dhammo nāma**A teaching:*";
P_HTM[720]="*buddhabhāsito, sāvakabhāsito, isibhāsito, devatābhāsito, atthūpasañhito, dhammūpasañhito.**what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[721]="*Deseyyāti**Gives:*";
P_HTM[722]="*padena deseti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he teaches by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[723]="*Akkharāya deseti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he teaches by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[724]="*Aññatra viññunā purisaviggahenāti**Except in the presence of a man who understands:*";
P_HTM[725]="*ṭhapetvā viññuṃ purisaviggahaṃ.**unless a man who understands is present.*";
P_HTM[726]="*Viññū nāma purisaviggaho,**A man who understands:*";
P_HTM[727]="*paṭibalo hoti subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ.**one who is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is indecent and what is decent.*";
P_HTM[728]="*Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, and he perceives her as such, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[729]="*Mātugāme vematiko uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he is unsure of it, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[730]="*Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as such, and he teaches her more than five or six sentences, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[731]="*Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakassa vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā uttarichappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti, aññatra viññunā purisaviggahena, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he teaches more than five or six sentences to a female spirit, a female ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a female animal in the form of a woman, except in the presence of a man who understands, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[732]="*Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[733]="*Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[734]="*Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[735]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[736]="*viññunā purisaviggahena,**if a man who understands is present;*";
P_HTM[737]="*chappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti,**if he teaches five or six sentences;*";
P_HTM[738]="*ūnakachappañcavācāhi dhammaṃ deseti,**if he teaches less than five or six sentences;*";
P_HTM[739]="*uṭṭhahitvā puna nisīditvā deseti,**if he gets up, sits down again, and then teaches;*";
P_HTM[740]="*mātugāmo uṭṭhahitvā puna nisīdati tasmiṃ deseti,**if the woman gets up and sits down again, and he then teaches her;*";
P_HTM[741]="*aññassa mātugāmassa deseti,**if he teaches another woman;*";
P_HTM[742]="*pañhaṃ pucchati,**if he asks a question;*";
P_HTM[743]="*pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,**if he is asked a question and then speaks;*";
P_HTM[744]="*aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ mātugāmo suṇāti,**if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and a woman listens in;*";
P_HTM[745]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[746]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[747]="*Dhammadesanāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on teaching, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[748]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[749]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[750]="*8. Bhūtārocanasikkhāpada**8. The training rule on telling truthfully*";
P_HTM[751]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood near Vesālī,*";
P_HTM[752]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā sandiṭṭhā sambhattā bhikkhū vaggumudāya nadiyā tīre vassaṃ upagacchiṃsu.**a number of monks who were friends had entered the rainy-season residence on the banks of the river Vaggumudā.*";
P_HTM[753]="*Tena kho pana samayena vajjī dubbhikkhā hoti—dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ.**At that time Vajjī was short of food and afflicted with hunger, with crops affected by whiteheads and turned to straw. It was not easy to get by on almsfood.*";
P_HTM[754]="*Atha kho tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—“etarahi kho vajjī dubbhikkhā—dvīhitikā setaṭṭhikā salākāvuttā, na sukarā uñchena paggahena yāpetuṃ. Kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vaseyyāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilameyyāmā”ti?**The monks considered the difficult circumstances, and they thought, “How can we live in concord and harmony, have a comfortable rainy season, and get almsfood without trouble?”*";
P_HTM[755]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—“handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhema. Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti.**Some said, “We could work for the householders, and they’ll support us in return.”*";
P_HTM[756]="*Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[757]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—“alaṃ, āvuso, kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena?**Others said, “There’s no need to work for the householders.*";
P_HTM[758]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ harāma. Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti.**Let’s instead take messages for them, and they’ll support us in return.”*";
P_HTM[759]="*Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[760]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—“alaṃ, āvuso; kiṃ gihīnaṃ kammantaṃ adhiṭṭhitena. Kiṃ gihīnaṃ dūteyyaṃ haṭena.**Still others said, “There’s no need to do work or take messages for them.*";
P_HTM[761]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissāma—**Let’s instead talk up one another’s superhuman qualities to the householders:*";
P_HTM[762]="*‘asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu dutiyassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu tatiyassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, asuko bhikkhu sotāpanno, asuko bhikkhu sakadāgāmī, asuko bhikkhu anāgāmī, asuko bhikkhu arahā, asuko bhikkhu tevijjo, asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño’ti.**‘That monk has the first absorption, that monk the second absorption, that monk the third, that monk the fourth; that monk is a stream-enterer, that monk a once-returner, that a non-returner, that a perfected one; that monk has the three true insights, and that the six direct knowledges.’*";
P_HTM[763]="*Evaṃ te amhākaṃ dātuṃ maññissanti.**Then they’ll support us.*";
P_HTM[764]="*Evaṃ mayaṃ samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasissāma, na ca piṇḍakena kilamissāmā”ti.**In this way we’ll live in concord and harmony, spend the rainy season in comfort, and have no trouble getting almsfood.*";
P_HTM[765]="*“Eso yeva kho, āvuso, seyyo, yo amhākaṃ gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇo bhāsito”ti.**This is the way to go.”*";
P_HTM[766]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsiṃsu—**Then those monks did just that.*";
P_HTM[767]="*“asuko bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī …pe… asuko bhikkhu chaḷabhiñño”ti.* **";
P_HTM[768]="*Atha kho te manussā—“lābhā vata no, suladdhaṃ vata no, yesaṃ no evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā, na vata no ito pubbe evarūpā bhikkhū vassaṃ upagatā, yathayime bhikkhū sīlavanto kalyāṇadhammā”ti.**And the people there thought, “We’re so fortunate that such monks have come to us for the rainy-season residence. Such virtuous and good monks have never before entered the rains residence with us.”*";
P_HTM[769]="*Te na tādisāni bhojanāni attanā bhuñjanti, mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakammakaraporisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñātisālohitānaṃ denti yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti.**And they gave such food and drink to those monks that they did not even eat and drink themselves, or give to their parents, to their wives and children, to their slaves, servants, and workers, to their friends and companions, or to their relatives.*";
P_HTM[770]="*Na tādisāni khādanīyāni sāyanīyāni pānāni attanā khādanti sāyanti pivanti mātāpitūnaṃ denti puttadārassa denti dāsakammakaraporisassa denti mittāmaccānaṃ denti ñātisālohitānaṃ denti, yādisāni bhikkhūnaṃ denti.* **";
P_HTM[771]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū vaṇṇavā ahesuṃ pīṇindriyā pasannamukhavaṇṇā vippasannachavivaṇṇā.**Soon those monks had a good color, bright faces, clear skin, and sharp senses.*";
P_HTM[772]="*Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ vassaṃvuṭṭhānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ bhagavantaṃ dassanāya upasaṅkamituṃ.**Now it was the custom for monks who had completed the rainy-season residence to go and visit the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[773]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū vassaṃvuṭṭhā temāsaccayena senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena vesālī tena pakkamiṃsu.**And so, when the three months were over and they had completed the rains residence, those monks put their dwellings in order, took their bowls and robes, and set out for Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[774]="*Anupubbena yena vesālī mahāvanaṃ kūṭāgārasālā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**When they eventually arrived, they went to the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood.*";
P_HTM[775]="*upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**There they approached the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[776]="*Tena kho pana samayena disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū kisā honti lūkhā dubbaṇṇā uppaṇḍuppaṇḍukajātā dhamanisanthatagattā.**At that time the monks who had completed the rains residence in that region were thin, haggard and pale, with veins protruding all over their bodies.*";
P_HTM[777]="*Vaggumudātīriyā pana bhikkhū vaṇṇavā honti pīṇindriyā pasannamukhavaṇṇā vippasannachavivaṇṇā.**Yet the monks from the banks of the Vaggumudā had a good color, bright faces, clear skin, and  sharp senses.*";
P_HTM[778]="*Āciṇṇaṃ kho panetaṃ buddhānaṃ bhagavantānaṃ āgantukehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ paṭisammodituṃ.**Since it is the custom for Buddhas to greet newly arrived monks,*";
P_HTM[779]="*Atha kho bhagavā vaggumudātīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—**the Buddha said to them,*";
P_HTM[780]="*“kacci, bhikkhave, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyaṃ,**“I hope you’re keeping well, monks, I hope you’re getting by.*";
P_HTM[781]="*kacci samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha, na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?**I hope you had a comfortable rains residence, living in concord and harmony, and that you had no trouble getting almsfood?”*";
P_HTM[782]="*“Khamanīyaṃ, bhagavā, yāpanīyaṃ, bhagavā.**“We’re keeping well, Venerable Sir, we’re getting by.*";
P_HTM[783]="*Samaggā ca mayaṃ, bhante, sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasimhā, na ca piṇḍakena kilamimhā”ti.**We had a comfortable rains residence, living in concord and harmony, and we had no trouble getting almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[784]="*Jānantāpi tathāgatā pucchanti, jānantāpi na pucchanti.**When Buddhas know what is going on, sometimes they ask and sometimes not.*";
P_HTM[785]="*Kālaṃ viditvā pucchanti, kālaṃ viditvā na pucchanti.**They know the right time to ask and when not to ask.*";
P_HTM[786]="*Atthasañhitaṃ tathāgatā pucchanti, no anatthasañhitaṃ.**Buddhas ask when it is beneficial, otherwise not,*";
P_HTM[787]="*Anatthasañhite setughāto tathāgatānaṃ.**for Buddhas are incapable of doing what is unbeneficial.*";
P_HTM[788]="*Dvīhākārehi buddhā bhagavanto bhikkhū paṭipucchanti—“dhammaṃ vā desessāma, sāvakānaṃ vā sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmā”ti.**Buddhas question the monks for two reasons: to give a teaching or to lay down a training rule.*";
P_HTM[789]="*Atha kho bhagavā vaggumudātīriye bhikkhū etadavoca—“yathā kathaṃ pana tumhe, bhikkhave, samaggā sammodamānā avivadamānā phāsukaṃ vassaṃ vasittha, na ca piṇḍakena kilamitthā”ti?**And the Buddha said to those monks, “In what way, monks, did you have a comfortable rains residence, with no trouble getting almsfood?”*";
P_HTM[790]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They then told him.*";
P_HTM[791]="*“Kacci pana vo, bhikkhave, bhūtan”ti?**“But did you really have those superhuman qualities?”*";
P_HTM[792]="*“Bhūtaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“Yes, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[793]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them,*";
P_HTM[794]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, bhikkhave, udarassa kāraṇā gihīnaṃ aññamaññassa uttarimanussadhammassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsissatha.**“How could you for the sake of your stomachs talk up one another’s superhuman qualities to householders?*";
P_HTM[795]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[796]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[797]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu anupasampannassa uttarimanussadhammaṃ āroceyya bhūtasmiṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk truthfully tells a person who is not fully ordained of a superhuman quality, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[798]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[799]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[800]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[801]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[802]="*Anupasampanno nāma**A person who is not fully ordained:*";
P_HTM[803]="*bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā, avaseso anupasampanno nāma.**anyone except a fully ordained monk or a fully ordained nun.*";
P_HTM[804]="*Uttarimanussadhammo nāma**A superhuman quality:*";
P_HTM[805]="*jhānaṃ, vimokkho, samādhi, samāpatti, ñāṇadassanaṃ, maggabhāvanā, phalasacchikiriyā, kilesappahānaṃ, vinīvaraṇatā cittassa, suññāgāre abhirati.**absorption, release, stillness, attainment, knowledge and vision, development of the path, realization of the fruits, abandoning the defilements, a mind without hindrances, delighting in solitude.*";
P_HTM[806]="*Jhānanti**Absorption:*";
P_HTM[807]="*paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ, dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ, tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ, catutthaṃ jhānaṃ.**the first absorption, the second absorption, the third absorption, the fourth absorption.*";
P_HTM[808]="*Vimokkhoti**Release:*";
P_HTM[809]="*suññato vimokkho, animitto vimokkho, appaṇihito vimokkho.**emptiness release, signless release, desireless release.*";
P_HTM[810]="*Samādhīti**Stillness:*";
P_HTM[811]="*suññato samādhi, animitto samādhi, appaṇihito samādhi.**emptiness stillness, signless stillness, desireless stillness.*";
P_HTM[812]="*Samāpattīti**Attainment:*";
P_HTM[813]="*suññatā samāpatti, animittā samāpatti, appaṇihitā samāpatti.**emptiness attainment, signless attainment, desireless attainment.*";
P_HTM[814]="*Ñāṇadassananti**Knowledge and vision:*";
P_HTM[815]="*tisso vijjā.**the three true insights.*";
P_HTM[816]="*Maggabhāvanāti**Development of the path:*";
P_HTM[817]="*cattāro satipaṭṭhānā, cattāro sammappadhānā, cattāro iddhipādā, pañcindriyāni, pañca balāni, satta bojjhaṅgā, ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo.**the four applications of mindfulness, the four right efforts, the four foundations for supernormal power, the five spiritual faculties, the five spiritual powers, the seven factors of awakening, the noble eightfold path.*";
P_HTM[818]="*Phalasacchikiriyāti**Realization of the fruits:*";
P_HTM[819]="*sotāpattiphalassa sacchikiriyā, sakadāgāmiphalassa sacchikiriyā, anāgāmiphalassa sacchikiriyā, arahattassa sacchikiriyā.**realization of the fruit of stream-entry, realization of the fruit of once-returning, realization of the fruit of non-returning, realization of perfection.*";
P_HTM[820]="*Kilesappahānanti**Abandoning the defilements:*";
P_HTM[821]="*rāgassa pahānaṃ, dosassa pahānaṃ, mohassa pahānaṃ.**the abandoning of sensual desire, the abandoning of ill will, the abandoning of confusion.*";
P_HTM[822]="*Vinīvaraṇatā cittassāti**A mind without hindrances:*";
P_HTM[823]="*rāgā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā, dosā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā, mohā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇatā.**a mind without sensual desire, a mind without ill will, a mind without confusion.*";
P_HTM[824]="*Suññāgāre abhiratīti**Delighting in solitude:*";
P_HTM[825]="*paṭhamena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati, dutiyena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati, tatiyena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati, catutthena jhānena suññāgāre abhirati.**because of the first absorption there is delight in solitude, because of the second absorption there is delight in solitude, because of the third absorption there is delight in solitude, because of the fourth absorption there is delight in solitude.*";
P_HTM[826]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[827]="*anupasampannassa—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[828]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[829]="*anupasampannassa—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjāmī”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I’m attaining the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[830]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[831]="*anupasampannassa—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpanno”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I’ve attained the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[832]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[833]="*anupasampannassa—“paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhimhī”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I obtain the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[834]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[835]="*anupasampannassa—“paṭhamassa jhānassa vasimhī”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I master the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[836]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[837]="*anupasampannassa—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I’ve realized the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[838]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[839]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[840]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**the third absorption …*";
P_HTM[841]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; catutthassa jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the fourth absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the fourth absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[842]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[843]="*anupasampannassa— “suññataṃ vimokkhaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the emptiness release …*";
P_HTM[844]="*animittaṃ vimokkhaṃ …**the signless release …*";
P_HTM[845]="*appaṇihitaṃ vimokkhaṃ …**the desireless release …*";
P_HTM[846]="*suññataṃ samādhiṃ …**the emptiness stillness …*";
P_HTM[847]="*animittaṃ samādhiṃ …**the signless stillness …*";
P_HTM[848]="*appaṇihitaṃ samādhiṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; appaṇihitassa samādhissa lābhimhi, vasimhi; appaṇihito samādhi sacchikato mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the desireless stillness … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the desireless stillness,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[849]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[850]="*anupasampannassa— “suññataṃ samāpattiṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the emptiness attainment …*";
P_HTM[851]="*animittaṃ samāpattiṃ …**the signless attainment …*";
P_HTM[852]="*appaṇihitaṃ samāpattiṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; appaṇihitāya samāpattiyā lābhimhi, vasimhi; appaṇihitā samāpatti sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the desireless attainment … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the desireless attainment,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[853]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[854]="*anupasampannassa— “tisso vijjā samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; tissannaṃ vijjānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; tisso vijjā sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the three true insights … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the three true insights,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[855]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[856]="*anupasampannassa— “cattāro satipaṭṭhāne …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the four applications of mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[857]="*cattāro sammappadhāne …**the four right efforts …*";
P_HTM[858]="*cattāro iddhipāde samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; catunnaṃ iddhipādānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; cattāro iddhipādā sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the four foundations for supernormal power … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the four foundations for supernormal power,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[859]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[860]="*anupasampannassa— “pañcindriyāni …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the five spiritual faculties …*";
P_HTM[861]="*pañca balāni samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; pañcannaṃ balānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; pañca balāni sacchikatāni mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the five spiritual powers … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the five spiritual powers,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[862]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[863]="*anupasampannassa— “satta bojjhaṅge samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; sattannaṃ bojjhaṅgānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; satta bojjhaṅgā sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the seven factors of awakening … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the seven factors of awakening,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[864]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[865]="*anupasampannassa— “ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; ariyassa aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; ariyo aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sacchikato mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the noble eightfold path … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the noble eightfold path,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[866]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[867]="*anupasampannassa— “sotāpattiphalaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the fruit of stream-entry …*";
P_HTM[868]="*sakadāgāmiphalaṃ …**the fruit of once-returning …*";
P_HTM[869]="*anāgāmiphalaṃ …**the fruit of non-returning …*";
P_HTM[870]="*arahattaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; arahattassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; arahattaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**perfection … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized perfection,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[871]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[872]="*anupasampannassa— “rāgo me catto …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I’ve given up sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[873]="*doso me catto …**I’ve given up ill will …*";
P_HTM[874]="*moho me catto, vanto, mutto, pahīno, paṭinissaṭṭho, ukkheṭito, samukkheṭito”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**I’ve given up confusion, I’ve renounced it, I’ve let it go, I’ve abandoned it, I’ve relinquished it, I’ve forsaken it, I’ve thrown it aside,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[875]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[876]="*anupasampannassa— “rāgā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “My mind is free from the hindrance of sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[877]="*dosā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ …**My mind is free from the hindrance of ill will …*";
P_HTM[878]="*mohā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[879]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[880]="*anupasampannassa— “suññāgāre paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption in solitude …*";
P_HTM[881]="*dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[882]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**the third absorption …*";
P_HTM[883]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the fourth absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the fourth absorption in solitude,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[884]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[885]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ dutiyañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa dutiyassa ca jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ dutiyañca jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the second absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the second absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[886]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[887]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ tatiyañca jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the third absorption …*";
P_HTM[888]="*paṭhamañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa catutthassa ca jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the first absorption and the fourth absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the fourth absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[889]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[890]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ suññatañca vimokkhaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the emptiness release …*";
P_HTM[891]="*animittañca vimokkhaṃ …**and the signless release …*";
P_HTM[892]="*appaṇihitañca vimokkhaṃ …**and the desireless release …*";
P_HTM[893]="*suññatañca samādhiṃ …**and the emptiness stillness …*";
P_HTM[894]="*animittañca samādhiṃ …**and the signless stillness …*";
P_HTM[895]="*appaṇihitañca samādhiṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa appaṇihitassa ca samādhissa lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ appaṇihito ca samādhi sacchikato mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**and the desireless stillness … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the desireless stillness,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[896]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[897]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ suññatañca samāpattiṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the emptiness attainment …*";
P_HTM[898]="*animittañca samāpattiṃ …**the signless attainment …*";
P_HTM[899]="*appaṇihitañca samāpattiṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa appaṇihitāya ca samāpattiyā lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ appaṇihitā ca samāpatti sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the desireless attainment … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the desireless attainment,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[900]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[901]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ tisso ca vijjā samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa tissannañca vijjānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ tisso ca vijjā sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the three true insights … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the three true insights,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[902]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[903]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ cattāro ca satipaṭṭhāne …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the four applications of mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[904]="*cattāro ca sammappadhāne …**the four right efforts …*";
P_HTM[905]="*cattāro ca iddhipāde samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa catunnañca iddhipādānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ cattāro ca iddhipādā sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the four foundations for supernormal power … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the four foundations for supernormal power,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[906]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[907]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ, pañca ca indriyāni …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the five spiritual faculties …*";
P_HTM[908]="*pañca ca balāni samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa pañcannañca balānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ pañca ca balāni sacchikatāni mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the five spiritual powers … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the five spiritual powers,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[909]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[910]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ satta ca bojjhaṅge samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa sattannañca bojjhaṅgānaṃ lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ satta ca bojjhaṅgā sacchikatā mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the seven factors of awakening … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the seven factors of awakening,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[911]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[912]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ ariyañca aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa ariyassa ca aṭṭhaṅgikassa maggassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ ariyo ca aṭṭhaṅgiko maggo sacchikato mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the noble eightfold path … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and the noble eightfold path,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[913]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[914]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ sotāpattiphalañca …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the fruit of stream-entry …*";
P_HTM[915]="*sakadāgāmiphalañca …**and the fruit of once-returning …*";
P_HTM[916]="*anāgāmiphalañca …**and the fruit of non-returning …*";
P_HTM[917]="*arahattañca samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; paṭhamassa ca jhānassa arahattassa ca lābhimhi, vasimhi; paṭhamañca jhānaṃ arahattañca sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**and perfection … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and perfection,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[918]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[919]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno …pe… rāgo ca me catto …**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and I’ve given up sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[920]="*doso ca me catto …**and I’ve given up ill will …*";
P_HTM[921]="*moho ca me catto, vanto, mutto, pahīno, paṭinissaṭṭho, ukkheṭito, samukkheṭito”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**and I’ve given up confusion … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master …I’ve realized the first absorption and I’ve given up confusion,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[922]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[923]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno …pe… rāgā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ …**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and my mind is free from the hindrance of sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[924]="*dosā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ …**and my mind is free from the hindrance of ill will …*";
P_HTM[925]="*mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**and my mind is free from the hindrance of confusion … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the first absorption and my mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[926]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[927]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyañca jhānaṃ tatiyañca jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption and the third absorption …*";
P_HTM[928]="*dutiyañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; dutiyassa ca jhānassa catutthassa ca jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; dutiyañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**the second absorption and the fourth absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the second absorption and the fourth absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[929]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[930]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyañca jhānaṃ suññatañca vimokkhaṃ …pe… mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption and the emptiness release … and my mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[931]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[932]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyañca jhānaṃ paṭhamañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; dutiyassa ca jhānassa paṭhamassa ca jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; dutiyañca jhānaṃ paṭhamañca jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa …pe….**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption and the first absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … I’ve realized the second absorption and the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession. …*";
P_HTM[933]="*Mūlaṃ saṅkhittaṃ.**The basis in brief is finished.*";
P_HTM[934]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[935]="*anupasampannassa— “mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ, paṭhamañca jhānaṃ samāpajjiṃ, samāpajjāmi, samāpanno; mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ, paṭhamassa ca jhānassa lābhimhi, vasimhi; mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ, paṭhamañca jhānaṃ sacchikataṃ mayā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa …pe….**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion and I attained the first absorption … I’m attaining … I’ve attained … I obtain … I master … My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion and I’ve realized the first absorption,” he commits an offense entailing confession. …*";
P_HTM[936]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[937]="*anupasampannassa— “mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ, dosā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa …pe….**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion and my mind is free from the hindrance of ill will,” he commits an offense entailing confession. …*";
P_HTM[938]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[939]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ dutiyañca jhānaṃ tatiyañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ suññatañca vimokkhaṃ animittañca vimokkhaṃ appaṇihitañca vimokkhaṃ suññatañca samādhiṃ animittañca samādhiṃ appaṇihitañca samādhiṃ suññatañca samāpattiṃ animittañca samāpattiṃ appaṇihitañca samāpattiṃ tisso ca vijjā cattāro ca satipaṭṭhāne cattāro ca sammappadhāne cattāro ca iddhipāde pañca ca indriyāni pañca ca balāni satta ca bojjhaṅge ariyañca aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ sotāpattiphalañca sakadāgāmiphalañca anāgāmiphalañca arahattañca samāpajjiṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the second absorption and the third absorption and the fourth absorption and the emptiness release and the signless release and the desireless release and the emptiness stillness and the signless stillness and the desireless stillness and the emptiness attainment and the signless attainment and the desireless attainment and the three true insights and the four applications of mindfulness and the four right efforts and the four foundations for supernormal power and the five spiritual faculties and the five spiritual powers and the seven factors of awakening and the noble eightfold path and the fruit of stream entry and the fruit of once-returning and the fruit of non-returning and perfection …*";
P_HTM[940]="*rāgo ca me catto, doso ca me catto, moho ca me catto, vanto, mutto, pahīno, paṭinissaṭṭho, ukkheṭito samukkheṭito, rāgā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ, dosā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ, mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**and I’ve given up sensual desire, renounced it, let it go, abandoned it, relinquished it, forsaken it, thrown it aside; and I’ve given up ill will, renounced it, let it go, abandoned it, relinquished it, forsaken it, thrown it aside; and I’ve given up confusion, renounced it, let it go, abandoned it, relinquished it, forsaken it, thrown it aside; and my mind is free from the hindrance of sensual desire; and my mind is free from the hindrance of ill will; and my mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[941]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[942]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti vattukāmo—“dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption,” but actually says, “I attained the second absorption,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[943]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[944]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti vattukāmo—“tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption,” but actually says, “I attained the third absorption …*";
P_HTM[945]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ,**the fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[946]="*suññataṃ vimokkhaṃ,**the emptiness release …*";
P_HTM[947]="*animittaṃ vimokkhaṃ,**the signless release …*";
P_HTM[948]="*appaṇihitaṃ vimokkhaṃ,**the desireless release …*";
P_HTM[949]="*suññataṃ samādhiṃ,**the emptiness stillness …*";
P_HTM[950]="*animittaṃ samādhiṃ,**the signless stillness …*";
P_HTM[951]="*appaṇihitaṃ samādhiṃ,**the desireless stillness …*";
P_HTM[952]="*suññataṃ samāpattiṃ,**the emptiness attainment …*";
P_HTM[953]="*animittaṃ samāpattiṃ,**the signless attainment …*";
P_HTM[954]="*appaṇihitaṃ samāpattiṃ,**the desireless attainment …*";
P_HTM[955]="*tisso vijjā,**the three true insights …*";
P_HTM[956]="*cattāro satipaṭṭhāne,**the four applications of mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[957]="*cattāro sammappadhāne,**the four right efforts …*";
P_HTM[958]="*cattāro iddhipāde,**the four foundations for supernormal power …*";
P_HTM[959]="*pañcindriyāni,**the five spiritual faculties …*";
P_HTM[960]="*pañca balāni,**the five spiritual powers …*";
P_HTM[961]="*satta bojjhaṅge,**the seven factors of awakening …*";
P_HTM[962]="*ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ,**the noble eightfold path …*";
P_HTM[963]="*sotāpattiphalaṃ,**the fruit of stream entry …*";
P_HTM[964]="*sakadāgāmiphalaṃ,**the fruit of once-returning …*";
P_HTM[965]="*anāgāmiphalaṃ,**the fruit of non-returning …*";
P_HTM[966]="*arahattaṃ samāpajjiṃ …pe…**perfection … etc. …*";
P_HTM[967]="*rāgo me catto,**I’ve given up sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[968]="*doso me catto,**I’ve given up ill will …*";
P_HTM[969]="*moho me catto, vanto, mutto, pahīno; paṭinissaṭṭho, ukkheṭito, samukkheṭito;**I’ve given up confusion, renounced it, let it go, abandoned it, relinquished it, forsaken it, thrown it aside …*";
P_HTM[970]="*rāgā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ,**my mind is free from the hindrance of sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[971]="*dosā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ,**my mind is free from the hindrance of ill will …*";
P_HTM[972]="*mohā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**my mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[973]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[974]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti vattukāmo …pe…**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption” …*";
P_HTM[975]="*“mohā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa …pe….**but actually says, “My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[976]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[977]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti vattukāmo—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa …pe….**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption,” but actually says, “I attained the first absorption,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[978]="*Mūlaṃ saṅkhittaṃ.**The basis in brief is finished.*";
P_HTM[979]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[980]="*anupasampannassa— “mohā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti vattukāmo—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa …pe….**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” but actually says, “I attained the first absorption,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[981]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[982]="*anupasampannassa— “mohā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti vattukāmo—“dosā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa …pe….**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” but actually says, “My mind is free from the hindrance of ill will,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[983]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[984]="*anupasampannassa— “paṭhamañca jhānaṃ dutiyañca jhānaṃ tatiyañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ …pe… dosā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti vattukāmo—“mohā me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the first absorption and the second absorption and the third absorption and the fourth absorption … and my mind is free from the hindrance of ill will,” but actually says, “My mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[985]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[986]="*anupasampannassa— “dutiyañca jhānaṃ tatiyañca jhānaṃ catutthañca jhānaṃ …pe… mohā ca me cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti vattukāmo—“paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajjin”ti bhaṇantassa paṭivijānantassa āpatti pācittiyassa, na paṭivijānantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa …pe….**if a monk means to say to a person who is not fully ordained, “I attained the second absorption and the third absorption and the fourth absorption … and my mind is free from the hindrance of confusion,” but actually says, “I attained the first absorption,” then, if the listener understands, he commits an offense entailing confession; if the listener does not understand, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[987]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[988]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te vihāre vasi so bhikkhu paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, samāpajjati, samāpanno; so bhikkhu paṭhamassa jhānassa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who stayed in your dwelling attained the first absorption … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the first absorption,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[989]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[990]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te vihāre vasi so bhikkhu dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who stayed in your dwelling attained the second absorption …*";
P_HTM[991]="*tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ …**the third absorption …*";
P_HTM[992]="*catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, samāpajjati, samāpanno; so bhikkhu catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**the fourth absorption … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the fourth absorption,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[993]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[994]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te vihāre vasi so bhikkhu suññataṃ vimokkhaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who stayed in your dwelling attained the emptiness release …*";
P_HTM[995]="*animittaṃ vimokkhaṃ**the signless release …*";
P_HTM[996]="*appaṇihitaṃ vimokkhaṃ**the desireless release …*";
P_HTM[997]="*suññataṃ samādhiṃ**the emptiness stillness …*";
P_HTM[998]="*animittaṃ samādhiṃ**the signless stillness …*";
P_HTM[999]="*appaṇihitaṃ samādhiṃ samāpajji, samāpajjati, samāpanno; so bhikkhu appaṇihitassa samādhissa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā appaṇihito samādhi sacchikato”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**the desireless stillness … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the desireless stillness,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1000]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1001]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te vihāre vasi so bhikkhu suññataṃ samāpattiṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who stayed in your dwelling attained the emptiness attainment …*";
P_HTM[1002]="*animittaṃ samāpattiṃ**the signless attainment …*";
P_HTM[1003]="*appaṇihitaṃ samāpattiṃ samāpajji, samāpajjati, samāpanno; appaṇihitāya samāpattiyā lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā appaṇihitā samāpatti sacchikatā”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**the desireless attainment … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the desireless attainment,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1004]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1005]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te vihāre vasi so bhikkhu tisso vijjā …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who stayed in your dwelling attained the three true insights …*";
P_HTM[1006]="*cattāro satipaṭṭhāne,**the four applications of mindfulness …*";
P_HTM[1007]="*cattāro sammappadhāne,**the four right efforts …*";
P_HTM[1008]="*cattāro iddhipāde,**the four foundations for supernormal power …*";
P_HTM[1009]="*pañcindriyāni,**the five spiritual faculties …*";
P_HTM[1010]="*pañca balāni,**the five spiritual powers …*";
P_HTM[1011]="*satta bojjhaṅge,**the seven factors of awakening …*";
P_HTM[1012]="*ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ,**the noble eightfold path …*";
P_HTM[1013]="*sotāpattiphalaṃ,**the fruit of stream entry …*";
P_HTM[1014]="*sakadāgāmiphalaṃ,**the fruit of once-returning …*";
P_HTM[1015]="*anāgāmiphalaṃ,**the fruit of non-returning …*";
P_HTM[1016]="*arahattaṃ samāpajji … samāpajjati, samāpanno …pe…**perfection … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized …*";
P_HTM[1017]="*tassa bhikkhuno rāgo catto,**has given up sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[1018]="*doso catto,**has given up ill will …*";
P_HTM[1019]="*moho catto, vanto, mutto, pahīno, paṭinissaṭṭho, ukkheṭito, samukkheṭito;**has given up confusion, renounced it, let it go, abandoned it, relinquished it, forsaken it, thrown it aside …*";
P_HTM[1020]="*tassa bhikkhuno rāgā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ,**has a mind free from the hindrance of sensual desire …*";
P_HTM[1021]="*dosā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇaṃ,**has a mind free from the hindrance of ill will …*";
P_HTM[1022]="*mohā cittaṃ vinīvaraṇan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**has a mind free from the hindrance of confusion,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1023]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1024]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te vihāre vasi so bhikkhu suññāgāre paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who stayed in your dwelling attained the first absorption in solitude …*";
P_HTM[1025]="*dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji,**the second absorption … the third absorption … the fourth absorption …*";
P_HTM[1026]="*samāpajjati,**is attaining …*";
P_HTM[1027]="*samāpanno; so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the fourth absorption in solitude,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1028]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1029]="*anupasampannassa— “yo te cīvaraṃ paribhuñji,**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who made use of your robe …*";
P_HTM[1030]="*yo te piṇḍapātaṃ paribhuñji,**who made use of your almsfood …*";
P_HTM[1031]="*yo te senāsanaṃ paribhuñji,**who made use of your dwelling …*";
P_HTM[1032]="*yo te gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ paribhuñji so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, samāpajjati, samāpanno; so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**who made use of your medicines attained the fourth absorption in solitude … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the fourth absorption in solitude,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1033]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1034]="*anupasampannassa— “yena te vihāro paribhutto …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk who has made use of your dwelling …*";
P_HTM[1035]="*yena te cīvaraṃ paribhuttaṃ,**who has made use of your robe …*";
P_HTM[1036]="*yena te piṇḍapāto paribhutto,**who has made use of your almsfood …*";
P_HTM[1037]="*yena te senāsanaṃ paribhuttaṃ,**who has made use of your furniture …*";
P_HTM[1038]="*yena te gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāro paribhutto so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji, samāpajjati, samāpanno; so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**who has made use of your medicines attained the fourth absorption in solitude … is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the fourth absorption in solitude,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1039]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1040]="*anupasampannassa— “yaṃ tvaṃ āgamma vihāraṃ adāsi …pe…**if a monk says to a person who is not fully ordained, “The monk you gave a dwelling to …*";
P_HTM[1041]="*cīvaraṃ adāsi,**you gave a robe to …*";
P_HTM[1042]="*piṇḍapātaṃ adāsi,**you gave almsfood to …*";
P_HTM[1043]="*senāsanaṃ adāsi,**you gave furniture to …*";
P_HTM[1044]="*gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhāraṃ adāsi so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ samāpajji,**you gave medicines to attained the fourth absorption in solitude …*";
P_HTM[1045]="*samāpajjati, samāpanno; so bhikkhu suññāgāre catutthassa jhānassa lābhī, vasī; tena bhikkhunā suññāgāre catutthaṃ jhānaṃ sacchikatan”ti bhaṇantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**is attaining … has attained … obtains … masters … has realized the fourth absorption in solitude,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1046]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1047]="*upasampannassa, bhūtaṃ āroceti,**if he truthfully tells one who is fully ordained;*";
P_HTM[1048]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1049]="*Bhūtārocanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on telling truthfully, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1050]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1051]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[1052]="*9. Duṭṭhullārocanasikkhāpada**9. The training rule on telling about what is grave*";
P_HTM[1053]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[1054]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto chabbaggiyehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍanakato hoti.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan was quarreling with the monks from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[1055]="*So sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṅghaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ yāci.**He then committed an offense of intentional emission of semen. He asked the Sangha for probation for that offense,*";
P_HTM[1056]="*Tassa saṅgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi.**which he received.*";
P_HTM[1057]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**Just then an association in Sāvatthī was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1058]="*So parivasanto bhattagge āsanapariyante nisīdi.**Because Upananda was on probation, he sat on the last seat in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[1059]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū te upāsake etadavocuṃ—**The monks from the group of six then told those lay followers,*";
P_HTM[1060]="*“eso, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto tumhākaṃ sambhāvito kulūpako; yeneva hatthena saddhādeyyaṃ bhuñjati teneva hatthena upakkamitvā asuciṃ mocesi.**“This Venerable Upananda, the esteemed associate of your families, eats the food given in faith with the same hand he uses to masturbate.*";
P_HTM[1061]="*So sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṅghaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ yāci.**After committing an offense of intentional emission of semen, he asked the Sangha for probation for that offense,*";
P_HTM[1062]="*Tassa saṅgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi.**which he received.*";
P_HTM[1063]="*So parivasanto āsanapariyante nisinno”ti.**And because he’s on probation, he now sits on the last seat.”*";
P_HTM[1064]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1065]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six tell a person who’s not fully ordained about a monk’s grave offense?” …*";
P_HTM[1066]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1067]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1068]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1069]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa ārocessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1070]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1071]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1072]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ anupasampannassa āroceyya, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk tells a person who is not fully ordained about a monk’s grave offense, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1073]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1074]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1075]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1076]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1077]="*Bhikkhussāti**A monk’s:*";
P_HTM[1078]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**another monk’s.*";
P_HTM[1079]="*Duṭṭhullā nāma āpatti—**A grave offense:*";
P_HTM[1080]="*cattāri ca pārājikāni, terasa ca saṅghādisesā.**the four offenses entailing expulsion and the thirteen offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[1081]="*Anupasampanno nāma**A person who is not fully ordained:*";
P_HTM[1082]="*bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca ṭhapetvā avaseso anupasampanno nāma.**anyone except a fully ordained monk or a fully ordained nun.*";
P_HTM[1083]="*Āroceyyāti**Tells:*";
P_HTM[1084]="*āroceyya itthiyā vā purisassa vā gahaṭṭhassa vā pabbajitassa vā.**tells a woman or a man, a lay person or a monastic.*";
P_HTM[1085]="*Aññatra bhikkhusammutiyāti**Except if the monks have agreed:*";
P_HTM[1086]="*ṭhapetvā bhikkhusammutiṃ.**unless the monks have agreed.*";
P_HTM[1087]="*Atthi bhikkhusammuti āpattipariyantā, na kulapariyantā.**There is agreement of the monks with a limit on offenses, but not on families.*";
P_HTM[1088]="*Atthi bhikkhusammuti kulapariyantā, na āpattipariyantā, atthi bhikkhusammuti āpattipariyantā ca kulapariyantā ca, atthi bhikkhusammuti neva āpattipariyantā na kulapariyantā.**There is agreement of the monks with a limit on families, but not on offenses. There is agreement of the monks with a limit both on offenses and on families. There is agreement of the monks with neither a limit on offenses nor on families.*";
P_HTM[1089]="*Āpattipariyantā nāma**With a limit on offenses:*";
P_HTM[1090]="*āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti— “ettakāhi āpattīhi ārocetabbo”ti.**offenses are specified: “These particular offenses can be told about.”*";
P_HTM[1091]="*Kulapariyantā nāma**With limit on families:*";
P_HTM[1092]="*kulāni pariggahitāni honti— “ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti.**families are specified: “These particular families can be told.”*";
P_HTM[1093]="*Āpattipariyantā ca kulapariyantā ca nāma**With a limit both on offenses and on families:*";
P_HTM[1094]="*āpattiyo ca pariggahitāyo honti, kulāni ca pariggahitāni honti— “ettakāhi āpattīhi ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti.**both offenses and families are specified: “These particular offenses can be told about, and these particular families can be told.”*";
P_HTM[1095]="*Neva āpattipariyantā na kulapariyantā nāma**With neither a limit on offenses nor on families:*";
P_HTM[1096]="*āpattiyo ca apariggahitāyo honti, kulāni ca apariggahitāni honti— “ettakāhi āpattīhi ettakesu kulesu ārocetabbo”ti.**neither offenses nor families are specified in this way.*";
P_HTM[1097]="*Āpattipariyante yā āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti, tā āpattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāhi āpattīhi āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When there is a limit on offenses, if he tells about other offenses than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1098]="*Kulapariyante yāni kulāni pariggahitāni honti, tāni kulāni ṭhapetvā aññesu kulesu āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When there is a limit on families, if he tells other families than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1099]="*Āpattipariyante ca kulapariyante ca yā āpattiyo pariggahitāyo honti, tā āpattiyo ṭhapetvā yāni kulāni pariggahitāni honti, tāni kulāni ṭhapetvā aññāhi āpattīhi aññesu kulesu āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When there is a limit both on offenses and on families, if he tells about other offenses than those that are specified and he tells other families than those that are specified, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1100]="*Neva āpattipariyante na kulapariyante, anāpatti.**When there is neither a limit on offenses nor on families, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1101]="*Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the offense is grave, and he perceives it as such, and he tells a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1102]="*Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the offense is grave, but he is unsure of it, and he tells a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1103]="*Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī anupasampannassa āroceti, aññatra bhikkhusammutiyā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the offense is grave, but he perceives it as minor, and he tells a person who is not fully ordained, then, except if the monks have agreed, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1104]="*Aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he tells about a minor offense, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1105]="*Anupasampannassa duṭṭhullaṃ vā aduṭṭhullaṃ vā ajjhācāraṃ āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he tells about the misconduct of a person who is not fully ordained, whether grave or minor, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1106]="*Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the offense is minor, but he perceives it as grave, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1107]="*Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the offense is minor, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1108]="*Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the offense is minor, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1109]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1110]="*vatthuṃ āroceti no āpattiṃ,**if he tells about the action that was the basis for the offense, but not the class of offense;*";
P_HTM[1111]="*āpattiṃ āroceti no vatthuṃ,**if he tells about the class of offense, but not the action that was the basis for the offense;*";
P_HTM[1112]="*bhikkhusammutiyā,**if the monks have agreed;*";
P_HTM[1113]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1114]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1115]="*Duṭṭhullārocanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on telling about what is grave, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1116]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1117]="*Musāvādavagga**The sub-chapter on lying*";
P_HTM[1118]="*10. Pathavīkhaṇanasikkhāpada**10. The training rule on digging the earth*";
P_HTM[1119]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine,*";
P_HTM[1120]="*Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū navakammaṃ karontā pathaviṃ khaṇantipi khaṇāpentipi.**the monks there were doing building work. And they dug the earth and had it dug.*";
P_HTM[1121]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1122]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā pathaviṃ khaṇissantipi khaṇāpessantipi.**“How can the Sakyan monastics dig the earth and have it dug?*";
P_HTM[1123]="*Ekindriyaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jīvaṃ viheṭhentī”ti.**They are hurting one-sensed life.”*";
P_HTM[1124]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[1125]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[1126]="*“kathañhi nāma āḷavakā bhikkhū pathaviṃ khaṇissantipi khaṇāpessantipī”ti …pe…**“How can those monks at Āḷavī dig the earth and have it dug?” …*";
P_HTM[1127]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, pathaviṃ khaṇathapi khaṇāpethapī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[1128]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1129]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1130]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, pathaviṃ khaṇissathapi khaṇāpessathapi.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[1131]="*Jīvasaññino hi, moghapurisā, manussā pathaviyā.**People regard the earth as conscious.*";
P_HTM[1132]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1133]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1134]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu pathaviṃ khaṇeyya vā khaṇāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk digs the earth or has it dug, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1135]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1136]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1137]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1138]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1139]="*Pathavī nāma**The earth:*";
P_HTM[1140]="*dve pathaviyo— jātā ca pathavī ajātā ca pathavī.**there are two kinds of earth: productive earth and unproductive earth.*";
P_HTM[1141]="*Jātā nāma pathavī—**Productive earth:*";
P_HTM[1142]="*suddhapaṃsu suddhamattikā appapāsāṇā appasakkharā appakaṭhalā appamarumbā appavālikā, yebhuyyenapaṃsukā, yebhuyyenamattikā.**pure soil, pure clay, with few stones, with few pebbles, with few potsherds, with little gravel, with little sand; mostly soil, mostly clay.*";
P_HTM[1143]="*Adaḍḍhāpi vuccati jātā pathavī.**If it is unburnt, it is also called “productive earth”.*";
P_HTM[1144]="*Yopi paṃsupuñjo vā mattikāpuñjo vā atirekacātumāsaṃ ovaṭṭho, ayampi vuccati jātā pathavī.**A pile of soil or clay that has been rained on for more than four months—this too is called “productive earth”.*";
P_HTM[1145]="*Ajātā nāma pathavī—**Unproductive earth:*";
P_HTM[1146]="*suddhapāsāṇā suddhasakkharā suddhakaṭhalā suddhamarumbā suddhavālikā appapaṃsukā appamattikā, yebhuyyenapāsāṇā, yebhuyyenasakkharā, yebhuyyenakaṭhalā, yebhuyyenamarumbā, yebhuyyenavālikā.**just stones, just pebbles, just potsherds, just gravel, just sand, with little soil, with little clay; mostly stones, mostly pebbles, mostly potsherds, mostly gravel, mostly sand.*";
P_HTM[1147]="*Daḍḍhāpi vuccati ajātā pathavī.**If it is burnt, it is also called “unproductive earth”.*";
P_HTM[1148]="*Yopi paṃsupuñjo vā mattikāpuñjo vā omakacātumāsaṃ ovaṭṭho, ayampi vuccati ajātā pathavī.**A pile of soil or a pile that has been rained on for less than four months—this too is called “unproductive earth”.*";
P_HTM[1149]="*Khaṇeyyāti**Digs:*";
P_HTM[1150]="*sayaṃ khaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he digs it himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1151]="*Khaṇāpeyyāti**Has dug:*";
P_HTM[1152]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1153]="*Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi khaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he only asks once, then even if the other digs a lot, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1154]="*Pathaviyā pathavisaññī khaṇati vā khaṇāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, dahati vā dahāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is earth, and he perceives it as such, and he digs it or has it dug, or he breaks it or has it broken, or he burns it or has it burnt, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1155]="*Pathaviyā vematiko khaṇati vā khaṇāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, dahati vā dahāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is earth, but he is unsure of it, and he digs it or has it dug, or he breaks it or has it broken, or he burns it or has it burnt, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1156]="*Pathaviyā apathavisaññī khaṇati vā khaṇāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, dahati vā dahāpeti vā, anāpatti.**If it is earth, but he does not perceive it as such, and he digs it or has it dug, or he breaks it or has it broken, or he burns it or has it burnt, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1157]="*Apathaviyā pathavisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not earth, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1158]="*Apathaviyā vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not earth, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1159]="*Apathaviyā apathavisaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not earth, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1160]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1161]="*“imaṃ jāna, imaṃ dehi, imaṃ āhara, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karohī”ti bhaṇati,**if he says, “Consider this,” “Give this,” “Bring this,” “There’s need for this,” “Make this allowable;”*";
P_HTM[1162]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[1163]="*asatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[1164]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[1165]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1166]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1167]="*Pathavīkhaṇanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on digging the earth, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1168]="*Musāvādavaggo paṭhamo.**The first sub-chapter on lying is finished.*";
P_HTM[1169]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[1170]="*Musā omasapesuññaṃ,**Falsely, abusive, and malicious talebearing,*";
P_HTM[1171]="*padaseyyāya ve duve;**Memorizing, and two on beds;*";
P_HTM[1172]="*Aññatra viññunā bhūtā,**Except with one who understands, true,*";
P_HTM[1173]="*duṭṭhullāpatti khaṇanāti.**Grave offense, digging.*";
P_HTM[1174]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1175]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1176]="*11. Bhūtagāmasikkhāpada**11. The training rule on plants*";
P_HTM[1177]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine,*";
P_HTM[1178]="*Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū navakammaṃ karontā rukkhaṃ chindantipi chedāpentipi.**the monks there were doing building work. They were cutting down trees and having them cut down.*";
P_HTM[1179]="*Aññataropi āḷavako bhikkhu rukkhaṃ chindati.**Then, when a certain monk was cutting down a tree,*";
P_HTM[1180]="*Tasmiṃ rukkhe adhivatthā devatā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**the deity that lived in it said to him,*";
P_HTM[1181]="*“mā, bhante, attano bhavanaṃ kattukāmo mayhaṃ bhavanaṃ chindī”ti.**“Venerable, don’t cut down our dwelling because you want to build a dwelling for yourself.”*";
P_HTM[1182]="*So bhikkhu anādiyanto chindiyeva, tassā ca devatāya dārakassa bāhuṃ ākoṭesi.**Not taking any heed, he just cut it down, and he hurt the arm of that deity’s child.*";
P_HTM[1183]="*Atha kho tassā devatāya etadahosi—**The deity thought,*";
P_HTM[1184]="*“yannūnāhaṃ imaṃ bhikkhuṃ idheva jīvitā voropeyyan”ti.**“Why don’t I just kill this monk?”*";
P_HTM[1185]="*Atha kho tassā devatāya etadahosi—**But then it reconsidered,*";
P_HTM[1186]="*“na kho metaṃ patirūpaṃ yāhaṃ imaṃ bhikkhuṃ idheva jīvitā voropeyyaṃ.**“It wouldn’t be right to just kill this monk.*";
P_HTM[1187]="*Yannūnāhaṃ bhagavato etamatthaṃ āroceyyan”ti.**Let me instead tell the Buddha about this matter.”*";
P_HTM[1188]="*Atha kho sā devatā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And it approached the Buddha and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[1189]="*“Sādhu sādhu, devate.**“Well done, deity!*";
P_HTM[1190]="*Sādhu kho tvaṃ, devate, taṃ bhikkhuṃ jīvitā na voropesi.**It’s good that you didn’t kill that monk.*";
P_HTM[1191]="*Sacajja tvaṃ, devate, taṃ bhikkhuṃ jīvitā voropeyyāsi, bahuñca tvaṃ, devate, apuññaṃ pasaveyyāsi.**If you had killed that monk, you would have made much demerit.*";
P_HTM[1192]="*Gaccha tvaṃ, devate, amukasmiṃ okāse rukkho vivitto tasmiṃ upagacchā”ti.**The tree over there is empty. Take that as your dwelling.”*";
P_HTM[1193]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized the monks,*";
P_HTM[1194]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā rukkhaṃ chindissantipi chedāpessantipi ekindriyaṃ samaṇā sakyaputtiyā jīvaṃ viheṭhentī”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics cut down trees and have them cut down? They are hurting life with one sense.”*";
P_HTM[1195]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[1196]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[1197]="*“kathañhi nāma āḷavakā bhikkhū rukkhaṃ chindissantipi chedāpessantipī”ti …pe…**“How can those monks at Āḷavī cut down trees and have them cut down?”…*";
P_HTM[1198]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, rukkhaṃ chindathāpi chedāpethāpī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[1199]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1200]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1201]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, rukkhaṃ chindissathāpi, chedāpessathāpi.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[1202]="*Jīvasaññino hi, moghapurisā, manussā rukkhasmiṃ.**People regard trees as conscious.*";
P_HTM[1203]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1204]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1205]="*“Bhūtagāmapātabyatāya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk destroys plants, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1206]="*Bhūtagāmo nāma**Plants:*";
P_HTM[1207]="*pañca bījajātāni— mūlabījaṃ, khandhabījaṃ, phaḷubījaṃ, aggabījaṃ, bījabījameva pañcamaṃ.**there are five kinds of propagation: propagation from roots, propagation from stems, propagation from joints, propagation from cuttings, propagation from seeds.*";
P_HTM[1208]="*Mūlabījaṃ nāma—**Propagation from roots:*";
P_HTM[1209]="*haliddi, siṅgiveraṃ, vacā, vacattaṃ, ativisā, kaṭukarohiṇī, usīraṃ, bhaddamuttakaṃ, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi mūle jāyanti, mūle sañjāyanti, etaṃ mūlabījaṃ nāma.**turmeric, ginger, sweet flag, white sweet flag, atis root, black hellebore, khus root, nutgrass, or any other plant produced from roots, that grows from roots—this is called “propagation from roots”.*";
P_HTM[1210]="*Khandhabījaṃ nāma—**Propagation from stems:*";
P_HTM[1211]="*assattho, nigrodho, pilakkho, udumbaro, kacchako, kapitthano, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi khandhe jāyanti, khandhe sañjāyanti, etaṃ khandhabījaṃ nāma.**the Bodhi tree, the banyan tree, the Indian rock fig, the cluster fig, the Indian cedar, the portia tree, or any other plant produced from stems, that grows from stems—this is called “propagation from stems”.*";
P_HTM[1212]="*Phaḷubījaṃ nāma—**Propagation from joints:*";
P_HTM[1213]="*ucchu, veḷu, naḷo, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi pabbe jāyanti, pabbe sañjāyanti, etaṃ phaḷubījaṃ nāma.**sugarcane, bamboo, reed, or any other plant produced from joints, that grows from joints—this is called “propagation from joints”.*";
P_HTM[1214]="*Aggabījaṃ nāma—**Propagation from cuttings:*";
P_HTM[1215]="*ajjukaṃ, phaṇijjakaṃ, hiriveraṃ, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi agge jāyanti, agge sañjāyanti, etaṃ aggabījaṃ nāma.**shrubby basil, rajmahal hemp, Vicks plant, or any other plant produced from cuttings, that grows from cuttings—this is called “propagation from cuttings”.*";
P_HTM[1216]="*Bījabījaṃ nāma—**Propagation from seeds:*";
P_HTM[1217]="*pubbaṇṇaṃ, aparaṇṇaṃ, yāni vā panaññānipi atthi bīje jāyanti, bīje sañjāyanti, etaṃ bījabījaṃ nāma.**grains, vegetables, or any other plant produced from seeds, that grows from seeds—this is called “propagation from seeds”.*";
P_HTM[1218]="*Bīje bījasaññī chindati vā chedāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, pacati vā pacāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is capable of propagation, and he perceives that it is, and he cuts it down or has it cut down, or he breaks it or has it broken, or he cooks it or has it cooked, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1219]="*Bīje vematiko chindati vā chedāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, pacati vā pacāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is capable of propagation, but he is unsure of it, and  he cuts it down or has it cut down, or he breaks it or has it broken, or he cooks it or has it cooked, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1220]="*Bīje abījasaññī chindati vā chedāpeti vā, bhindati vā bhedāpeti vā, pacati vā pacāpeti vā, anāpatti.**If it is capable of propagation, but he perceives that it is not, and he cuts it down or has it cut down, or he breaks it or has it broken, or he cooks it or has it cooked, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1221]="*Abīje bījasaññī āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not capable of propagation, but he perceives that it is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1222]="*Abīje vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not capable of propagation, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1223]="*Abīje abījasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not capable of propagation, and he perceives that it is not, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1224]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1225]="*“imaṃ jāna, imaṃ dehi, imaṃ āhara, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karohī”ti bhaṇati,**if he says, “Consider this”, “Give this”, “Bring this”, “There’s need for this”, “Make this allowable;”*";
P_HTM[1226]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[1227]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[1228]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[1229]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1230]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1231]="*Bhūtagāmasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on plants, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1232]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1233]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1234]="*12. Aññavādakasikkhāpada**12. The training rule on evasive speech*";
P_HTM[1235]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[1236]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo anācāraṃ ācaritvā saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—**Venerable Channa was misbehaving. Then, when he was examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha, he spoke evasively,*";
P_HTM[1237]="*“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā”ti?**“Who has committed an offense? What offense was committed? In regard to what was it committed? How was it committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?”*";
P_HTM[1238]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1239]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissati—**“How can Venerable Channa speak evasively when examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha?”…*";
P_HTM[1240]="*‘ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā’”ti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[1241]="*saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarasi—**“Is it true, Channa, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1242]="*‘ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1243]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1244]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[1245]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarissasi—**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1246]="*“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1247]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1248]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[1249]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1250]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ ropetu.**“Well then, monks, the Sangha should charge Channa with evasive speech.*";
P_HTM[1251]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, ropetabbaṃ.**And he is to be charged like this.*";
P_HTM[1252]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1253]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1254]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati.**The monk Channa speaks evasively when examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1255]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ ropeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should charge him with evasive speech.*";
P_HTM[1256]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1257]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1258]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati.**The monk Channa speaks evasively when examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1259]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ ropeti.**The Sangha is charging him with evasive speech.*";
P_HTM[1260]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakassa ropanā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of charging him with evasive speech should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1261]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1262]="*Ropitaṃ saṅghena channassa bhikkhuno aññavādakaṃ.**The Sangha has charged the monk Channa with evasive speech.*";
P_HTM[1263]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1264]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ channaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**After rebuking Channa in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[1265]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1266]="*“Aññavādake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk speaks evasively, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1267]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[1268]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno aññenaññaṃ paṭicaranto—**Later, when Channa was again being examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha, he thought,*";
P_HTM[1269]="*“āpattiṃ āpajjissāmī”ti tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ viheseti.**“By speaking evasively I’ll commit an offense,” and he instead harassed the Sangha by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[1270]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1271]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ vihesessatī”ti …pe…**“When he’s examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha, how can Venerable Channa harass the Sangha by remaining silent?” …*";
P_HTM[1272]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ vihesesī”ti?**“Is it true, Channa, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1273]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1274]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[1275]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ vihesessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1276]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1277]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[1278]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1279]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ ropetu.**“Well then, monks, the Sangha should charge Channa with harassment.*";
P_HTM[1280]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, ropetabbaṃ.**And he is to be charged like this.*";
P_HTM[1281]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1282]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1283]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ viheseti.**The monk Channa, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha, harasses the Sangha by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[1284]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ ropeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should charge him with harassment.*";
P_HTM[1285]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1286]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1287]="*Ayaṃ channo bhikkhu saṅghamajjhe āpattiyā anuyuñjīyamāno tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ viheseti.**The monk Channa, when examined about an offense in the midst of the Sangha, harasses the Sangha by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[1288]="*Saṅgho channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ ropeti.**The Sangha is charging him with harassment.*";
P_HTM[1289]="*Yassāyasmato khamati channassa bhikkhuno vihesakassa ropanā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of charging him of harassment should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1290]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1291]="*Ropitaṃ saṅghena channassa bhikkhuno vihesakaṃ.**The Sangha has charged the monk Channa with harassment.*";
P_HTM[1292]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1293]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ channaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**After rebuking Channa in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[1294]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1295]="*“Aññavādake vihesake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk speaks evasively or harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1296]="*Aññavādako nāma**One who speaks evasively:*";
P_HTM[1297]="*saṅghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati— “ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā”ti. Eso aññavādako nāma.**when being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, he speaks evasively because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying, “Who has committed an offense? What offense was committed? In regard to what was it committed? How was it committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?”—this is called “one who speaks evasively”.*";
P_HTM[1298]="*Vihesako nāma**One who harasses:*";
P_HTM[1299]="*saṅghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ viheseti. Eso vihesako nāma.**when being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, he harasses the Sangha by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it—this is called “one who harasses”.*";
P_HTM[1300]="*Aropite aññavādake saṅghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—**If he has not been charged with evasive speech, but he is being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then speaks evasively because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying,*";
P_HTM[1301]="*“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“Who has committed an offense? What offense was committed? In regard to what was it committed? How was it committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1302]="*Aropite vihesake saṅghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ viheseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he has not been charged with harassment, but he is being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then harasses the Sangha by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1303]="*Ropite aññavādake saṅghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo aññenaññaṃ paṭicarati—**If he has been charged with evasive speech, and he is being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then speaks evasively because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, saying,*";
P_HTM[1304]="*“ko āpanno, kiṃ āpanno, kismiṃ āpanno, kathaṃ āpanno, kaṃ bhaṇatha, kiṃ bhaṇathā”ti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**“Who has committed an offense? What offense was committed? In regard to what was it committed? How was it committed? Who are you talking about? What are you talking about?” then he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1305]="*Ropite vihesake saṅghamajjhe vatthusmiṃ vā āpattiyā vā anuyuñjīyamāno taṃ na kathetukāmo taṃ na ugghāṭetukāmo tuṇhībhūto saṅghaṃ viheseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has been charged with harassment, and he is being examined in the midst of the Sangha about an action that was the basis for an offense or about the class of an offense, and he then harasses the Sangha by remaining silent because he does not want to talk about it or reveal it, then he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1306]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī aññavādake vihesake, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he speaks evasively or he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1307]="*Dhammakamme vematiko aññavādake vihesake, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he speaks evasively or he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1308]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī aññavādake vihesake, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he speaks evasively or he harasses, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1309]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1310]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1311]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1312]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1313]="*ajānanto pucchati,**if he asks because he does not know;*";
P_HTM[1314]="*gilāno vā na katheti;**if he does not speak because he is sick;*";
P_HTM[1315]="*“saṅghassa bhaṇḍanaṃ vā kalaho vā viggaho vā vivādo vā bhavissatī”ti na katheti;**if he does not speak because he thinks there will be quarrels or disputes in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1316]="*“saṅghabhedo vā saṅgharāji vā bhavissatī”ti na katheti;**if he does not speak because he thinks there will be a fracture or schism in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[1317]="*“adhammena vā vaggena vā nakammārahassa vā kammaṃ karissatī”ti na katheti;**if he does not speak because he thinks the legal procedure will be illegitimate, done by an incomplete assembly, or done to one who does not deserve a legal procedure;*";
P_HTM[1318]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1319]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1320]="*Aññavādakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on evasive speech, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1321]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1322]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1323]="*13. Ujjhāpanakasikkhāpada**13. The training rule on complaining*";
P_HTM[1324]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[1325]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā dabbo mallaputto saṅghassa senāsanañca paññapeti bhattāni ca uddisati.**At that time Venerable Dabba the Mallian was assigning the dwellings and designating the meals,*";
P_HTM[1326]="*Tena kho pana samayena mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū navakā ceva honti appapuññā ca.**and the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka were newly ordained.*";
P_HTM[1327]="*Yāni saṅghassa lāmakāni senāsanāni tāni tesaṃ pāpuṇanti lāmakāni ca bhattāni.**They had little merit, getting inferior dwellings and meals.*";
P_HTM[1328]="*Te āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ bhikkhū ujjhāpenti—**They then complained about Dabba to other monks,*";
P_HTM[1329]="*“chandāya dabbo mallaputto senāsanaṃ paññapeti, chandāya ca bhattāni uddisatī”ti.**“Dabba the Mallian assigns dwellings and designates meals based on favoritism.”*";
P_HTM[1330]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1331]="*“kathañhi nāma mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ bhikkhū ujjhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka complain about Venerable Dabba to other monks?”…*";
P_HTM[1332]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ bhikkhū ujjhāpethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[1333]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1334]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1335]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ bhikkhū ujjhāpessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[1336]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1337]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1338]="*“Ujjhāpanake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk complains, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1339]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[1340]="*Tena kho pana samayena mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū—**Knowing that the Buddha had prohibited complaining, the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka thought of other ways of getting the monks to hear about their grievances.*";
P_HTM[1341]="*“‘bhagavatā ujjhāpanakaṃ paṭikkhittan’ti ‘ettāvatā bhikkhū sossantī’”ti bhikkhūnaṃ sāmantā āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ khiyyanti—**They then criticized Dabba the Mallian in the vicinity of other monks,*";
P_HTM[1342]="*“chandāya dabbo mallaputto senāsanaṃ paññapeti, chandāya ca bhattāni uddisatī”ti.**“Dabba assigns dwellings and designates meals based on favoritism.”*";
P_HTM[1343]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1344]="*“kathañhi nāma mettiyabhūmajakā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ khiyyissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks Mettiya and Bhūmajaka criticize Venerable Dabba?”…*";
P_HTM[1345]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ khiyyathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[1346]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1347]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1348]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, dabbaṃ mallaputtaṃ khiyyissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[1349]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1350]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1351]="*“Ujjhāpanake khiyyanake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk complains or criticizes, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1352]="*Ujjhāpanakaṃ nāma**Complaining:*";
P_HTM[1353]="*upasampannaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ senāsanapaññāpakaṃ vā bhattuddesakaṃ vā yāgubhājakaṃ vā phalabhājakaṃ vā khajjabhājakaṃ vā appamattakavissajjakaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo, ayasaṃ kattukāmo, maṅkukattukāmo, upasampannaṃ ujjhāpeti vā khiyyati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when someone who is fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of fresh foods or the distributor of small requisites, and he has been appointed by the Sangha as such, then if a monk complains about him or criticizes him to one who is fully ordained—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1354]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī ujjhāpanake khiyyanake āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he complains or criticizes, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1355]="*Dhammakamme vematiko ujjhāpanake khiyyanake āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he complains or criticizes, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1356]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī ujjhāpanake khiyyanake āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he complains or criticizes, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1357]="*Anupasampannaṃ ujjhāpeti vā khiyyati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he complains or criticizes him to one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1358]="*Upasampannaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ senāsanapaññāpakaṃ vā bhattuddesakaṃ vā yāgubhājakaṃ vā phalabhājakaṃ vā khajjabhājakaṃ vā appamattakavissajjakaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo, ayasaṃ kattukāmo, maṅkukattukāmo, upasampannaṃ vā anupasampannaṃ vā ujjhāpeti vā khiyyati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When someone who is fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of fresh foods or the distributor of small requisites, but he has not been appointed by the Sangha as such, then if a monk complains about him or criticizes him to one who is fully ordained or to one who is not fully ordained—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1359]="*Anupasampannaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ vā asammataṃ vā senāsanapaññāpakaṃ vā bhattuddesakaṃ vā yāgubhājakaṃ vā phalabhājakaṃ vā khajjabhājakaṃ vā appamattakavissajjakaṃ vā avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo, ayasaṃ kattukāmo, maṅkukattukāmo, upasampannaṃ vā anupasampannaṃ vā ujjhāpeti vā khiyyati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When someone who is not fully ordained is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of fresh foods or the distributor of small requisites, whether he has been appointed by the Sangha as such or not, then if a monk complains about him or criticizes him to one who is fully ordained or to one who is not fully ordained—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1360]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1361]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1362]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1363]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1364]="*pakatiyā chandā dosā mohā bhayā karontaṃ ujjhāpeti vā khiyyati vā,**if he complains about or criticizes one who regularly acts out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, or fear;*";
P_HTM[1365]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1366]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1367]="*Ujjhāpanakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on complaining, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1368]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1369]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1370]="*14. Senāsanasikkhāpada**14. The training rule on furniture*";
P_HTM[1371]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery during winter,*";
P_HTM[1372]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū hemantike kāle ajjhokāse senāsanaṃ paññapetvā kāyaṃ otāpentā kāle ārocite taṃ pakkamantā neva uddhariṃsu na uddharāpesuṃ, anāpucchā pakkamiṃsu.**the monks put furniture outside in order to warm themselves in the sun. But when the time for departure was announced, they departed without putting it away, having it put away, or taking leave.*";
P_HTM[1373]="*Senāsanaṃ ovaṭṭhaṃ hoti.**The furniture was rained on.*";
P_HTM[1374]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1375]="*“kathaṃ hi nāma bhikkhū ajjhokāse senāsanaṃ paññapetvā taṃ pakkamantā neva uddharissanti na uddharāpessanti, anāpucchā pakkamissanti, senāsanaṃ ovaṭṭhan”ti.**“How could those monks put furniture outside and then depart without putting it away, having it put away, or taking leave? The furniture was rained on.”*";
P_HTM[1376]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū te anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1377]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū ajjhokāse …pe…**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?…*";
P_HTM[1378]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1379]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu saṅghikaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā bhisiṃ vā kocchaṃ vā ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk takes a bed, a bench, a mattress, or a stool belonging to the Sangha and puts it outside or has it put outside, and he then departs without putting it away, having it put away, or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1380]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[1381]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū ajjhokāse vasitvā kālasseva senāsanaṃ abhiharanti.**Soon afterwards, monks who had stayed outside brought the furniture back even though it was not the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[1382]="*Addasā kho bhagavā te bhikkhū kālasseva senāsanaṃ abhiharante.**The Buddha saw this.*";
P_HTM[1383]="*Disvāna etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**After giving a teaching, he addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1384]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭha māse avassikasaṅkete maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā yattha kākā vā kulalā vā na ūhadanti tattha senāsanaṃ nikkhipitun”ti.**“Monks, during the eight months outside of the rainy season, I allow you to store furniture under a roof-cover or at the foot of a tree or wherever crows or ravens donʼt leave droppings.”*";
P_HTM[1385]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1386]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1387]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1388]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1389]="*Saṅghikaṃ nāma**Belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1390]="*saṅghassa dinnaṃ hoti pariccattaṃ.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1391]="*Mañco nāma**A bed:*";
P_HTM[1392]="*cattāro mañcā—**there are four kinds of beds:*";
P_HTM[1393]="*masārako, bundikābaddho, kuḷīrapādako, āhaccapādako.**one with legs and frame, called _masāraka_; one with legs and frame, called _bundikābaddha_; one with crooked legs; one with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[1394]="*Pīṭhaṃ nāma**A bench:*";
P_HTM[1395]="*cattāri pīṭhāni— masārakaṃ, bundikābaddhaṃ, kuḷīrapādakaṃ, āhaccapādakaṃ.**there are four kinds of benches: one with legs and frame, called _masāraka_; one with legs and frame, called _bundikābaddha_; one with crooked legs; one with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[1396]="*Bhisi nāma**A mattress:*";
P_HTM[1397]="*pañca bhisiyo— uṇṇabhisi, coḷabhisi, vākabhisi, tiṇabhisi, paṇṇabhisi.**there are five kinds of mattresses: a mattress stuffed with wool, a mattress stuffed with cloth, a mattress stuffed with bark, a mattress stuffed with grass, a mattress stuffed with leaves.*";
P_HTM[1398]="*Kocchaṃ nāma—**A stool:*";
P_HTM[1399]="*vākamayaṃ vā usīramayaṃ vā muñjamayaṃ vā pabbajamayaṃ vā anto saṃveṭhetvā baddhaṃ hoti.**one made of bark, one made of khus grass, one made of reed. It is upholstered and then bound together.*";
P_HTM[1400]="*Santharitvāti**Puts outside:*";
P_HTM[1401]="*sayaṃ santharitvā.**puts outside oneself.*";
P_HTM[1402]="*Santharāpetvāti**Has put outside:*";
P_HTM[1403]="*aññaṃ santharāpetvā.**gets another to put outside.*";
P_HTM[1404]="*Anupasampannaṃ santharāpeti, tassa palibodho.**If he gets one who is not fully ordained to put it outside, it is the responsibility of the monk.*";
P_HTM[1405]="*Upasampannaṃ santharāpeti, santhārakassa palibodho.**If he gets one who is fully ordained to put it outside, it is the responsibility of the one who puts it outside.*";
P_HTM[1406]="*Taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyyāti**Departs without putting it away:*";
P_HTM[1407]="*na sayaṃ uddhareyya.**he does not put it away himself.*";
P_HTM[1408]="*Na uddharāpeyyāti**Having it put away:*";
P_HTM[1409]="*na aññaṃ uddharāpeyya.**he does not get another to put it away.*";
P_HTM[1410]="*Anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyyāti**Or taking leave:*";
P_HTM[1411]="*bhikkhuṃ vā sāmaṇeraṃ vā ārāmikaṃ vā anāpucchā majjhimassa purisassa leḍḍupātaṃ atikkamantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he does not take leave of a monk, a novice monk, or a monastery worker, then when he goes beyond the distance of a stone-throw of an average man, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1412]="*Saṅghike saṅghikasaññī ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, and he perceives it as such, and he puts it outside or has it put outside, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1413]="*Saṅghike vematiko …pe…**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he is unsure of it …*";
P_HTM[1414]="*saṅghike puggalikasaññī ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he puts it outside or has it put outside, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1415]="*Cimilikaṃ vā uttarattharaṇaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā taṭṭikaṃ vā cammakhaṇḍaṃ vā pādapuñchaniṃ vā phalakapīṭhaṃ vā ajjhokāse santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a mat underlay, a bedspread, a floor cover, a straw mat, a hide, a foot-wiping cloth, or a wooden bench, and he puts it outside or has it put outside, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1416]="*Puggalike saṅghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Sangha, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1417]="*Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1418]="*Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as such, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1419]="*Attano puggalike anāpatti.**If it belongs to himself, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1420]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1421]="*uddharitvā gacchati,**if he departs after putting it away;*";
P_HTM[1422]="*uddharāpetvā gacchati,**if he departs after having it put away;*";
P_HTM[1423]="*āpucchaṃ gacchati,**if he departs after taking leave;*";
P_HTM[1424]="*otāpento gacchati,**if he departs while he is sunning it;*";
P_HTM[1425]="*kenaci palibuddhaṃ hoti,**if the furniture is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[1426]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[1427]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1428]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1429]="*Senāsanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on furniture, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1430]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1431]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1432]="*15. Dutiyasenāsanasikkhāpada**15. The second training rule on furniture*";
P_HTM[1433]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1434]="*Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū sahāyakā honti.**At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were friends.*";
P_HTM[1435]="*Te vasantāpi ekatova vasanti, pakkamantāpi ekatova pakkamanti.**The lived together, and when going somewhere they would leave together.*";
P_HTM[1436]="*Te aññatarasmiṃ saṅghike vihāre seyyaṃ santharitvā taṃ pakkamantā neva uddhariṃsu na uddharāpesuṃ, anāpucchā pakkamiṃsu.**On one occasion they put out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, but then departed without putting it away, having it put away, or taking leave.*";
P_HTM[1437]="*Senāsanaṃ upacikāhi khāyitaṃ hoti.**The furniture was eaten by termites.*";
P_HTM[1438]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1439]="*“kathañhi nāma sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū saṅghike vihāre seyyaṃ santharitvā taṃ pakkamantā neva uddharissanti na uddharāpessanti, anāpucchā pakkamissanti, senāsanaṃ upacikāhi khāyitan”ti.**“How could those monks from the group of seventeen put out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, and then depart without putting it away, getting it put away, or taking leave? The furniture was eaten by termites.”*";
P_HTM[1440]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1441]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū saṅghike vihāre seyyaṃ santharitvā taṃ pakkamantā neva uddhariṃsu na uddharāpesuṃ, anāpucchā pakkamiṃsu, senāsanaṃ upacikāhi khāyitan”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those monks did this?”*";
P_HTM[1442]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1443]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[1444]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā saṅghike vihāre seyyaṃ santharitvā taṃ pakkamantā neva uddharissanti na uddharāpessanti, anāpucchā pakkamissanti, senāsanaṃ upacikāhi khāyitaṃ.**“How could those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[1445]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1446]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1447]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu saṅghike vihāre seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk puts out bedding in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, or has it put out, and he then departs without putting it away, having it put away, or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1448]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1449]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1450]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1451]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1452]="*Saṅghiko nāma vihāro**A dwelling belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1453]="*saṅghassa dinno hoti pariccatto.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1454]="*Seyyaṃ nāma**Bedding:*";
P_HTM[1455]="*bhisi, cimilikā uttarattharaṇaṃ, bhūmattharaṇaṃ, taṭṭikā, cammakhaṇḍo, nisīdanaṃ, paccattharaṇaṃ, tiṇasanthāro, paṇṇasanthāro.**a mattress, a mat underlay, a bedspread, a floor cover, a straw mat, a hide, a sitting mat, a sheet, a spread of grass, a spread of leaves.*";
P_HTM[1456]="*Santharitvāti**Puts out:*";
P_HTM[1457]="*sayaṃ santharitvā.**puts out oneself.*";
P_HTM[1458]="*Santharāpetvāti**Has put out:*";
P_HTM[1459]="*aññaṃ santharāpetvā.**gets another to put out.*";
P_HTM[1460]="*Taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyyāti**Departs without putting it away:*";
P_HTM[1461]="*na sayaṃ uddhareyya.**he does not put it away himself.*";
P_HTM[1462]="*Na uddharāpeyyāti**Having it put away:*";
P_HTM[1463]="*na aññaṃ uddharāpeyya.**he does not get another to put it away.*";
P_HTM[1464]="*Anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyyāti**Or taking leave:*";
P_HTM[1465]="*bhikkhuṃ vā sāmaṇeraṃ vā ārāmikaṃ vā anāpucchā parikkhittassa ārāmassa parikkhepaṃ atikkamantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he does not take leave of a monk, a novice monk, or a monastery worker, and he crosses the boundary of an enclosed monastery, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1466]="*Aparikkhittassa ārāmassa upacāraṃ atikkamantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he goes beyond the vicinity of an unenclosed monastery, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1467]="*Saṅghike saṅghikasaññī seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, and he perceives it as such, and he puts out bedding there or has it put out, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1468]="*Saṅghike vematiko seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he is unsure of it, and he puts out bedding there or has it put out, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1469]="*Saṅghike puggalikasaññī seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he puts out bedding there or has it put out, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1470]="*Vihārassa upacāre vā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts out bedding, or has it put out, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in the assembly hall, under a roof-cover, or at the foot of a tree, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1471]="*Mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā vihāre vā vihārassūpacāre vā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā taṃ pakkamanto neva uddhareyya na uddharāpeyya, anāpucchaṃ vā gaccheyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts out a bed or a bench, or has it put out, in a dwelling, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in the assembly hall, under a roof-cover, or at the foot of a tree, and he then departs without putting it away or having it put away or taking leave, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1472]="*Puggalike saṅghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Sangha, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1473]="*Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1474]="*Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as such, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1475]="*Attano puggalike anāpatti.**If it belongs to himself, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1476]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1477]="*uddharitvā gacchati,**if he departs after putting it away;*";
P_HTM[1478]="*uddharāpetvā gacchati,**if he departs after having it put away;*";
P_HTM[1479]="*āpucchaṃ gacchati,**if he departs after taking leave;*";
P_HTM[1480]="*kenaci palibuddhaṃ hoti,**if the bedding is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[1481]="*sāpekkho gantvā tattha ṭhito āpucchati,**if he abandons his intention to return, and at that spot takes leave;*";
P_HTM[1482]="*kenaci palibuddho hoti,**if he is obstructed;*";
P_HTM[1483]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[1484]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1485]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1486]="*Dutiyasenāsanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The second training rule on furniture, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1487]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1488]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1489]="*16. Anupakhajjasikkhāpada**16. The training rule on encroaching*";
P_HTM[1490]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[1491]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū varaseyyāyo palibundhenti, therā bhikkhū vuṭṭhāpenti.**the monks from the group of six had taken possession of the best sleeping places. When the the senior monks evicted them,*";
P_HTM[1492]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**they thought,*";
P_HTM[1493]="*“kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena idheva vassaṃ vaseyyāmā”ti?**“How can we get to stay here during the rainy season?”*";
P_HTM[1494]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappenti—**They then arranged their sleeping places so as to encroach on the senior monks, thinking,*";
P_HTM[1495]="*“yassa sambādho bhavissati so pakkamissatī”ti.**“Whoever feels crowded will leave.”*";
P_HTM[1496]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1497]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappessantī”ti.**“How could the monks from the group of six arrange their sleeping places so as to encroach on the senior monks?”*";
P_HTM[1498]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1499]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1500]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1501]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1502]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, there bhikkhū anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1503]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1504]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1505]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu saṅghike vihāre jānaṃ pubbupagataṃ bhikkhuṃ anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeyya— yassa sambādho bhavissati so pakkamissatī’ti, etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If, in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, a monk arranges his sleeping place in a way that encroaches on a monk that he knows arrived there before him, with the intention that anyone who feels crowded will leave, and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1506]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1507]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1508]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1509]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1510]="*Saṅghiko nāma vihāro**A dwelling belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1511]="*saṅghassa dinno hoti pariccatto.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1512]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[1513]="*vuḍḍhoti jānāti, gilānoti jānāti, saṅghena dinnoti jānāti.**he knows that he is senior, he knows that he is sick, he knows that it was given to him by the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1514]="*Anupakhajjāti**To encroach on:*";
P_HTM[1515]="*anupavisitvā.**enters after.*";
P_HTM[1516]="*Seyyaṃ kappeyyāti**Arranges his sleeping place:*";
P_HTM[1517]="*mañcassa vā pīṭhassa vā pavisantassa vā nikkhamantassa vā upacāre seyyaṃ santharati vā santharāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he puts out his sleeping place in the vicinity of the bed, the bench, the entrance, or the exit, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1518]="*Abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1519]="*Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññanti**He does so only for this reason and no other:*";
P_HTM[1520]="*na añño koci paccayo hoti anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappetuṃ.**there is no other reason for arranging his sleeping place in a way that encroaches.*";
P_HTM[1521]="*Saṅghike saṅghikasaññī anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, and he perceives it as such, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1522]="*Saṅghike vematiko anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he is unsure of it, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1523]="*Saṅghike puggalikasaññī anupakhajja seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he arranges his sleeping place there in a way that encroaches, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1524]="*Mañcassa vā pīṭhassa vā pavisantassa vā nikkhamantassa vā upacāraṃ ṭhapetvā seyyaṃ santharati vā santharāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts out his sleeping place, or has it put out, anywhere apart from the vicinity of the bed, the bench, the entrance, or the exit, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1525]="*Abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1526]="*Vihārassa upacāre vā upaṭṭhānasālāyaṃ vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā ajjhokāse vā seyyaṃ santharati vā santharāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts out his sleeping place, or has it put out, in the vicinity of a dwelling, in an assembly hall, under a roof-cover, at the foot of a tree, or out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1527]="*Abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sits down or lies down on it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1528]="*Puggalike saṅghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Sangha, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1529]="*Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1530]="*Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as such, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1531]="*Attano puggalike anāpatti.**If it belongs to himself, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1532]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1533]="*gilāno pavisati,**if he enters because he is sick;*";
P_HTM[1534]="*sītena vā uṇhena vā pīḷito pavisati,**if he enters because he is feeling cold or hot;*";
P_HTM[1535]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[1536]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1537]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1538]="*Anupakhajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on encroaching, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1539]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1540]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1541]="*17. Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpada**17. The training rule on throwing out*";
P_HTM[1542]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1543]="*Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū aññataraṃ paccantimaṃ mahāvihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti—**At that time the monks from the group of seventeen were repairing a large dwelling nearby,*";
P_HTM[1544]="*“idha mayaṃ vassaṃ vasissāmā”ti.**intending to stay there for the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[1545]="*Addasaṃsu kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonte.**The monks from the group of six saw this*";
P_HTM[1546]="*Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—**and said,*";
P_HTM[1547]="*“ime, āvuso, sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vihāraṃ paṭisaṅkharonti.**“These monks from the group of seventeen are repairing a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1548]="*Handa ne vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti.**Let’s throw them out.”*";
P_HTM[1549]="*Ekacce evamāhaṃsu—**But some of them said,*";
P_HTM[1550]="*“āgamethāvuso, yāva paṭisaṅkharonti; paṭisaṅkhate vuṭṭhāpessāmā”ti.**“Let’s wait until they’ve finished repairing it.”*";
P_HTM[1551]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six said to those from the group of seventeen,*";
P_HTM[1552]="*“uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti.**“Leave, this dwelling is ours.”*";
P_HTM[1553]="*“Nanu, āvuso, paṭikacceva ācikkhitabbaṃ, mayañcaññaṃ paṭisaṅkhareyyāmā”ti.**“Shouldn’t you have told us beforehand? We would’ve repaired another one.”*";
P_HTM[1554]="*“Nanu, āvuso, saṅghiko vihāro”ti?**“Doesn’t this dwelling belong to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[1555]="*“Āmāvuso, saṅghiko vihāro”ti.**“Yes, it does.”*";
P_HTM[1556]="*“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti.**“Well then, leave! This dwelling is ours.”*";
P_HTM[1557]="*“Mahallako, āvuso, vihāro.**“The dwelling is large.*";
P_HTM[1558]="*Tumhepi vasatha, mayampi vasissāmā”ti.**You can stay here and so can we.”*";
P_HTM[1559]="*“Uṭṭhethāvuso, amhākaṃ vihāro pāpuṇātī”ti kupitā anattamanā gīvāyaṃ gahetvā nikkaḍḍhanti.**But they said, “Leave, this dwelling is ours,” and they grabbed them by the necks and threw them out in anger.*";
P_HTM[1560]="*Te nikkaḍḍhīyamānā rodanti.**The monks from the group of seventeen cried.*";
P_HTM[1561]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?**When other monks asked them why,*";
P_HTM[1562]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhe saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhantī”ti.**they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[1563]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1564]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhissantī”ti.**“How could the monks from the group of six angrily throw other monks out of a dwelling belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[1565]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1566]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1567]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1568]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1569]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhū saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍhissatha?**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1570]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1571]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1572]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ kupito anattamano saṅghikā vihārā nikkaḍḍheyya vā nikkaḍḍhāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk, in anger, throws a monk out of a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, or has him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1573]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1574]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1575]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1576]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1577]="*Bhikkhunti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[1578]="*aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ.**another monk.*";
P_HTM[1579]="*Kupito anattamanoti**In anger:*";
P_HTM[1580]="*anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto.**discontent, having hatred, hostile.*";
P_HTM[1581]="*Saṅghiko nāma vihāro**A dwelling belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1582]="*saṅghassa dinno hoti pariccatto.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1583]="*Nikkaḍḍheyyāti**Throws out:*";
P_HTM[1584]="*gabbhe gahetvā pamukhaṃ nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he takes hold of him in a room and throws him out to entryway, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1585]="*Pamukhe gahetvā bahi nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he takes hold of him in the entryway and throws him outside, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1586]="*Ekena payogena bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Even if he makes him go through many doors with a single effort, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1587]="*Nikkaḍḍhāpeyyāti**Has thrown out:*";
P_HTM[1588]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1589]="*Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he only asks once, then even if the other makes him go through many doors, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1590]="*Saṅghike saṅghikasaññī kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, and he perceives it as such, and in anger he throws him out, or has him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1591]="*Saṅghike vematiko kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he is unsure of it, and in anger he throws him out, or has him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1592]="*Saṅghike puggalikasaññī kupito anattamano nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and in anger he throws him out, or has him thrown out, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1593]="*Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he throws out one of his requisites, or he has it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1594]="*Vihārassa upacārā vā upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍapā vā rukkhamūlā vā ajjhokāsā vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he throws him out, or has him thrown out, from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1595]="*Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he throws out one of his requisites from any of these places, or he has it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1596]="*Anupasampannaṃ vihārā vā vihārassa upacārā vā upaṭṭhānasālāya vā maṇḍapā vā rukkhamūlā vā ajjhokāsā vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he throws out one who is not fully ordained, or has them thrown out, from a dwelling, from the vicinity of a dwelling, from an assembly hall, from under a roof-cover, from the foot of a tree, or from a space out in the open, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1597]="*Tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he throws out one of their requisites from any of these places, or has it thrown out, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1598]="*Puggalike saṅghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Sangha, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1599]="*Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1600]="*Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as such, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1601]="*Attano puggalike anāpatti.**If it belongs to himself, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1602]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1603]="*alajjiṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out one who is shameless, or has him thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1604]="*tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out the requisites belonging to that person, or has them thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1605]="*ummattakaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out one who is insane, or has him thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1606]="*tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out the requisites belonging to that person, or has them thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1607]="*bhaṇḍanakārakaṃ kalahakārakaṃ vivādakārakaṃ bhassakārakaṃ saṅghe adhikaraṇakārakaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out one who is quarrelsome and argumentative, who creates legal issues in the Sangha, or has them thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1608]="*tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out the requisites belonging to that person, or has them thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1609]="*antevāsikaṃ vā saddhivihārikaṃ vā na sammā vattantaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out a pupil or student who is not conducting himself properly, or has him thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1610]="*tassa parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if he throws out the requisites belonging to such a person, or has them thrown out;*";
P_HTM[1611]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1612]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1613]="*Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on throwing out, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1614]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1615]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1616]="*18. Vehāsakuṭisikkhāpada**18. The training rule on upper stories*";
P_HTM[1617]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1618]="*Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū saṅghike vihāre uparivehāsakuṭiyā eko heṭṭhā viharati, eko upari.**At that time two monks were staying in a dwelling with an upper story belonging to the Sangha, one staying below and one above.*";
P_HTM[1619]="*Uparimo bhikkhu āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ sahasā abhinisīdi.**The monk above sat down forcefully on a bed with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[1620]="*Mañcapādo nippatitvā heṭṭhimassa bhikkhuno matthake avatthāsi.**A leg fell off and hit the monk below on the head.*";
P_HTM[1621]="*So bhikkhu vissaramakāsi.**He cried out.*";
P_HTM[1622]="*Bhikkhū upadhāvitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**Monks came rushing to*";
P_HTM[1623]="*“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, vissaramakāsī”ti?**and asked him why,*";
P_HTM[1624]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**and he told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[1625]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1626]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu saṅghike vihāre uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ sahasā abhinisīdissatī”ti.**“How could a monk sit down forcefully on a bed with detachable legs on an upper story in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha?”*";
P_HTM[1627]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking that monk in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1628]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, saṅghike vihāre uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ sahasā abhinisīdasī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1629]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1630]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[1631]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṅghike vihāre uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ sahasā abhinisīdissasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1632]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1633]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1634]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu saṅghike vihāre uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā abhinisīdeyya vā abhinipajjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk sits down or lies down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on an upper story in a dwelling belonging to the Sangha, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1635]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1636]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1637]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1638]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1639]="*Saṅghiko nāma vihāro**A dwelling belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1640]="*saṅghassa dinno hoti pariccatto.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[1641]="*Vehāsakuṭi nāma**An upper story:*";
P_HTM[1642]="*majjhimassa purisassa asīsaghaṭṭā.**a man of average height does not hit his head.*";
P_HTM[1643]="*Āhaccapādako nāma mañco**A bed with detachable legs:*";
P_HTM[1644]="*aṅge vijjhitvā ṭhito hoti.**it stands after inserting the limbs.*";
P_HTM[1645]="*Āhaccapādakaṃ nāma pīṭhaṃ**A bench with detachable legs:*";
P_HTM[1646]="*aṅge vijjhitvā ṭhitaṃ hoti.**it stands after inserting the limbs.*";
P_HTM[1647]="*Abhinisīdeyyāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[1648]="*tasmiṃ abhinisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he sits down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1649]="*Abhinipajjeyyāti**Lies down:*";
P_HTM[1650]="*tasmiṃ abhinipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he lies down on it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1651]="*Saṅghike saṅghikasaññī uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, and he perceives it as such, and he sits down or lies down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on an upper story, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1652]="*Saṅghike vematiko …pe…**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he is unsure of it …*";
P_HTM[1653]="*saṅghike puggalikasaññī uparivehāsakuṭiyā āhaccapādakaṃ mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it belongs to the Sangha, but he perceives it as belonging to an individual, and he sits down or lies down on a bed or a bench with detachable legs on an upper story, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1654]="*Puggalike saṅghikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he perceives it as belonging to the Sangha, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1655]="*Puggalike vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1656]="*Puggalike puggalikasaññī aññassa puggalike, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it belongs to an individual, and he perceives it as such, but that individual is not himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1657]="*Attano puggalike, anāpatti.**If it belongs to himself, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1658]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1659]="*avehāsakuṭiyā**if there is no upper story;*";
P_HTM[1660]="*sīsaghaṭṭāya**if the upper story is so low that one hits the head;*";
P_HTM[1661]="*heṭṭhā aparibhogaṃ hoti,**if the lower story is not in use;*";
P_HTM[1662]="*padarasañcitaṃ hoti,**if the upper story has floorboards;*";
P_HTM[1663]="*paṭāṇi dinnā hoti,**if the legs are fastened by bolts;*";
P_HTM[1664]="*tasmiṃ ṭhito gaṇhati vā laggeti vā,**if he stands on it to get hold of something or to put something up;*";
P_HTM[1665]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1666]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1667]="*Vehāsakuṭisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on upper stories, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1668]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1669]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1670]="*19. Mahallakavihārasikkhāpada**19. The training rule on large dwellings*";
P_HTM[1671]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1672]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato channassa upaṭṭhāko mahāmatto āyasmato channassa vihāraṃ kārāpeti.**At that time a government official who was Venerable Channa’s supporter was making him a dwelling.*";
P_HTM[1673]="*Atha kho āyasmā channo katapariyositaṃ vihāraṃ punappunaṃ chādāpeti, punappunaṃ lepāpeti.**When the dwelling was finished, Channa had it roofed and plastered over and over.*";
P_HTM[1674]="*Atibhārito vihāro paripati.**Being overloaded, the dwelling collapsed.*";
P_HTM[1675]="*Atha kho āyasmā channo tiṇañca kaṭṭhañca saṅkaḍḍhanto aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa yavakhettaṃ dūsesi.**Then, while collecting grass and sticks, Channa spoiled the barley field belonging to a certain brahmin.*";
P_HTM[1676]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That brahmin complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[1677]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā amhākaṃ yavakhettaṃ dūsessantī”ti.**“How can the venerables spoil my barley field?”*";
P_HTM[1678]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa brāhmaṇassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that brahmin,*";
P_HTM[1679]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized Channa,*";
P_HTM[1680]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo katapariyositaṃ vihāraṃ punappunaṃ chādāpessati, punappunaṃ lepāpessati, atibhārito vihāro paripatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Channa have a finished dwelling roofed and plastered over and over, so that it collapsed from overloading?”*";
P_HTM[1681]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ channaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking him in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned Channa:*";
P_HTM[1682]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, katapariyositaṃ vihāraṃ punappunaṃ chādāpesi, punappunaṃ lepāpesi, atibhārito vihāro paripatī”ti?**“Is it true, Channa, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1683]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1684]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[1685]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, katapariyositaṃ vihāraṃ punappunaṃ chādāpessasi, punappunaṃ lepāpessasi, atibhārito vihāro paripati.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1686]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1687]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1688]="*“Mahallakaṃ pana bhikkhunā vihāraṃ kārayamānena yāva dvārakosā aggaḷaṭṭhapanāya ālokasandhiparikammāya dvatticchadanassa pariyāyaṃ appaharite ṭhitena adhiṭṭhātabbaṃ. Tato ce uttari appaharitepi ṭhito adhiṭṭhaheyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘When a monk is building a large dwelling, then standing where there are no cultivated plants, he may apply two or three courses of roofing material, taking it as far as the doorcase and using it for fixing the door and for treating the window openings. If he applies more than that, even if he stands where there are no cultivated plants, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1689]="*Mahallako nāma vihāro**A large dwelling:*";
P_HTM[1690]="*sassāmiko vuccati.**one with an owner is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[1691]="*Vihāro nāma**A dwelling:*";
P_HTM[1692]="*ullitto vā hoti avalitto vā ullittāvalitto vā.**plastered inside or plastered outside or plastered both inside and outside.*";
P_HTM[1693]="*Kārayamānenāti**Is building:*";
P_HTM[1694]="*karonto vā kārāpento vā.**building it himself or having it built.*";
P_HTM[1695]="*Yāva dvārakosāti**As far as the doorcase:*";
P_HTM[1696]="*piṭṭhasaṅghāṭassa samantā hatthapāsā.**a distance of an arm’s reach next to the door frame.*";
P_HTM[1697]="*Aggaḷaṭṭhapanāyāti**For fixing the door:*";
P_HTM[1698]="*dvāraṭṭhapanāya.**for the fixing of the door.*";
P_HTM[1699]="*Ālokasandhiparikammāyāti**For treating the window openings:*";
P_HTM[1700]="*vātapānaparikammāya setavaṇṇaṃ kāḷavaṇṇaṃ gerukaparikammaṃ mālākammaṃ latākammaṃ makaradantakaṃ pañcapaṭikaṃ.**for treating the window openings there is white color, black color, and treating with red ocher; and there is making a garland pattern, a creeper pattern, a shark-teeth pattern, and the fivefold pattern.*";
P_HTM[1701]="*Dvatticchadanassa pariyāyaṃ appaharite ṭhitena adhiṭṭhātabbanti—**Standing where there are no cultivated plants, he may apply two or three courses of roofing material:*";
P_HTM[1702]="*haritaṃ nāma pubbaṇṇaṃ aparaṇṇaṃ.**cultivated plants: grain and vegetables;*";
P_HTM[1703]="*Sace harite ṭhito adhiṭṭhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he applies it while standing where there are cultivated plants, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1704]="*Maggena chādentassa dve magge adhiṭṭhahitvā tatiyaṃ maggaṃ āṇāpetvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**For someone covering in lines, after covering with two layers, he may ask for a third layer, and he should then leave.*";
P_HTM[1705]="*Pariyāyena chādentassa dve pariyāye adhiṭṭhahitvā tatiyaṃ pariyāyaṃ āṇāpetvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**For someone covering in circles, after covering with two layers, he may ask for a third layer, and he should then leave.*";
P_HTM[1706]="*Tato ce uttari appaharitepi ṭhito adhiṭṭhaheyyāti**If he applies more than that, even if he stands where there are no cultivated plants:*";
P_HTM[1707]="*iṭṭhakāya chādentassa iṭṭhakiṭṭhakāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he is covering with bricks, then for every brick, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1708]="*Silāya chādentassa silāya silāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is covering with slate, then for every piece of slate, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1709]="*Sudhāya chādentassa piṇḍe piṇḍe āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is covering with plaster, then for every lump, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1710]="*Tiṇena chādentassa karaḷe karaḷe āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is covering with grass, then for every handful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1711]="*Paṇṇena chādentassa paṇṇe paṇṇe āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is covering with leaves, then for every leaf, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1712]="*Atirekadvattipariyāye atirekasaññī adhiṭṭhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two or three courses, and he perceives it as more, and he applies it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1713]="*Atirekadvattipariyāye vematiko adhiṭṭhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two or three courses, but he is unsure of it, and he applies it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1714]="*Atirekadvattipariyāye ūnakasaññī adhiṭṭhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two or three courses, but he perceives it as less, and he applies it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1715]="*Ūnakadvattipariyāye atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than two or three courses, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1716]="*Ūnakadvattipariyāye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than two or three courses, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1717]="*Ūnakadvattipariyāye ūnakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is less than two or three courses, and he perceives it as less, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1718]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1719]="*dvattipariyāye,**if he applies two or three courses;*";
P_HTM[1720]="*ūnakadvattipariyāye,**if he applies less than two or three courses;*";
P_HTM[1721]="*leṇe,**if it is a shelter;*";
P_HTM[1722]="*guhāya,**if it is a cave;*";
P_HTM[1723]="*tiṇakuṭikāya,**if it is a grass hut;*";
P_HTM[1724]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[1725]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[1726]="*vāsāgāraṃ ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,**if it is anything apart from a dwelling;*";
P_HTM[1727]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1728]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1729]="*Mahallakavihārasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on large dwellings, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1730]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1731]="*Bhūtagāmavagga**The sub-chapter on plants*";
P_HTM[1732]="*20. Sappāṇakasikkhāpada**20. The training rule on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[1733]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine,*";
P_HTM[1734]="*Tena kho pana samayena āḷavakā bhikkhū navakammaṃ karontā jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ tiṇampi mattikampi siñcantipi siñcāpentipi.**the monks there were doing building work. They poured water that they knew contained living beings onto grass and clay, and they had others do the same.*";
P_HTM[1735]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[1736]="*“kathañhi nāma āḷavakā bhikkhū jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ tiṇampi mattikampi siñcissantipi siñcāpessantipī”ti.**“How can the monks at Āḷavī pour water that they know contains living beings onto grass and clay, and have others do the same?”*";
P_HTM[1737]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū āḷavake bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[1738]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ tiṇampi mattikampi siñcathapi siñcāpethapī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[1739]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1740]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1741]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ tiṇampi mattikampi siñcissathapi siñcāpessathapi.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[1742]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1743]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1744]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ tiṇaṃ vā mattikaṃ vā siñceyya vā siñcāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk pours water that he knows contains living beings onto grass or clay, or has it poured, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1745]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1746]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1747]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1748]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1749]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[1750]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti. Aññe vā tassa ārocenti.**he knows by himself or others have told him.*";
P_HTM[1751]="*Siñceyyāti**Pours:*";
P_HTM[1752]="*sayaṃ siñcati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he pours it himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1753]="*Siñcāpeyyāti**Has poured:*";
P_HTM[1754]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1755]="*Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi siñcati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he only asks once, then even if the other pours a lot, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1756]="*Sappāṇake sappāṇakasaññī tiṇaṃ vā mattikaṃ vā siñcati vā siñcāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it contains living beings, and he perceives it as such, and he pours it onto grass or clay, or he has it poured, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1757]="*Sappāṇake vematiko tiṇaṃ vā mattikaṃ vā siñcati vā siñcāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it contains living beings, but he is unsure of it, and he pours it onto grass or clay, or he has it poured, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1758]="*Sappāṇake appāṇakasaññī tiṇaṃ vā mattikaṃ vā siñcati vā siñcāpeti vā, anāpatti.**If it contains living beings, but he does not perceive it as such, and he pours it onto grass or clay, or he has it poured, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1759]="*Appāṇake sappāṇakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it does not contain living beings, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1760]="*Appāṇake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it does not contain living beings, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1761]="*Appāṇake appāṇakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it does not contain living beings, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1762]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1763]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[1764]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[1765]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[1766]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1767]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1768]="*Sappāṇakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on containing living beings, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1769]="*Bhūtagāmavaggo dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on plants is finished.*";
P_HTM[1770]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[1771]="*Bhūtaṃ aññāya ujjhāyaṃ,**Plant, with evasion, complaining,*";
P_HTM[1772]="*pakkamantena te duve;**the two with departing;*";
P_HTM[1773]="*Pubbe nikkaḍḍhanāhacca,**Before, throwing out, removable,*";
P_HTM[1774]="*dvāraṃ sappāṇakena cāti.**Door, and containing living beings.*";
P_HTM[1775]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1776]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[1777]="*21. Ovādasikkhāpada**21. The training rule on the instruction*";
P_HTM[1778]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[1779]="*Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.**At that time the senior monks who were instructing the nuns received robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines.*";
P_HTM[1780]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**When the monks from the group of six found out about this,*";
P_HTM[1781]="*“etarahi kho, āvuso, therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1782]="*Handāvuso, mayampi bhikkhuniyo ovadāmā”ti.**they thought, “Well then, let’s instruct the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[1783]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—“amhepi, bhaginiyo, upasaṅkamatha; mayampi ovadissāmā”ti.**They then went to the nuns and said, “Come to us, Sisters, and we too will instruct you.”*";
P_HTM[1784]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**Soon afterwards those nuns went to the monks from the group of six,*";
P_HTM[1785]="*upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[1786]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojesuṃ—“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti.**But after giving just a short teaching, those monks spent the day on pointless talk. They then dismissed the nuns, saying, “Go, Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[1787]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavā etadavoca—“kacci, bhikkhuniyo, ovādo iddho ahosī”ti?**The nuns went to the Buddha and bowed, and the Buddha said to them, “Nuns, I hope the instruction was effective?”*";
P_HTM[1788]="*“Kuto, bhante, ovādo iddho bhavissati.**“Venerable Sir, how could the instruction be effective?*";
P_HTM[1789]="*Ayyā chabbaggiyā parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojesun”ti.**After giving just a short teaching, the monks from the group of six spent the day on pointless talk, and then dismissed us.”*";
P_HTM[1790]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**The Buddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened those nuns with a teaching.*";
P_HTM[1791]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu.**The nuns bowed, circumambulated the Buddha with their right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[1792]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks from the group of six:*";
P_HTM[1793]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[1794]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1795]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1796]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you act like this?*";
P_HTM[1797]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1798]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking them …*";
P_HTM[1799]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1800]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannituṃ.**“Monks, you should appoint an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1801]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, sammannitabbo.**And this is how he should be appointed.*";
P_HTM[1802]="*Paṭhamaṃ bhikkhu yācitabbo.**First a monk should be asked*";
P_HTM[1803]="*Yācitvā byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**and then a competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[1804]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1805]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammanneyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, it should appoint monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1806]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[1807]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1808]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1809]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunovādakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1810]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1811]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter: …*";
P_HTM[1812]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**For the third time I speak on this matter:*";
P_HTM[1813]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[1814]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannati.**The Sangha appoints monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1815]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno bhikkhunovādakassa sammuti, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of appointing monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[1816]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[1817]="*Sammato saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu bhikkhunovādako.**The Sangha has appointed monk so-and-so as an instructor of the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1818]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[1819]="*Atha kho bhagavā chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after rebuking the monks from the group of six in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[1820]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1821]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu asammato bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who has not been appointed instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1822]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[1823]="*Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū sammatā bhikkhuniyo ovadantā tatheva lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.**After being appointed to do so, the senior monks who instructed the nuns still received robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines.*";
P_HTM[1824]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**When they found out about this, the monks from the group of six said,*";
P_HTM[1825]="*“etarahi kho, āvuso, therā bhikkhū sammatā bhikkhuniyo ovadantā tatheva lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.* **";
P_HTM[1826]="*Handāvuso, mayampi nissīmaṃ gantvā aññamaññaṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadāmā”ti.**“Well then, let’s go outside the monastic boundary, appoint each other as instructors of the nuns, and then instruct them.”*";
P_HTM[1827]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nissīmaṃ gantvā aññamaññaṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannitvā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—“mayampi, bhaginiyo, sammatā.**After doing just that, they again went to the nuns and said, “Sisters, we too have been appointed.*";
P_HTM[1828]="*Amhepi upasaṅkamatha. Mayampi ovadissāmā”ti.**Come to us, and we will instruct you.”*";
P_HTM[1829]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Once again the nuns went to the monks from the group of six and everything unfolded as before.*";
P_HTM[1830]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojesuṃ—* **";
P_HTM[1831]="*“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1832]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;* **";
P_HTM[1833]="*upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[1834]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavā etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[1835]="*“kacci, bhikkhuniyo, ovādo iddho ahosī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[1836]="*“Kuto, bhante, ovādo iddho bhavissati.* **";
P_HTM[1837]="*Ayyā chabbaggiyā parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojesun”ti.* **";
P_HTM[1838]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi …pe…* **";
P_HTM[1839]="*atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu.* **";
P_HTM[1840]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**The Buddha then had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks from the group of six:*";
P_HTM[1841]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[1842]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1843]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[1844]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīnaṃ parittaññeva dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā divasaṃ tiracchānakathāya vītināmetvā uyyojessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you act like this?*";
P_HTM[1845]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1846]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking them …*";
P_HTM[1847]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[1848]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannituṃ.**“Monks, you may appoint a monk who possesses eight qualities as an instructor of the nuns:*";
P_HTM[1849]="*Sīlavā hoti, pātimokkhasaṃvarasaṃvuto viharati ācāragocarasampanno aṇumattesu vajjesu bhayadassāvī, samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu;**He is virtuous and restrained by the Monastic Code. His conduct is good, he associates with the right people, and he sees danger in minor faults. He undertakes and trains in the training rules.*";
P_HTM[1850]="*bahussuto hoti sutadharo sutasannicayo, ye te dhammā ādikalyāṇā majjhekalyāṇā pariyosānakalyāṇā sātthaṃ sabyañjanaṃ kevalaparipuṇṇaṃ parisuddhaṃ brahmacariyaṃ abhivadanti tathārūpāssa dhammā bahussutā honti dhātā vacasā paricitā manasā anupekkhitā diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā;**He has learned much, and he retains and accumulates what he has learned. Those teachings that are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, that have a true goal and are well articulated, and that set out the perfectly complete and pure spiritual life—he has learned many such teachings, retained them in mind, recited them verbally, mentally investigated them, and penetrated them well by view.*";
P_HTM[1851]="*ubhayāni kho panassa pātimokkhāni vitthārena svāgatāni honti suvibhattāni suppavattīni suvinicchitāni suttaso anubyañjanaso;**He has properly learned both Monastic Codes in detail. He has analyzed them well, thoroughly mastered them, and investigated them well, both in terms of the rules and their detailed exposition.*";
P_HTM[1852]="*kalyāṇavāco hoti kalyāṇavākkaraṇo;**He is well-spoken and has a good voice.*";
P_HTM[1853]="*yebhuyyena bhikkhunīnaṃ piyo hoti manāpo;**He is generally liked by and pleasing to the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1854]="*paṭibalo hoti bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ;**He is capable of instructing the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1855]="*na kho panetaṃ bhagavantaṃ uddissa pabbajitāya kāsāyavatthavasanāya garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannapubbo hoti;**He has never committed a heavy offense against a Buddhist nun.*";
P_HTM[1856]="*vīsativasso vā hoti atirekavīsativasso vā—**He has been fully ordained for at least twenty years.*";
P_HTM[1857]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imehi aṭṭhahaṅgehi samannāgataṃ bhikkhuṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ sammannitun”ti.**Monks, you may appoint a monk who possesses these eight qualities as an instructor of the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[1858]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[1859]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[1860]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[1861]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[1862]="*Asammato nāma**Who has not been appointed:*";
P_HTM[1863]="*ñatticatutthena kammena asammato.**who has not been appointed through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[1864]="*Bhikkhuniyo nāma**Nuns:*";
P_HTM[1865]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**they have been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[1866]="*Ovadeyyāti**Instructs:*";
P_HTM[1867]="*aṭṭhahi garudhammehi ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he instructs in the eight important principles, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1868]="*Aññena dhammena ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he instructs in any other teaching, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1869]="*Ekatoupasampannaṃ ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1870]="*Tena sammatena bhikkhunā pariveṇaṃ sammajjitvā pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpetvā āsanaṃ paññapetvā dutiyaṃ gahetvā nisīditabbaṃ.**The monk who has been appointed should sweep the precincts, set out water for drinking and water for washing, prepare a seat, get hold of a companion, and then sit down.*";
P_HTM[1871]="*Bhikkhunīhi tattha gantvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīditabbaṃ.**The nuns should go there, bow down to the monk, and sit down.*";
P_HTM[1872]="*Tena bhikkhunā pucchitabbā—**The monk should then ask them,*";
P_HTM[1873]="*“samaggāttha, bhaginiyo”ti?**“Sisters, are you all present?”*";
P_HTM[1874]="*Sace “samaggāmhāyyā”ti bhaṇanti, “vattanti, bhaginiyo, aṭṭha garudhammā”ti?**If they say, “We’re all present, Venerable,” he should say, “Are you keeping the eight important principles?”*";
P_HTM[1875]="*Sace “vattantāyyā”ti bhaṇanti, “eso, bhaginiyo, ovādo”ti niyyādetabbo.**If they say, “We are,” he should say, “This is the instruction.”*";
P_HTM[1876]="*Sace “na vattantāyyā”ti bhaṇanti, osāretabbā.**If they say, “We’re not,” he should recite the important principles:*";
P_HTM[1877]="*“Vassasatūpasampannāya bhikkhuniyā tadahupasampannassa bhikkhuno abhivādanaṃ paccuṭṭhānaṃ añjalikammaṃ sāmīcikammaṃ kātabbaṃ;**“A nun who has been fully ordained for a hundred years should bow down to a monk who was given the full ordination on that very day, and she should stand up for him, raise her joined palms to him, and do acts of respect toward him.*";
P_HTM[1878]="*ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1879]="*Na bhikkhuniyā abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasitabbaṃ;**A nun should not spend the rainy-season residence in a monastery without monks.*";
P_HTM[1880]="*ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1881]="*Anvaddhamāsaṃ bhikkhuniyā bhikkhusaṅghato dve dhammā paccāsīsitabbā**Every half-month a nun should seek two things from the Sangha of monks:*";
P_HTM[1882]="*uposathapucchakañca ovādūpasaṅkamanañca,**asking it about the observance day and going to it for the instruction.*";
P_HTM[1883]="*ayampi dhammo …pe…**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1884]="*vassaṃ vuṭṭhāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe tīhi ṭhānehi pavāretabbaṃ**A nun who has completed the rainy-season residence should invite correction from both Sanghas in regard to three things:*";
P_HTM[1885]="*diṭṭhena vā sutena vā parisaṅkāya vā;**what has been seen, what has been heard, and what has been suspected.*";
P_HTM[1886]="*ayampi dhammo …pe…**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1887]="*garudhammaṃ ajjhāpannāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe pakkhamānattaṃ caritabbaṃ;**A nun who has committed a heavy offense must undertake a trial period for a half-month toward both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[1888]="*ayampi dhammo …pe…**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1889]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya ubhatosaṅghe upasampadā pariyesitabbā;**A trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years may seek for full ordination in both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[1890]="*ayampi dhammo …pe…**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1891]="*na bhikkhuniyā kenaci pariyāyena bhikkhu akkositabbo paribhāsitabbo;**A nun may not in any way abuse or revile a monk.*";
P_HTM[1892]="*ayampi dhammo …pe…**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.*";
P_HTM[1893]="*ajjatagge ovaṭo bhikkhunīnaṃ bhikkhūsu vacanapatho, anovaṭo bhikkhūnaṃ bhikkhunīsu vacanapatho;**From today onwards, nuns may not correct monks, but monks may correct nuns.*";
P_HTM[1894]="*ayampi dhammo sakkatvā garukatvā mānetvā pūjetvā yāvajīvaṃ anatikkamanīyo”ti.**This rule too is to be honored and respected all one’s life, and is not to be breached.”*";
P_HTM[1895]="*Sace “samaggāmhāyyā”ti bhaṇantaṃ aññaṃ dhammaṃ bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they say, “We’re all present, Venerable,” and he instructs them with another teaching, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1896]="*Sace “vaggāmhāyyā”ti bhaṇantaṃ aṭṭha garudhamme bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they say, “We’re not all present, Venerable,” and he instructs them in the eight important principles, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1897]="*Ovādaṃ aniyyādetvā aññaṃ dhammaṃ bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he does not give the instruction, but he gives them another teaching, then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1898]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ vaggasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure and he perceives it as such, and the Sangha of nuns is incomplete and he perceives it as such, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1899]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ vematiko ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure and he perceives it as such, and the Sangha of nuns is incomplete but he is unsure of it, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1900]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī vaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ samaggasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure and he perceives it as such, and the Sangha of nuns is incomplete but he perceives it as complete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
