P_HTM[1931]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī samaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ vaggasaññī ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure and he perceives it as such, and the Sangha of nuns is complete but he perceives it as incomplete, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1932]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī samaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ vematiko ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure and he perceives it as such, and the Sangha of nuns is complete but he is unsure of it, then if he instructs those nuns, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1933]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī samaggaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ samaggasaññī ovadati, anāpatti.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure and he perceives it as such, and the Sangha of nuns is complete and he perceives it as such, then if he instructs those nuns, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1934]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1935]="*uddesaṃ dento,**if he recites;*";
P_HTM[1936]="*paripucchaṃ dento,**if he tests them;*";
P_HTM[1937]="*“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno, osāreti,**if he recites when asked to do so;*";
P_HTM[1938]="*pañhaṃ pucchati,**if he asks a question;*";
P_HTM[1939]="*pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,**if he replies when asked a question;*";
P_HTM[1940]="*aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,**if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;*";
P_HTM[1941]="*sikkhamānāya,**if it is to a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[1942]="*sāmaṇeriyā,**if it is to a novice nun;*";
P_HTM[1943]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[1944]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[1945]="*Ovādasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on the instruction, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[1946]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[1947]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[1948]="*22. Atthaṅgatasikkhāpada**22. The training rule on set*";
P_HTM[1949]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[1950]="*Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadanti pariyāyena. Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato cūḷapanthakassa pariyāyo hoti bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ.**the senior monks were taking turns instructing the nuns. Then, on one occasion, it was the turn of Venerable Cūḷapanthaka.*";
P_HTM[1951]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—“na dāni ajja ovādo iddho bhavissati, taññeva dāni udānaṃ ayyo cūḷapanthako punappunaṃ bhaṇissatī”ti.**The nuns said, “Today the instruction won’t be effective. Venerable Cūḷapanthaka will just be repeating the same thing over and over.”*";
P_HTM[1952]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo yenāyasmā cūḷapanthako tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ cūḷapanthakaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu.**Soon afterwards those nuns went to Cūḷapanthaka, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[1953]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho tā bhikkhuniyo āyasmā cūḷapanthako etadavoca—“samaggāttha, bhaginiyo”ti?**Cūḷapanthaka then said to them, “Are you all here, Sisters?”*";
P_HTM[1954]="*“Samaggāmhāyyā”ti.**“We’re all here, Venerable.”*";
P_HTM[1955]="*“Vattanti, bhaginiyo, aṭṭha garudhammā”ti?**“Are you keeping the eight important principles?”*";
P_HTM[1956]="*“Vattantāyyā”ti.**“We are.”*";
P_HTM[1957]="*“Eso, bhaginiyo, ovādo”ti niyyādetvā imaṃ udānaṃ punappunaṃ abhāsi—**After saying, “This is the instruction,” he uttered the same heartfelt exclamation again and again:*";
P_HTM[1958]="*“Adhicetaso appamajjato,**“For the heedful one possessed of the higher mind,*";
P_HTM[1959]="*Munino monapathesu sikkhato;**For the sage training on the path to sagacity—*";
P_HTM[1960]="*Sokā na bhavanti tādino,**There are no sorrows for such a one,*";
P_HTM[1961]="*Upasantassa sadā satīmato”ti.**The peaceful one, who is always mindful.”*";
P_HTM[1962]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—“nanu avocumhā—na dāni ajja ovādo iddho bhavissati, taññeva dāni udānaṃ ayyo cūḷapanthako punappunaṃ bhaṇissatī”ti.**And the nuns said, “Didn’t we say that the instruction wouldn’t be effective, that Venerable Cūḷapanthaka would just be repeating the same thing over and over?”*";
P_HTM[1963]="*Assosi kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ.**Cūḷapanthaka overheard that conversation between the nuns.*";
P_HTM[1964]="*Atha kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako vehāsaṃ abbhuggantvā ākāse antalikkhe caṅkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi seyyampi kappeti dhūmāyatipi pajjalatipi antaradhāyatipi, tañceva udānaṃ bhaṇati aññañca bahuṃ buddhavacanaṃ.**He then rose up into the air, walked back and forth in space, and he stood, sat down, and lay down there. He emitted smoke and fire, and he disappeared, all the while uttering the same heartfelt exclamation and many other sayings by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[1965]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns said,*";
P_HTM[1966]="*“acchariyaṃ vata bho, abbhutaṃ vata bho.**“It’s astonishing and amazing!*";
P_HTM[1967]="*Na vata no ito pubbe ovādo evaṃ iddho bhūtapubbo yathā ayyassa cūḷapanthakassā”ti.**No previous instruction has been as effective as this one from Venerable Cūḷapanthaka!”*";
P_HTM[1968]="*Atha kho āyasmā cūḷapanthako tā bhikkhuniyo yāva samandhakārā ovaditvā uyyojesi—“gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti.**And Cūḷapanthaka kept on instructing those nuns until the dark of night and then dismissed them, saying, “Go, Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[1969]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo nagaradvāre thakite bahinagare vasitvā kālasseva nagaraṃ pavisanti.**But because the gates to town were closed, those nuns spent the night outside and only entered early in the morning.*";
P_HTM[1970]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—“abrahmacāriniyo imā bhikkhuniyo;**People complained and criticized them, “These nuns aren’t celibate.*";
P_HTM[1971]="*ārāme bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ vasitvā idāni nagaraṃ pavisantī”ti.**They spend the night in the monastery with the monks and only now do they enter town.”*";
P_HTM[1972]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[1973]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized Cūḷapanthaka,*";
P_HTM[1974]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā cūḷapanthako atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Cūḷapanthaka instruct the nuns after the sun has set?”…*";
P_HTM[1975]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadasī”ti?**“Is it true, Cūḷapanthaka, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[1976]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[1977]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[1978]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadissasi.**“Cūḷapanthaka, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[1979]="*Netaṃ, cūḷapanthaka, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[1980]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[1981]="*“Sammatopi ce bhikkhu atthaṅgate sūriye bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘Even if he has been appointed, if a monk instructs the nuns after sunset, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[1982]="*Sammato nāma**Has been appointed:*";
P_HTM[1983]="*ñatticatutthena kammena sammato.**Has been appointed through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements.*";
P_HTM[1984]="*Atthaṅgate sūriyeti**After sunset:*";
P_HTM[1985]="*oggate sūriye.**after the sun has gone down.*";
P_HTM[1986]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[1987]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**they have been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[1988]="*Ovadeyyāti**Instructs:*";
P_HTM[1989]="*aṭṭhahi vā garudhammehi aññena vā dhammena ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he instructs in the eight important principles or he gives any other teaching, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1990]="*Atthaṅgate atthaṅgatasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the sun has set, and he perceives that it has, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1991]="*Atthaṅgate vematiko ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the sun has set, but he is unsure of it, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1992]="*Atthaṅgate anatthaṅgatasaññī ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the sun has set, but he perceives that it has not, and he instructs the nuns, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[1993]="*Ekatoupasampannāya ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1994]="*Anatthaṅgate atthaṅgatasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the sun has not set, but he perceives that it has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1995]="*Anatthaṅgate vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the sun has not set, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[1996]="*Anatthaṅgate anatthaṅgatasaññī, anāpatti.**If the sun has not set, and he perceives that it has not, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[1997]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[1998]="*uddesaṃ dento,**if he recites;*";
P_HTM[1999]="*paripucchaṃ dento,**if he tests them;*";
P_HTM[2000]="*“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno, osāreti,**if he recites when asked to do so;*";
P_HTM[2001]="*pañhaṃ pucchati,**if he asks a question;*";
P_HTM[2002]="*pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,**if he replies when asked a question;*";
P_HTM[2003]="*aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,**if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;*";
P_HTM[2004]="*sikkhamānāya,**if it is to a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[2005]="*sāmaṇeriyā,**if it is to a novice nun;*";
P_HTM[2006]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2007]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2008]="*Atthaṅgatasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on set, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2009]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2010]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2011]="*23. Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpada**23. The training rule on the nuns’ dwelling place*";
P_HTM[2012]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in the Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu,*";
P_HTM[2013]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovadanti.**the monks from the group of six went to the nuns’ dwelling place and instructed the nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[2014]="*Bhikkhuniyo chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards the nuns said to the nuns from the group of six,*";
P_HTM[2015]="*“ethāyye, ovādaṃ gamissāmā”ti.**“Come, Venerables, let’s go to the instruction.”*";
P_HTM[2016]="*“Yampi mayaṃ, ayye, gaccheyyāma ovādassa kāraṇā, ayyā chabbaggiyā idheva āgantvā amhe ovadantī”ti.**“There’s no need. The monks from the group of six came and instructed us right here.”*";
P_HTM[2017]="*Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns complained and criticized the monks from the group of six,*";
P_HTM[2018]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti.**“How could the monks from the group of six go and instruct the nuns at their dwelling place?”*";
P_HTM[2019]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The those nuns told the monks.*";
P_HTM[2020]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2021]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissantī”ti …pe…**“How could those monks do this?”…*";
P_HTM[2022]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[2023]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2024]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[2025]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[2026]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2027]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2028]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk goes to the nuns’ dwelling place, and then instructs them, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2029]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2030]="*Tena kho pana samayena mahāpajāpati gotamī gilānā hoti.**Soon afterwards Mahāpajāpati Gotamī became sick.*";
P_HTM[2031]="*Therā bhikkhū yena mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**The senior monks went to see her*";
P_HTM[2032]="*upasaṅkamitvā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavocuṃ—“**and said,*";
P_HTM[2033]="*kacci, gotami, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“We hope you’re bearing up, Gotamī, we hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[2034]="*“Na me, ayyā, khamanīyaṃ na yāpanīyaṃ”.**“I’m not bearing up, Venerables, and I’m not getting better.*";
P_HTM[2035]="*“Iṅghayyā, dhammaṃ desethā”ti.**Please give me a teaching.”*";
P_HTM[2036]="*“Na, bhagini, kappati bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo dhammaṃ desetun”ti kukkuccāyantā na desesuṃ.**“It’s not allowable for us to go and teach the nuns at their dwelling place.” And being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not teach her.*";
P_HTM[2037]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena mahāpajāpati gotamī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Soon afterwards, after robing up in the morning, the Buddha took his bowl and robe and went to Mahāpajāpati Gotamī, where he sat down on the prepared seat.*";
P_HTM[2038]="*Nisajja kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ etadavoca—**He said to her,*";
P_HTM[2039]="*“kacci, gotami, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up, Gotamī, I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[2040]="*“Pubbe me, bhante, therā bhikkhū āgantvā dhammaṃ desenti.**“Previously, Venerable Sir, the senior monks would come and teach me,*";
P_HTM[2041]="*Tena me phāsu hoti.**and because of that I would be comfortable.*";
P_HTM[2042]="*Idāni pana—‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti, kukkuccāyantā na desenti.**But now that this has been prohibited by the Buddha, they don’t teach because they’re afraid of wrongdoing.*";
P_HTM[2043]="*Tena me na phāsu hotī”ti.**Because of that I’m not comfortable.”*";
P_HTM[2044]="*Atha kho bhagavā mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**After instructing, inspiring, and gladdening her with a teaching, the Buddha got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[2045]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2046]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā gilānaṃ bhikkhuniṃ ovadituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to go and instruct a sick nun at her dwelling place.*";
P_HTM[2047]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2048]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhikkhuniyo ovadeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk goes to the nuns’ dwelling place and then instructs them, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2049]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānā hoti bhikkhunī—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**This is the appropriate occasion: a nun is sick.’”*";
P_HTM[2050]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2051]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2052]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2053]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2054]="*Bhikkhunupassayo nāma**The nuns’ dwelling place:*";
P_HTM[2055]="*yattha bhikkhuniyo ekarattampi vasanti.**wherever nuns stay, even for a single night.*";
P_HTM[2056]="*Upasaṅkamitvāti**Goes to:*";
P_HTM[2057]="*tattha gantvā.**goes there.*";
P_HTM[2058]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2059]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2060]="*Ovadeyyāti**Instructs:*";
P_HTM[2061]="*aṭṭhahi garudhammehi ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he instructs about the eight important principles, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2062]="*Aññatra samayāti**Except on an appropriate occasion:*";
P_HTM[2063]="*ṭhapetvā samayaṃ.**unless it is an appropriate occasion.*";
P_HTM[2064]="*Gilānā nāma bhikkhunī**A sick nun:*";
P_HTM[2065]="*na sakkoti ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā gantuṃ.**she is not able to go to the instruction or to a formal meeting of the community.*";
P_HTM[2066]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññī bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is fully ordained, and he perceives her as such, and he goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2067]="*Upasampannāya vematiko bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2068]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññī bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā aññatra samayā ovadati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is fully ordained, but he does not perceive her as such, and he goes to her dwelling place and then instructs her, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2069]="*Aññena dhammena ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he instructs her with another teaching, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2070]="*Ekatoupasampannāya ovadati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he instructs a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2071]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not fully ordained, but he perceives her as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2072]="*Anupasampannāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2073]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññī, anāpatti.**If she is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2074]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2075]="*samaye,**if it is an appropriate occasion;*";
P_HTM[2076]="*uddesaṃ dento,**if he recites;*";
P_HTM[2077]="*paripucchaṃ dento,**if he tests them;*";
P_HTM[2078]="*“osārehi ayyā”ti vuccamāno osāreti,**if he recites when asked to do so;*";
P_HTM[2079]="*pañhaṃ pucchati,**if he asks a question;*";
P_HTM[2080]="*pañhaṃ puṭṭho katheti,**if he replies when asked a question;*";
P_HTM[2081]="*aññassatthāya bhaṇantaṃ bhikkhuniyo suṇanti,**if he is speaking for the benefit of someone else and the nuns listen in;*";
P_HTM[2082]="*sikkhamānāya,**if it is to a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[2083]="*sāmaṇeriyā,**if it is to a novice nun;*";
P_HTM[2084]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2085]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2086]="*Bhikkhunupassayasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on the nuns’ dwelling place, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2087]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2088]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2089]="*24. Āmisasikkhāpada**24. The training rule on worldly gain*";
P_HTM[2090]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2091]="*Tena kho pana samayena therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantā lābhino honti cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārānaṃ.**At that time the senior monks who were instructing the nuns received robes, almsfood, dwellings, and medicines.*";
P_HTM[2092]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—**And the monks from the group of six said this about them,*";
P_HTM[2093]="*“na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī”ti.**“The senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns as a service, but for the sake of worldly gain.”*";
P_HTM[2094]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2095]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vakkhanti—**“How can the monks from the group of six say that*";
P_HTM[2096]="*‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’”ti …pe…**the senior monks aren’t instructing the nuns to render a service, but for the sake of worldly gain?” …*";
P_HTM[2097]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, evaṃ vadetha—**“Is it true, monks, that you say this?”*";
P_HTM[2098]="*‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[2099]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2100]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[2101]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, evaṃ vakkhatha—**“Foolish men, how can you say this?*";
P_HTM[2102]="*‘na bahukatā therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadituṃ; āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovadantī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[2103]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2104]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2105]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya—‘āmisahetu therā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo ovandantī’ti, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk says that the senior monks are instructing the nuns for the sake of worldly gain, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2106]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2107]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2108]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2109]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2110]="*Āmisahetūti**For the sake of worldly gain:*";
P_HTM[2111]="*cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu.**for the sake of robes, for the sake of almsfood, for the sake of a dwelling, for the sake of medicines, for the sake of honor, for the sake of respect, for the sake of deference, for the sake of veneration, for the sake of worship.*";
P_HTM[2112]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti**Says:*";
P_HTM[2113]="*upasampannaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti— “cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, concerning one who is fully ordained and who has been appointed by the Sangha as an instructor of nuns—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—he says, “He instructs for the sake of robes,” “… for the sake of almsfood,” “… for the sake of a dwelling,” “… for the sake of medicines,” “… for the sake of honor,” “… for the sake of respect,” “… for the sake of deference,” “… for the sake of veneration,” “… for the sake of worship,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2114]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2115]="*Dhammakamme vematiko evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2116]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2117]="*Upasampannaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—**When someone who is fully ordained is an instructor of nuns, but he has not been appointed by the Sangha as such, and a monk—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—says,*";
P_HTM[2118]="*“cīvarahetu …pe… pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“He instructs for the sake of robes,” “… for the sake of almsfood,” “… for the sake of a dwelling,” “… for the sake of medicines,” “… for the sake of honor,” “… for the sake of respect,” “… for the sake of deference,” “… for the sake of veneration,” “… for the sake of worship,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2119]="*Anupasampannaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ vā asammataṃ vā bhikkhunovādakaṃ avaṇṇaṃ kattukāmo ayasaṃ kattukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti—**When someone who is not fully ordained is an instructor of nuns, whether or not he has been appointed by the Sangha as such, and a monk—desiring to disparage him, desiring to give him a bad reputation, desiring to humiliate him—says,*";
P_HTM[2120]="*“cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadatī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“He instructs for the sake of robes,” “… for the sake of almsfood,” “… for the sake of a dwelling,” “… for the sake of medicines,” “… for the sake of honor,” “… for the sake of respect,” “… for the sake of deference,” “… for the sake of veneration,” “… for the sake of worship,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2121]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2122]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2123]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2124]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2125]="*pakatiyā cīvarahetu piṇḍapātahetu senāsanahetu gilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārahetu sakkārahetu garukārahetu mānanahetu vandanahetu pūjanahetu ovadantaṃ bhaṇati,**if he says it to one who regularly gives the instruction for the sake of robes, … for the sake of almsfood, … for the sake of a dwelling, … for the sake of medicines, … for the sake of honor, … for the sake of respect, … for the sake of deference, … for the sake of veneration, … for the sake of worship;*";
P_HTM[2126]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2127]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2128]="*Āmisasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on worldly gain, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2129]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2130]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2131]="*25. Cīvaradānasikkhāpada**25. The training rule on giving robe-cloth*";
P_HTM[2132]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[2133]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarissā visikhāya piṇḍāya carati. Aññatarāpi bhikkhunī tassā visikhāya piṇḍāya carati.**a certain monk was walking for almsfood along a street in Sāvatthī, as was a certain nun.*";
P_HTM[2134]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—“gaccha, bhagini, amukasmiṃ okāse bhikkhā diyyatī”ti.**That monk said to that nun, “Go to such-and-such a place, Sister, and you’ll get alms,”*";
P_HTM[2135]="*Sāpi kho evamāha—“gacchāyya, amukasmiṃ okāse bhikkhā diyyatī”ti.**and she said the same to him.*";
P_HTM[2136]="*Te abhiṇhadassanena sandiṭṭhā ahesuṃ.**And because they met frequently, they became friends.*";
P_HTM[2137]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa cīvaraṃ bhājīyati.**Just then robe-cloth belonging to the Sangha was being distributed.*";
P_HTM[2138]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī ovādaṃ gantvā yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi.**Then, after going to the instruction, that nun went to that monk and bowed.*";
P_HTM[2139]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho taṃ bhikkhuniṃ so bhikkhu etadavoca—“ ayaṃ me, bhagini, cīvarapaṭivīso; sādiyissasī”ti?**He then said to her, “Sister, will you accept my share of the robe-cloth?”*";
P_HTM[2140]="*“Āmāyya, dubbalacīvarāmhī”ti.**“Yes, Venerable, my robes are worn.”*";
P_HTM[2141]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu tassā bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ adāsi.**And he gave his robe-cloth to that nun.*";
P_HTM[2142]="*Sopi kho bhikkhu dubbalacīvaro hoti.**As a consequence, his robes, too, became worn.*";
P_HTM[2143]="*Bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—“karohi dāni te, āvuso, cīvaran”ti.**Other monks said to him, “Why don’t you make a robe for yourself?”*";
P_HTM[2144]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And he told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2145]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[2146]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dassatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk give robe-cloth to a nun?” …*";
P_HTM[2147]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ adāsī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[2148]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2149]="*“Ñātikā te, bhikkhu, aññātikā”ti?**“Is she a relative of yours?”*";
P_HTM[2150]="*“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[2151]="*“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā.**“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are unrelated don’t know what’s appropriate and inappropriate, what’s good and bad, in dealing with each other.*";
P_HTM[2152]="*Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dassasi.**And still you did this.*";
P_HTM[2153]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2154]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2155]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives robe-cloth to an unrelated nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2156]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2157]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā bhikkhunīnaṃ pārivattakaṃ cīvaraṃ na denti.**Once this had happened, the monks did not even give robe-cloth to the nuns in exchange, being afraid of wrongdoing.*";
P_HTM[2158]="*Bhikkhuniyo ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2159]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā amhākaṃ pārivattakaṃ cīvaraṃ na dassantī”ti.**“How can they not give us robe-cloth in exchange?”*";
P_HTM[2160]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those nuns*";
P_HTM[2161]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2162]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2163]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pañcannaṃ pārivattakaṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to give things in except in exchange  to five kinds of people:*";
P_HTM[2164]="*Bhikkhussa, bhikkhuniyā, sikkhamānāya, sāmaṇerassa, sāmaṇeriyā—**monks, nuns, trainee nuns, novice monks, and novice nuns.*";
P_HTM[2165]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, imesaṃ pañcannaṃ pārivattakaṃ dātuṃ.* **";
P_HTM[2166]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2167]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ dadeyya, aññatra pārivattakā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives robe-cloth to an unrelated nun, except in exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2168]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2169]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2170]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2171]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2172]="*Aññātikā nāma**Unrelated:*";
P_HTM[2173]="*mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā.**anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side.*";
P_HTM[2174]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2175]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2176]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**Robe-cloth:*";
P_HTM[2177]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ.**one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[2178]="*Aññatra pārivattakāti**Except in exchange:*";
P_HTM[2179]="*ṭhapetvā pārivattakaṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**unless there is an exchange.*";
P_HTM[2180]="*Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is unrelated and he perceives her as such, and he gives her robe-cloth, except in exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2181]="*Aññātikāya vematiko cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is unrelated, but he is unsure of it, and he gives her robe-cloth, except in exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2182]="*Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he gives her robe-cloth, except in exchange, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2183]="*Ekato upasampannāya cīvaraṃ deti, aññatra pārivattakā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gives robe-cloth to a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, except in exchange, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2184]="*Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2185]="*Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is related, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2186]="*Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti.**If she is related and he perceives her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2187]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2188]="*ñātikāya,**if she is related;*";
P_HTM[2189]="*pārivattakaṃ parittena vā vipulaṃ, vipulena vā parittaṃ,**if much is exchanged with little or little is exchanged with much;*";
P_HTM[2190]="*bhikkhunī vissāsaṃ gaṇhāti,**if the nun takes it on trust;*";
P_HTM[2191]="*tāvakālikaṃ gaṇhāti,**if she borrows it;*";
P_HTM[2192]="*cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ deti,**if he gives any requisite apart from robe-cloth;*";
P_HTM[2193]="*sikkhamānāya,**if it is a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[2194]="*sāmaṇeriyā,**if it is a novice nun;*";
P_HTM[2195]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2196]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2197]="*Cīvaradānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on giving robe-cloth, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2198]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2199]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2200]="*26. Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpada**26. The training rule on sewing robes*";
P_HTM[2201]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2202]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī paṭṭo hoti cīvarakammaṃ kātuṃ.**At that time Venerable Udāyī had become skilled in making robes.*";
P_HTM[2203]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—**On one occasion a certain nun went to Udāyī and said to him,*";
P_HTM[2204]="*“sādhu me, bhante, ayyo cīvaraṃ sibbatū”ti.**“Venerable, would you please sew me a robe?”*";
P_HTM[2205]="*Atha kho āyasmā udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbitvā surattaṃ suparikammakataṃ katvā majjhe paṭibhānacittaṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā saṃharitvā nikkhipi.**He then sewed a robe for that nun, well-dyed and beautifully executed, and he drew a picture in the middle of it. He then folded it and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[2206]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī yenāyasmā udāyī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards that nun went to Udāyī and said,*";
P_HTM[2207]="*“kahaṃ taṃ, bhante, cīvaran”ti?**“Sir, where’s the robe?”*";
P_HTM[2208]="*“Handa, bhagini, imaṃ cīvaraṃ yathāsaṃhaṭaṃ haritvā nikkhipitvā yadā bhikkhunisaṅgho ovādaṃ āgacchati tadā imaṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā bhikkhunisaṅghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito āgacchā”ti.**“Now, Sister, take this robe as it’s folded and put it aside. When the Sangha of nuns goes to the instruction, then put it on and follow right behind the other nuns.”*";
P_HTM[2209]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ yathāsaṃhaṭaṃ haritvā nikkhipitvā yadā bhikkhunisaṅgho ovādaṃ āgacchati tadā taṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā bhikkhunisaṅghassa piṭṭhito piṭṭhito āgacchati.**And that nun did just that.*";
P_HTM[2210]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[2211]="*“yāva chinnikā imā bhikkhuniyo dhuttikā ahirikāyo, yatra hi nāma cīvare paṭibhānacittaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti.**“How indecent these nuns are, what shameless scoundrels, seeing as they draw pictures on their robes.”*";
P_HTM[2212]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns asked her,*";
P_HTM[2213]="*“kassidaṃ kamman”ti?**“Who did this?”*";
P_HTM[2214]="*“Ayyassa udāyissā”ti.**“Venerable Udāyī.”*";
P_HTM[2215]="*“Yepi te chinnakā dhuttakā ahirikā tesampi evarūpaṃ na sobheyya, kiṃ pana ayyassa udāyissā”ti.**“This sort of work would not even make an indecent, shameless scoundrel look good, let alone Venerable Udāyī.”*";
P_HTM[2216]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The nuns told the monks,*";
P_HTM[2217]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[2218]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Udāyī sew a robe for a nun?” …*";
P_HTM[2219]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbasī”ti?**“Is it true, Udāyī, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[2220]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2221]="*“Ñātikā te, udāyi, aññātikā”ti?**“Is she a relative of yours?”*";
P_HTM[2222]="*“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[2223]="*“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā pāsādikaṃ vā apāsādikaṃ vā.**“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are unrelated don’t know what’s appropriate and inappropriate, what’s inspiring and uninspiring, in dealing with each other.*";
P_HTM[2224]="*Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbissasi.**So how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[2225]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2226]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2227]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ sibbeyya vā sibbāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk sews a robe for an unrelated nun, or has one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2228]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2229]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2230]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2231]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2232]="*Aññātikā nāma**Unrelated:*";
P_HTM[2233]="*mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā.**anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side.*";
P_HTM[2234]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2235]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2236]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**A robe:*";
P_HTM[2237]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ.**one of the six kinds of robes.*";
P_HTM[2238]="*Sibbeyyāti**Sews:*";
P_HTM[2239]="*sayaṃ sibbati ārāpathe ārāpathe āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he sews it himself, then for each stitch he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2240]="*Sibbāpeyyāti**Has sewn:*";
P_HTM[2241]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2242]="*Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi sibbati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he only asks once, then even if the other sews a lot, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2243]="*Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is unrelated and he perceives her as such, and he sews her a robe or has one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2244]="*Aññātikāya vematiko cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is unrelated, but he is unsure of it, and he sews her a robe or has one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2245]="*Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he sews her a robe or has one sewn, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2246]="*Ekatoupasampannāya cīvaraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sews a robe, or has one sewn, for a nun who is fully ordained only on one side, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2247]="*Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2248]="*Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is related, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2249]="*Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti.**If she is related and he perceives her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2250]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2251]="*ñātikāya,**if she is related;*";
P_HTM[2252]="*cīvaraṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ sibbati vā sibbāpeti vā,**if he sews any requisite apart from a robe, or has it sewn;*";
P_HTM[2253]="*sikkhamānāya,**if it is a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[2254]="*sāmaṇeriyā,**if it is a novice nun;*";
P_HTM[2255]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2256]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2257]="*Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on sewing robes, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2258]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2259]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2260]="*27. Saṃvidhānasikkhāpada**27. The training rule on appointments*";
P_HTM[2261]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2262]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six traveled by appointment with nuns.*";
P_HTM[2263]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2264]="*“yatheva mayaṃ sapajāpatikā āhiṇḍāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya āhiṇḍantī”ti.**“Just as we walk about with our wives, so these Sakyan monastics walk about by appointment with nuns.”*";
P_HTM[2265]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[2266]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2267]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six travel by appointment with the nuns?” …*";
P_HTM[2268]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[2269]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2270]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[2271]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissatha.**“Foolish men, how can do this?*";
P_HTM[2272]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2273]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha.**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2274]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk travels by appointment with a nun, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2275]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2276]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti.**Soon afterwards a number of monks and nuns were traveling from Sāketa to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2277]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The nuns said to the monks,*";
P_HTM[2278]="*“mayampi ayyehi saddhiṃ gamissāmā”ti.**“Let’s go together.”*";
P_HTM[2279]="*“Na, bhaginī, kappati bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.**“Sisters, it’s not allowable for us to travel by appointment with nuns.*";
P_HTM[2280]="*Tumhe vā paṭhamaṃ gacchatha mayaṃ vā gamissāmā”ti.**Either you go first, or we will.”*";
P_HTM[2281]="*“Ayyā, bhante, aggapurisā.**“You have the higher status, Venerables.*";
P_HTM[2282]="*Ayyāva paṭhamaṃ gacchantū”ti.**Please go first.”*";
P_HTM[2283]="*Atha kho tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pacchā gacchantīnaṃ antarāmagge corā acchindiṃsu ca dūsesuñca.**But because the nuns went behind, they were robbed and raped by bandits.*";
P_HTM[2284]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**When they arrived at Sāvatthī, they told the nuns there what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2285]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The nuns then told the monks,*";
P_HTM[2286]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2287]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2288]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, satthagamanīye magge sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to travel by appointment with a nun if it’s a risky and dangerous road that should be traveled with a group.*";
P_HTM[2289]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2290]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk travels by appointment with a nun, even just to the next village, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2291]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Satthagamanīyo hoti maggo sāsaṅkasammato sappaṭibhayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**This is the appropriate occasion: the road is considered risky and dangerous and should be traveled with a group.’”*";
P_HTM[2292]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2293]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2294]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2295]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2296]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2297]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2298]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[2299]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[2300]="*Saṃvidhāyāti—**By appointment:*";
P_HTM[2301]="*“gacchāma, bhagini, gacchāmāyya; gacchāmāyya, gacchāma, bhagini; ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā gacchāmā”ti saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he makes an appointment like this: he says, “Let’s go, Sister,” and she replies, “Yes, let’s go, Venerable;” or she says, “Let’s go, Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s go, Sister;” or he says, “Let’s go today,” “Let’s go tomorrow,” “Let’s go the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2302]="*Antamaso gāmantarampīti**Even just to the next village:*";
P_HTM[2303]="*kukkuṭasampāte gāme, gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2304]="*Agāmake araññe, addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2305]="*Aññatra samayāti**Except on an appropriate occasion:*";
P_HTM[2306]="*ṭhapetvā samayaṃ.**unless it is an appropriate occasion.*";
P_HTM[2307]="*Satthagamanīyo nāma**The road should be traveled with a group:*";
P_HTM[2308]="*maggo na sakkā hoti vinā satthena gantuṃ.**it is not possible to travel without a group.*";
P_HTM[2309]="*Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma**Risky:*";
P_HTM[2310]="*tasmiṃ magge corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati.**a place has been seen along that road where criminals are camped, eating, standing, sitting, or lying down.*";
P_HTM[2311]="*Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma**Dangerous:*";
P_HTM[2312]="*tasmiṃ magge corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā dissanti, sappaṭibhayaṃ gantvā appaṭibhayaṃ dassetvā uyyojetabbā— “gacchatha, bhaginiyo”ti.**criminals have been seen along that road, injuring, robbing, or beating people. If they go together thinking it is dangerous, but then see that it is not, the nuns are to be dismissed, “Go, Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[2313]="*Saṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there is an appointment, and he perceives that there is, and he travels with a nun, even just to the next village, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2314]="*Saṃvidahite vematiko ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there is an appointment, but he is unsure of it, and he travels with a nun, even just to the next village, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2315]="*Saṃvidahite, asaṃvidahitasaññī ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there is an appointment, but he does not perceive that there is, and he travels with a nun, even just to the next village, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2316]="*Bhikkhu saṃvidahati bhikkhunī na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the monk makes an appointment, but the nun does not express her agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2317]="*Asaṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there is no appointment, but he perceives that there is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2318]="*Asaṃvidahite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there is no appointment, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2319]="*Asaṃvidahite asaṃvidahitasaññī, anāpatti.**If there is no appointment, and he does not perceive that there is, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2320]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2321]="*samaye,**if it is an appropriate occasion;*";
P_HTM[2322]="*asaṃvidahitvā gacchati,**if he goes without an appointment;*";
P_HTM[2323]="*bhikkhunī saṃvidahati, bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,**if the nun has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;*";
P_HTM[2324]="*visaṅketena gacchanti,**if they go, but not according to the appointment;*";
P_HTM[2325]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[2326]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2327]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2328]="*Saṃvidhānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The  training rule on appointments, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2329]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2330]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2331]="*28. Nāvābhiruhanasikkhāpada**28. The training rule on boarding boats*";
P_HTM[2332]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2333]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six were boarding boats by appointment with nuns.*";
P_HTM[2334]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2335]="*“yatheva mayaṃ sapajāpatikā nāvāya kīḷāma, evamevime samaṇā sakyaputtiyā bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya nāvāya kīḷantī”ti.**“Just as we enjoy ourselves on boats with our wives, so these Sakyan monastics make appointments with the nuns and then enjoy themselves on boats.”*";
P_HTM[2336]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[2337]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2338]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six board boats by appointments with nuns?” …*";
P_HTM[2339]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[2340]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2341]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[2342]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[2343]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2344]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2345]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruheyya, uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk boards a boat by appointment with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2346]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2347]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca bhikkhuniyo ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti.**Soon afterwards a number of monks and nuns were traveling from Sāketa to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2348]="*Antarāmagge nadī taritabbā hoti.**On the way they needed to cross a river.*";
P_HTM[2349]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The nuns said to the monks,*";
P_HTM[2350]="*“mayampi ayyehi saddhiṃ uttarissāmā”ti.**“Let’s cross together.”*";
P_HTM[2351]="*“Na, bhaginī, kappati bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhituṃ;**“Sisters, it’s not allowable for us to board a boat by appointment with a nun.*";
P_HTM[2352]="*tumhe vā paṭhamaṃ uttaratha mayaṃ vā uttarissāmā”ti.**Either you cross first, or we will.”*";
P_HTM[2353]="*“Ayyā, bhante, aggapurisā.**“You have the higher status, Venerables.*";
P_HTM[2354]="*Ayyāva paṭhamaṃ uttarantū”ti.**Please go first.”*";
P_HTM[2355]="*Atha kho tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pacchā uttarantīnaṃ corā acchindiṃsu ca dūsesuñca.**But because the nuns crossed afterwards, they were robbed and raped by bandits.*";
P_HTM[2356]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**When they arrived at Sāvatthī they told the nuns there what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2357]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The nuns then told the monks,*";
P_HTM[2358]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2359]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2360]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tiriyaṃ taraṇāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to board a boat by appointment with a nun if it’s for the purpose of crossing.*";
P_HTM[2361]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2362]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruheyya uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk boards a boat by appointment with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, except for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2363]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2364]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2365]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2366]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2367]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2368]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2369]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[2370]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[2371]="*Saṃvidhāyāti**By appointment:*";
P_HTM[2372]="*“abhiruhāma, bhagini, abhiruhāmāyya; abhiruhāmāyya, abhiruhāma, bhagini; ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā abhiruhāmā”ti saṃvidahati āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he makes an appointment like this: he says, “Let’s board, Sister,” and she replies, “Yes, let’s board, Venerable;” or she says, “Lets’s board, Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s board, Sister;” or he says, “Let’s board today,” “Let’s board tomorrow,” “Let’s board the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2373]="*Bhikkhuniyā abhiruḷhe bhikkhu abhiruhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the monk boards when the nun has already boarded, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2374]="*Bhikkhumhi abhiruḷhe bhikkhunī abhiruhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the nun boards when the monks has already boarded, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2375]="*Ubho vā abhiruhanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they both board together, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2376]="*Uddhaṅgāmininti**To go upstream:*";
P_HTM[2377]="*ujjavanikāya.**for the purpose of going against the stream.*";
P_HTM[2378]="*Adhogāmininti**To go downstream:*";
P_HTM[2379]="*ojavanikāya.**for the purpose of going with the stream.*";
P_HTM[2380]="*Aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāyāti**Except for the purpose of crossing:*";
P_HTM[2381]="*ṭhapetvā tiriyaṃ taraṇaṃ.**unless it is to go across.*";
P_HTM[2382]="*Kukkuṭasampāte gāme, gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2383]="*Agāmake araññe, aḍḍhayojane aḍḍhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2384]="*Saṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there is an appointment, and he perceives that there is, and he boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, except for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2385]="*Saṃvidahite vematiko ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there is an appointment, but he is unsure of it, and he boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, except for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2386]="*Saṃvidahite asaṃvidahitasaññī ekaṃ nāvaṃ abhiruhati uddhaṅgāminiṃ vā adhogāminiṃ vā, aññatra tiriyaṃ taraṇāya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there is an appointment, but he does not perceive that there is, and he boards a boat with a nun, either to go upstream or downstream, except for the purpose of crossing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2387]="*Bhikkhu saṃvidahati, bhikkhunī na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the monk makes an appointment, but the nun does not express her agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2388]="*Asaṃvidahite saṃvidahitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there is no appointment, but he perceives that there is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2389]="*Asaṃvidahite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there is no appointment, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2390]="*Asaṃvidahite, asaṃvidahitasaññī, anāpatti.**If there is no appointment, and he does not perceive that there is, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2391]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2392]="*tiriyaṃ taraṇāya,**if it is for the purpose of crossing;*";
P_HTM[2393]="*asaṃvidahitvā abhiruhanti,**if they board without an appointment;*";
P_HTM[2394]="*bhikkhunī saṃvidahati, bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,**if the nun has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;*";
P_HTM[2395]="*visaṅketena abhiruhanti,**if they board, but not according to the appointment;*";
P_HTM[2396]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[2397]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2398]="*ādikammissāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2399]="*Nāvābhiruhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on boarding boats, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2400]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2401]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2402]="*29. Paripācitasikkhāpada**29. The training rule on had prepared*";
P_HTM[2403]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2404]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī aññatarassa kulassa kulūpikā hoti niccabhattikā.**At that time the nun Thullanandā was associating with a family from which she received a regular meal.*";
P_HTM[2405]="*Tena ca gahapatinā therā bhikkhū nimantitā honti.**Now on one occasion the head of that family had invited some senior monks.*";
P_HTM[2406]="*Atha kho thullanandā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ gahapatiṃ etadavoca—**On the same day, the nun Thullanandā robed up in the morning, took her bowl and robe, and went to that family. And she asked the head of the family,*";
P_HTM[2407]="*“kimidaṃ, gahapati, pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattan”ti?**“Why have you prepared so much food?”*";
P_HTM[2408]="*“Therā mayā, ayye, nimantitā”ti.**“Because, Venerable, I’ve invited the senior monks.”*";
P_HTM[2409]="*“Ke pana te, gahapati, therā”ti?**“But who are those senior monks?”*";
P_HTM[2410]="*“Ayyo sāriputto ayyo mahāmoggallāno ayyo mahākaccāno ayyo mahākoṭṭhiko ayyo mahākappino ayyo mahācundo ayyo anuruddho ayyo revato ayyo upāli ayyo ānando ayyo rāhulo”ti.**“Venerable Sāriputta, Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, Venerable Mahākaccāna, Venerable Mahākoṭṭhika, Venerable Mahākappina, Venerable Mahācunda, Venerable Anuruddha, Venerable Revata, Venerable Upāli, Venerable Ānanda, and Venerable Rāhula.”*";
P_HTM[2411]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, gahapati, mahānāge tiṭṭhamāne ceṭake nimantesī”ti?**“But why do you invite such inferior monks instead of the great ones?”*";
P_HTM[2412]="*“Ke pana te, ayye, mahānāgā”ti?**“Who are these great monks?”*";
P_HTM[2413]="*“Ayyo devadatto ayyo kokāliko ayyo kaṭamodakatissako ayyo khaṇḍadeviyā putto ayyo samuddadatto”ti.**“Venerable Devadatta, Venerable Kokālika, Venerable Kaṭamodakatissaka, Venerable Khaṇḍadeviyā-putta, and Venerable Samuddadatta.”*";
P_HTM[2414]="*Ayaṃ carahi thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā antarā kathā vippakatā, atha te therā bhikkhū pavisiṃsu.**While this conversation was taking place, the senior monks entered.*";
P_HTM[2415]="*“Saccaṃ mahānāgā kho tayā, gahapati, nimantitā”ti.**Thullanandā said, “Is it true that you’ve invited these great monks?”*";
P_HTM[2416]="*“Idāneva kho tvaṃ, ayye, ceṭake akāsi; idāni mahānāge”ti.**“Just before you called them inferior and now you call them great.”*";
P_HTM[2417]="*Gharato ca nikkaḍḍhi, niccabhattañca pacchindi.**And that lay person threw her out of the house and made an end of her regular meal.*";
P_HTM[2418]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized Devadatta,*";
P_HTM[2419]="*“kathañhi nāma devadatto jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Devadatta eat almsfood knowing that a nun had it prepared?” …*";
P_HTM[2420]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, devadatta, jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Devadatta, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[2421]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2422]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[2423]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[2424]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2425]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2426]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats almsfood knowing that a nun had it prepared, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2427]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2428]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu rājagahā pabbajito ñātikulaṃ agamāsi.**Soon afterwards a monk who had earlier left Rājagaha returned to see his family.*";
P_HTM[2429]="*Manussā—“cirassampi bhadanto āgato”ti sakkaccaṃ bhattaṃ akaṃsu.**Because it was long since he had last returned, people prepared food for him respectfully.*";
P_HTM[2430]="*Tassa kulassa kulūpikā bhikkhunī te manusse etadavoca—**And the nun who was associating with that family said to them,*";
P_HTM[2431]="*“dethayyassa, āvuso, bhattan”ti.**“Give food to that monk.”*";
P_HTM[2432]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—**The monk thought,*";
P_HTM[2433]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggahesi.**“The Buddha has prohibited us from eating almsfood knowing that a nun had it prepared,” and being afraid of wrongdoing, he did not accept it.*";
P_HTM[2434]="*Nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ, chinnabhatto ahosi.**And because he was unable to walk for alms, he missed his meal.*";
P_HTM[2435]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**After returning to the monastery, he told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[2436]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2437]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2438]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, pubbe gihisamārambhe jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat almsfood knowing that a nun had it prepared if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway.*";
P_HTM[2439]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2440]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ bhikkhuniparipācitaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjeyya, aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats almsfood knowing that a nun had it prepared, except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2441]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2442]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2443]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2444]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2445]="*Jānāti nāma**Knowing:*";
P_HTM[2446]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti aññe vā tassa ārocenti sā vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the nun has told him.*";
P_HTM[2447]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2448]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2449]="*Paripāceti nāma**Has it prepared:*";
P_HTM[2450]="*pubbe adātukāmānaṃ akattukāmānaṃ— “ayyo bhāṇako, ayyo bahussuto, ayyo suttantiko, ayyo vinayadharo, ayyo dhammakathiko, detha ayyassa, karotha ayyassā”ti esā paripāceti nāma.**if she says to those who do not already want to give or want to prepare, “This monk is a reciter,” “This monk is learned,” “This monk is an expert on the discourses,” “This monk is an expert on the Monastic Law,” “This monk is an expounder of the Teaching;” “Give to this monk,” “Prepare for this monk”—this is called “has it prepared”.*";
P_HTM[2451]="*Piṇḍapāto nāma**Almsfood:*";
P_HTM[2452]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ.**any of the five cooked foods.*";
P_HTM[2453]="*Aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhāti**Except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway:*";
P_HTM[2454]="*ṭhapetvā gihisamārambhaṃ.**unless the householder had intended to prepare it.*";
P_HTM[2455]="*Gihisamārambho nāma**The householder had intended to prepare it:*";
P_HTM[2456]="*ñātakā vā honti pavāritā vā pakatipaṭiyattaṃ vā.**they are relatives or they have invited or they give regularly.*";
P_HTM[2457]="*Aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhā bhuñjissāmīti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives it with the intention of eating it, except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2458]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre, āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2459]="*Paripācite paripācitasaññī bhuñjati, aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If a nun had it prepared, and he perceives as such, and he eats it, except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2460]="*Paripācite vematiko bhuñjati, aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a nun had it prepared, but he is unsure of it, and he eats it, except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2461]="*Paripācite aparipācitasaññī bhuñjati, aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhā, anāpatti.**If a nun had it prepared, but he does not perceive it as such, and he eats it, except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2462]="*Ekatoupasampannāya paripācitaṃ bhuñjati, aññatra pubbe gihisamārambhā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a nun who is fully ordained only on one side had it prepared, and he eats it, except if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2463]="*Aparipācite paripācitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a nun did not have it prepared, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2464]="*Aparipācite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a nun did not have it prepared, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2465]="*Aparipācite aparipācitasaññī, anāpatti.**If a nun did not have it prepared, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2466]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2467]="*pubbe gihisamārambhe,**if the householder had intended to prepare it anyway;*";
P_HTM[2468]="*sikkhamānā paripāceti,**if a trainee nun has it prepared;*";
P_HTM[2469]="*sāmaṇerī paripāceti,**if a novice nun has it prepared;*";
P_HTM[2470]="*pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,**if it is anything apart from the five cooked food;*";
P_HTM[2471]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2472]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2473]="*Paripācitasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on had prepared, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2474]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2475]="*Ovādavagga**The sub-chapter on the instruction*";
P_HTM[2476]="*30. Rahonisajjasikkhāpada**30. The training rule on sitting in private*";
P_HTM[2477]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[2478]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato udāyissa purāṇadutiyikā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti.**Venerable Udāyīʼs ex-wife became a nun.*";
P_HTM[2479]="*Sā āyasmato udāyissa santike abhikkhaṇaṃ āgacchati, āyasmāpi udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā santike abhikkhaṇaṃ gacchati.**She often went to see Udāyī, and he often went to see her.*";
P_HTM[2480]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī tassā bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesi.**And Udāyī would sit in private alone with that nun.*";
P_HTM[2481]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[2482]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Udāyī sit in private alone with a nun?” …*";
P_HTM[2483]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?**“Is it true, Udāyī, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[2484]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2485]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[2486]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[2487]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2488]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2489]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk sits in private alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2490]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2491]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2492]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2493]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2494]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[2495]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[2496]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[2497]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[2498]="*Eko ekāyāti**Alone:*";
P_HTM[2499]="*bhikkhu ceva hoti bhikkhunī ca.**just the monk and the nun.*";
P_HTM[2500]="*Raho nāma**In private:*";
P_HTM[2501]="*cakkhussa raho sotassa raho.**there is private to the eye and there is private to the ear.*";
P_HTM[2502]="*Cakkhussa raho nāma**Private to the eye:*";
P_HTM[2503]="*na sakkā hoti akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇīyamāne bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne sīsaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne passituṃ.**one is unable to see them winking, raising an eyebrow, or nodding.*";
P_HTM[2504]="*Sotassa raho nāma**Private to the ear:*";
P_HTM[2505]="*na sakkā hoti pakatikathā sotuṃ.**one is unable to hear ordinary speech.*";
P_HTM[2506]="*Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti**Sits:*";
P_HTM[2507]="*bhikkhuniyā nisinnāya bhikkhu upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the monk sits down or lies down next to the seated nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2508]="*Bhikkhu nisinne bhikkhunī upanisinnā vā hoti upanipannā vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the nun sits down or lies down next to the seated monk, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2509]="*Ubho vā nisinnā honti ubho vā nipannā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If both are seated or both are lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2510]="*Raho rahosaññī eko ekāya nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is private, and he perceives it as such, and he sits down alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2511]="*Raho vematiko eko ekāya nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is private, but he is unsure of it, and he sits down alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2512]="*Raho arahosaññī eko ekāya nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is private, but he does not perceive it as such, and he sits down alone with a nun, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2513]="*Araho rahosaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not private, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2514]="*Araho vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not private, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2515]="*Araho arahosaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not private, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2516]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2517]="*yo koci viññū dutiyo hoti,**if he has a companion who understands;*";
P_HTM[2518]="*tiṭṭhati na nisīdati,**if he stands and does not sit down;*";
P_HTM[2519]="*arahopekkho,**if he is not seeking privacy;*";
P_HTM[2520]="*aññavihito nisīdati,**if he sits down preoccupied with something else;*";
P_HTM[2521]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2522]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2523]="*Rahonisajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on sitting in private, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2524]="*Ovādavaggo tatiyo.**The third sub-chapter on the instruction is finished.*";
P_HTM[2525]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[2526]="*Asammataatthaṅgatū,**Not appointed, set,*";
P_HTM[2527]="*Passayāmisadānena;**Dwelling place, worldly gain, and with giving;*";
P_HTM[2528]="*Sibbati addhānaṃ nāvaṃ bhuñjeyya,**He sews, a road, a boat, should eat,*";
P_HTM[2529]="*Eko ekāya te dasāti.**Alone: those are the ten.*";
P_HTM[2530]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2531]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[2532]="*31. Āvasathapiṇḍasikkhāpada**31. The training rule on alms-meals at public guesthouses*";
P_HTM[2533]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[2534]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā avidūre aññatarassa pūgassa āvasathapiṇḍo paññatto hoti.**a certain association was preparing an alms-meal at a public guesthouse not far from Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[2535]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisitvā piṇḍaṃ alabhamānā āvasathaṃ agamaṃsu.**Then, after robing up in the morning, the monks from the group of six took their bowl and robe and entered Sāvatthī for alms. Not getting anything, they went to that public guesthouse.*";
P_HTM[2536]="*Manussā—“cirassampi bhadantā āgatā”ti sakkaccaṃ parivisiṃsu.**Because it was long since they had been there, people served them respectfully.*";
P_HTM[2537]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dutiyampi divasaṃ …pe… tatiyampi divasaṃ pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya sāvatthiṃ piṇḍāya pavisitvā piṇḍaṃ alabhamānā āvasathaṃ gantvā bhuñjiṃsu.**A second and a third day those monks did the same thing.*";
P_HTM[2538]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**Then they thought,*";
P_HTM[2539]="*“kiṃ mayaṃ karissāma ārāmaṃ gantvā.**“What’s the point of returning to the monastery?*";
P_HTM[2540]="*Hiyyopi idheva āgantabbaṃ bhavissatī”ti,**Tomorrow we’ll just have to come back here.”*";
P_HTM[2541]="*tattheva anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjanti.**So they stayed on and on right there, eating alms at the guesthouse,*";
P_HTM[2542]="*Titthiyā apasakkanti.**while the monastics of other religions left.*";
P_HTM[2543]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2544]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics stay on and on, eating alms at the guesthouse?*";
P_HTM[2545]="*Nayimesaññeva āvasathapiṇḍo paññatto;**We don’t prepare the alms-food just for them;*";
P_HTM[2546]="*sabbesaññeva āvasathapiṇḍo paññatto”ti.**we prepare it for everyone.”*";
P_HTM[2547]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[2548]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2549]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six stay on and on, eating alms at a public guesthouse?” …*";
P_HTM[2550]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[2551]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2552]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[2553]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[2554]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2555]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2556]="*“Eko āvasathapiṇḍo bhuñjitabbo. Tato ce uttari bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats more than one alms-meal at a public guesthouse, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2557]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2558]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā sāriputto kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchanto yena aññataro āvasatho tenupasaṅkami.**Soon afterwards Venerable Sāriputta was traveling through the Kosalan country on his way to Sāvatthī when he came to a public guesthouse.*";
P_HTM[2559]="*Manussā—“cirassampi thero āgato”ti sakkaccaṃ parivisiṃsu.**Because it was long since he had been there, people served him respectfully.*";
P_HTM[2560]="*Atha kho āyasmato sāriputtassa bhuttāvissa kharo ābādho uppajji, nāsakkhi tamhā āvasathā pakkamituṃ.**After he had eaten, Sāriputta became severely ill, and he was unable to leave that guesthouse.*";
P_HTM[2561]="*Atha kho te manussā dutiyampi divasaṃ āyasmantaṃ sāriputtaṃ etadavocuṃ—**On the second day, too, those people said to him,*";
P_HTM[2562]="*“bhuñjatha, bhante”ti.**“Please eat, Venerable.”*";
P_HTM[2563]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto—**But since he knew that*";
P_HTM[2564]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggahesi;**the Buddha had prohibited eating alms at a public guesthouse after staying on and on, and because he was afraid of wrongdoing, he did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2565]="*chinnabhatto ahosi.**As a consequence, he missed his meal.*";
P_HTM[2566]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāriputto sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**When he arrived at Sāvatthī, he told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[2567]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2568]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2569]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā anuvasitvā anuvasitvā āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to stay on at a public guesthouse and eat alms there.*";
P_HTM[2570]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2571]="*“Agilānena bhikkhunā eko āvasathapiṇḍo bhuñjitabbo. Tato ce uttari bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who is not sick eats more than one alms-meal at a public guesthouse, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2572]="*Agilāno nāma**Who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[2573]="*sakkoti tamhā āvasathā pakkamituṃ.**he is able to leave that public guesthouse.*";
P_HTM[2574]="*Gilāno nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[2575]="*na sakkoti tamhā āvasathā pakkamituṃ.**he is unable to leave that public guesthouse.*";
P_HTM[2576]="*Āvasathapiṇḍo nāma**Alms-meal at a public guesthouse:*";
P_HTM[2577]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ— sālāya vā maṇḍape vā rukkhamūle vā ajjhokāse vā anodissa yāvadattho paññatto hoti.**as much as one needs of any of the five cooked foods, prepared for the general public, in a building, under a roof-cover, at the foot of a tree, or out in the open.*";
P_HTM[2578]="*Agilānena bhikkhunā sakiṃ bhuñjitabbo. Tato ce uttari “bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**A monk who is not sick may eat there once. If he receives food beyond that with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2579]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2580]="*Agilāno agilānasaññī tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, and he perceives himself as not sick, and he eats more than one alms-meal at a public guesthouse, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2581]="*Agilāno vematiko tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he eats more than one alms-meal at a public guesthouse, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2582]="*Agilāno gilānasaññī tatuttari āvasathapiṇḍaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he eats more than one alms-meal at a public guesthouse, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2583]="*Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is sick, but he perceives himself as not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2584]="*Gilāno vematiko āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is sick, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2585]="*Gilāno gilānasaññī, anāpatti.**If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2586]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2587]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[2588]="*agilāno sakiṃ bhuñjati,**if he is not sick and he eats once;*";
P_HTM[2589]="*gacchanto, vā āgacchanto vā bhuñjati,**if he eats while coming or going;*";
P_HTM[2590]="*sāmikā nimantetvā bhojenti,**if he eats after being invited by the owners;*";
P_HTM[2591]="*odissa paññatto hoti,**if the food is prepared specifically for him;*";
P_HTM[2592]="*na yāvadattho paññatto hoti,**if there is not as much as he needs;*";
P_HTM[2593]="*pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,**if it is anything apart from the five cooked foods;*";
P_HTM[2594]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2595]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2596]="*Āvasathapiṇḍasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on alms-meals at public guesthouses, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2597]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2598]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[2599]="*32. Gaṇabhojanasikkhāpada**32. The training rule on eating in a group*";
P_HTM[2600]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[2601]="*Tena kho pana samayena devadatto parihīnalābhasakkāro sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjati.**At that time, because of decline in material support and loss of respect, Devadatta and his followers ate at invitations only after repeatedly asking.*";
P_HTM[2602]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[2603]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?*";
P_HTM[2604]="*Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti.**Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t prefer tasty food?”*";
P_HTM[2605]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[2606]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2607]="*“kathañhi nāma devadatto sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissatī”ti …pe…**“How can Devadatta and his followers eat at invitations after repeatedly asking?” …*";
P_HTM[2608]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, devadatta, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Devadatta, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[2609]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2610]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[2611]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, sapariso kulesu viññāpetvā viññāpetvā bhuñjissasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[2612]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2613]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2614]="*“Gaṇabhojane pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats in a group, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2615]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2616]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā gilāne bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti.**Soon afterwards people invited sick monks to a meal.*";
P_HTM[2617]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2618]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2619]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2620]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat in a group.*";
P_HTM[2621]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2622]="*“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2623]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**This is the appropriate occasion: he is sick.’”*";
P_HTM[2624]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2625]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvaradānasamaye sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyādetvā bhikkhū nimantenti—**Soon afterwards, during the robe-giving season, people prepared a meal together with robe-cloth and then invited the monks, saying,*";
P_HTM[2626]="*“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti.**“We wish to offer a meal and then give robe-cloth.”*";
P_HTM[2627]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2628]="*Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati.**As a result, they only got a small amount of robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[2629]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2630]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group during the robe-giving season.*";
P_HTM[2631]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2632]="*“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2633]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season.’”*";
P_HTM[2634]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2635]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvarakārake bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti.**Soon afterwards people invited the robe-making monks for a meal.*";
P_HTM[2636]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2637]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2638]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group at a time when you are making robes.*";
P_HTM[2639]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2640]="*“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2641]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes.’”*";
P_HTM[2642]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2643]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū manussehi saddhiṃ addhānaṃ gacchanti.**Soon afterwards some monks went traveling with a group of people.*";
P_HTM[2644]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—**The monks said to those people,*";
P_HTM[2645]="*“muhuttaṃ, āvuso, āgametha; piṇḍāya carissāmā”ti.**“Please wait a moment while we walk for alms.”*";
P_HTM[2646]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—**They replied,*";
P_HTM[2647]="*“idheva, bhante, bhuñjathā”ti.**“Venerables, please eat right here.”*";
P_HTM[2648]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na paṭiggaṇhanti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2649]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2650]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, addhānagamanasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when you’re traveling.*";
P_HTM[2651]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2652]="*“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2653]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes; he is traveling.’”*";
P_HTM[2654]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2655]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū manussehi saddhiṃ nāvāya gacchanti.**Soon afterwards some monks were traveling by boat with a group of people.*";
P_HTM[2656]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—“muhuttaṃ, āvuso, tīraṃ upanetha; piṇḍāya carissāmā”ti.**The monks said to those people, “Please go to the shore for a moment while we walk for alms.”*";
P_HTM[2657]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—“idheva, bhante, bhuñjathā”ti.**They replied, “Venerables, please eat right here.”*";
P_HTM[2658]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na paṭiggaṇhanti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2659]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2660]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, nāvābhiruhanasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when on board a boat.*";
P_HTM[2661]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2662]="*“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2663]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, nāvābhiruhanasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes; he is traveling; he is on a boat.’”*";
P_HTM[2664]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2665]="*Tena kho pana samayena disāsu vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhū rājagahaṃ āgacchanti bhagavantaṃ dassanāya.**Soon afterwards monks who had completed the rainy-season residence in various regions were coming to Rājagaha to visit the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2666]="*Manussā nānāverajjake bhikkhū passitvā bhattena nimantenti.**People saw those monks who had come from various countries and invited them for a meal.*";
P_HTM[2667]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2668]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2669]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, mahāsamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group on big occasions.*";
P_HTM[2670]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2671]="*“Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2672]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, nāvābhiruhanasamayo, mahāsamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes; he is traveling; he is on a boat; it is a big occasion.’”*";
P_HTM[2673]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2674]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño māgadhassa seniyassa bimbisārassa ñātisālohito ājīvakesu pabbajito hoti. Atha kho so ājīvako yena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ etadavoca—“icchāmahaṃ, mahārāja, sabbapāsaṇḍikabhattaṃ kātun”ti.**Soon afterwards a relative of King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha who had gone forth with the Ājīvaka ascetics went to the King and said, “Great King, I wish to make a meal for the monastics of all religions.”*";
P_HTM[2675]="*“Sace tvaṃ, bhante, buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṅghaṃ paṭhamaṃ bhojeyyāsi”.**“That’s fine, Sir, if you first feed the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[2676]="*“Evaṃ kareyyāmī”ti.**“I’ll do that.”*";
P_HTM[2677]="*Atha kho so ājīvako bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—“adhivāsentu me bhikkhū svātanāya bhattan”ti.**And he sent a message to the monks: “Please accept a meal from me tomorrow.”*";
P_HTM[2678]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā gaṇabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating in a group and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2679]="*Atha kho so ājīvako yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi, sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho so ājīvako bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**That Ājīvaka ascetic then went to the Buddha, exchanged pleasantries with him, and said,*";
P_HTM[2680]="*“bhavampi gotamo pabbajito, ahampi pabbajito;**“Good Gotama has gone forth and so have I.*";
P_HTM[2681]="*arahati pabbajito pabbajitassa piṇḍaṃ paṭiggahetuṃ.**One who has gone forth should receive alms from another who has gone forth.*";
P_HTM[2682]="*Adhivāsetu me bhavaṃ gotamo svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**Good Gotama, please accept a meal from me tomorrow together with the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[2683]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[2684]="*Atha kho so ājīvako bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā pakkāmi.**The Ājīvaka understood that the Buddha had consented, and he left.*";
P_HTM[2685]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2686]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, samaṇabhattasamaye gaṇabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat in a group when the meal is given by a monastic.*";
P_HTM[2687]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2688]="*Gaṇabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats in a group, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2689]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, nāvābhiruhanasamayo, mahāsamayo, samaṇabhattasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes; he is traveling; he is on a boat; it is a big occasion; it is a meal given by a monastic.’”*";
P_HTM[2690]="*Gaṇabhojanaṃ nāma**Eats in a group:*";
P_HTM[2691]="*yattha cattāro bhikkhū pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantitā bhuñjanti. Etaṃ gaṇabhojanaṃ nāma.**wherever four monks, after being invited, eat any of the five cooked foods—this is called “eats in a group”.*";
P_HTM[2692]="*Aññatra samayāti**Except on an appropriate occasion:*";
P_HTM[2693]="*ṭhapetvā samayaṃ.**unless it is an appropriate occasion.*";
P_HTM[2694]="*Gilānasamayo nāma**He is sick:*";
P_HTM[2695]="*antamaso pādāpi phalitā honti. “Gilānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**even if he has cracked feet, he may eat in a group.*";
P_HTM[2696]="*Cīvaradānasamayo nāma**It is the robe-giving season:*";
P_HTM[2697]="*anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañcamāsā. “Cīvaradānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**if he has not participated in the robe-making procedure, he may eat in a group during the last month of the rainy season. If he has participated in the robe-making procedure, he may eat in a group during the five month period.*";
P_HTM[2698]="*Cīvarakārasamayo nāma**It is a time of making robes:*";
P_HTM[2699]="*cīvare kayiramāne. “Cīvarakārasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**when he is making robes, he may eat in a group.*";
P_HTM[2700]="*Addhānagamanasamayo nāma**He is traveling:*";
P_HTM[2701]="*“addhayojanaṃ gacchissāmī”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ, gacchantena bhuñjitabbaṃ, gatena bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he may eat in a group if he intends to travel at least six kilometers, while traveling, and after traveling.*";
P_HTM[2702]="*Nāvābhiruhanasamayo nāma**He is on a boat:*";
P_HTM[2703]="*“nāvaṃ abhiruhissāmī”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ, āruḷhena bhuñjitabbaṃ, oruḷhena bhuñjitabbaṃ.**he may eat in a group if he intends to board a boat, while on board, and after disembarking.*";
P_HTM[2704]="*Mahāsamayo nāma**It is a big occasion:*";
P_HTM[2705]="*yattha dve tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā yāpenti, catutthe āgate na yāpenti. “Mahāsamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**if two or three monks can get by on walking for alms, but not a group of four, he may eat in a group.*";
P_HTM[2706]="*Samaṇabhattasamayo nāma**It is a meal given by a monastic:*";
P_HTM[2707]="*yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno bhattaṃ karoti. “Samaṇabhattasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**if any kind of wanderer is making the meal, he may eat in a group.*";
P_HTM[2708]="*“Aññatra samayā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives something intending to eat it, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2709]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2710]="*Gaṇabhojane gaṇabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he eats in a group, and he perceives it as such, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2711]="*Gaṇabhojane vematiko, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he eats in a group, but he is unsure of it, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2712]="*Gaṇabhojane nagaṇabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he eats in a group, but he does not perceive it as such, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2713]="*Nagaṇabhojane gaṇabhojanasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he does not eat in a group, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2714]="*Nagaṇabhojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he does not eat in a group, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2715]="*Nagaṇabhojane nagaṇabhojanasaññī, anāpatti.**If he does not eat in a group, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2716]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2717]="*samaye,**if it is an appropriate occasion;*";
P_HTM[2718]="*dve tayo ekato bhuñjanti,**if two or three eat together;*";
P_HTM[2719]="*piṇḍāya caritvā ekato sannipatitvā bhuñjanti,**if they eat together after walking for alms;*";
P_HTM[2720]="*niccabhattaṃ,**if it is a regular meal invitation;*";
P_HTM[2721]="*salākabhattaṃ,**if it is a meal for which lots are drawn;*";
P_HTM[2722]="*pakkhikaṃ,**if it is a half-monthly meal;*";
P_HTM[2723]="*uposathikaṃ,**if it is on the observance day;*";
P_HTM[2724]="*pāṭipadikaṃ,**if it is on the day after the observance day;*";
P_HTM[2725]="*pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,**if it is anything apart from the five cooked foods;*";
P_HTM[2726]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2727]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2728]="*Gaṇabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on eating in a group, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2729]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2730]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[2731]="*33. Paramparabhojanasikkhāpada**33. The training rule on eating a meal before another*";
P_HTM[2732]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood near Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[2733]="*Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ paṇītānaṃ bhattānaṃ bhattapaṭipāṭi adhiṭṭhitā hoti.**At that time a succession of fine meals had been arranged in Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[2734]="*Atha kho aññatarassa daliddassa kammakārassa etadahosi—“na kho idaṃ orakaṃ bhavissati yathayime manussā sakkaccaṃ bhattaṃ karonti; yannūnāhampi bhattaṃ kareyyan”ti.**A certain poor worker thought, “Why don’t I prepare a meal? It must be really worthwhile, seeing as these people prepare a meal with such respect.”*";
P_HTM[2735]="*Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro yena kirapatiko tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ kirapatikaṃ etadavoca—“icchāmahaṃ, ayyaputta, buddhappamukhassa bhikkhusaṅghassa bhattaṃ kātuṃ.**He then went to his boss Kira and said, “Sir, I wish to prepare a meal for the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2736]="*Dehi me vetanan”ti.**Please give me my salary.”*";
P_HTM[2737]="*Sopi kho kirapatiko saddho hoti pasanno.**Because Kira also had faith and confidence,*";
P_HTM[2738]="*Atha kho so kirapatiko tassa daliddassa kammakārassa abbhātirekaṃ vetanaṃ adāsi.**he gave the worker his salary and much extra.*";
P_HTM[2739]="*Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so daliddo kammakāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**Soon afterwards that worker went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down, and said,*";
P_HTM[2740]="*“adhivāsetu me, bhante, bhagavā svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā”ti.**“Venerable Sir, please accept a meal from me tomorrow together with the Sangha of monks.”*";
P_HTM[2741]="*“Mahā kho, āvuso, bhikkhusaṅgho, jānāhī”ti.**“The Sangha is large.”*";
P_HTM[2742]="*“Hotu, bhante, mahā bhikkhusaṅgho.**“No problem!*";
P_HTM[2743]="*Bahū me badarā paṭiyattā badaramissena peyyā paripūrissantī”ti.**I’ve prepare much jujube, supplemented with jujube drinks.”*";
P_HTM[2744]="*Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena.**The Buddha consented by remaining silent, and the worker understood.*";
P_HTM[2745]="*Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**He got up from his seat, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[2746]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū—“daliddena kira kammakārena svātanāya buddhappamukho bhikkhusaṅgho nimantito, badaramissena peyyā paripūrissantī”ti.**The monks heard that a poor worker had invited the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha on the following day for a meal supplemented with jujube drinks.*";
P_HTM[2747]="*Te kālasseva piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjiṃsu.**And so they ate in the morning after walking for alms.*";
P_HTM[2748]="*Assosuṃ kho manussā—“daliddena kira kammakārena buddhappamukho bhikkhusaṅgho nimantito”ti. Te daliddassa kammakārassa pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ abhihariṃsu.**When people heard that a poor worker had invited the Sangha of monks headed by the Buddha for a meal, they brought much food of various kinds to him.*";
P_HTM[2749]="*Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocāpesi—“kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**The following morning that worker prepared his food, and then had the Buddha informed that the meal was ready.*";
P_HTM[2750]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena tassa daliddassa kammakārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghena.**The Buddha robed up, took his bowl and robe and, together with the Sangha of monks, went to the house of that poor worker, where he sat down on the prepared seat in the dining hall.*";
P_HTM[2751]="*Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro bhattagge bhikkhū parivisati. Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The worker served the monks, but they kept saying,*";
P_HTM[2752]="*“thokaṃ, āvuso, dehi. Thokaṃ, āvuso, dehī”ti.**“Give just a little.”*";
P_HTM[2753]="*“Mā kho tumhe, bhante, ‘ayaṃ daliddo kammakāro’ti thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhittha.**“Venerables, don’t accept so little because you think I’m just a poor worker.*";
P_HTM[2754]="*Pahūtaṃ me khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyattaṃ.**I’ve prepared much food of various kinds.*";
P_HTM[2755]="*Paṭiggaṇhatha, bhante, yāvadatthan”ti.**Please accept as much as you like.”*";
P_HTM[2756]="*“Na kho mayaṃ, āvuso, etaṅkāraṇā thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhāma.**“We’re not accepting so little because of that,*";
P_HTM[2757]="*Api ca, mayaṃ kālasseva piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjimhā; tena mayaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ paṭiggaṇhāmā”ti.**but because we ate in the morning after walking for alms.”*";
P_HTM[2758]="*Atha kho so daliddo kammakāro ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That poor worker complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2759]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā mayā nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissanti.**“How could the venerables eat elsewhere when invited by me?*";
P_HTM[2760]="*Na cāhaṃ paṭibalo yāvadatthaṃ dātun”ti?**Am I not able to give as much as they need?”*";
P_HTM[2761]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa daliddassa kammakārassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that worker,*";
P_HTM[2762]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2763]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How could those monks eat elsewhere when invited for a meal?” …*";
P_HTM[2764]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”*";
P_HTM[2765]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2766]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[2767]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā aññatra nimantitā aññatra bhuñjissanti.**“How could those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[2768]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2769]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2770]="*“Paramparabhojane pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats a meal before another, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2771]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2772]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu gilāno hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain monk became sick.*";
P_HTM[2773]="*Aññataro bhikkhu piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—“bhuñjāhi, āvuso”ti.**Another monk took some almsfood, went to that monk, and told him to eat it.*";
P_HTM[2774]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso, atthi me bhattapaccāsā”ti.**“I can’t. I’m expecting another meal.”*";
P_HTM[2775]="*Tassa bhikkhuno piṇḍapāto ussūre āharīyittha. So bhikkhu na cittarūpaṃ bhuñji.**But since that almsfood only arrived at midday, that monk did not get to eat as much as he had intended.*";
P_HTM[2776]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2777]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2778]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat a meal before another.*";
P_HTM[2779]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2780]="*“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats a meal before another, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2781]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**This is the appropriate occasion: he is sick.’”*";
P_HTM[2782]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2783]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvaradānasamaye sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyādetvā bhikkhū nimantenti—“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti.**Soon afterwards, during the robe-giving season, people prepared a meal together with robe-cloth and then invited the monks, saying, “We wish to offer a meal and give robe-cloth.”*";
P_HTM[2784]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā paramparabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating a meal before another and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2785]="*Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati.**As a result, they only got a small amount of robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[2786]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2787]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another during the robe-giving season.*";
P_HTM[2788]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2789]="*“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats a meal before another, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2790]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season.’”*";
P_HTM[2791]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2792]="*Tena kho pana samayena manussā cīvarakārake bhikkhū bhattena nimantenti.**Soon afterwards people invited the robe-making monks for a meal.*";
P_HTM[2793]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā paramparabhojanan”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating a meal before another and being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not accept.*";
P_HTM[2794]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[2795]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another at a time when you are making robes.*";
P_HTM[2796]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2797]="*“Paramparabhojane, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk eats a meal before another, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2798]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Gilānasamayo, cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: he is sick; it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes.’”*";
P_HTM[2799]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2800]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya āyasmatā ānandena pacchāsamaṇena yena aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami;**Soon afterwards, after robing up in the morning, the Buddha took his bowl and robe and went to a certain family with Venerable Ānanda as his attendant.*";
P_HTM[2801]="*upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi. Atha kho te manussā bhagavato ca āyasmato ca ānandassa bhojanaṃ adaṃsu.**He sat down on the prepared seat, and the people there gave cooked food.*";
P_HTM[2802]="*Āyasmā ānando kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggaṇhāti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, Ānanda did not accept it.*";
P_HTM[2803]="*“Gaṇhāhi, ānandā”ti.**The Buddha said, “Accept it, Ānanda.”*";
P_HTM[2804]="*“Alaṃ, bhagavā, atthi me bhattapaccāsā”ti.**“I can’t, Venerable Sir, I’m expecting another meal.”*";
P_HTM[2805]="*“Tenahānanda, vikappetvā gaṇhāhī”ti.**“Well then, Ānanda, transfer that meal to someone else and then receive this.”*";
P_HTM[2806]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—“**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2807]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vikappetvā paramparabhojanaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat a meal before another if you transfer the other meal to someone else.*";
P_HTM[2808]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, vikappetabbaṃ—‘mayhaṃ bhattapaccāsaṃ itthannāmassa dammī’”ti.**And, monks, this is how it should be transferred: ‘I give my expected meal to so-and-so.’”*";
P_HTM[2809]="*Paramparabhojanaṃ nāma**Eats a meal before another:*";
P_HTM[2810]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantito, taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjati, etaṃ paramparabhojanaṃ nāma.**if he has been invited to eat any of the five cooked foods, and he then eats any of the five cooked foods elsewhere—this is called “eats a meal before another”.*";
P_HTM[2811]="*Aññatra samayāti**Except on an appropriate occasion:*";
P_HTM[2812]="*ṭhapetvā samayaṃ.**unless it is an appropriate occasion.*";
P_HTM[2813]="*Gilānasamayo nāma**He is sick:*";
P_HTM[2814]="*na sakkoti ekāsane nisinno yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjituṃ. “Gilānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**if he is not able to eat as much as he needs in one sitting, he may eat a meal before another.*";
P_HTM[2815]="*Cīvaradānasamayo nāma**It is the robe-giving season:*";
P_HTM[2816]="*anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā. “Cīvaradānasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**if he has not participated in the robe-making procedure, he may eat a meal before another during the last month of the rainy season. If he has participated in the robe-making procedure, he may eat a meal before another during the five month period.*";
P_HTM[2817]="*Cīvarakārasamayo nāma**It is a time of making robes:*";
P_HTM[2818]="*cīvare kayiramāne. “Cīvarakārasamayo”ti bhuñjitabbaṃ.**when he is making robes, he may eat a meal before another.*";
P_HTM[2819]="*“Aññatra samayā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives food with the intention of eating it, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2820]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2821]="*Paramparabhojane paramparabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a meal before another, and he perceives it as such, and he eats it, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2822]="*Paramparabhojane vematiko, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a meal before another, but he is unsure of it, and he eats it, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2823]="*Paramparabhojane naparamparabhojanasaññī, aññatra samayā, bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a meal before another, but he does not perceive it as such, and he eats it, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2824]="*Naparamparabhojane paramparabhojanasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a meal before another, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2825]="*Naparamparabhojane vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a meal before another, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2826]="*Naparamparabhojane naparamparabhojanasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a meal before another, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2827]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2828]="*samaye,**if it is an appropriate occasion;*";
P_HTM[2829]="*vikappetvā bhuñjati,**if he transfers his other meal to someone else and then eats;*";
P_HTM[2830]="*dve tayo nimantane ekato bhuñjati,**if he eats the food from two or three invitational meals together;*";
P_HTM[2831]="*nimantanapaṭipāṭiyā bhuñjati,**if he eats the meals in the same order that the invitations were received;*";
P_HTM[2832]="*sakalena gāmena nimantito tasmiṃ gāme yattha katthaci bhuñjati,**if he is invited by a whole village and he eats anywhere in that village;*";
P_HTM[2833]="*sakalena pūgena nimantito tasmiṃ pūge yattha katthaci bhuñjati,**if he is invited by a whole association and he eats anywhere that belongs to that association;*";
P_HTM[2834]="*nimantiyamāno bhikkhaṃ gahessāmīti bhaṇati,**if, when being invited, he says, “I’ll get almsfood;”*";
P_HTM[2835]="*niccabhatte,**if it is a regular meal invitation;*";
P_HTM[2836]="*salākabhatte,**if it is a meal for which lots are drawn;*";
P_HTM[2837]="*pakkhike,**if it is a half-monthly meal;*";
P_HTM[2838]="*uposathike,**if it is on the observance day;*";
P_HTM[2839]="*pāṭipadike,**if it is on the day after the observance day;*";
P_HTM[2840]="*pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha anāpatti,**if it is anything apart from the five cooked foods;*";
P_HTM[2841]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2842]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2843]="*Paramparabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on eating a meal before another, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2844]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2845]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[2846]="*34. Kāṇamātusikkhāpada**34. The training rule on Kāṇamātā*";
P_HTM[2847]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[2848]="*Tena kho pana samayena kāṇamātā upāsikā saddhā hoti pasannā.**At that time there was a female lay follower Kāṇamātā who had faith and confidence.*";
P_HTM[2849]="*Kāṇā gāmake aññatarassa purisassa dinnā hoti.**She had a daughter, Kāṇā, who had been given in marriage to a man in a certain village.*";
P_HTM[2850]="*Atha kho kāṇā mātugharaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**On one occasion Kāṇā went to her mother’s house on some business.*";
P_HTM[2851]="*Atha kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—“āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgatan”ti.**Kāṇā’s husband sent her a message: “Please come, Kāṇā, I want you back.”*";
P_HTM[2852]="*Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā “kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantun”ti pūvaṃ paci.**Kāṇamātā thought, “It’s shameful to go empty-handed,” and she baked pastries.*";
P_HTM[2853]="*Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ pāvisi. Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi.**Just when the pastries were finished, an alms-collecting monk entered Kāṇamātā’s house, and she gave him pastries.*";
P_HTM[2854]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi.**After leaving, he told another monk, and he too was given pastries.*";
P_HTM[2855]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi.**And the same happened a third time.*";
P_HTM[2856]="*Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi.**At that, all the pastries were gone.*";
P_HTM[2857]="*Dutiyampi kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—“āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgatan”ti.**A second time Kāṇā’s husband sent her the same message, and everything unfolded as before.*";
P_HTM[2858]="*Dutiyampi kho kāṇamātā upāsikā “kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantun”ti pūvaṃ paci.* **";
P_HTM[2859]="*Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ pāvisi.* **";
P_HTM[2860]="*Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[2861]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[2862]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[2863]="*Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi.* **";
P_HTM[2864]="*Tatiyampi kho kāṇāya sāmiko kāṇāya santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—“āgacchatu kāṇā, icchāmi kāṇāya āgataṃ.**A third time he sent the same message,*";
P_HTM[2865]="*Sace kāṇā nāgacchissati, ahaṃ aññaṃ pajāpatiṃ ānessāmī”ti.**adding, “If Kāṇā doesn’t come, I’ll find another wife.”*";
P_HTM[2866]="*Tatiyampi kho kāṇamātā upāsikā kismiṃ viya rittahatthaṃ gantunti pūvaṃ paci.**But once again all the pastries were given to monks.*";
P_HTM[2867]="*Pakke pūve aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ pāvisi.* **";
P_HTM[2868]="*Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā tassa bhikkhuno pūvaṃ dāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[2869]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[2870]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi pūvaṃ dāpesi.* **";
P_HTM[2871]="*Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pūvaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi.* **";
P_HTM[2872]="*Atha kho kāṇāya sāmiko aññaṃ pajāpatiṃ ānesi.**Kāṇā’s husband found another wife,*";
P_HTM[2873]="*Assosi kho kāṇā—“tena kira purisena aññā pajāpati ānītā”ti. Sā rodantī aṭṭhāsi.**And when Kāṇā heard what had happened, she cried.*";
P_HTM[2874]="*Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena kāṇamātāya upāsikāya nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Soon afterwards, after robing up in the morning, the Buddha took his bowl and robe and went to Kāṇamātā’s house, where he sat down on the prepared seat.*";
P_HTM[2875]="*Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Kāṇamātā approached the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[2876]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho kāṇamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ bhagavā etadavoca—“kissāyaṃ kāṇā rodatī”ti? Atha kho kāṇamātā upāsikā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**The Buddha asked her why Kāṇā was crying, and she told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[2877]="*Atha kho bhagavā kāṇamātaraṃ upāsikaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassetvā samādapetvā samuttejetvā sampahaṃsetvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**After instructing, inspiring, and gladdening her with a teaching, the Buddha got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[2878]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro sattho rājagahā paṭiyālokaṃ gantukāmo hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain caravan was ready to go south from Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[2879]="*Aññataro piṇḍacāriko bhikkhu taṃ satthaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**An alms-collecting monk went up to that caravan to get almsfood,*";
P_HTM[2880]="*Aññataro upāsako tassa bhikkhuno sattuṃ dāpesi.**and a lay follower gave him flour products.*";
P_HTM[2881]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi sattuṃ dāpesi.**After leaving, that monk told another monk, and he too was given flour products.*";
P_HTM[2882]="*So nikkhamitvā aññassa ācikkhi. Tassapi sattuṃ dāpesi.**And the same happened a third time.*";
P_HTM[2883]="*Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pātheyyaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi.**At that, all his provisions were gone.*";
P_HTM[2884]="*Atha kho so upāsako te manusse etadavoca—**That lay follower said to the other people in the caravan,*";
P_HTM[2885]="*“ajjaṇho, ayyā, āgametha, yathāpaṭiyattaṃ pātheyyaṃ ayyānaṃ dinnaṃ.**“Sirs, please wait one day. I’ve given my provisions to the monks.*";
P_HTM[2886]="*Pātheyyaṃ paṭiyādessāmī”ti.**I need to prepare more.”*";
P_HTM[2887]="*“Nāyyo sakkā āgametuṃ, payāto sattho”ti agamaṃsu.**“We can’t wait. The caravan is already on its way.” And they left.*";
P_HTM[2888]="*Atha kho tassa upāsakassa pātheyyaṃ paṭiyādetvā pacchā gacchantassa corā acchindiṃsu.**After preparing provisions, that lay follower followed after the caravan, but he was robbed by thieves.*";
P_HTM[2889]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[2890]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā paṭiggahessanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics receive without moderation?*";
P_HTM[2891]="*Ayaṃ imesaṃ datvā pacchā gacchanto corehi acchinno”ti.**This man gave to them, and then because he was following after the caravan he was robbed by thieves.”*";
P_HTM[2892]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[2893]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[2894]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2895]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[2896]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya, saṅghaphāsutāya …pe… vinayānuggahāya.**for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[2897]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2898]="*“Bhikkhuṃ paneva kulaṃ upagataṃ pūvehi vā manthehi vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyya, ākaṅkhamānena bhikkhunā dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahetabbā tato ce uttari paṭiggaṇheyya pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk goes to a family and is invited to take pastries or baked goods, he may accept two or three bowlfuls if he wishes. If he accepts more than that, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2899]="*Dvattipattapūre paṭiggahetvā tato nīharitvā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvibhajitabbaṃ. Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti.**If he accepts two or three bowlfuls, he should take it away and share it with the monks. This is the proper procedure.’”*";
P_HTM[2900]="*Bhikkhuṃ paneva kulaṃ upagatanti**A monk goes to a family:*";
P_HTM[2901]="*kulaṃ nāma cattāri kulāni—khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ.**a family: there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[2902]="*Upagatanti**Goes to:*";
P_HTM[2903]="*tattha gataṃ.**he has gone there.*";
P_HTM[2904]="*Pūvaṃ nāma**Pastries:*";
P_HTM[2905]="*yaṃ kiñci paheṇakatthāya paṭiyattaṃ.**whatever has been prepared for the purpose of sending away.*";
P_HTM[2906]="*Manthaṃ nāma**Baked goods:*";
P_HTM[2907]="*yaṃ kiñci pātheyyatthāya paṭiyattaṃ.**whatever has been prepared as provisions for a journey.*";
P_HTM[2908]="*Abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyāti**Is invited to take:*";
P_HTM[2909]="*yāvatakaṃ icchasi tāvatakaṃ gaṇhāhīti.**“Take as much as you like.”*";
P_HTM[2910]="*Ākaṅkhamānenāti**If he wishes:*";
P_HTM[2911]="*icchamānena.**if he desires.*";
P_HTM[2912]="*Dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahetabbāti**He may accept two or three bowlfuls:*";
P_HTM[2913]="*dvetayo pattapūrā paṭiggahetabbā.**two or three bowlfuls can be accepted.*";
P_HTM[2914]="*Tato ce uttari paṭigaṇheyyāti**If he accepts more than that:*";
P_HTM[2915]="*tatuttari paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when he accepts more than that, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2916]="*Dvattipattapūre paṭiggahetvā**If he accepts two or three bowlfuls:*";
P_HTM[2917]="*tato nikkhamantena bhikkhuṃ passitvā ācikkhitabbaṃ—“amutra mayā dvattipattapūrā paṭiggahitā, mā kho tattha paṭiggaṇhī”ti.**leaving that place and seeing a monk, he should tell him, “I’ve accepted two or three bowlfuls from such-and-such a place; don’t accept anything from there.”*";
P_HTM[2918]="*Sace passitvā na ācikkhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sees a monk, but does not tell him, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2919]="*Sace ācikkhite paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If one who is told accepts from there regardless, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2920]="*Tato nīharitvā bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ saṃvibhajitabbanti**He should take it away and share it with the monks:*";
P_HTM[2921]="*paṭikkamanaṃ nīharitvā saṃvibhajitabbaṃ.**he should take it away when returning from almsround and then share it.*";
P_HTM[2922]="*Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti**This is the proper procedure:*";
P_HTM[2923]="*ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā.**this is the right method.*";
P_HTM[2924]="*Atirekadvattipattapūre atirekasaññī paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, and he perceives it as more, and he accepts it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2925]="*Atirekadvattipattapūre vematiko paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, but he is unsure of it, and he accepts it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2926]="*Atirekadvattipattapūre ūnakasaññī paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two or three bowlfuls, but he perceives it as less, and he accepts it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[2927]="*Ūnakadvattipattapūre atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2928]="*Ūnakadvattipattapūre vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[2929]="*Ūnakadvattipattapūre ūnakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is less than two or three bowlfuls, and he perceives it as less, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[2930]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[2931]="*dvattipattapūre paṭiggaṇhāti,**if he accepts two or three bowlfuls;*";
P_HTM[2932]="*ūnakadvattipattapūre paṭiggaṇhāti,**if he accepts less than two or three bowlfuls;*";
P_HTM[2933]="*na paheṇakatthāya na pātheyyatthāya paṭiyattaṃ denti,**if they give anything that has not been prepared for sending away or as provisions for a journey;*";
P_HTM[2934]="*paheṇakatthāya vā pātheyyatthāya vā paṭiyattasesakaṃ denti,**if they give the leftovers from what was prepared for sending away or as provisions for a journey;*";
P_HTM[2935]="*gamane paṭippassaddhe denti,**if they give after the plans to travel have been canceled;*";
P_HTM[2936]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[2937]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[2938]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[2939]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[2940]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[2941]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[2942]="*Kāṇamātusikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on Kāṇamātā, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[2943]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[2944]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[2945]="*35. Pavāraṇāsikkhāpada**35. The training rule on invitations*";
P_HTM[2946]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[2947]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro brāhmaṇo bhikkhū nimantetvā bhojesi.**a certain brahmin had invited the monks for a meal.*";
P_HTM[2948]="*Bhikkhū bhuttāvī pavāritā ñātikulāni gantvā ekacce bhuñjiṃsu ekacce piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya agamaṃsu.**When the monks had finished and refused an invitation to eat more, they went to their respective families, where some ate and some took away almsfood.*";
P_HTM[2949]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo paṭivissake etadavoca—**Soon afterwards that brahmin said to his neighbors,*";
P_HTM[2950]="*“bhikkhū mayā, ayyā, santappitā.**“The monks have been satisfied by me.*";
P_HTM[2951]="*Etha, tumhepi santappessāmī”ti.**Come, and I’ll satisfy you, too.”*";
P_HTM[2952]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—“kiṃ tvaṃ, ayyo, amhe santappessasi?**“How could you satisfy us?*";
P_HTM[2953]="*Yepi tayā nimantitā tepi amhākaṃ gharāni āgantvā ekacce bhuñjiṃsu ekacce piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya agamaṃsū”ti.**Those monks who were invited by you came to our houses. Some of them ate there and some took away almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[2954]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That brahmin complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2955]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā amhākaṃ ghare bhuñjitvā aññatra bhuñjissanti.**“How could the venerables eat in our house and afterwards eat elsewhere?*";
P_HTM[2956]="*Na cāhaṃ paṭibalo yāvadatthaṃ dātun”ti.**Am I not able to give them as much as they need?”*";
P_HTM[2957]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa brāhmaṇassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that brahmin,*";
P_HTM[2958]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[2959]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How could those monks finish their meal and refuse an invitation to eat more, and then eat elsewhere?” …*";
P_HTM[2960]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”*";
P_HTM[2961]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2962]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[2963]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjissanti.**“How could those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[2964]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[2965]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2966]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk has finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more, and then eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2967]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[2968]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṇīte piṇḍapāte nīharanti.**Soon afterwards the monks were bringing back fine almsfood for the sick monks.*";
P_HTM[2969]="*Gilānā na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjanti.**But because the sick monks were unable to eat as much as they had intended,*";
P_HTM[2970]="*Tāni bhikkhū chaṭṭenti.**the monks threw the leftovers away.*";
P_HTM[2971]="*Assosi kho bhagavā uccāsaddaṃ mahāsaddaṃ kākoravasaddaṃ.**When the Buddha heard the loud sound of crows cawing,*";
P_HTM[2972]="*Sutvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—**he asked Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[2973]="*“kiṃ nu kho so, ānanda, uccāsaddo mahāsaddo kākoravasaddo”ti?**“Ānanda, why is there this loud sound of crows cawing?”*";
P_HTM[2974]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Ānanda told him what had happened, and the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[2975]="*“Bhuñjeyyuṃ panānanda, bhikkhū gilānātirittan”ti.**“But Ānanda, don’t the monks eat the leftovers from those who are sick?”*";
P_HTM[2976]="*“Na bhuñjeyyuṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“No, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[2977]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[2978]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānassa ca agilānassa ca atirittaṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to eat the leftovers both from those who are sick and from those who are not sick.*";
P_HTM[2979]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, atirittaṃ kātabbaṃ—**And, monks, this is how you make food leftover:*";
P_HTM[2980]="*‘alametaṃ sabban’ti.**‘I don’t need of any of this.’*";
P_HTM[2981]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[2982]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito anatirittaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk has finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more, and then eats fresh or cooked food that is not left over, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[2983]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[2984]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[2985]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[2986]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[2987]="*Bhuttāvī nāma**Has finished his meal:*";
P_HTM[2988]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti.**has eaten any of the five cooked foods, even what fits on the tip of a blade of grass.*";
P_HTM[2989]="*Pavārito nāma**Refused an invitation to eat more:*";
P_HTM[2990]="*asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhito abhiharati, paṭikkhepo paññāyati.**there is eating; there is cooked food; it is offered by one standing within arm’s reach; there is a refusal.*";
P_HTM[2991]="*Anatirittaṃ nāma**Not left over:*";
P_HTM[2992]="*akappiyakataṃ hoti,**the making it leftover is done with food that is unallowable;*";
P_HTM[2993]="*appaṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,**it is done with food that has not been received;*";
P_HTM[2994]="*anuccāritakataṃ hoti,**it is done with food that is not held in hand;*";
P_HTM[2995]="*ahatthapāse kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who is not within arm’s reach;*";
P_HTM[2996]="*abhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who has not finished his meal;*";
P_HTM[2997]="*bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā vuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who has finished his meal, who has refused an invitation to eat more, but who has risen from his seat;*";
P_HTM[2998]="*“alametaṃ sabban”ti avuttaṃ hoti,**“I don’t need of any of this,” has not been said;*";
P_HTM[2999]="*na gilānātirittaṃ hoti—**it is not leftover from one who is sick—*";
P_HTM[3000]="*etaṃ anatirittaṃ nāma.**this is called “not leftover”.*";
P_HTM[3001]="*Atirittaṃ nāma**Left over:*";
P_HTM[3002]="*kappiyakataṃ hoti,**the making it leftover is done with food that is allowable;*";
P_HTM[3003]="*paṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,**it is done with food that has been received;*";
P_HTM[3004]="*uccāritakataṃ hoti,**it is done with food that is held in hand;*";
P_HTM[3005]="*hatthapāse kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who is within arm’s reach;*";
P_HTM[3006]="*bhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who has finished his meal;*";
P_HTM[3007]="*bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā avuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who has finished his meal, who has refused an invitation to eat more, and who has not risen from his seat;*";
P_HTM[3008]="*“alametaṃ sabban”ti vuttaṃ hoti,**“I don’t need of any of this,” has been said;*";
P_HTM[3009]="*gilānātirittaṃ hoti—**it is leftover from one who is sick—*";
P_HTM[3010]="*etaṃ atirittaṃ nāma.**this is called “leftover”.*";
P_HTM[3011]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[3012]="*pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[3013]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[3014]="*pañca bhojanāni— odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[3015]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he receives it intending to eat it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3016]="*Anatiritte anatirittasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is not leftover, and he does not perceive it as such, and he eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3017]="*Anatiritte vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is not leftover, but he is unsure of it, and he eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3018]="*Anatiritte atirittasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is not leftover, but he perceives it as such, and he eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3019]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3020]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3021]="*Atiritte anatirittasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is leftover, but he does not perceive it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3022]="*Atiritte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is leftover, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3023]="*Atiritte atirittasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is leftover, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3024]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3025]="*atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjati,**if he eats it after having it made leftover;*";
P_HTM[3026]="*“atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti,**if he receives it with the intention of having it made leftover and then eating it;*";
P_HTM[3027]="*aññassatthāya haranto gacchati,**if he is taking food for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[3028]="*gilānassa sesakaṃ bhuñjati,**if he eats the leftovers from a sick person;*";
P_HTM[3029]="*yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,**if, when there is a reason, he uses post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics;*";
P_HTM[3030]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3031]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3032]="*Pavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on invitations, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3033]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3034]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[3035]="*36. Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpada**36. The second training rule on invitations*";
P_HTM[3036]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3037]="*Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhū kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti.**At that time two monks were traveling through the Kosalan country on their way to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3038]="*Eko bhikkhu anācāraṃ ācarati.**One monk misbehaved*";
P_HTM[3039]="*Dutiyo bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**and the other said to him,*";
P_HTM[3040]="*“māvuso, evarūpamakāsi, netaṃ kappatī”ti.**“Don’t do that! It’s not allowable.”*";
P_HTM[3041]="*So tasmiṃ upanandhi.**Because of that the first monk became resentful.*";
P_HTM[3042]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū sāvatthiṃ agamaṃsu.**They then carried on to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[3043]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghabhattaṃ hoti.**Soon afterwards an association in Sāvatthī was offering a meal to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3044]="*Dutiyo bhikkhu bhuttāvī pavārito hoti.**When the second monk had finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more,*";
P_HTM[3045]="*Upanaddho bhikkhu ñātikulaṃ gantvā piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya yena so bhikkhu tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**the resentful monk brought back some almsfood from his own family. He then said to the other,*";
P_HTM[3046]="*“bhuñjāhi, āvuso”ti.**“Please eat!”*";
P_HTM[3047]="*“Alaṃ, āvuso, paripuṇṇomhī”ti.**“There’s no need. I’m full.”*";
P_HTM[3048]="*“Sundaro, āvuso, piṇḍapāto, bhuñjāhī”ti.**“The almsfood is nice, please eat.”*";
P_HTM[3049]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu tena bhikkhunā nippīḷiyamāno taṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñji.**And because he was pressured, he ate the almsfood.*";
P_HTM[3050]="*Upanaddho bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**The resentful monk then said to him,*";
P_HTM[3051]="*“tvampi nāma, āvuso, maṃ vattabbaṃ maññasi yaṃ tvaṃ bhuttāvī pavārito anatirittaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti.**“Who are you to correct me when you eat food that’s not leftover even though you have finished your meal and refused an invitation to eat more?”*";
P_HTM[3052]="*“Nanu, āvuso, ācikkhitabban”ti.**“Shouldn’t you have told me?”*";
P_HTM[3053]="*“Nanu, āvuso, pucchitabban”ti.**“Shouldn’t you have asked?”*";
P_HTM[3054]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**The second monk told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[3055]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized the other,*";
P_HTM[3056]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāressatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk invite another monk to eat food that’s not leftover, when the other has finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more ?” …*";
P_HTM[3057]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāresī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3058]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3059]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3060]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena bhojanena abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāressasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3061]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3062]="*evañca pana bhikkhave imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3063]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhuttāviṃ pavāritaṃ anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyya—‘handa, bhikkhu, khāda vā bhuñja vā’ti, jānaṃ āsādanāpekkho, bhuttasmiṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk invites a monk, who he knows has finished his meal and refused an invitation to eat more, to eat fresh or cooked food that is not left over, saying, “Here, monk, eat,” aiming to criticize him, then when the other has eaten, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3064]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3065]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3066]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3067]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3068]="*Bhikkhunti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[3069]="*aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ.**another monk.*";
P_HTM[3070]="*Bhuttāvī nāma**Who has finished his meal:*";
P_HTM[3071]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ, antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti.**who has eaten any of the five cooked foods, even what fits on the tip of a blade of grass.*";
P_HTM[3072]="*Pavārito nāma**Refused an invitation to eat more:*";
P_HTM[3073]="*asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhito abhiharati, paṭikkhepo paññāyati.**there is eating; there is cooked food; it is offered by one standing within arm’s reach; there is a refusal.*";
P_HTM[3074]="*Anatirittaṃ nāma**Not left over:*";
P_HTM[3075]="*akappiyakataṃ hoti,**the making it leftover is done with food that is unallowable;*";
P_HTM[3076]="*appaṭiggahitakataṃ hoti,**it is done with food that has not been received;*";
P_HTM[3077]="*anuccāritakataṃ hoti,**it is done with food that is not held in hand;*";
P_HTM[3078]="*ahatthapāse kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who is not within arm’s reach;*";
P_HTM[3079]="*abhuttāvinā kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who has not finished his meal;*";
P_HTM[3080]="*bhuttāvinā pavāritena āsanā vuṭṭhitena kataṃ hoti,**it is done by one who has finished his meal, who has refused an invitation to eat more, but who has risen from his seat;*";
P_HTM[3081]="*“alametaṃ sabban”ti avuttaṃ hoti,**“I don’t need of any of this,” has not been said;*";
P_HTM[3082]="*na gilānātirittaṃ hoti—**it is not leftover from one who is sick—*";
P_HTM[3083]="*etaṃ anatirittaṃ nāma.**this is called “not leftover”.*";
P_HTM[3084]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[3085]="*pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[3086]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[3087]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[3088]="*Abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreyyāti**Invites to eat:*";
P_HTM[3089]="*yāvatakaṃ icchasi tāvatakaṃ gaṇhāhīti.**saying, “Take as much as you like.”*";
P_HTM[3090]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[3091]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the monk has told him.*";
P_HTM[3092]="*Āsādanāpekkhoti**Aiming to criticize him:*";
P_HTM[3093]="*“iminā imaṃ codessāmi sāressāmi paṭicodessāmi paṭisāressāmi maṅkuṃ karissāmī”ti abhiharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he offers it to him, thinking, “With this I’ll accuse him,” “I’ll remind him,” “I’ll counter-accuse him,” “I’ll counter-remind him,” “I’ll humiliate him,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3094]="*Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, because of what he says, the other monk receives it with the intention of eating it, then the donor commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3095]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, the donor commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3096]="*Bhojanapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the other monk has finished eating, the donor commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3097]="*Pavārite pavāritasaññī anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk has refused an invitation to eat more, and the donor perceives that he has, and he invites him to eat fresh or cooked food which is not leftover, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3098]="*Pavārite vematiko anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk has refused an invitation to eat more, but the donor is unsure of it, and he invites him to eat fresh or cooked food which is not leftover, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3099]="*Pavārite appavāritasaññī anatirittena khādanīyena vā bhojanīyena vā abhihaṭṭhuṃ pavāreti, anāpatti.**If the other monk has refused an invitation to eat more, but the donor does not perceive that he has, and he invites him to eat fresh or cooked food which is not leftover, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3100]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya abhiharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he invites him to eat post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3101]="*Tassa vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, because of what he says, the other monk receives it with the intention of eating it, then the donor commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3102]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, the donor commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3103]="*Appavārite pavāritasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk has not refused an invitation to eat more, but the donor perceives that he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3104]="*Appavārite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk has not refused an invitation to eat more, but the donor is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3105]="*Appavārite appavāritasaññī, anāpatti.**If the other monk has not refused an invitation to eat more, and the donor does not perceive that he has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3106]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3107]="*atirittaṃ kārāpetvā deti,**if he gives it after having it made leftover;*";
P_HTM[3108]="*“atirittaṃ kārāpetvā bhuñjāhī”ti deti,**if he gives it, saying, “Have it made leftover and then eat it;”*";
P_HTM[3109]="*aññassatthāya haranto gacchāhīti deti,**if he gives it, saying, “Take this food for the benefit of someone else;”*";
P_HTM[3110]="*gilānassa sesakaṃ deti,**if he gives the leftovers from a sick person;*";
P_HTM[3111]="*“yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjā”ti deti,**if he gives, saying, “When there’s a reason, use these post-midday tonics,” “… use these seven-day tonics,” “… use  these lifetime tonics;”*";
P_HTM[3112]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3113]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3114]="*Dutiyapavāraṇāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The second training rule on invitations, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3115]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3116]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[3117]="*37. Vikālabhojanasikkhāpada**37. The training rule on eating at the wrong time*";
P_HTM[3118]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[3119]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe giraggasamajjo hoti.**At that time in Rājagaha there was a hilltop fair,*";
P_HTM[3120]="*Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū giraggasamajjaṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu.**which the monks from the group of seventeen went to see.*";
P_HTM[3121]="*Manussā sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū passitvā nahāpetvā vilimpetvā bhojetvā khādanīyaṃ adaṃsu.**When people saw the monks, they bathed them, anointed them, fed them cooked food, and gave them fresh food.*";
P_HTM[3122]="*Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū khādanīyaṃ ādāya ārāmaṃ gantvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**They brought that fresh food back to the monastery and said to the monks from the group of six,*";
P_HTM[3123]="*“gaṇhāthāvuso, khādanīyaṃ khādathā”ti.**“Help yourselves!”*";
P_HTM[3124]="*“Kuto tumhehi, āvuso, khādanīyaṃ laddhan”ti?**“But where did you get this food?”*";
P_HTM[3125]="*Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**And they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[3126]="*“Kiṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjathā”ti?**“So, do you eat at the wrong time?”*";
P_HTM[3127]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[3128]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks from the group of six complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[3129]="*“kathañhi nāma sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjissantī”ti.**“How can those monks from the group of seventeen eat at the wrong time?”*";
P_HTM[3130]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the monks,*";
P_HTM[3131]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[3132]="*“kathañhi nāma sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of seventeen eat at the wrong time?” …*";
P_HTM[3133]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[3134]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3135]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[3136]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, vikāle bhojanaṃ bhuñjissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[3137]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3138]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3139]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu vikāle khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats fresh or cooked food at the wrong time, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3140]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3141]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3142]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3143]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3144]="*Vikālo nāma**At the wrong time:*";
P_HTM[3145]="*majjhanhike vītivatte yāva aruṇuggamanā.**when the middle of the day has passed, until dawn.*";
P_HTM[3146]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[3147]="*pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[3148]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[3149]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[3150]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3151]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3152]="*Vikāle vikālasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the wrong time, and he perceives it as such, and he eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3153]="*Vikāle vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the wrong time, but he is unsure of it, and he eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3154]="*Vikāle kālasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the wrong time, but he perceives it as the right time, and he eats fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3155]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3156]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3157]="*Kāle vikālasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is the right time, but he perceives it as the wrong time, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3158]="*Kāle vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is the right time, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3159]="*Kāle kālasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is the right time, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3160]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3161]="*yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,**if, when there is a reason, he uses post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics;*";
P_HTM[3162]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3163]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3164]="*Vikālabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on eating at the wrong time, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3165]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3166]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[3167]="*38. Sannidhikārakasikkhāpada**38. The training rule on storing*";
P_HTM[3168]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3169]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato ānandassa upajjhāyo āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso araññe viharati.**At that time Venerable Belaṭṭhasīsa, Venerable Ānanda’s preceptor, was staying in the wilderness.*";
P_HTM[3170]="*So piṇḍāya caritvā sukkhakuraṃ ārāmaṃ haritvā sukkhāpetvā nikkhipati.**After walking for alms, he brought plain boiled rice back to the monastery, where he dried and stored it.*";
P_HTM[3171]="*Yadā āhārena attho hoti, tadā udakena temetvā temetvā bhuñjati, cirena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisati.**Whenever he got hungry, he moistened and ate it. As a result, he only went the village for alms after a long time.*";
P_HTM[3172]="*Bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ belaṭṭhasīsaṃ etadavocuṃ—**The monks asked him,*";
P_HTM[3173]="*“kissa tvaṃ, āvuso, cirena gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisasī”ti?**“Why do you only go for alms after such a long time?”*";
P_HTM[3174]="*Atha kho āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And he told them.*";
P_HTM[3175]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti?**“But do you eat food that you’ve stored?”*";
P_HTM[3176]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[3177]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[3178]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā belaṭṭhasīso sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjissatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Belaṭṭhasīsa eat food that he has stored?” …*";
P_HTM[3179]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, belaṭṭhasīsa, sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Belaṭṭhasīsa, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[3180]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3181]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3182]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, belaṭṭhasīsa, sannidhikārakaṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjissasi.**“Belaṭṭhasīsa, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[3183]="*Netaṃ, belaṭṭhasīsa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3184]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3185]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu sannidhikārakaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats fresh or cooked food that he has stored, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3186]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3187]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3188]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3189]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3190]="*Sannidhikārakaṃ nāma**That he has stored:*";
P_HTM[3191]="*ajja paṭiggahitaṃ aparajju khāditaṃ hoti.**received today and eaten on the following day.*";
P_HTM[3192]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[3193]="*pañca bhojanāni—yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[3194]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[3195]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[3196]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3197]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3198]="*Sannidhikārake sannidhikārakasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has been stored, and he perceives that it has, and he eats the fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3199]="*Sannidhikārake vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has been stored, but he is unsure of it, and he eats the fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3200]="*Sannidhikārake asannidhikārakasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has been stored, but he does not perceive that it has, and he eats the fresh or cooked food, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3201]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3202]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3203]="*Asannidhikārake sannidhikārakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has not been stored, but he perceives that it has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3204]="*Asannidhikārake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has not been stored, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3205]="*Asannidhikārake asannidhikārakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it has not been stored, and he does not perceive that it has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3206]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3207]="*yāvakālikaṃ yāvakāle nidahitvā bhuñjati,**if he both stores and eats it during the right time;*";
P_HTM[3208]="*yāmakālikaṃ yāme nidahitvā bhuñjati,**if he both stores and eats post-midday tonics during the remainder of the day;*";
P_HTM[3209]="*sattāhakālikaṃ sattāhaṃ nidahitvā bhuñjati,**if he both stores and eats seven-day tonics during the seven-day period;*";
P_HTM[3210]="*yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,**if he uses lifetime tonics when there is a reason;*";
P_HTM[3211]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3212]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3213]="*Sannidhikārakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on storing, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3214]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3215]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[3216]="*39. Paṇītabhojanasikkhāpada**39. The training rule on fine foods*";
P_HTM[3217]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[3218]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**the monks from the group of six ate fine foods that they had requested for themselves.*";
P_HTM[3219]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[3220]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics eat fine foods that they have requested for themselves?*";
P_HTM[3221]="*Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti.**Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t prefer tasty food?”*";
P_HTM[3222]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[3223]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[3224]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six eat fine foods that they have requested for themselves?” …*";
P_HTM[3225]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[3226]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3227]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[3228]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[3229]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3230]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3231]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanāni, seyyathidaṃ— sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ maccho maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhi. Yo pana bhikkhu evarūpāni paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk asks for any of these kinds of fine foods for himself—that is, ghee, butter, oil, honey, syrup, fish, meat, milk, and curd—and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3232]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3233]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti.**At one time a number of monks were sick.*";
P_HTM[3234]="*Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The monks who were looking after them asked,*";
P_HTM[3235]="*“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up? I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[3236]="*“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjāma, tena no phāsu hoti;**“Previously we ate fine foods that we had requested ourselves, and then we were comfortable.*";
P_HTM[3237]="*idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na viññāpema, tena no na phāsu hotī”ti.**But now that the Buddha has prohibited this, we don’t request because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. And because of that we’re not comfortable.”*";
P_HTM[3238]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3239]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[3240]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat fine foods that he has requested for himself.*";
P_HTM[3241]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3242]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanāni, seyyathidaṃ— sappi navanītaṃ telaṃ madhu phāṇitaṃ maccho maṃsaṃ khīraṃ dadhi. Yo pana bhikkhu evarūpāni paṇītabhojanāni agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who is not sick asks for any of these kinds of fine foods for himself—that is, ghee, butter, oil, honey, syrup, fish, meat, milk, and curd—and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3243]="*Yāni kho pana tāni paṇītabhojanānīti**These kinds of fine foods:*";
P_HTM[3244]="*sappi nāma**Ghee:*";
P_HTM[3245]="*gosappi vā ajikāsappi vā mahiṃsasappi vā, yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati tesaṃ sappi.**ghee from cows, ghee from goats, ghee from buffaloes, or ghee from whatever animal whose meat is allowable.*";
P_HTM[3246]="*Navanītaṃ nāma**Butter:*";
P_HTM[3247]="*tesaññeva navanītaṃ.**butter from those same animals.*";
P_HTM[3248]="*Telaṃ nāma**Oil:*";
P_HTM[3249]="*tilatelaṃ sāsapatelaṃ madhukatelaṃ eraṇḍatelaṃ vasātelaṃ.**sesame oil, mustard-seed oil, honey-tree oil, castor oil, oil from fat.*";
P_HTM[3250]="*Madhu nāma**Honey:*";
P_HTM[3251]="*makkhikāmadhu.**honey from bees.*";
P_HTM[3252]="*Phāṇitaṃ nāma**Syrup:*";
P_HTM[3253]="*ucchumhā nibbattaṃ.**from sugarcane.*";
P_HTM[3254]="*Maccho nāma**Fish:*";
P_HTM[3255]="*udako vuccati.**what lives in water is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[3256]="*Maṃsaṃ nāma**Meat:*";
P_HTM[3257]="*yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati, tesaṃ maṃsaṃ.**the meat of those animals whose meat is allowable.*";
P_HTM[3258]="*Khīraṃ nāma**Milk:*";
P_HTM[3259]="*gokhīraṃ vā ajikākhīraṃ vā mahiṃsakhīraṃ vā, yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati, tesaṃ khīraṃ.**milk from cows, milk from goats, milk from buffaloes, or milk from whatever animal whose meat is allowable.*";
P_HTM[3260]="*Dadhi nāma**Curd:*";
P_HTM[3261]="*tesaññeva dadhi.**curd from those same animals.*";
P_HTM[3262]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3263]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3264]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3265]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3266]="*Evarūpāni paṇītabhojanānīti**Any of these kinds of fine foods:*";
P_HTM[3267]="*tathārūpāni paṇītabhojanāni.**such kinds of fine foods.*";
P_HTM[3268]="*Agilāno nāma**Who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[3269]="*yassa vinā paṇītabhojanāni phāsu hoti.**who is comfortable without fine foods.*";
P_HTM[3270]="*Gilāno nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[3271]="*yassa vinā paṇītabhojanāni na phāsu hoti.**who is not comfortable without fine foods.*";
P_HTM[3272]="*Agilāno attano atthāya viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**If he is not sick and he requests for himself, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3273]="*Paṭilābhena “bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When he receives it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3274]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3275]="*Agilāno agilānasaññī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, and he does not perceive himself as sick, and he eats fine foods that he has requested for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3276]="*Agilāno vematiko paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he eats fine foods that he has requested for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3277]="*Agilāno gilānasaññī paṇītabhojanāni attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he eats fine foods that he has requested for himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3278]="*Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is sick, but he does not perceive himself as sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3279]="*Gilāno vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is sick, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3280]="*Gilāno gilānasaññī anāpatti.**If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3281]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3282]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[3283]="*gilāno hutvā viññāpetvā agilāno bhuñjati,**if he asked for it when he was sick, but eats it when he is no longer sick;*";
P_HTM[3284]="*gilānassa sesakaṃ bhuñjati,**if he eats the leftovers from one who is sick;*";
P_HTM[3285]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[3286]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[3287]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[3288]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[3289]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3290]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3291]="*Paṇītabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on fine foods, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3292]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3293]="*Bhojanavagga**The sub-chapter on eating*";
P_HTM[3294]="*40. Dantaponasikkhāpada**40. The training rule on tooth cleaners*";
P_HTM[3295]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood near Vesālī.*";
P_HTM[3296]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sabbapaṃsukūliko susāne viharati.**At that time a monk who only used discarded things was staying in a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[3297]="*So manussehi diyyamānaṃ na icchati paṭiggahetuṃ, susānepi rukkhamūlepi ummārepi ayyavosāṭitakāni sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjati.**He disliked receiving things from people. Instead he would take whatever was offered to the dead at the charnel ground, at the foot of trees, or at the threshold, and he would use that.*";
P_HTM[3298]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[3299]="*“kathañhi nāma ayaṃ bhikkhu amhākaṃ ayyavosāṭitakāni sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjissati.**“How can this monk take the offerings to our ancestors and use them?*";
P_HTM[3300]="*Theroyaṃ bhikkhu vaṭharo manussamaṃsaṃ maññe khādatī”ti.**This monk is big and strong. One might even suspect him of eating human flesh!”*";
P_HTM[3301]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[3302]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[3303]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharissatī”ti …pe…**“How can this monk eat food that hasn’t been given?” …*";
P_HTM[3304]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharasī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[3305]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3306]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3307]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āharissasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[3308]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3309]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3310]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats food that has not been given, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3311]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3312]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū udakadantapone kukkuccāyanti.**Soon afterwards the monks did not use water or tooth cleaners because they were afraid of wrongdoing.*";
P_HTM[3313]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[3314]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, udakadantaponaṃ sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to use water and tooth cleaners after taking them yourselves.*";
P_HTM[3315]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3316]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhareyya, aññatra udakadantaponā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eats food that has not been given, except for water and tooth cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3317]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3318]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3319]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3320]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3321]="*Adinnaṃ nāma**That has not been given:*";
P_HTM[3322]="*appaṭiggahitakaṃ vuccati.**what has not been received is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[3323]="*Dinnaṃ nāma**Given:*";
P_HTM[3324]="*kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā dente hatthapāse ṭhito kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā paṭiggaṇhāti, etaṃ dinnaṃ nāma.**standing within arm’s reach of one giving by body or by what is connected to his body or by releasing, he receives it by body or by what is connected to his body—this is called “given”.*";
P_HTM[3325]="*Āhāro nāma**Food:*";
P_HTM[3326]="*udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā yaṃ kiñci ajjhoharaṇīyaṃ, eso āhāro nāma.**whatever is edible, apart from water and tooth cleaners—this is called “food”.*";
P_HTM[3327]="*Aññatra udakadantaponāti**Except for water and tooth cleaners:*";
P_HTM[3328]="*ṭhapetvā udakadantaponaṃ.**apart from water and tooth cleaners.*";
P_HTM[3329]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti gaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he takes it with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3330]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3331]="*Appaṭiggahitake appaṭiggahitakasaññī adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been received, and he does not perceive it as such, and he eats it, except for water and tooth cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3332]="*Appaṭiggahitake vematiko adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been received, but he is unsure of it, and he eats it, except for water and tooth cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3333]="*Appaṭiggahitake paṭiggahitakasaññī adinnaṃ mukhadvāraṃ āhāraṃ āhāreti, aññatra udakadantaponā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been not received, but he perceives it as such, and he eats it, except for water and tooth cleaners, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3334]="*Paṭiggahitake appaṭiggahitakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been received, but he does not perceive it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3335]="*Paṭiggahitake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been received, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3336]="*Paṭiggahitake paṭiggahitakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it has been received, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3337]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3338]="*udakadantapone,**if it is water or tooth cleaners;*";
P_HTM[3339]="*cattāri mahāvikaṭāni sati paccaye asati kappiyakārake sāmaṃ gahetvā paribhuñjati,**if, when there is a reason, but there is no attendant, he himself takes the four filthy edibles and eats them;*";
P_HTM[3340]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3341]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3342]="*Dantaponasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on tooth cleaners, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3343]="*Bhojanavaggo catuttho.**The fourth sub-chapter on eating is finished.*";
P_HTM[3344]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[3345]="*Piṇḍo gaṇaṃ paraṃ pūvaṃ,**Alms, group, another, pastry,*";
P_HTM[3346]="*dve ca vuttā pavāraṇā;**And two are spoken on invitations;*";
P_HTM[3347]="*Vikāle sannidhī khīraṃ,**At the wrong time, store, milk,*";
P_HTM[3348]="*dantaponena te dasāti.**And with tooth cleaner—those are the ten.*";
P_HTM[3349]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3350]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3351]="*41. Acelakasikkhāpada**41. The training rule on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3352]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood near Vesālī,*";
P_HTM[3353]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa khādanīyaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**the Sangha had an abundance of fresh food.*";
P_HTM[3354]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi. “Tenahānanda, vighāsādānaṃ pūvaṃ dehī”ti.**Venerable Ānanda told the Buddha, who said, “Well then, Ānanda, give the pastries to those who take leftovers.”*";
P_HTM[3355]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā vighāsāde paṭipāṭiyā nisīdāpetvā ekekaṃ pūvaṃ dento aññatarissā paribbājikāya ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsi.**“Yes, Sir.” Ānanda had them sit in a row and gave them one pastry each, until he accidentally gave two to a female wanderer.*";
P_HTM[3356]="*Sāmantā paribbājikāyo taṃ paribbājikaṃ etadavocuṃ—“jāro te eso samaṇo”ti.**The female wanderers sitting next to her said to her, “This monastic is your lover.”*";
P_HTM[3357]="*“Na me so samaṇo jāro, ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsī”ti.**“He’s not. He gave me two, thinking they were one.”*";
P_HTM[3358]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**And a second time …*";
P_HTM[3359]="*tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando ekekaṃ pūvaṃ dento tassāyeva paribbājikāya ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsi.**And a third time Ānanda gave them one pastry each, until he accidentally gave two to that same female wanderer.*";
P_HTM[3360]="*Sāmantā paribbājikāyo taṃ paribbājikaṃ etadavocuṃ—“jāro te eso samaṇo”ti.**Once again the female wanderers sitting next to her said to her, “This monastic is your lover.”*";
P_HTM[3361]="*“Na me so samaṇo jāro, ekaṃ maññamāno dve pūve adāsī”ti.**“He’s not. He gave me two, thinking they were one.”*";
P_HTM[3362]="*“Jāro na jāro”ti bhaṇḍiṃsu.**And they started to argue about whether or not they were lovers.*";
P_HTM[3363]="*Aññataropi ājīvako parivesanaṃ agamāsi.**A certain Ājīvaka ascetic, too, went to that distribution of food.*";
P_HTM[3364]="*Aññataro bhikkhu pahūtena sappinā odanaṃ madditvā tassa ājīvakassa mahantaṃ piṇḍaṃ adāsi.**A monk mixed rice with a large amount of ghee and gave him a large lump.*";
P_HTM[3365]="*Atha kho so ājīvako taṃ piṇḍaṃ ādāya agamāsi.**He took it and left.*";
P_HTM[3366]="*Aññataro ājīvako taṃ ājīvakaṃ etadavoca—“kuto tayā, āvuso, piṇḍo laddho”ti?**Another Ājīvaka asked him, “Where did you get that lump?”*";
P_HTM[3367]="*“Tassāvuso, samaṇassa gotamassa muṇḍagahapatikassa parivesanāya laddho”ti.**“From the food distribution of the ascetic Gotama, that shaven-headed householder.”*";
P_HTM[3368]="*Assosuṃ kho upāsakā tesaṃ ājīvakānaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ.**Some lay followers overheard that conversation between those Ājīvaka ascetics.*";
P_HTM[3369]="*Atha kho te upāsakā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdiṃsu. Ekamantaṃ nisinnā kho te upāsakā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**They then went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down, and said,*";
P_HTM[3370]="*“ime, bhante, titthiyā avaṇṇakāmā buddhassa avaṇṇakāmā dhammassa avaṇṇakāmā saṅghassa.**“Venerable Sir, these monastics of other religions want to disparage the Buddha, the Teaching, and the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3371]="*Sādhu, bhante, ayyā titthiyānaṃ sahatthā na dadeyyun”ti.**It would be good if the monks didn’t give anything to the monastics of other religions with their own hands.”*";
P_HTM[3372]="*Atha kho bhagavā te upāsake dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. Atha kho te upāsakā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkamiṃsu.**After the Buddha had instructed, inspired, and gladdened those lay followers with a teaching, they got up from their seats, bowed down, circumambulated him with their right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[3373]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[3374]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[3375]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya, saṅghaphāsutāya …pe… saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya.**for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[3376]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3377]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu acelakassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives fresh or cooked food to a naked ascetic, to a male wanderer, or to a female wanderer with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3378]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3379]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3380]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3381]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3382]="*Acelako nāma**A naked ascetic:*";
P_HTM[3383]="*yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno naggo.**any wanderer who is naked.*";
P_HTM[3384]="*Paribbājako nāma**A male wanderer:*";
P_HTM[3385]="*bhikkhuñca sāmaṇerañca ṭhapetvā yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno.**any male wanderer apart from Buddhist monks and novice monks.*";
P_HTM[3386]="*Paribbājikā nāma**A female wanderer:*";
P_HTM[3387]="*bhikkhuniñca sikkhamānañca sāmaṇeriñca ṭhapetvā yā kāci paribbājikasamāpannā.**any female wanderer apart from Buddhist nuns, trainee nuns, and novice nuns.*";
P_HTM[3388]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[3389]="*pañca bhojanāni—udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, water, and tooth cleaners, the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[3390]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[3391]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[3392]="*Dadeyyāti**Gives:*";
P_HTM[3393]="*kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he gives by body or by what is connected to the body or by releasing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3394]="*Titthiye titthiyasaññī sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a monastic of another religion, and he perceives them as such, and he gives them fresh or cooked food with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3395]="*Titthiye vematiko sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a monastic of another religion, but he is unsure of it, and he gives them fresh or cooked food with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3396]="*Titthiye atitthiyasaññī sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a monastic of another religion, but he does not perceive them as such, and he gives them fresh or cooked food with his own hands, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3397]="*Udakadantaponaṃ deti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gives water or a tooth cleaner, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3398]="*Atitthiye titthiyasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a monastic of another religion, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3399]="*Atitthiye vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a monastic of another religion, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3400]="*Atitthiye atitthiyasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a monastic of another religion, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3401]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3402]="*dāpeti na deti,**if he does not give, but has it given;*";
P_HTM[3403]="*upanikkhipitvā deti,**if he gives by placing it near the person;*";
P_HTM[3404]="*bāhirālepaṃ deti,**if he gives ointments for external use;*";
P_HTM[3405]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3406]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3407]="*Acelakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on naked ascetics, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3408]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3409]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3410]="*42. Uyyojanasikkhāpada**42. The training rule on sending away*";
P_HTM[3411]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3412]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhātuno saddhivihārikaṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan said to his brother’s student,*";
P_HTM[3413]="*“ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti.**“Come, let’s go to the village for alms.”*";
P_HTM[3414]="*Tassa adāpetvā uyyojesi—**Then, without getting him any food, he sent him away, saying,*";
P_HTM[3415]="*“gacchāvuso, na me tayā saddhiṃ kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hoti, ekakassa me kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hotī”ti.**“Go away! I’m not comfortable talking or sitting with you, but only if I talk and sit by myself.”*";
P_HTM[3416]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu upakaṭṭhe kāle nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ, paṭikkamanepi bhattavissaggaṃ na sambhāvesi, chinnabhatto ahosi.**But since the right time for eating was coming to an end, he was unable to walk for alms. And as he returned to the monastery, there was nobody offering food, and so he missed his meal.*";
P_HTM[3417]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He then went to the monastery and told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[3418]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3419]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti tassa adāpetvā uyyojessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Upananda say to a monk, ‘Come, let’s go to the village for alms,’ and then send him away without getting him any food?” …*";
P_HTM[3420]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti tassa adāpetvā uyyojesī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3421]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3422]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3423]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhuṃ—“ehāvuso, gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pavisissāmā”ti tassa adāpetvā uyyojessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3424]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3425]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3426]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ—‘ehāvuso, gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vā piṇḍāya pavisissāmā’ti tassa dāpetvā vā adāpetvā vā uyyojeyya— ‘gacchāvuso, na me tayā saddhiṃ kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hoti, ekakassa me kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hotī’ti, etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk says to a monk, “Come, let’s go to the village or town for alms,” and then, whether he has had food given to him or not, sends him away, saying, “Go away, I’m not comfortable talking or sitting with you, but only if I talk and sit by myself,” and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3427]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3428]="*yo, yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3429]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3430]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3431]="*Bhikkhunti**To a monk:*";
P_HTM[3432]="*aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ.**to another monk.*";
P_HTM[3433]="*Ehāvuso, gāmaṃ vā nigamaṃ vāti**Come … to the village or town:*";
P_HTM[3434]="*gāmopi nigamopi nagarampi, gāmo ceva nigamo ca.**a village, also a town, also a city; both a village and a town.*";
P_HTM[3435]="*Tassa dāpetvāti**He has had food given to him:*";
P_HTM[3436]="*yāguṃ vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dāpetvā.**he has had rice porridge, a meal, fresh food, or cooked food given to him.*";
P_HTM[3437]="*Adāpetvāti**Not:*";
P_HTM[3438]="*na kiñci dāpetvā.**he has not had anything given to him.*";
P_HTM[3439]="*Uyyojeyyāti**Sends away:*";
P_HTM[3440]="*mātugāmena saddhiṃ hasitukāmo kīḷitukāmo raho nisīditukāmo anācāraṃ ācaritukāmo evaṃ vadeti— “gacchāvuso, na me tayā saddhiṃ kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hoti, ekakassa me kathā vā nisajjā vā phāsu hotī”ti uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if, wanting to laugh with a woman, wanting to enjoy himself with her, wanting to sit down in private with her, wanting to misbehave with her, he says, “Go away! I’m not comfortable talking or sitting with you, but only if I talk and sit by myself,” and he sends him away, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3441]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vā savanūpacāraṃ vā vijahantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk is in the process of going beyond the range of sight or the range of hearing, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3442]="*Vijahite, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the other monk has gone beyond, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3443]="*Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññanti**He does so only for this reason and no other:*";
P_HTM[3444]="*na añño koci paccayo hoti uyyojetuṃ.**there is no other reason for sending him away.*";
P_HTM[3445]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī uyyojeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he sends him away, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3446]="*Upasampanne vematiko uyyojeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he sends him away, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3447]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī uyyojeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he sends him away, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3448]="*Kalisāsanaṃ āropeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts him down, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3449]="*Anupasampannaṃ uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sends away one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3450]="*Kalisāsanaṃ āropeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts him down, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3451]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3452]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3453]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3454]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3455]="*“ubho ekato na yāpessāmā”ti uyyojeti,**if he sends him away, thinking, “Together we won’t get enough;”*";
P_HTM[3456]="*“mahagghaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ passitvā lobhadhammaṃ uppādessatī”ti uyyojeti,**if he sends him away, thinking, “If he sees these valuable goods, he’ll become greedy;”*";
P_HTM[3457]="*“mātugāmaṃ passitvā anabhiratiṃ uppādessatī”ti uyyojeti,**if he sends him away, thinking, “If he sees this woman, he’ll become lustful;”*";
P_HTM[3458]="*“gilānassa vā ohiyyakassa vā vihārapālassa vā yāguṃ vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā nīharā”ti uyyojeti,**if he sends him away, saying, “Take rice porridge or a meal or fresh food or cooked food to the one who is sick or to the one who is left behind or to the one who is guarding the dwellings;”*";
P_HTM[3459]="*na anācāraṃ ācaritukāmo,**if he does not want to misbehave;*";
P_HTM[3460]="*sati karaṇīye uyyojeti,**if he sends him away when there is something to be done;*";
P_HTM[3461]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3462]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3463]="*Uyyojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on sending away, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3464]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3465]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3466]="*43. Sabhojanasikkhāpada**43. The training rule on lustful*";
P_HTM[3467]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3468]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sahāyakassa gharaṃ gantvā tassa pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ sayanighare nisajjaṃ kappesi.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan went to the house of a friend and sat down with his wife in their bedroom.*";
P_HTM[3469]="*Atha kho so puriso yenāyasmā upanando sakyaputto tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**The husband approached Upananda, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[3470]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho so puriso pajāpatiṃ etadavoca—“dadehāyyassa bhikkhan”ti.**He then said to his wife, “Please give him alms.”*";
P_HTM[3471]="*Atha kho sā itthī āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa bhikkhaṃ adāsi.**And she did so.*";
P_HTM[3472]="*Atha kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—“gacchatha, bhante, yato ayyassa bhikkhā dinnā”ti.**Soon afterwards he said, “Please leave, Sir, the alms have been given.”*";
P_HTM[3473]="*Atha kho sā itthī sallakkhetvā—“pariyuṭṭhito ayaṃ puriso”ti, āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—“nisīdatha, bhante, mā agamitthā”ti.**But the woman, knowing that her husband was lustful, said, “Please sit, Sir, don’t go.”*";
P_HTM[3474]="*Dutiyampi kho so puriso …pe…**A second time and*";
P_HTM[3475]="*tatiyampi kho so puriso āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—“gacchatha, bhante, yato ayyassa bhikkhā dinnā”ti.**a third time he repeated his request,*";
P_HTM[3476]="*Tatiyampi kho sā itthī āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ etadavoca—“nisīdatha, bhante, mā agamitthā”ti.**and both times his wife repeated hers.*";
P_HTM[3477]="*Atha kho so puriso nikkhamitvā bhikkhū ujjhāpesi—**He then left the house and complained to the monks,*";
P_HTM[3478]="*“ayaṃ, bhante, ayyo upanando mayhaṃ pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ sayanighare nisinno.**“Venerables, Venerable Upananda is seated with my wife in our bedroom.*";
P_HTM[3479]="*So mayā uyyojīyamāno na icchati gantuṃ.**When I ask him to leave because we’re busy, he doesn’t want to go.”*";
P_HTM[3480]="*Bahukiccā mayaṃ bahukaraṇīyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3481]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3482]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Upananda sit down intruding on a lustful couple?” …*";
P_HTM[3483]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3484]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3485]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3486]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3487]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3488]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3489]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk sits down intruding on a lustful couple, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3490]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3491]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3492]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3493]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3494]="*Sabhojanaṃ nāma kulaṃ**A lustful couple:*";
P_HTM[3495]="*itthī ceva hoti puriso ca, itthī ca puriso ca ubho anikkhantā honti, ubho avītarāgā.**both a woman and a man are present. The woman and the man have not both left, and both are not without lust.*";
P_HTM[3496]="*Anupakhajjāti**Intruding on:*";
P_HTM[3497]="*anupavisitvā.**enters after.*";
P_HTM[3498]="*Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[3499]="*mahallake ghare piṭṭhasaṅghāṭassa hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā nisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**in a large house, if he sits down more than one arm’s reach inside the door frame, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3500]="*Khuddake ghare piṭṭhivaṃsaṃ atikkamitvā nisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**In a small house, if he sits down beyond the ridge beam, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3501]="*Sayanighare sayanigharasaññī sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a bedroom, and he perceives it as such, and he sits down intruding on a lustful couple, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3502]="*Sayanighare vematiko sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a bedroom, but he is unsure of it, and he sits down intruding on a lustful couple, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3503]="*Sayanighare nasayanigharasaññī sabhojane kule anupakhajja nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a bedroom, but he does not perceive it as such, and he sits down intruding on a lustful couple, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3504]="*Nasayanighare sayanigharasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a bedroom, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3505]="*Nasayanighare vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a bedroom, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3506]="*Nasayanighare nasayanigharasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a bedroom, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3507]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3508]="*mahallake ghare piṭṭhasaṅghāṭassa hatthapāsaṃ avijahitvā nisīdati,**if, in a large house, he sits down, but not more one arm’s reach inside the door frame;*";
P_HTM[3509]="*khuddake ghare piṭṭhivaṃsaṃ anatikkamitvā nisīdati,**if, in a small house, he sits down, but not beyond the ridge beam;*";
P_HTM[3510]="*bhikkhu dutiyo hoti,**if he has a companion monk;*";
P_HTM[3511]="*ubho nikkhantā honti,**if both have left;*";
P_HTM[3512]="*ubho vītarāgā,**if both are without lust;*";
P_HTM[3513]="*nasayanighare,**if it is not a bedroom;*";
P_HTM[3514]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3515]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3516]="*Sabhojanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on lustful, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3517]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3518]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3519]="*44. Rahopaṭicchannasikkhāpada**44. The training rule on private and concealed*";
P_HTM[3520]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3521]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sahāyakassa gharaṃ gantvā tassa pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappesi.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan went to the house of a friend and sat down with his wife in private on a concealed seat.*";
P_HTM[3522]="*Atha kho so puriso ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**The husband complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[3523]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayhaṃ pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Upananda sit with my wife in private on a concealed seat?”*";
P_HTM[3524]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that man,*";
P_HTM[3525]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3526]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Upananda sit in private on a concealed seat with a woman?” …*";
P_HTM[3527]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3528]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3529]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3530]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3531]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3532]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3533]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk sits down in private on a concealed seat with a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3534]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3535]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3536]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3537]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3538]="*Mātugāmo nāma**A woman:*";
P_HTM[3539]="*manussitthī, na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā, antamaso tadahujātāpi dārikā, pageva mahattarī.**a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal; even a girl born on that very day, let alone an older one.*";
P_HTM[3540]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[3541]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[3542]="*Raho nāma**In private:*";
P_HTM[3543]="*cakkhussa raho sotassa raho.**there is private to the eye and there is private to the ear.*";
P_HTM[3544]="*Cakkhussa raho nāma**Private to the eye:*";
P_HTM[3545]="*na sakkā hoti akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇīyamāne bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne sīsaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne passituṃ.**one is unable to see them winking, raising an eyebrow, or nodding.*";
P_HTM[3546]="*Sotassa raho nāma**Private to the ear:*";
P_HTM[3547]="*na sakkā hoti pakatikathā sotuṃ.**one is unable to hear ordinary speech.*";
P_HTM[3548]="*Paṭicchannaṃ nāma āsanaṃ**A concealed seat:*";
P_HTM[3549]="*kuṭṭena vā kavāṭena vā kilañjena vā sāṇipākārena vā rukkhena vā thambhena vā kotthaḷiyā vā, yena kenaci paṭicchannaṃ hoti.**it is concealed by a wall, a screen, a door, a cloth screen, a tree, a pillar, a grain container, or anything else.*";
P_HTM[3550]="*Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[3551]="*mātugāme nisinne bhikkhu upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the monk sits down or lies down next to the seated woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3552]="*Bhikkhu nisinne mātugāmo upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the woman sits down or lies down next to the seated monk, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3553]="*Ubho vā nisinnā honti ubho vā nipannā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If both are seated or both are lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3554]="*Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, and he perceives her as such, and he sits down in private on a concealed seat with her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3555]="*Mātugāme vematiko raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he is unsure of it, and he sits down in private on a concealed seat with her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3556]="*Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as such, and he sits down in private on a concealed seat with her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3557]="*Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatāya vā manussaviggahitthiyā vā saddhiṃ raho paṭicchanne āsane nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sits down in private on a concealed seat with a female spirit, a female ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a female animal in form of a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3558]="*Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3559]="*Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3560]="*Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3561]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3562]="*yo koci viññū puriso dutiyo hoti,**if he has a male companion who understands;*";
P_HTM[3563]="*tiṭṭhati na nisīdati,**if he stands and does not sit down;*";
P_HTM[3564]="*arahopekkho,**if he is not seeking privacy;*";
P_HTM[3565]="*aññavihito nisīdati,**if he sits down preoccupied with something else;*";
P_HTM[3566]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3567]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3568]="*Rahopaṭicchannasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on private and concealed, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3569]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3570]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3571]="*45. Rahonisajjasikkhāpada**45. The training rule on sitting down in private*";
P_HTM[3572]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3573]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sahāyakassa gharaṃ gantvā tassa pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesi.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan went to the house of a friend and sat down in private alone with his wife.*";
P_HTM[3574]="*Atha kho so puriso ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**The husband complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[3575]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyo upanando mayhaṃ pajāpatiyā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Upananda sit down in private alone with my wife?”*";
P_HTM[3576]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa purisassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that man,*";
P_HTM[3577]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3578]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Upananda sit down in private alone with a woman?” …*";
P_HTM[3579]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappesī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3580]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3581]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3582]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3583]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pāsādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3584]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3585]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk sits down in private alone with a woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3586]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3587]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3588]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3589]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3590]="*Mātugāmo nāma**A woman:*";
P_HTM[3591]="*manussitthī, na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā, viññū paṭibalā subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ.**a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal. She understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is decent and what is indecent.*";
P_HTM[3592]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[3593]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[3594]="*Eko ekāyāti**Alone:*";
P_HTM[3595]="*bhikkhu ceva hoti mātugāmo ca.**just the monk and the woman.*";
P_HTM[3596]="*Raho nāma**In private:*";
P_HTM[3597]="*cakkhussa raho, sotassa raho.**there is private to the eye and there is private to the ear.*";
P_HTM[3598]="*Cakkhussa raho nāma**Private to the eye:*";
P_HTM[3599]="*na sakkā hoti akkhiṃ vā nikhaṇīyamāne bhamukaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne sīsaṃ vā ukkhipīyamāne passituṃ.**one is unable to see them winking, raising an eyebrow, or nodding.*";
P_HTM[3600]="*Sotassa raho nāma**Private to the ear:*";
P_HTM[3601]="*na sakkā hoti pakatikathā sotuṃ.**one is unable to hear ordinary speech.*";
P_HTM[3602]="*Nisajjaṃ kappeyyāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[3603]="*mātugāme nisinne bhikkhu upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the monk sits down or lies down next to the seated woman, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3604]="*Bhikkhu nisinne mātugāmo upanisinno vā hoti upanipanno vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the woman sits down or lies down next to the seated monk, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3605]="*Ubho vā nisinnā honti ubho vā nipannā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If both are seated or both are lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3606]="*Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, and he perceives her as such, and he sits down in private alone with her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3607]="*Mātugāme vematiko eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he is unsure of it, and he sits down in private alone with her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3608]="*Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as such, and he sits down in private alone with her, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3609]="*Yakkhiyā vā petiyā vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā saddhiṃ eko ekāya raho nisajjaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he sits down in private alone with a female spirit, with a female ghost, with a _paṇḍaka_, or with a female animal in the form of a woman, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3610]="*Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3611]="*Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3612]="*Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3613]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3614]="*yo koci viññū puriso dutiyo hoti,**if he has a male companion who understands;*";
P_HTM[3615]="*tiṭṭhati na nisīdati,**if he stands and does not sit down;*";
P_HTM[3616]="*arahopekkho**if he is not seeking privacy;*";
P_HTM[3617]="*aññavihito nisīdati,**if he sits down preoccupied with something else;*";
P_HTM[3618]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3619]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3620]="*Rahonisajjasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on sitting in private, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3621]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3622]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3623]="*46. Cārittasikkhāpada**46. The training rule on visiting*";
P_HTM[3624]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[3625]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ bhattena nimantesi.**At that time a family that was supporting Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had invited him to a meal,*";
P_HTM[3626]="*Aññepi bhikkhū bhattena nimantesi.**and they had invited other monks too.*";
P_HTM[3627]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto purebhattaṃ, kulāni payirupāsati.**But since Upananda was visiting other families before that meal,*";
P_HTM[3628]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—**the other monks said to that family,*";
P_HTM[3629]="*“dethāvuso, bhattan”ti.**“Please give the meal.”*";
P_HTM[3630]="*“Āgametha, bhante, yāvāyyo upanando āgacchatī”ti.**“Please wait, Sirs, until Venerable Upananda arrives.”*";
P_HTM[3631]="*Dutiyampi kho te bhikkhū …pe…**A second time …*";
P_HTM[3632]="*tatiyampi kho te bhikkhū te manusse etadavocuṃ—**A third time those monks said,*";
P_HTM[3633]="*“dethāvuso, bhattaṃ; pure kālo atikkamatī”ti.**“Please give the meal before it is too late.”*";
P_HTM[3634]="*“Yampi mayaṃ, bhante, bhattaṃ karimhā ayyassa upanandassa kāraṇā.**“But we prepared the meal because of Venerable Upananda.*";
P_HTM[3635]="*Āgametha, bhante, yāvāyyo upanando āgacchatī”ti.**Please wait until he arrives.”*";
P_HTM[3636]="*Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto purebhattaṃ kulāni payirupāsitvā divā āgacchati.**Then, after visiting those families, Upananda arrived late,*";
P_HTM[3637]="*Bhikkhū na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjiṃsu.**and those monks did not eat as much as they had intended.*";
P_HTM[3638]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3639]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Upananda visit families first when invited to a meal?” …*";
P_HTM[3640]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[3641]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3642]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3643]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[3644]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3645]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3646]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3647]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3648]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa upaṭṭhākakulaṃ saṅghassatthāya khādanīyaṃ pāhesi—**Soon afterwards a family that was supporting Upananda sent fresh food to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3649]="*“ayyassa upanandassa dassetvā saṅghassa dātabban”ti.**They instructed that the food should be shown to Upananda and then given to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[3650]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho hoti.**But on that occasion Upananda had entered the village for alms.*";
P_HTM[3651]="*Atha kho te manussā ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhū pucchiṃsu—**When those people arrived at the monastery,*";
P_HTM[3652]="*“kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo upanando”ti?**they asked for Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3653]="*“Esāvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto gāmaṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭho”ti.**and they were told where he was.*";
P_HTM[3654]="*“Idaṃ, bhante, khādanīyaṃ ayyassa upanandassa dassetvā saṅghassa dātabban”ti.**They said, “Venerables, after showing it to Venerable Upananda, this fresh food is to be given to the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[3655]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The monks told the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[3656]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**who then gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[3657]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, paṭiggahetvā nikkhipatha yāva upanando āgacchatī”ti.**“Well then, monks, receive it and put it aside until Upananda returns.”*";
P_HTM[3658]="*Atha kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto—“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ purebhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjitun”ti pacchābhattaṃ kulāni payirupāsitvā divā paṭikkami, khādanīyaṃ ussāriyittha.**When he heard that the Buddha had prohibited visiting families before the meal, Upananda visited them after the meal instead. As a consequence, he returned late to the monastery, and the food had to be returned to the donors.*";
P_HTM[3659]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[3660]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Upananda visit families after the meal?” …*";
P_HTM[3661]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[3662]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3663]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[3664]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, pacchābhattaṃ kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjissasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[3665]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3666]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3667]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3668]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3669]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvaradānasamaye kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti.**Soon afterwards it was the robe-giving season. But being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not visit families.*";
P_HTM[3670]="*Cīvaraṃ parittaṃ uppajjati.**As a result, they only got a small amount of robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[3671]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[3672]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvaradānasamaye kulāni payirupāsituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to visit families during the robe-giving season.*";
P_HTM[3673]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3674]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3675]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Cīvaradānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**This is the appropriate occasion: it is the robe-giving season.’”*";
P_HTM[3676]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3677]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū cīvarakammaṃ karonti, attho ca hoti sūciyāpi suttenapi satthakenapi.**Soon afterwards the monks were making robes, and they needed a needle, thread, and scissors.*";
P_HTM[3678]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti.**But being afraid of wrongdoing, they did not visit families.*";
P_HTM[3679]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[3680]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, cīvarakārasamaye kulāni payirupāsituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to visit families at a time of making robes.*";
P_HTM[3681]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3682]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3683]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes.’”*";
P_HTM[3684]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3685]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti, attho ca hoti bhesajjehi.**Soon afterwards there were sick monks who needed medicines.*";
P_HTM[3686]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā kulāni na payirupāsanti.**But being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not visit families.*";
P_HTM[3687]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[3688]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā kulāni payirupāsituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to visit families after taking leave of an available monk.*";
P_HTM[3689]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3690]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu nimantito sabhatto samāno santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk who has been invited to a meal visits families beforehand or afterwards without taking leave of an available monk, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3691]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Cīvaradānasamayo, cīvarakārasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: it is the robe-giving season; it is a time of making robes.’”*";
P_HTM[3692]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3693]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3694]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3695]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3696]="*Nimantito nāma**Invited:*";
P_HTM[3697]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantito.**invited to eat any of the five cooked foods.*";
P_HTM[3698]="*Sabhatto nāma**To a meal:*";
P_HTM[3699]="*yena nimantito tena sabhatto.**the invitation includes a meal.*";
P_HTM[3700]="*Santaṃ nāma bhikkhuṃ**An available monk:*";
P_HTM[3701]="*sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ.**he is able to take leave and then enter.*";
P_HTM[3702]="*Asantaṃ nāma bhikkhuṃ**No available monk:*";
P_HTM[3703]="*na sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ.**he is not able to take leave and then enter.*";
P_HTM[3704]="*Purebhattaṃ nāma**Beforehand:*";
P_HTM[3705]="*yena nimantito taṃ abhuttāvī.**he has not yet eaten what he has been invited to eat.*";
P_HTM[3706]="*Pacchābhattaṃ nāma**Afterwards:*";
P_HTM[3707]="*yena nimantito taṃ antamaso kusaggenapi bhuttaṃ hoti.**even if he has just eaten what fits on the tip of a blade of grass from what he has been invited to eat.*";
P_HTM[3708]="*Kulaṃ nāma**A family:*";
P_HTM[3709]="*cattāri kulāni— khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ.**there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[3710]="*Kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjeyyāti**Visits families:*";
P_HTM[3711]="*aññassa gharūpacāraṃ okkamantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he enters the vicinity of someone else’s house, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3712]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ ummāraṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he crosses the threshold with the first foot, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3713]="*Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he crosses the threshold with the second foot, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3714]="*Aññatra samayāti**Except on an appropriate occasion:*";
P_HTM[3715]="*ṭhapetvā samayaṃ.**unless it is an appropriate occasion.*";
P_HTM[3716]="*Cīvaradānasamayo nāma**It is the robe-giving season:*";
P_HTM[3717]="*anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā.**for one who has not participated in the robe-making procedure, it is the last month of the rainy season. For one who has participated in the robe-making procedure, it is the five-month period.*";
P_HTM[3718]="*Cīvarakārasamayo nāma**It is a time of making robes:*";
P_HTM[3719]="*cīvare kayiramāne.**when he is making robes.*";
P_HTM[3720]="*Nimantite nimantitasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has been invited, and he perceives that he has, and he visits families beforehand or afterwards without taking leave of an available monk, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3721]="*Nimantite vematiko santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has been invited, but he is unsure of it, and he visits families beforehand or afterwards without taking leave of an available monk, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3722]="*Nimantite animantitasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā purebhattaṃ vā pacchābhattaṃ vā kulesu cārittaṃ āpajjati, aññatra samayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has been invited, but he does not perceive that he has, and he visits families beforehand or afterwards without taking leave of an available monk, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3723]="*Animantite nimantitasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he has not been invited, but he perceives that he has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3724]="*Animantite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he has not been invited, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3725]="*Animantite animantitasaññī, anāpatti.**If he has not been invited, and he does not perceive that he has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3726]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3727]="*samaye,**if it is an appropriate occasion;*";
P_HTM[3728]="*santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā pavisati,**if he enters after taking leave of an available monk;*";
P_HTM[3729]="*asantaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā pavisati,**if, when there is no available monk, he enters without taking leave;*";
P_HTM[3730]="*aññassa gharena maggo hoti,**if the road passes someone else’s house;*";
P_HTM[3731]="*gharūpacārena maggo hoti,**if the road passes the vicinity of someone else’s house;*";
P_HTM[3732]="*antarārāmaṃ gacchati,**if he is going between monasteries;*";
P_HTM[3733]="*bhikkhunupassayaṃ gacchati,**if he is going to the dwelling place of nuns;*";
P_HTM[3734]="*titthiyaseyyaṃ gacchati,**if he is going to the dwelling place of the monastics of another religion;*";
P_HTM[3735]="*paṭikkamanaṃ gacchati,**if he is returning to the monastery;*";
P_HTM[3736]="*bhattiyagharaṃ gacchati,**if he is going to the house where he has been invited;*";
P_HTM[3737]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[3738]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3739]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3740]="*Cārittasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on visiting, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3741]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3742]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked monastics*";
P_HTM[3743]="*47. Mahānāmasikkhāpada**47. The training rule on Mahānāma*";
P_HTM[3744]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in the Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu.*";
P_HTM[3745]="*Tena kho pana samayena mahānāmassa sakkassa bhesajjaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**At that time Mahānāma the Sakyan had an abundance of tonics.*";
P_HTM[3746]="*Atha kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**He went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down, and said,*";
P_HTM[3747]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavāretun”ti.**“Venerable Sir, I wish to invite the Sangha to ask for tonics for four months.”*";
P_HTM[3748]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma.**“Good, good, Mahānāma.*";
P_HTM[3749]="*Tena hi tvaṃ, mahānāma, saṅghaṃ catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavārehī”ti.**Please do so.”*";
P_HTM[3750]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti.**But the monks were afraid of wrongdoing and did not accept.*";
P_HTM[3751]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They then told the Buddha what had happened. …*";
P_HTM[3752]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, catumāsaṃ bhesajjappaccayapavāraṇaṃ sāditun”ti.**“Monks, I allow you to accept an invitation to ask for tonics for four months.”*";
P_HTM[3753]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ parittaṃ bhesajjaṃ viññāpenti. Tatheva mahānāmassa sakkassa bhesajjaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**Yet the monks only asked Mahānāma for a small amount of tonics, and so he still had an abundance.*";
P_HTM[3754]="*Dutiyampi kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**A second time he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down, and said,*";
P_HTM[3755]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ aparampi catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavāretun”ti.**“Sir, I wish to invite the Sangha to ask for tonics for a further four months.”*";
P_HTM[3756]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma.**“Good, good, Mahānāma.*";
P_HTM[3757]="*Tena hi tvaṃ, mahānāma, saṅghaṃ aparampi catumāsaṃ bhesajjena pavārehī”ti.**Please do so.”*";
P_HTM[3758]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti.**Again the monks were afraid of wrongdoing and did not accept.*";
P_HTM[3759]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[3760]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, puna pavāraṇampi sāditun”ti.**“Monks, I allow you to accept a further invitation.”*";
P_HTM[3761]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ parittaṃyeva bhesajjaṃ viññāpenti. Tatheva mahānāmassa sakkassa bhesajjaṃ ussannaṃ hoti.**Once again the monks only asked Mahānāma for a small amount of tonics, and so he still had an abundance.*";
P_HTM[3762]="*Tatiyampi kho mahānāmo sakko yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho mahānāmo sakko bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**A third time he went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down, and said,*";
P_HTM[3763]="*“icchāmahaṃ, bhante, saṅghaṃ yāvajīvaṃ bhesajjena pavāretun”ti.**“Sir, I wish to invite the Sangha to ask for tonics for life.”*";
P_HTM[3764]="*“Sādhu sādhu, mahānāma.**“Good, good, Mahānāma.*";
P_HTM[3765]="*Tena hi tvaṃ, mahānāma, saṅghaṃ yāvajīvaṃ bhesajjena pavārehī”ti.**Please do so.”*";
P_HTM[3766]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti.**Yet again the monks were afraid of wrongdoing and did not accept.*";
P_HTM[3767]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[3768]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, niccapavāraṇampi sāditun”ti.**“Monks, I allow you to accept a permanent invitation.”*";
P_HTM[3769]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dunnivatthā honti duppārutā anākappasampannā.**At that time the monks from the group of six were shabbily dressed and improper in appearance.*";
P_HTM[3770]="*Mahānāmo sakko vattā hoti—“kissa tumhe, bhante, dunnivatthā duppārutā anākappasampannā?**Mahānāma criticized them, “Venerables, why are you shabbily dressed and improper in appearance?*";
P_HTM[3771]="*Nanu nāma pabbajitena sunivatthena bhavitabbaṃ supārutena ākappasampannenā”ti?**Shouldn’t one who has gone forth be suitably dressed and proper in appearance?”*";
P_HTM[3772]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahānāme sakke upanandhiṃsu.**The monks from the group of six developed a grudge against Mahānāma.*";
P_HTM[3773]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—“kena nu kho mayaṃ upāyena mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ maṅkuṃ kareyyāmā”ti? Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**Thinking of ways to humiliate him, it occurred to them,*";
P_HTM[3774]="*“mahānāmena kho, āvuso, sakkena saṅgho bhesajjena pavārito. Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ sappiṃ viññāpemā”ti.**“Mahānāma has invited the Sangha to ask for tonics. Let’s ask him for ghee.”*";
P_HTM[3775]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū yena mahānāmo sakko tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ etadavocuṃ—“doṇena, āvuso, sappinā attho”ti.**They then went to Mahānāma and said, “We need a _doṇa_ measure of ghee.”*";
P_HTM[3776]="*“Ajjaṇho, bhante, āgametha.**“Please wait until tomorrow.*";
P_HTM[3777]="*Manussā vajaṃ gatā sappiṃ āharituṃ.**People have gone to the cow-pen to get ghee.*";
P_HTM[3778]="*Kālaṃ āharissathā”ti.**You may come and get it in the morning.”*";
P_HTM[3779]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**A second time*";
P_HTM[3780]="*tatiyampi kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahānāmaṃ sakkaṃ etadavocuṃ—“doṇena, āvuso, sappinā attho”ti.**and a third time the monks from the group of six said the same thing,*";
P_HTM[3781]="*“Ajjaṇho, bhante, āgametha.**and Mahānāma replied as before.*";
P_HTM[3782]="*Manussā vajaṃ gatā sappiṃ āharituṃ.* **";
P_HTM[3783]="*Kālaṃ āharissathā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[3784]="*“Kiṃ pana tayā, āvuso, adātukāmena pavāritena, yaṃ tvaṃ pavāretvā na desī”ti.**They then said, “Why do you give an invitation if you don’t wish to give?”*";
P_HTM[3785]="*Atha kho mahānāmo sakko ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—“kathañhi nāma bhadantā—‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamethā’ti vuccamānā nāgamessantī”ti.**Mahānāma complained and criticized them, “How can they not wait for one day when asked?”*";
P_HTM[3786]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū mahānāmassa sakkassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of Mahānāma,*";
P_HTM[3787]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[3788]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahānāmena sakkena—‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamethā’ti vuccamānā nāgamessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six not wait for one day when asked by Mahānāma?” …*";
P_HTM[3789]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, mahānāmena sakkena—‘ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamethā’ti vuccamānā nāgamethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[3790]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3791]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[3792]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, mahānāmena sakkena—“ajjaṇho, bhante, āgamethā”ti vuccamānā nāgamessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you act like this?*";
P_HTM[3793]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3794]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3795]="*“Agilānena bhikkhunā catumāsappaccayapavāraṇā sāditabbā, aññatra punapavāraṇāya, aññatra niccapavāraṇāya; tato ce uttari sādiyeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘A monk who is not sick may accept an invitation to ask for requisites for four months. If he accepts one beyond that limit, except if it is a further invitation or a permanent invitation, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3796]="*Agilānena bhikkhunā catumāsappaccayapavāraṇā sāditabbāti**A monk who is not sick may accept an invitation to ask for requisites for four months:*";
P_HTM[3797]="*gilānappaccayapavāraṇā sāditabbā.**he may accept an invitation to ask for requisites for the sick.*";
P_HTM[3798]="*Punapavāraṇāpi sāditabbāti**He may also accept a further invitation:*";
P_HTM[3799]="*yadā gilāno bhavissāmi tadā viññāpessāmīti.**he should think, “I’ll ask when I’m sick.”*";
P_HTM[3800]="*Niccapavāraṇāpi sāditabbāti**He may also accept a permanent invitation:*";
P_HTM[3801]="*yadā gilāno bhavissāmi tadā viññāpessāmīti.**he should think, “I’ll ask when I’m sick.”*";
P_HTM[3802]="*Tato ce uttari sādiyeyyāti**If he accepts one beyond that limit:*";
P_HTM[3803]="*atthi pavāraṇā bhesajjapariyantā na rattipariyantā,**there are invitations that have a limit on the tonics, but no limit on the time period;*";
P_HTM[3804]="*atthi pavāraṇā rattipariyantā na bhesajjapariyantā,**there are invitations that have a limit on the time period, but no limit on the tonics;*";
P_HTM[3805]="*atthi pavāraṇā bhesajjapariyantā ca rattipariyantā ca,**there are invitations that have a limit on both the tonics and the time period;*";
P_HTM[3806]="*atthi pavāraṇā neva bhesajjapariyantā na rattipariyantā.**there are invitations that have neither a limit on the tonics nor on the time period.*";
P_HTM[3807]="*Bhesajjapariyantā nāma**Limit on the tonics:*";
P_HTM[3808]="*bhesajjāni pariggahitāni honti—“ettakehi bhesajjehi pavāremī”ti.**the tonics are restricted: “I invite you to ask for these particular tonics.”*";
P_HTM[3809]="*Rattipariyantā nāma**Limit on the time period:*";
P_HTM[3810]="*rattiyo pariggahitāyo honti—“ettakāsu rattīsu pavāremī”ti.**the time period is restricted: “I invite you to ask during this particular period of time.”*";
P_HTM[3811]="*Bhesajjapariyantā ca rattipariyantā ca nāma**Limit on both the tonics and the time period:*";
P_HTM[3812]="*bhesajjāni ca pariggahitāni honti rattiyo ca pariggahitāyo honti—“ettakehi bhesajjehi ettakāsu rattīsu pavāremī”ti.**both the tonics and the time period are restricted: “I invite you to ask for these particular tonics during this particular period of time.”*";
P_HTM[3813]="*Neva bhesajjapariyantā na rattipariyantā nāma**Neither a limit on the tonics nor on the time period:*";
P_HTM[3814]="*bhesajjāni ca apariggahitāni honti rattiyo ca apariggahitāyo honti.**neither the tonics nor the time period is restricted.*";
P_HTM[3815]="*Bhesajjapariyante—yehi bhesajjehi pavārito hoti tāni bhesajjāni ṭhapetvā aññāni bhesajjāni viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When there is a limit on the tonics, if he asks for tonics other than those he has been invited to ask for, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3816]="*Rattipariyante—yāsu rattīsu pavārito hoti, tā rattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāsu rattīsu viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When there is a limit on the time period, if he asks outside of the period during which he has been invited to ask, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3817]="*Bhesajjapariyante ca rattipariyante ca—yehi bhesajjehi pavārito hoti, tāni bhesajjāni ṭhapetvā yāsu rattīsu pavārito hoti, tā rattiyo ṭhapetvā aññāni bhesajjāni aññāsu rattīsu viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When there is a limit on both the tonics and on the time period, if he asks for tonics other than those he has been invited to ask for and he asks outside of the period during which he has been invited to ask, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3818]="*Neva bhesajjapariyante na rattipariyante, anāpatti.**When there is neither a limit on the tonics nor on the time period, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3819]="*Na bhesajjena karaṇīyena bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he asks for tonics when he has no need for tonics, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3820]="*Aññena bhesajjena karaṇīyena aññaṃ bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he asks for a tonic other than the tonic he needs, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3821]="*Tatuttari tatuttarisaññī bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is beyond the limit, and he perceives it as such, and he asks for tonics, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3822]="*Tatuttari vematiko bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is beyond the limit, but he is unsure of it, and he asks for tonics, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3823]="*Tatuttari natatuttarisaññī bhesajjaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is beyond the limit, but he does not perceive it as such, and he asks for tonics, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3824]="*Natatuttari tatuttarisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not beyond the limit, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3825]="*Natatuttari vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not beyond the limit, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3826]="*Natatuttari natatuttarisaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not beyond the limit, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3827]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3828]="*yehi bhesajjehi pavārito hoti tāni bhesajjāni viññāpeti,**if he asks for those tonics for which he was invited to ask;*";
P_HTM[3829]="*yāsu rattīsu pavārito hoti tāsu rattīsu viññāpeti,**if he asks during the time period for which he was invited to ask;*";
P_HTM[3830]="*“imehi tayā bhesajjehi pavāritāmha, amhākañca iminā ca iminā ca bhesajjena attho”ti ācikkhitvā viññāpeti,**if he asks by informing, “You have invited me to ask for these tonics, but I need such-and-such a tonic;”*";
P_HTM[3831]="*“yāsu tayā rattīsu pavāritāmha tāyo ca rattiyo vītivattā amhākañca bhesajjena attho”ti ācikkhitvā viññāpeti,**if he asks by informing, “The time period during which you invited me to ask has passed, but I need tonics;”*";
P_HTM[3832]="*ñātakānaṃ**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[3833]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[3834]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[3835]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[3836]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3837]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3838]="*Mahānāmasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on Mahānāma, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3839]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3840]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3841]="*48. Uyyuttasenāsikkhāpada**48. The training rule on armies*";
P_HTM[3842]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3843]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo senāya abbhuyyāto hoti.**King Pasenadi of Kosala was marching out with the army,*";
P_HTM[3844]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu.**and the monks from the group of six went to see it.*";
P_HTM[3845]="*Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo chabbaggiye bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante.**When King Pasenadi saw the monks coming,*";
P_HTM[3846]="*Disvāna pakkosāpetvā etadavoca—**he summoned them and said,*";
P_HTM[3847]="*“kissa tumhe, bhante, āgatatthā”ti?**“Venerables, why have you come here?”*";
P_HTM[3848]="*“Mahārājānaṃ mayaṃ daṭṭhukāmā”ti.**“We wish to see the great king.”*";
P_HTM[3849]="*“Kiṃ, bhante, maṃ diṭṭhena yuddhābhinandinaṃ;**“What’s the use of seeing me finding pleasure in battle?*";
P_HTM[3850]="*nanu bhagavā passitabbo”ti?**Shouldn’t you see the Buddha?”*";
P_HTM[3851]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**And people complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[3852]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya āgacchissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics go to see the army?*";
P_HTM[3853]="*Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā senāya āgacchāmā”ti.**It’s our misfortune that we must go out with the army for the sake of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”*";
P_HTM[3854]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[3855]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[3856]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six go to see the army?” …*";
P_HTM[3857]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3858]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3859]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[3860]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gacchissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3861]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3862]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3863]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk goes to see an army, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3864]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[3865]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa bhikkhuno mātulo senāya gilāno hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain monk had a sick uncle in the army.*";
P_HTM[3866]="*So tassa bhikkhuno santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—**The uncle sent a message to that monk:*";
P_HTM[3867]="*“ahañhi senāya gilāno.**“I’m with the army and I’m sick.*";
P_HTM[3868]="*Āgacchatu bhadanto.**Please come, Venerable.*";
P_HTM[3869]="*Icchāmi bhadantassa āgatan”ti.**I want you to come.”*";
P_HTM[3870]="*Atha kho tassa bhikkhuno etadahosi—“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—‘na uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gantabban’ti.**Knowing that the Buddha had laid down a rule against going to see an army, that monk thought,*";
P_HTM[3871]="*Ayañca me mātulo senāya gilāno.**“I have a sick uncle in the army.*";
P_HTM[3872]="*Kathaṃ nu kho mayā paṭipajjitabban”ti?**What should I do now?”*";
P_HTM[3873]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And he told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[3874]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[3875]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tathārūpappaccayā senāya gantuṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to go to the army when there’s a suitable reason.*";
P_HTM[3876]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3877]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu uyyuttaṃ senaṃ dassanāya gaccheyya, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk goes to see an army, except if there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3878]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[3879]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[3880]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[3881]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[3882]="*Uyyuttā nāma senā**An army:*";
P_HTM[3883]="*gāmato nikkhamitvā niviṭṭhā vā hoti payātā vā.**it has left the inhabited area and is either encamped or marching.*";
P_HTM[3884]="*Senā nāma**An army:*";
P_HTM[3885]="*hatthī assā rathā pattī.**elephants, horses, chariots, infantry.*";
P_HTM[3886]="*Dvādasapuriso hatthī, tipuriso asso, catupuriso ratho, cattāro purisā sarahatthā patti.**An elephant has twelve men; a horse has three men; a chariot has four men; an infantry unit has four men with arrows in hand.*";
P_HTM[3887]="*Dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is on his way to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3888]="*Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3889]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time he moves outside the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3890]="*Aññatra tathārūpappaccayāti**Except if there is a suitable reason:*";
P_HTM[3891]="*ṭhapetvā tathārūpappaccayaṃ.**unless there is a suitable reason.*";
P_HTM[3892]="*Uyyutte uyyuttasaññī dassanāya gacchati, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an army, and he perceives it as such, and he goes to see it, except if there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3893]="*Uyyutte vematiko dassanāya gacchati, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an army, but he is unsure of it, and he goes to see it, except if there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3894]="*Uyyutte anuyyuttasaññī dassanāya gacchati, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an army, but he does not perceive it as such, and he goes to see it, except if there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3895]="*Ekamekaṃ dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is on his way to see one division of a fourfold army, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3896]="*Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3897]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**Every time he moves outside the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3898]="*Anuyyutte uyyuttasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not an army, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3899]="*Anuyyutte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not an army, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3900]="*Anuyyutte anuyyuttasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not an army, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3901]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3902]="*ārāme ṭhito passati,**if he sees it while standing in a monastery;*";
P_HTM[3903]="*bhikkhussa ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgacchati,**if the army comes to where the monk is standing, sitting, or lying down;*";
P_HTM[3904]="*paṭipathaṃ gacchanto passati,**if he sees it while walking in the opposite direction;*";
P_HTM[3905]="*tathārūpappaccayā,**if he has a suitable reason;*";
P_HTM[3906]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[3907]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3908]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3909]="*Uyyuttasenāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on armies, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3910]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3911]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3912]="*49. Senāvāsasikkhāpada**49. The training rule on staying with armies*";
P_HTM[3913]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3914]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sati karaṇīye senaṃ gantvā atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasanti.**the monks from the group of six went to the army on some business, and they stayed there for more than three nights.*";
P_HTM[3915]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[3916]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā senāya vasissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics stay with the army?*";
P_HTM[3917]="*Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā senāya paṭivasāmā”ti.**It’s our misfortune that we must stay with the army for the sake of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”*";
P_HTM[3918]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[3919]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[3920]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six stay with the army for more than three nights?” …*";
P_HTM[3921]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3922]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3923]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[3924]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, atirekatirattaṃ senāya vasissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3925]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3926]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3927]="*“Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo senaṃ gamanāya, dirattatirattaṃ tena bhikkhunā senāya vasitabbaṃ. Tato ce uttari vaseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If that monk has a reason for going to the army, he may stay with the army for two or three nights. If he stays longer than that, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3928]="*Siyā ca tassa bhikkhuno kocideva paccayo senaṃ gamanāyāti**If that monk has a reason for going to the army:*";
P_HTM[3929]="*siyā paccayo siyā karaṇīyaṃ.**if he has a reason, if he has something to  do.*";
P_HTM[3930]="*Dirattatirattaṃ tena bhikkhunā senāya vasitabbanti**He may stay with the army for two or three nights:*";
P_HTM[3931]="*dvetisso rattiyo vasitabbaṃ.**he may stay for two or for three nights.*";
P_HTM[3932]="*Tato ce uttari vaseyyāti**If he stays longer than that:*";
P_HTM[3933]="*catutthe divase atthaṅgate sūriye senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he is staying with the army at sunset on the fourth day, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3934]="*Atirekatiratte atirekasaññī senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than three nights, and he perceives it as more, and he is staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3935]="*Atirekatiratte vematiko senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than three nights, but he is unsure of it, and he is staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3936]="*Atirekatiratte ūnakasaññī senāya vasati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than three nights, but he perceives it as less, and he is staying with the army, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3937]="*Ūnakatiratte atirekasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than three nights, but he perceives it as more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3938]="*Ūnakatiratte vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than three nights, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3939]="*Ūnakatiratte ūnakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is less than three nights, and he perceives it as less, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[3940]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3941]="*dvetisso rattiyo vasati,**if he stays for two or three nights;*";
P_HTM[3942]="*ūnakadvetisso rattiyo vasati,**if he stays for less than two or three nights;*";
P_HTM[3943]="*dve rattiyo vasitvā tatiyāya rattiyā purāruṇā nikkhamitvā puna vasati,**if he stays for two nights, then leaves before dawn on the third night, and then stays again;*";
P_HTM[3944]="*gilāno vasati,**if he stays because he is sick;*";
P_HTM[3945]="*gilānassa karaṇīyena vasati,**if he stays because he has to take care of someone who is sick;*";
P_HTM[3946]="*senā vā paṭisenāya ruddhā hoti,**if the army is obstructed by an enemy army;*";
P_HTM[3947]="*kenaci palibuddho hoti,**if he is obstructed from leaving;*";
P_HTM[3948]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[3949]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3950]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3951]="*Senāvāsasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on staying with armies, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[3952]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[3953]="*Acelakavagga**The sub-chapter on naked ascetics*";
P_HTM[3954]="*50. Uyyodhikasikkhāpada**50. The training rule on battles*";
P_HTM[3955]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[3956]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dirattatirattaṃ senāya vasamānā uyyodhikampi balaggampi senābyūhampi anīkadassanampi gacchanti.**the monks from the group of six were staying with the army for two or three nights. They went to see battles, troop reviews, the massing of the army, and troop inspections.*";
P_HTM[3957]="*Aññataropi chabbaggiyo bhikkhu uyyodhikaṃ gantvā kaṇḍena paṭividdho hoti.**One of the monks who went to a battle was struck by an arrow.*";
P_HTM[3958]="*Manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ uppaṇḍesuṃ—**People teased him,*";
P_HTM[3959]="*“kacci, bhante, suyuddhaṃ ahosi, kati te lakkhāni laddhānī”ti?**“We hope you had a good battle, Venerable. How many targets did you hit?”*";
P_HTM[3960]="*So bhikkhu tehi manussehi uppaṇḍiyamāno maṅku ahosi.**And because they teased him, he felt humiliated.*";
P_HTM[3961]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[3962]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya āgacchissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics go to see a battle?*";
P_HTM[3963]="*Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā uyyodhikaṃ āgacchāmā”ti.**It’s our misfortune that we must go to battles for the sake of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”*";
P_HTM[3964]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[3965]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[3966]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya gacchissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six go to see a battle?” …*";
P_HTM[3967]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya gacchathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[3968]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[3969]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[3970]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, uyyodhikaṃ dassanāya gacchissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[3971]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[3972]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[3973]="*“Dirattatirattañce bhikkhu senāya vasamāno uyyodhikaṃ vā balaggaṃ vā senābyūhaṃ vā anīkadassanaṃ vā gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who is staying with an army for two or three nights goes to a battle, a troop review, a massing of the army, or a troop inspection, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[3974]="*Dirattatirattañce bhikkhu senāya vasamānoti**If a monk who is staying with an army for two or three nights:*";
P_HTM[3975]="*dvetisso rattiyo vasamāno.**he is staying for two or for three nights.*";
P_HTM[3976]="*Uyyodhikaṃ nāma**A battle:*";
P_HTM[3977]="*yattha sampahāro dissati.**wherever fighting is seen.*";
P_HTM[3978]="*Balaggaṃ nāma**A troop review:*";
P_HTM[3979]="*ettakā hatthī, ettakā assā, ettakā rathā, ettakā pattī.**so many elephants, so many horses, so many chariots, so much infantry.*";
P_HTM[3980]="*Senābyūhaṃ nāma**A massing of the army:*";
P_HTM[3981]="*ito hatthī hontu, ito assā hontu, ito rathā hontu, ito pattikā hontu.**the elephants should set out from here; the horses should set out from here; the chariots should set out from here; the infantry should set out from here.*";
P_HTM[3982]="*Anīkaṃ nāma**A troop:*";
P_HTM[3983]="*hatthānīkaṃ, assānīkaṃ, rathānīkaṃ, pattānīkaṃ.**An elephant troop, a horse troop, a chariot troop, an infantry troop.*";
P_HTM[3984]="*Tayo hatthī pacchimaṃ hatthānīkaṃ, tayo assā pacchimaṃ assānīkaṃ, tayo rathā pacchimaṃ rathānīkaṃ, cattāro purisā sarahatthā pattī pacchimaṃ pattānīkaṃ.**The smallest troop of elephants is three elephants; the smallest troop of horses is three horses; the smallest troop of chariots is three chariots; the smallest troop of infantry is four men with arrows in hand.*";
P_HTM[3985]="*Dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is on his way to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3986]="*Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3987]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time he moves outside the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[3988]="*Ekamekaṃ dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is on his way to see one division of a fourfold army, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3989]="*Yattha ṭhito passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**Wherever he stands to see it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3990]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**Every time he moves outside the range of sight and then sees it again, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[3991]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[3992]="*ārāme ṭhito passati,**if he sees it while standing in a monastery;*";
P_HTM[3993]="*bhikkhussa ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgantvā sampahāro dissati,**if the army comes to where the monk is standing, sitting, or lying down, and he then sees fighting;*";
P_HTM[3994]="*paṭipathaṃ gacchanto passati,**if he sees it while walking in the opposite direction;*";
P_HTM[3995]="*sati karaṇīye gantvā passati,**if he goes because there is something to be done, and he then sees it;*";
P_HTM[3996]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[3997]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[3998]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[3999]="*Uyyodhikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on battles, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4000]="*Acelakavaggo pañcamo.**The fifth sub-chapter on naked ascetics is finished.*";
P_HTM[4001]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[4002]="*Pūvaṃ kathopanandassa,**Pastry, talking, three on Upananda,*";
P_HTM[4003]="*tayaṃpaṭṭhākameva ca;**And indeed supporting;*";
P_HTM[4004]="*Mahānāmo pasenadi,**Mahānāma, Pasenadi,*";
P_HTM[4005]="*senāviddho ime dasāti.**Army, and struck: those are the ten.*";
P_HTM[4006]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4007]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4008]="*51. Surāpānasikkhāpada**51. The training rule on drinking alcoholic drinks*";
P_HTM[4009]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā cetiyesu cārikaṃ caramāno yena bhaddavatikā tena pāyāsi.**On one occasion when the Buddha was wandering in the country of Ceti on his way to Bhaddavatikā,*";
P_HTM[4010]="*Addasaṃsu kho gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**he was seen by a number of cow-herds, shepherds, farmers, and travelers.*";
P_HTM[4011]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—“mā kho, bhante, bhagavā ambatitthaṃ agamāsi.**They said to him, “Venerable Sir, don’t go to Ambatittha.*";
P_HTM[4012]="*Ambatitthe, bhante, jaṭilassa assame nāgo paṭivasati iddhimā āsiviso ghoraviso.**There’s a highly venomous dragon with supernormal powers there, in the hermitage of a dreadlocked ascetic.*";
P_HTM[4013]="*So bhagavantaṃ mā viheṭhesī”ti.**Don’t let it harm you.”*";
P_HTM[4014]="*Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**The Buddha was silent.*";
P_HTM[4015]="*Dutiyampi kho …pe…**They repeated their request a second*";
P_HTM[4016]="*tatiyampi kho gopālakā pasupālakā kassakā pathāvino bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and a third time,*";
P_HTM[4017]="*“mā kho, bhante, bhagavā ambatitthaṃ agamāsi.* **";
P_HTM[4018]="*Ambatitthe, bhante, jaṭilassa assame nāgo paṭivasati iddhimā āsiviso ghoraviso.* **";
P_HTM[4019]="*So bhagavantaṃ mā viheṭhesī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4020]="*Tatiyampi kho bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi.**and the Buddha remained silent.*";
P_HTM[4021]="*Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bhaddavatikā tadavasari. Tatra sudaṃ bhagavā bhaddavatikāyaṃ viharati.**The Buddha then continued on to Bhaddavatikā, and he stayed there.*";
P_HTM[4022]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāgato yena ambatitthassa jaṭilassa assamo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā agyāgāraṃ pavisitvā tiṇasanthārakaṃ paññapetvā nisīdi pallaṅkaṃ ābhujitvā ujuṃ kāyaṃ paṇidhāya parimukhaṃ satiṃ upaṭṭhapetvā.**Just then Venerable Sāgata went to the hermitage of that dreadlocked ascetic and entered his fire hut. After putting out a straw mat, he sat down, crossed his legs, straightened his body, and established mindfulness in front of him.*";
P_HTM[4023]="*Addasā kho so nāgo āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ paviṭṭhaṃ. Disvāna dummano padhūpāyi.**Seeing that Sāgata had entered the fire hut, the dragon was upset and emitted smoke.*";
P_HTM[4024]="*Āyasmāpi sāgato padhūpāyi.**Sāgata, too, emitted smoke.*";
P_HTM[4025]="*Atha kho so nāgo makkhaṃ asahamāno pajjali.**The dragon was not able to contain his rage and emitted flames.*";
P_HTM[4026]="*Āyasmāpi sāgato tejodhātuṃ samāpajjitvā pajjali.**Sāgata entered the fire element and he, too, emitted flames.*";
P_HTM[4027]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāgato tassa nāgassa tejasā tejaṃ pariyādiyitvā yena bhaddavatikā tenupasaṅkami.**Then, after conquering fire with fire, Sāgata went to Bhaddavatikā.*";
P_HTM[4028]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhaddavatikāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena kosambī tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**After staying at Bhaddavatikā for as long as he liked, the Buddha set out wandering toward Kosambī.*";
P_HTM[4029]="*Assosuṃ kho kosambikā upāsakā—“ayyo kira sāgato ambatitthikena nāgena saddhiṃ saṅgāmesī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4030]="*Atha kho bhagavā anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena kosambī tadavasari. Atha kho kosambikā upāsakā bhagavato paccuggamanaṃ karitvā yenāyasmā sāgato tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**When he arrived, the lay followers there received him.*";
P_HTM[4031]="*upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho kosambikā upāsakā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ etadavocuṃ—**But the lay followers at Kosambī had heard about Sāgata fighting the Ambatittha dragon. And so after receiving the Buddha, they went to see Sāgata. They bowed, stood to one side, and said,*";
P_HTM[4032]="*“kiṃ, bhante, ayyānaṃ dullabhañca manāpañca, kiṃ paṭiyādemā”ti?**“Venerable, what can we prepare for you that’s delicious but hard to get?”*";
P_HTM[4033]="*Evaṃ vutte, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kosambike upāsake etadavocuṃ—“atthāvuso, kāpotikā nāma pasannā bhikkhūnaṃ dullabhā ca manāpā ca, taṃ paṭiyādethā”ti.**The monks from the group of six replied, “There’s a delicious liquor called Kāpotikā, which is hard for the monks to get. Prepare that.”*";
P_HTM[4034]="*Atha kho kosambikā upāsakā ghare ghare kāpotikaṃ pasannaṃ paṭiyādetvā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ piṇḍāya paviṭṭhaṃ disvāna āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ etadavocuṃ—“pivatu, bhante, ayyo sāgato kāpotikaṃ pasannaṃ, pivatu, bhante, ayyo sāgato kāpotikaṃ pasannan”ti.**And the lay followers prepared Kāpotikā in house after house. Then, when they saw that Sāgata had entered the town for alms, they said to him, “Drink, Venerable, drink the Kāpotikā liquor.”*";
P_HTM[4035]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāgato ghare ghare kāpotikaṃ pasannaṃ pivitvā nagaramhā nikkhamanto nagaradvāre paripati.**Sāgata drank that liquor in house after house, and as he was leaving town, he collapsed at the town gate.*";
P_HTM[4036]="*Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ nagaramhā nikkhamanto addasa āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ nagaradvāre paripatantaṃ.**Just then the Buddha, together with a number of monks, was also leaving town, and he saw Sāgata at the town gate.*";
P_HTM[4037]="*Disvāna bhikkhū āmantesi—“gaṇhatha, bhikkhave, sāgatan”ti.**He said, “Monks, pick up Sāgata.”*";
P_HTM[4038]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho te bhikkhū bhagavato paṭissuṇitvā āyasmantaṃ sāgataṃ ārāmaṃ netvā yena bhagavā tena sīsaṃ katvā nipātesuṃ.**Saying, “Yes, Sir,” they led him to the monastery, where they put him down with his head toward the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4039]="*Atha kho āyasmā sāgato parivattitvā yena bhagavā tena pāde karitvā seyyaṃ kappesi.**But Sāgata turned around, pointing his feet toward the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4040]="*Atha kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi—“nanu, bhikkhave, pubbe sāgato tathāgate sagāravo ahosi sappatisso”ti?**The Buddha said, “Previously, monks, wasn’t Sāgata respectful and deferential toward me?”*";
P_HTM[4041]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[4042]="*“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, sāgato etarahi tathāgate sagāravo sappatisso”ti?**“But is he now?”*";
P_HTM[4043]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4044]="*“Nanu, bhikkhave, sāgato ambatitthikena nāgena saddhiṃ saṅgāmesī”ti?**“Just recently, didn’t Sāgata fight the Ambatittha dragon?”*";
P_HTM[4045]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[4046]="*“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, sāgato etarahi pahoti nāgena saddhiṃ saṅgāmetun”ti?**“Would he now be able to fight a dragon?”*";
P_HTM[4047]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not.”*";
P_HTM[4048]="*“Api nu kho, bhikkhave, taṃ pātabbaṃ yaṃ pivitvā visaññī assā”ti?**“So, monks, should one drink that which makes one senseless?”*";
P_HTM[4049]="*“No hetaṃ, bhante”.**“Certainly not, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4050]="*“Ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, sāgatassa ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable, monks, it’s not proper for Sāgata, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[4051]="*Kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, sāgato majjaṃ pivissati.**How could Sāgata drink alcoholic drinks?*";
P_HTM[4052]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4053]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4054]="*“Surāmerayapāne pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk drinks this or that kind of alcoholic drink, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4055]="*Surā nāma**This kind of alcoholic drink:*";
P_HTM[4056]="*piṭṭhasurā pūvasurā odanasurā kiṇṇapakkhittā sambhārasaṃyuttā.**alcoholic drinks made from flour, alcoholic drinks made from pastries, alcoholics drink made from rice, those with yeast added, those made from a combination of ingredients.*";
P_HTM[4057]="*Merayo nāma**That kind of alcoholic drink:*";
P_HTM[4058]="*pupphāsavo phalāsavo madhvāsavo guḷāsavo sambhārasaṃyutto.**alcoholic drinks made from flowers, alcoholic drinks made from fruit, alcoholic drinks made from honey, alcoholic drinks made from sugar, those made from a combination of ingredients.*";
P_HTM[4059]="*Piveyyāti**Drinks:*";
P_HTM[4060]="*antamaso kusaggenapi pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he drinks even what fits on the tip of a blade of grass, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4061]="*Majje majjasaññī pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an alcoholic drink, and he perceives it as such, and he drinks it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4062]="*Majje vematiko pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an alcoholic drink, but he is unsure of it, and he drinks it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4063]="*Majje amajjasaññī pivati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an alcoholic drink, but he perceives it as non-alcoholic, and he drinks it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4064]="*Amajje majjasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a non-alcoholic drink, but he perceives it as alcoholic, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4065]="*Amajje vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a non-alcoholic drink, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4066]="*Amajje amajjasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is a non-alcoholic drink, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4067]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4068]="*amajjañca hoti majjavaṇṇaṃ majjagandhaṃ majjarasaṃ taṃ pivati,**if he drinks a non-alcoholic drink that has the color, smell, or taste of an alcoholic drink;*";
P_HTM[4069]="*sūpasampāke,**if it is cooked in a bean curry;*";
P_HTM[4070]="*maṃsasampāke,**if it is cooked with meat;*";
P_HTM[4071]="*telasampāke,**if it is cooked with oil;*";
P_HTM[4072]="*āmalakaphāṇite,**if it is in syrup from emblic myrobalan;*";
P_HTM[4073]="*amajjaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ pivati,**if he drinks a drink that is normally alcoholic, but which is actually without alcohol;*";
P_HTM[4074]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4075]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4076]="*Surāpānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on drinking alcoholic drinks, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4077]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4078]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4079]="*52. Aṅgulipatodakasikkhāpada**52. The training rule on tickling*";
P_HTM[4080]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4081]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiyaṃ bhikkhuṃ aṅgulipatodakena hāsesuṃ.**the monks from the group of six tickled one of the monks from the group of seventeen to make him laugh.*";
P_HTM[4082]="*So bhikkhu uttanto anassāsako kālamakāsi.**Not being able to catch his breath, he died.*";
P_HTM[4083]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4084]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ aṅgulipatodakena hāsessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six tickle a monk to make him laugh?” …*";
P_HTM[4085]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ aṅgulipatodakena hāsethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[4086]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4087]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[4088]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhuṃ aṅgulipatodakena hāsessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[4089]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4090]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4091]="*“Aṅgulipatodake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk tickles someone, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4092]="*Aṅgulipatodako nāma**Tickles another:*";
P_HTM[4093]="*upasampanno upasampannaṃ hasādhippāyo kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if one who is fully ordained touches another who is fully ordained, body to body, with the aim of making him laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4094]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī aṅgulipatodakena hāseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he tickles him to make him laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4095]="*Upasampanne vematiko aṅgulipatodakena hāseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he tickles him to make him laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4096]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī aṅgulipatodakena hāseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he tickles him to make him laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4097]="*Kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with his own body, he touches what is connected to the other monk’s body, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4098]="*Kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with what is connected to his own body, he touches the other monk’s body, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4099]="*Kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with what is connected to his own body, he touches what is connected to the other monk’s body, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4100]="*Nissaggiyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, by releasing something, he touches the other monk’s body, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4101]="*Nissaggiyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, by releasing something, he touches what is connected to the other monk’s body, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4102]="*Nissaggiyena nissaggiyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, by releasing something, he touches what is released by the other monk, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4103]="*Anupasampannaṃ kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with his own body, he touches the body of someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4104]="*Kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with his own body, he touches what is connected to the body of someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4105]="*Kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with what is connected to his own body, he touches the body of someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4106]="*Kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, with what is connected to his own body, he touches what is connected to the body of someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4107]="*Nissaggiyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, by releasing something, he touches the body of someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4108]="*Nissaggiyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, by releasing something, he touches what is connected to the body of someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4109]="*Nissaggiyena nissaggiyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, by releasing something, he touches what is released by the someone who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4110]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4111]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4112]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4113]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4114]="*na hasādhippāyo,**if he is not aiming to make him laugh;*";
P_HTM[4115]="*sati karaṇīye āmasati,**if he touches him when there is a need;*";
P_HTM[4116]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4117]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4118]="*Aṅgulipatodakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on tickling, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4119]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4120]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4121]="*53. Hasadhammasikkhāpada**53. The training rule on playing*";
P_HTM[4122]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**On one occasion when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4123]="*Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū aciravatiyā nadiyā udake kīḷanti.**the monks from the group of seventeen were playing in the water of the river Aciravatī.*";
P_HTM[4124]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo mallikāya deviyā saddhiṃ uparipāsādavaragato hoti.**Just then, while King Pasenadi of Kosala was up in his best stilt house with queen Mallikā,*";
P_HTM[4125]="*Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū aciravatiyā nadiyā udake kīḷante.**he saw the monks from the group of seventeen playing in the river.*";
P_HTM[4126]="*Disvāna mallikaṃ deviṃ etadavoca—**He said to queen Mallikā,*";
P_HTM[4127]="*“ete te, mallike, arahanto udake kīḷantī”ti.**“Mallikā, these perfected ones are playing in the water.”*";
P_HTM[4128]="*“Nissaṃsayaṃ kho, mahārāja, bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ apaññattaṃ.**“Great King, no doubt the Buddha hasn’t laid down a rule.*";
P_HTM[4129]="*Te vā bhikkhū appakataññuno”ti.**Either that, or these monks are ignorant.”*";
P_HTM[4130]="*Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi—**King Pasenadi thought,*";
P_HTM[4131]="*“kena nu kho ahaṃ upāyena bhagavato ca na āroceyyaṃ, bhagavā ca jāneyya ime bhikkhū udake kīḷitā”ti?**“How can the Buddha find out about these monks playing in the water without me telling him?”*";
P_HTM[4132]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū pakkosāpetvā mahantaṃ guḷapiṇḍaṃ adāsi—**Having sent for those monks, King Pasenadi gave them a large lump of sugar, saying,*";
P_HTM[4133]="*“imaṃ, bhante, guḷapiṇḍaṃ bhagavato dethā”ti.**“Venerables, please give this lump of sugar to the Buddha.”*";
P_HTM[4134]="*Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū taṃ guḷapiṇḍaṃ ādāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**The monks took the lump of sugar, went to the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[4135]="*upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[4136]="*“imaṃ, bhante, guḷapiṇḍaṃ rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavato detī”ti.**“Venerable Sir, this lump of sugar is a gift from King Pasenadi.”*";
P_HTM[4137]="*“Kahaṃ pana tumhe, bhikkhave, rājā addasā”ti.**“But, monks, where did you see the king?”*";
P_HTM[4138]="*“Aciravatiyā nadiyā, bhagavā, udake kīḷante”ti.**“From the river Aciravatī, while playing in the water.”*";
P_HTM[4139]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[4140]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, udake kīḷissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you play in water?*";
P_HTM[4141]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4142]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4143]="*“Udake hasadhamme pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk plays in water, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4144]="*Udake hasadhammo nāma**Plays in water:*";
P_HTM[4145]="*uparigopphake udake hasādhippāyo nimujjati vā ummujjati vā palavati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, aiming to have fun, he immerses himself or emerges on the surface or swims, in water that is more than ankle deep, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4146]="*Udake hasadhamme hasadhammasaññī, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is playing in water, and he perceives that he is, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4147]="*Udake hasadhamme vematiko, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is playing in water, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4148]="*Udake hasadhamme ahasadhammasaññī, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is playing in water, but he does not perceive that he is, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4149]="*Heṭṭhāgopphake udake kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is playing in water less than ankle deep, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4150]="*Udake nāvāya kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is playing in a boat in water, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4151]="*Hatthena vā pādena vā kaṭṭhena vā kaṭhalāya vā udakaṃ paharati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he strikes the water with his hand, with his foot, with a stick, or with a stone, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4152]="*Bhājanagataṃ udakaṃ vā kañjikaṃ vā khīraṃ vā takkaṃ vā rajanaṃ vā passāvaṃ vā cikkhallaṃ vā kīḷati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he plays with water in a vessel, or with conjee, milk, buttermilk, dye, urine, or mud in a vessel, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4153]="*Udake ahasadhamme hasadhammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not playing in water, but he perceives that he is, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4154]="*Udake ahasadhamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not playing in water, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4155]="*Udake ahasadhamme ahasadhammasaññī, anāpatti.**If he is not playing in water, and he does not perceive that he is, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4156]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4157]="*na hasādhippāyo,**if he is not aiming to have fun;*";
P_HTM[4158]="*sati karaṇīye udakaṃ otaritvā nimujjati vā ummujjati vā palavati vā,**if, when there is something to be done, he enters the water and then immerses himself or emerges on the surface or swims;*";
P_HTM[4159]="*pāraṃ gacchanto nimujjati vā ummujjati vā palavati vā,**if, while crossing a body of water, he immerses himself or emerges on the surface or swims;*";
P_HTM[4160]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[4161]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4162]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4163]="*Hasadhammasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on playing, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4164]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4165]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4166]="*54. Anādariyasikkhāpada**54. The training rule on disrespect*";
P_HTM[4167]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4168]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo anācāraṃ ācarati.**Venerable Channa was misbehaving.*";
P_HTM[4169]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The monks would tell him,*";
P_HTM[4170]="*“māvuso channa, evarūpaṃ akāsi.**“Channa, don’t do that;*";
P_HTM[4171]="*Netaṃ kappatī”ti.**it’s not allowable,”*";
P_HTM[4172]="*So anādariyaṃ paṭicca karotiyeva.**and he just did it again out of disrespect.*";
P_HTM[4173]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[4174]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo anādariyaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Channa act disrespectfully?” …*";
P_HTM[4175]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, anādariyaṃ karosī”ti?**“Is it true, Channa, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[4176]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4177]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[4178]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, anādariyaṃ karissasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[4179]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4180]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4181]="*“Anādariye pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk is disrespectful, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4182]="*Anādariyaṃ nāma**Disrespectful:*";
P_HTM[4183]="*dve anādariyāni— puggalānādariyañca dhammānādariyañca.**there are two kinds of disrespect: disrespect for the person and disrespect for the rule.*";
P_HTM[4184]="*Puggalānādariyaṃ nāma**Disrespect for the person:*";
P_HTM[4185]="*upasampannena paññattena vuccamāno— “ayaṃ ukkhittako vā vambhito vā garahito vā, imassa vacanaṃ akataṃ bhavissatī”ti anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, when corrected by one who is fully ordained about a rule that has been laid down, he thinks, “They’ve been ejected,” “They’ve been reproved,” or “They’ve been censured,” and then, “I won’t do what they say,” and he acts disrespectfully, then he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4186]="*Dhammānādariyaṃ nāma**Disrespect for the rule:*";
P_HTM[4187]="*upasampannena paññattena vuccamāno— “kathāyaṃ nasseyya vā vinasseyya vā antaradhāyeyya vā”, taṃ vā na sikkhitukāmo anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, when corrected by one who is fully ordained about a rule that has been laid down, he thinks, “What can be done so that this rule is lost?” “What can be done so that it perishes?”  or “What can be done so that it disappears?” or he does not want to train in that rule, and he acts disrespectfully, then he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4188]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and he perceives them as such, and he acts disrespectfully, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4189]="*Upasampanne vematiko anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he acts disrespectfully, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4190]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but he does not perceive them as such, and he acts disrespectfully, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4191]="*Apaññattena vuccamāno—**If, when corrected about something that has not been laid down, he thinks,*";
P_HTM[4192]="*“idaṃ na sallekhāya na dhutatthāya na pāsādikatāya na apacayāya na vīriyārambhāya saṃvattatī”ti anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“This isn’t conducive to the erasing of defilements,” “This isn’t conducive to ascetic practices,” “This isn’t conducive to being inspiring,” “This isn’t conducive to a reduction in things,” or “This isn’t conducive to being energetic,” and he acts disrespectfully, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4193]="*Anupasampannena paññattena vā apaññattena vā vuccamāno—**If, when corrected by one who is not fully ordained, whether or not it has been laid down, he thinks,*";
P_HTM[4194]="*“idaṃ na sallekhāya na dhutatthāya na pāsādikatāya na apacayāya na vīriyārambhāya saṃvattatī”ti anādariyaṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“This isn’t conducive to the erasing of defilements,” “This isn’t conducive to ascetic practices,” “This isn’t conducive to being inspiring,” “This isn’t conducive to a reduction in things,” or “This isn’t conducive to being energetic,” and he acts disrespectfully, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4195]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4196]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4197]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4198]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4199]="*“evaṃ amhākaṃ ācariyānaṃ uggaho paripucchā”ti bhaṇati,**if he says, “This is how we were taught and tested by our teachers;”*";
P_HTM[4200]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4201]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4202]="*Anādariyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on disrespect, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4203]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4204]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4205]="*55. Bhiṃsāpanasikkhāpada**55. The training rule on scaring*";
P_HTM[4206]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4207]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiye bhikkhū bhiṃsāpenti.**the monks from the group of six were scaring the monks from the group of seventeen.*";
P_HTM[4208]="*Te bhiṃsāpīyamānā rodanti.**They cried.*";
P_HTM[4209]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Other monks asked them why,*";
P_HTM[4210]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4211]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū amhe bhiṃsāpentī”ti.**and they told them.*";
P_HTM[4212]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4213]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six scare other monks?” …*";
P_HTM[4214]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[4215]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4216]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[4217]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[4218]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4219]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4220]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ bhiṃsāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk scares a monk, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4221]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4222]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4223]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4224]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4225]="*Bhikkhunti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[4226]="*aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ.**another monk.*";
P_HTM[4227]="*Bhiṃsāpeyyāti**Scares:*";
P_HTM[4228]="*upasampanno upasampannaṃ bhiṃsāpetukāmo rūpaṃ vā saddaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā rasaṃ vā phoṭṭhabbaṃ vā upasaṃharati. Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if one who is fully ordained, wishing to scare another who is fully ordained, arranges a sight, a sound, a smell, a taste, or a physical contact, then whether the other monk is scared or not, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4229]="*Corakantāraṃ vā vāḷakantāraṃ vā pisācakantāraṃ vā ācikkhati. Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he tells him about a wilderness inhabited by criminals, predatory animals, or demons, then whether the other monk is scared or not, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4230]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī bhiṃsāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he scares him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4231]="*Upasampanne vematiko bhiṃsāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he scares him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4232]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī bhiṃsāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he scares him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4233]="*Anupasampannaṃ bhiṃsāpetukāmo rūpaṃ vā saddaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā rasaṃ vā phoṭṭhabbaṃ vā upasaṃharati.**If, wishing to scare someone who is not fully ordained, he arranges a sight, a sound, a smell, a taste, or a physical contact,*";
P_HTM[4234]="*Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**then whether the other person is scared or not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4235]="*Corakantāraṃ vā vāḷakantāraṃ vā pisācakantāraṃ vā ācikkhati.**If he tells him about a wilderness inhabited by criminals, predatory animals, or demons,*";
P_HTM[4236]="*Bhāyeyya vā so na vā bhāyeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**then whether the other person is scared or not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4237]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4238]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4239]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4240]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4241]="*na bhiṃsāpetukāmo rūpaṃ vā saddaṃ vā gandhaṃ vā rasaṃ vā phoṭṭhabbaṃ vā upasaṃharati, corakantāraṃ vā vāḷakantāraṃ vā pisācakantāraṃ vā ācikkhati,**if he arranges a sight, a sound, a smell, a taste, or a physical contact, or he tells about a wilderness inhabited by criminals, predatory animals, or demons, but not because he wishes to scare anyone;*";
P_HTM[4242]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4243]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4244]="*Bhiṃsāpanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on scaring, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4245]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4246]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4247]="*56. Jotikasikkhāpada**56. The training rule on fire*";
P_HTM[4248]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the Bhagga country at Susumāragira in the Bhesakaḷā Grove, the deer park.*";
P_HTM[4249]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū hemantike kāle aññataraṃ mahantaṃ susirakaṭṭhaṃ jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbesuṃ.**At that time, during winter, the monks were warming themselves after setting fire to a hollow log.*";
P_HTM[4250]="*Tasmiñca susire kaṇhasappo agginā santatto nikkhamitvā bhikkhū paripātesi.**Heated by the fire, a black snake came out of the log and attacked the monks.*";
P_HTM[4251]="*Bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ upadhāviṃsu.**The monks ran here and there.*";
P_HTM[4252]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4253]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbessantī”ti …pe…**“How could those monks light a fire to warm themselves?” …*";
P_HTM[4254]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks did this?”*";
P_HTM[4255]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4256]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[4257]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbessanti.**“How could those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[4258]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4259]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4260]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādaheyya vā samādahāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk lights a fire to warm himself, or has one lit, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4261]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4262]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti.**At one time a number of monks were sick.*";
P_HTM[4263]="*Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The monks who were looking after them asked,*";
P_HTM[4264]="*“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up? I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[4265]="*“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbema;**“Previously we lit a fire to warm ourselves,*";
P_HTM[4266]="*tena no phāsu hoti.**and then we were comfortable.*";
P_HTM[4267]="*Idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na visibbema, tena no na phāsu hotī”ti.**But now that the Buddha has prohibited this, we don’t warm ourselves because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. Because of that we’re not comfortable.”*";
P_HTM[4268]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[4269]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā jotiṃ samādahitvā vā samādahāpetvā vā visibbetuṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to light a fire to warm himself, or to have one lit.*";
P_HTM[4270]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4271]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu agilāno visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādaheyya vā samādahāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who is not sick lights a fire to warm himself, or has one lit, he commits an offense entailing confession.’*";
P_HTM[4272]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4273]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū padīpepi jotikepi jantāgharepi kukkuccāyanti.**Soon afterwards the monks did not light lamps, small fires, or saunas because they were afraid of wrongdoing.*";
P_HTM[4274]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha …*";
P_HTM[4275]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tathārūpappaccayā jotiṃ samādahituṃ samādahāpetuṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to light a fire, or to have one lit, if there’s a suitable reason.*";
P_HTM[4276]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4277]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu agilāno visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādaheyya vā samādahāpeyya vā, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk who is not sick lights a fire to warm himself, or has one lit, except if there is a suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4278]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4279]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4280]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4281]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4282]="*Agilāno nāma**Who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[4283]="*yassa vinā agginā phāsu hoti.**who is comfortable without a fire.*";
P_HTM[4284]="*Gilāno nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[4285]="*yassa vinā agginā na phāsu hoti.**who is not comfortable without a fire.*";
P_HTM[4286]="*Visibbanāpekkhoti**To warm himself:*";
P_HTM[4287]="*tappitukāmo.**wanting to heat himself.*";
P_HTM[4288]="*Joti nāma**A fire:*";
P_HTM[4289]="*aggi vuccati.**flames are what is meant.*";
P_HTM[4290]="*Samādaheyyāti**Lights:*";
P_HTM[4291]="*sayaṃ samādahati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he lights it himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4292]="*Samādahāpeyyāti**Has one lit:*";
P_HTM[4293]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4294]="*Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi samādahati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he only asks once, then even if the other lights many fires, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4295]="*Aññatra tathā rūpappaccayāti**Except if there is a suitable reason:*";
P_HTM[4296]="*ṭhapetvā tathārūpappaccayaṃ.**unless there is an suitable reason.*";
P_HTM[4297]="*Agilāno agilānasaññī visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādahati vā samādahāpeti vā, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, and he does not perceive himself as sick, and he lights a fire to warm himself, or has one lit, except if there is an suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4298]="*Agilāno vematiko visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādahati vā samādahāpeti vā, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he lights a fire to warm himself, or has one lit, except if there is an suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4299]="*Agilāno gilānasaññī visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādahati vā samādahāpeti vā, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he lights a fire to warm himself, or has one lit, except if there is an suitable reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4300]="*Paṭilātaṃ ukkhipati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he puts back a burning piece of wood that has fallen off, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4301]="*Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is sick, but he does not perceive himself as sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4302]="*Gilāno vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is sick, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4303]="*Gilāno gilānasaññī, anāpatti.**If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4304]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4305]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[4306]="*aññena kataṃ visibbeti,**if he warms himself over a fire lit by another;*";
P_HTM[4307]="*vītaccitaṅgāraṃ visibbeti,**if he warms himself over flameless coals;*";
P_HTM[4308]="*padīpe jotike jantāghare tathārūpappaccayā,**if he lights a lamp, a small fire, or a sauna, when there is an suitable reason;*";
P_HTM[4309]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[4310]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4311]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4312]="*Jotikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on fire, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4313]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4314]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4315]="*57. Nahānasikkhāpada**57. The training rule on bathing*";
P_HTM[4316]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary,*";
P_HTM[4317]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū tapode nahāyanti.**the monks were bathing in the hot springs.*";
P_HTM[4318]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro “sīsaṃ nahāyissāmī”ti tapodaṃ gantvā—**Just then King Seniya Bimbisāra of Magadha went to the hot springs, intending to wash his hair.*";
P_HTM[4319]="*“yāvāyyā nahāyantī”ti ekamantaṃ paṭimānesi. Bhikkhū yāva samandhakārā nahāyiṃsu.**He waited respectfully for the monks to finish, but they kept on bathing until dark.*";
P_HTM[4320]="*Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro vikāle sīsaṃ nahāyitvā, nagaradvāre thakite bahinagare vasitvā, kālasseva asambhinnena vilepanena yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami;**Only then was King Bimbisāra able to wash his hair. And because the town gates had been shut, he had to spend the night outside the city. In the morning, with his make-up still on,*";
P_HTM[4321]="*upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**he went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[4322]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ bhagavā etadavoca—“kissa tvaṃ, mahārāja, kālasseva āgato asambhinnena vilepanenā”ti?**The Buddha said to him, “Great King, why have you come so early in the morning, with your make-up still on?”*";
P_HTM[4323]="*Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**The King told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[4324]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājānaṃ māgadhaṃ seniyaṃ bimbisāraṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. Atha kho rājā māgadho seniyo bimbisāro bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**The Buddha then instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching, after which the King got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[4325]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[4326]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū rājānampi passitvā na mattaṃ jānitvā nahāyantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that monks bathed without moderation, even after seeing the King?”*";
P_HTM[4327]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4328]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[4329]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā rājānampi passitvā na mattaṃ jānitvā nahāyissanti.**“How could those foolish men act in this way?*";
P_HTM[4330]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4331]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4332]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk bathes at intervals of less than a half-month, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4333]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4334]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū uṇhasamaye pariḷāhasamaye kukkuccāyantā na nahāyanti, sedagatena gattena sayanti.**Soon afterwards, because they were afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not bathe when it was hot or when they had a fever, and they went to sleep covered in sweat.*";
P_HTM[4335]="*Cīvarampi senāsanampi dussati.**As a consequence, their robes and beds were soiled.*";
P_HTM[4336]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[4337]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, uṇhasamaye pariḷāhasamaye orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ.**“Monks, if it’s hot or you have a fever, I allow you to bathe at intervals of less than a half-month.*";
P_HTM[4338]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4339]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk bathes at intervals of less than a half-month, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4340]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānanti vassānassa paṭhamo māso iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo pariḷāhasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**This is the appropriate occasion: it is the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever season, comprising the last one-and-a-half months of summer and the first month of the rainy season.’”*";
P_HTM[4341]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4342]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti.**Soon afterwards some monks were sick.*";
P_HTM[4343]="*Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The monks who were looking after them asked,*";
P_HTM[4344]="*“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up? I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[4345]="*“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyāma, tena no phāsu hoti;**“Previously we bathed at intervals of less than a half-month, and then we were comfortable.*";
P_HTM[4346]="*idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na nahāyāma, tena no na phāsu hotī”ti.**But now that the Buddha has prohibited this, we don’t bathe because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. Because of that we’re not comfortable.”*";
P_HTM[4347]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[4348]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to bathe at intervals of less than a half-month.*";
P_HTM[4349]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4350]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk bathes at intervals of less than a half-month, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4351]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānanti vassānassa paṭhamo māso iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo, pariḷāhasamayo, gilānasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: it is the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever season, comprising the last one-and-a-half months of summer and the first month of the rainy season; he is sick.’”*";
P_HTM[4352]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4353]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū navakammaṃ katvā kukkuccāyantā na nahāyanti.**Soon afterwards the monks were doing building work, but because they were afraid of wrongdoing they did not bathe.*";
P_HTM[4354]="*Te sedagatena gattena sayanti. Cīvarampi senāsanampi dussati.**As a consequence, they went to sleep covered in sweat, and their robes and beds were soiled.*";
P_HTM[4355]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[4356]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kammasamaye orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to bathe at intervals of less than a half-month when you’re working.*";
P_HTM[4357]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4358]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk bathes at intervals of less than a half-month, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4359]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānanti vassānassa paṭhamo māso iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo, pariḷāhasamayo, gilānasamayo, kammasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: it is the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever season, comprising the last one-and-a-half months of summer and the first month of the rainy season; he is sick; he is working.’”*";
P_HTM[4360]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4361]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū addhānaṃ gantvā kukkuccāyantā na nahāyanti.**Soon afterwards the monks were traveling, but because they were afraid of wrongdoing they did not bathe.*";
P_HTM[4362]="*Te sedagatena gattena sayanti. Cīvarampi senāsanampi dussati.**As a consequence, they went to sleep covered in sweat, and their robes and beds were soiled.*";
P_HTM[4363]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[4364]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, addhānagamanasamaye orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to bathe at intervals of less than a half-month when you’re traveling.*";
P_HTM[4365]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4366]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk bathes at intervals of less than a half-month, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4367]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānanti vassānassa paṭhamo māso iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo, pariḷāhasamayo, gilānasamayo, kammasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: it is the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever season, comprising the last one-and-a-half months of summer and the first month of the rainy season; he is sick; he is working; he is traveling.’”*";
P_HTM[4368]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[4369]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ajjhokāse cīvarakammaṃ karontā sarajena vātena okiṇṇā honti. Devo ca thokaṃ thokaṃ phusāyati.**Soon afterwards a number of monks were making robes out in the open, when they were hit by dusty winds and fine rain.*";
P_HTM[4370]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā na nahāyanti, kilinnena gattena sayanti.**But because they were afraid of wrongdoing, they did not bathe afterwards, and they went to sleep while still moist.*";
P_HTM[4371]="*Cīvarampi senāsanampi dussati.**As a consequence, their robes and beds were soiled.*";
P_HTM[4372]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. …*";
P_HTM[4373]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, vātavuṭṭhisamaye orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyituṃ.**“Monks, if there is wind and rain, I allow you to bathe at intervals of less than a half-month.*";
P_HTM[4374]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4375]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu orenaddhamāsaṃ nahāyeyya, aññatra samayā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk bathes at intervals of less than a half-month, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4376]="*Tatthāyaṃ samayo. Diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānanti vassānassa paṭhamo māso iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo, pariḷāhasamayo, gilānasamayo, kammasamayo, addhānagamanasamayo, vātavuṭṭhisamayo—ayaṃ tattha samayo”ti.**These are the appropriate occasions: it is the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever season, comprising the last one-and-a-half months of summer and the first month of the rainy season; he is sick; he is working; he is traveling; there is wind and rain.’”*";
P_HTM[4377]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4378]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4379]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4380]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4381]="*Orenaddhamāsanti**At intervals of less than a half-month:*";
P_HTM[4382]="*ūnakaddhamāsaṃ.**after less than a half-month.*";
P_HTM[4383]="*Nahāyeyyāti**Bathes:*";
P_HTM[4384]="*cuṇṇena vā mattikāya vā nahāyati, payoge payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if he bathes with bath powder or soap, then for every effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4385]="*Nahānapariyosāne, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the bath is finished, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4386]="*Aññatra samayāti**Except on an appropriate occasion:*";
P_HTM[4387]="*ṭhapetvā samayaṃ.**unless it is an appropriate occasion.*";
P_HTM[4388]="*Uṇhasamayo nāma**The hot season:*";
P_HTM[4389]="*diyaḍḍho māso seso gimhānaṃ.**the last month-and-a-half of summer.*";
P_HTM[4390]="*Pariḷāhasamayo nāma**The fever season:*";
P_HTM[4391]="*vassānassa paṭhamo māso “iccete aḍḍhateyyamāsā uṇhasamayo pariḷāhasamayo”ti nahāyitabbaṃ.**the first month of the rainy season. During the two-and-a-half-month period of the hot season and the fever season, he may bathe.*";
P_HTM[4392]="*Gilānasamayo nāma**He is sick:*";
P_HTM[4393]="*yassa vinā nahānena na phāsu hoti. Gilānasamayoti nahāyitabbaṃ.**he is not comfortable without bathing. If he is sick, he may bathe.*";
P_HTM[4394]="*Kammasamayo nāma**He is working:*";
P_HTM[4395]="*antamaso pariveṇampi sammaṭṭhaṃ hoti. “Kammasamayo”ti nahāyitabbaṃ.**even if he just sweeps the precincts of a building. If he is working, he may bathe.*";
P_HTM[4396]="*Addhānagamanasamayo nāma**He is traveling:*";
P_HTM[4397]="*“addhayojanaṃ gacchissāmī”ti nahāyitabbaṃ, gacchantena nahāyitabbaṃ, gatena nahāyitabbaṃ.**if he intends to travel six kilometers, he may bathe; while traveling, he may bathe; after he has traveled, he may bathe.*";
P_HTM[4398]="*Vātavuṭṭhisamayo nāma**There is wind and rain:*";
P_HTM[4399]="*bhikkhū sarajena vātena okiṇṇā honti, dve vā tīṇi vā udakaphusitāni kāye patitāni honti. “Vātavuṭṭhisamayo”ti nahāyitabbaṃ.**monks are hit by dusty winds, and two or three drops of rain fall on their bodies. If there is wind and rain, they may bathe.*";
P_HTM[4400]="*Ūnakaddhamāse ūnakasaññī, aññatra samayā, nahāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an interval of less than a half-month, and he perceives it as less, and he bathes, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4401]="*Ūnakaddhamāse vematiko, aññatra samayā, nahāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an interval of less than a half-month, but he is unsure of it, and he bathes, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4402]="*Ūnakaddhamāse atirekasaññī, aññatra samayā, nahāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an interval of less than a half-month, but he perceives it as more, and he bathes, except on an appropriate occasion, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4403]="*Atirekaddhamāse ūnakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an interval of more than a half-month, but he perceives it as less, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4404]="*Atirekaddhamāse vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an interval of more than a half-month, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4405]="*Atirekaddhamāse atirekasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is an interval of more than a half-month, and he perceives it as more, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4406]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4407]="*samaye,**if it is an appropriate occasion;*";
P_HTM[4408]="*addhamāsaṃ nahāyati,**if he bathes at intervals of a half-month;*";
P_HTM[4409]="*atirekaddhamāsaṃ nahāyati,**if he bathes at intervals of more than a half-month;*";
P_HTM[4410]="*pāraṃ gacchanto nahāyati,**if he bathes while crossing a body of water;*";
P_HTM[4411]="*sabbapaccantimesu janapadesu,**if he is not in the central Ganges plain;*";
P_HTM[4412]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[4413]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4414]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4415]="*Nahānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on bathing, the seventh is finished.*";
P_HTM[4416]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4417]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4418]="*58. Dubbaṇṇakaraṇasikkhāpada**58. The training rule on making stains*";
P_HTM[4419]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4420]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū ca paribbājakā ca sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti. Antarāmagge corā nikkhamitvā te acchindiṃsu.**a number of monks and wanderers were robbed while traveling from Sāketa to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[4421]="*Sāvatthiyā rājabhaṭā nikkhamitvā te core sabhaṇḍe gahetvā bhikkhūnaṃ santike dūtaṃ pāhesuṃ—**The King’s men set out from Sāvatthī and caught the thieves and their loot. They then sent a message to the monks:*";
P_HTM[4422]="*“āgacchantu, bhadantā, sakaṃ sakaṃ cīvaraṃ sañjānitvā gaṇhantū”ti.**“Venerables, please come and pick out your own robes.”*";
P_HTM[4423]="*Bhikkhū na sañjānanti.**But the monks did not recognize them.*";
P_HTM[4424]="*Te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The people complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4425]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā attano attano cīvaraṃ na sañjānissantī”ti.**“How can they not recognize their own robes?”*";
P_HTM[4426]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[4427]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[4428]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhūnaṃ tadanucchavikaṃ tadanulomikaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**He had the Sangha gathered, gave a teaching on what is right and proper, and then addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[4429]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[4430]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya, saṅghaphāsutāya …pe…**for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it,*";
P_HTM[4431]="*saddhammaṭṭhitiyā, vinayānuggahāya.**for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[4432]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4433]="*“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā cīvaralābhena tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ ādātabbaṃ—nīlaṃ vā kaddamaṃ vā kāḷasāmaṃ vā. Anādā ce bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ navaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘When a monk gets a new robe, he should apply one of three kinds of stains: blue-green, mud-color, or dark brown. If a monk uses a new robe without applying any of the three kinds of stains, he commits an offense entailing confession.’*";
P_HTM[4434]="*Navaṃ nāma**New:*";
P_HTM[4435]="*akatakappaṃ vuccati.**a mark has not been made is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[4436]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**A robe:*";
P_HTM[4437]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ.**one of the six kinds of robes.*";
P_HTM[4438]="*Tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ ādātabbanti**He should apply one of three kinds of stains:*";
P_HTM[4439]="*antamaso kusaggenapi ādātabbaṃ.**even if he just applies what fits on the tip of a blade of grass.*";
P_HTM[4440]="*Nīlaṃ nāma**Blue-green:*";
P_HTM[4441]="*dve nīlāni— kaṃsanīlaṃ, palāsanīlaṃ.**there are two kinds of blue-green: the color of copper-sulphate and the color of leaves.*";
P_HTM[4442]="*Kaddamo nāma**Mud-color:*";
P_HTM[4443]="*odako vuccati.**watery is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[4444]="*Kāḷasāmaṃ nāma**Dark brown:*";
P_HTM[4445]="*yaṃ kiñci kāḷasāmakaṃ.**whatever is dark brownish.*";
P_HTM[4446]="*Anādā ce bhikkhu tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇanti**If a monk … without applying any of the three kinds of stains:*";
P_HTM[4447]="*antamaso kusaggenapi anādiyitvā tiṇṇaṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇānaṃ aññataraṃ dubbaṇṇakaraṇaṃ navaṃ cīvaraṃ paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he uses a new robe without first applying one of the three kinds of stains, even just the amount on the tip of a blade of grass, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4448]="*Anādinne anādinnasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been applied, and he perceives that it has not, and he uses the robe, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4449]="*Anādinne vematiko paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been applied, but he is unsure of it, and he uses the robe, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4450]="*Anādinne ādinnasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been applied, but he perceives that it has, and he uses the robe, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4451]="*Ādinne anādinnasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been applied, but he perceives that it has not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4452]="*Ādinne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been applied, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4453]="*Ādinne ādinnasaññī, anāpatti.**If it has been applied, and he perceives that it has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4454]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4455]="*ādiyitvā paribhuñjati,**if he applies the stain and then uses it;*";
P_HTM[4456]="*kappo naṭṭho hoti,**if the mark has disappeared;*";
P_HTM[4457]="*kappakatokāso jiṇṇo hoti,**if the area where the mark was applied is worn;*";
P_HTM[4458]="*kappakatena akappakataṃ saṃsibbitaṃ hoti,**if what had been marked is sewn together with what has not been marked;*";
P_HTM[4459]="*aggaḷe,**if it is a patch;*";
P_HTM[4460]="*anuvāte,**if it is a lengthwise border;*";
P_HTM[4461]="*paribhaṇḍe,**if it is a crosswise border;*";
P_HTM[4462]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4463]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4464]="*Dubbaṇṇakaraṇasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on making stains, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4465]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4466]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4467]="*59. Vikappanasikkhāpada**59. The training rule on transferring to another*";
P_HTM[4468]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4469]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhātuno saddhivihārikassa bhikkhuno sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjati.**At that time Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had transferred a robe to a monk who was his brother’s student. He then used that robe without that monk having relinquished it.*";
P_HTM[4470]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi—**That monk told the monks,*";
P_HTM[4471]="*“ayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto mayhaṃ cīvaraṃ sāmaṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjatī”ti.**“Venerable Upananada is using a robe that he has transferred to me, even though I haven’t relinquished it.”*";
P_HTM[4472]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized Upananda,*";
P_HTM[4473]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Upananda use a robe he has transferred, without the other monk relinquishing it?” …*";
P_HTM[4474]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, upananda, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjasī”ti?**“Is it true, Upananda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[4475]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4476]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[4477]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhussa sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjissasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[4478]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4479]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4480]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa vā bhikkhuniyā vā sikkhamānāya vā sāmaṇerassa vā sāmaṇeriyā vā sāmaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappetvā appaccuddhāraṇaṃ paribhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk himself transfers a robe to a monk, to a nun, to a trainee nun, to a novice monk, or to a novice nun, and he then uses it without it first being relinquished, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4481]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4482]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4483]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4484]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4485]="*Bhikkhussāti**To a monk:*";
P_HTM[4486]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**to another monk.*";
P_HTM[4487]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[4488]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[4489]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[4490]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one training for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[4491]="*Sāmaṇero nāma**A novice monk:*";
P_HTM[4492]="*dasasikkhāpadiko.**a male training in the ten training rules.*";
P_HTM[4493]="*Sāmaṇerī nāma**A novice nun:*";
P_HTM[4494]="*dasasikkhāpadikā.**a female training in the ten training rules.*";
P_HTM[4495]="*Sāmanti**Himself:*";
P_HTM[4496]="*sayaṃ vikappetvā.**having himself done the transfer.*";
P_HTM[4497]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**A robe:*";
P_HTM[4498]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ.**one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[4499]="*Vikappanā nāma**Transfer:*";
P_HTM[4500]="*dve vikappanā— sammukhāvikappanā ca parammukhāvikappanā ca.**there are two kinds of transfers: transfer face-to-face and transfer in the absence of.*";
P_HTM[4501]="*Sammukhāvikappanā nāma**Transfer face-to-face:*";
P_HTM[4502]="*“imaṃ cīvaraṃ tuyhaṃ vikappemi itthannāmassa vā”ti.**one should say, “I transfer this robe-cloth to you,” or “I transfer this robe-cloth to so-and-so.”*";
P_HTM[4503]="*Parammukhāvikappanā nāma**Transfer in the absence of:*";
P_HTM[4504]="*“imaṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanatthāya tuyhaṃ dammī”ti.**one should say, “I give this robe-cloth to you for the purpose of transfer.”*";
P_HTM[4505]="*Tena vattabbo— “ko te mitto vā sandiṭṭho vā”ti?**The other should ask, “Who is your friend or companion?”*";
P_HTM[4506]="*“Itthannāmo ca itthannāmo cā”ti.**One should reply, “So-and-so and so-and-so.”*";
P_HTM[4507]="*Tena vattabbo— “ahaṃ tesaṃ dammi, tesaṃ santakaṃ paribhuñja vā vissajjehi vā yathāpaccayaṃ vā karohī”ti.**The other should say, “I give it to them. Please use their property, give it away, or do as you like with it.”*";
P_HTM[4508]="*Appaccuddhāraṇaṃ nāma**Without it first being relinquished:*";
P_HTM[4509]="*tassa vā adinnaṃ, tassa vā avissasanto paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if it is not given to him or he uses it without taking it on trust, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4510]="*Appaccuddhāraṇe appaccuddhāraṇasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, and he perceives that it has not, and he uses it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4511]="*Appaccuddhāraṇe vematiko paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, but he is unsure of it, and he uses it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4512]="*Appaccuddhāraṇe appaccuddhāraṇasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, but he perceives that it has, and he uses it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4513]="*Adhiṭṭheti vā vissajjeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he determines it or gives it away, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4514]="*Paccuddhāraṇe appaccuddhāraṇasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been relinquished, but he perceives that it has not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4515]="*Paccuddhāraṇe vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been relinquished, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4516]="*Paccuddhāraṇe paccuddhāraṇasaññī, anāpatti.**If it has been relinquished, and he perceives that it has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4517]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4518]="*so vā deti,**if the other person gives it; or*";
P_HTM[4519]="*tassa vā vissasanto paribhuñjati,**if he uses it after taking the other person’s property on trust;*";
P_HTM[4520]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4521]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4522]="*Vikappanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on transferring to another, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4523]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4524]="*Surāpānavagga**The sub-chapter on drinking alcohol*";
P_HTM[4525]="*60. Cīvaraapanidhānasikkhāpada**60. The training rule on hiding robes*";
P_HTM[4526]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4527]="*Tena kho pana samayena sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū asannihitaparikkhārā honti.**On one occasion when the monks from the group of seventeen had not put away their requisites,*";
P_HTM[4528]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhenti.**the monks from the group of six hid their bowls and robes.*";
P_HTM[4529]="*Sattarasavaggiyā bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The monks from the group of seventeen said to them,*";
P_HTM[4530]="*“dethāvuso, amhākaṃ pattampi cīvarampī”ti.**“Give us our bowls and robes.”*";
P_HTM[4531]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū hasanti, te rodanti.**The monks from the group of six laughed, but the monks from the group of seventeen cried.*";
P_HTM[4532]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The monks asked them,*";
P_HTM[4533]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?**“Why are you crying?”*";
P_HTM[4534]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū amhākaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhentī”ti.**“Because the monks from the group of six have hidden our bowls and robes.”*";
P_HTM[4535]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4536]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six hide the bowls and robes of other monks?” …*";
P_HTM[4537]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[4538]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4539]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[4540]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ pattampi cīvarampi apanidhessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[4541]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4542]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4543]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ vā kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidheyya vā apanidhāpeyya vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk hides a monk’s bowl, robe, sitting mat, needle case, or belt, or he has it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4544]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4545]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4546]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4547]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4548]="*Bhikkhussāti**A monk’s:*";
P_HTM[4549]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**another monk’s.*";
P_HTM[4550]="*Patto nāma**Bowl:*";
P_HTM[4551]="*dve pattā—ayopatto, mattikāpatto.**There are two kinds of bowls: iron bowls and ceramic bowls.*";
P_HTM[4552]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**Robe:*";
P_HTM[4553]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ, vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ.**one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[4554]="*Nisīdanaṃ nāma**sitting mat:*";
P_HTM[4555]="*sadasaṃ vuccati.**one with a border is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[4556]="*Sūcigharaṃ nāma**Needle case:*";
P_HTM[4557]="*sasūcikaṃ vā asūcikaṃ vā.**with or without needles.*";
P_HTM[4558]="*Kāyabandhanaṃ nāma**Belt:*";
P_HTM[4559]="*dve kāyabandhanāni— paṭṭikā, sūkarantakaṃ.**there are two kinds of belts: those made from strips of cloth and those made from pigs’ intestines.*";
P_HTM[4560]="*Apanidheyya vāti**Hides:*";
P_HTM[4561]="*sayaṃ apanidheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he hides it himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4562]="*Apanidhāpeyya vāti**Has hidden:*";
P_HTM[4563]="*aññaṃ āṇāpesi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4564]="*Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi apanidheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he only asks once, then even if the other hides many things, he commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4565]="*Antamaso hasāpekkhopīti**Even if just for a laugh:*";
P_HTM[4566]="*kīḷādhippāyo.**aiming to have fun.*";
P_HTM[4567]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ vā kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he hides his bowl or robe or sitting mat or needle case or belt, or he has it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4568]="*Upasampanne vematiko …pe…**If the other monk is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he hides his bowl or robe or sitting mat or needle case or belt, or he has it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4569]="*upasampanne anupasampannasaññī pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā nisīdanaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ vā kāyabandhanaṃ vā apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he hides his bowl or robe or sitting mat or needle case or belt, or he has it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4570]="*Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he hides another requisite, or he has it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4571]="*Anupasampannassa pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ apanidheti vā apanidhāpeti vā, antamaso hasāpekkhopi, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he hides the bowl or robe or other requisite of someone who is not fully ordained, or he has it hidden, even if just for a laugh, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4572]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4573]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4574]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4575]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4576]="*nahasādhippāyo,**if he is not aiming to have fun;*";
P_HTM[4577]="*dunnikkhittaṃ paṭisāmeti,**if he puts away what has been improperly put away;*";
P_HTM[4578]="*“dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā dassāmī”ti paṭisāmeti,**if he puts something away with the thought, “After giving a teaching, I’ll give it back;”*";
P_HTM[4579]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4580]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4581]="*Cīvaraapanidhānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on hiding robes, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4582]="*Surāpānavaggo chaṭṭho.**The sixth sub-chapter on drinking alcohol is finished.*";
P_HTM[4583]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[4584]="*Surā aṅguli hāso ca,**Alcohol, finger, and laughter,*";
P_HTM[4585]="*anādariyañca bhiṃsanaṃ;**And disrespect, scaring;*";
P_HTM[4586]="*Jotinahānadubbaṇṇaṃ,**Fire, bathing, stain,*";
P_HTM[4587]="*sāmaṃ apanidhena cāti.**Himself, and with hiding.*";
P_HTM[4588]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4589]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4590]="*61. Sañciccasikkhāpada**61. The training rule on intentionally*";
P_HTM[4591]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4592]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī issāso hoti, kākā cassa amanāpā honti.**At that time Venerable Udāyī was skilled in archery. And because he disliked crows,*";
P_HTM[4593]="*So kāke vijjhitvā vijjhitvā sīsaṃ chinditvā sūle paṭipāṭiyā ṭhapesi.**he shot them. He cut off their heads and then set them out in a row impaled on stakes.*";
P_HTM[4594]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The monks asked him,*";
P_HTM[4595]="*“kenime, āvuso, kākā jīvitā voropitā”ti?**“Who killed these crows?”*";
P_HTM[4596]="*“Mayā, āvuso.**“I did.*";
P_HTM[4597]="*Amanāpā me kākā”ti.**I don’t like crows.”*";
P_HTM[4598]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[4599]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā udāyī sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropessatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Udāyī intentionally kill living beings?” …*";
P_HTM[4600]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, udāyi, sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropesī”ti?**“Is it true, Udāyī, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[4601]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4602]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[4603]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropessasi.**“Foolish man, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[4604]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4605]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4606]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu sañcicca pāṇaṃ jīvitā voropeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk intentionally kills a living being, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4607]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4608]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4609]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4610]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4611]="*Sañciccāti**Intentionally:*";
P_HTM[4612]="*jānanto sañjānanto cecca abhivitaritvā vītikkamo.**knowing, perceiving, having intended, having decided, he transgresses.*";
P_HTM[4613]="*Pāṇo nāma**A living being:*";
P_HTM[4614]="*tiracchānagatapāṇo vuccati.**an animal is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[4615]="*Jīvitā voropeyyāti**Kills:*";
P_HTM[4616]="*jīvitindriyaṃ upacchindati uparodheti santatiṃ vikopeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he cuts off and makes an end of the life faculty, if he destroys its continuity, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4617]="*Pāṇe pāṇasaññī jīvitā voropeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a living being, and he perceives it as such, and he kills it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4618]="*Pāṇe vematiko jīvitā voropeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a living being, but he is unsure of it, and he kills it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4619]="*Pāṇe appāṇasaññī jīvitā voropeti, anāpatti.**If it is a living being, but he does not perceive it as such, and he kills it, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4620]="*Appāṇe pāṇasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a living being, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4621]="*Appāṇe vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a living being, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4622]="*Appāṇe appāṇasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a living being, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4623]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4624]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[4625]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[4626]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[4627]="*namaraṇādhippāyassa,**if he is not aiming at death;*";
P_HTM[4628]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4629]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4630]="*Sañciccasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on intentionally, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4631]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4632]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4633]="*62. Sappāṇakasikkhāpada**62. The training rule on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4634]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4635]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ paribhuñjanti.**the monks from the group of six were using water that they knew contained living beings.*";
P_HTM[4636]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4637]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ paribhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six use water that they know contains living beings?” …*";
P_HTM[4638]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ paribhuñjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[4639]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4640]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[4641]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ paribhuñjissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[4642]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4643]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4644]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ sappāṇakaṃ udakaṃ paribhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk uses water that he knows contains living beings, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4645]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4646]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4647]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4648]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4649]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[4650]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti.**he knows by himself or others have told him.*";
P_HTM[4651]="*“Sappāṇakan”ti jānanto, “paribhogena marissantī”ti jānanto paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he uses it, knowing that it contains living beings and knowing that they will die if the water is used, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4652]="*Sappāṇake sappāṇakasaññī paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it contains living beings, and he perceives it as such, and he uses it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4653]="*Sappāṇake vematiko paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it contains living beings, but he is unsure of it, and he uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4654]="*Sappāṇake appāṇakasaññī paribhuñjati, anāpatti.**If it contains living beings, but he does not perceive it as such, and he uses it, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4655]="*Appāṇake sappāṇakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it does not contain living beings, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4656]="*Appāṇake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it does not contain living beings, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4657]="*Appāṇake appāṇakasaññī, anāpatti.**If it does not contain living beings, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4658]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4659]="*“sappāṇakan”ti ajānanto,**if he does not know that it contains living beings;*";
P_HTM[4660]="*“appāṇakan”ti jānanto,**if he knows that it does not contain living beings;*";
P_HTM[4661]="*“paribhogena na marissantī”ti jānanto paribhuñjati,**if he uses it knowing that they will not die;*";
P_HTM[4662]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4663]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4664]="*Sappāṇakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on containing living beings, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4665]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4666]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4667]="*63. Ukkoṭanasikkhāpada**63. The training rule on reopening*";
P_HTM[4668]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4669]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ yathādhammaṃ nihatādhikaraṇaṃ punakammāya ukkoṭenti—**At that time the monks from the group of six were reopening a legal issue that they knew had been legitimately settled, saying,*";
P_HTM[4670]="*“akataṃ kammaṃ dukkaṭaṃ kammaṃ puna kātabbaṃ kammaṃ anihataṃ dunnihataṃ puna nihanitabban”ti.**“The legal procedure hasn’t been done;” “It’s been done badly;” “It should be done again;” “It’s not been settled;” “It’s been badly settled;” “It should be settled again.”*";
P_HTM[4671]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[4672]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ yathādhammaṃ nihatādhikaraṇaṃ punakammāya ukkoṭessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six reopen a legal issue that they know has been legitimately settled?” …*";
P_HTM[4673]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ yathādhammaṃ nihatādhikaraṇaṃ punakammāya ukkoṭethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you’re doing this?”*";
P_HTM[4674]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4675]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[4676]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ yathādhammaṃ nihatādhikaraṇaṃ punakammāya ukkoṭessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[4677]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4678]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4679]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ yathādhammaṃ nihatādhikaraṇaṃ punakammāya ukkoṭeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk reopens a legal issue that he knows has been legitimately settled, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4680]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4681]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4682]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4683]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4684]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[4685]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the Sangha has told him.*";
P_HTM[4686]="*Yathādhammaṃ nāma**Legitimately:*";
P_HTM[4687]="*dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena kataṃ, etaṃ yathādhammaṃ nāma.**done according to the Teaching, according to the Monastic Law, according to the Teacher’s instruction—this is called “legitimately”.*";
P_HTM[4688]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ nāma**A legal issue:*";
P_HTM[4689]="*cattāri adhikaraṇāni— vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**there are four kinds of legal issues: legal issues arising from disputes, legal issues arising from accusations, legal issues arising from offenses, legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[4690]="*Punakammāya ukkoṭeyyāti**Reopens:*";
P_HTM[4691]="*“akataṃ kammaṃ dukkaṭaṃ kammaṃ punakātabbaṃ kammaṃ anihataṃ dunnihataṃ puna nihanitabban”ti ukkoṭeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he reopens it, saying, “The legal procedure hasn’t been done;” “It’s been done badly;” “It should be done again;” “It’s not been settled;” “It’s been badly settled;” “It should be settled again,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4692]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī ukkoṭeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he reopens it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4693]="*Dhammakamme vematiko ukkoṭeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he reopens it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4694]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī ukkoṭeti, anāpatti.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he reopens it, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4695]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4696]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4697]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4698]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4699]="*“adhammena vā vaggena vā na kammārahassa vā kammaṃ katan”ti jānanto ukkoṭeti,**if he reopens it because he knows that the legal procedure was illegitimate, done by an incomplete assembly, or done against one who did not deserve it;*";
P_HTM[4700]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4701]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4702]="*Ukkoṭanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on reopening, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4703]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4704]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4705]="*64. Duṭṭhullasikkhāpada**64. The training rule on what is grave*";
P_HTM[4706]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4707]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā bhātuno saddhivihārikassa bhikkhuno ārocesi—**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan had committed an offense of intentional emission of semen.*";
P_HTM[4708]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpanno.**He told his brother’s student about this,*";
P_HTM[4709]="*Mā kassaci ārocehī”ti.**adding, “Don’t tell anyone.”*";
P_HTM[4710]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṅghaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ yāci.**Soon afterwards another monk also committed an offense of intentional emission of semen. He asked the Sangha for probation,*";
P_HTM[4711]="*Tassa saṅgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi.**which he got.*";
P_HTM[4712]="*So parivasanto taṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā etadavoca—**While he was on probation, he saw Upananda’s brother’s student and said to him,*";
P_HTM[4713]="*“ahaṃ, āvuso, sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā saṅghaṃ tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ yāciṃ, tassa me saṅgho tassā āpattiyā parivāsaṃ adāsi, sohaṃ parivasāmi, vediyāmahaṃ, āvuso, vediyatīti maṃ āyasmā dhāretū”ti.**“I’ve committed an offense of intentional emission of semen. I asked the Sangha for probation, which I got. I’m now undergoing probation. Please remember me as such.”*";
P_HTM[4714]="*“Kiṃ nu kho, āvuso, yo aññopi imaṃ āpattiṃ āpajjati sopi evaṃ karotī”ti?**“Do others who have committed this offense need to do the same?”*";
P_HTM[4715]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[4716]="*“Ayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmā upanando sakyaputto sañcetanikaṃ sukkavissaṭṭhiṃ āpattiṃ āpajjitvā so me āroceti mā kassaci ārocehī”ti.**“Venerable Upananda committed this offense and told me not to tell anyone.”*";
P_HTM[4717]="*“Kiṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, paṭicchādesī”ti?**“So did you conceal it?”*";
P_HTM[4718]="*“Evamāvuso”ti.**“Yes.”*";
P_HTM[4719]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That monk then told other monks.*";
P_HTM[4720]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[4721]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhussa jānaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādessatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk knowingly conceal a monk’s grave offense?” …*";
P_HTM[4722]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhussa jānaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādesī”ti.**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[4723]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4724]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[4725]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhussa jānaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[4726]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4727]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4728]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa jānaṃ duṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk knowingly conceals a monk’s grave offense, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4729]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4730]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4731]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4732]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4733]="*Bhikkhussāti**A monk’s:*";
P_HTM[4734]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**another monk’s.*";
P_HTM[4735]="*Jānāti nāma**Knowingly:*";
P_HTM[4736]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the offender has told him.*";
P_HTM[4737]="*Duṭṭhullā nāma āpatti**Grave offense:*";
P_HTM[4738]="*cattāri ca pārājikāni terasa ca saṅghādisesā.**the four offenses entailing expulsion and the thirteen offenses entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[4739]="*Paṭicchādeyyāti**Conceals:*";
P_HTM[4740]="*“imaṃ jānitvā codessanti, sāressanti khuṃsessanti, vambhessanti, maṅkuṃ karissanti nārocessāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte, āpatti pācittiyassa.**thinking, “If they find out about this, they’ll accuse him, remind him, scold him, censure him, humiliate him; I won’t tell,” then by the mere fact of giving up his duty, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4741]="*Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī paṭicchādeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a grave offense, and he perceives it as such, and he conceals it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4742]="*Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a grave offense, but he is unsure of it, and he conceals it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4743]="*Duṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a grave offense, but he perceives it as minor, and he conceals it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4744]="*Aduṭṭhullaṃ āpattiṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he conceals a minor offense, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4745]="*Anupasampannassa duṭṭhullaṃ vā aduṭṭhullaṃ vā ajjhācāraṃ paṭicchādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he conceals the grave or minor misconduct of one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4746]="*Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā duṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a minor offense, but he perceives it as grave, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4747]="*Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a minor offense, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4748]="*Aduṭṭhullāya āpattiyā aduṭṭhullāpattisaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a minor offense, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4749]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4750]="*“saṅghassa bhaṇḍanaṃ vā kalaho vā viggaho vā vivādo vā bhavissatī”ti nāroceti,**if he does not tell because he thinks there will be quarrels or disputes in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[4751]="*“saṅghabhedo vā saṅgharāji vā bhavissatī”ti nāroceti,**if he does not tell because he thinks there will be a fracture or schism in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[4752]="*“ayaṃ kakkhaḷo pharuso jīvitantarāyaṃ vā brahmacariyantarāyaṃ vā karissatī”ti nāroceti,**if he does not tell because he thinks the person he is telling about is cruel and harsh and that he might become a danger to life or to the living of the spiritual life;*";
P_HTM[4753]="*aññe patirūpe bhikkhū apassanto nāroceti,**if he does not tell because he does not see any suitable monks;*";
P_HTM[4754]="*nachādetukāmo nāroceti,**if he does not tell, but not because he wants to conceal;*";
P_HTM[4755]="*“paññāyissati sakena kammenā”ti nāroceti,**if he does not tell because he thinks the other person will be known through his own actions;*";
P_HTM[4756]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4757]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4758]="*Duṭṭhullasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on what is grave, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4759]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4760]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4761]="*65. Ūnavīsativassasikkhāpada**65. The training rule on less than twenty years old*";
P_HTM[4762]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[4763]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe sattarasavaggiyā dārakā sahāyakā honti.**At that time in Rājagaha there was a group of seventeen boys who were friends,*";
P_HTM[4764]="*Upālidārako tesaṃ pāmokkho hoti.**with Upāli as their leader.*";
P_HTM[4765]="*Atha kho upālissa mātāpitūnaṃ etadahosi—**Upāli’s parents considered,*";
P_HTM[4766]="*“kena nu kho upāyena upāli amhākaṃ accayena sukhañca jīveyya na ca kilameyyā”ti?**“How can we make sure that Upāli is able to live happily without exhausting himself after we’ve passed away?*";
P_HTM[4767]="*Atha kho upālissa mātāpitūnaṃ etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[4768]="*“sace kho upāli lekhaṃ sikkheyya, evaṃ kho upāli amhākaṃ accayena sukhañca jīveyya, na ca kilameyyā”ti.**He could become a clerk,*";
P_HTM[4769]="*Atha kho upālissa mātāpitūnaṃ etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[4770]="*“sace kho upāli lekhaṃ sikkhissati, aṅguliyo dukkhā bhavissanti.**but then his fingers will hurt.*";
P_HTM[4771]="*Sace kho upāli gaṇanaṃ sikkheyya, evaṃ kho upāli amhākaṃ accayena sukhañca jīveyya na ca kilameyyā”ti.**Or he could become an accountant,*";
P_HTM[4772]="*Atha kho upālissa mātāpitūnaṃ etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[4773]="*“sace kho upāli gaṇanaṃ sikkhissati, urassa dukkho bhavissati.**but then his chest will hurt.*";
P_HTM[4774]="*Sace kho upāli rūpaṃ sikkheyya, evaṃ kho upāli amhākaṃ accayena sukhañca jīveyya na ca kilameyyā”ti.**Or he could become a banker,*";
P_HTM[4775]="*Atha kho upālissa mātāpitūnaṃ etadahosi—* **";
P_HTM[4776]="*“sace kho upāli rūpaṃ sikkhissati, akkhīni dukkhā bhavissanti.**but then his eyes will hurt.*";
P_HTM[4777]="*Ime kho samaṇā sakyaputtiyā sukhasīlā sukhasamācārā subhojanāni bhuñjitvā nivātesu sayanesu sayanti.**But these Sakyan monastics have pleasant habits and a happy life. They eat nice food and sleep in beds sheltered from the wind.*";
P_HTM[4778]="*Sace kho upāli samaṇesu sakyaputtiyesu pabbajeyya, evaṃ kho upāli amhākaṃ accayena sukhañca jīveyya, na ca kilameyyā”ti.**If Upāli goes forth with them, he’ll be able to live happily without exhausting himself after we’ve passed away.”*";
P_HTM[4779]="*Assosi kho upālidārako mātāpitūnaṃ imaṃ kathāsallāpaṃ.**Upāli overheard this conversation between his parents.*";
P_HTM[4780]="*Atha kho upālidārako yena te dārakā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te dārake etadavoca—**He then went to the other boys and said,*";
P_HTM[4781]="*“etha mayaṃ, ayyā, samaṇesu sakyaputtiyesu pabbajissāmā”ti.**“Come, let’s go forth with the Sakyan monastics.”*";
P_HTM[4782]="*“Sace kho tvaṃ, ayya, pabbajissasi, evaṃ mayampi pabbajissāmā”ti.**“If you go forth, so will we.”*";
P_HTM[4783]="*Atha kho te dārakā ekamekassa mātāpitaro upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**The boys went each to his own parents and said,*";
P_HTM[4784]="*“anujānātha maṃ agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajjāyā”ti.**“Please allow me to go forth into homelessness.”*";
P_HTM[4785]="*Atha kho tesaṃ dārakānaṃ mātāpitaro—* **";
P_HTM[4786]="*“sabbepime dārakā samānacchandā kalyāṇādhippāyā”ti anujāniṃsu.**Since the parents knew that the boys all had the same desire and good intention, they gave their approval.*";
P_HTM[4787]="*Te bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā pabbajjaṃ yāciṃsu.**The boys then went to the monks and asked for the going forth.*";
P_HTM[4788]="*Te bhikkhū pabbājesuṃ upasampādesuṃ.**And the monks gave them the going forth and the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[4789]="*Te rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya rodanti—**Soon afterwards they got up early in the morning and cried,*";
P_HTM[4790]="*“yāguṃ detha, bhattaṃ detha, khādanīyaṃ dethā”ti.**“Give us rice porridge, give us a meal, give us fresh food.”*";
P_HTM[4791]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The monks said,*";
P_HTM[4792]="*“āgametha, āvuso, yāva ratti vibhāyati.**“Wait until it gets light.*";
P_HTM[4793]="*Sace yāgu bhavissati, pivissatha.**If any of that becomes available then, you can have it.*";
P_HTM[4794]="*Sace bhattaṃ bhavissati, bhuñjissatha.* **";
P_HTM[4795]="*Sace khādanīyaṃ bhavissati, khādissatha.* **";
P_HTM[4796]="*No ce bhavissati yāgu vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā, piṇḍāya caritvā bhuñjissathā”ti.**If not, you’ll eat after walking for alms.”*";
P_HTM[4797]="*Evampi kho te bhikkhū bhikkhūhi vuccamānā rodantiyeva—**But they carried on as before.*";
P_HTM[4798]="*“yāguṃ detha, bhattaṃ detha, khādanīyaṃ dethā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4799]="*Senāsanaṃ ūhadantipi ummihantipi.**And they defecated and urinated on the furniture.*";
P_HTM[4800]="*Assosi kho bhagavā rattiyā paccūsasamayaṃ paccuṭṭhāya dārakasaddaṃ.**After rising early in the morning, the Buddha heard the sound of those boys.*";
P_HTM[4801]="*Sutvāna āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—**He asked Venerable Ānanda,*";
P_HTM[4802]="*“kiṃ nu kho so, ānanda, dārakasaddo”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4803]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**who told him what was happening.*";
P_HTM[4804]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[4805]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū jānaṃ ūnavīsativassaṃ puggalaṃ upasampādentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the monks give the full ordination to people they know are less than twenty years old?”*";
P_HTM[4806]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4807]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[4808]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā jānaṃ ūnavīsativassaṃ puggalaṃ upasampādessanti.**“How can those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[4809]="*Ūnakavīsativasso, bhikkhave, puggalo akkhamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātiko hoti.**A person who is less than twenty years old is unable to endure cold and heat; hunger and thirst; horseflies, mosquitoes, wind, and the burning sun; creeping animals and insects; and rude and unwelcome speech. And they are unable to bear up with bodily feelings that are painful, severe, sharp, and destructive of life.*";
P_HTM[4810]="*Vīsativassova kho, bhikkhave, puggalo khamo hoti sītassa uṇhassa …pe…**But a person who’s twenty is able to endure these things.*";
P_HTM[4811]="*pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātiko hoti.* **";
P_HTM[4812]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4813]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4814]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ ūnavīsativassaṃ puggalaṃ upasampādeyya, so ca puggalo anupasampanno, te ca bhikkhū gārayhā, idaṃ tasmiṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives the full ordination to a person he knows is less than twenty years old, he commits an offense entailing confession. Moreover, that person has not received the full ordination and those monks are blameworthy.’”*";
P_HTM[4815]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4816]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4817]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4818]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4819]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[4820]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the candidate has told him.*";
P_HTM[4821]="*Ūnavīsativasso nāma**Less than twenty years old:*";
P_HTM[4822]="*appattavīsativasso.**who has not reached twenty years.*";
P_HTM[4823]="*“Upasampādessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariyaṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full ordination, he searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or he establishes a monastic boundary, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4824]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4825]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4826]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[4827]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariyassa ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**while the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4828]="*Ūnavīsativasse ūnavīsativassasaññī upasampādeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is less than twenty years old, and he perceives them as less, and he gives them the full ordination, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4829]="*Ūnavīsativasse vematiko upasampādeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is less than twenty years old, but he is unsure of it, and he gives them the full ordination, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4830]="*Ūnavīsativasse paripuṇṇavīsativassasaññī upasampādeti, anāpatti.**If the other person is less than twenty years old, but he perceives them as more, and he gives them the full ordination, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4831]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativasse ūnavīsativassasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is more than twenty years old, but he perceives them as less, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4832]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativasse vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is more than twenty years old, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4833]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativasse paripuṇṇavīsativassasaññī, anāpatti.**If the other person is more than twenty years old, and he perceives them as more, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4834]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4835]="*ūnavīsativassaṃ paripuṇṇavīsativassasaññī upasampādeti,**if he gives the full ordination to someone less than twenty years old, but he perceives them as more than twenty;*";
P_HTM[4836]="*paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ paripuṇṇavīsativassasaññī upasampādeti,**if he gives the full ordination to someone more than twenty years old, and he perceives them as more than twenty;*";
P_HTM[4837]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4838]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4839]="*Ūnavīsativassasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on less than twenty years old, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4840]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4841]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4842]="*66. Theyyasatthasikkhāpada**66. The training rule on a group of traveling thieves*";
P_HTM[4843]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4844]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro sattho rājagahā paṭiyālokaṃ gantukāmo hoti.**a certain group of travelers was about to go south from Rājagaha.*";
P_HTM[4845]="*Aññataro bhikkhu te manusse etadavoca—**A monk said to those people,*";
P_HTM[4846]="*“ahampāyasmantehi saddhiṃ gamissāmī”ti.**“Let me travel with you.”*";
P_HTM[4847]="*“Mayaṃ kho, bhante, suṅkaṃ pariharissāmā”ti.**“But we’re smuggling goods.”*";
P_HTM[4848]="*“Pajānāthāvuso”ti.**“That’s your business.”*";
P_HTM[4849]="*Assosuṃ kho kammiyā—**The customs officers heard*";
P_HTM[4850]="*“sattho kira suṅkaṃ pariharissatī”ti.**about that group of travelers.*";
P_HTM[4851]="*Te magge pariyuṭṭhiṃsu.**They then blocked the road,*";
P_HTM[4852]="*Atha kho te kammiyā taṃ satthaṃ gahetvā acchinditvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**caught the group, confiscated the goods, and asked that monk,*";
P_HTM[4853]="*“kissa tvaṃ, bhante, jānaṃ theyyasatthena saddhiṃ gacchasī”ti?**“Venerable, why are you knowingly traveling with a group of thieves?”*";
P_HTM[4854]="*Palibundhetvā muñciṃsu.**And they detained him.*";
P_HTM[4855]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**After being released, that monk went to Sāvatthī, where he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[4856]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[4857]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu jānaṃ theyyasatthena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk knowingly travel by appointment with a group of thieves?” …*";
P_HTM[4858]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, jānaṃ theyyasatthena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjasī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[4859]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4860]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[4861]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, jānaṃ theyyasatthena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[4862]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4863]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4864]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ theyyasatthena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk knowingly travels by appointment with a group of thieves, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4865]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4866]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4867]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4868]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4869]="*Jānāti nāma**Knowingly:*";
P_HTM[4870]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the group of travelers has told him.*";
P_HTM[4871]="*Theyyasattho nāma**A group of thieves:*";
P_HTM[4872]="*corā katakammā vā honti akatakammā vā, rājānaṃ vā theyyaṃ gacchanti suṅkaṃ vā pariharanti.**thieves who have done their deed or thieves who have not. They are stealing from the king or smuggling.*";
P_HTM[4873]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[4874]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[4875]="*Saṃvidhāyāti—**By appointment:*";
P_HTM[4876]="*“gacchāmāvuso, gacchāma, bhante; gacchāma, bhante, gacchāmāvuso, ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā gacchāmā”ti saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he makes an appointment like this: the monk says, “Let’s go,” and they reply, “Yes, let’s go, Venerable;” or they say, “Let’s go, Venerable,” and the monk replies, “Yes, let’s go;” or the monk says, “Let’s go today,” “Let’s go tomorrow,” or “Let’s go the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4877]="*Antamaso gāmantarampīti**Even just to the next village:*";
P_HTM[4878]="*kukkuṭasampāte gāme gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4879]="*Agāmake araññe addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4880]="*Theyyasatthe theyyasatthasaññī saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a group of traveling thieves, and he perceives it as such, and he travels by appointment with them, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4881]="*Theyyasatthe vematiko saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a group of traveling thieves, but he is unsure of it, and he travels by appointment with them, even just to the next village, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4882]="*Theyyasatthe atheyyasatthasaññī saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, anāpatti.**If it is a group of traveling thieves, but he does not perceive it as such, and he travels by appointment with them, even just to the next village, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4883]="*Bhikkhu saṃvidahati, manussā na saṃvidahanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the monk makes an appointment, but the group does not express its agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4884]="*Atheyyasatthe theyyasatthasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a group of traveling thieves, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4885]="*Atheyyasatthe vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a group of traveling thieves, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4886]="*Atheyyasatthe atheyyasatthasaññī anāpatti.**If it is not a group of traveling thieves, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4887]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4888]="*asaṃvidahitvā gacchati,**if he goes, but not by appointment;*";
P_HTM[4889]="*manussā saṃvidahanti bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,**if the group has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;*";
P_HTM[4890]="*visaṅketena gacchati,**if he goes, but not according to the appointment;*";
P_HTM[4891]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[4892]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4893]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4894]="*Theyyasatthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on a group of traveling thieves, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4895]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4896]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4897]="*67. Saṃvidhānasikkhāpada**67. The training rule on appointments*";
P_HTM[4898]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[4899]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchanto aññatarena gāmadvārena atikkamati.**a monk who was traveling through the Kosalan country on his way to Sāvatthī walked through the gateway of a certain village.*";
P_HTM[4900]="*Aññatarā itthī sāmikena saha bhaṇḍitvā gāmato nikkhamitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā etadavoca—**A woman who had had an argument with her husband walked through the same gateway. When she saw that monk, she asked him,*";
P_HTM[4901]="*“kahaṃ, bhante, ayyo gamissatī”ti?**“Venerable, where are you going?”*";
P_HTM[4902]="*“Sāvatthiṃ kho ahaṃ, bhagini, gamissāmī”ti.**“I’m going to Sāvatthī.”*";
P_HTM[4903]="*“Ahaṃ ayyena saddhiṃ gamissāmī”ti.**“May I go with you?”*";
P_HTM[4904]="*“Eyyāsi, bhaginī”ti.**“Sure.”*";
P_HTM[4905]="*Atha kho tassā itthiyā sāmiko gāmato nikkhamitvā manusse pucchi—**Soon afterwards that woman’s husband also left that village. He asked around,*";
P_HTM[4906]="*“apāyyo, evarūpiṃ itthiṃ passeyyāthā”ti?**“Have you seen such-and-such a woman?”*";
P_HTM[4907]="*“Esāyyo, pabbajitena saha gacchatī”ti.**“She’s walking along with a monastic.”*";
P_HTM[4908]="*Atha kho so puriso anubandhitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ gahetvā ākoṭetvā muñci.**He then followed after them, caught that monk, and gave him a beating.*";
P_HTM[4909]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle padhūpento nisīdi.**The monk sat down fuming at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[4910]="*Atha kho sā itthī taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—**And the woman said to her husband,*";
P_HTM[4911]="*“nāyyo, so bhikkhu maṃ nippātesi;**“This monk didn’t make me go;*";
P_HTM[4912]="*api ca ahameva tena bhikkhunā saddhiṃ gacchāmi;**I was the one who went with him.*";
P_HTM[4913]="*akārako so bhikkhu;**He’s innocent.*";
P_HTM[4914]="*gaccha, naṃ khamāpehī”ti.**Go and ask his forgiveness.”*";
P_HTM[4915]="*Atha kho so puriso taṃ bhikkhuṃ khamāpesi.**And he did so.*";
P_HTM[4916]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That monk then went to Sāvatthī, where he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[4917]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[4918]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu mātugāmena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk travel by appointment with a woman?” …*";
P_HTM[4919]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, mātugāmena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjasī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[4920]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4921]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[4922]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mātugāmena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjissasi.**“Foolish man, how could do this?*";
P_HTM[4923]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[4924]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ, uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[4925]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mātugāmena saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjeyya, antamaso gāmantarampi, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk travels by appointment with a woman, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[4926]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[4927]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[4928]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[4929]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[4930]="*Mātugāmo nāma**A woman:*";
P_HTM[4931]="*manussitthī, na yakkhī na petī na tiracchānagatā viññū paṭibalā subhāsitadubbhāsitaṃ duṭṭhullāduṭṭhullaṃ ājānituṃ.**a human female, not a female spirit, not a female ghost, not a female animal. She understands and is capable of discerning bad speech and good speech, what is indecent and what is decent.*";
P_HTM[4932]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[4933]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[4934]="*Saṃvidhāyāti—**By appointment:*";
P_HTM[4935]="*“gacchāma bhagini, gacchāmāyya, gacchāmāyya, gacchāma bhagini, ajja vā hiyyo vā pare vā gacchāmā”ti saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he makes an appointment like this: he says, “Let’s go,” and she replies, “Yes, let’s go, Venerable;” or she says, “Let’s go, Venerable,” and he replies, “Yes, let’s go;” or he says, “Let’s go today,” “Let’s go tomorrow,” or “Let’s go the day after tomorrow,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4936]="*Antamaso gāmantarampīti**Even just to the next village:*";
P_HTM[4937]="*kukkuṭasampāte gāme gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4938]="*Agāmake araññe addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4939]="*Mātugāme mātugāmasaññī saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, and he perceives her as such, and he travels by appointment with her, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4940]="*Mātugāme vematiko saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he is unsure of it, and he travels by appointment with her, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4941]="*Mātugāme amātugāmasaññī saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a woman, but he does not perceive her as such, and he travels by appointment with her, even just to the next village, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[4942]="*Bhikkhu saṃvidahati mātugāmo na saṃvidahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the monk makes an appointment, but the woman does not express her agreement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4943]="*Yakkhiyā vā petiyā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahitthiyā vā saddhiṃ saṃvidhāya ekaddhānamaggaṃ paṭipajjati, antamaso gāmantarampi, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he travels by appointment with a female spirit, with a female ghost, with a _paṇḍaka_, with a female animal in the form of a woman, even just to the next village, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4944]="*Amātugāme mātugāmasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4945]="*Amātugāme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a woman, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[4946]="*Amātugāme amātugāmasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not a woman, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[4947]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[4948]="*asaṃvidahitvā gacchati,**if he goes, but not by appointment;*";
P_HTM[4949]="*mātugāmo saṃvidahati bhikkhu na saṃvidahati,**if the woman has made an appointment, but he has not expressed his agreement;*";
P_HTM[4950]="*visaṅketena gacchati,**if he goes, but not according to the appointment;*";
P_HTM[4951]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[4952]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[4953]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[4954]="*Saṃvidhānasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on appointments, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[4955]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[4956]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[4957]="*68. Ariṭṭhasikkhāpada**68. The training rule on Ariṭṭha*";
P_HTM[4958]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[4959]="*Tena kho pana samayena ariṭṭhassa nāma bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti—**At that time the monk Ariṭṭha, the ex-vulture-killer, had the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[4960]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Teaching of the Buddha, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[4961]="*Assosuṃ kho sambahulā bhikkhū—**A number of monks heard*";
P_HTM[4962]="*“ariṭṭhassa kira nāma bhikkhuno gaddhabādhipubbassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**that Ariṭṭha had that view.*";
P_HTM[4963]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4964]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;* **";
P_HTM[4965]="*upasaṅkamitvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etadavocuṃ—**They went to him and asked,*";
P_HTM[4966]="*“saccaṃ kira te, āvuso ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**“Is it true, Ariṭṭha,*";
P_HTM[4967]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti?**that you have such a view?”*";
P_HTM[4968]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi— ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.**“Yes, indeed. As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[4969]="*“Mā, āvuso ariṭṭha, evaṃ avaca. Mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi. Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ. Na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**“No, Ariṭṭha, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent him. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[4970]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso ariṭṭha, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**The Buddha has given many discourses about the obstructive things being obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.*";
P_HTM[4971]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**The Buddha has said that there is little enjoyment in worldly pleasures, but much suffering and much trouble, and that the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[4972]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**The Buddha has said that worldly pleasures are similar to a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[4973]="*Maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …pe…**similar to a piece of meat …*";
P_HTM[4974]="*tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a grass torch …*";
P_HTM[4975]="*aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a pit of coals …*";
P_HTM[4976]="*supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a dream …*";
P_HTM[4977]="*yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to borrowed goods …*";
P_HTM[4978]="*rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to fruits on a tree …*";
P_HTM[4979]="*asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to a knife and chopping block …*";
P_HTM[4980]="*sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā …**similar to swords and stakes …*";
P_HTM[4981]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo”ti.**similar to a snake’s head; they are much suffering and much trouble, and the danger in them is greater.”*";
P_HTM[4982]="*Evampi kho ariṭṭho bhikkhu gaddhabādhipubbo tehi bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva taṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati—**But even though the monks corrected Ariṭṭha like this, he stubbornly held on to that bad and erroneous view, and continued to insist on it.*";
P_HTM[4983]="*“evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi— ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[4984]="*Yato ca kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Since they were unable to make him give up that view, they went to the Buddha and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[4985]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned Ariṭṭha:*";
P_HTM[4986]="*“saccaṃ kira te, ariṭṭha, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**“Is it true, Ariṭṭha, that you have such a view?”*";
P_HTM[4987]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[4988]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi— ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.**“Yes indeed, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[4989]="*Kassa nu kho nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mayā evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi?**“Foolish man, who do you think I have taught like this?*";
P_HTM[4990]="*Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, anekapariyāyena antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**Haven’t I given many discourses about the obstructive things being obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them?*";
P_HTM[4991]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā mayā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**I have said that there is little enjoyment in worldly pleasures, but much suffering and much trouble, and that the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[4992]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …pe…**I have said that worldly pleasures are similar to a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[4993]="*maṃsapesūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a piece of meat …*";
P_HTM[4994]="*tiṇukkūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a grass torch …*";
P_HTM[4995]="*aṅgārakāsūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a pit of coals …*";
P_HTM[4996]="*supinakūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a dream …*";
P_HTM[4997]="*yācitakūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to borrowed goods …*";
P_HTM[4998]="*rukkhaphalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to fruits on a tree …*";
P_HTM[4999]="*asisūnūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to a knife and chopping block …*";
P_HTM[5000]="*sattisūlūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …**similar to swords and stakes …*";
P_HTM[5001]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**similar to a snake’s head; they are much suffering and much trouble, and the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[5002]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, moghapurisa, attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhasi, attānañca khaṇasi, bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavasi.**And yet, foolish man, by misunderstanding you have misrepresented me, hurt yourself, and made much demerit.*";
P_HTM[5003]="*Tañhi te, moghapurisa, bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for your long-lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[5004]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5005]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5006]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu evaṃ vadeyya—**‘If a monk says,*";
P_HTM[5007]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them,”*";
P_HTM[5008]="*so bhikkhu bhikkhūhi evamassa vacanīyo—**then the monks should correct him like this:*";
P_HTM[5009]="*‘māyasmā evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya,**“No, Venerable, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent the Buddha. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5010]="*anekapariyāyenāvuso, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā, alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāyā’ti.**In many discourses the Buddha has declared the obstructive things to be obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5011]="*Evañca so bhikkhu bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva paggaṇheyya, so bhikkhu bhikkhūhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbo tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If that monk continues as before, the monks should press him up to three times to make him give up that view.*";
P_HTM[5012]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsiyamāno taṃ paṭinissajjeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ,**If he then gives it up, all is well.*";
P_HTM[5013]="*no ce paṭinissajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**If he does not, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5014]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5015]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5016]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5017]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5018]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Says:*";
P_HTM[5019]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5020]="*So bhikkhūti**Him:*";
P_HTM[5021]="*yo so evaṃvādī bhikkhu.**the monk who speaks in that way.*";
P_HTM[5022]="*Bhikkhūhīti**The monks:*";
P_HTM[5023]="*aññehi bhikkhūhi. Ye passanti ye suṇanti tehi vattabbo—**other monks, those who see it or hear about it, They should correct him,*";
P_HTM[5024]="*“māyasmā evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya,**“No, Venerable, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent the Buddha. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5025]="*anekapariyāyenāvuso antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāyā”ti.**In many discourses the Buddha has declared the obstructive things to be obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5026]="*Dutiyampi vattabbo.**And they should correct him a second*";
P_HTM[5027]="*Tatiyampi vattabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[5028]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If he gives up that view, all is well.*";
P_HTM[5029]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he does not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5030]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5031]="*So bhikkhu saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbo—**That monk, even if he has to be pulled into the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[5032]="*“māyasmā evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya,**“No, Venerable, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent the Buddha. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5033]="*anekapariyāyenāvuso antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāyā”ti.**In many discourses the Buddha has declared the obstructive things to be obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5034]="*Dutiyampi vattabbo.**And they should correct him a second*";
P_HTM[5035]="*Tatiyampi vattabbo.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[5036]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If he gives up that view, all is well.*";
P_HTM[5037]="*No ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he does not, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5038]="*So bhikkhu samanubhāsitabbo.**He should then be pressed.*";
P_HTM[5039]="*“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbo.**“And, monks, he should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[5040]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5041]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5042]="*Itthannāmassa bhikkhuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**Monk so-and-so has the following a bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[5043]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5044]="*So taṃ diṭṭhiṃ na paṭinissajjati.**He is not giving up that view.*";
P_HTM[5045]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ samanubhāseyya—**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press him*";
P_HTM[5046]="*tassā diṭṭhiyā paṭinissaggāya.**to make him give it up.*";
P_HTM[5047]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5048]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5049]="*Itthannāmassa bhikkhuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**Monk so-and-so has the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[5050]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5051]="*So taṃ diṭṭhiṃ na paṭinissajjati.**He is not giving up that view.*";
P_HTM[5052]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ samanubhāsati tassā diṭṭhiyā paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses him to make him give it up.*";
P_HTM[5053]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno samanubhāsanā, tassā diṭṭhiyā paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of pressing him to make him give it up should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5054]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5055]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**A second time …*";
P_HTM[5056]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi—**A third time I speak on this matter:*";
P_HTM[5057]="*suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5058]="*Itthannāmassa bhikkhuno evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**Monk so-and-so has the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[5059]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5060]="*So taṃ diṭṭhiṃ na paṭinissajjati.**He is not giving up that view.*";
P_HTM[5061]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ samanubhāsati tassā diṭṭhiyā paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses him to make him give it up.*";
P_HTM[5062]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno samanubhāsanā, tassā diṭṭhiyā paṭinissaggāya, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of pressing him to make him give it up should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5063]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5064]="*Samanubhaṭṭho saṅghena itthannāmo bhikkhu, tassā diṭṭhiyā paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha has pressed this monk to give up that view.*";
P_HTM[5065]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[5066]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5067]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5068]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5069]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he does not give up his view, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5070]="*Dhammakamme vematiko na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he does not give up his view, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5071]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he does not give up his view, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5072]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5073]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5074]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5075]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5076]="*asamanubhāsantassa,**if he has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[5077]="*paṭinissajjantassa,**if he gives it up;*";
P_HTM[5078]="*ummattakassāti.**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5079]="*if he is the first offender.* **";
P_HTM[5080]="*Ariṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on Ariṭṭha, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5081]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5082]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[5083]="*69. Ukkhittasambhogasikkhāpada**69. The training rule on living with one who has been ejected*";
P_HTM[5084]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[5085]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ tathāvādinā ariṭṭhena bhikkhunā akaṭānudhammena taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ sambhuñjantipi saṃvasantipi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six lived with the monk Ariṭṭha, and they did formal meetings and shared a sleeping place with him. Yet they knew that he was saying such things, that he had not made amends according to the rule, and that he had not given up that view.*";
P_HTM[5086]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5087]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ tathāvādinā ariṭṭhena bhikkhunā akaṭānudhammena taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ sambhuñjissantipi saṃvasissantipi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six live, do formal meetings, and share a sleeping place with the monk Ariṭṭha, even though they know that he’s saying such things, that he hasn’t made amends according to the rule, and that he hasn’t given up that view?” …*";
P_HTM[5088]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ tathāvādinā ariṭṭhena bhikkhunā akaṭānudhammena taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ sambhuñjathāpi saṃvasathāpi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[5089]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5090]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5091]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ tathāvādinā ariṭṭhena bhikkhunā akaṭānudhammena taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ sambhuñjissathāpi saṃvasissathāpi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[5092]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5093]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5094]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ tathāvādinā bhikkhunā akaṭānudhammena taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ sambhuñjeyya vā saṃvaseyya vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk lives, does formal meetings, or shares a sleeping place with a monk who he knows is saying such things, who has not made amends according to the rule, and who has not given up that view, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5095]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5096]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5097]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5098]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5099]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[5100]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the offender has told him.*";
P_HTM[5101]="*Tathāvādināti—**Who is saying such things:*";
P_HTM[5102]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti evaṃ vādinā.**one who says this: “As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5103]="*Akaṭānudhammo nāma**Who has not made amends according to the rule:*";
P_HTM[5104]="*ukkhitto anosārito.**who has been ejected and not reinstated.*";
P_HTM[5105]="*Taṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhinti**With a monk who has not given up that view:*";
P_HTM[5106]="*etaṃ diṭṭhiṃ appaṭinissaṭṭhena saddhiṃ.**with a monk who has not given up this view.*";
P_HTM[5107]="*Sambhuñjeyya vāti**Lives with:*";
P_HTM[5108]="*sambhogo nāma dve sambhogā— āmisasambhogo ca dhammasambhogo ca.**there are two types of living together: material living together and spiritual living together.*";
P_HTM[5109]="*Āmisasambhogo nāma**Material living together:*";
P_HTM[5110]="*āmisaṃ deti vā paṭiggaṇhāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he gives or receives material things, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5111]="*Dhammasambhogo nāma**Spiritual living together:*";
P_HTM[5112]="*uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā, padena uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**he recites or has the other recite. If he recites or has the other recite by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5113]="*Akkharāya uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he recites or has the other recite by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5114]="*Saṃvaseyya vāti**Does formal meetings with:*";
P_HTM[5115]="*ukkhittakena saddhiṃ uposathaṃ vā pavāraṇaṃ vā saṅghakammaṃ vā karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he does the observance-day procedure, the invitation procedure, or a legal procedure with one who has been ejected, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5116]="*Saha vā seyyaṃ kappeyyāti**Shares a sleeping place with:*";
P_HTM[5117]="*ekacchanne ukkhittake nipanne bhikkhu nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**under the same ceiling: if the monk lies down when the one who has been ejected is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5118]="*Bhikkhu nipanne ukkhittako nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the monk is already lying down when the one who has been ejected lies down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5119]="*Ubho vā nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5120]="*Uṭṭhahitvā punappunaṃ nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5121]="*Ukkhittake ukkhittakasaññī sambhuñjati vā saṃvasati vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other monk has been ejected, and he perceives him as such, and he lives or does formal meetings or shares a sleeping place with him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5122]="*Ukkhittake vematiko sambhuñjati vā saṃvasati vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk has been ejected, but he is unsure of it, and he lives or does formal meetings or shares a sleeping place with him, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5123]="*Ukkhittake anukkhittakasaññī sambhuñjati vā saṃvasati vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeti, anāpatti.**If the other monk has been ejected, but he does not perceive him as such, and he lives or does formal meetings or shares a sleeping place with him, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5124]="*Anukkhittake ukkhittakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk has not been ejected, but he perceives him as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5125]="*Anukkhittake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other monk has not been ejected, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5126]="*Anukkhittake anukkhittakasaññī, anāpatti.**If the other monk has not been ejected, and he does not perceive him as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5127]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5128]="*anukkhittoti jānāti,**if he knows that he has not been ejected;*";
P_HTM[5129]="*ukkhitto osāritoti jānāti,**if he knows that he has been reinstated after being ejected;*";
P_HTM[5130]="*taṃ diṭṭhiṃ paṭinissaṭṭhoti jānāti,**if he knows that he has given up that view;*";
P_HTM[5131]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5132]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5133]="*Ukkhittasambhogasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on living with one who has been ejected, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5134]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5135]="*Sappāṇakavagga**The sub-chapter on containing living beings*";
P_HTM[5136]="*70. Kaṇṭakasikkhāpada**70. The training rule on Kaṇṭaka*";
P_HTM[5137]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[5138]="*Tena kho pana samayena kaṇṭakassa nāma samaṇuddesassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ hoti—**At that time the novice monastic Kaṇṭaka had the following bad and erroneous view:*";
P_HTM[5139]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the teachings of the Buddha, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5140]="*Assosuṃ kho sambahulā bhikkhū kaṇṭakassa nāma kira samaṇuddesassa evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**A number of monks heard that the novice monastic Kaṇṭaka had that view.*";
P_HTM[5141]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5142]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū yena kaṇṭako samaṇuddeso tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ etadavocuṃ—**They went to see him and asked,*";
P_HTM[5143]="*“saccaṃ kira te, āvuso kaṇṭaka, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**“Is it true, Kaṇṭaka, that you have such a view?”*";
P_HTM[5144]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5145]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi— ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.**“Yes, indeed. As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5146]="*“Mā, āvuso kaṇṭaka, evaṃ avaca. Mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi. Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ. Na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**“No, Kaṇṭaka, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent him. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5147]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso kaṇṭaka, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya.**The Buddha has given many discourses about the obstructive things being obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.*";
P_HTM[5148]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā bhagavatā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo …pe…**The Buddha has said that there’s little enjoyment in worldly pleasures, but much suffering and much trouble, and that the danger in them is greater. … ”*";
P_HTM[5149]="*evampi kho kaṇṭako samaṇuddeso tehi bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva taṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ thāmasā parāmāsā abhinivissa voharati—**But even though the monks corrected Kaṇṭaka like this, he stubbornly held on to that bad and erroneous view, and he continued to insist on it.*";
P_HTM[5150]="*“evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi— ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.* **";
P_HTM[5151]="*Yato ca kho te bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ etasmā pāpakā diṭṭhigatā vivecetuṃ, atha kho te bhikkhū yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Since those monks were unable to make him give up that view, they went to the Buddha and told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[5152]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the Kaṇṭaka:*";
P_HTM[5153]="*“saccaṃ kira te, kaṇṭaka, evarūpaṃ pāpakaṃ diṭṭhigataṃ uppannaṃ—**“Is it true, Kaṇṭaka, that you have such a view?”*";
P_HTM[5154]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5155]="*“Evaṃ byā kho ahaṃ, bhante, bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi— ‘yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’”ti.**“Yes indeed, Venerable Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5156]="*“Kassa nu kho nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, mayā evaṃ dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāsi?**“Foolish man, who do you think I have taught like this?*";
P_HTM[5157]="*Nanu mayā, moghapurisa, anekapariyāyena antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā, alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāya?**Haven’t I given many discourses about the obstructive things being obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them?*";
P_HTM[5158]="*Appassādā kāmā vuttā mayā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**I have said that there is little enjoyment in worldly pleasures, but much suffering and much trouble, and that the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[5159]="*Aṭṭhikaṅkalūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā …pe…**I have said that worldly pleasures are similar to a skeleton …*";
P_HTM[5160]="*sappasirūpamā kāmā vuttā mayā bahudukkhā bahupāyāsā, ādīnavo ettha bhiyyo.**similar to a snake’s head; they are much suffering and much trouble, and the danger in them is greater.*";
P_HTM[5161]="*Atha ca pana tvaṃ, moghapurisa, attanā duggahitena amhe ceva abbhācikkhasi attānañca khaṇasi bahuñca apuññaṃ pasavasi.**And yet, foolish man, by misunderstanding you have misrepresented me, hurt yourself, and made much demerit.*";
P_HTM[5162]="*Tañhi te, moghapurisa, bhavissati dīgharattaṃ ahitāya dukkhāya.**This will be for your long-lasting harm and suffering.*";
P_HTM[5163]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5164]="*pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti.**and cause some to lose it.”*";
P_HTM[5165]="*Vigarahitvā …pe…**Having rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[5166]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5167]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, saṅgho kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ nāsetu.**“Well then, monks, the Sangha should expel the novice monastic Kaṇṭaka.*";
P_HTM[5168]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nāsetabbo—**And this is how he should be expelled:*";
P_HTM[5169]="*‘ajjatagge te, āvuso kaṇṭaka, na ceva so bhagavā satthā apadisitabbo.**‘From today, Kaṇṭaka, you may not refer to the Buddha as your teacher.*";
P_HTM[5170]="*Yampi caññe samaṇuddesā labhanti bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ dirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ sāpi te natthi.**And you can no longer share a sleeping place with the monks for two or three nights, as can other novices.*";
P_HTM[5171]="*Cara pire vinassā’”ti.**Go! Away with you!’”*";
P_HTM[5172]="*Atha kho saṅgho kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ nāsesi.**The Sangha then expelled Kaṇṭaka.*";
P_HTM[5173]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ tathānāsitaṃ kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ upalāpentipi upaṭṭhāpentipi sambhuñjantipi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappenti.**Soon afterwards the monks from the group of six supported Kaṇṭaka, and they were attended on by him, lived with him, and shared a sleeping place with him. Yet they knew that he had been expelled.*";
P_HTM[5174]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[5175]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ tathānāsitaṃ kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ upalāpessantipi upaṭṭhāpessantipi sambhuñjissantipi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six support Kaṇṭaka, and be attended on by him, live with him, and share a sleeping place with him, even though they know that he has been expelled?” …*";
P_HTM[5176]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ tathānāsitaṃ kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ upalāpethāpi upaṭṭhāpethāpi sambhuñjathāpi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[5177]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5178]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5179]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ tathānāsitaṃ kaṇṭakaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ upalāpessathāpi upaṭṭhāpessathāpi sambhuñjissathāpi sahāpi seyyaṃ kappessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[5180]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5181]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5182]="*“Samaṇuddesopi ce evaṃ vadeyya—**‘Also if a novice monastic says,*";
P_HTM[5183]="*‘tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā’ti,**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them,”*";
P_HTM[5184]="*so samaṇuddeso bhikkhūhi evamassa vacanīyo—**then the monks should correct him like this:*";
P_HTM[5185]="*‘māvuso samaṇuddesa, evaṃ avaca, mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi, na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ, na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**“No, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent the Buddha. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5186]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso samaṇuddesa, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāyā’ti.**In many discourses the Buddha has declared the obstructive things to be obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5187]="*Evañca so samaṇuddeso bhikkhūhi vuccamāno tatheva paggaṇheyya, so samaṇuddeso bhikkhūhi evamassa vacanīyo—**If that novice monastic continues as before, he should be told:*";
P_HTM[5188]="*‘ajjatagge te, āvuso samaṇuddesa, na ceva so bhagavā satthā apadisitabbo.**“From today on you may not refer to the Buddha as your teacher.*";
P_HTM[5189]="*Yampi caññe samaṇuddesā labhanti bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ dirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ sāpi te natthi.**And you can no longer share a sleeping place with the monks for two or three nights, as can other novice monastics.*";
P_HTM[5190]="*Cara pire vinassā’ti.**Go! Away with you!”*";
P_HTM[5191]="*Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ tathānāsitaṃ samaṇuddesaṃ upalāpeyya vā upaṭṭhāpeyya vā sambhuñjeyya vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**If a monk supports that novice monastic, or he is attended on by him, lives with him, or shares a sleeping place with him, even though he knows that he has been expelled in this way, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5192]="*Samaṇuddeso nāma**A novice monastic:*";
P_HTM[5193]="*sāmaṇero vuccati.**a novice monk is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[5194]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Says:*";
P_HTM[5195]="*“tathāhaṃ bhagavatā dhammaṃ desitaṃ ājānāmi, yathā yeme antarāyikā dhammā vuttā bhagavatā, te paṭisevato nālaṃ antarāyāyā”ti.**“As I understand the Buddha’s Teaching, the things he calls obstructive are unable to obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5196]="*So samaṇuddesoti**Him:*";
P_HTM[5197]="*yo so evaṃvādī samaṇuddeso.**the novice monastic who speaks in that way.*";
P_HTM[5198]="*Bhikkhūhīti**The monks:*";
P_HTM[5199]="*aññehi bhikkhūhi, ye passanti ye suṇanti tehi vattabbo— “mā, āvuso samaṇuddesa, evaṃ avaca. Mā bhagavantaṃ abbhācikkhi. Na hi sādhu bhagavato abbhakkhānaṃ. Na hi bhagavā evaṃ vadeyya.**other monks, those who see it or hear about it. They should correct him, “No, don’t misrepresent the Buddha, for it’s not good to misrepresent the Buddha. The Buddha would never say such a thing.*";
P_HTM[5200]="*Anekapariyāyenāvuso samaṇuddesa, antarāyikā dhammā antarāyikā vuttā bhagavatā. Alañca pana te paṭisevato antarāyāyā”ti.**In many discourses the Buddha has declared the obstructive things to be obstructive and how they obstruct one who indulges in them.”*";
P_HTM[5201]="*Dutiyampi vattabbo …**And they should correct him a second time …*";
P_HTM[5202]="*tatiyampi vattabbo …**And they should correct him a third time …*";
P_HTM[5203]="*sace paṭinissajjati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ, no ce paṭinissajjati so samaṇuddeso bhikkhūhi evamassa vacanīyo—**If he gives up that view, all is well. If he does not, he should be told:*";
P_HTM[5204]="*“ajjatagge te, āvuso samaṇuddesa, na ceva so bhagavā satthā apadisitabbo.**“From today on you may not refer to the Buddha as your teacher.*";
P_HTM[5205]="*Yampi caññe samaṇuddesā labhanti bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ dirattatirattaṃ sahaseyyaṃ sāpi te natthi.**And you can no longer share a sleeping place with the monks for two or three nights, as can other novice monastics.*";
P_HTM[5206]="*Cara pire vinassā”ti.**Go! Away with you!”*";
P_HTM[5207]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5208]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5209]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5210]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5211]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[5212]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the offending novice monastic has told him.*";
P_HTM[5213]="*Tathānāsitanti**Expelled in this way:*";
P_HTM[5214]="*evaṃ nāsitaṃ.**expelled like this.*";
P_HTM[5215]="*Samaṇuddeso nāma**Novice monastic:*";
P_HTM[5216]="*sāmaṇero vuccati.**novice monk is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[5217]="*Upalāpeyya vāti**Supports:*";
P_HTM[5218]="*tassa pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā uddesaṃ vā paripucchaṃ vā dassāmīti upalāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he supports him, saying, “I’ll give him a bowl,” “I’ll give him a robe,” “I’ll recite to him,” or “I’ll test him,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5219]="*Upaṭṭhāpeyya vāti**Is attended on by:*";
P_HTM[5220]="*tassa cuṇṇaṃ vā mattikaṃ vā dantakaṭṭhaṃ vā mukhodakaṃ vā sādiyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he accepts bath powder, soap, a tooth cleaner, or water for rinsing the mouth from him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5221]="*Sambhuñjeyya vāti**Lives with:*";
P_HTM[5222]="*sambhogo nāma dve sambhogā—**there are two types of living together:*";
P_HTM[5223]="*āmisasambhogo ca dhammasambhogo ca.**material living together and spiritual living together.*";
P_HTM[5224]="*Āmisasambhogo nāma**Material living together:*";
P_HTM[5225]="*āmisaṃ deti vā paṭiggaṇhāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he gives or receives material things, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5226]="*Dhammasambhogo nāma**Spiritual living together:*";
P_HTM[5227]="*uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā, padena uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**he recites or has the other recite. If he recites or has the other recite by the line, then for every line he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5228]="*Akkharāya uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he recites or has the other recite by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5229]="*Saha vā seyyaṃ kappeyyāti**Shares a sleeping place with:*";
P_HTM[5230]="*ekacchanne nāsitake samaṇuddese nipanne bhikkhu nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**under the same ceiling: if the monk lies down when the expelled novice monastic is already lying down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5231]="*Bhikkhu nipanne nāsitako samaṇuddeso nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if the monk is already lying down when the expelled novice monastic lies down, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5232]="*Ubho vā nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if they both lie down together, he commits an offense entailing confession;*";
P_HTM[5233]="*Uṭṭhahitvā punappunaṃ nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**every time they get up and then lie down again, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5234]="*Nāsitake nāsitakasaññī upalāpeti vā upaṭṭhāpeti vā sambhuñjati vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the novice monastic has been expelled, and he perceives him as such, and he supports him or is attended on by him or lives with him or shares a sleeping place with him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5235]="*Nāsitake vematiko upalāpeti vā upaṭṭhāpeti vā sambhuñjati vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the novice monastic has been expelled, but he is unsure of it, and he supports him or is attended on by him or lives with him or shares a sleeping place with him, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5236]="*Nāsitake anāsitakasaññī upalāpeti vā upaṭṭhāpeti vā sambhuñjati vā saha vā seyyaṃ kappeti, anāpatti.**If the novice monastic has been expelled, but he does not perceive him as such, and he supports him or is attended on by him or lives with him or shares a sleeping place with him, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5237]="*Anāsitake nāsitakasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the novice monastic has not been expelled, but he perceives him such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5238]="*Anāsitake vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the novice monastic has not been expelled, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5239]="*Anāsitake anāsitakasaññī, anāpatti.**If the novice monastic has not been expelled, and he does not perceive him as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5240]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5241]="*anāsitakoti jānāti;**if he knows that he has not been expelled;*";
P_HTM[5242]="*taṃ diṭṭhiṃ paṭinissaṭṭhoti jānāti;**if he knows that he has given up that view;*";
P_HTM[5243]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5244]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5245]="*Kaṇṭakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on Kaṇṭaka, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5246]="*Sappāṇakavaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on containing living beings is finished.*";
P_HTM[5247]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[5248]="*Sañciccavadhasappāṇaṃ,**Intentionally killing, containing living beings,*";
P_HTM[5249]="*ukkoṭaṃ duṭṭhullachādanaṃ;**Agitation, concealing what is grave;*";
P_HTM[5250]="*Ūnavīsati satthañca,**Less than twenty, and group of travelers,*";
P_HTM[5251]="*saṃvidhānaṃ ariṭṭhakaṃ;**Appointment, on Ariṭṭha;*";
P_HTM[5252]="*Ukkhittaṃ kaṇṭakañceva,**Ejected, and Kaṇṭaka:*";
P_HTM[5253]="*dasa sikkhāpadā imeti.**These ten training rules.*";
P_HTM[5254]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5255]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5256]="*71. Sahadhammikasikkhāpada**71. The training rule on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5257]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5258]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā channo anācāraṃ ācarati.**Venerable Channa was misbehaving.*";
P_HTM[5259]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**The monks told him,*";
P_HTM[5260]="*“māvuso channa, evarūpaṃ akāsi.**“Don’t do that, Channa,*";
P_HTM[5261]="*Netaṃ kappatī”ti.**it’s not allowable,”*";
P_HTM[5262]="*So evaṃ vadeti—**and he would reply,*";
P_HTM[5263]="*“na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī”ti.**“I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is an expert on the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[5264]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[5265]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā channo bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could Venerable Channa say this when legitimately corrected by the monks?” …*";
P_HTM[5266]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’”ti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[5267]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, channa, bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vadesi—**“Is it true, Channa, that you said this?”*";
P_HTM[5268]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5269]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5270]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[5271]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vakkhasi—**“Foolish man, how could you say this when legitimately corrected by the monks?*";
P_HTM[5272]="*‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5273]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5274]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5275]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhūhi sahadhammikaṃ vuccamāno evaṃ vadeyya—‘na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī’ti, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk, when legitimately corrected by the monks, says, “I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who is an expert on the Monastic Law,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5276]="*Sikkhamānena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā aññātabbaṃ paripucchitabbaṃ paripañhitabbaṃ. Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti.**A monk who is training should understand, should question, should enquire. This is the proper procedure.’”*";
P_HTM[5277]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5278]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5279]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5280]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5281]="*Bhikkhūhīti**By the monks:*";
P_HTM[5282]="*aññehi bhikkhūhi.**by other monks.*";
P_HTM[5283]="*Sahadhammikaṃ nāma**Legitimately:*";
P_HTM[5284]="*yaṃ bhagavatā paññattaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ etaṃ sahadhammikaṃ nāma.**the training rules laid down by the Buddha—this is called “legitimately”.*";
P_HTM[5285]="*Tena vuccamāno evaṃ vadeti— “na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paripucchāmī”ti. Paṇḍitaṃ byattaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ paripucchāmīti bhaṇati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**When corrected in regard to this, he says, “I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who’s an expert on the Monastic Law.” If he says, “I’ll question one who’s wise,” “I’ll question one who’s competent,” “I’ll question one who’s intelligent,” “I’ll question one who’s learned,” “I’ll question an expounder of the Teaching,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5286]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the one who corrects him is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5287]="*Upasampanne vematiko evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the one who corrects him is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5288]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī evaṃ vadeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the one who corrects him is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he says such a thing, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5289]="*Apaññattena vuccamāno—**If he is corrected about something that has not been laid down:*";
P_HTM[5290]="*“idaṃ na sallekhāya na dhutatthāya na pāsādikatāya na apacayāya na vīriyārambhāya saṃvattatī”ti evaṃ vadeti, “na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paṇḍitaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ paripucchāmī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“This isn’t conducive to the erasing of defilements,” “This isn’t conducive to ascetic practices,” “This isn’t conducive to being inspiring,” “This isn’t conducive to a reduction in things,” “This isn’t conducive to being energetic,” and he says, “I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who’s competent,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s an expert on the Monastic Law,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s wise,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s intelligent,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s learned,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s an expounder of the Teaching,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5291]="*Anupasampannena paññattena vā apaññattena vā vuccamāno—**If he is corrected by one who is not fully ordained about something that has or has not been laid down:*";
P_HTM[5292]="*“idaṃ na sallekhāya na dhutatthāya na pāsādikatāya na apacayāya na vīriyārambhāya saṃvattatī”ti evaṃ vadeti, “na tāvāhaṃ, āvuso, etasmiṃ sikkhāpade sikkhissāmi yāva na aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ byattaṃ vinayadharaṃ paṇḍitaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ paripucchāmī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“This isn’t conducive to the erasing of defilements,” “This isn’t conducive to ascetic practices,” “This isn’t conducive to being inspiring,” “This isn’t conducive to a reduction in things,” “This isn’t conducive to being energetic,” and he says, “I won’t practice this training rule until I’ve questioned a monk who’s competent,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s an expert on the Monastic Law,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s wise,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s intelligent,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s learned,” “… until I’ve questioned a monk who’s an expounder of the Teaching,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5293]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the one who corrects him is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5294]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the one who corrects him is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5295]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the one who corrects him is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5296]="*Sikkhamānenāti**Who is training:*";
P_HTM[5297]="*sikkhitukāmena.**who wants to train.*";
P_HTM[5298]="*Aññātabbanti**Should understand:*";
P_HTM[5299]="*jānitabbaṃ.**should find out.*";
P_HTM[5300]="*Paripucchitabbanti**Should question:*";
P_HTM[5301]="*“idaṃ, bhante, kathaṃ; imassa vā kvattho”ti?**should ask, “Venerable, how is this? What’s the meaning of this?”*";
P_HTM[5302]="*Paripañhitabbanti**Should enquire:*";
P_HTM[5303]="*cintetabbaṃ tulayitabbaṃ.**should reflect, should weigh up.*";
P_HTM[5304]="*Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti**This is the proper procedure:*";
P_HTM[5305]="*ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā.**this is the right method.*";
P_HTM[5306]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5307]="*“jānissāmi sikkhissāmī”ti bhaṇati,**if he says, “I’ll find out and I’ll train;”*";
P_HTM[5308]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5309]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5310]="*Sahadhammikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on legitimately, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5311]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5312]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5313]="*72. Vilekhanasikkhāpada**72. The training rule on annoyance*";
P_HTM[5314]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[5315]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavā bhikkhūnaṃ anekapariyāyena vinayakathaṃ katheti, vinayassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, vinayapariyattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa āyasmato upālissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.**At that time the Buddha gave many talks about the Monastic Law, spoke in praise of the Monastic Law and of learning the Monastic Law, and repeatedly praised Venerable Upāli.*";
P_HTM[5316]="*Bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**When the monks heard this, they thought,*";
P_HTM[5317]="*“bhagavā kho anekapariyāyena vinayakathaṃ katheti, vinayassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, vinayapariyattiyā vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, ādissa ādissa āyasmato upālissa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsati.* **";
P_HTM[5318]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇāmā”ti, te ca bahū bhikkhū therā ca navā ca majjhimā ca āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇanti.**“Well then, let’s learn the Monastic Law from Venerable Upāli.” And many monks, both senior and junior, as well as those of middle standing, learned the Monastic Law from Upāli.*";
P_HTM[5319]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ etadahosi—**The monks from the group of six*";
P_HTM[5320]="*“etarahi kho, āvuso, bahū bhikkhū therā ca navā ca majjhimā ca āyasmato upālissa santike vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇanti.**considered this and thought,*";
P_HTM[5321]="*Sace ime vinaye pakataññuno bhavissanti amhe yenicchakaṃ yadicchakaṃ yāvadicchakaṃ ākaḍḍhissanti parikaḍḍhissanti.**“If these monks become well-versed in the Monastic Law, they’ll boss us around as they like.*";
P_HTM[5322]="*Handa mayaṃ, āvuso, vinayaṃ vivaṇṇemā”ti.**So let’s disparage the Monastic Law.”*";
P_HTM[5323]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhū upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—**They went to the other monks and said,*";
P_HTM[5324]="*“kiṃ panimehi khuddānukhuddakehi sikkhāpadehi uddiṭṭhehi, yāvadeva kukkuccāya vihesāya vilekhāya saṃvattantī”ti.**“What’s the point of reciting these minor and insignificant training rules, when they just lead to anxiety, oppression, and annoyance?”*";
P_HTM[5325]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5326]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vinayaṃ vivaṇṇessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six disparage the Monastic Law?” …*";
P_HTM[5327]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, vinayaṃ vivaṇṇethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[5328]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5329]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5330]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, vinayaṃ vivaṇṇessatha.**“Foolish men, how can do this?*";
P_HTM[5331]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5332]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5333]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadeyya—‘kiṃ panimehi khuddānukhuddakehi sikkhāpadehi uddiṭṭhehi, yāvadeva kukkuccāya vihesāya vilekhāya saṃvattantī’ti, sikkhāpadavivaṇṇake pācittiyan”ti.**‘When the Monastic Code is being recited, if a monk says, “What’s the point of reciting these minor and insignificant training rules, when they just lead to anxiety, oppression, and annoyance?” then in disparaging the training rules, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5334]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5335]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5336]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5337]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5338]="*Pātimokkhe uddissamāneti**When the Monastic Code is being recited:*";
P_HTM[5339]="*uddisante vā uddisāpente vā sajjhāyaṃ vā karonte.**when reciting it, when having it recited, or when practicing it.*";
P_HTM[5340]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Says:*";
P_HTM[5341]="*“kiṃ panimehi khuddānukhuddakehi sikkhāpadehi uddiṭṭhehi, yāvadeva kukkuccāya vihesāya vilekhāya saṃvattantī”ti.**“What’s the point of reciting these minor and insignificant training rules, when they just lead to anxiety, oppression, and annoyance?”*";
P_HTM[5342]="*“Ye imaṃ pariyāpuṇanti tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ hoti, vihesā hoti, vilekhā hoti, ye imaṃ na pariyāpuṇanti tesaṃ kukkuccaṃ na hoti vihesā na hoti vilekhā na hoti. Anuddiṭṭhaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, anuggahitaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, apariyāpuṭaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, adhāritaṃ idaṃ varaṃ, vinayo vā antaradhāyatu, ime vā bhikkhū appakataññuno hontū”ti upasampannassa vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he disparages the Monastic Law to one who is fully ordained, saying, “Those who learn this will be anxious,” “They will feel oppressed,” “They will be annoyed;” “Those who don’t learn this won’t be anxious,” “They won’t feel oppressed,” “They won’t be annoyed;” “It’s better left unrecited,” “It’s better left unlearned,” “It’s better left unstudied,” “It’s better left unmastered;” “May the Monastic Law disappear, or may these monks remain ignorant,” then he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5343]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he disparages the Monastic Law to one who is fully ordained, and he perceives them as fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5344]="*Upasampanne vematiko vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he disparages the Monastic Law to one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5345]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī vinayaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he disparages the Monastic Law to one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive them as fully ordained, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5346]="*Aññaṃ dhammaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he disparages some other rule, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5347]="*Anupasampannassa vinayaṃ vā aññaṃ vā dhammaṃ vivaṇṇeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he disparages the Monastic Law or some other rule to one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5348]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is to one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5349]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is to one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5350]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is to one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5351]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5352]="*na vivaṇṇetukāmo, “iṅgha tvaṃ suttante vā gāthāyo vā abhidhammaṃ vā pariyāpuṇassu, pacchā vinayaṃ pariyāpuṇissasī”ti bhaṇati,**if, not desiring to disparage, he says, “Listen, learn discourses or verses or philosophy, and later you can learn the Monastic Law;”*";
P_HTM[5353]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5354]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5355]="*Vilekhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on annoyance, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5356]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5357]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5358]="*73. Mohanasikkhāpada**73. The training rule on deception*";
P_HTM[5359]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5360]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū anācāraṃ ācaritvā “aññāṇakena āpannāti jānantū”ti pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadanti—**the monks from the group of six were misbehaving. They said to each other, “Let’s make the other monks think that we committed these offenses because we didn’t know the rules.” Then, during the recitation of the Monastic Code, they said,*";
P_HTM[5361]="*“idāneva kho mayaṃ jānāma, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī”ti.**“Just now did we find out that this rule too is included in the Monastic Code and comes up for recitation every half-month.”*";
P_HTM[5362]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5363]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vakkhanti—**“How could the monks from the group of six say this during the recitation of the Monastic Code?” …*";
P_HTM[5364]="*‘idāneva kho mayaṃ jānāma, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī’”ti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[5365]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadetha—**“Is it true, monks, that you said this?”*";
P_HTM[5366]="*‘idāneva kho mayaṃ jānāma, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5367]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5368]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5369]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vakkhatha—**“Foolish men, how could you say this during the recitation of the Monastic Code?*";
P_HTM[5370]="*‘idāneva kho mayaṃ jānāma, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5371]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5372]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5373]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu anvaddhamāsaṃ pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadeyya—**‘During the half-monthly recitation of the Monastic Code, a monk might say,*";
P_HTM[5374]="*‘idāneva kho ahaṃ jānāmi, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī’ti.**“Just now did I find out that this rule too has come down in the Monastic Code, is included in the Monastic Code, and comes up for recitation every half-month.”*";
P_HTM[5375]="*Tañce bhikkhuṃ aññe bhikkhū jāneyyuṃ nisinnapubbaṃ iminā bhikkhunā dvattikkhattuṃ pātimokkhe uddissamāne, ko pana vādo bhiyyo, na ca tassa bhikkhuno aññāṇakena mutti atthi, yañca tattha āpattiṃ āpanno tañca yathādhammo kāretabbo, uttari cassa moho āropetabbo—**If other monks know that that monk has previously sat through at least two or three recitations of the Monastic Code, then that monk is not let off because of ignorance, and he is to be dealt with according to the rule. Further, he should be charged with deception:*";
P_HTM[5376]="*‘tassa te, āvuso, alābhā, tassa te dulladdhaṃ, yaṃ tvaṃ pātimokkhe uddissamāne na sādhukaṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi karosī’ti.**“It’s a loss for you that you don’t pay proper attention during the recitation of the Monastic Code.”*";
P_HTM[5377]="*Idaṃ tasmiṃ mohanake pācittiyan”ti.**And for the act of deception, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5378]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5379]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5380]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5381]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5382]="*Anvaddhamāsanti**Half-monthly:*";
P_HTM[5383]="*anuposathikaṃ.**on every observance day.*";
P_HTM[5384]="*Pātimokkhe uddissamāneti**During the recitation of the Monastic Code:*";
P_HTM[5385]="*uddisante.**during the reciting.*";
P_HTM[5386]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti**Might say:*";
P_HTM[5387]="*anācāraṃ ācaritvā—**after misbehaving, he thinks,*";
P_HTM[5388]="*“aññāṇakena āpannoti jānantū”ti pātimokkhe uddissamāne evaṃ vadeti—**“Let them think that I committed these offenses because I didn’t know the rules.” If, during the recitation of the Monastic Code, he then says,*";
P_HTM[5389]="*“idāneva kho ahaṃ jānāmi, ayampi kira dhammo suttāgato suttapariyāpanno anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchatī”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**“Just now did I find out that this rule too has come down in the Monastic Code, is included in the Monastic Code, and comes up for recitation every half-month,” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5390]="*Tañce mohetukāmaṃ bhikkhuṃ aññe bhikkhū jāneyyuṃ nisinnapubbaṃ iminā bhikkhunā dvattikkhattuṃ pātimokkhe uddissamāne, ko pana vādo bhiyyo, na ca tassa bhikkhuno aññāṇakena mutti atthi, yañca tattha āpattiṃ āpanno, tañca yathādhammo kāretabbo, uttari cassa moho āropetabbo.**If other monks know that the monk who wants to deceive has previously sat through at least two or three recitations of the Monastic Code, then that monk is not let off because of ignorance, and he is to be dealt with according to the rule. Further, he should be charged with deception:*";
P_HTM[5391]="*“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, āropetabbo.**“And, monks, he is to be charged like this.*";
P_HTM[5392]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5393]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5394]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu pātimokkhe uddissamāne na sādhukaṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi karoti.**Monk so-and-so did not pay proper attention during the recitation of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[5395]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno mohaṃ āropeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should charge him with deception.*";
P_HTM[5396]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[5397]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[5398]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmo bhikkhu pātimokkhe uddissamāne na sādhukaṃ aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasi karoti.**Monk so-and-so did not pay proper attention during the recitation of the Monastic Code.*";
P_HTM[5399]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa bhikkhuno mohaṃ āropeti.**The Sangha charges him with deception.*";
P_HTM[5400]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa bhikkhuno mohassa āropanā, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of charging him with deception should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[5401]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[5402]="*Āropito saṅghena itthannāmassa bhikkhuno moho.**The Sangha has charged monk so-and-so with deception.*";
P_HTM[5403]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[5404]="*Anāropite mohe moheti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he deceives, but he has not been charged with deception, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5405]="*Āropite mohe moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he deceives, and he has been charged with deception, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5406]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as legitimate, and he deceives, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5407]="*Dhammakamme vematiko moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he deceives, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5408]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī moheti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he deceives, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5409]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5410]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5411]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5412]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5413]="*na vitthārena sutaṃ hoti,**if he has not heard it in full;*";
P_HTM[5414]="*ūnakadvattikkhattuṃ vitthārena sutaṃ hoti,**if he has heard it fewer than two or three times in full;*";
P_HTM[5415]="*na mohetukāmassa,**if he does not want to deceive;*";
P_HTM[5416]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5417]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5418]="*Mohanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on deception, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5419]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5420]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5421]="*74. Pahārasikkhāpada**74. The training rule on hitting*";
P_HTM[5422]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the when Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5423]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ denti.**the monks from the group of six hit the monks from the group of seventeen in anger.*";
P_HTM[5424]="*Te rodanti.**They cried.*";
P_HTM[5425]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Other monks asked them why,*";
P_HTM[5426]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5427]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhākaṃ pahāraṃ dentī”ti.**and they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[5428]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5429]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ dassantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six hit other monks in anger?” …*";
P_HTM[5430]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ dethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5431]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5432]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5433]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā bhikkhūnaṃ pahāraṃ dassatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5434]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5435]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5436]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa kupito anattamano pahāraṃ dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk hits a monk in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5437]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5438]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5439]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5440]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5441]="*Bhikkhussāti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[5442]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**another monk.*";
P_HTM[5443]="*Kupito anattamanoti**In anger:*";
P_HTM[5444]="*anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto.**discontent, having hatred, hostile.*";
P_HTM[5445]="*Pahāraṃ dadeyyāti**Hits:*";
P_HTM[5446]="*kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā antamaso uppalapattenapi pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he hits with his body, with anything connected to his body, or with anything released, even if only with a lotus leaf, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5447]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he hits him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5448]="*Upasampanne vematiko kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he hits him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5449]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he hits him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5450]="*Anupasampannassa kupito anattamano pahāraṃ deti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he hits one who is not fully ordained in anger, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5451]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5452]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5453]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5454]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5455]="*kenaci viheṭhīyamāno mokkhādhippāyo pahāraṃ deti,**if he hits in self-defence;*";
P_HTM[5456]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5457]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5458]="*Pahārasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on hitting, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5459]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5460]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5461]="*75. Talasattikasikkhāpada**75. The training rule on raising a hand*";
P_HTM[5462]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5463]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggiranti.**the monks from the group of six raised their hands in anger against the monks from the group of seventeen.*";
P_HTM[5464]="*Te pahārasamuccitā rodanti.**Expecting to be hit, they cried.*";
P_HTM[5465]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Other monks asked them why,*";
P_HTM[5466]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5467]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā amhākaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirantī”ti.**and they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[5468]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5469]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[5470]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5471]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5472]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5473]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kupitā anattamanā sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ talasattikaṃ uggirissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5474]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5475]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5476]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggireyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk raises a hand in anger against a monk, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5477]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5478]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5479]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5480]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5481]="*Bhikkhussāti**Against a monk:*";
P_HTM[5482]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**against another monk.*";
P_HTM[5483]="*Kupito anattamanoti**In anger:*";
P_HTM[5484]="*anabhiraddho āhatacitto khilajāto.**discontent, having hatred, hostile.*";
P_HTM[5485]="*Talasattikaṃ uggireyyāti**Raises a hand:*";
P_HTM[5486]="*kāyaṃ vā kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ vā antamaso uppalapattampi uccāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he raises any part of his body or anything connected to his body, even if only a lotus leaf, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5487]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he raises a hand against him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5488]="*Upasampanne vematiko kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he raises a hand against him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5489]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he raises a hand against him in anger, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5490]="*Anupasampannassa kupito anattamano talasattikaṃ uggirati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he raises a hand in anger against one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5491]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5492]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5493]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5494]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5495]="*kenaci viheṭhīyamāno mokkhādhippāyo talasattikaṃ uggirati,**if he raises his hand in self-defence;*";
P_HTM[5496]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5497]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5498]="*Talasattikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on raising a hand, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5499]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5500]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5501]="*76. Amūlakasikkhāpada**76. The training rule on groundless*";
P_HTM[5502]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5503]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃsenti.**the monks from the group of six groundlessly charged a monk with an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[5504]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5505]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃsessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[5506]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃsethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5507]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5508]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5509]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃsessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5510]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5511]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5512]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhuṃ amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk groundlessly charges a monk with an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5513]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5514]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5515]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5516]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5517]="*Bhikkhunti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[5518]="*aññaṃ bhikkhuṃ.**another monk.*";
P_HTM[5519]="*Amūlakaṃ nāma**Groundless:*";
P_HTM[5520]="*adiṭṭhaṃ assutaṃ aparisaṅkitaṃ.**not seen, not heard, not suspected.*";
P_HTM[5521]="*Saṅghādisesenāti**An offense entailing suspension:*";
P_HTM[5522]="*terasannaṃ aññatarena.**one of the thirteen.*";
P_HTM[5523]="*Anuddhaṃseyyāti**Charges:*";
P_HTM[5524]="*codeti vā codāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he accuses him or has him accused, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5525]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he groundlessly charges him with an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5526]="*Upasampanne vematiko amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he groundlessly charges him with an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5527]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī amūlakena saṅghādisesena anuddhaṃseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he groundlessly charges him with an offense entailing suspension, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5528]="*Ācāravipattiyā vā diṭṭhivipattiyā vā anuddhaṃseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he charges someone with failure in conduct or of failure in view, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5529]="*Anupasampannaṃ anuddhaṃseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he charges one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5530]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5531]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5532]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5533]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5534]="*tathāsaññī codeti vā codāpeti vā,**if he accuses someone, or has someone accused, according to what he has perceived;*";
P_HTM[5535]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5536]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5537]="*Amūlakasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on groundless, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5538]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5539]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5540]="*77. Sañciccasikkhāpada**77. The training rule on intentionally*";
P_HTM[5541]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5542]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sattarasavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahanti—**the monks from the group of six intentionally made the monks from the group of seventeen anxious. They said,*";
P_HTM[5543]="*“bhagavatā, āvuso, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—**“The Buddha has laid down a rule*";
P_HTM[5544]="*‘na ūnavīsativasso puggalo upasampādetabbo’ti.**that a person who is less than twenty years old shouldn’t be given the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[5545]="*Tumhe ca ūnavīsativassā upasampannā.**And you were less than twenty when you got the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[5546]="*Kacci no tumhe anupasampannā”ti?**Could it be that you’re not fully ordained?”*";
P_HTM[5547]="*Te rodanti.**They cried.*";
P_HTM[5548]="*Bhikkhū evamāhaṃsu—**Other monks asked them why,*";
P_HTM[5549]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, rodathā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[5550]="*“Ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū amhākaṃ sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahantī”ti.**and they said, “The monks from the group of six intentionally make us anxious.”*";
P_HTM[5551]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5552]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[5553]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[5554]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5555]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5556]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[5557]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5558]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5559]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhussa sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadaheyya—‘itissa muhuttampi aphāsu bhavissatī’ti etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk intentionally makes a monk anxious, thinking, “In this way he will be ill at ease at least for a moment,” and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5560]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5561]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5562]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5563]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5564]="*Bhikkhussāti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[5565]="*aññassa bhikkhussa.**another monk.*";
P_HTM[5566]="*Sañciccāti**Intentionally:*";
P_HTM[5567]="*jānanto sañjānanto cecca abhivitaritvā vītikkamo.**knowing, perceiving, having intended, having decided, he transgresses.*";
P_HTM[5568]="*Kukkuccaṃ upadaheyyāti**Makes anxious:*";
P_HTM[5569]="*“ūnavīsativasso maññe tvaṃ upasampanno, vikāle maññe tayā bhuttaṃ, majjaṃ maññe tayā pītaṃ, mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho maññe tayā nisinnan”ti kukkuccaṃ upadahati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he makes him anxious, saying, “It would seem that you were less than twenty years old when you were given the full ordination,” “It would seem that you have eaten at the wrong time,” “It would seem that you have drunk alcohol,” “It would seem that you have been sitting in private with a woman,” he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5570]="*Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā, anaññanti**He does so only for this reason and no other:*";
P_HTM[5571]="*na añño koci paccayo hoti kukkuccaṃ upadahituṃ.**there is no other reason for making him anxious.*";
P_HTM[5572]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he intentionally makes him anxious, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5573]="*Upasampanne vematiko sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he intentionally makes him anxious, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5574]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he intentionally makes him anxious, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5575]="*Anupasampannassa sañcicca kukkuccaṃ upadahati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he intentionally makes one who is not fully ordained anxious, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5576]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5577]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5578]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5579]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5580]="*na kukkuccaṃ upadahitukāmo “ūnavīsativasso maññe tvaṃ upasampanno, vikāle maññe tayā bhuttaṃ, majjaṃ maññe tayā pītaṃ, mātugāmena saddhiṃ raho maññe tayā nisinnaṃ, iṅgha jānāhi, mā te pacchā kukkuccaṃ ahosī”ti bhaṇati,**if, not wanting to make him anxious, he says, “It would seem that you were less than twenty years old when you were given the full ordination,” “It would seem that you have eaten at the wrong time,” “It would seem that you have drunk alcohol,” “It would seem that you have been sitting in private with a woman,” and then “Find out about it, so that you don’t get anxious later;”*";
P_HTM[5581]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5582]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5583]="*Sañciccasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on intentionally, the seventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5584]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5585]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5586]="*78. Upassutisikkhāpada**78. The training rule on eavesdropping*";
P_HTM[5587]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5588]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pesalehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍanti.**the monks from the group of six were arguing with the good monks.*";
P_HTM[5589]="*Pesalā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—**The good monks said,*";
P_HTM[5590]="*“alajjino ime, āvuso, chabbaggiyā bhikkhū.**“These monks from the group of six are shameless;*";
P_HTM[5591]="*Na sakkā imehi saha bhaṇḍitun”ti.**it’s not possible to argue with them.”*";
P_HTM[5592]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū evaṃ vadanti—**And the monks from the group of six said,*";
P_HTM[5593]="*“kissa tumhe, āvuso, amhe alajjivādena pāpethā”ti?**“Why are you slandering us by calling us shameless?”*";
P_HTM[5594]="*“Kahaṃ pana tumhe, āvuso, assutthā”ti?**“How did you know?”*";
P_HTM[5595]="*“Mayaṃ āyasmantānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhamhā”ti.**“We were eavesdropping on you.”*";
P_HTM[5596]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5597]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six eavesdrop on monks they are arguing and disputing with?” …*";
P_HTM[5598]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5599]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5600]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5601]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭhissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5602]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5603]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5604]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānaṃ upassutiṃ tiṭṭheyya—‘yaṃ ime bhaṇissanti taṃ sossāmī’ti etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññaṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk eavesdrops on monks who are arguing and disputing, thinking, “I’ll hear what they say,” and he does so only for this reason and no other, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5605]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5606]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5607]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5608]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5609]="*Bhikkhūnanti**On monks:*";
P_HTM[5610]="*aññesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ.**on other monks.*";
P_HTM[5611]="*Bhaṇḍanajātānaṃ kalahajātānaṃ vivādāpannānanti**Who are arguing and disputing:*";
P_HTM[5612]="*adhikaraṇajātānaṃ.**who are engaged in a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[5613]="*Upassutiṃ tiṭṭheyyāti**Eavesdrops:*";
P_HTM[5614]="*“imesaṃ sutvā codessāmi sāressāmi paṭicodessāmi paṭisāressāmi maṅkū karissāmī”ti gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he is on his way to eavesdrop, thinking, “After hearing what they say, I’ll accuse them,” “… I’ll remind them,” “… I’ll counter-accuse them,” “… I’ll counter-remind them,” “… I’ll humiliate them,” he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5615]="*Yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever he stands to listen, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5616]="*Pacchato gacchanto turito gacchati sossāmīti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is walking behind someone, and he speeds up with the intention to eavesdrop, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5617]="*Yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever he stands to listen, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5618]="*Purato gacchanto ohiyyati sossāmīti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is walking in front of someone, and he slows down with the intention to eavesdrop, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5619]="*Yattha ṭhito suṇāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever he stands to eavesdrop, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5620]="*Bhikkhussa ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgantvā mantentaṃ ukkāsitabbaṃ, vijānāpetabbaṃ, no ce ukkāseyya vā vijānāpeyya vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he goes to where a monk who is speaking privately is standing, seated, or lying down, he should clear his throat or make his presence known. If he does not clear his throat or make his presence known, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5621]="*Etadeva paccayaṃ karitvā anaññanti**He does so only for this reason and no other:*";
P_HTM[5622]="*na añño koci paccayo hoti upassutiṃ tiṭṭhituṃ.**there is no other reason for eavesdropping.*";
P_HTM[5623]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññī upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, and he perceives him as such, and he eavesdrops on him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5624]="*Upasampanne vematiko upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he eavesdrops on him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5625]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññī upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is one who is fully ordained, but he does not perceive him as such, and he eavesdrops on him, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5626]="*Anupasampannassa upassutiṃ tiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he eavesdrops on one who is not fully ordained, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5627]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5628]="*Anupasampanne vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5629]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is one who is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5630]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5631]="*“imesaṃ sutvā oramissāmi viramissāmi vūpasamissāmi attānaṃ parimocessāmī”ti gacchati,**if he goes, thinking, “After hearing what they say, I’ll refrain,” “… I’ll abstain,” “… I’ll resolve it,” “… I’ll free myself;”*";
P_HTM[5632]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5633]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5634]="*Upassutisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on eavesdropping, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5635]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5636]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5637]="*79. Kammapaṭibāhanasikkhāpada**79. The training rule on obstructing a legal procedure*";
P_HTM[5638]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[5639]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū anācāraṃ ācaritvā ekamekassa kamme kayiramāne paṭikkosanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six were misbehaving, but when a legal procedure was being done against any one of them, they would object.*";
P_HTM[5640]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅgho sannipatito hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**On one occasion the Sangha had gathered on some business.*";
P_HTM[5641]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū cīvarakammaṃ karontā ekassa chandaṃ adaṃsu.**The monks from the group of six were busy making robes and so they gave their consent to one among them.*";
P_HTM[5642]="*Atha kho saṅgho—* **";
P_HTM[5643]="*“ayaṃ, āvuso, chabbaggiyo bhikkhu ekako āgato, handassa mayaṃ kammaṃ karomā”ti tassa kammaṃ akāsi.**When the monks saw that only one monk from the group of six had come, they did a legal procedure against him.*";
P_HTM[5644]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu yena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami.**When he returned to the monks from the group of six,*";
P_HTM[5645]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**they asked him,*";
P_HTM[5646]="*“kiṃ, āvuso, saṅgho akāsī”ti?**“What did the Sangha do?”*";
P_HTM[5647]="*“Saṅgho me, āvuso, kammaṃ akāsī”ti.**“It did a legal procedure against me.”*";
P_HTM[5648]="*“Na mayaṃ, āvuso, etadatthāya chandaṃ adamhā—**“We didn’t give our consent for that.*";
P_HTM[5649]="*‘tuyhaṃ kammaṃ karissatī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[5650]="*Sace ca mayaṃ jāneyyāma ‘tuyhaṃ kammaṃ karissatī’ti, na mayaṃ chandaṃ dadeyyāmā”ti.**If we had known that a procedure would be done against you, we wouldn’t have given our consent.”*";
P_HTM[5651]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5652]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū dhammikānaṃ kammānaṃ chandaṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six give their consent to legitimate legal procedures and then criticize them afterwards?” …*";
P_HTM[5653]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, dhammikānaṃ kammānaṃ chandaṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5654]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5655]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5656]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, dhammikānaṃ kammānaṃ chandaṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5657]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5658]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5659]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu dhammikānaṃ kammānaṃ chandaṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives his consent to legitimate legal procedures, and then criticizes them afterwards, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5660]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5661]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5662]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5663]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5664]="*Dhammikaṃ nāma kammaṃ**A legitimate legal procedure:*";
P_HTM[5665]="*apalokanakammaṃ ñattikammaṃ ñattidutiyakammaṃ ñatticatutthakammaṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena kataṃ, etaṃ dhammikaṃ nāma kammaṃ.**a legal procedure consisting of getting permission, a legal procedure consisting of one motion, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement, a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements; done according to the Teaching, according to the Monastic Law, according to the Teacher’s instruction. This is called a “legitimate legal procedure”.*";
P_HTM[5666]="*Chandaṃ datvā khiyyati āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he gives his consent, and then criticizes the procedure, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5667]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī chandaṃ datvā khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he criticizes it after giving his consent, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5668]="*Dhammakamme vematiko chandaṃ datvā khiyyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he criticizes it after giving his consent, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5669]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī chandaṃ datvā khiyyati, anāpatti.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he criticizes it after giving his consent, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5670]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5671]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5672]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5673]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5674]="*“adhammena vā vaggena vā na kammārahassa vā kammaṃ katan”ti jānanto khiyyati,**if he criticizes it because he knows that the legal procedure was illegitimate, done by an incomplete assembly, or done against one who did not deserve it;*";
P_HTM[5675]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5676]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5677]="*Kammapaṭibāhanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on obstructing a legal procedure, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5678]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5679]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5680]="*80. Chandaṃadatvāgamanasikkhāpada**80. The training rule on leaving without giving consent*";
P_HTM[5681]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5682]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅgho sannipatito hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**the Sangha had gathered on some business.*";
P_HTM[5683]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū cīvarakammaṃ karontā ekassa chandaṃ adaṃsu.**The monks from the group of six were busy making robes and so they gave their consent to one among them.*";
P_HTM[5684]="*Atha kho saṅgho “yassatthāya sannipatito taṃ kammaṃ karissāmī”ti ñattiṃ ṭhapesi.**When the Sangha was ready to do the legal procedure for which it had gathered, it put forward a motion.*";
P_HTM[5685]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—**That monk from the group of six thought,*";
P_HTM[5686]="*“evamevime ekamekassa kammaṃ karonti, kassa tumhe kammaṃ karissathā”ti chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkāmi.**“This is just how they do legal procedures against us one by one, but against who will you do this one?” and without giving his consent, he got up from his seat and left.*";
P_HTM[5687]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[5688]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu saṅghe vinicchayakathāya vattamānāya chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamissatī”ti …pe…**“When the Sangha is in the process of deliberating, how could that monk get up from his seat and leave without giving his consent?” …*";
P_HTM[5689]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, saṅghe vinicchayakathāya vattamānāya chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamasī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5690]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5691]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[5692]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṅghe vinicchayakathāya vattamānāya chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamissasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5693]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5694]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5695]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu saṅghe vinicchayakathāya vattamānāya chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkameyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘When the Sangha is in the process of deliberating, if a monk gets up from his seat and leaves without first giving his consent, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5696]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5697]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5698]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5699]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5700]="*Saṅghe vinicchayakathā nāma**When the Sangha is deliberating:*";
P_HTM[5701]="*vatthu vā ārocitaṃ hoti avinicchitaṃ, ñatti vā ṭhapitā hoti, kammavācā vā vippakatā hoti.**when the topic has been announced but the deliberation is not yet concluded, or when the motion has been put forward, or when the announcement is still under way.*";
P_HTM[5702]="*Chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkameyyāti—**Gets up from his seat and leaves without first giving his consent:*";
P_HTM[5703]="*“kathaṃ idaṃ kammaṃ kuppaṃ assa vaggaṃ assa na kareyyā”ti gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he leaves, thinking, “How may this legal procedure be disturbed?” or “How may this legal procedure be done by an incomplete assembly?” or “How may this legal procedure not be done?” then he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5704]="*Parisāya hatthapāsaṃ vijahantassa āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is in the process of going beyond arm’s reach of the gathering, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5705]="*Vijahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**When he has gone beyond arm’s reach, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5706]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he gets up from his seat and leaves without first giving his consent, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5707]="*Dhammakamme vematiko chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he gets up from his seat and leaves without first giving his consent, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5708]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī chandaṃ adatvā uṭṭhāyāsanā pakkamati, anāpatti.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he gets up from his seat and leaves without first giving his consent, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5709]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5710]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5711]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5712]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5713]="*“saṅghassa bhaṇḍanaṃ vā kalaho vā viggaho vā vivādo vā bhavissatī”ti gacchati,**if he leaves because he thinks there will be quarrels or disputes in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[5714]="*“saṅghabhedo vā saṅgharāji vā bhavissatī”ti gacchati,**if he leaves because he thinks there will be a fracture or schism in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[5715]="*“adhammena vā vaggena vā na kammārahassa vā kammaṃ karissatī”ti gacchati,**if he leaves because he thinks the legal procedure will be illegitimate, done by an incomplete assembly, or done against one who does not deserve it;*";
P_HTM[5716]="*gilāno gacchati,**if he leaves because he is sick;*";
P_HTM[5717]="*gilānassa karaṇīyena gacchati,**if he leaves because he has to take care of someone who is sick;*";
P_HTM[5718]="*uccārena vā passāvena vā pīḷito gacchati,**if he leaves because he needs to relieve himself;*";
P_HTM[5719]="*“na kammaṃ kopetukāmo puna paccāgamissāmī”ti gacchati,**if he leaves with the intention to return, and not because he wants to invalidate the legal procedure;*";
P_HTM[5720]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5721]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5722]="*Chandaṃ adatvā gamanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on leaving without giving consent, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5723]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5724]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5725]="*81. Dubbalasikkhāpada**81. The training rule on what is worn out*";
P_HTM[5726]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[5727]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā dabbo mallaputto saṅghassa senāsanañca paññapeti bhattāni ca uddisati.**At that time Venerable Dabba the Mallian, who was the assigner of dwellings and the designator of meals,*";
P_HTM[5728]="*So cāyasmā dubbalacīvaro hoti.**had a robe that was worn out.*";
P_HTM[5729]="*Tena kho pana samayena saṅghassa ekaṃ cīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**Just then the Sangha had obtained a robe,*";
P_HTM[5730]="*Atha kho saṅgho taṃ cīvaraṃ āyasmato dabbassa mallaputtassa adāsi.**which it gave to Dabba.*";
P_HTM[5731]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks from the group of six complained and criticized it,*";
P_HTM[5732]="*“yathāsanthutaṃ bhikkhū saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇāmentī”ti.**“The monks are diverting the Sangha’s material gains according to friendship.”*";
P_HTM[5733]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[5734]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū samaggena saṅghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six give out a robe as part of a unanimous Sangha and then criticize it afterwards?” …*";
P_HTM[5735]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, samaggena saṅghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5736]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5737]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5738]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, samaggena saṅghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5739]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ, vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5740]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5741]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu samaggena saṅghena cīvaraṃ datvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjeyya ‘yathāsanthutaṃ bhikkhū saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇāmentī’ti, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk gives out a robe as part of a unanimous Sangha and then criticizes it afterwards, saying, “The monks are diverting the Sangha’s material gains according to friendship,” he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5742]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5743]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5744]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5745]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5746]="*Samaggo nāma saṅgho**A unanimous Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5747]="*samānasaṃvāsako samānasīmāyaṃ ṭhito.**belonging to the same Buddhist sect and staying within the same monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[5748]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**A robe:*";
P_HTM[5749]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ.**one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[5750]="*Datvāti**Gives out:*";
P_HTM[5751]="*sayaṃ datvā.**gives out himself.*";
P_HTM[5752]="*Yathāsanthutaṃ nāma**According to friendship:*";
P_HTM[5753]="*yathāmittatā yathāsandiṭṭhatā yathāsambhattatā yathāsamānupajjhāyakatā yathāsamānācariyakatā.**according to friendship, according to companionship, according to who one is devoted to, according to being a co-student, according to being a co-pupil.*";
P_HTM[5754]="*Saṅghikaṃ nāma**The Sangha’s:*";
P_HTM[5755]="*saṅghassa dinnaṃ hoti pariccattaṃ.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5756]="*Lābho nāma**Material gains:*";
P_HTM[5757]="*cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, antamaso cuṇṇapiṇḍopi, dantakaṭṭhampi, dasikasuttampi.**robes, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicines; even a bit of bath powder, a tooth cleaner, or a piece of string.*";
P_HTM[5758]="*Pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjeyyāti**Criticizes it afterwards:*";
P_HTM[5759]="*upasampannassa saṅghena sammatassa senāsanapaññāpakassa vā bhattuddesakassa vā yāgubhājakassa vā phalabhājakassa vā khajjabhājakassa vā appamattakavissajjakassa vā cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when robe-cloth has been given to someone who is fully ordained and who is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of fresh foods or the distributor of minor requisites, and he has been appointed by the Sangha as such, then if a monk criticizes the giving, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5760]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññī cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, and he criticizes the giving of robe-cloth, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5761]="*Dhammakamme vematiko cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, and he criticizes the giving of robe-cloth, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5762]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññī cīvaraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as illegitimate, and he criticizes it the giving of robe-cloth, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5763]="*Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he criticizes the giving of another requisite, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5764]="*Upasampannassa saṅghena asammatassa senāsanapaññāpakassa vā bhattuddesakassa vā yāgubhājakassa vā phalabhājakassa vā khajjabhājakassa vā appamattakavissajjakassa vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When robe-cloth or another requisite has been given to someone who is fully ordained and who is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of fresh foods or the distributor of minor requisites, but he has not been appointed by the Sangha as such, then if a monk criticizes the giving, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5765]="*Anupasampannassa saṅghena sammatassa vā asammatassa vā senāsanapaññāpakassa vā bhattuddesakassa vā yāgubhājakassa vā phalabhājakassa vā khajjabhājakassa vā appamattakavissajjakassa vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ dinne khiyyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When robe-cloth or another requisite has been given to someone who is not fully ordained and who is the assigner of dwellings or the designator of meals or the distributor of rice porridge or the distributor of fruit or the distributor of fresh foods or the distributor of minor requisites, whether he has been appointed by the Sangha as such or not, then if a monk criticizes the giving, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5766]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he perceives it as legitimate, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5767]="*Adhammakamme vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5768]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5769]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5770]="*pakatiyā chandā dosā mohā bhayā karontaṃ “kvattho tassa dinnena laddhāpi vinipātessati na sammā upanessatī”ti khiyyati,**if he criticizes one who regularly acts out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, or fear, saying, “What’s the point of giving it to him—he’ll ruin it or use it inappropriately;”*";
P_HTM[5771]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5772]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5773]="*Dubbalasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ ekādasamaṃ.**The training rule on what is worn out, the eleventh, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5774]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5775]="*Sahadhammikavagga**The sub-chapter on legitimately*";
P_HTM[5776]="*82. Pariṇāmanasikkhāpada**82. The training rule on diverting*";
P_HTM[5777]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5778]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarassa pūgassa saṅghassa sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyattaṃ hoti—**an association had prepared a meal together with robes for the Sangha. They said,*";
P_HTM[5779]="*“bhojetvā cīvarena acchādessāmā”ti.**“After giving the food, we’ll offer the robes.”*";
P_HTM[5780]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhū yena so pūgo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**But the monks from the group of six went to that association*";
P_HTM[5781]="*upasaṅkamitvā taṃ pūgaṃ etadavocuṃ—**and said,*";
P_HTM[5782]="*“dethāvuso, imāni cīvarāni imesaṃ bhikkhūnan”ti.**“Please give these robes to these monks.”*";
P_HTM[5783]="*“Na mayaṃ, bhante, dassāma.**“Venerables, we can’t do that.*";
P_HTM[5784]="*Amhākaṃ saṅghassa anuvassaṃ sacīvarabhikkhā paññattā”ti.**We’ve prepared our annual alms-offering together with robes for the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[5785]="*“Bahū, āvuso, saṅghassa dāyakā, bahū saṅghassa bhattā.**“The Sangha has many donors and supporters.*";
P_HTM[5786]="*Ime tumhe nissāya tumhe sampassantā idha viharanti.**But since these monks are staying here, they are looking to you for support.*";
P_HTM[5787]="*Tumhe ce imesaṃ na dassatha, atha ko carahi imesaṃ dassati?**If you don’t give to them, who will?*";
P_HTM[5788]="*Dethāvuso, imāni cīvarāni imesaṃ bhikkhūnan”ti.**So give them these robes.”*";
P_HTM[5789]="*Atha kho so pūgo chabbaggiyehi bhikkhūhi nippīḷiyamāno yathāpaṭiyattaṃ cīvaraṃ chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ datvā saṅghaṃ bhattena parivisi.**Being pressured by the monks from the group of six, that association gave the prepared robes to those monks and served the food to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5790]="*Ye te bhikkhū jānanti saṅghassa sacīvarabhattaṃ paṭiyattaṃ “na ca jānanti chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ dinnan”ti te evamāhaṃsu—**The monks who knew that a meal together with robes had been prepared for the Sangha, but not that the robes had been given to those monks from the group of six, said,*";
P_HTM[5791]="*“oṇojethāvuso, saṅghassa cīvaran”ti.**“You may offer the robes.”*";
P_HTM[5792]="*“Natthi, bhante.**“There aren’t any.*";
P_HTM[5793]="*Yathāpaṭiyattaṃ cīvaraṃ ayyā chabbaggiyā ayyānaṃ chabbaggiyānaṃ pariṇāmesun”ti.**The robes we had prepared were diverted by the monks from the group of six.”*";
P_HTM[5794]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[5795]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū jānaṃ saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa pariṇāmessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six divert to an individual things they knew were intended for the Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[5796]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, jānaṃ saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa pariṇāmethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5797]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5798]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[5799]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, jānaṃ saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa pariṇāmessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5800]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5801]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5802]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu jānaṃ saṅghikaṃ lābhaṃ pariṇataṃ puggalassa pariṇāmeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk diverts to an individual material support that he knows was intended for the Sangha, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5803]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5804]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5805]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5806]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5807]="*Jānāti nāma**He knows:*";
P_HTM[5808]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassa ārocenti, so vā āroceti.**he knows by himself or others have told him or the donor has told him.*";
P_HTM[5809]="*Saṅghikaṃ nāma**For the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[5810]="*saṅghassa dinnaṃ hoti pariccattaṃ.**given to the Sangha, given up to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[5811]="*Lābho nāma**Material support:*";
P_HTM[5812]="*cīvarapiṇḍapātasenāsanagilānappaccayabhesajjaparikkhārā, antamaso cuṇṇapiṇḍopi, dantakaṭṭhampi, dasikasuttampi.**robes, almsfood, a dwelling, and medicine; even a bit of bath powder, a tooth cleaner, or a piece of string.*";
P_HTM[5813]="*Pariṇataṃ nāma**Intended:*";
P_HTM[5814]="*“dassāma karissāmā”ti vācā bhinnā hoti, taṃ puggalassa pariṇāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if they have said, “We’ll give,” “We’ll prepare,” and he diverts it to an individual, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5815]="*Pariṇate pariṇatasaññī puggalassa pariṇāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is intended for the Sangha and he perceives it as such, and he diverts it to an individual, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5816]="*Pariṇate vematiko puggalassa pariṇāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is intended for the Sangha, but he is unsure of it, and he diverts it to an individual, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5817]="*Pariṇate apariṇatasaññī puggalassa pariṇāmeti, anāpatti.**If it is intended for the Sangha, but he does not perceive it as such, and he diverts it to an individual, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5818]="*Saṅghassa pariṇataṃ aññasaṅghassa vā cetiyassa vā pariṇāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is intended for one Sangha and he diverts it to another Sangha or to a shrine, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5819]="*Cetiyassa pariṇataṃ aññacetiyassa vā saṅghassa vā puggalassa vā pariṇāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is intended for one shrine and he diverts it to another shrine or to a sangha or to an individual, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5820]="*Puggalassa pariṇataṃ aññapuggalassa vā saṅghassa vā cetiyassa vā pariṇāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is intended for an individual and he diverts it to another individual or to a sangha or to a shrine, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5821]="*Apariṇate pariṇatasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not intended for the Sangha, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5822]="*Apariṇate vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not intended for the Sangha, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5823]="*Apariṇate apariṇatasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is not intended for the Sangha and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5824]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5825]="*“kattha demā”ti pucchīyamāno—**if being asked,*";
P_HTM[5826]="*“yattha tumhākaṃ deyyadhammo paribhogaṃ vā labheyya paṭisaṅkhāraṃ vā labheyya ciraṭṭhitiko vā assa yattha vā pana tumhākaṃ cittaṃ pasīdati tattha dethā”ti bhaṇati,**“Where may we give?” he says, “Give where your gift goes toward equipment,” “… where it goes toward repairs,” “… where it will last for a long time,” “… where you feel inspired;”*";
P_HTM[5827]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5828]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5829]="*Pariṇāmanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dvādasamaṃ.**The training rule on diverting, the twelfth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5830]="*Sahadhammikavaggo aṭṭhamo.**The eighth sub-chapter on legitimately is finished.*";
P_HTM[5831]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[5832]="*Sahadhamma vivaṇṇañca,**Legitimately, and disparaging,*";
P_HTM[5833]="*mohāpanaṃ pahārakaṃ;**Deception, hitting;*";
P_HTM[5834]="*Talasatti amūlañca,**Raising a hand, and groundless,*";
P_HTM[5835]="*sañcicca ca upassuti;**And intentionally, eavesdropping;*";
P_HTM[5836]="*Paṭibāhana chandañca,**Obstructing, and consent,*";
P_HTM[5837]="*dabbañca pariṇāmananti.**And Dabba, diverting.*";
P_HTM[5838]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5839]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[5840]="*83. Antepurasikkhāpada**83. The training rule on royal compounds*";
P_HTM[5841]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5842]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo uyyānapālaṃ āṇāpesi—“gaccha, bhaṇe, uyyānaṃ sodhehi. Uyyānaṃ gamissāmā”ti.**King Pasenadi of Kosala told his park-keeper, “Go and clean up the park; I’ll be going there.”*";
P_HTM[5843]="*“Evaṃ, devā”ti kho so uyyānapālo rañño pasenadissa kosalassa paṭissutvā uyyānaṃ sodhento addasa bhagavantaṃ aññatarasmiṃ rukkhamūle nisinnaṃ.**“Yes, sir.” While cleaning the park, he saw the Buddha seated at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[5844]="*Disvāna yena rājā pasenadi kosalo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca—“suddhaṃ, deva, uyyānaṃ. Api ca bhagavā tattha nisinno”ti.**He then went to King Pasenadi and said, “The park is clean, sir, but the Buddha is sitting there.”*";
P_HTM[5845]="*“Hotu, bhaṇe. Mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāsissāmā”ti.**“Marvellous! I’ll visit him.”*";
P_HTM[5846]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uyyānaṃ gantvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami. Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako bhagavantaṃ payirupāsanto nisinno hoti.**The King went to the park and approached the Buddha, but just then a lay follower was seated there.*";
P_HTM[5847]="*Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo taṃ upāsakaṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāsantaṃ nisinnaṃ. Disvāna bhīto aṭṭhāsi.**When the King saw him, he became fearful and stopped.*";
P_HTM[5848]="*Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi—“nārahatāyaṃ puriso pāpo hotuṃ, yathā bhagavantaṃ payirupāsatī”ti. Yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**But he considered, “This man isn’t likely to be bad, since he’s visiting the Buddha,” and so he approached the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[5849]="*Atha kho so upāsako bhagavato gāravena rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ neva abhivādesi na paccuṭṭhāsi. Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo anattamano ahosi—“kathañhi nāmāyaṃ puriso mayi āgate neva abhivādessati na paccuṭṭhessatī”ti.**But when that lay follower, because of his respect for the Buddha, neither bowed down to the King nor stood up for him, the King became annoyed.*";
P_HTM[5850]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ anattamanaṃ viditvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca—“eso kho, mahārāja, upāsako bahussuto āgatāgamo kāmesu vītarāgo”ti.**The Buddha realized what was happening and said to the King, “Great King, this lay follower is learned, a master of the tradition, and he’s free from sensual desire.”*";
P_HTM[5851]="*Atha kho rañño pasenadissa kosalassa etadahosi—“nārahatāyaṃ upāsako orako hotuṃ, bhagavāpi imassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsatī”ti.**The King thought, “This lay follower doesn’t deserve to be in an inferior position, since even the Buddha praises him.”*";
P_HTM[5852]="*Taṃ upāsakaṃ etadavoca—“vadeyyāsi, upāsaka, yena attho”ti.**And he said to that lay follower, “Please say what you want.”*";
P_HTM[5853]="*“Suṭṭhu, devā”ti.**“Thank you, sir.”*";
P_HTM[5854]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**The Buddha then instructed, inspired, and gladdened King Pasenadi with a teaching, after which the King got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated the Buddha with his right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[5855]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo uparipāsādavaragato hoti. Addasā kho rājā pasenadi kosalo taṃ upāsakaṃ rathikāya chattapāṇiṃ gacchantaṃ.**Soon afterwards King Pasenadi was up in his best stilt house, when he saw that lay follower walking along the street, holding a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[5856]="*Disvāna pakkosāpetvā etadavoca—“tvaṃ kira, upāsaka, bahussuto āgatāgamo.**He summoned him and said, “You are a learned Buddhist, a master of the tradition.*";
P_HTM[5857]="*Sādhu, upāsaka, amhākaṃ itthāgāraṃ dhammaṃ vācehī”ti.**It would be good if you would teach my harem.”*";
P_HTM[5858]="*“Yamahaṃ, deva, jānāmi ayyānaṃ vāhasā, ayyāva devassa itthāgāraṃ dhammaṃ vācessantī”ti.**“Whatever I know, sir, I know because of the monks. They should teach the harem.”*";
P_HTM[5859]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo—“saccaṃ kho upāsako āhā”ti yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho rājā pasenadi kosalo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**Knowing that the lay follower was right, the King went to the Buddha, bowed, sat down, and said,*";
P_HTM[5860]="*“sādhu, bhante, bhagavā ekaṃ bhikkhuṃ āṇāpetu yo amhākaṃ itthāgāraṃ dhammaṃ vācessatī”ti.**“It would be good, Venerable Sir, if you would tell a monk to teach my harem.”*";
P_HTM[5861]="*Atha kho bhagavā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi …pe… padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**The Buddha then instructed, inspired, and gladdened King Pasenadi with a teaching, after which the King got up from his seat, paid his respects as before, and left.*";
P_HTM[5862]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ āmantesi—“tenahānanda, rañño itthāgāraṃ dhammaṃ vācehī”ti.**Soon afterwards, the Buddha said to Venerable Ānanda, “Well then, Ānanda, teach the King’s harem.”*";
P_HTM[5863]="*“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā ānando bhagavato paṭissutvā kālena kālaṃ pavisitvā rañño itthāgāraṃ dhammaṃ vāceti.**“Yes, Sir.” And from time to time he would enter the harem and teach.*";
P_HTM[5864]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami.**Then, after robing up one the morning, Ānanda took his bowl and robe and went to King Pasenadi’s house.*";
P_HTM[5865]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājā pasenadi kosalo mallikāya deviyā saddhiṃ sayanagato hoti.**On that occasion the King was in bed with Queen Mallikā.*";
P_HTM[5866]="*Addasā kho mallikā devī āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. Disvāna sahasā vuṭṭhāsi; pītakamaṭṭhaṃ dussaṃ pabhassittha.**The Queen saw Ānanda coming and she quickly got up, but her burnished golden dressing gown fell off.*";
P_HTM[5867]="*Atha kho āyasmā ānando tatova paṭinivattitvā ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Ānanda turned around right there and returned to the monastery. And he told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[5868]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[5869]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā ānando pubbe appaṭisaṃvidito rañño antepuraṃ pavisissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Ānanda enter the royal compound without first being announced?” …*";
P_HTM[5870]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, ānanda, pubbe appaṭisaṃvidito rañño antepuraṃ pavisasī”ti?**“Is it true, Ānanda, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5871]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5872]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[5873]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, ānanda, pubbe appaṭisaṃvidito rañño antepuraṃ pavisissasi.**“Ānanda, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5874]="*Netaṃ, ānanda, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5875]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**Having rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[5876]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[5877]="*“Dasayime, bhikkhave, ādīnavā rājantepurappavesane.**“Monks, there are these ten dangers in entering a royal compound.*";
P_HTM[5878]="*Katame dasa?**What ten?*";
P_HTM[5879]="*Idha, bhikkhave, rājā mahesiyā saddhiṃ nisinno hoti, tattha bhikkhu pavisati.**It may be that a monk enters where the king is sitting with his queen.*";
P_HTM[5880]="*Mahesī vā bhikkhuṃ disvā sitaṃ pātukaroti.**The queen smiles when she sees the monk*";
P_HTM[5881]="*Bhikkhu vā mahesiṃ disvā sitaṃ pātukaroti.**or the monk smiles when he sees the queen.*";
P_HTM[5882]="*Tattha rañño evaṃ hoti—**The king thinks,*";
P_HTM[5883]="*‘addhā imesaṃ kataṃ vā karissanti vā’ti.**‘Surely they’ve done it, or they’re going to.’*";
P_HTM[5884]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, paṭhamo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5885]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā bahukicco bahukaraṇīyo.**Again, because the king is very busy,*";
P_HTM[5886]="*Aññataraṃ itthiṃ gantvā nassarati.**he does not remember having slept with a certain woman,*";
P_HTM[5887]="*Sā tena gabbhaṃ gaṇhi.**yet she becomes pregnant because of that.*";
P_HTM[5888]="*Tattha rañño evaṃ hoti—**The king thinks,*";
P_HTM[5889]="*‘na kho idha añño koci pavisati aññatra pabbajitena.**‘Only the monk enters here.*";
P_HTM[5890]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5891]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dutiyo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5892]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rañño antepure aññataraṃ ratanaṃ nassati.**Again, a gem disappears from the royal compound.*";
P_HTM[5893]="*Tattha rañño evaṃ hoti—**The king thinks,*";
P_HTM[5894]="*‘na kho idha añño koci pavisati aññatra pabbajitena.**‘Only the monk enters here.*";
P_HTM[5895]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5896]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, tatiyo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5897]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rañño antepure abbhantarā guyhamantā bahiddhā sambhedaṃ gacchanti.**Again, secret discussions in the royal compound are spread outside.*";
P_HTM[5898]="*Tattha rañño evaṃ hoti—**The king thinks,*";
P_HTM[5899]="*‘na kho idha añño koci pavisati aññatra pabbajitena.**‘Only the monk enters here.*";
P_HTM[5900]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5901]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, catuttho ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5902]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rañño antepure putto vā pitaraṃ pattheti pitā vā puttaṃ pattheti.**Again, in the royal compound a father assails his son, or a son assails his father.*";
P_HTM[5903]="*Tesaṃ evaṃ hoti—**They think,*";
P_HTM[5904]="*‘na kho idha añño koci pavisati aññatra pabbajitena.**‘Only the monk enters here.*";
P_HTM[5905]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5906]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, pañcamo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5907]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā nīcaṭṭhāniyaṃ ucce ṭhāne ṭhapeti.**Again, the king promotes someone.*";
P_HTM[5908]="*Yesaṃ taṃ amanāpaṃ tesaṃ evaṃ hoti—**Those who dislike this think,*";
P_HTM[5909]="*‘rājā kho pabbajitena saṃsaṭṭho.**‘The king is close to the monk.*";
P_HTM[5910]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5911]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, chaṭṭho ādīnavo, rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5912]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā uccaṭṭhāniyaṃ nīce ṭhāne ṭhapeti.**Again, the king demotes someone.*";
P_HTM[5913]="*Yesaṃ taṃ amanāpaṃ tesaṃ evaṃ hoti—**Those who dislike this think,*";
P_HTM[5914]="*‘rājā kho pabbajitena saṃsaṭṭho.**‘The king is close to the monk.*";
P_HTM[5915]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5916]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, sattamo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5917]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā akāle senaṃ uyyojeti.**Again, the king sends out the army at an inappropriate time.*";
P_HTM[5918]="*Yesaṃ taṃ amanāpaṃ tesaṃ evaṃ hoti—**Those who dislike this think,*";
P_HTM[5919]="*‘rājā kho pabbajitena saṃsaṭṭho.**‘The king is close to the monk.*";
P_HTM[5920]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5921]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, aṭṭhamo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5922]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rājā kāle senaṃ uyyojetvā antarāmaggato nivattāpeti.**Again, after sending out the army at an appropriate time, the king orders it to turn back while still en route.*";
P_HTM[5923]="*Yesaṃ taṃ amanāpaṃ tesaṃ evaṃ hoti—**Those who dislike this think,*";
P_HTM[5924]="*‘rājā kho pabbajitena saṃsaṭṭho.**‘The king is close to the monk.*";
P_HTM[5925]="*Siyā nu kho pabbajitassa kamman’ti.**Is he responsible for this?’*";
P_HTM[5926]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, navamo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5927]="*Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, rañño rājantepuraṃ hatthisammaddaṃ assasammaddaṃ rathasammaddaṃ rajanīyāni rūpasaddagandharasaphoṭṭhabbāni, yāni na pabbajitassa sāruppāni.**Again, a royal compound is crowded with elephants, horses, and chariots, as well as enticing sights, sounds, smells, tastes, and tangibles that are not suitable for a monk.*";
P_HTM[5928]="*Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, dasamo ādīnavo rājantepurappavesane.* **";
P_HTM[5929]="*Ime kho, bhikkhave, dasa ādīnavā rājantepurappavesane”ti.**Monks, these are the ten dangers in entering a royal compound.”*";
P_HTM[5930]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after rebuking Ānanda in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support … the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[5931]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5932]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu rañño khattiyassa muddhāvasittassa anikkhantarājake aniggataratanake pubbe appaṭisaṃvidito indakhīlaṃ atikkāmeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk, without first being announced, crosses the threshold to the bedroom of a consecrated aristocrat king, when both the king and the queen are present, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5933]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[5934]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[5935]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[5936]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[5937]="*Khattiyo nāma**Aristocrat:*";
P_HTM[5938]="*ubhato sujāto hoti, mātito ca pitito ca saṃsuddhagahaṇiko, yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā akkhitto anupakuṭṭho jātivādena.**well-born on both his mother’s side and his father’s side, pure in descent, irreproachable and impeccable with respect to birth going back seven generations of male ancestors.*";
P_HTM[5939]="*Muddhāvasitto nāma**Consecrated:*";
P_HTM[5940]="*khattiyābhisekena abhisitto hoti.**consecrated with the aristocratic consecration.*";
P_HTM[5941]="*Anikkhantarājaketi**The king is present:*";
P_HTM[5942]="*rājā sayanigharā anikkhanto hoti.**the king has not left the bedroom.*";
P_HTM[5943]="*Aniggataratanaketi**The queen is present:*";
P_HTM[5944]="*mahesī sayanigharā anikkhantā hoti, ubho vā anikkhantā honti.**the queen has not left the bedroom. Or both have not left.*";
P_HTM[5945]="*Pubbe appaṭisaṃviditoti**Without first being announced:*";
P_HTM[5946]="*pubbe anāmantetvā.**without first having informed.*";
P_HTM[5947]="*Indakhīlo nāma**The threshold:*";
P_HTM[5948]="*sayanigharassa ummāro vuccati.**the threshold to the bedroom is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[5949]="*Sayanigharaṃ nāma**The bedroom:*";
P_HTM[5950]="*yattha katthaci rañño sayanaṃ paññattaṃ hoti, antamaso sāṇipākāraparikkhittampi.**wherever a king’s bed is prepared, even if just enclosed by a cloth screen.*";
P_HTM[5951]="*Indakhīlaṃ atikkāmeyyāti**Crosses the threshold to the bedroom:*";
P_HTM[5952]="*paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ ummāraṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he crosses the threshold with the first foot, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5953]="*Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he crosses with the second foot, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5954]="*Appaṭisaṃvidite appaṭisaṃviditasaññī indakhīlaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has not been announced, and he does not perceive it as such, and he crosses the threshold to the bedroom, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5955]="*Appaṭisaṃvidite vematiko indakhīlaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has not been announced, but he is unsure of it, and he crosses the threshold to the bedroom, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5956]="*Appaṭisaṃvidite paṭisaṃviditasaññī indakhīlaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has not been announced, but he perceives it as such, and he crosses the threshold to the bedroom, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[5957]="*Paṭisaṃvidite appaṭisaṃviditasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he has been announced, but he does not perceive it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5958]="*Paṭisaṃvidite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he has been announced, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[5959]="*Paṭisaṃvidite paṭisaṃviditasaññī, anāpatti.**If he has been announced, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[5960]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[5961]="*paṭisaṃvidite,**if he has been announced;*";
P_HTM[5962]="*na khattiyo hoti,**if it is not an aristocrat king;*";
P_HTM[5963]="*na khattiyābhisekena abhisitto hoti,**if the king has not been consecrated with the aristocratic consecration;*";
P_HTM[5964]="*rājā sayanigharā nikkhanto hoti,**if the king has left the bedroom;*";
P_HTM[5965]="*mahesī sayanigharā nikkhantā hoti,**if the queen has left the bedroom;*";
P_HTM[5966]="*ubho vā nikkhantā honti,**if they both have left;*";
P_HTM[5967]="*na sayanighare,**if it is not a bedroom;*";
P_HTM[5968]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[5969]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[5970]="*Antepurasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on royal compounds, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[5971]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[5972]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[5973]="*84. Ratanasikkhāpada**84. The training rule on precious things*";
P_HTM[5974]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[5975]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu aciravatiyā nadiyā nahāyati. Aññataropi brāhmaṇo pañcasatānaṃ thavikaṃ thale nikkhipitvā aciravatiyā nadiyā nahāyanto vissaritvā agamāsi.**a monk was bathing in the river Aciravatī, when a brahmin, too, came there to bathe. He deposited a bag with five hundred coins on the ground, bathed, forgot about the bag, and left.*";
P_HTM[5976]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—“tassāyaṃ brāhmaṇassa thavikā, mā idha nassī”ti aggahesi.**The monk thought, “This is the bag belonging to that brahmin; it wouldn’t be nice if it got lost,” and he picked it up.*";
P_HTM[5977]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo saritvā turito ādhāvitvā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavoca—“api me, bho, thavikaṃ passeyyāsī”ti?**Soon the brahmin remembered. He hurried back and asked that monk, “Sir, did you see my bag?”*";
P_HTM[5978]="*“Handa, brāhmaṇā”ti adāsi.**Saying, “I did indeed,” he gave it to him.*";
P_HTM[5979]="*Atha kho tassa brāhmaṇassa etadahosi—“kena nu kho ahaṃ upāyena imassa bhikkhuno puṇṇapattaṃ na dadeyyan”ti.**The brahmin thought, “How can I avoid giving a reward to this monk?”*";
P_HTM[5980]="*“Na me, bho, pañcasatāni, sahassaṃ me”ti palibundhetvā muñci.**And he said, “I didn’t have five hundred coins, I had a thousand!” And he seized hold of that monk.*";
P_HTM[5981]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**After being released, that monk went to the monastery and told the monks what had happened.*";
P_HTM[5982]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[5983]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu ratanaṃ uggahessatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk pick up precious things?” …*";
P_HTM[5984]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, ratanaṃ uggahesī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[5985]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[5986]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[5987]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, ratanaṃ uggahessasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[5988]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[5989]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[5990]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu ratanaṃ vā ratanasammataṃ vā uggaṇheyya vā uggaṇhāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk picks up something precious or something regarded as precious, or he has it picked up, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[5991]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[5992]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyā ussavo hoti. Manussā alaṅkatappaṭiyattā uyyānaṃ gacchanti.**Soon afterwards they were holding a celebration in Sāvatthī, with people going to the park all dressed up,*";
P_HTM[5993]="*Visākhāpi migāramātā alaṅkatappaṭiyattā “uyyānaṃ gamissāmī”ti**as did Visākhā Migāramātā.*";
P_HTM[5994]="*gāmato nikkhamitvā—“kyāhaṃ karissāmi uyyānaṃ gantvā, yannūnāhaṃ bhagavantaṃ payirupāseyyan”ti**As she was leaving her village, she thought, “What will I do when I get to the park? Why don’t I pay a visit to the Buddha!”*";
P_HTM[5995]="*ābharaṇaṃ omuñcitvā uttarāsaṅgena bhaṇḍikaṃ bandhitvā dāsiyā adāsi—“handa, je, imaṃ bhaṇḍikaṃ gaṇhāhī”ti.**She then removed all her ornaments, bound them in a bundle with her upper robe, and gave it to her slave girl, saying, “Listen, look after this bundle.”*";
P_HTM[5996]="*Atha kho visākhā migāramātā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**Visākhā then went to the Buddha, bowed, and sat down.*";
P_HTM[5997]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho visākhaṃ migāramātaraṃ bhagavā dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi. Atha kho visākhā migāramātā bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā uṭṭhāyāsanā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**And the Buddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching, after which she got up from her seat, bowed down, circumambulated him with her right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[5998]="*Atha kho sā dāsī taṃ bhaṇḍikaṃ vissaritvā agamāsi.**And the slave girl left too, forgetting the bundle.*";
P_HTM[5999]="*Bhikkhū passitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ. “Tena hi, bhikkhave, uggahetvā nikkhipathā”ti.**The monks saw it and told the Buddha. “Well then, monks, pick it up and put it aside.”*";
P_HTM[6000]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6001]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ratanaṃ vā ratanasammataṃ vā ajjhārāme uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipituṃ—‘yassa bhavissati so harissatī’ti.**“Within a monastery, monks, you should pick up precious things or what’s regarded as precious, or have it picked up, and then put it aside with the thought, ‘Whoever owns this will come and get it.’*";
P_HTM[6002]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6003]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu ratanaṃ vā ratanasammataṃ vā, aññatra ajjhārāmā, uggaṇheyya vā uggaṇhāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk picks up something precious or something regarded as precious, or he has it picked up, except within a monastery, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6004]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6005]="*Tena kho pana samayena kāsīsu janapade anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa kammantagāmo hoti.**At that time the householder Anāthapiṇḍika had a whole village working for him in the country of Kāsī,*";
P_HTM[6006]="*Tena ca gahapatinā antevāsī āṇatto hoti—“sace bhadantā āgacchanti, bhattaṃ kareyyāsī”ti.**and he had told an apprentice there that if the monks arrived he should make them a meal.*";
P_HTM[6007]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū kāsīsu janapade cārikaṃ caramānā yena anāthapiṇḍikassa gahapatissa kammantagāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**Soon afterwards a number of monks were wandering in the country of Kāsī, when they came to that village.*";
P_HTM[6008]="*Addasā kho so puriso te bhikkhū dūratova āgacchante. Disvāna yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū abhivādetvā etadavoca—“adhivāsentu, bhante, ayyā svātanāya gahapatino bhattan”ti.**When that man saw them coming, he approached them, bowed, and said, “Venerables, please accept a meal from Anāthapiṇḍika tomorrow.”*";
P_HTM[6009]="*Adhivāsesuṃ kho te bhikkhū tuṇhībhāvena.**The monks accepted by remaining silent.*";
P_HTM[6010]="*Atha kho so puriso tassā rattiyā accayena paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā kālaṃ ārocāpetvā aṅgulimuddikaṃ omuñcitvā te bhikkhū bhattena parivisitvā—**The following morning, after having various kinds of fine food prepared, he had the monks informed that it was time for the meal. He removed a ring from his finger and then offered the food to the monks, saying,*";
P_HTM[6011]="*“ayyā bhuñjitvā gacchantu, ahampi kammantaṃ gamissāmī”ti aṅgulimuddikaṃ vissaritvā agamāsi.**“Venerables, please leave after you’ve eaten. I have to go to work.” And he left, forgetting his ring.*";
P_HTM[6012]="*Bhikkhū passitvā—“sace mayaṃ gamissāma nassissatāyaṃ aṅgulimuddikā”ti tattheva acchiṃsu.**The monks saw it and said, “If we just go, this ring will be lost,” and so they stayed right there.*";
P_HTM[6013]="*Atha kho so puriso kammantā āgacchanto te bhikkhū passitvā etadavoca—“kissa, bhante, ayyā idheva acchantī”ti?**When that man returned from work, he saw the monks and said to them, “Why are you still here?”*";
P_HTM[6014]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū tassa purisassa etamatthaṃ ārocetvā**And the monks told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6015]="*sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Those monks then went to Sāvatthī where they told the monks,*";
P_HTM[6016]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6017]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**After giving a teaching, the Buddha addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6018]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, ratanaṃ vā ratanasammataṃ vā ajjhārāme vā ajjhāvasathe vā uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipituṃ—**“Within a monastery, monks, or inside a lodging, you should pick up precious things or what’s regarded as precious, or have it picked up, and then put it aside with the thought,*";
P_HTM[6019]="*‘yassa bhavissati so harissatī’ti.**‘Whoever owns this will come and get it.’*";
P_HTM[6020]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6021]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu ratanaṃ vā ratanasammataṃ vā, aññatra ajjhārāmā vā ajjhāvasathā vā, uggaṇheyya vā uggaṇhāpeyya vā, pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk picks up something precious or something regarded as precious, or he has it picked up, except within a monastery or inside a lodging, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6022]="*Ratanaṃ vā pana bhikkhunā ratanasammataṃ vā ajjhārāme vā ajjhāvasathe vā uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipitabbaṃ—‘yassa bhavissati so harissatī’ti. Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcī”ti.**If he picks up something precious or something regarded as precious, or he has it picked up, within a monastery or inside a lodging, he should put it aside with the thought, “Whoever owns it will fetch it.” This is the proper procedure.’”*";
P_HTM[6023]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6024]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6025]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6026]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6027]="*Ratanaṃ nāma**Something precious:*";
P_HTM[6028]="*muttā maṇi veḷuriyo saṅkho silā pavālaṃ rajataṃ jātarūpaṃ lohitaṅko masāragallaṃ.**a pearl, a gem, a beryl, mother-of-pearl, quartz, a coral, silver, gold, a ruby, a cat’s eye.*";
P_HTM[6029]="*Ratanasammataṃ nāma**Something regarded as precious:*";
P_HTM[6030]="*yaṃ manussānaṃ upabhogaparibhogaṃ, etaṃ ratanasammataṃ nāma.**whatever people regard as valuable or useful—this is called “regarded as precious”.*";
P_HTM[6031]="*Aññatra ajjhārāmā vā ajjhāvasathā vāti**Except within a monastery or inside a lodging:*";
P_HTM[6032]="*ṭhapetvā ajjhārāmaṃ ajjhāvasathaṃ.**apart from within a monastery or inside a lodging.*";
P_HTM[6033]="*Ajjhārāmo nāma**Within a monastery:*";
P_HTM[6034]="*parikkhittassa ārāmassa anto ārāmo, aparikkhittassa upacāro.**if the monastery is enclosed, then within the enclosure. If the monastery is unenclosed, then in the vicinity.*";
P_HTM[6035]="*Ajjhāvasatho nāma**Inside a lodging:*";
P_HTM[6036]="*parikkhittassa āvasathassa anto āvasatho, aparikkhittassa upacāro.**if the lodging is enclosed, then within the enclosure. If the lodging is unenclosed, then in the vicinity.*";
P_HTM[6037]="*Uggaṇheyyāti**Picks up:*";
P_HTM[6038]="*sayaṃ gaṇhāti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he takes hold of it himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6039]="*Uggaṇhāpeyyāti**Has picked up:*";
P_HTM[6040]="*aññaṃ gāhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he gets someone else to take hold of it, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6041]="*Ratanaṃ vā pana bhikkhunā ratanasammataṃ vā ajjhārāme vā ajjhāvasathe vā uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipitabbanti**If he picks up something precious or something regarded as precious, or he has it picked up, within a monastery or inside a lodging, he should put it aside:*";
P_HTM[6042]="*rūpena vā nimittena vā saññāṇaṃ katvā nikkhipitvā ācikkhitabbaṃ—“yassa bhaṇḍaṃ naṭṭhaṃ so āgacchatū”ti.**after taking note of its appearance or distinguishing marks, he should put it aside, and then make an announcement: “Whoever has lost anything should come.”*";
P_HTM[6043]="*Sace tattha āgacchati so vattabbo—“āvuso, kīdisaṃ te bhaṇḍan”ti?**If anyone comes, they should be told, “Please describe your goods.”*";
P_HTM[6044]="*Sace rūpena vā nimittena vā sampādeti dātabbaṃ, no ce sampādeti “vicināhi, āvuso”ti vattabbo.**If they rightly describe the appearance or distinguishing marks, it should be given to them. If they do not, they should be told, “Keep looking.”*";
P_HTM[6045]="*Tamhā āvāsā pakkamantena ye tattha honti bhikkhū patirūpā, tesaṃ hatthe nikkhipitvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**If that monk is leaving that monastery, he should first place those goods into the hands of suitable monks there.*";
P_HTM[6046]="*No ce honti bhikkhū patirūpā, ye tattha honti gahapatikā patirūpā, tesaṃ hatthe nikkhipitvā pakkamitabbaṃ.**If there are no suitable monks, he should place those goods into the hands of suitable householders there.*";
P_HTM[6047]="*Ayaṃ tattha sāmīcīti**This is the proper procedure:*";
P_HTM[6048]="*ayaṃ tattha anudhammatā.**this is the right method.*";
P_HTM[6049]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6050]="*ratanaṃ vā ratanasammataṃ vā ajjhārāme vā ajjhāvasathe vā uggahetvā vā uggahāpetvā vā nikkhipati—“yassa bhavissati so harissatī”ti,**if he picks up something precious or something regarded as precious, or he has it picked up, within a monastery or inside a lodging, and then puts it aside with the thought, “Whoever owns it will fetch it;”*";
P_HTM[6051]="*ratanasammataṃ vissāsaṃ gaṇhāti, tāvakālikaṃ gaṇhāti, paṃsukūlasaññissa,**if he takes something regarded as precious on trust or he borrows it or he perceives it as discarded;*";
P_HTM[6052]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6053]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6054]="*Ratanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dutiyaṃ.**The training rule on precious things, the second, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6055]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6056]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6057]="*85. Vikālagāmappavisanasikkhāpada**85. The training rule on entering an inhabited area at the wrong time*";
P_HTM[6058]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6059]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitvā sabhāyaṃ nisīditvā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathenti, seyyathidaṃ—**At that time the monks from the group of six entered the village at the wrong time, sat down in the public meeting hall, and talked about all sorts of pointless things:*";
P_HTM[6060]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ mahāmattakathaṃ senākathaṃ bhayakathaṃ yuddhakathaṃ annakathaṃ pānakathaṃ vatthakathaṃ sayanakathaṃ mālākathaṃ gandhakathaṃ ñātikathaṃ yānakathaṃ gāmakathaṃ nigamakathaṃ nagarakathaṃ janapadakathaṃ itthikathaṃ sūrakathaṃ visikhākathaṃ kumbhaṭṭhānakathaṃ pubbapetakathaṃ nānattakathaṃ lokakkhāyikaṃ samuddakkhāyikaṃ itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā.**about kings, gangsters, and officials; about armies, dangers, and battles; about food, drink, clothes, and beds; about garlands and perfumes; about relatives, vehicles, villages, towns, and countries; about women and heroes; gossip; about the departed; about various trivialities; about the world and the sea; about the various kinds of existence.*";
P_HTM[6061]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6062]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitvā sabhāyaṃ nisīditvā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathessanti, seyyathidaṃ—**“How can the Sakyan monastics enter the village at the wrong time, sit down in the public meeting hall, and talk about such pointless things?*";
P_HTM[6063]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6064]="*itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6065]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[6066]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6067]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitvā sabhāyaṃ nisīditvā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathessanti, seyyathidaṃ—**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[6068]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ …pe…**…*";
P_HTM[6069]="*itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā”ti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6070]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitvā sabhāyaṃ nisīditvā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathetha, seyyathidaṃ—**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[6071]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6072]="*itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā”ti?* **";
P_HTM[6073]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6074]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[6075]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitvā sabhāyaṃ nisīditvā anekavihitaṃ tiracchānakathaṃ kathessatha, seyyathidaṃ—**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[6076]="*rājakathaṃ corakathaṃ …pe…* **";
P_HTM[6077]="*itibhavābhavakathaṃ iti vā.* **";
P_HTM[6078]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6079]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6080]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu vikāle gāmaṃ paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk enters an inhabited area at the wrong time, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6081]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6082]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchantā sāyaṃ aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upagacchiṃsu.**Soon afterwards a number of monks were walking through the Kosalan country on their way to Sāvatthī, when one evening they came to a certain village.*";
P_HTM[6083]="*Manussā te bhikkhū passitvā etadavocuṃ—**People saw them and said,*";
P_HTM[6084]="*“pavisatha, bhante”ti.**“Venerables, please enter the village.”*";
P_HTM[6085]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū—* **";
P_HTM[6086]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitun”ti kukkuccāyantā na pavisiṃsu.**But knowing that entering a village at the wrong time had been prohibited by the Buddha and being afraid of wrongdoing, they declined.*";
P_HTM[6087]="*Corā te bhikkhū acchindiṃsu.**And so thieves robbed them.*";
P_HTM[6088]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They then went to Sāvatthī and told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[6089]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6090]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6091]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, āpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to enter an inhabited area at the wrong time after taking leave.*";
P_HTM[6092]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6093]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk, without taking leave, enters an inhabited area at the wrong time, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6094]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6095]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchanto sāyaṃ aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upagacchi.**Soon afterwards a monk was walking through the Kosalan country on his way to Sāvatthī, when one evening he came to a certain village.*";
P_HTM[6096]="*Manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā etadavocuṃ—**People saw him and said,*";
P_HTM[6097]="*“pavisatha, bhante”ti.**“Venerable, please enter the village.”*";
P_HTM[6098]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—* **";
P_HTM[6099]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na pāvisi.**But knowing that entering a village at the wrong time without taking leave had been prohibited by the Buddha and being afraid of wrongdoing, he declined.*";
P_HTM[6100]="*Corā taṃ bhikkhuṃ acchindiṃsu.**And so thieves robbed him.*";
P_HTM[6101]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He then went to Sāvatthī and told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[6102]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6103]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6104]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to enter an inhabited area at the wrong time after taking leave of an available monk.*";
P_HTM[6105]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6106]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk, when a monk is available, enters an inhabited area at the wrong time without taking leave of him, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6107]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6108]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu ahinā daṭṭho hoti.**Soon afterwards a monk was bitten by a snake.*";
P_HTM[6109]="*Aññataro bhikkhu “aggiṃ āharissāmī”ti gāmaṃ gacchati.**Another monk went to the village to get fire.*";
P_HTM[6110]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—**He then remembered*";
P_HTM[6111]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na pāvisi …pe…**that the Buddha has prohibited entering a village at the wrong time without taking leave of an available monk. And being afraid of wrongdoing, he did not enter.*";
P_HTM[6112]="*bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6113]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6114]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tathārūpe accāyike karaṇīye santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ pavisituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to enter an inhabited area at the wrong time without taking leave of an available monk if there is some appropriate urgent business.*";
P_HTM[6115]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6116]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā vikāle gāmaṃ paviseyya, aññatra tathārūpā accāyikā karaṇīyā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk, when another monk is available, enters an inhabited area at the wrong time without taking leave of him, except if there is some appropriate urgent business, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6117]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6118]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6119]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6120]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6121]="*Santo nāma bhikkhu**An available monk:*";
P_HTM[6122]="*sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ.**he is able to take leave of him and then enter.*";
P_HTM[6123]="*Asanto nāma bhikkhu**No available monk:*";
P_HTM[6124]="*na sakkā hoti āpucchā pavisituṃ.**he is not able to take leave and then enter.*";
P_HTM[6125]="*Vikālo nāma**At the wrong time:*";
P_HTM[6126]="*majjhanhike vītivatte yāva aruṇuggamanā.**when the middle of the day has passed, until dawn.*";
P_HTM[6127]="*Gāmaṃ paviseyyāti**Enters an inhabited area:*";
P_HTM[6128]="*parikkhittassa gāmassa parikkhepaṃ atikkamantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**if he crosses the boundary of an enclosed inhabited area, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6129]="*Aparikkhittassa gāmassa upacāraṃ okkamantassa āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he enters the vicinity of an unenclosed inhabited area, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6130]="*Aññatra tathārūpā accāyikā karaṇīyāti**Except if there is some appropriate urgent business:*";
P_HTM[6131]="*ṭhapetvā tathārūpaṃ accāyikaṃ karaṇīyaṃ.**unless there is some appropriate urgent business.*";
P_HTM[6132]="*Vikāle vikālasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā gāmaṃ pavisati, aññatra tathārūpā accāyikā karaṇīyā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the wrong time, and he perceives it as such, and he enters an inhabited area without taking leave of an available monk, except if there is some appropriate urgent business, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6133]="*Vikāle vematiko santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā gāmaṃ pavisati, aññatra tathārūpā accāyikā karaṇīyā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the wrong time, but he is unsure of it, and he enters an inhabited area without taking leave of an available monk, except if there is some appropriate urgent business, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6134]="*Vikāle kālasaññī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā gāmaṃ pavisati, aññatra tathārūpā accāyikā karaṇīyā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the wrong time, but he perceives it as the right time, and he enters an inhabited area without taking leave of an available monk, except if there is some appropriate urgent business, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6135]="*Kāle vikālasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is the right time, but he perceives it as the wrong time, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6136]="*Kāle vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is the right time, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6137]="*Kāle kālasaññī, anāpatti.**If it is the right time, and he perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[6138]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6139]="*tathārūpe accāyike karaṇīye,**if there is some appropriate urgent business;*";
P_HTM[6140]="*santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā pavisati,**if he enters after taking leave of an available monk;*";
P_HTM[6141]="*asantaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā pavisati,**if he enters without taking leave when there is no available monk;*";
P_HTM[6142]="*antarārāmaṃ gacchati,**if he is going between monasteries;*";
P_HTM[6143]="*bhikkhunupassayaṃ gacchati,**if he is going to the dwelling place of nuns;*";
P_HTM[6144]="*titthiyaseyyaṃ gacchati,**if he is going to the dwelling place of the monastics of another religion;*";
P_HTM[6145]="*paṭikkamanaṃ gacchati,**if he is returning to the monastery;*";
P_HTM[6146]="*gāmena maggo hoti,**if the road goes via an inhabited area;*";
P_HTM[6147]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[6148]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6149]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6150]="*Vikālagāmappavisanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ tatiyaṃ.**The training rule on entering an inhabited area at the wrong time, the third, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6151]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6152]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6153]="*86. Sūcigharasikkhāpada**86. The training rule on needle cases*";
P_HTM[6154]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in the Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu.*";
P_HTM[6155]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena dantakārena bhikkhū pavāritā honti—**At that time an ivory-worker had invited the monks*";
P_HTM[6156]="*“yesaṃ ayyānaṃ sūcigharena attho ahaṃ sūcigharenā”ti.**who needed needle cases to ask for one.*";
P_HTM[6157]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū bahū sūcighare viññāpenti.**And the monks asked for many needle cases.*";
P_HTM[6158]="*Yesaṃ khuddakā sūcigharā te mahante sūcighare viññāpenti.**Those who had small needle cases asked for large ones,*";
P_HTM[6159]="*Yesaṃ mahantā sūcigharā te khuddake sūcighare viññāpenti.**and those who had large needle cases asked for small ones.*";
P_HTM[6160]="*Atha kho so dantakāro bhikkhūnaṃ bahū sūcighare karonto na sakkoti aññaṃ vikkāyikaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ kātuṃ, attanāpi na yāpeti, puttadāropissa kilamati.**The ivory-worker was so busy making needle cases for the monks that he was unable to make goods for sale. He could not make a living for himself, and his wives and children suffered.*";
P_HTM[6161]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6162]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū sūcighare viññāpessanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics not have any sense of moderation and ask for many needle cases?*";
P_HTM[6163]="*Ayaṃ imesaṃ bahū sūcighare karonto na sakkoti aññaṃ vikkāyikaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ kātuṃ, attanāpi na yāpeti, puttadāropissa kilamatī”ti.**This ivory-worker is so busy making needle cases for them that he’s unable to make goods for sale. He can’t make a living for himself, and his wives and children are suffering.”*";
P_HTM[6164]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[6165]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6166]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū sūcighare viññāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can those monks not have a sense of moderation and ask for many needle cases?” …*";
P_HTM[6167]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū sūcighare viññāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that there are monks who do this?”*";
P_HTM[6168]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6169]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[6170]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahū sūcighare viññāpessanti.**“How can those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[6171]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6172]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6173]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu aṭṭhimayaṃ vā dantamayaṃ vā visāṇamayaṃ vā sūcigharaṃ kārāpeyya bhedanakaṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk has a needle case made from bone, ivory, or horn, it is to be destroyed, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6174]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6175]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6176]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6177]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6178]="*Aṭṭhi nāma**Bone:*";
P_HTM[6179]="*yaṃ kiñci aṭṭhi.**any kind of bone.*";
P_HTM[6180]="*Danto nāma**Ivory:*";
P_HTM[6181]="*hatthidanto vuccati.**elephant tooth is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[6182]="*Visāṇaṃ nāma**Horn:*";
P_HTM[6183]="*yaṃ kiñci visāṇaṃ.**any kind of horn.*";
P_HTM[6184]="*Kārāpeyyāti**Has made:*";
P_HTM[6185]="*karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if he makes one or has one made, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6186]="*Paṭilābhena bhinditvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**When he gets it, it is to be destroyed, and he is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6187]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6188]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6189]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6190]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6191]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6192]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6193]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6194]="*gaṇṭhikāya,**if it is a toggle;*";
P_HTM[6195]="*araṇike,**if it is a fire kindler;*";
P_HTM[6196]="*vidhe,**if it is a buckle;*";
P_HTM[6197]="*añjaniyā,**if it is an ointment box;*";
P_HTM[6198]="*añjanisalākāya,**if it is an ointment stick;*";
P_HTM[6199]="*vāsijaṭe,**if it is a adz handle;*";
P_HTM[6200]="*udakapuñchaniyā,**if it is a water wiper;*";
P_HTM[6201]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6202]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6203]="*Sūcigharasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ catutthaṃ.**The training rule on needle cases, the fourth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6204]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6205]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6206]="*87. Mañcapīṭhasikkhāpada**87. The training rule on beds and benches*";
P_HTM[6207]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[6208]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā upanando sakyaputto ucce mañce sayati.**Venerable Upananda the Sakyan was sleeping on a high bed.*";
P_HTM[6209]="*Atha kho bhagavā sambahulehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ senāsanacārikaṃ āhiṇḍanto yenāyasmato upanandassa sakyaputtassa vihāro tenupasaṅkami.**On one occasion, as the Buddha and a number of monks were walking about the dwellings, they came to Upananda’s dwelling.*";
P_HTM[6210]="*Addasā kho āyasmā upanando sakyaputto bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**Upananda saw the Buddha coming*";
P_HTM[6211]="*Disvāna bhagavantaṃ etadavoca—**and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6212]="*“āgacchatu me, bhante, bhagavā sayanaṃ passatū”ti.**“Sir, please come and see my bed.”*";
P_HTM[6213]="*Atha kho bhagavā tatova paṭinivattitvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**The Buddha turned around on the spot and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6214]="*“āsayato, bhikkhave, moghapuriso veditabbo”ti.**“A fool, monks, can be recognized by his sleeping place.”*";
P_HTM[6215]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ upanandaṃ sakyaputtaṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**After criticizing Upananda in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support … the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[6216]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6217]="*“Navaṃ pana bhikkhunā mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā kārayamānena aṭṭhaṅgulapādakaṃ kāretabbaṃ sugataṅgulena, aññatra heṭṭhimāya aṭaniyā; taṃ atikkāmayato chedanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk is having a new bed or bench made, it is to have legs eight standard fingerbreadths long below the lowest frame. If the legs exceed that, they are to be cut down, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6218]="*Navaṃ nāma**New:*";
P_HTM[6219]="*karaṇaṃ upādāya vuccati.**newly made is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[6220]="*Mañco nāma**A bed:*";
P_HTM[6221]="*cattāro mañcā— masārako, bundikābaddho, kuḷīrapādako, āhaccapādako.**there are four kinds of beds: one with legs and frame, called _masāraka_; one with legs and frame, called _bundikābaddha_; one with crooked legs; one with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[6222]="*Pīṭhaṃ nāma**A bench:*";
P_HTM[6223]="*cattāri pīṭhāni— masārakaṃ, bundikābaddhaṃ, kuḷīrapādakaṃ, āhaccapādakaṃ.**there are four kinds of benches: one with legs and frame, called _masāraka_; one with legs and frame, called _bundikābaddha_; one with crooked legs; one with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[6224]="*Kārayamānenāti**Is having made:*";
P_HTM[6225]="*karonto vā kārāpento vā.**making it himself or having it made.*";
P_HTM[6226]="*Aṭṭhaṅgulapādakaṃ kāretabbaṃ sugataṅgulena, aññatra heṭṭhimāya aṭaniyāti**It is to have legs eight standard fingerbreadths long below the lowest frame:*";
P_HTM[6227]="*ṭhapetvā heṭṭhimaṃ aṭaniṃ;**apart from the lowest frame.*";
P_HTM[6228]="*taṃ atikkāmetvā karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ, paṭilābhena chinditvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**If he makes one, or has one made, that exceeds that, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct. When he gets it, the legs are to be cut down, and he is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6229]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6230]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6231]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6232]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6233]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6234]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6235]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6236]="*pamāṇikaṃ karoti,**if he makes it the right size;*";
P_HTM[6237]="*ūnakaṃ karoti,**if he makes it smaller than the right size;*";
P_HTM[6238]="*aññena kataṃ pamāṇātikkantaṃ paṭilabhitvā chinditvā paribhuñjati,**if he gets one made by another that exceeds the right size and then cuts the legs down before using it;*";
P_HTM[6239]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6240]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6241]="*Mañcapīṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ pañcamaṃ.**The training rule on beds and benches, the fifth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6242]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6243]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6244]="*88. Tūlonaddhasikkhāpada**88. The training rule on upholstered with cotton down*";
P_HTM[6245]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[6246]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mañcampi pīṭhampi tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpenti.**the monks from the group of six had beds and benches made upholstered with cotton down.*";
P_HTM[6247]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6248]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā mañcampi pīṭhampi tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpessanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics have beds and benches made upholstered with cotton down? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6249]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[6250]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6251]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mañcampi pīṭhampi tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[6252]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, mañcampi pīṭhampi tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[6253]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6254]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[6255]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, mañcampi pīṭhampi tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpessatha.**“Foolish men, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[6256]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6257]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6258]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu mañcaṃ vā pīṭhaṃ vā tūlonaddhaṃ kārāpeyya, uddālanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a monk has a bed or a bench made upholstered with cotton down, it is to be stripped, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6259]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6260]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6261]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6262]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6263]="*Mañco nāma**A bed:*";
P_HTM[6264]="*cattāro mañcā— masārako, bundikābaddho, kuḷīrapādako, āhaccapādako.**there are four kinds of beds: one with legs and frame, called _masāraka_; one with legs and frame, called _bundikābaddha_; one with crooked legs; one with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[6265]="*Pīṭhaṃ nāma**A bench:*";
P_HTM[6266]="*cattāri pīṭhāni— masārakaṃ, bundikābaddhaṃ, kuḷīrapādakaṃ, āhaccapādakaṃ.**there are four kinds of benches: one with legs and frame, called _masāraka_; one with legs and frame, called _bundikābaddha_; one with crooked legs; one with detachable legs.*";
P_HTM[6267]="*Tūlaṃ nāma**Cotton down:*";
P_HTM[6268]="*tīṇi tūlāni— rukkhatūlaṃ, latātūlaṃ, poṭakitūlaṃ.**there are three kinds of cotton down: cotton down from trees, cotton down from creepers, cotton down from grass.*";
P_HTM[6269]="*Kārāpeyyāti**Has made:*";
P_HTM[6270]="*karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if he makes one or has one made, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6271]="*Paṭilābhena uddāletvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**When he gets it, it is to be stripped, and he is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6272]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6273]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6274]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6275]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6276]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6277]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6278]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6279]="*āyoge,**if it is for a back-and-knee strap;*";
P_HTM[6280]="*kāyabandhane,**if it is for a belt;*";
P_HTM[6281]="*aṃsabaddhake,**if it is for a shoulder strap;*";
P_HTM[6282]="*pattatthavikāya,**if it is for a bowl bag;*";
P_HTM[6283]="*parissāvane,**if it is for a water filter;*";
P_HTM[6284]="*bibbohanaṃ karoti,**if he is making a pillow;*";
P_HTM[6285]="*aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā uddāletvā paribhuñjati,**if he gets one made by another and then strips it before using it;*";
P_HTM[6286]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6287]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6288]="*Tūlonaddhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ.**The training rule on upholstered with cotton down, the sixth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6289]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6290]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6291]="*89. Nisīdanasikkhāpada**89. The training rule on sitting mats*";
P_HTM[6292]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[6293]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ nisīdanaṃ anuññātaṃ hoti.**he allowed the sitting mat for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6294]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—* **";
P_HTM[6295]="*“bhagavatā nisīdanaṃ anuññātan”ti appamāṇikāni nisīdanāni dhārenti.**Knowing this, the monks from the group of six used sitting mats that were inappropriate in size.*";
P_HTM[6296]="*Mañcassapi pīṭhassapi puratopi pacchatopi olambenti.**The sitting mats hung down from beds and benches, both in front and behind.*";
P_HTM[6297]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6298]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū appamāṇikāni nisīdanāni dhāressantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six use such sitting mats?” …*";
P_HTM[6299]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, appamāṇikāni nisīdanāni dhārethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[6300]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6301]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[6302]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, appamāṇikāni nisīdanāni dhāressatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[6303]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6304]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6305]="*“Nisīdanaṃ pana bhikkhunā kārayamānena pamāṇikaṃ kāretabbaṃ.**‘If a monk is having a sitting mat made, it is to be made the right size.*";
P_HTM[6306]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso dve vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ diyaḍḍhaṃ.**This is the right size: two standard handspans long and one-and-a-half wide.*";
P_HTM[6307]="*Taṃ atikkāmayato chedanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**If it exceeds that, it is to be cut down, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6308]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6309]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā udāyī mahākāyo hoti.**At that time there was a big monk called Venerable Udāyī.*";
P_HTM[6310]="*So bhagavato purato nisīdanaṃ paññapetvā samantato samañchamāno nisīdati.**After putting out his sitting mat in front of the Buddha, he stretched it on all sides before sitting down.*";
P_HTM[6311]="*Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ udāyiṃ etadavoca—**The Buddha asked him,*";
P_HTM[6312]="*“kissa tvaṃ, udāyi, nisīdanaṃ samantato samañchasi;**“Udāyī, why are you stretching the sitting mat on all sides,*";
P_HTM[6313]="*seyyathāpi purāṇāsikoṭṭho”ti?**as if an old hide?”*";
P_HTM[6314]="*“Tathā hi pana, bhante, bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ atikhuddakaṃ nisīdanaṃ anuññātan”ti.**“Because, Venerable Sir, the sitting mat you’ve allowed for the monks is too small.”*";
P_HTM[6315]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6316]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, nisīdanassa dasaṃ vidatthiṃ.**“Monks, I allow a border of one handspan for the sitting mat.*";
P_HTM[6317]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6318]="*“Nisīdanaṃ pana bhikkhunā kārayamānena pamāṇikaṃ kāretabbaṃ.**‘If a monk is having a sitting mat made, it should be made the right size.*";
P_HTM[6319]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso dve vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ diyaḍḍhaṃ. Dasā vidatthi.**This is the right size: two standard handspans long and one-and-a-half wide, and a border of one handspan.*";
P_HTM[6320]="*Taṃ atikkāmayato chedanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**If it exceeds that, it is to be cut down, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6321]="*Nisīdanaṃ nāma**A sitting mat:*";
P_HTM[6322]="*sadasaṃ vuccati.**one with a border is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[6323]="*Kārayamānenāti**Is having made:*";
P_HTM[6324]="*karonto vā kārāpento vā pamāṇikaṃ kāretabbaṃ.**making it himself or having it made, it should be made the right size.*";
P_HTM[6325]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ— dīghaso dve vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ diyaḍḍhaṃ. Dasā vidatthi.**This is the right size: two standard handspans long and one-and-a-half wide, and a border of one handspan.*";
P_HTM[6326]="*Taṃ atikkāmetvā karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**If he makes one, or has one made, that exceeds that, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6327]="*Paṭilābhena chinditvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**When he gets it, it is to be cut down, and he is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6328]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6329]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6330]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6331]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6332]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6333]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6334]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6335]="*pamāṇikaṃ karoti,**if he makes it the right size;*";
P_HTM[6336]="*ūnakaṃ karoti,**if he makes it smaller than the right size;*";
P_HTM[6337]="*aññena kataṃ pamāṇātikkantaṃ paṭilabhitvā chinditvā paribhuñjati,**if he gets one made by another that exceeds the right size and then cuts it down before using it;*";
P_HTM[6338]="*vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,**if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a cloth screen, a mattress, or a pillow;*";
P_HTM[6339]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6340]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6341]="*Nisīdanasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ sattamaṃ.**The training rule on sitting mats, the seventh, is finished.*";
