P_HTM[6344]="*90. Kaṇḍuppaṭicchādisikkhāpada**90. The training rule on itch covers*";
P_HTM[6345]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[6346]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ kaṇḍuppaṭicchādi anuññātā hoti.**he allowed the itch-covering cloth for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6347]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—* **";
P_HTM[6348]="*“bhagavatā kaṇḍuppaṭicchādi anuññātā”ti appamāṇikāyo kaṇḍuppaṭicchādiyo dhārenti;**Knowing this, the monks from the group of six wore itch covers that were inappropriate in size.*";
P_HTM[6349]="*puratopi pacchatopi ākaḍḍhantā āhiṇḍanti.**As they were walking about, they were dragging them along, both in front and behind.*";
P_HTM[6350]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6351]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū appamāṇikāyo kaṇḍuppaṭicchādiyo dhāressantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six wear such itch covers?” …*";
P_HTM[6352]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, appamāṇikāyo kaṇḍuppaṭicchādiyo dhārethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[6353]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
