P_HTM[6355]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, appamāṇikāyo kaṇḍuppaṭicchādiyo dhāressatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[6356]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6357]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6358]="*“Kaṇḍuppaṭicchādiṃ pana bhikkhunā kārayamānena pamāṇikā kāretabbā.**‘If a monk is having an itch-covering cloth made, it should be made the right size.*";
P_HTM[6359]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso catasso vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ dve vidatthiyo.**This is the right size: four standard handspans long and two wide.*";
P_HTM[6360]="*Taṃ atikkāmayato chedanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**If it exceeds that, it is to be cut down, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6361]="*Kaṇḍuppaṭicchādi nāma**An itch-covering cloth:*";
P_HTM[6362]="*yassa adhonābhi ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ kaṇḍu vā pīḷakā vā assāvo vā thullakacchu vā ābādho, tassa paṭicchādanatthāya.**it is for the purpose of covering an itch or a boil or a running sore or a carbuncle, below the navel and above the knees.*";
