P_HTM[6379]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6380]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6381]="*Kaṇḍuppaṭicchādisikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ aṭṭhamaṃ.**The training rule on itch covers, the eighth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6382]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6383]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6384]="*91. Vassikasāṭikāsikkhāpada**91. The training rule on rainy-season robes*";
P_HTM[6385]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[6386]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ vassikasāṭikā anuññātā hoti.**he allowed the rainy-season robe for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6387]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū—* **";
P_HTM[6388]="*“bhagavatā vassikasāṭikā anuññātā”ti appamāṇikāyo vassikasāṭikāyo dhārenti.**Knowing this, the monks from the group of six wore rainy-season robes that were inappropriate in size.*";
P_HTM[6389]="*Puratopi pacchatopi ākaḍḍhantā āhiṇḍanti.**As they were walking about, they were dragging them along, both in front and behind.*";
P_HTM[6390]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6391]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū appamāṇikāyo vassikasāṭikāyo dhāressantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six wear such rainy-season robes?” …*";
P_HTM[6392]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, appamāṇikāyo vassikasāṭikāyo dhārethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[6393]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6394]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[6395]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, appamāṇikāyo vassikasāṭikāyo dhāressatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[6396]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6397]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6398]="*“Vassikasāṭikaṃ pana bhikkhunā kārayamānena pamāṇikā kāretabbā.**‘If a monk is having a rainy-season robe made, it should be made the right size.*";
P_HTM[6399]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso cha vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ aḍḍhateyyā.**This is the right size: six standard handspans long and two-and-a-half wide.*";
P_HTM[6400]="*Taṃ atikkāmayato chedanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**If it exceeds that, it is to be cut down, and he commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[6401]="*Vassikasāṭikā nāma**A rainy-season robe:*";
P_HTM[6402]="*vassānassa catumāsatthāya.**it is for use during the four months of the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[6403]="*Kārayamānenāti**Is having made:*";
P_HTM[6404]="*karonto vā kārāpento vā. Pamāṇikā kāretabbā.**making it himself or having it made, it should be made to the right size.*";
P_HTM[6405]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ— dīghaso cha vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ aḍḍhateyyā.**This is the right size: six standard handspans long and two and a half wide.*";
P_HTM[6406]="*Taṃ atikkāmetvā karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**If he makes one or has one made that exceeds that, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6407]="*Paṭilābhena chinditvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**When he gets it, it is to be cut down, and he is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6408]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6409]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6410]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6411]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6412]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6413]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6414]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6415]="*pamāṇikaṃ karoti,**if he makes it the right size;*";
P_HTM[6416]="*ūnakaṃ karoti,**if he makes it smaller than the right size;*";
P_HTM[6417]="*aññena kataṃ pamāṇātikkantaṃ paṭilabhitvā chinditvā paribhuñjati,**if he gets one made by another that exceeds the right size and then cuts it down before using it;*";
P_HTM[6418]="*vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,**if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a cloth screen, a mattress, or a pillow;*";
P_HTM[6419]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6420]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6421]="*Vassikasāṭikāsikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ navamaṃ.**The training rule on rainy-season robes, the ninth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6422]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[6423]="*Ratanavagga**The sub-chapter on precious things*";
P_HTM[6424]="*92. Nandasikkhāpada**92. The training rule on Nanda*";
P_HTM[6425]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6426]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā nando bhagavato mātucchāputto abhirūpo hoti dassanīyo pāsādiko caturaṅgulomako bhagavatā.**At that time there was a handsome and graceful monk called Venerable Nanda, the Buddha’s cousin. He was 7 centimeters shorter than the Buddha,*";
P_HTM[6427]="*So sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ dhāreti.**but he wore a robe that was the same size as the Buddha’s.*";
P_HTM[6428]="*Addasaṃsu kho therā bhikkhū āyasmantaṃ nandaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ.**When the senior monks saw him coming,*";
P_HTM[6429]="*Disvāna—* **";
P_HTM[6430]="*“bhagavā āgacchatī”ti āsanā vuṭṭhahanti.**they thought it was the Buddha and got up from their seats.*";
P_HTM[6431]="*Te upagate jānitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**But when he came close, they realized who it was, and they complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[6432]="*“kathañhi nāma āyasmā nando sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ dhāressatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Nanda wear a robe the same size as the Buddha’s?” …*";
P_HTM[6433]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, nanda, sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ dhāresī”ti?**“Is it true, Nanda, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[6434]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6435]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[6436]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, nanda, sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ dhāressasi.**“Nanda, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[6437]="*Netaṃ, nanda, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6438]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6439]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ cīvaraṃ kārāpeyya atirekaṃ vā, chedanakaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**‘If a monk has a robe made that is the standard robe measure or larger, it is to be cut down, and he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6440]="*Tatridaṃ sugatassa sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ—dīghaso nava vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ cha vidatthiyo.**This is the standard robe measure: nine standard handspans long and six wide.’”*";
P_HTM[6441]="*Idaṃ sugatassa sugatacīvarappamāṇan”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6442]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6443]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6444]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6445]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6446]="*Sugatacīvarappamāṇaṃ nāma**The standard robe measure:*";
P_HTM[6447]="*dīghaso nava vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ cha vidatthiyo.**nine standard handspans long and six wide.*";
P_HTM[6448]="*Kārāpeyyāti**Has made:*";
P_HTM[6449]="*karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if he makes one or has one made, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6450]="*Paṭilābhena chinditvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**When he gets it, it is to be cut down, and he is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6451]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6452]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6453]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6454]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he has others finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[6455]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6456]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6457]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6458]="*ūnakaṃ karoti,**if he makes it smaller than the standard robe;*";
P_HTM[6459]="*aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā chinditvā paribhuñjati,**if he gets one made by another that is too large and then cuts it down before using it;*";
P_HTM[6460]="*vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,**if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a cloth screen, a mattress, or a pillow;*";
P_HTM[6461]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6462]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6463]="*Nandasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ.**The training rule on Nanda, the tenth, is finished.*";
P_HTM[6464]="*Ratanavaggo navamo.**The ninth sub-chapter on precious things is finished.*";
P_HTM[6465]="*Tassuddānaṃ**This is the summary:*";
P_HTM[6466]="*Rañño ca ratanaṃ santaṃ,**King’s, and precious things, available,*";
P_HTM[6467]="*sūci mañcañca tūlikaṃ;**Needle, and bed, cotton down;*";
P_HTM[6468]="*Nisīdanañca kaṇḍuñca,**And sitting mat, and itch,*";
P_HTM[6469]="*vassikā sugatena cāti.**Rainy-season, and by the standard.*";
P_HTM[6470]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, āyasmanto, dvenavuti pācittiyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the ninety-two rules on confession have been recited.*";
P_HTM[6471]="*Tatthāyasmante pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[6472]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[6473]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[6474]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[6475]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[6476]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[6477]="*Parisuddhetthāyasmanto, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[6478]="*Khuddakaṃ samattaṃ.**The section on minor rules has been completed.*";
P_HTM[6479]="*Pācittiyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing confession is finished.*";
P_HTM[6480]="*127. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment *";
P_HTM[6481]="*1. Paṭhamapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpada**1. The first training rule on acknowledgment*";
P_HTM[6482]="*Ime kho panāyasmanto cattāro pāṭidesanīyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these four rules on acknowledgment come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[6483]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[6484]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā paṭikkamanakāle aññataraṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā etadavoca—**a certain nun was returning from almsround in Sāvatthī. She saw a monk and said to him,*";
P_HTM[6485]="*“handāyya, bhikkhaṃ paṭiggaṇhā”ti.**“Here, Venerable, please take some almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[6486]="*“Suṭṭhu, bhaginī”ti sabbeva aggahesi.**Saying, “Alright, Sister,” he took everything.*";
P_HTM[6487]="*Sā upakaṭṭhe kāle nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ, chinnabhattā ahosi.**But because the time for eating was coming to an end, she was not able to go for alms, and she missed her meal.*";
P_HTM[6488]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī dutiyampi divasaṃ …pe…**The next day*";
P_HTM[6489]="*tatiyampi divasaṃ sāvatthiyaṃ piṇḍāya caritvā paṭikkamanakāle taṃ bhikkhuṃ passitvā etadavoca—**and the following day the same thing happened again.*";
P_HTM[6490]="*“handāyya, bhikkhaṃ paṭiggaṇhā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6491]="*“Suṭṭhu, bhaginī”ti sabbeva aggahesi.* **";
P_HTM[6492]="*Sā upakaṭṭhe kāle nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ, chinnabhattā ahosi.* **";
P_HTM[6493]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī catutthe divase rathikāya pavedhentī gacchati.**On the fourth day that nun was walking along a street, trembling.*";
P_HTM[6494]="*Seṭṭhi gahapati rathena paṭipathaṃ āgacchanto taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**A wealthy merchant coming by carriage in the opposite direction saw her and shouted out,*";
P_HTM[6495]="*“apehāyye”ti.**“Watch out, Venerable!”*";
P_HTM[6496]="*Sā vokkamantī tattheva paripati.**As she stepped aside, she collapsed right there.*";
P_HTM[6497]="*Seṭṭhi gahapati taṃ bhikkhuniṃ khamāpesi—**And the merchant asked her for forgiveness:*";
P_HTM[6498]="*“khamāhāyye, mayāsi pātitā”ti.**“Forgive me, Venerable, since you fell because of me.”*";
P_HTM[6499]="*“Nāhaṃ, gahapati, tayā pātitā.**“I didn’t fall because of you,*";
P_HTM[6500]="*Api ca ahameva dubbalā”ti.**but because I’m weak.”*";
P_HTM[6501]="*“Kissa pana tvaṃ, ayye, dubbalā”ti?**“But why are you so weak?”*";
P_HTM[6502]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī seṭṭhissa gahapatissa etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**The nun told him what had happened.*";
P_HTM[6503]="*Seṭṭhi gahapati taṃ bhikkhuniṃ gharaṃ netvā bhojetvā ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**He then brought her to his house and gave her a meal. Afterwards he complained and criticized the monks,*";
P_HTM[6504]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā bhikkhuniyā hatthato āmisaṃ paṭiggahessanti.**“How can the venerables receive food directly from a nun?*";
P_HTM[6505]="*Kicchalābho mātugāmo”ti.**It’s difficult for women to get material support.”*";
P_HTM[6506]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tassa seṭṭhissa gahapatissa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The monks heard the complaints of that merchant,*";
P_HTM[6507]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized that monk,*";
P_HTM[6508]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu bhikkhuniyā hatthato āmisaṃ paṭiggahessatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk receive food directly from a nun?” …*";
P_HTM[6509]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhikkhuniyā hatthato āmisaṃ paṭiggahesī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[6510]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6511]="*“Ñātikā te, bhikkhu, aññātikā”ti?**“Is she a relative of yours?”*";
P_HTM[6512]="*“Aññātikā, bhagavā”ti.**“No, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6513]="*“Aññātako, moghapurisa, aññātikāya na jānāti patirūpaṃ vā appatirūpaṃ vā santaṃ vā asantaṃ vā.**“Foolish man, a man and a woman who are unrelated don’t know what’s appropriate and inappropriate, what’s good and bad, in dealing with each other.*";
P_HTM[6514]="*Kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthato āmisaṃ paṭiggahessasi.**So how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[6515]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6516]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6517]="*“Yo pana bhikkhu aññātikāya bhikkhuniyā antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, paṭidesetabbaṃ tena bhikkhunā—**‘If a monk receives fresh or cooked food directly from an unrelated nun who has entered an inhabited area, and then eats it, he must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6518]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ, taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6519]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6520]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6521]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6522]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6523]="*Aññātikā nāma**Unrelated:*";
P_HTM[6524]="*mātito vā pitito vā yāva sattamā pitāmahayugā asambaddhā.**anyone who is not a descendant of one’s male ancestors going back seven generations, either on the mother’s side or on the father’s side.*";
P_HTM[6525]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[6526]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[6527]="*Antaragharaṃ nāma**An inhabited area:*";
P_HTM[6528]="*rathikā byūhaṃ siṅghāṭakaṃ gharaṃ.**a street, a cul-de-sac, an intersection, a house.*";
P_HTM[6529]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[6530]="*pañca bhojanāni yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics, the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[6531]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**cooked food:*";
P_HTM[6532]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[6533]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives the food with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6534]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6535]="*Aññātikāya aññātikasaññī antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is unrelated and he perceives her as such, and he receives fresh or cooked food directly from her when she has entered an inhabited area, and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6536]="*Aññātikāya vematiko antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is unrelated, but he is unsure of it, and he receives fresh or cooked food directly from her when she has entered an inhabited area, and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6537]="*Aññātikāya ñātikasaññī antaragharaṃ paviṭṭhāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is unrelated, but he perceives her as related, and he receives fresh or cooked food directly from her when she has entered an inhabited area, and then eats it, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6538]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6539]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6540]="*Ekatoupasampannāya hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā—**If he receives fresh or cooked food, with the intention of eating it, directly from a nun who is fully ordained only on one side,*";
P_HTM[6541]="*“khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6542]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6543]="*Ñātikāya aññātikasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is related, but he perceives her as unrelated, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6544]="*Ñātikāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is related, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6545]="*Ñātikāya ñātikasaññī, anāpatti.**If she is related, and he perceives her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[6546]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6547]="*ñātikāya,**if she is related;*";
P_HTM[6548]="*dāpeti na deti,**if she has someone else give it and does not give herself;*";
P_HTM[6549]="*upanikkhipitvā deti,**if she gives by placing it near;*";
P_HTM[6550]="*antarārāme,**if it is inside a monastery;*";
P_HTM[6551]="*bhikkhunupassaye,**if it is at the dwelling place of nuns;*";
P_HTM[6552]="*titthiyaseyyāya,**if it is at the dwelling place of the monastics of another religion;*";
P_HTM[6553]="*paṭikkamane,**if it is on returning to the monastery;*";
P_HTM[6554]="*gāmato nīharitvā deti,**if she gives after carrying it out of the village;*";
P_HTM[6555]="*yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ “sati paccaye paribhuñjā”ti deti,**if she gives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics, saying, “Use these when there’s a reason;”*";
P_HTM[6556]="*sikkhamānāya,**if it is a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[6557]="*sāmaṇeriyā,**if it is a novice nun;*";
P_HTM[6558]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6559]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6560]="*Paṭhamapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule on acknowledgment is finished.*";
P_HTM[6561]="*127. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment *";
P_HTM[6562]="*2. Dutiyapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpada**2. The second training rule on acknowledgment*";
P_HTM[6563]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[6564]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kulesu nimantitā bhuñjanti.**At that time, when families invited monks to meals,*";
P_HTM[6565]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vosāsantiyo ṭhitā honti—**the nuns from the group of six were directing people toward the monks from the group of six, saying,*";
P_HTM[6566]="*“idha sūpaṃ detha, idha odanaṃ dethā”ti.**“Give curry here; give rice here.”*";
P_HTM[6567]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhū yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjanti.**The monks from the group of six ate as much as they wanted,*";
P_HTM[6568]="*Aññe bhikkhū na cittarūpaṃ bhuñjanti.**but not so the other monks.*";
P_HTM[6569]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6570]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhuniyo vosāsantiyo na nivāressantī”ti …pe…**“How could the monks from the group of six not restrain the nuns from giving directions?” …*";
P_HTM[6571]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vosāsantiyo na nivārethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you didn’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[6572]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6573]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[6574]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, bhikkhuniyo vosāsantiyo na nivāressatha.**“Foolish men, how could you not do this?*";
P_HTM[6575]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6576]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6577]="*“Bhikkhū paneva kulesu nimantitā bhuñjanti, tatra ce sā bhikkhunī vosāsamānarūpā ṭhitā hoti—‘idha sūpaṃ detha, idha odanaṃ dethā’ti, tehi bhikkhūhi sā bhikkhunī apasādetabbā— ‘apasakka tāva, bhagini, yāva bhikkhū bhuñjantī’ti. Ekassa cepi bhikkhuno na paṭibhāseyya taṃ bhikkhuniṃ apasādetuṃ— ‘apasakka tāva, bhagini, yāva bhikkhū bhuñjantī’ti paṭidesetabbaṃ tehi bhikkhūhi—**‘When monks eat at invitations to families, if a nun is there giving directions, saying, “Give bean curry here; give rice here,” then those monks should stop her: “Stop, Sister, while the monks are eating.” If not even a single monk addresses that nun in this way to stop her, they must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6578]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjimhā asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ, taṃ paṭidesemā’”ti.**“We have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing which is to be acknowledged. We acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6579]="*Bhikkhū paneva kulesu nimantitā bhuñjantīti**When monks eat at invitations to families:*";
P_HTM[6580]="*kulaṃ nāma cattāri kulāni— khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ.**a family: there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[6581]="*Nimantitā bhuñjantīti**Eat at invitations:*";
P_HTM[6582]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantitā bhuñjanti.**eat any of the five cooked foods at invitations.*";
P_HTM[6583]="*Bhikkhunī nāma**A nun:*";
P_HTM[6584]="*ubhatosaṅghe upasampannā.**she has been given the full ordination by both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[6585]="*Vosāsantī nāma**Giving directions:*";
P_HTM[6586]="*yathāmittatā yathāsandiṭṭhatā yathāsambhattatā yathāsamānupajjhāyakatā yathāsamānācariyakatā— “idha sūpaṃ detha, idha odanaṃ dethā”ti. Esā vosāsantī nāma.**saying, “Give bean curry here; give rice here,” according to friendship, according to companionship, according to who one is devoted to, according to being a co-student, according to being a co-pupil—this is called “giving directions”.*";
P_HTM[6587]="*Tehi bhikkhūhīti**Those monks:*";
P_HTM[6588]="*bhuñjamānehi bhikkhūhi.**the monks who are eating.*";
P_HTM[6589]="*Sā bhikkhunīti**Her:*";
P_HTM[6590]="*yā sā vosāsantī bhikkhunī.**the nun who is giving directions.*";
P_HTM[6591]="*Tehi bhikkhūhi sā bhikkhunī apasādetabbā— “apasakka tāva, bhagini, yāva bhikkhū bhuñjantī”ti.**Those monks should stop her: ‘Stop, Sister, while the monks are eating’:*";
P_HTM[6592]="*Ekassa cepi bhikkhuno anapasādito— “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if she is not stopped by even one monk, and a monk then receives food with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6593]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6594]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññī vosāsantiyā na nivāreti, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is fully ordained, and he perceives her as such, and he does not restrain her from giving directions, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6595]="*Upasampannāya vematiko vosāsantiyā na nivāreti, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, and he does not restrain her from giving directions, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6596]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññī vosāsantiyā na nivāreti, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is fully ordained, but he does not perceive her as such, and he does not restrain her from giving directions, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6597]="*Ekatoupasampannāya vosāsantiyā na nivāreti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he does not restrain a nun who is fully ordained only on one side from giving directions, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6598]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the person is not fully ordained, but he perceives them as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6599]="*Anupasampannāya vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the person is not fully ordained, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6600]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññī, anāpatti.**If the person is not fully ordained, and he does not perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[6601]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6602]="*attano bhattaṃ dāpeti na deti,**if a nun has someone else give her own food, but she does not give it herself;*";
P_HTM[6603]="*aññesaṃ bhattaṃ deti na dāpeti,**if a nun gives someone else’s food, but she does not have anyone give it;*";
P_HTM[6604]="*yaṃ na dinnaṃ taṃ dāpeti,**if a nun has someone give what has not yet been given;*";
P_HTM[6605]="*yattha na dinnaṃ tattha dāpeti,**if a nun has someone give to someone who has not yet received anything;*";
P_HTM[6606]="*sabbesaṃ samakaṃ dāpeti,**if a nun has someone give equally to all;*";
P_HTM[6607]="*sikkhamānā vosāsati,**if a trainee nun is giving directions;*";
P_HTM[6608]="*sāmaṇerī vosāsati,**if a novice nun is giving directions;*";
P_HTM[6609]="*pañca bhojanāni ṭhapetvā sabbattha, anāpatti,**if it is anything apart from the five kinds of cooked food;*";
P_HTM[6610]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6611]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6612]="*Dutiyapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule on acknowledgment is finished.*";
P_HTM[6613]="*127. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment *";
P_HTM[6614]="*3. Tatiyapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpada**3. The third training rule on acknowledgment*";
P_HTM[6615]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6616]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ aññataraṃ kulaṃ ubhatopasannaṃ hoti.**At that time in Sāvatthī there was a family where both the husband and the wife had confidence.*";
P_HTM[6617]="*Saddhāya vaḍḍhati, bhogena hāyati, yaṃ tasmiṃ kule uppajjati purebhattaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ sabbaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ vissajjetvā appekadā anasitā acchanti.**They were growing in faith, but declining in wealth. Whatever food they had in the morning, they gave to the monks. Sometimes they went without food.*";
P_HTM[6618]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized the monks,*";
P_HTM[6619]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā na mattaṃ jānitvā paṭiggahessanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics not have a sense of moderation in receiving offerings?*";
P_HTM[6620]="*Ime imesaṃ datvā appekadā anasitā acchantī”ti.**After giving to them, these people sometimes go without.”*";
P_HTM[6621]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[6622]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6623]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6624]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, yaṃ kulaṃ saddhāya vaḍḍhati, bhogena hāyati evarūpassa kulassa ñattidutiyena kammena sekkhasammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, if a family’s faith is growing, but its wealth is declining, I allow you to designate it as ‘in training’, through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement.*";
P_HTM[6625]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And the designation should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[6626]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[6627]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6628]="*Itthannāmaṃ kulaṃ saddhāya vaḍḍhati, bhogena hāyati.**Such-and-such a family is growing in faith, but declining in wealth.*";
P_HTM[6629]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmassa kulassa sekkhasammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should designate that family as “in training”.*";
P_HTM[6630]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[6631]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[6632]="*Itthannāmaṃ kulaṃ saddhāya vaḍḍhati, bhogena hāyati.**Such-and-such a family is growing in faith, but declining in wealth.*";
P_HTM[6633]="*Saṅgho itthannāmassa kulassa sekkhasammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha designates that family as “in training”.*";
P_HTM[6634]="*Yassāyasmato khamati itthannāmassa kulassa sekkhasammutiyā dānaṃ, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of designating that family as “in training” should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[6635]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[6636]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmassa kulassa sekkhasammuti.**The Sangha designates such-and-such a family as “in training”.*";
P_HTM[6637]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[6638]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6639]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni sekkhasammatāni kulāni, yo pana bhikkhu tathārūpesu sekkhasammatesu kulesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, paṭidesetabbaṃ tena bhikkhunā—**‘There are families that are designated as “in training”. If a monk eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from such a family, he must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6640]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6641]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6642]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ ussavo hoti.**Soon afterwards there was a celebration in Sāvatthī*";
P_HTM[6643]="*Manussā bhikkhū nimantetvā bhojenti.**and people invited the monks for a meal.*";
P_HTM[6644]="*Tampi kho kulaṃ bhikkhū nimantesi.**And so did the family that had been designated as in training.*";
P_HTM[6645]="*Bhikkhū kukkuccāyantā nādhivāsenti—* **";
P_HTM[6646]="*“paṭikkhittaṃ bhagavatā sekkhasammatesu kulesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādituṃ bhuñjitun”ti.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited eating fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from such a family, and being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not accept.*";
P_HTM[6647]="*Te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**That family complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6648]="*“kiṃ nu kho nāma amhākaṃ jīvitena yaṃ ayyā amhākaṃ na paṭiggaṇhantī”ti.**“What is it with us that they don’t receive from us?”*";
P_HTM[6649]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[6650]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6651]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6652]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, nimantitena sekkhasammatesu kulesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādituṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, if you have been invited, I allow you to eat fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from a family designated as in training.*";
P_HTM[6653]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6654]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni sekkhasammatāni kulāni, yo pana bhikkhu tathārūpesu sekkhasammatesu kulesu pubbe animantito khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, paṭidesetabbaṃ tena bhikkhunā—**‘There are families that are designated as “in training”. If a monk, without first being invited, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from such a family, he must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6655]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ, taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6656]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6657]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu tassa kulassa kulūpako hoti.**Soon afterwards a certain monk was associating with that family.*";
P_HTM[6658]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**One morning he robed up, took his bowl and robe, went to them, and sat down on the prepared seat.*";
P_HTM[6659]="*Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu gilāno hoti.**Just then that monk was sick,*";
P_HTM[6660]="*Atha kho te manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**and so they invited him to eat.*";
P_HTM[6661]="*“bhuñjatha, bhante”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6662]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—* **";
P_HTM[6663]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ animantitena sekkhasammatesu kulesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādituṃ bhuñjitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggahesi;**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited an uninvited monk from eating fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from such a family, and being afraid of wrongdoing, he did not accept.*";
P_HTM[6664]="*nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ;**And being unable to walk for alms,*";
P_HTM[6665]="*chinnabhatto ahosi.**he missed his meal.*";
P_HTM[6666]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu ārāmaṃ gantvā bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He then returned to the monastery and told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[6667]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6668]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6669]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā sekkhasammatesu kulesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādituṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from a family designated as in training.*";
P_HTM[6670]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6671]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni sekkhasammatāni kulāni, yo pana bhikkhu tathārūpesu sekkhasammatesu kulesu pubbe animantito agilāno khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, paṭidesetabbaṃ tena bhikkhunā—**‘There are families that are designated as “in training”. If a monk, without being sick and without first being invited, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from such a family, he must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6672]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ, taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6673]="*Yāni kho pana tāni sekkhasammatāni kulānīti**There are families that are designated as “in training”:*";
P_HTM[6674]="*sekkhasammataṃ nāma kulaṃ yaṃ kulaṃ saddhāya vaḍḍhati, bhogena hāyati. Evarūpassa kulassa ñattidutiyena kammena sekkhasammuti dinnā hoti.**a family designated as in training: a family in which the faith is growing but the wealth is declining. Such a family is designated as “in training” through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement.*";
P_HTM[6675]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6676]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6677]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6678]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6679]="*Tathārūpesu sekkhasammatesu kulesūti**Such a family:*";
P_HTM[6680]="*evarūpesu sekkhasammatesu kulesu.**that kind of family.*";
P_HTM[6681]="*Animantito nāma**Without being invited:*";
P_HTM[6682]="*ajjatanāya vā svātanāya vā animantito, gharūpacāraṃ okkamante nimanteti, eso animantito nāma.**not invited for later on the same day or for the following day, but only after entering the vicinity of the house—this is called “without being invited”.*";
P_HTM[6683]="*Nimantito nāma**Invited:*";
P_HTM[6684]="*ajjatanāya vā svātanāya vā nimantito, gharūpacāraṃ anokkamante nimanteti, eso nimantito nāma.**invited for later on the same day or for the following day, but not after entering the vicinity of the house—this is called “invited”.*";
P_HTM[6685]="*Agilāno nāma**Without being sick:*";
P_HTM[6686]="*sakkoti piṇḍāya carituṃ.**who is able to walk for alms.*";
P_HTM[6687]="*Gilāno nāma**Sick:*";
P_HTM[6688]="*na sakkoti piṇḍāya carituṃ.**who is unable to walk for alms.*";
P_HTM[6689]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[6690]="*pañca bhojanāni yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[6691]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[6692]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour  products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[6693]="*Animantito agilāno “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, without being sick and without being invited, he receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6694]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6695]="*Sekkhasammate sekkhasammatasaññī animantito agilāno khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If a family is designated as in training, and he perceives it as such, and he, without being sick and without being invited, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from that family, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6696]="*Sekkhasammate vematiko …pe…**If a family is designated as in training, but he is unsure of it, and he, without being sick and without being invited, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from that family, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6697]="*sekkhasammate asekkhasammatasaññī animantito agilāno khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If a family is designated as in training, but he does not perceive it as such, and he, without being sick and without being invited, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it from that family, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6698]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6699]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6700]="*Asekkhasammate sekkhasammatasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a family is not designated as in training, but he perceives it as such, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6701]="*Asekkhasammate vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a family is not designated as in training, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6702]="*Asekkhasammate asekkhasammatasaññī, anāpatti.**If a family is not designated as in training, and he does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[6703]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6704]="*nimantitassa,**if he has been invited;*";
P_HTM[6705]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[6706]="*nimantitassa vā gilānassa vā sesakaṃ bhuñjati,**if he eats the leftovers from one who has been invited or who is sick;*";
P_HTM[6707]="*aññesaṃ bhikkhā tattha paññattā hoti,**if other people’s almsfood is prepared there;*";
P_HTM[6708]="*gharato nīharitvā denti,**if they give after coming out from the house;*";
P_HTM[6709]="*niccabhatte,**if it is a regular meal invitation;*";
P_HTM[6710]="*salākabhatte,**if it is a meal for which lots are drawn;*";
P_HTM[6711]="*pakkhike,**if it is a half-monthly meal;*";
P_HTM[6712]="*uposathike,**if it is on the observance day;*";
P_HTM[6713]="*pāṭipadike,**if it is on the day after the observance day;*";
P_HTM[6714]="*yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ— “sati paccaye paribhuñjā”ti deti,**if the family gives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics, saying, “Use these when there’s a reason;”*";
P_HTM[6715]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6716]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6717]="*Tatiyapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule on acknowledgment is finished.*";
P_HTM[6718]="*127. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment *";
P_HTM[6719]="*4. Catutthapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpada**4. The fourth training rule on acknowledgment*";
P_HTM[6720]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in the Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu,*";
P_HTM[6721]="*Tena kho pana samayena sākiyadāsakā avaruddhā honti.**the slaves of the Sakyans were rebelling.*";
P_HTM[6722]="*Sākiyāniyo icchanti āraññakesu senāsanesu bhattaṃ kātuṃ.**The Sakyan women wished to prepare a meal at the wilderness dwellings,*";
P_HTM[6723]="*Assosuṃ kho sākiyadāsakā—**but the slaves heard about this*";
P_HTM[6724]="*“sākiyāniyo kira āraññakesu senāsanesu bhattaṃ kattukāmā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6725]="*Te magge pariyuṭṭhiṃsu.**and infested the path.*";
P_HTM[6726]="*Sākiyāniyo paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ ādāya āraññakaṃ senāsanaṃ agamaṃsu.**When the Sakyan women took various kinds of fine food and set out for a wilderness dwelling,*";
P_HTM[6727]="*Sākiyadāsakā nikkhamitvā sākiyāniyo acchindiṃsu ca dūsesuñca.**the slaves emerged, and they robbed and raped those Sakyan women.*";
P_HTM[6728]="*Sākiyā nikkhamitvā te core sabhaṇḍe gahetvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**Soon afterwards the Sakyan men came out, and they got hold of those criminals together with their loot. They then complained and criticized the monks,*";
P_HTM[6729]="*“kathañhi nāma bhadantā ārāme core paṭivasante nārocessantī”ti.**“How could they not announce that there are criminals staying in the monastery?”*";
P_HTM[6730]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū sākiyānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of the Sakyans*";
P_HTM[6731]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6732]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6733]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca saṅghasuṭṭhutāya …pe…**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons: for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad people, for the ease of well-behaved monks, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[6734]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6735]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanāni sāsaṅkasammatāni sappaṭibhayāni, yo pana bhikkhu tathārūpesu senāsanesu pubbe appaṭisaṃviditaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, paṭidesetabbaṃ tena bhikkhunā—**‘There are wilderness dwellings that are considered risky and dangerous. If a monk, without first making an announcement about those dwellings, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside that monastery, he must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6736]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6737]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[6738]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro bhikkhu āraññakesu senāsanesu gilāno hoti.**Soon afterwards a monk in a wilderness dwelling was sick.*";
P_HTM[6739]="*Manussā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ādāya āraññakaṃ senāsanaṃ agamaṃsu.**People took fresh or cooked food and went to that wilderness dwelling,*";
P_HTM[6740]="*Atha kho te manussā taṃ bhikkhuṃ etadavocuṃ—**and they invited that monk to eat.*";
P_HTM[6741]="*“bhuñjatha, bhante”ti.* **";
P_HTM[6742]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu—* **";
P_HTM[6743]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ āraññakesu senāsanesu khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādituṃ bhuñjitun”ti kukkuccāyanto na paṭiggahesi, nāsakkhi piṇḍāya carituṃ, chinnabhatto ahosi.**But knowing that the Buddha had prohibited the eating of fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it at a wilderness dwelling, and being afraid of wrongdoing, he did not accept it. And being unable to walk for alms, he missed his meal.*";
P_HTM[6744]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**He then told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[6745]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6746]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[6747]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā āraññakesu senāsanesu pubbe appaṭisaṃviditaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādituṃ bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk, without first making an announcement, to eat fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it at a wilderness dwelling.*";
P_HTM[6748]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6749]="*“Yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanāni sāsaṅkasammatāni sappaṭibhayāni, yo pana bhikkhu tathārūpesu senāsanesu pubbe appaṭisaṃviditaṃ khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā agilāno khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, paṭidesetabbaṃ tena bhikkhunā—**‘There are wilderness dwellings that are considered risky and dangerous. If a monk who is not sick, without first making an announcement about those dwellings, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside that monastery, he must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[6750]="*‘gārayhaṃ, āvuso, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ, taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[6751]="*Yāni kho pana tāni āraññakāni senāsanānīti**There are wilderness dwellings:*";
P_HTM[6752]="*āraññakaṃ nāma senāsanaṃ pañcadhanusatikaṃ pacchimaṃ.**a wilderness dwelling: if it is at least 800 meters away from any inhabited area.*";
P_HTM[6753]="*Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma**Risky:*";
P_HTM[6754]="*ārāme ārāmūpacāre corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati.**in the monastery, or in the vicinity of the monastery, criminals have been seen camped, eating, standing, seated, or lying down.*";
P_HTM[6755]="*Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma**Dangerous:*";
P_HTM[6756]="*ārāme ārāmūpacāre corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā dissanti.**in the monastery, or in the vicinity of the monastery, criminals have been seen injuring, robbing, or beating people.*";
P_HTM[6757]="*Yo panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[6758]="*yo yādiso …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[6759]="*bhikkhūti**Monk:*";
P_HTM[6760]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti.**… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a unanimous Sangha through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of monk is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[6761]="*Tathārūpesu senāsanesūti**About those dwellings:*";
P_HTM[6762]="*evarūpesu senāsanesu.**about such kinds of dwellings.*";
P_HTM[6763]="*Appaṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma**Without making an announcement:*";
P_HTM[6764]="*pañcannaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ, etaṃ appaṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**if an announcement is made to any of one’s five co-monastics, this is called “without making an announcement”.*";
P_HTM[6765]="*Ārāmaṃ ārāmūpacāraṃ ṭhapetvā paṭisaṃviditaṃ, etaṃ appaṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**If an announcement is made about anything apart from the monastery or its vicinity, this is called “without making an announcement”.*";
P_HTM[6766]="*Paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma**Making an announcement:*";
P_HTM[6767]="*yo koci itthī vā puriso vā ārāmaṃ ārāmūpacāraṃ āgantvā āroceti— “itthannāmassa, bhante, khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā āharissantī”ti. Sace sāsaṅkaṃ hoti, sāsaṅkanti ācikkhitabbaṃ; sace sappaṭibhayaṃ hoti, sappaṭibhayanti ācikkhitabbaṃ;**if a woman or a man comes to the monastery or the vicinity of the monastery and says, “Venerable, they’ll bring so-and-so’s fresh or cooked food,” then, if it is risky, this should be declared, and if it is dangerous, that should be declared.*";
P_HTM[6768]="*sace— “hotu, bhante, āhariyissatī”ti bhaṇati, corā vattabbā— “manussā idhūpacaranti apasakkathā”ti.**If the person says, “Never mind, it will be brought,” then the criminals are to be told, “People are coming here; go away.”*";
P_HTM[6769]="*Yāguyā paṭisaṃvidite tassā parivāro āhariyyati, etaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**When an announcement has been made in regard to rice porridge, and accompanying food is brought, this is called “announced”.*";
P_HTM[6770]="*Bhattena paṭisaṃvidite tassa parivāro āhariyyati, etaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**When an announcement has been made in regard to rice, and accompanying food is brought, this is called “announced”.*";
P_HTM[6771]="*Khādanīyena paṭisaṃvidite tassa parivāro āhariyyati, etaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**When an announcement has been made in regard to fresh food, and accompanying food is brought, this is called “announced”.*";
P_HTM[6772]="*Kulena paṭisaṃvidite yo tasmiṃ kule manusso khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā āharati, etaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**When an announcement has been made in regard to a particular family, then when any person from that family brings fresh or cooked food, this is called “announced”.*";
P_HTM[6773]="*Gāmena paṭisaṃvidite yo tasmiṃ gāme manusso khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā āharati, etaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**When an announcement has been made in regard to a particular village, then when any person from that village brings fresh or cooked food, this is called “announced”.*";
P_HTM[6774]="*Pūgena paṭisaṃvidite yo tasmiṃ pūge manusso khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā āharati, etaṃ paṭisaṃviditaṃ nāma.**When an announcement has been made in regard to a particular association, then when any person from that association brings fresh or cooked food, this is called “announced”.*";
P_HTM[6775]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[6776]="*pañca bhojanāni yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics—the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[6777]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[6778]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[6779]="*Ajjhārāmo nāma**Inside that monastery:*";
P_HTM[6780]="*parikkhittassa ārāmassa antoārāmo.**if the monastery is enclosed, then within the enclosure.*";
P_HTM[6781]="*Aparikkhittassa upacāro.**If the monastery is unenclosed, then in the vicinity.*";
P_HTM[6782]="*Agilāno nāma**Who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[6783]="*sakkoti piṇḍāya carituṃ.**who is able to walk for alms.*";
P_HTM[6784]="*Gilāno nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[6785]="*na sakkoti piṇḍāya carituṃ.**who is unable to walk for alms.*";
P_HTM[6786]="*Appaṭisaṃviditaṃ agilāno “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, without making an announcement, one who is not sick receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6787]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6788]="*Appaṭisaṃvidite appaṭisaṃviditasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā agilāno khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If there has been no announcement, and he does not perceive that there has, and he, not being sick, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside that monastery, then he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6789]="*Appaṭisaṃvidite vematiko khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā agilāno khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If there has been no announcement, but he is unsure of it, and he, not being sick, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside that monastery, then he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6790]="*Appaṭisaṃvidite paṭisaṃviditasaññī khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā ajjhārāme sahatthā paṭiggahetvā agilāno khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If there has been no announcement, but he perceives that there has, and he, not being sick, eats fresh or cooked food after personally receiving it inside that monastery, then he commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[6791]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6792]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6793]="*Paṭisaṃvidite appaṭisaṃviditasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there has been an announcement, but he does not perceive that there has, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6794]="*Paṭisaṃvidite vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there has been an announcement, but he is unsure of it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6795]="*Paṭisaṃvidite paṭisaṃviditasaññī, anāpatti.**If there has been an announcement, and he perceives that there has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[6796]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6797]="*paṭisaṃvidite,**if there has been an announcement;*";
P_HTM[6798]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[6799]="*paṭisaṃvidite vā gilānassa vā sesakaṃ bhuñjati,**if he eats the leftovers from where there has been an announcement or from one who is sick;*";
P_HTM[6800]="*bahārāme paṭiggahetvā antoārāme bhuñjati,**if he receives the food outside the monastery and then eats it inside;*";
P_HTM[6801]="*tattha jātakaṃ mūlaṃ vā tacaṃ vā pattaṃ vā pupphaṃ vā phalaṃ vā bhuñjati,**if he eats a root, bark, a leaf, a flower, or a fruit originating in that monastery;*";
P_HTM[6802]="*yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,**if, when there is a reason, he uses post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics;*";
P_HTM[6803]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6804]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6805]="*Catutthapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule entailing acknowledgment is finished.*";
P_HTM[6806]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, āyasmanto, cattāro pāṭidesanīyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the four rules on acknowledgment have been recited.*";
P_HTM[6807]="*Tatthāyasmante pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[6808]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[6809]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[6810]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[6811]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[6812]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[6813]="*Parisuddhetthāyasmanto, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[6814]="*Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment is finished.*";
P_HTM[6815]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[6816]="*Parimaṇḍalavagga**The sub-chapter on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[6817]="*1. Parimaṇḍalasikkhāpada**1. The training rule on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[6818]="*Ime kho panāyasmanto sekhiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these rules to be trained in come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[6819]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6820]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū puratopi pacchatopi olambentā nivāsenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six wore their sarongs hanging down in front and behind.*";
P_HTM[6821]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[6822]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā puratopi pacchatopi olambentā nivāsessanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics wear their sarongs hanging down in front and behind? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[6823]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[6824]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[6825]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū puratopi pacchatopi olambentā nivāsessantī”ti.**“How can the monks from the group of six wear their sarongs hanging down in front and behind?”*";
P_HTM[6826]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**After rebuking those monks in many ways, they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[6827]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā chabbaggiye bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks from the group of six:*";
P_HTM[6828]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, puratopi pacchatopi olambentā nivāsethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[6829]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[6830]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[6831]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, puratopi pacchatopi olambentā nivāsessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[6832]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[6833]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[6834]="*“Parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will wear my sarong evenly all around,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[6835]="*Parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetabbaṃ nābhimaṇḍalaṃ jāṇumaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentena.**One should wear one’s sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees.*";
P_HTM[6836]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambento nivāseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, wears his sarong hanging down in front or behind, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[6837]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[6838]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[6839]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[6840]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[6841]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[6842]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[6843]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[6844]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[6845]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[6846]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[6847]="*Parimaṇḍalavagga**The sub-chapter on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[6848]="*2. Dutiyaparimaṇḍalasikkhāpada**2. The second training rule on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[6849]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6850]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū puratopi pacchatopi olambentā pārupanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six wore their upper robes hanging down in front and behind. …*";
P_HTM[6851]="*“Parimaṇḍalaṃ pārupissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will wear my upper robe evenly all around,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[6852]="*Parimaṇḍalaṃ pārupitabbaṃ ubho kaṇṇe samaṃ katvā.**One should wear one’s upper robe evenly all around, making both corners even.*";
P_HTM[6853]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambento pārupati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, wears his upper robe hanging down in front or behind, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
