P_HTM[6882]="*4. Dutiyasuppaṭicchannasikkhāpada**4. The second training rule on well-covered*";
P_HTM[6883]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6884]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kāyaṃ vivaritvā antaraghare nisīdanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were sitting in inhabited areas with their bodies uncovered. …*";
P_HTM[6885]="*“Suppaṭicchanno antaraghare nisīdissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will sit well-covered in inhabited areas,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[6886]="*Suppaṭicchannena antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**One should be well-covered while sitting in an inhabited area.*";
P_HTM[6887]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca kāyaṃ vivaritvā antaraghare nisīdati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, sits in an inhabited area with his body uncovered, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
