P_HTM[6900]="*5. Susaṃvutasikkhāpada**5. The training rule on well-restrained*";
P_HTM[6901]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6902]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū hatthampi pādampi kīḷāpentā antaraghare gacchanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were playing with their hands and feet while walking in inhabited areas. …*";
P_HTM[6903]="*“Susaṃvuto antaraghare gamissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will walk well-restrained in inhabited areas,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[6904]="*Susaṃvutena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**One should be well-restrained while walking in an inhabited area.*";
P_HTM[6905]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca hatthaṃ vā pādaṃ vā kīḷāpento antaraghare gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, plays with his hands and feet while walking in an inhabited area, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
