P_HTM[6932]="*7. Okkhittacakkhusikkhāpada**7. The training rule on lowered eyes*";
P_HTM[6933]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[6934]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ olokentā antaraghare gacchanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were looking here and there while walking in inhabited areas. …*";
P_HTM[6935]="*“Okkhittacakkhu antaraghare gamissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will walk with lowered eyes in inhabited areas,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[6936]="*Okkhittacakkhunā antaraghare gantabbaṃ yugamattaṃ pekkhantena.**One should lower one’s eyes while walking in an inhabited area, looking a plow’s length ahead.*";
P_HTM[6937]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca tahaṃ tahaṃ olokento antaraghare gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, looks here and there while walking in an inhabited area, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
