P_HTM[7145]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7146]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīdanti sīsaṃ olambentā …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were swaying and hanging their heads while sitting in inhabited areas. …*";
P_HTM[7147]="*“Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīdissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not sway my head while sitting in inhabited areas,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7148]="*Na sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīditabbaṃ.**One should not sway one’s head while sitting in an inhabited area;*";
P_HTM[7149]="*Sīsaṃ paggahetvā nisīditabbaṃ.**one should sit keeping one’s head straight.*";
P_HTM[7150]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sīsappacālakaṃ antaraghare nisīdati sīsaṃ olambento, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, sways and hangs his head while sitting in an inhabited area, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7151]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7152]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7153]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7154]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7155]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7156]="*vāsūpagatassa,**if he has entered his dwelling;*";
P_HTM[7157]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7158]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7159]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7160]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7161]="*Ujjagghikavaggo dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on laughing loudly is finished.*";
