P_HTM[7167]="*“Na khambhakato antaraghare gamissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not walk in inhabited areas with arms akimbo,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7168]="*Na khambhakatena antaraghare gantabbaṃ.**One should not walk in an inhabited area with arms akimbo.*";
P_HTM[7169]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca ekato vā ubhato vā khambhaṃ katvā antaraghare gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, walks in an inhabited area with one or both arms akimbo, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7170]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7171]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7172]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
