P_HTM[7278]="*29. Samasūpakapaṭiggahaṇasikkhāpada**29. The training rule on receiving an even measure of bean curry*";
P_HTM[7279]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7280]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū piṇḍapātaṃ paṭiggaṇhantā sūpaññeva bahuṃ paṭiggaṇhanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were receiving almsfood with large amounts of bean curry. …*";
P_HTM[7281]="*“Samasūpakaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ paṭiggahessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will receive almsfood with the right proportion of bean curry,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7282]="*Sūpo nāma**Bean curry:*";
P_HTM[7283]="*dve sūpā— muggasūpo, māsasūpo hatthahāriyo.**there are two kinds of bean curry, to be taken with the hand: mung-bean curry and black-gram curry.*";
P_HTM[7284]="*Samasūpako piṇḍapāto paṭiggahetabbo.**Almsfood should be received with the right proportion of bean curry.*";
P_HTM[7285]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sūpaññeva bahuṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, receives much bean curry, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7286]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7287]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7288]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7289]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7290]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7291]="*rasarase,**if it is any food apart from bean curry;*";
P_HTM[7292]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[7293]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[7294]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[7295]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[7296]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7297]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7298]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
