P_HTM[7320]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7321]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū asakkaccaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjanti abhuñjitukāmā viya …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were eating almsfood contemptuously, as if not wanting to eat it. …*";
P_HTM[7322]="*“Sakkaccaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will eat almsfood respectfully,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7323]="*Sakkaccaṃ piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**Almsfood is to be eaten respectfully.*";
P_HTM[7324]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca asakkaccaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, eats almsfood contemptuously, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7325]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7326]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7327]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7328]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7329]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7330]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7331]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7332]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7333]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7334]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7335]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7336]="*32. Pattasaññīsikkhāpada**32. The training rule on attention on the almsbowl*";
P_HTM[7337]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7338]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ olokentā piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjanti, ākirantepi atikkantepi na jānanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were eating almsfood while looking here and there, and they did not know whether people were still giving or whether they had received too much. …*";
P_HTM[7339]="*“Pattasaññī piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will eat almsfood with attention on the almsbowl,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7340]="*Pattasaññinā piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**Almsfood is to be eaten with attention on the bowl.*";
P_HTM[7341]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca tahaṃ tahaṃ olokento piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, eats almsfood while looking here and there, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7342]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7343]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7344]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7345]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7346]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7347]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7348]="*33. Sapadānasikkhāpada**33. The training rule on in order*";
P_HTM[7349]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7350]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ omasitvā piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six ate almsfood picking here and there. …*";
P_HTM[7351]="*“Sapadānaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will eat almsfood in order,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7352]="*Sapadānaṃ piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**Almsfood is to be eaten in order.*";
P_HTM[7353]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca tahaṃ tahaṃ omasitvā piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, eats almsfood picking here and there, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7354]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7355]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7356]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7357]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7358]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7359]="*aññesaṃ dento omasati,**if he picks things out to give to others;*";
P_HTM[7360]="*aññassa bhājane ākiranto omasati,**if he picks things out to put it into someone else’s vessel;*";
P_HTM[7361]="*uttaribhaṅge,**if it is a non-bean curry;*";
P_HTM[7362]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7363]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7364]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7365]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7366]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7367]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7368]="*34. Samasūpakasikkhāpada**34. The training rule on an even measure of bean curry*";
P_HTM[7369]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7370]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjantā sūpaññeva bahuṃ bhuñjanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were eating almsfood with large amounts of bean curry. …*";
P_HTM[7371]="*“Samasūpakaṃ piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will eat almsfood with the right proportion of bean curry,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7372]="*Sūpo nāma**Bean curry:*";
P_HTM[7373]="*dve sūpā—**there are two kinds of bean curry, to be taken with the hand:*";
P_HTM[7374]="*muggasūpo, māsasūpo hatthahāriyo.**mung-bean curry and black-gram curry.*";
P_HTM[7375]="*Samasūpako piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**Almsfood should be eaten with the right proportion of bean curry.*";
P_HTM[7376]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sūpaññeva bahuṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, eats much bean curry, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7377]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7378]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7379]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7380]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7381]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7382]="*rasarase,**if it is any food apart from bean curry;*";
P_HTM[7383]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[7384]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[7385]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[7386]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7387]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7388]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7389]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7390]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7391]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7392]="*35. Thūpakatasikkhāpada**35. The training rule on making a heap*";
P_HTM[7393]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7394]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū thūpakato omadditvā piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six ate their almsfood picking from a heap. …*";
P_HTM[7395]="*“Na thūpakato omadditvā piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not eat almsfood picking from a heap,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7396]="*Na thūpakato omadditvā piṇḍapāto bhuñjitabbo.**Almsfood should not be eaten picking from a heap.*";
P_HTM[7397]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca thūpakato omadditvā piṇḍapātaṃ bhuñjati āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, eats almsfood picking from a heap, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7398]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7399]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7400]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7401]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7402]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7403]="*parittake sese ekato saṅkaḍḍhitvā omadditvā bhuñjati,**if only a little food remains and he eats it after collecting it in one place and then picking from it;*";
P_HTM[7404]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7405]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7406]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7407]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7408]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7409]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7410]="*36. Odanappaṭicchādanasikkhāpada**36. The training rule on covering with rice*";
P_HTM[7411]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7412]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sūpampi byañjanampi odanena paṭicchādenti bhiyyokamyataṃ upādāya …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were covering their curries with rice because they wanted more. …*";
P_HTM[7413]="*“Na sūpaṃ vā byañjanaṃ vā odanena paṭicchādessāmi bhiyyokamyataṃ upādāyāti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not cover my curries with rice because I want more,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7414]="*Na sūpaṃ vā byañjanaṃ vā odanena paṭicchādetabbaṃ bhiyyokamyataṃ upādāya.**One should not cover one’s curries with rice because one wants more.*";
P_HTM[7415]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sūpaṃ vā byañjanaṃ vā odanena paṭicchādeti bhiyyokamyataṃ upādāya, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, covers his curries with rice because he wants more, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7416]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7417]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7418]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7419]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7420]="*sāmikā paṭicchādetvā denti,**if the owners cover it and then give;*";
P_HTM[7421]="*na bhiyyokamyataṃ upādāya,**if it is not out of a desire for more;*";
P_HTM[7422]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7423]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7424]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7425]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7426]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7427]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7428]="*37. Sūpodanaviññattisikkhāpada**37. The training rule on asking for rice and bean curry*";
P_HTM[7429]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7430]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**At that time the monks from the group of six ate rice and bean curry that they had requested themselves.*";
P_HTM[7431]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7432]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics eat rice and bean curry that they have requested themselves?*";
P_HTM[7433]="*Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ.**Who doesn’t like nice food?*";
P_HTM[7434]="*Kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti.**Who doesn’t prefer tasty food?”*";
P_HTM[7435]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[7436]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[7437]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[7438]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjathā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[7439]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[7440]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[7441]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[7442]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[7443]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7444]="*“Na sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not ask for bean curry or rice for myself and then eat it,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7445]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[7446]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti.**Soon afterwards a number of monks were sick.*";
P_HTM[7447]="*Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—**The monks who were looking after them asked,*";
P_HTM[7448]="*“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up? I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[7449]="*“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjāma, tena no phāsu hoti.**“Previously we ate rice and bean curry that we had requested ourselves, and then we were comfortable.*";
P_HTM[7450]="*Idāni pana—**But now*";
P_HTM[7451]="*‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na viññāpema, tena no na phāsu hotī”ti.**that the Buddha has prohibited this, we don’t ask because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. And because of that we’re not comfortable.”*";
P_HTM[7452]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7453]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā sūpampi odanampi attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to eat rice and bean curry that he has requested for himself.*";
P_HTM[7454]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7455]="*“Na sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“When not sick, I will not ask for bean curry or rice for myself and then eat it,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7456]="*Na sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā agilānena attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjitabbaṃ.**When one is not sick, one should not ask for bean curry or rice for oneself and then eat it.*";
P_HTM[7457]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sūpaṃ vā odanaṃ vā agilāno attano atthāya viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk who is not sick, out of disrespect, eats bean curry or rice that he has requested for himself, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7458]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7459]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7460]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7461]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7462]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7463]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[7464]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[7465]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[7466]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of his own property;*";
P_HTM[7467]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7468]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7469]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7470]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7471]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7472]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7473]="*38. Ujjhānasaññīsikkhāpada**38. The training rule on finding fault*";
P_HTM[7474]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7475]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ujjhānasaññī paresaṃ pattaṃ olokenti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were looking at the bowls of others finding fault. …*";
P_HTM[7476]="*“Na ujjhānasaññī paresaṃ pattaṃ olokessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not look at another’s almsbowl finding fault,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7477]="*Na ujjhānasaññinā paresaṃ patto oloketabbo.**One should not look at the bowl of another finding fault.*";
P_HTM[7478]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca ujjhānasaññī paresaṃ pattaṃ oloketi, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, looks at the bowl of another finding fault, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7479]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7480]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7481]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7482]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7483]="*“dassāmī”ti vā “dāpessāmī”ti vā oloketi,**if he looks with the intention of giving or having someone give;*";
P_HTM[7484]="*na ujjhānasaññissa,**if he is not finding fault;*";
P_HTM[7485]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7486]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7487]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7488]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7489]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7490]="*Sakkaccavagga**The sub-chapter on respectfully*";
P_HTM[7491]="*39. Kabaḷasikkhāpada**39. The training rule on mouthfuls*";
P_HTM[7492]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7493]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū mahantaṃ kabaḷaṃ karonti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six were making large mouthfuls. …*";
P_HTM[7494]="*“Nātimahantaṃ kabaḷaṃ karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not make a mouthful that’s too large,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7495]="*Nātimahanto kabaḷo kātabbo.**One should not make mouthfuls that are too large.*";
