P_HTM[7686]="*51. Surusurukārakasikkhāpada**51. The training rule on slurping*";
P_HTM[7687]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā kosambiyaṃ viharati ghositārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Kosambī in Ghosita’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7688]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena brāhmaṇena saṅghassa payopānaṃ paṭiyattaṃ hoti.**At that time a brahmin had prepared a milk drink for the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7689]="*Bhikkhū surusurukārakaṃ khīraṃ pivanti.**The monks drank the milk making a slurping sound.*";
P_HTM[7690]="*Aññataro naṭapubbako bhikkhu evamāha—**A monk who was previously an entertainer made a joke of it, saying,*";
P_HTM[7691]="*“sabboyaṃ maññe saṅgho sītīkato”ti.**“It’s as if the whole sangha is cooled.”*";
P_HTM[7692]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized him,*";
P_HTM[7693]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhu saṅghaṃ ārabbha davaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a monk joke about the Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[7694]="*“saccaṃ kira tvaṃ, bhikkhu, saṅghaṃ ārabbha davaṃ akāsī”ti?**“Is it true, monk, that you did this?”*";
P_HTM[7695]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[7696]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked him …*";
P_HTM[7697]="*kathañhi nāma tvaṃ, moghapurisa, saṅghaṃ ārabbha davaṃ karissasi.**“Foolish man, how could you do this?*";
P_HTM[7698]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisa, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[7699]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking him …*";
P_HTM[7700]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7701]="*“na, bhikkhave, buddhaṃ vā dhammaṃ vā saṅghaṃ vā ārabbha davo kātabbo.**“Monks, you should not joke about the Buddha, the Teaching, or the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[7702]="*Yo kareyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If you do, you commit an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[7703]="*Atha kho bhagavā taṃ bhikkhuṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**After rebuking that monk in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support … the Buddha said,*";
P_HTM[7704]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7705]="*“Na surusurukārakaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not slurp while eating,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7706]="*Na surusurukārakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**One should not slurp while eating.*";
P_HTM[7707]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca surusurukārakaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, slurps while eating, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7708]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7709]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7710]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7711]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7712]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7713]="*Surusuruvagga**The sub-chapter on slurping*";
P_HTM[7714]="*52. Hatthanillehakasikkhāpada**52. The training rule on licking the hands*";
P_HTM[7715]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7716]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū hatthanillehakaṃ bhuñjanti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were licking their hands while eating. …*";
P_HTM[7717]="*“Na hatthanillehakaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not lick my hands while eating,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7718]="*Na hatthanillehakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**One should not lick one’s hands while eating.*";
P_HTM[7719]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca hatthanillehakaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, licks his hands while eating, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7720]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7721]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7722]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7723]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7724]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7725]="*Surusuruvagga**The sub-chapter on slurping*";
P_HTM[7726]="*53. Pattanillehakasikkhāpada**53. The training rule on licking the almsbowl*";
P_HTM[7727]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7728]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pattanillehakaṃ bhuñjanti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six were licking their bowls while eating. …*";
P_HTM[7729]="*“Na pattanillehakaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not lick my almsbowl while eating,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7730]="*Na pattanillehakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**One should not lick one’s bowl while eating.*";
P_HTM[7731]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca pattanillehakaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, licks his bowl while eating, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7732]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7733]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7734]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7735]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7736]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7737]="*parittake sese ekato saṅkaḍḍhitvā nillehitvā bhuñjati,**if only a little food remains and he eats it after collecting it in one place and then licking it;*";
P_HTM[7738]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7739]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7740]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7741]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7742]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7743]="*Surusuruvagga**The sub-chapter on slurping*";
P_HTM[7744]="*54. Oṭṭhanillehakasikkhāpada**54. The training rule on licking the lips*";
P_HTM[7745]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7746]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū oṭṭhanillehakaṃ bhuñjanti …pe…**At that time the monks from the group of six were licking their lips while eating. …*";
P_HTM[7747]="*“Na oṭṭhanillehakaṃ bhuñjissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not lick my lips while eating,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7748]="*Na oṭṭhanillehakaṃ bhuñjitabbaṃ.**One should not lick one’s lips while eating.*";
P_HTM[7749]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca oṭṭhanillehakaṃ bhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, licks his lips while eating, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7750]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7751]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7752]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7753]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7754]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7755]="*Surusuruvagga**The sub-chapter on slurping*";
P_HTM[7756]="*55. Sāmisasikkhāpada**55. The training rule on with food*";
P_HTM[7757]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the Bhagga country at Susumāragira in the Bhesakaḷā Grove,*";
P_HTM[7758]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kokanade pāsāde sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggaṇhanti.**the monks in the Kokanada stilt house were receiving the drinking-water vessel with hands soiled with food.*";
P_HTM[7759]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7760]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggahessanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics receive drinking-water vessels with hands soiled with food? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7761]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[7762]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[7763]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggahessantī”ti …pe…**“How can those monks do this?” …*";
P_HTM[7764]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggaṇhantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that they do this?”*";
P_HTM[7765]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[7766]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[7767]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggahessanti.**“How can those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[7768]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[7769]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7770]="*“Na sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggahessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not receive the drinking-water vessel with a hand soiled with food,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7771]="*Na sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālako paṭiggahetabbo.**One should not receive the drinking-water vessel with a hand soiled with food.*";
P_HTM[7772]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sāmisena hatthena pānīyathālakaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, receives the drinking-water vessel with a hand soiled with food, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7773]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7774]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7775]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7776]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7777]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7778]="*“dhovissāmī”ti vā “dhovāpessāmī”ti vā paṭiggaṇhāti,**if he receives it with the intention of washing it or having it washed;*";
P_HTM[7779]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7780]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7781]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7782]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7783]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7784]="*Surusuruvagga**The sub-chapter on slurping*";
P_HTM[7785]="*56. Sasitthakasikkhāpada**56. The training rule on containing rice*";
P_HTM[7786]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the Bhagga country at Susumāragira in the Bhesakaḷā Grove,*";
P_HTM[7787]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū kokanade pāsāde sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍenti.**the monks in the Kokanada stilt house were discarding their bowl-washing water containing rice in inhabited areas.*";
P_HTM[7788]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7789]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍessanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics discard their bowl-washing water containing rice in inhabited areas? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[7790]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[7791]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[7792]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍessantī”ti …pe…**“How can those monks do this?” …*";
P_HTM[7793]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that they do this?”*";
P_HTM[7794]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[7795]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[7796]="*kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍessanti.**“How can those foolish men do this?*";
P_HTM[7797]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[7798]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7799]="*“Na sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not discard bowl-washing water containing rice in inhabited areas,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7800]="*Na sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍetabbaṃ.**One should not discard bowl-washing water containing rice in an inhabited area.*";
P_HTM[7801]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca sasitthakaṃ pattadhovanaṃ antaraghare chaḍḍeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, discards bowl-washing water containing rice in an inhabited area, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7802]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7803]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7804]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[7805]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[7806]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[7807]="*uddharitvā vā bhinditvā vā paṭiggahe vā nīharitvā vā chaḍḍeti,**if he discards it after removing the rice, after breaking it up, into a container, or after taking it outside;*";
P_HTM[7808]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[7809]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[7810]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7811]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[7812]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[7813]="*Surusuruvagga**The sub-chapter on slurping*";
P_HTM[7814]="*57. Chattapāṇisikkhāpada**57. The training rule on holding a sunshade*";
P_HTM[7815]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying in the Bhagga country at Susumāragira in the Bhesakaḷā Grove, the deer park.*";
P_HTM[7816]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū chattapāṇissa dhammaṃ desenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six gave teachings to people holding sunshades.*";
P_HTM[7817]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[7818]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū chattapāṇissa dhammaṃ desessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six give teachings to people holding a sunshade?” …*";
P_HTM[7819]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, chattapāṇissa dhammaṃ desethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[7820]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[7821]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[7822]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, chattapāṇissa dhammaṃ desessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[7823]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[7824]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7825]="*“Na chattapāṇissa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not give a teaching to anyone holding a sunshade,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7826]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[7827]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū chattapāṇissa gilānassa dhammaṃ desetuṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Soon afterwards, being afraid of wrongdoing, the monks did not give teachings to sick people holding a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[7828]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[7829]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā chattapāṇissa gilānassa dhammaṃ na desessantī”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics not give teachings to someone who’s sick holding a sunshade?”*";
P_HTM[7830]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[7831]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[7832]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[7833]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, chattapāṇissa gilānassa dhammaṃ desetuṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to give a teaching to someone who’s sick holding a sunshade.*";
P_HTM[7834]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[7835]="*“Na chattapāṇissa agilānassa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not give a teaching to anyone holding a sunshade who is not sick,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[7836]="*Chattaṃ nāma**A sunshade:*";
P_HTM[7837]="*tīṇi chattāni— setacchattaṃ, kilañjacchattaṃ, paṇṇacchattaṃ maṇḍalabaddhaṃ salākabaddhaṃ.**there are three kinds of sunshades: the white sunshade, the reed sunshade, the leaf sunshade. They are bound at the rim and bound at the ribs.*";
P_HTM[7838]="*Dhammo nāma**Teaching:*";
P_HTM[7839]="*buddhabhāsito sāvakabhāsito isibhāsito devatābhāsito atthūpasañhito dhammūpasañhito.**what has been spoken by the Buddha, what has been spoken by disciples, what has been spoken by sages, what has been spoken by gods, what is connected with what is beneficial, what is connected with the Teaching.*";
P_HTM[7840]="*Deseyyāti**Give:*";
P_HTM[7841]="*padena deseti, pade pade āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if he teaches by the line, then for every line he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7842]="*Akkharāya deseti, akkharakkharāya āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he teaches by the syllable, then for every syllable he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7843]="*Na chattapāṇissa agilānassa dhammo desetabbo.**One should not give a teaching to anyone holding a sunshade who is not sick.*";
P_HTM[7844]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca chattapāṇissa agilānassa dhammaṃ deseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, gives a teaching to someone holding a sunshade who is not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7845]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7846]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
