P_HTM[7851]="*58. Daṇḍapāṇisikkhāpada**58. The training rule on holding a staff*";
P_HTM[7852]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[7853]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū daṇḍapāṇissa dhammaṃ desenti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six gave teachings to people holding staffs. …*";
P_HTM[7854]="*“Na daṇḍapāṇissa agilānassa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not give a teaching to anyone holding a staff who is not sick,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[7855]="*Daṇḍo nāma**A staff:*";
P_HTM[7856]="*majjhimassa purisassa catuhattho daṇḍo.**a stick measuring 1.6 meters.*";
P_HTM[7857]="*Tato ukkaṭṭho adaṇḍo, omako adaṇḍo.**What is longer than that is not a staff, nor what is shorter.*";
P_HTM[7858]="*Na daṇḍapāṇissa agilānassa dhammo desetabbo.**One should not give a teaching to anyone holding a staff who is not sick.*";
P_HTM[7859]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca daṇḍapāṇissa agilānassa dhammaṃ deseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk out, of disrespect, gives a teaching to someone holding a staff who is not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[7860]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[7861]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[7862]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[7863]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
