P_HTM[8009]="*69. Nīcāsanasikkhāpada**69. The training rule on low seats*";
P_HTM[8010]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8011]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa dhammaṃ desenti.**At that time the monks from the group of six were sitting on low seats while giving teachings to people sitting on high seats.*";
P_HTM[8012]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8013]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa dhammaṃ desessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six sit on low seats while giving teachings to people sitting on high seats?” …*";
P_HTM[8014]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa dhammaṃ desethā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[8015]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8016]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[8017]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa dhammaṃ desessatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[8018]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8019]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after rebuking them …*";
P_HTM[8020]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8021]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, bārāṇasiyaṃ aññatarassa chapakassa pajāpati gabbhinī ahosi.**“Once upon a time in Bārāṇasī, monks, there was a low-caste man whose wife became pregnant.*";
P_HTM[8022]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, sā chapakī taṃ chapakaṃ etadavoca—**She said to him,*";
P_HTM[8023]="*‘gabbhinīmhi, ayyaputta.**‘I’m pregnant.*";
P_HTM[8024]="*Icchāmi ambaṃ khāditun’ti.**I crave mangoes.’*";
P_HTM[8025]="*‘Natthi ambaṃ, akālo ambassā’ti.**‘But there are no mangoes. It’s the wrong season.’*";
P_HTM[8026]="*‘Sace na labhissāmi marissāmī’ti.**‘If I don’t get any, I’ll die.’*";
P_HTM[8027]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño ambo dhuvaphalo hoti.**At that time the king had a mango tree that was always bearing fruit.*";
P_HTM[8028]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, so chapako yena so ambo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ ambaṃ abhiruhitvā nilīno acchi.**Then that low-caste man went to that mango tree, climbed it, and hid himself.*";
P_HTM[8029]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, rājā purohitena brāhmaṇena saddhiṃ yena so ambo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ucce āsane nisīditvā mantaṃ pariyāpuṇāti.**Just then the king and his brahmin counselor went to that same mango tree. There the king sat on a high seat while learning the Vedas.*";
P_HTM[8030]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, tassa chapakassa etadahosi—**The low-caste man thought,*";
P_HTM[8031]="*‘yāva adhammiko ayaṃ rājā, yatra hi nāma ucce āsane nisīditvā mantaṃ pariyāpuṇissati.**‘How wrong-headed this king is, in that he sits on a high seat while learning the Vedas.*";
P_HTM[8032]="*Ayañca brāhmaṇo adhammiko, yatra hi nāma nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa mantaṃ vācessati.**And the brahmin is wrong-headed too, in that he sits on a low seat while teaching the Vedas to one sitting on a high seat.*";
P_HTM[8033]="*Ahañcamhi adhammiko, yohaṃ itthiyā kāraṇā rañño ambaṃ avaharāmi.**And I’m wrong-headed too, in that I steal mangoes from the king because of a woman.*";
P_HTM[8034]="*Sabbamidaṃ carimaṃ katan’ti**This is all so low!’*";
P_HTM[8035]="*tattheva paripati.**And he fell out of the tree right there.*";
P_HTM[8036]="*‘Ubho atthaṃ na jānanti,**‘Neither understands what is good,*";
P_HTM[8037]="*ubho dhammaṃ na passare;**Neither sees the Truth:*";
P_HTM[8038]="*Yo cāyaṃ mantaṃ vāceti,**Not he who teaches the Vedas,*";
P_HTM[8039]="*yo cādhammenadhīyati’.**Nor he who learns improperly.’*";
P_HTM[8040]="*‘Sālīnaṃ odano bhutto,**‘I’ve eaten the finest rice,*";
P_HTM[8041]="*sucimaṃsūpasecano;**With a curry of pure meat:*";
P_HTM[8042]="*Tasmā dhamme na vattāmi,**Therefore I’m not practicing the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[8043]="*dhammo ariyebhi vaṇṇito’.**The Teaching praised by the Noble Ones.’*";
P_HTM[8044]="*‘Dhiratthu taṃ dhanalābhaṃ,**‘A curse it is the obtaining of wealth,*";
P_HTM[8045]="*yasalābhañca brāhmaṇa;**And the obtaining of fame, too, brahmin;*";
P_HTM[8046]="*Yā vutti vinipātena,**These things come with a low rebirth,*";
P_HTM[8047]="*adhammacaraṇena vā.**Or with wrong-headed behavior.*";
P_HTM[8048]="*Paribbaja mahābrahme,**‘Go forth, great brahmin,*";
P_HTM[8049]="*pacantaññepi pāṇino;**Other beings will do the cooking;*";
P_HTM[8050]="*Mā tvaṃ adhammo ācarito,**Don’t go against the Teaching,*";
P_HTM[8051]="*asmā kumbhamivābhidā’ti.**Because you’ll break like a jar.’*";
P_HTM[8052]="*Tadāpi me, bhikkhave, amanāpā nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa mantaṃ vācetuṃ, kimaṅgaṃ pana etarahi na amanāpā bhavissati nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa dhammaṃ desetuṃ.**Even at that time, monks, I was displeased by someone teaching the Vedas while sitting on a low seat to someone sitting on a high seat. How, then, could it not be displeasing now?*";
P_HTM[8053]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8054]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[8055]="*“Na nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa agilānassa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not give a teaching while sitting on a low seat to anyone sitting on a high seat who is not sick,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[8056]="*Na nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa agilānassa dhammo desetabbo.**One should not give a teaching while sitting on a low seat to anyone sitting on a high seat who is not sick.*";
P_HTM[8057]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca nīce āsane nisīditvā ucce āsane nisinnassa agilānassa dhammaṃ deseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, gives a teaching while sitting on a low seat to someone sitting on a high seat who is not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8058]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8059]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8060]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8061]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8062]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[8063]="*Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[8064]="*70. Ṭhitasikkhāpada**70. The training rule on standing*";
P_HTM[8065]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8066]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ṭhitā nisinnassa dhammaṃ desenti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were standing while giving teachings to people who were sitting. …*";
P_HTM[8067]="*“Na ṭhito nisinnassa agilānassa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not give a teaching while standing to anyone sitting who is not sick,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[8068]="*Na ṭhitena nisinnassa agilānassa dhammo desetabbo.**One should not give a teaching while standing to anyone sitting who is not sick.*";
P_HTM[8069]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca ṭhito nisinnassa agilānassa dhammaṃ deseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, gives a teaching while standing to someone sitting who is not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8070]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8071]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8072]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8073]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8074]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[8075]="*Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[8076]="*71. Pacchatogamanasikkhāpada**71. The training rule on walking behind*";
P_HTM[8077]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8078]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pacchato gacchantā purato gacchantassa dhammaṃ desenti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were walking behind while giving teachings to people walking in front. …*";
P_HTM[8079]="*“Na pacchato gacchanto purato gacchantassa agilānassa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not give a teaching while walking behind to anyone walking in front who is not sick,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[8080]="*Na pacchato gacchantena purato gacchantassa agilānassa dhammo desetabbo.**One should not give a teaching while walking behind to anyone walking in front who is not sick.*";
P_HTM[8081]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca pacchato gacchanto purato gacchantassa agilānassa dhammaṃ deseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, gives a teaching while walking behind to someone walking in front who is not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8082]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8083]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8084]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8085]="*Ekādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eleventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8086]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[8087]="*Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[8088]="*72. Uppathenagamanasikkhāpada**72. The training rule on walking off the path*";
P_HTM[8089]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8090]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū uppathena gacchantā pathena gacchantassa dhammaṃ desenti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were walking next to the path while giving teachings to people walking on the path. …*";
P_HTM[8091]="*“Na uppathena gacchanto pathena gacchantassa agilānassa dhammaṃ desessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘I will not give a teaching while walking next to the path to anyone walking on the path who is not sick,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[8092]="*Na uppathena gacchantena pathena gacchantassa agilānassa dhammo desetabbo.**One should not give a teaching while walking next to the path to anyone walking on the path who is not sick.*";
P_HTM[8093]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca uppathena gacchanto pathena gacchantassa agilānassa dhammaṃ deseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a monk, out of disrespect, gives a teaching while walking next to the path to someone walking on the path who is not sick, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8094]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8095]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8096]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8097]="*Dvādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The twelfth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8098]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[8099]="*Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[8100]="*73. Ṭhitouccārasikkhāpada**73. The training rule on defecating while standing*";
P_HTM[8101]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8102]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū ṭhitā uccārampi passāvampi karonti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were defecating and urinating while standing. …*";
P_HTM[8103]="*“Na ṭhito agilāno uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘When not sick, I will not defecate or urinate while standing,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[8104]="*Na ṭhitena agilānena uccāro vā passāvo vā kātabbo.**If one is not sick, one should not defecate or urinate while standing.*";
P_HTM[8105]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca ṭhito agilāno uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, out of disrespect, a monk who is not sick defecates or urinates while standing, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8106]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8107]="*asañcicca …pe…**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8108]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8109]="*Terasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The thirteenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8110]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[8111]="*Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[8112]="*74. Hariteuccārasikkhāpada**74. The training rule on defecating on cultivated plants*";
P_HTM[8113]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8114]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū harite uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karonti …pe….**At that time the monks from the group of six were defecating, urinating, and spitting on cultivated plants. …*";
P_HTM[8115]="*“Na harite agilāno uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**“‘When not sick, I will not defecate, urinate, or spit on cultivated plants,’ this is how you should train.”*";
P_HTM[8116]="*Na harite agilānena uccāro vā passāvo vā kheḷo vā kātabbo.**If one is not sick, one should not defecate, urinate, or spit on cultivated plants.*";
P_HTM[8117]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca harite agilāno uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, out of disrespect, a monk who is not sick defecates, urinates, or spits on cultivated plants, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8118]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8119]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8120]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[8121]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[8122]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[8123]="*appaharite kato haritaṃ ottharati,**if he does it in a place with no cultivated plants, but it then spreads to cultivated plants;*";
P_HTM[8124]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[8125]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[8126]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8127]="*Cuddasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourteenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8128]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[8129]="*Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[8130]="*75. Udakeuccārasikkhāpada**75. The training rule on defecating in water*";
P_HTM[8131]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8132]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karonti.**At that time the monks from the group of six were defecating, urinating, and spitting in water.*";
P_HTM[8133]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8134]="*“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karissanti, seyyathāpi gihī kāmabhogino”ti.**“How can the Sakyan monastics defecate, urinate, and spit in water? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[8135]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The monks heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[8136]="*Ye te bhikkhū appicchā …pe… te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the monks of few desires complained and criticized those monks,*";
P_HTM[8137]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the monks from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[8138]="*“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karothā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that you do this?”*";
P_HTM[8139]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8140]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha rebuked them …*";
P_HTM[8141]="*kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karissatha.**“Foolish men, how can you do this?*";
P_HTM[8142]="*Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8143]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**“And, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[8144]="*“Na udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not defecate, urinate, or spit in water,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[8145]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the monks.*";
P_HTM[8146]="*Tena kho pana samayena gilānā bhikkhū udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi kātuṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Soon afterwards, being afraid of wrongdoing, sick monks did not defecate, urinate, or spit in water.*";
P_HTM[8147]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8148]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8149]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi kātuṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick monk to defecate, urinate, or spit in water.*";
P_HTM[8150]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—**And so, monks, this training rule should be recited like this:*";
P_HTM[8151]="*“Na udake agilāno uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“When not sick, I will not defecate, urinate, or spit in water,” this is how you should train.’”*";
P_HTM[8152]="*Na udake agilānena uccāro vā passāvo vā kheḷo vā kātabbo.**If one is not sick, one should not defecate, urinate, or spit in water.*";
P_HTM[8153]="*Yo anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake agilāno uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, out of disrespect, a monk who is not sick defecates, urinates, or spits in water, he commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8154]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8155]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8156]="*assatiyā,**if he is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[8157]="*ajānantassa,**if he does not know;*";
P_HTM[8158]="*gilānassa,**if he is sick;*";
P_HTM[8159]="*thale kato udakaṃ ottharati,**if he does it on dry ground, but it then spreads to water;*";
P_HTM[8160]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[8161]="*ummattakassa,**if he is insane;*";
P_HTM[8162]="*khittacittassa,**if he is deranged;*";
P_HTM[8163]="*vedanāṭṭassa,**if he is overwhelmed by pain;*";
P_HTM[8164]="*ādikammikassāti.**if he is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8165]="*Pannarasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifteenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[8166]="*Pādukavaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on shoes is finished.*";
P_HTM[8167]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, āyasmanto, sekhiyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the rules to be trained in have been recited.*";
P_HTM[8168]="*Tatthāyasmante pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[8169]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[8170]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[8171]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[8172]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[8173]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[8174]="*Parisuddhetthāyasmanto, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[8175]="*Sekhiyā niṭṭhitā.**The rules to be trained in are finished.*";
P_HTM[8176]="*Sekhiyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on training is finished.*";
P_HTM[8177]="*127. Pārājikakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion *";
P_HTM[8178]="*5. Ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalikāsikkhāpada**5. The training rule on above the knees*";
P_HTM[8179]="*Namo tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sammāsambuddhassa.**Homage to the Buddha, the Perfected One, the fully Awakened One*";
P_HTM[8180]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[8181]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāḷho migāranattā bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihāraṃ kattukāmo hoti.**Migāra’s grandson Sāḷha wanted to build a dwelling for the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[8182]="*Atha kho sāḷho migāranattā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca—**He went to the nuns and said,*";
P_HTM[8183]="*“icchāmahaṃ, ayye, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihāraṃ kātuṃ.**“Venerables, I wish to build a dwelling for the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[8184]="*Detha me navakammikaṃ bhikkhunin”ti.**Please give me the nun in charge of building work.”*";
P_HTM[8185]="*Tena kho pana samayena catasso bhaginiyo bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā honti—**At that time four sisters had gone forth as nuns:*";
P_HTM[8186]="*nandā, nandavatī, sundarīnandā, thullanandāti.**Nandā, Nandavatī, Sundarīnandā, and Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[8187]="*Tāsu sundarīnandā bhikkhunī taruṇapabbajitā abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā paṇḍitā byattā medhāvinī dakkhā analasā, tatrupāyāya vīmaṃsāya samannāgatā, alaṃ kātuṃ alaṃ saṃvidhātuṃ.**Of these, the nun Sundarīnandā had gone forth when she was young, and she was beautiful, intelligent, skilled, and diligent, and she possessed good judgment in regard to doing and arranging things well.*";
P_HTM[8188]="*Atha kho bhikkhunisaṅgho sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ sammannitvā sāḷhassa migāranattuno navakammikaṃ adāsi.**After appointing Sundarīnandā to be in charge of building work, the Sangha made her work with Sāḷha.*";
P_HTM[8189]="*Tena kho pana samayena sundarīnandā bhikkhunī sāḷhassa migāranattuno nivesanaṃ abhikkhaṇaṃ gacchati—**As a consequence of this, Sundarīnandā would often go to Sāḷha’s house to ask for tools,*";
P_HTM[8190]="*“vāsiṃ detha, parasuṃ detha, kuṭhāriṃ detha, kudālaṃ detha, nikhādanaṃ dethā”ti.**whether an adz, a hatchet, an ax, a spade, or a chisel.*";
P_HTM[8191]="*Sāḷhopi migāranattā bhikkhunupassayaṃ abhikkhaṇaṃ gacchati katākataṃ jānituṃ.**And Sāḷha would often go to the nuns’ dwelling place to find out about the progress of the building work.*";
P_HTM[8192]="*Te abhiṇhadassanena paṭibaddhacittā ahesuṃ.**And because they saw each other frequently, they fell in love.*";
P_HTM[8193]="*Atha kho sāḷho migāranattā sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dūsetuṃ okāsaṃ alabhamāno etadevaatthāya bhikkhunisaṅghassa bhattaṃ akāsi.**But because Sāḷha could not find any opportunity to be intimate with Sundarīnandā, he invited the Sangha of nuns for a meal.*";
P_HTM[8194]="*Atha kho sāḷho migāranattā bhattagge āsanaṃ paññapento “ettakā bhikkhuniyo ayyāya sundarīnandāya vuḍḍhatarā”ti—ekamantaṃ āsanaṃ paññapesi “ettakā navakatarā”ti—ekamantaṃ āsanaṃ paññapesi.**When preparing the seats in the dining hall, he counted the number of nuns senior to Venerable Sundarīnandā and placed their seats to one side, and he counted the number of nuns junior to her and placed their seat on the other side.*";
P_HTM[8195]="*Paṭicchanne okāse nikūṭe sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā āsanaṃ paññapesi, yathā therā bhikkhuniyo jāneyyuṃ—“navakānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ santike nisinnā”ti; navakāpi bhikkhuniyo jāneyyuṃ—“therānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ santike nisinnā”ti.**He then placed Sundarīnandā’s seat in a concealed spot in a corner. In this way the senior nuns would think she was seated close to the junior ones and the junior nuns would think she was seated close to the senior ones.*";
P_HTM[8196]="*Atha kho sāḷho migāranattā bhikkhunisaṅghassa kālaṃ ārocāpesi—“kālo, ayye, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti.**Soon afterwards he informed the Sangha that the meal was ready.*";
P_HTM[8197]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī sallakkhetvā—“na bahukato sāḷho migāranattā bhikkhunisaṅghassa bhattaṃ akāsi; maṃ so dūsetukāmo.**Sundarīnandā thought, “Sāḷha hasn’t prepared a meal for the Sangha as a service, but because he wants to be intimate with me.*";
P_HTM[8198]="*Sacāhaṃ gamissāmi vissaro me bhavissatī”ti, antevāsiniṃ bhikkhuniṃ āṇāpesi—“gaccha me piṇḍapātaṃ nīhara.**If I go, I will get into trouble.” She then told a nun who was her pupil, “Go and bring back almsfood for me.*";
P_HTM[8199]="*Yo ce maṃ pucchati, ‘gilānā’ti paṭivedehī”ti.**If anyone asks about me, tell them I’m sick.”*";
P_HTM[8200]="*“Evaṃ, ayye”ti kho sā bhikkhunī sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā paccassosi.**“Yes, Venerable,” she replied.*";
P_HTM[8201]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāḷho migāranattā bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhito hoti sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ paṭipucchanto—**Soon afterwards Sāḷha was standing outside the gateway of his house repeatedly inquiring after Sundarīnandā:*";
P_HTM[8202]="*“kahaṃ, ayye, ayyā sundarīnandā? Kahaṃ, ayye, ayyā sundarīnandā”ti?**“Venerables, where’s Venerable Sundarīnandā?”*";
P_HTM[8203]="*Evaṃ vutte, sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā antevāsinī bhikkhunī sāḷhaṃ migāranattāraṃ etadavoca—“gilānāvuso; piṇḍapātaṃ nīharissāmī”ti.**The nun who was Sundarīnandā’s pupil told him: “She’s sick. I’m bringing her almsfood.”*";
P_HTM[8204]="*Atha kho sāḷho migāranattā—“yampāhaṃ atthāya bhikkhunisaṅghassa bhattaṃ akāsiṃ ayyāya sundarīnandāya kāraṇā”ti manusse āṇāpetvā—**Sāḷha thought, “I invited the Sangha of nuns because of Sundarīnandā,”*";
P_HTM[8205]="*“bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ bhattena parivisathā”ti vatvā yena bhikkhunupassayo tenupasaṅkami.**and after telling the people there to serve the meal to the Sangha of nuns, he left for the nuns’ dwelling place.*";
P_HTM[8206]="*Tena kho pana samayena sundarīnandā bhikkhunī bahārāmakoṭṭhake ṭhitā hoti sāḷhaṃ migāranattāraṃ patimānentī.**Just then Sundarīnandā was standing outside the monastery gateway longing for Sāḷha.*";
P_HTM[8207]="*Addasā kho sundarīnandā bhikkhunī sāḷhaṃ migāranattāraṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. Disvāna upassayaṃ pavisitvā sasīsaṃ pārupitvā mañcake nipajji.**When she saw him coming, she entered the dwelling, put on her upper robe so that it covered her head, and lay down on her bed.*";
P_HTM[8208]="*Atha kho sāḷho migāranattā yena sundarīnandā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—“kiṃ te, ayye, aphāsu, kissa nipannāsī”ti?**Sāḷha approached her and said, “Venerable, what’s wrong with you? Why are you lying down?”*";
P_HTM[8209]="*“Evañhetaṃ, āvuso, hoti yā anicchantaṃ icchatī”ti.**“That’s what happens when you desire someone who doesn’t desire you in return.”*";
P_HTM[8210]="*“Kyāhaṃ taṃ, ayye, na icchissāmi?**“What do you mean I don’t desire you?*";
P_HTM[8211]="*Api cāhaṃ okāsaṃ na labhāmi taṃ dūsetun”ti.**I just couldn’t find an opportunity to be intimate with you.”*";
P_HTM[8212]="*Avassuto avassutāya sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajji.**And both having lust, he made physical contact with Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[8213]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī jarādubbalā caraṇagilānā sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā avidūre nipannā hoti.**Just then a nun who was weak from old age and had problems with her feet was lying down not far from Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[8214]="*Addasā kho sā bhikkhunī sāḷhaṃ migāranattāraṃ avassutaṃ avassutāya sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjantaṃ.**She saw how Sāḷha made physical contact with Sundarīnandā while both of them had lust.*";
P_HTM[8215]="*Disvāna ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—“kathañhi nāma ayyā sundarīnandā avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyissatī”ti.**She complained and criticized her, “How could Venerable Sundarīnandā consent to a man making physical contact with her, when they both had lust?”*";
P_HTM[8216]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That nun then told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8217]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā santuṭṭhā lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires, who had a sense of conscience, and who were contented, afraid of wrongdoing, and fond of the training, complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8218]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā sundarīnandā avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyissatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Sundarīnandā consent to a man making physical contact with her, when they both had lust?”*";
P_HTM[8219]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ. Ye te bhikkhū appicchā santuṭṭhā lajjino kukkuccakā sikkhākāmā te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—“kathañhi nāma sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyissatī”ti.**Those nuns then told the monks. And the monks of few desires, who had a sense of conscience, and who were contented, afraid of wrongdoing, and fond of the training, criticized her in the same way.*";
P_HTM[8220]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**After criticizing the nun Sundarīnandā in many ways, they told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8221]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8222]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Sundarīnandā acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[8223]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8224]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā—**The Buddha criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8225]="*“ananucchavikaṃ, bhikkhave, sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā ananulomikaṃ appatirūpaṃ assāmaṇakaṃ akappiyaṃ akaraṇīyaṃ.**“It’s not suitable, monks, it’s not proper for the nun Sundarīnandā, it’s not worthy of a monastic, it’s not allowable, it’s not to be done.*";
P_HTM[8226]="*Kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa kāyasaṃsaggaṃ sādiyissati.**How could Sundarīnandā consent to a man making physical contact with her, when they both had lust?*";
P_HTM[8227]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya pasannānaṃ vā bhiyyobhāvāya.**This will affect people’s confidence,*";
P_HTM[8228]="*Atha khvetaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānañceva appasādāya pasannānañca ekaccānaṃ aññathattāyā”ti.**and cause some to lose it.”*";
P_HTM[8229]="*Atha kho bhagavā sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya dupposatāya mahicchatāya asantuṭṭhitāya saṅgaṇikāya kosajjassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā, anekapariyāyena subharatāya suposatāya appicchassa santuṭṭhassa sallekhassa dhutassa pāsādikassa apacayassa vīriyārambhassa vaṇṇaṃ bhāsitvā, bhikkhūnaṃ tadanucchavikaṃ tadanulomikaṃ dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**And the Buddha spoke in many ways in dispraise of being difficult to support and maintain, in dispraise of great desires, discontent, socializing, and laziness; but he spoke in many ways in praise of being easy to support and maintain, of fewness of wishes, contentment, self-elimination, ascetic practices, serenity, reduction in things, and being energetic. After giving a teaching on what is right and proper, he addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[8230]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[8231]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya, saṅghaphāsutāya, dummaṅkūnaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ niggahāya, pesalānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ phāsuvihārāya, diṭṭhadhammikānaṃ āsavānaṃ saṃvarāya, samparāyikānaṃ āsavānaṃ paṭighātāya, appasannānaṃ pasādāya, pasannānaṃ bhiyyobhāvāya, saddhammaṭṭhitiyā vinayānuggahāya.**for the well-being of the Sangha, for the comfort of the Sangha, for the restraint of bad nuns, for the ease of good nuns, for the restraint of corruptions relating to the present life, for the restraint of corruptions relating to future lives, to give rise to confidence in those without it, to increase the confidence of those who have it, for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[8232]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8233]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ āmasanaṃ vā parāmasanaṃ vā gahaṇaṃ vā chupanaṃ vā paṭipīḷanaṃ vā sādiyeyya, ayampi pārājikā hoti asaṃvāsā ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalikā”ti.**‘If a lustful nun consents to a lustful man making physical contact with her, to touching her, to taking hold of her, to contacting her, or to squeezing her, anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, she too is expelled and excluded from the community. The training rule on above the knees.’”*";
P_HTM[8234]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8235]="*yā yādisā yathāyuttā yathājaccā yathānāmā yathāgottā yathāsīlā yathāvihārinī yathāgocarā therā vā navā vā majjhimā vā, esā vuccati yā panāti.**whoever, of such a kind, of such activity, of such caste, of such name, of such family, of such conduct, of such behavior, of such association, who is senior, who is junior, or who is of middle standing—this is called “a”.*";
P_HTM[8236]="*Bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8237]="*bhikkhikāti bhikkhunī;**she is a nun because she lives on alms;*";
P_HTM[8238]="*bhikkhācariyaṃ ajjhupagatāti bhikkhunī;**a nun because she has gone over to living on alms;*";
P_HTM[8239]="*bhinnapaṭadharāti bhikkhunī;**a nun because she wears a patchwork cloth;*";
P_HTM[8240]="*samaññāya bhikkhunī;**a nun by convention;*";
P_HTM[8241]="*paṭiññāya bhikkhunī;**a nun on account of her claim;*";
P_HTM[8242]="*ehi bhikkhunīti bhikkhunī;**a “come, nun” nun;*";
P_HTM[8243]="*tīhi saraṇagamanehi upasampannāti bhikkhunī;**a nun given the full ordination by taking the three refuges;*";
P_HTM[8244]="*bhadrā bhikkhunī;**a good nun;*";
P_HTM[8245]="*sārā bhikkhunī;**a nun of substance;*";
P_HTM[8246]="*sekhā bhikkhunī;**a trainee nun;*";
P_HTM[8247]="*asekhā bhikkhunī;**a fully trained nun;*";
P_HTM[8248]="*samaggena ubhatosaṅghena ñatticatutthena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena upasampannāti bhikkhunī.**a nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand.*";
P_HTM[8249]="*Tatra yāyaṃ bhikkhunī samaggena ubhatosaṅghena ñatticatutthena kammena akuppena ṭhānārahena upasampannā, ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8250]="*Avassutā nāma**Lustful:*";
P_HTM[8251]="*sārattā apekkhavatī paṭibaddhacittā.**having lust, longing for, in love with.*";
P_HTM[8252]="*Avassuto nāma**Lustful:*";
P_HTM[8253]="*sāratto apekkhavā paṭibaddhacitto.**having lust, longing for, in love with.*";
P_HTM[8254]="*Purisapuggalo nāma**Man:*";
P_HTM[8255]="*manussapuriso na yakkho na peto na tiracchānagato viññū paṭibalo kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjituṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of making physical contact.*";
P_HTM[8256]="*Adhakkhakanti**Below the collar bone:*";
P_HTM[8257]="*heṭṭhakkhakaṃ.**down from the collar bone.*";
P_HTM[8258]="*Ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalanti**Above the knees:*";
P_HTM[8259]="*uparijāṇumaṇḍalaṃ.**up from the knees.*";
P_HTM[8260]="*Āmasanaṃ nāma**Making physical contact:*";
P_HTM[8261]="*āmaṭṭhamattaṃ.**making mere physical contact.*";
P_HTM[8262]="*Parāmasanaṃ nāma**Touching:*";
P_HTM[8263]="*itocito ca sañcopanaṃ.**touching here and there.*";
P_HTM[8264]="*Gahaṇaṃ nāma**Taking hold of:*";
P_HTM[8265]="*gahitamattaṃ.**the mere taking hold of.*";
P_HTM[8266]="*Chupanaṃ nāma**Contacting:*";
P_HTM[8267]="*phuṭṭhamattaṃ.**mere contacting.*";
P_HTM[8268]="*Paṭipīḷanaṃ vā sādiyeyyāti**Consents to squeezing:*";
P_HTM[8269]="*aṅgaṃ gahetvā nippīḷanaṃ sādiyati.**consents to the taking hold of a bodily part and then pressing.*";
P_HTM[8270]="*Ayampīti**She too:*";
P_HTM[8271]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8272]="*Pārājikā hotīti**Is expelled:*";
P_HTM[8273]="*seyyathāpi nāma puriso sīsacchinno abhabbo tena sarīrabandhanena jīvituṃ; evameva bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ āmasanaṃ vā parāmasanaṃ vā gahaṇaṃ vā chupanaṃ vā paṭipīḷanaṃ vā sādiyantī assamaṇī hoti asakyadhītā. Tena vuccati pārājikā hotīti.**just as a man with his head cut off is unable to continue living by reconnecting it to the body, so is a lustful nun who consents to a lustful man making physical contact with her, to touching her, to taking hold of her, to contacting her, or to squeezing her, anywhere below the collar bone but above the knees, not a monastic, not a daughter of the Sakyan. Therefore it is said “she is expelled”.*";
P_HTM[8274]="*Asaṃvāsāti**Excluded from the community:*";
P_HTM[8275]="*saṃvāso nāma ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā— eso saṃvāso nāma.**Community: joint legal procedures, a joint recitation, the same training—this is called “community”.*";
P_HTM[8276]="*So tāya saddhiṃ natthi, tena vuccati asaṃvāsāti.**She does not take part in this—therefore it is called “excluded from the community”.*";
P_HTM[8277]="*Ubhatoavassute adhakkhakaṃ ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ kāyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti pārājikassa.**If both have lust and either of them makes physical contact, below the collar bone but above the knees, body to body, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8278]="*Kāyena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If either of them, with their own body, makes physical contact with something connected to the other’s body, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8279]="*Kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If either of them, with something connected to their own body, makes physical contact with the other’s body, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8280]="*Kāyapaṭibaddhena kāyapaṭibaddhaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If either of them, with something connected to their own body, makes physical contact with something connected to the other’s body, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8281]="*Nissaggiyena kāyaṃ āmasati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If either of them, with something released by them, makes physical contact with the other’s body, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
