P_HTM[8333]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8334]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8335]="*assatiyā,**if she is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[8336]="*ajānantiyā,**if she does not know;*";
P_HTM[8337]="*asādiyantiyā,**if she does not consent;*";
P_HTM[8338]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8339]="*khittacittāya,**if she is deranged;*";
P_HTM[8340]="*vedanāṭṭāya,**if she is overwhelmed by pain;*";
P_HTM[8341]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8342]="*Paṭhamapārājikaṃ samattaṃ.**The fifth offense entailing expulsion is finished.*";
P_HTM[8343]="*127. Pārājikakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion *";
P_HTM[8344]="*6. Vajjappaṭicchādikāsikkhāpada**6. The training rule on those who conceal offenses*";
P_HTM[8345]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8346]="*Tena kho pana samayena sundarīnandā bhikkhunī sāḷhena migāranattunā gabbhinī hoti.**At that time the nun Sundarīnandā was pregnant by Migāra’s grandson Sāḷha.*";
P_HTM[8347]="*Yāva gabbho taruṇo ahosi tāva chādesi.**When the fetus got large, she concealed her condition.*";
P_HTM[8348]="*Paripakke gabbhe vibbhamitvā vijāyi.**And when the fetus was fully grown, she disrobed and gave birth.*";
P_HTM[8349]="*Bhikkhuniyo thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—**The nuns said to the nun Thullanandā,*";
P_HTM[8350]="*“sundarīnandā kho, ayye, aciravibbhantā vijātā.**“Venerable, Sundarīnandā gave birth shortly after disrobing.”*";
P_HTM[8351]="*Kacci no sā bhikkhunīyeva samānā gabbhinī”ti?**“Could it be that she was pregnant while she was still a nun?”*";
P_HTM[8352]="*“Evaṃ, ayye”ti.**“Yes, Venerables.”*";
P_HTM[8353]="*“Kissa pana tvaṃ, ayye, jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodesi na gaṇassa ārocesī”ti?**“But, Venerable, when you knew that a nun had committed an offense entailing expulsion, why didn’t you either confront her yourself or tell a group of nuns?”*";
P_HTM[8354]="*“Yo etissā avaṇṇo mayheso avaṇṇo, yā etissā akitti mayhesā akitti, yo etissā ayaso mayheso ayaso, yo etissā alābho mayheso alābho.**“Her disrepute is my disrepute, her infamy is my infamy, her notoriety is my notoriety, her loss is my loss.*";
P_HTM[8355]="*Kyāhaṃ, ayye, attano avaṇṇaṃ attano akittiṃ attano ayasaṃ attano alābhaṃ paresaṃ ārocessāmī”ti?**Why would I tell others of my own disrepute, infamy, notoriety, and loss?”*";
P_HTM[8356]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8357]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodessati na gaṇassa ārocessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā, knowing that a nun had committed an offense entailing expulsion, neither confront her herself nor tell a group of nuns?”*";
P_HTM[8358]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Then those nuns told the monks what had happened,*";
P_HTM[8359]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**and the monks in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[8360]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe bhikkhusaṅghaṃ sannipātāpetvā bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8361]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodeti na gaṇassa ārocetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[8362]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8363]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8364]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodessati na gaṇassa ārocessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā, knowing that a nun had committed an offense entailing expulsion, neither confront her herself nor tell a group of nuns?*";
P_HTM[8365]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8366]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8367]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodeyya na gaṇassa āroceyya, yadā ca sā ṭhitā vā assa cutā vā nāsitā vā avassaṭā vā, sā pacchā evaṃ vadeyya—‘pubbevāhaṃ, ayye, aññāsiṃ etaṃ bhikkhuniṃ evarūpā ca evarūpā ca sā bhaginīti, no ca kho attanā paṭicodessaṃ na gaṇassa ārocessan’ti, ayampi pārājikā hoti asaṃvāsā vajjappaṭicchādikā”ti.**‘If a nun knows that a nun has committed an offense entailing expulsion, but she neither confronts her herself nor tells a group of nuns, and afterward—whether that nun remains or has died or has been expelled or has converted—she says, “Venerables, although I previously knew that this nun was like this, I thought, ‘I will neither confront her myself nor tell a group of nuns,’” she too is expelled and excluded from the community. The training rule on those who conceal offenses.’”*";
P_HTM[8368]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8369]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8370]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8371]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8372]="*Jānāti nāma**Knows:*";
P_HTM[8373]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassā ārocenti, sā vā āroceti.**she knows by herself or others have told her or she has told her.*";
P_HTM[8374]="*Pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannanti**Has committed an offense entailing expulsion:*";
P_HTM[8375]="*aṭṭhannaṃ pārājikānaṃ aññataraṃ pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ.**she has committed any one of the eight offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8376]="*Nevattanā paṭicodeyyāti**She neither confronts her herself:*";
P_HTM[8377]="*na sayaṃ codeyya.**she does not herself accuse her.*";
P_HTM[8378]="*Na gaṇassa āroceyyāti**Nor tells a group of nuns:*";
P_HTM[8379]="*na aññāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ āroceyya.**she does not tell other nuns.*";
P_HTM[8380]="*Yadā ca sā ṭhitā vā assa cutā vāti**Whether that nun remains or has died:*";
P_HTM[8381]="*ṭhitā nāma saliṅge ṭhitā vuccati.**Remains: what is meant is that she remains as a nun.*";
P_HTM[8382]="*Cutā nāma kālaṅkatā vuccati.**Has died: what is meant is that she has passed away.*";
P_HTM[8383]="*Nāsitā nāma**Has been expelled:*";
P_HTM[8384]="*sayaṃ vā vibbhantā hoti aññehi vā nāsitā.**she has either disrobed herself or been expelled by others.*";
P_HTM[8385]="*Avassaṭā nāma**Has converted:*";
P_HTM[8386]="*titthāyatanaṃ saṅkantā vuccati.**what is meant is that she has joined another religious community.*";
P_HTM[8387]="*Sā pacchā evaṃ vadeyya— “pubbevāhaṃ, ayye, aññāsiṃ etaṃ bhikkhuniṃ evarūpā ca evarūpā ca sā bhaginī”ti. No ca kho attanā paṭicodessanti**Afterward she says, “Venerables, although I previously knew that this nun was like this, I thought, ‘I will neither confront her myself’”:*";
P_HTM[8388]="*sayaṃ vā na codessaṃ.**“I won’t accuse her myself.”*";
P_HTM[8389]="*Na gaṇassa ārocessanti**“Nor tell a group of nuns”:*";
P_HTM[8390]="*na aññāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ ārocessaṃ.**“Nor tell other nuns.”*";
P_HTM[8391]="*Ayampīti**She too:*";
P_HTM[8392]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8393]="*Pārājikā hotīti**Is expelled:*";
P_HTM[8394]="*seyyathāpi nāma paṇḍupalāso bandhanā pamutto abhabbo haritatthāya, evameva bhikkhunī jānaṃ pārājikaṃ dhammaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ bhikkhuniṃ nevattanā paṭicodessāmi na gaṇassa ārocessāmīti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte assamaṇī hoti asakyadhītā. Tena vuccati pārājikā hotīti.**just as a fallen, withered leaf is incapable of becoming green again, so is a nun who knows that a nun has committed an offense entailing expulsion, but who thinks, “I will neither confront her myself nor tell a group of nuns,” by the mere fact of giving up her duty, not a monastic, not a daughter of the Sakyan. Therefore it is said “she is expelled”.*";
P_HTM[8395]="*Asaṃvāsāti**Excluded from the community:*";
P_HTM[8396]="*saṃvāso nāma ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā. Eso saṃvāso nāma.**Community: joint legal procedures, a joint recitation, the same training—this is called “community”.*";
P_HTM[8397]="*So tāya saddhiṃ natthi. Tena vuccati asaṃvāsāti.**She does not take part in this—therefore it is called “excluded from the community”.*";
P_HTM[8398]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8399]="*“saṅghassa bhaṇḍanaṃ vā kalaho vā viggaho vā vivādo vā bhavissatī”ti nāroceti,**if she does not tell because she thinks there will be quarrels or disputes in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[8400]="*“saṅghabhedo vā saṅgharāji vā bhavissatī”ti nāroceti,**if she does not tell because she thinks there will be a schism or fracture in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[8401]="*“ayaṃ kakkhaḷā pharusā jīvitantarāyaṃ vā brahmacariyantarāyaṃ vā karissatī”ti nāroceti,**if she does not tell because she thinks the person she is telling about is cruel and harsh and that she might become a danger to life or to the living of the spiritual life;*";
P_HTM[8402]="*aññā patirūpā bhikkhuniyo apassantī nāroceti,**if she does not tell because she does not see any suitable nuns;*";
P_HTM[8403]="*nacchādetukāmā nāroceti,**if she does not tell, but not because she wants to conceal;*";
P_HTM[8404]="*paññāyissati sakena kammenāti nāroceti,**if she does not tell because she thinks the other person will be known through her own actions;*";
P_HTM[8405]="*ummattikāya …pe…**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8406]="*if she is deranged;* **";
P_HTM[8407]="*if she is overwhelmed by pain;* **";
P_HTM[8408]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8409]="*Dutiyapārājikaṃ samattaṃ.**The sixth offense entailing expulsion is finished.*";
P_HTM[8410]="*127. Pārājikakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion *";
P_HTM[8411]="*7. Ukkhittānuvattikāsikkhāpada**7. The training rule on taking sides with one who has been ejected*";
P_HTM[8412]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[8413]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ anuvattati.**the nun Thullanandā was taking sides with the monk Ariṭṭha, an ex-vulture-killer, who had been ejected by a unanimous Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8414]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8415]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ anuvattissatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Thullanandā take sides with the monk Ariṭṭha who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[8416]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ anuvattatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā is doing this?”*";
P_HTM[8417]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8418]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8419]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ ariṭṭhaṃ bhikkhuṃ gaddhabādhipubbaṃ anuvattissati.**“How can the nun Thullanandā take sides with the monk Ariṭṭha who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha?*";
P_HTM[8420]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8421]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8422]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anādaraṃ appaṭikāraṃ akatasahāyaṃ tamanuvatteyya, sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi evamassa vacanīyā—**‘If a nun takes sides with a monk who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha—in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—and who is disrespectful, who has not made amends, and who has not made friends, the nuns should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[8423]="*‘eso kho, ayye, bhikkhu samaggena saṅghena ukkhitto dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anādaro appaṭikāro akatasahāyo, māyye, etaṃ bhikkhuṃ anuvattī’ti.**“Venerable, this monk has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction. He’s disrespectful, hasn’t made amends, and hasn’t made friends. Venerable, don’t take sides with this monk.”*";
P_HTM[8424]="*Evañca sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyya, sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If that nun continues as before, the nuns should press her up to three times to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[8425]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsiyamānā taṃ paṭinissajjeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If she then stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[8426]="*No ce paṭinissajjeyya, ayampi pārājikā hoti asaṃvāsā ukkhittānuvattikā”ti.**If she does not stop, she too is expelled and excluded from the community. The training rule on taking sides with one who has been ejected.’”*";
P_HTM[8427]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8428]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8429]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8430]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8431]="*Samaggo nāma saṅgho**A unanimous Sangha:*";
P_HTM[8432]="*samānasaṃvāsako samānasīmāyaṃ ṭhito.**those belonging to the same Buddhist sect and staying within the same monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[8433]="*Ukkhitto nāma**Who has been ejected:*";
P_HTM[8434]="*āpattiyā adassane vā appaṭikamme vā appaṭinissagge vā ukkhitto.**who has been ejected for not recognizing an offense, for not making amends, or for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[8435]="*Dhammena vinayenāti**in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8436]="*yena dhammena yena vinayena.**in accordance with that rule, in accordance with that Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8437]="*Satthusāsanenāti**In accordance with the Teacher’s instruction:*";
P_HTM[8438]="*jinasāsanena buddhasāsanena.**in accordance with the Conqueror’s instruction, in accordance with the Buddha’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[8439]="*Anādaro nāma**Who is disrespectful:*";
P_HTM[8440]="*saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā puggalaṃ vā kammaṃ vā nādiyati.**he does not heed the Sangha, groups of monks, individual monks, or legal procedures.*";
P_HTM[8441]="*Appaṭikāro nāma**Who has not made amends:*";
P_HTM[8442]="*ukkhitto anosārito.**he has been ejected and not reinstated.*";
P_HTM[8443]="*Akatasahāyo nāma**Who has not made friends:*";
P_HTM[8444]="*samānasaṃvāsakā bhikkhū vuccanti sahāyā.**monks belonging to the same Buddhist sect is what is meant by “friends”.*";
P_HTM[8445]="*So tehi saddhiṃ natthi, tena vuccati akatasahāyoti.**He is not together with them—therefore it is called “who has not made friends”.*";
P_HTM[8446]="*Tamanuvatteyyāti**Takes sides with:*";
P_HTM[8447]="*yaṃdiṭṭhiko so hoti yaṅkhantiko yaṃruciko, sāpi taṃdiṭṭhikā hoti taṅkhantikā taṃrucikā.**she has the same view, the same belief, the same persuasion as he does.*";
P_HTM[8448]="*Sā bhikkhunīti**Her:*";
P_HTM[8449]="*yā sā ukkhittānuvattikā bhikkhunī.**that nun who supports one who has been ejected.*";
P_HTM[8450]="*Bhikkhunīhīti**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[8451]="*aññāhi bhikkhunīhi. Yā passanti yā suṇanti tāhi vattabbā—**Other nuns who see it or hear about it. They should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[8452]="*“eso kho, ayye, bhikkhu samaggena saṅghena ukkhitto dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anādaro appaṭikāro akatasahāyo.**“Venerable, this monk has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction. He’s disrespectful, hasn’t made amends, and hasn’t made friends.*";
P_HTM[8453]="*Māyye, etaṃ bhikkhuṃ anuvattī”ti.**Venerable, don’t take sides with this monk.”*";
P_HTM[8454]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**And they should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[8455]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[8456]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[8457]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8458]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8459]="*Sā bhikkhunī saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—**That nun, even if she has to be pulled into the middle of the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[8460]="*“eso kho, ayye, bhikkhu samaggena saṅghena ukkhitto dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anādaro appaṭikāro akatasahāyo.**“Venerable, this monk has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction. He’s disrespectful, hasn’t made amends, and hasn’t made friends.*";
P_HTM[8461]="*Māyye, etaṃ bhikkhuṃ anuvattīti.**Venerable, don’t take sides with this monk.”*";
P_HTM[8462]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**They should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[8463]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[8464]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ.**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[8465]="*No ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8466]="*Sā bhikkhunī samanubhāsitabbā.**Should press her:*";
P_HTM[8467]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbā.**“And, monks, she should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[8468]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[8469]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[8470]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anādaraṃ appaṭikāraṃ akatasahāyaṃ tamanuvattati, sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**The nun so-and-so is taking sides with a monk who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha—in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—and who is disrespectful, who has not made amends, and who has not made friends. And she keeps on doing it.*";
P_HTM[8471]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[8472]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[8473]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[8474]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anādaraṃ appaṭikāraṃ akatasahāyaṃ tamanuvattati.**The nun so-and-so is taking sides with a monk who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha—in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction—and who is disrespectful, who has not made amends, and who has not made friends.*";
P_HTM[8475]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on doing it.*";
P_HTM[8476]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[8477]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of pressing her to make her stop should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[8478]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[8479]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[8480]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[8481]="*Samanubhaṭṭhā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha has pressed nun so-and-so to stop.*";
P_HTM[8482]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[8483]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ,**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8484]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā,**After each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8485]="*kammavācā pariyosāne āpatti pārājikassa.**When the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8486]="*Ayampīti**She too:*";
P_HTM[8487]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8488]="*Pārājikā hotīti**Is expelled:*";
P_HTM[8489]="*seyyathāpi nāma puthusilā dvedhā bhinnā appaṭisandhikā hoti, evameva bhikkhunī yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya na paṭinissajjantī assamaṇī hoti asakyadhītā. Tena vuccati pārājikā hotīti.**just as an ordinary stone that has broken in half cannot be put together again, so is a nun who does not stop when pressed three times not a monastic, not a daughter of the Sakyan. Therefore it is said “she is expelled”.*";
P_HTM[8490]="*Asaṃvāsāti**Excluded from the community:*";
P_HTM[8491]="*saṃvāso nāma ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā. Eso saṃvāso nāma.**Community: joint legal procedures, a joint recitation, the same training—this is called “community”.*";
P_HTM[8492]="*So tāya saddhiṃ natthi. Tena vuccati asaṃvāsāti.**She does not take part in this—therefore it is called “excluded from the community”.*";
P_HTM[8493]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pārājikassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, but she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8494]="*Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pārājikassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8495]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pārājikassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8496]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8497]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8498]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8499]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8500]="*asamanubhāsantiyā,**if she has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[8501]="*paṭinissajjantiyā,**if she stops;*";
P_HTM[8502]="*ummattikāya …pe…,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8503]="*if she is deranged;* **";
P_HTM[8504]="*if she is overwhelmed by pain;* **";
P_HTM[8505]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8506]="*Tatiyapārājikaṃ samattaṃ.**The seventh offense entailing expulsion is finished.*";
P_HTM[8507]="*127. Pārājikakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion *";
P_HTM[8508]="*8. Aṭṭhavatthukāsikkhāpada**8. The training rule having eight parts*";
P_HTM[8509]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8510]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthaggahaṇampi sādiyanti, saṅghāṭikaṇṇaggahaṇampi sādiyanti, santiṭṭhantipi, sallapantipi, saṅketampi gacchanti, purisassapi abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyanti, channampi anupavisanti, kāyampi tadatthāya upasaṃharanti etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya.**At that time the nuns from the group of six, being lustful and aiming to indulge in inappropriate sexual conduct, consented to lustful men holding their hand and the edge of their robes, and they stood with them, chatted with them, went to appointments with them, consented to men coming to them, entered covered places with them, and disposed their body for that purpose.*";
P_HTM[8511]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8512]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthaggahaṇampi sādiyissanti, saṅghāṭikaṇṇaggahaṇampi sādiyissanti, santiṭṭhissantipi, sallapissantipi, saṅketampi gacchissanti, purisassapi abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyissanti, channampi anupavisissanti, kāyampi tadatthāya upasaṃharissanti etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāyā”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six do such things?” …*";
P_HTM[8513]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthaggahaṇampi sādiyanti, saṅghāṭikaṇṇaggahaṇampi sādiyanti, santiṭṭhantipi, sallapantipi, saṅketampi gacchanti, purisassapi abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyanti, channampi anupavisanti, kāyampi tadatthāya upasaṃharanti etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāyā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do these things?”*";
P_HTM[8514]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8515]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[8516]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthaggahaṇampi sādiyissanti, saṅghāṭikaṇṇaggahaṇampi sādiyissanti, santiṭṭhissantipi, sallapissantipi, saṅketampi gacchissanti, purisassapi abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyissanti, channampi anupavisissanti, kāyampi tadatthāya upasaṃharissanti etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya.**“How can the nuns from the group of six, being lustful and aiming to indulge in inappropriate sexual conduct, consent to lustful men holding their hand and the edge of their robes, and how can they stand with them, chat with them, go to appointments with them, consent to men coming to them, enter covered places with them, and dispose their body for that purpose?*";
P_HTM[8517]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8518]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8519]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthaggahaṇaṃ vā sādiyeyya, saṅghāṭikaṇṇaggahaṇaṃ vā sādiyeyya, santiṭṭheyya vā, sallapeyya vā, saṅketaṃ vā gaccheyya, purisassa vā abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyeyya, channaṃ vā anupaviseyya, kāyaṃ vā tadatthāya upasaṃhareyya etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya, ayampi pārājikā hoti asaṃvāsā aṭṭhavatthukā”ti.**‘If, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, a lustful nun consents to a lustful man holding her hand and the edge of her robe, and she stands with him and chats with him and goes to an appointment with him and consents to him coming to her and enters a covered place with him and disposes her body for him for that purpose, she too is expelled and excluded from the community. The training rule having eight parts.’”*";
P_HTM[8520]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8521]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8522]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8523]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8524]="*Avassutā nāma**Lustful:*";
P_HTM[8525]="*sārattā apekkhavatī paṭibaddhacittā.**having lust, longing for, in love with.*";
P_HTM[8526]="*Avassuto nāma**Lustful:*";
P_HTM[8527]="*sāratto apekkhavā paṭibaddhacitto.**having lust, longing for, in love with.*";
P_HTM[8528]="*Purisapuggalo nāma**Man:*";
P_HTM[8529]="*manussapuriso, na yakkho na peto na tiracchānagato viññū paṭibalo kāyasaṃsaggaṃ samāpajjituṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of making physical contact.*";
P_HTM[8530]="*Hatthaggahaṇaṃ vā sādiyeyyāti**Consents to holding her hand:*";
P_HTM[8531]="*hattho nāma kapparaṃ upādāya yāva agganakhā.**hand: from the elbow to the tip of the nails.*";
P_HTM[8532]="*Etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya ubbhakkhakaṃ adhojāṇumaṇḍalaṃ gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she consents to him holding her above the collar bone or below the knees, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8533]="*Saṅghāṭikaṇṇaggahaṇaṃ vā sādiyeyyāti**And the edge of her robe:*";
P_HTM[8534]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya nivatthaṃ vā pārutaṃ vā gahaṇaṃ sādiyati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she consents to him holding her sarong or upper robe, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8535]="*Santiṭṭheyya vāti**And stands with him:*";
P_HTM[8536]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya purisassa hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she stands within arm’s reach of a man, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8537]="*Sallapeyya vāti**And chats with him:*";
P_HTM[8538]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya purisassa hatthapāse ṭhitā sallapati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she stands within arm’s reach of a man, chatting with him, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8539]="*Saṅketaṃ vā gaccheyyāti**And goes to an appointment with him:*";
P_HTM[8540]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya purisena— “itthannāmaṃ okāsaṃ āgacchā”ti—vuttā gacchati. Pade pade āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she goes to such-and-such a place when told by a man to do so, then for every step, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8541]="*Purisassa hatthapāsaṃ okkantamatte āpatti thullaccayassa.**For entering within arm’s reach of the man, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8542]="*Purisassa vā abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyeyyāti**And consents to him coming to her:*";
P_HTM[8543]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya purisassa abbhāgamanaṃ sādiyati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she consents to a man coming to her, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8544]="*Hatthapāsaṃ okkantamatte āpatti thullaccayassa.**When he enters within arm’s reach, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8545]="*Channaṃ vā anupaviseyyāti**And enters a covered place with him:*";
P_HTM[8546]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya yena kenaci paṭicchannaṃ okāsaṃ paviṭṭhamatte āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she enters a concealed place with any man, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8547]="*Kāyaṃ vā tadatthāya upasaṃhareyyāti**And disposes her body for him for that purpose:*";
P_HTM[8548]="*etassa asaddhammassa paṭisevanatthāya purisassa hatthapāse ṭhitā kāyaṃ upasaṃharati, āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, for the purpose of indulging in inappropriate sexual conduct, she disposes her body for a man while standing within arm’s reach of him, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8549]="*Ayampīti**She too:*";
P_HTM[8550]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses entailing expulsion.*";
P_HTM[8551]="*Pārājikā hotīti**Is expelled:*";
P_HTM[8552]="*seyyathāpi nāma tālo matthakacchinno abhabbo puna viruḷhiyā evameva bhikkhunī aṭṭhamaṃ vatthuṃ paripūrentī assamaṇī hoti asakyadhītā. Tena vuccati pārājikā hotīti.**just as a palm tree with its crown cut off is incapable of further growth, so is a nun who fulfills the eight parts not a monastic, not a daughter of the Sakyan. Therefore it is said “she is expelled”.*";
P_HTM[8553]="*Asaṃvāsāti**Excluded from the community:*";
P_HTM[8554]="*saṃvāso nāma ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā. Eso saṃvāso nāma.**Community: joint legal procedures, a joint recitation, the same training—this is called “community”.*";
P_HTM[8555]="*So tāya saddhiṃ natthi. Tena vuccati asaṃvāsāti.**She does not take part in this—therefore it is called “excluded from the community”.*";
P_HTM[8556]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8557]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[8558]="*assatiyā,**if she is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[8559]="*ajānantiyā,**if she does not know;*";
P_HTM[8560]="*asādiyantiyā,**if she does not consent;*";
P_HTM[8561]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8562]="*khittacittāya,**if she is deranged;*";
P_HTM[8563]="*vedanāṭṭāya,**if she is overwhelmed by pain;*";
P_HTM[8564]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8565]="*Catutthapārājikaṃ samattaṃ.**The eighth offense entailing expulsion is finished.*";
P_HTM[8566]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, aṭṭha pārājikā dhammā.**“Venerables, the eight rules on expulsion have been recited.*";
P_HTM[8567]="*Yesaṃ bhikkhunī aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā āpajjitvā na labhati bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ saṃvāsaṃ, yathā pure tathā pacchā, pārājikā hoti asaṃvāsā.**If a nun commits any one of them, she no longer belongs to the community of nuns. As before, so after, she is expelled and excluded from the community.*";
P_HTM[8568]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[8569]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[8570]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[8571]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[8572]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[8573]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[8574]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[8575]="*Bhikkhunivibhaṅge pārājikakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing expulsion in the nuns’ analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[8576]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[8577]="*1. Ussayavādikāsikkhāpada**1. The training rule on being litigious*";
P_HTM[8578]="*Ime kho panāyyāyo sattarasa saṅghādisesā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these seventeen rules on suspension come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[8579]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery.*";
P_HTM[8580]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro upāsako bhikkhunisaṅghassa udositaṃ datvā kālaṅkato hoti.**At that time a lay follower who had given a storehouse to the Sangha of nuns had died.*";
P_HTM[8581]="*Tassa dve puttā honti—**He had two sons,*";
P_HTM[8582]="*eko assaddho appasanno, eko saddho pasanno.**one with and one without faith and confidence,*";
P_HTM[8583]="*Te pettikaṃ sāpateyyaṃ vibhajiṃsu.**and they divided their father’s property between them.*";
P_HTM[8584]="*Atha kho so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ etadavoca—**Then the one without faith said to the other,*";
P_HTM[8585]="*“amhākaṃ udosito, taṃ bhājemā”ti.**“The storehouse is ours; let’s share it out.”*";
P_HTM[8586]="*Evaṃ vutte, so saddho pasanno taṃ assaddhaṃ appasannaṃ etadavoca—**But the one with faith responded,*";
P_HTM[8587]="*“māyyo, evaṃ avaca.**“No,*";
P_HTM[8588]="*Amhākaṃ pitunā bhikkhunisaṅghassa dinno”ti.**our father gave it to the Sangha of nuns.”*";
P_HTM[8589]="*Dutiyampi kho so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ etadavoca—**A second time they both said the same thing,*";
P_HTM[8590]="*“amhākaṃ udosito, taṃ bhājemā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8591]="*Atha kho so saddho pasanno taṃ assaddhaṃ appasannaṃ etadavoca—* **";
P_HTM[8592]="*“māyyo, evaṃ avaca.* **";
P_HTM[8593]="*Amhākaṃ pitunā bhikkhunisaṅghassa dinno”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8594]="*Tatiyampi kho so assaddho appasanno taṃ saddhaṃ pasannaṃ etadavoca—**and a third time the one without faith repeated his proposal.*";
P_HTM[8595]="*“amhākaṃ udosito, taṃ bhājemā”ti.* **";
P_HTM[8596]="*Atha kho so saddho pasanno—**The one with faith then thought,*";
P_HTM[8597]="*“sace mayhaṃ bhavissati, ahampi bhikkhunisaṅghassa dassāmī”ti—**“If I get it, I too would give it to the Sangha of nuns,”*";
P_HTM[8598]="*taṃ assaddhaṃ appasannaṃ etadavoca—**and he said,*";
P_HTM[8599]="*“bhājemā”ti.**“Let’s share it out.”*";
P_HTM[8600]="*Atha kho so udosito tehi bhājīyamāno tassa assaddhassa appasannassa pāpuṇāti.**But when they shared out that storehouse, it fell to the one without faith.*";
P_HTM[8601]="*Atha kho so assaddho appasanno bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca—**He then went to the nuns and said,*";
P_HTM[8602]="*“nikkhamathāyye, amhākaṃ udosito”ti.**“Please leave, Venerables, this storehouse is mine.”*";
P_HTM[8603]="*Evaṃ vutte thullanandā bhikkhunī taṃ purisaṃ etadavoca—**The nun Thullanandā said to him,*";
P_HTM[8604]="*“māyyo, evaṃ avaca, tumhākaṃ pitunā bhikkhunisaṅghassa dinno”ti.**“No, your father gave it to the Sangha of nuns.”*";
P_HTM[8605]="*“Dinno na dinno”ti vohārike mahāmatte pucchiṃsu.**Because they were unable to agree, they asked judges to decide on the matter.*";
P_HTM[8606]="*Mahāmattā evamāhaṃsu—**They said,*";
P_HTM[8607]="*“ko, ayye, jānāti bhikkhunisaṅghassa dinno”ti?**“Venerable, who knows that it was given to the Sangha of nuns?”*";
P_HTM[8608]="*Evaṃ vutte, thullanandā bhikkhunī te mahāmatte etadavoca—**Thullanandā replied,*";
P_HTM[8609]="*“api nāyyā tumhehi diṭṭhaṃ vā sutaṃ vā sakkhiṃ ṭhapayitvā dānaṃ diyyamānan”ti?**“But Sirs, didn’t you appoint a witness who saw or heard the giving of the gift?”*";
P_HTM[8610]="*Atha kho te mahāmattā—**Saying,*";
P_HTM[8611]="*“saccaṃ kho ayyā āhā”ti taṃ udositaṃ bhikkhunisaṅghassa akaṃsu.**“It’s true what the Venerable says,” the judges made the storehouse the property of the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[8612]="*Atha kho so puriso parājito ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**The defeated man complained and criticized the nuns,*";
P_HTM[8613]="*“assamaṇiyo imā muṇḍā bandhakiniyo.**“They’re not monastics these shaven-headed sluts.*";
P_HTM[8614]="*Kathañhi nāma amhākaṃ udositaṃ acchindāpessantī”ti.**How could they take my storehouse?”*";
P_HTM[8615]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī mahāmattānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Thullanandā told the judges of this*";
P_HTM[8616]="*Mahāmattā taṃ purisaṃ daṇḍāpesuṃ.**and they punished him.*";
P_HTM[8617]="*Atha kho so puriso daṇḍito bhikkhunupassayassa avidūre ājīvakaseyyaṃ kārāpetvā ājīvake uyyojesi—**That man then made a dwelling place for Ājīvaka ascetics not far from the nuns,*";
P_HTM[8618]="*“etā bhikkhuniyo accāvadathā”ti.**inciting them to abuse the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8619]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī mahāmattānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Once again Thullanandā told the judges*";
P_HTM[8620]="*Mahāmattā taṃ purisaṃ bandhāpesuṃ.**and the judges jailed him.*";
P_HTM[8621]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People then complained and criticized those nuns,*";
P_HTM[8622]="*“paṭhamaṃ bhikkhuniyo udositaṃ acchindāpesuṃ, dutiyaṃ daṇḍāpesuṃ, tatiyaṃ bandhāpesuṃ.**“First the nuns take his storehouse, then they have him punished, and then they have him jailed.*";
P_HTM[8623]="*Idāni ghātāpessantī”ti.**Now they’ll have him executed!”*";
P_HTM[8624]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**Nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[8625]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8626]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā ussayavādikā viharissatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā be litigious?”*";
P_HTM[8627]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**Then those nuns told the monks …*";
P_HTM[8628]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī ussayavādikā viharatī”ti.**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā is litigious?”*";
P_HTM[8629]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8630]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8631]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī ussayavādikā viharissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā be litigious?*";
P_HTM[8632]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8633]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8634]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ussayavādikā vihareyya gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā dāsena vā kammakārena vā antamaso samaṇaparibbājakenāpi, ayaṃ bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun is litigious toward a householder or a householder’s child or a slave or a worker or even toward a monastic or a wanderer, then that nun has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8635]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8636]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8637]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8638]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8639]="*Ussayavādikā nāma**Litigious:*";
P_HTM[8640]="*aḍḍakārikā vuccati.**what is meant is that she is the initiator of a lawsuit.*";
P_HTM[8641]="*Gahapati nāma**A householder:*";
P_HTM[8642]="*yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**whoever lives at home.*";
P_HTM[8643]="*Gahapatiputto nāma**A householder’s child:*";
P_HTM[8644]="*ye keci puttabhātaro.**whoever is a child or a sibling.*";
P_HTM[8645]="*Dāso nāma**A slave:*";
P_HTM[8646]="*antojāto dhanakkīto karamarānīto.**one born in the household, one who has been bought, one who has been brought back as a captive.*";
P_HTM[8647]="*Kammakāro nāma**A worker:*";
P_HTM[8648]="*bhaṭako āhatako.**a paid worker, a servant.*";
P_HTM[8649]="*Samaṇaparibbājako nāma**A monastic or a wanderer:*";
P_HTM[8650]="*bhikkhuñca bhikkhuniñca sikkhamānañca sāmaṇerañca sāmaṇeriñca ṭhapetvā yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno.**anyone who is a wanderer apart from Buddhist monks, nuns, trainee nuns, novice monks, and novice nuns.*";
P_HTM[8651]="*Aḍḍaṃ karissāmīti dutiyaṃ vā pariyesati gacchati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, thinking, “I’ll initiate a lawsuit,” she looks for a companion or just goes there herself, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8652]="*Ekassa āroceti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells one other person, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8653]="*Dutiyassa āroceti, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If she tells a second person, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8654]="*Aḍḍapariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**At the end of the lawsuit, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8655]="*Paṭhamāpattikanti**An immediate offense:*";
P_HTM[8656]="*saha vatthujjhācārā āpajjati asamanubhāsanāya.**there is an offense as soon as the misconduct is committed, and no pressing is required.*";
P_HTM[8657]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[8658]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8659]="*Saṅghādisesanti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[8660]="*saṅghova tassā āpattiyā mānattaṃ deti mūlāya paṭikassati abbheti, na sambahulā na ekā bhikkhunī. Tena vuccati “saṅghādiseso”ti.**only the Sangha gives the trial period for that offense, sends back to the beginning, and rehabilitates—not several nuns, not an individual nun. Therefore it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8661]="*Tasseva āpattinikāyassa nāmakammaṃ adhivacanaṃ. Tenapi vuccati “saṅghādiseso”ti.**This is the name and designation of this class of offense. Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8662]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8663]="*manussehi ākaḍḍhīyamānā gacchati,**if she goes there because people pull her;*";
P_HTM[8664]="*ārakkhaṃ yācati,**if she is asking for protection;*";
P_HTM[8665]="*anodissa ācikkhati,**if she tells without specifying a person;*";
P_HTM[8666]="*ummattikāya …pe…**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8667]="*if she is deranged;* **";
P_HTM[8668]="*if she is overwhelmed by pain;* **";
P_HTM[8669]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8670]="*Paṭhamasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[8671]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[8672]="*2. Corīvuṭṭhāpikāsikkhāpada**2. The training rule on one who gives the full admission to a criminal*";
P_HTM[8673]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8674]="*Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ aññatarassa licchavissa pajāpati aticārinī hoti.**At that time in Vesālī the wife of a certain Licchavī man was unfaithful.*";
P_HTM[8675]="*Atha kho so licchavi taṃ itthiṃ etadavoca—**He said to her,*";
P_HTM[8676]="*“sādhu viramāhi, anatthaṃ kho te karissāmī”ti.**“Please stop. If you don’t, I’ll punish you.”*";
P_HTM[8677]="*Evampi vuccamānā nādiyi.**But she did not listen.*";
P_HTM[8678]="*Tena kho pana samayena vesāliyaṃ licchavigaṇo sannipatito hoti kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Just then in Vesālī the Licchavī clan had gathered on some business.*";
P_HTM[8679]="*Atha kho so licchavi te licchavayo etadavoca—**That Licchavī man said to them,*";
P_HTM[8680]="*“ekaṃ me, ayyo, itthiṃ anujānāthā”ti.**“Sirs, please give me permission in regard to one of my wives.”*";
P_HTM[8681]="*“Kā nāma sā”ti?**“What is it with her?”*";
P_HTM[8682]="*“Mayhaṃ pajāpati aticarati, taṃ ghātessāmī”ti.**“She’s unfaithful. I wish to kill her.”*";
P_HTM[8683]="*“Jānāhī”ti.**“You may go ahead.”*";
P_HTM[8684]="*Assosi kho sā itthī—**When his wife heard*";
P_HTM[8685]="*“sāmiko kira maṃ ghātetukāmo”ti.**that her husband wanted to kill her,*";
P_HTM[8686]="*Varabhaṇḍaṃ ādāya sāvatthiṃ gantvā titthiye upasaṅkamitvā pabbajjaṃ yāci.**she took their most valuable possessions and went to Sāvatthī. There she went to the monastics of other religions and asked for the going forth,*";
P_HTM[8687]="*Titthiyā na icchiṃsu pabbājetuṃ.**but they refused.*";
P_HTM[8688]="*Bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā pabbajjaṃ yāci.**She then went to the Buddhist nuns and again asked for the going forth,*";
P_HTM[8689]="*Bhikkhuniyopi na icchiṃsu pabbājetuṃ.**but they too refused.*";
P_HTM[8690]="*Thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ upasaṅkamitvā bhaṇḍakaṃ dassetvā pabbajjaṃ yāci.**She then went to the nun Thullanandā, showed her the goods, and once again asked for the going forth.*";
P_HTM[8691]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī bhaṇḍakaṃ gahetvā pabbājesi.**Thullanandā took the goods and gave her the going forth.*";
P_HTM[8692]="*Atha kho so licchavi taṃ itthiṃ gavesanto sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitaṃ disvāna yena rājā pasenadi kosalo tenupasaṅkami;**That Licchavī man then went to Sāvatthī in search of his wife. When he saw that she had been given the going forth as a nun, he went to King Pasenadi of Kosala*";
P_HTM[8693]="*upasaṅkamitvā rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ etadavoca—**and said,*";
P_HTM[8694]="*“pajāpati me, deva, varabhaṇḍaṃ ādāya sāvatthiṃ anuppattā.**“Sir, my wife took my most valuable possessions and came to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8695]="*Taṃ devo anujānātū”ti.**Please permit me to deal with her.”*";
P_HTM[8696]="*“Tena hi, bhaṇe, vicinitvā ācikkhā”ti.**“Well then, find her and then inform me.”*";
P_HTM[8697]="*“Diṭṭhā, deva, bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā”ti.**“I’ve seen her. She’s gone forth as a nun.”*";
P_HTM[8698]="*“Sace, bhaṇe, bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā, na sā labbhā kiñci kātuṃ.**“If she’s gone forth as a nun, there’s nothing that can be done.*";
P_HTM[8699]="*Svākkhāto bhagavatā dhammo, caratu brahmacariyaṃ sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāyā”ti.**The Teaching of the Buddha is well-proclaimed. Let her practice the spiritual life for the full ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[8700]="*Atha kho so licchavi ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**Then that Licchavī man complained and criticized the nuns,*";
P_HTM[8701]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo coriṃ pabbājessantī”ti.**“How could the nuns give the going forth to a criminal?”*";
P_HTM[8702]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tassa licchavissa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The nuns heard the complaints of that Licchavī man,*";
P_HTM[8703]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8704]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā coriṃ pabbājessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give the going forth to a criminal?”*";
P_HTM[8705]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**The nuns told the monks. …*";
P_HTM[8706]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī coriṃ pabbājetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[8707]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8708]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8709]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī coriṃ pabbājessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā give the going forth to a criminal?*";
P_HTM[8710]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8711]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8712]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī jānaṃ coriṃ vajjhaṃ viditaṃ anapaloketvā rājānaṃ vā saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā pūgaṃ vā seṇiṃ vā aññatra kappā vuṭṭhāpeyya, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun, without getting permission from the king or the Sangha or a community or an association or a society, gives the full admission to a woman who she knows is a criminal and who is known as sentenced to death, then, except when it is allowable, that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8713]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8714]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8715]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8716]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8717]="*Jānāti nāma**She knows:*";
P_HTM[8718]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti aññe vā tassā ārocenti, sā vā āroceti.**she knows by herself or others have told her or she has told her.*";
P_HTM[8719]="*Corī nāma**A woman who is a criminal:*";
P_HTM[8720]="*yā pañcamāsakaṃ vā atirekapañcamāsakaṃ vā agghanakaṃ adinnaṃ theyyasaṅkhātaṃ ādiyati, esā corī nāma.**any woman who has stolen anything worth five _māsakas_ coins or more is called “a criminal”.*";
P_HTM[8721]="*Vajjhā nāma**Sentenced to death:*";
P_HTM[8722]="*yaṃ katvā vajjhappattā hoti.**she has been sentenced to death because of her action.*";
P_HTM[8723]="*Viditā nāma**Is known:*";
P_HTM[8724]="*aññehi manussehi ñātā hoti “vajjhā esā”ti.**it is known to other people that she has been sentenced to death.*";
P_HTM[8725]="*Anapaloketvāti**Without getting permission from:*";
P_HTM[8726]="*anāpucchā.**without having asked permission.*";
P_HTM[8727]="*Rājā nāma**The king:*";
P_HTM[8728]="*yattha rājā anusāsati, rājā apaloketabbo.**where a king reigns, permission should be gotten from the king.*";
P_HTM[8729]="*Saṅgho nāma**The Sangha:*";
P_HTM[8730]="*bhikkhunisaṅgho vuccati, bhikkhunisaṅgho apaloketabbo.**what is meant is the Sangha of nuns, and permission should be gotten from that Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8731]="*Gaṇo nāma**A community:*";
P_HTM[8732]="*yattha gaṇo anusāsati, gaṇo apaloketabbo.**where a community governs, permission should be gotten from that community.*";
P_HTM[8733]="*Pūgo nāma**An association:*";
P_HTM[8734]="*yattha pūgo anusāsati, pūgo apaloketabbo.**where an association governs, permission should be gotten from that association.*";
P_HTM[8735]="*Seṇi nāma**A society:*";
P_HTM[8736]="*yattha seṇi anusāsati, seṇi apaloketabbo.**where a society governs, permission should be gotten from that society.*";
P_HTM[8737]="*Aññatra kappāti**Except when it is allowable:*";
P_HTM[8738]="*ṭhapetvā kappaṃ.**unless it is allowable.*";
P_HTM[8739]="*Kappaṃ nāma**Allowable:*";
P_HTM[8740]="*dve kappāni— titthiyesu vā pabbajitā hoti aññāsu vā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā.**there are two allowable situations: she has gone forth with monastics of another religion or she has gone forth with other Buddhist nuns.*";
P_HTM[8741]="*Aññatra kappā “vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, then, except when it is allowable, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8742]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8743]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8744]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing suspension,*";
P_HTM[8745]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8746]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[8747]="*purimaṃ upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offense.*";
P_HTM[8748]="*Paṭhamāpattikanti**An immediate offense:*";
P_HTM[8749]="*saha vatthujjhācārā āpajjati asamanubhāsanāya.**there is an offense as soon as the misconduct is committed, and no pressing is required.*";
P_HTM[8750]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[8751]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8752]="*Saṅghādisesanti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[8753]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8754]="*Coriyā corisaññā aññatra kappā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If she is a criminal, and the nun perceives her as such, and she gives her the full admission, except when it is allowable, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8755]="*Coriyā vematikā aññatra kappā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is a criminal, but the nun is unsure of it, and she gives her the full admission, except when it is allowable, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8756]="*Coriyā acorisaññā aññatra kappā vuṭṭhāpeti, anāpatti.**If she is a criminal, but the nun does not perceive her as such, and she gives her the full admission, except when it is allowable, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[8757]="*Acoriyā corisaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not a criminal, but the nun perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8758]="*Acoriyā vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not a criminal, but the nun is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8759]="*Acoriyā acorisaññā, anāpatti.**If she is not a criminal, and the nun does not perceive her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[8760]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8761]="*ajānantī vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission without knowing that she is a criminal;*";
P_HTM[8762]="*apaloketvā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission after getting permission;*";
P_HTM[8763]="*kappakataṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission when it is allowable;*";
P_HTM[8764]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8765]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8766]="*Dutiyasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[8767]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[8768]="*3. Ekagāmantaragamanasikkhāpada**3. The training rule on walking alone to the next village*";
P_HTM[8769]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[8770]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhaddāya kāpilāniyā antevāsinī bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍitvā gāmakaṃ ñātikulaṃ agamāsi.**a nun who was a pupil of Bhaddā Kāpilānī had an argument with the nuns and then went to her relatives’ village.*";
P_HTM[8771]="*Bhaddā kāpilānī taṃ bhikkhuniṃ apassantī bhikkhuniyo pucchi—“kahaṃ itthannāmā, na dissatī”ti.**Not seeing her pupil anywhere, Bhaddā Kāpilānī asked the nuns, “Where’s so-and-so? She’s disappeared.”*";
P_HTM[8772]="*“Bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ, ayye, bhaṇḍitvā na dissatī”ti.**“She disappeared, Venerable, after arguing with the nuns.”*";
P_HTM[8773]="*“Ammā, amukasmiṃ gāmake etissā ñātikulaṃ. Tattha gantvā vicinathā”ti.**“My dears, her relatives live in such-and-such a village. Go there and look for her.”*";
P_HTM[8774]="*Bhikkhuniyo tattha gantvā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ passitvā etadavocuṃ—“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, ekikā āgatā, kaccisi appadhaṃsitā”ti?**The nuns went there, and when they saw her, they said to her, “Why did you go alone, Venerable? We hope you weren’t assaulted?”*";
P_HTM[8775]="*“Appadhaṃsitāmhi, ayye”ti.**“I wasn’t.”*";
P_HTM[8776]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8777]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī ekā gāmantaraṃ gacchissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun walk to the next village by herself?” …*";
P_HTM[8778]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā gāmantaraṃ gacchatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[8779]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8780]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8781]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā gāmantaraṃ gacchissati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[8782]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8783]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8784]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ekā gāmantaraṃ gaccheyya, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun walks to the next village by herself, then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8785]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8786]="*Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhuniyo sāketā sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti.**On one occasion two nuns were traveling from Sāketa to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8787]="*Antarāmagge nadī taritabbā hoti.**On the way they had to cross a river.*";
P_HTM[8788]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo nāvike upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—“sādhu no, āvuso, tārethā”ti.**They went to a boatman and said, “Please take us across.”*";
P_HTM[8789]="*“Nāyye, sakkā ubho sakiṃ tāretun”ti.**“I’m not able, Venerables, to take both of you across at the same time.”*";
P_HTM[8790]="*Eko ekaṃ uttāresi.**And so they crossed individually, alone with the boatman.*";
P_HTM[8791]="*Uttiṇṇo uttiṇṇaṃ dūsesi.**When he had crossed with the first nun, he raped her.*";
P_HTM[8792]="*Anuttiṇṇo anuttiṇṇaṃ dūsesi.**And after returning to the first bank, he raped the other nun as well.*";
P_HTM[8793]="*Tā pacchā samāgantvā pucchiṃsu—**Later, when they were reunited, they asked each other,*";
P_HTM[8794]="*“kaccisi, ayye, appadhaṃsitā”ti?**“Venerable, I hope you weren’t assaulted?”*";
P_HTM[8795]="*“Padhaṃsitāmhi, ayye.**“I was.*";
P_HTM[8796]="*Tvaṃ pana, ayye, appadhaṃsitā”ti?**And you, Venerable, were you assaulted?”*";
P_HTM[8797]="*“Padhaṃsitāmhi, ayye”ti.**“I was, too.”*";
P_HTM[8798]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They then continued on to Sāvatthī and told the nuns there what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8799]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[8800]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī ekā nadīpāraṃ gacchissatī”ti.**“How could a nun cross a river by herself?”*";
P_HTM[8801]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the monks,*";
P_HTM[8802]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**who in turn told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[8803]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā nadīpāraṃ gacchatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[8804]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8805]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[8806]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā nadīpāraṃ gacchissati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[8807]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8808]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8809]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ekā vā gāmantaraṃ gaccheyya, ekā vā nadīpāraṃ gaccheyya, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun walks to the next village by herself or crosses a river by herself, then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8810]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8811]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchantā sāyaṃ aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upagacchiṃsu.**On one occasion a number of nuns were walking through the Kosalan country on their way to Sāvatthī, when one evening they arrived at a certain village.*";
P_HTM[8812]="*Tattha aññatarā bhikkhunī abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā. Aññataro puriso tassā bhikkhuniyā saha dassanena paṭibaddhacitto hoti.**One of the nuns was beautiful and graceful, and a certain man fell in love with her as soon as he saw her.*";
P_HTM[8813]="*Atha kho so puriso tāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ seyyaṃ paññapento tassā bhikkhuniyā seyyaṃ ekamantaṃ paññāpesi.**Then, as he was preparing sleeping places for those nuns, he prepared hers to one side.*";
P_HTM[8814]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī sallakkhetvā—“pariyuṭṭhito ayaṃ puriso; sace rattiṃ āgacchissati, vissaro me bhavissatī”ti,**And that nun thought, “This man is obsessed with me. If I go there for the night, I’ll get into trouble.”*";
P_HTM[8815]="*bhikkhuniyo anāpucchā aññataraṃ kulaṃ gantvā seyyaṃ kappesi.**Then, without taking leave of the nuns, she went to a certain family and slept there.*";
P_HTM[8816]="*Atha kho so puriso rattiṃ āgantvā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ gavesanto bhikkhuniyo ghaṭṭesi.**When night arrived, that man went searching for that nun, and as he did so he bumped into the other nuns.*";
P_HTM[8817]="*Bhikkhuniyo taṃ bhikkhuniṃ apassantiyo evamāhaṃsu—“nissaṃsayaṃ kho sā bhikkhunī purisena saddhiṃ nikkhantā”ti.**Not seeing that nun anywhere, the nuns said, “No doubt she has left with a man.”*";
P_HTM[8818]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī tassā rattiyā accayena yena tā bhikkhuniyo tenupasaṅkami. Bhikkhuniyo taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, purisena saddhiṃ nikkhantā”ti?**The following morning that nun returned to the nuns, and they said to her, “Venerable, why did you leave with a man?”*";
P_HTM[8819]="*“Nāhaṃ, ayye, purisena saddhiṃ nikkhantā”ti.**“I didn’t leave with a man, Venerables.”*";
P_HTM[8820]="*Bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**She then told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[8821]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8822]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī ekā rattiṃ vippavasissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun spend the night apart by herself?” …*";
P_HTM[8823]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā rattiṃ vippavasatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[8824]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8825]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8826]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā rattiṃ vippavasissati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[8827]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8828]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8829]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ekā vā gāmantaraṃ gaccheyya, ekā vā nadīpāraṃ gaccheyya, ekā vā rattiṃ vippavaseyya, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun walks to the next village by herself or crosses a river by herself or spends the night apart by herself, then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8830]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[8831]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannā honti.**On one occasion a number of nuns were traveling through the Kosalan country on their way to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8832]="*Tattha aññatarā bhikkhunī vaccena pīḷitā ekikā ohīyitvā pacchā agamāsi.**One of the nuns, needing to defecate, stayed behind by herself, and then followed behind the others.*";
P_HTM[8833]="*Manussā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ passitvā dūsesuṃ.**People saw her and raped her.*";
P_HTM[8834]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī yena tā bhikkhuniyo tenupasaṅkami. Bhikkhuniyo taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, ekikā ohīnā, kaccisi appadhaṃsitā”ti?**She then went to the other nuns, and they said to her, “Why did you stay behind by yourself, Venerable? We hope you weren’t assaulted?”*";
P_HTM[8835]="*“Padhaṃsitāmhi, ayye”ti.**“I was.”*";
P_HTM[8836]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8837]="*kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī ekā gaṇamhā ohīyissatīti …pe…**“How could a nun lag behind her companions by herself?” …*";
P_HTM[8838]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā gaṇamhā ohīyatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[8839]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8840]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8841]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī ekā gaṇamhā ohīyissati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[8842]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8843]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8844]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ekā vā gāmantaraṃ gaccheyya, ekā vā nadīpāraṃ gaccheyya, ekā vā rattiṃ vippavaseyya, ekā vā gaṇamhā ohīyeyya, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun walks to the next village by herself or crosses a river by herself or spends the night apart by herself or lags behind her companions by herself, then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8845]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8846]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8847]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8848]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8849]="*Ekā vā gāmantaraṃ gaccheyyāti**Walks to the next village by herself:*";
P_HTM[8850]="*parikkhittassa gāmassa parikkhepaṃ paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti thullaccayassa,**if she crosses the boundary of an enclosed village with her first foot, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8851]="*dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If she then crosses it with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8852]="*Aparikkhittassa gāmassa upacāraṃ paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti thullaccayassa.**If she enters the vicinity of an unenclosed village with her first foot, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8853]="*Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If she then enters it with her second foot, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8854]="*Ekā vā nadīpāraṃ gaccheyyāti**Or crosses a river by herself:*";
P_HTM[8855]="*nadī nāma timaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādetvā yattha katthaci uttarantiyā bhikkhuniyā antaravāsako temiyati.**A river: wherever, after covering the three circles, the sarong gets wet when the nun is crossing.*";
P_HTM[8856]="*Paṭhamaṃ pādaṃ uttarantiyā āpatti thullaccayassa.**When she has crossed with the first foot, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8857]="*Dutiyaṃ pādaṃ uttarantiyā āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When she has crossed with the second foot, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8858]="*Ekā vā rattiṃ vippavaseyyāti**Or spends the night apart by herself:*";
P_HTM[8859]="*saha aruṇuggamanā dutiyikāya bhikkhuniyā hatthapāsaṃ vijahantiyā āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, at dawn, she is in the process of going beyond arm’s reach of her companion nun, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8860]="*Vijahite āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When she has gone beyond, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8861]="*Ekā vā gaṇamhā ohīyeyyāti**Or lags behind her companions by herself:*";
P_HTM[8862]="*agāmake araññe dutiyikāya bhikkhuniyā dassanūpacāraṃ vā savanūpacāraṃ vā vijahantiyā āpatti thullaccayassa.**if, in an uninhabited area, in the wilderness, she is in the process of going beyond the range of sight or the range of hearing of her companion nun, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8863]="*Vijahite āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When she has gone beyond, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8864]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[8865]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[8866]="*Paṭhamāpattikanti**An immediate offense:*";
P_HTM[8867]="*saha vatthujjhācārā āpajjati asamanubhāsanāya.**there is an offense as soon as the misconduct is committed, and no pressing is required.*";
P_HTM[8868]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[8869]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8870]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[8871]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8872]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8873]="*dutiyikā bhikkhunī pakkantā vā hoti vibbhantā vā kālaṅkatā vā pakkhasaṅkantā vā,**if her companion nun has left or disrobed or died or joined another faction;*";
P_HTM[8874]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[8875]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8876]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8877]="*Tatiyasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[8878]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[8879]="*4. Ukkhittakaosāraṇasikkhāpada**4. The training rule on reinstating one who has been ejected*";
P_HTM[8880]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8881]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī bhaṇḍanakārikā hoti kalahakārikā vivādakārikā bhassakārikā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārikā.**At that time the nun Caṇḍakāḷī was quarrelsome and argumentative, and she created legal issues in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8882]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī tassā kamme karīyamāne paṭikkosati.**But when a legal procedure was being done against her, the nun Thullanandā objected.*";
P_HTM[8883]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī gāmakaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Soon afterwards Thullanandā went to a village on some business.*";
P_HTM[8884]="*Atha kho bhikkhunisaṅgho—**The Sangha of nuns*";
P_HTM[8885]="*“thullanandā bhikkhunī pakkantā”ti, caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ āpattiyā adassane ukkhipi.**took the opportunity to eject Caṇḍakāḷī for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[8886]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī gāmake taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā punadeva sāvatthiṃ paccāgacchi.**When Thullanandā had finished her business in that village, she returned to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[8887]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā āgacchantiyā neva āsanaṃ paññapesi na pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakaṭhalikaṃ upanikkhipi na paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesi na pānīyena āpucchi.**On her return, Caṇḍakāḷī neither prepared a seat for her, nor set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, or water for washing the feet; and she did not go out to meet her to receive her bowl and robe, nor ask whether she wanted water to drink.*";
P_HTM[8888]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**Thullanandā asked her*";
P_HTM[8889]="*“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, mayi āgacchantiyā neva āsanaṃ paññapesi na pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakaṭhalikaṃ upanikkhipi na paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesi na pānīyena āpucchī”ti?**why she was acting like this.*";
P_HTM[8890]="*“Evañhetaṃ, ayye, hoti yathā taṃ anāthāyā”ti.**She replied, “That’s how it is, Venerable, when you don’t have a protector.”*";
P_HTM[8891]="*“Kissa pana tvaṃ, ayye, anāthā”ti?**“But how is it, Venerable, that you don’t have a protector?”*";
P_HTM[8892]="*“Imā maṃ, ayye, bhikkhuniyo—**“When the nuns knew*";
P_HTM[8893]="*‘ayaṃ anāthā appaññātā, natthi imissā kāci paṭivattā’ti, āpattiyā adassane ukkhipiṃsū”ti.**that no one would speak up for me because I am not esteemed by them and I didn’t have a protector, they ejected me for not recognizing an offense.”*";
P_HTM[8894]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—* **";
P_HTM[8895]="*“bālā etā abyattā etā, neva jānanti kammaṃ vā kammadosaṃ vā kammavipattiṃ vā kammasampattiṃ vā.**“They are incompetent fools. They don’t know about legal procedures or their flaws, nor what makes them fail or succeed.*";
P_HTM[8896]="*Mayaṃ kho jānāma kammampi kammadosampi kammavipattimpi kammasampattimpi.**But we know all these things.*";
P_HTM[8897]="*Mayaṃ kho akataṃ vā kammaṃ kāreyyāma kataṃ vā kammaṃ kopeyyāmā”ti, lahuṃ lahuṃ bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ sannipātetvā caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ osāresi.**We can get legal procedures done that haven’t been done, and we can get procedures that have been done overturned.” And she quickly gathered a sangha of nuns and reinstated the nun Caṇḍakāḷī.*";
P_HTM[8898]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8899]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāressatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā reinstate a nun who had been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, without first getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group?” …*";
P_HTM[8900]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāretī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[8901]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8902]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8903]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāressati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā reinstate a nun who had been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule, the Monastic Law, and the Teacher’s instruction, without first getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group?*";
P_HTM[8904]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8905]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8906]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī samaggena saṅghena ukkhittaṃ bhikkhuniṃ dhammena vinayena satthusāsanena anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghaṃ anaññāya gaṇassa chandaṃ osāreyya, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun, without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure and without the consent of the group, reinstates a nun who has been ejected by a unanimous Sangha in accordance with the rule and the Monastic Law and the Teacher’s instruction, then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8907]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8908]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8909]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8910]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8911]="*Samaggo nāma saṅgho**A unanimous Sangha:*";
P_HTM[8912]="*samānasaṃvāsako samānasīmāyaṃ ṭhito.**those belonging to the same Buddhist sect and staying within the same monastic boundary.*";
P_HTM[8913]="*Ukkhittā nāma**Who has been ejected:*";
P_HTM[8914]="*āpattiyā adassane vā appaṭikamme vā appaṭinissagge vā ukkhittā.**who has been ejected for not recognizing an offense, for not making amends, or for not giving up a bad view.*";
P_HTM[8915]="*Dhammena vinayenāti**In accordance with the rule and the Monastic Law:*";
P_HTM[8916]="*yena dhammena yena vinayena.**in accordance with that rule, in accordance with that Monastic Law.*";
P_HTM[8917]="*Satthusāsanenāti**In accordance with the Teacher’s instruction:*";
P_HTM[8918]="*jinasāsanena buddhasāsanena.**in accordance with the Conqueror’s instruction, in accordance with the Buddha’s instruction.*";
P_HTM[8919]="*Anapaloketvā kārakasaṅghanti**Without getting permission from the Sangha that did the legal procedure:*";
P_HTM[8920]="*kammakārakasaṅghaṃ anāpucchā.**without having asked permission of the Sangha that did the legal procedure of ejection.*";
P_HTM[8921]="*Anaññāya gaṇassa chandanti**Without the consent of the group:*";
P_HTM[8922]="*gaṇassa chandaṃ ajānitvā.**without being aware of any consent from the group.*";
P_HTM[8923]="*“Osāressāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to reinstate her, she searches for a group or establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8924]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ, dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā, kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct. After each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense. When the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8925]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[8926]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[8927]="*Paṭhamāpattikanti**An immediate offense:*";
P_HTM[8928]="*saha vatthujjhācārā āpajjati asamanubhāsanāya.**there is an offense as soon as the misconduct is committed, and no pressing is required.*";
P_HTM[8929]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[8930]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8931]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[8932]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8933]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā osāreti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she reinstates her, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8934]="*Dhammakamme vematikā osāreti āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she reinstates her, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8935]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā osāreti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she reinstates her, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8936]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8937]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8938]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8939]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8940]="*kammakārakasaṅghaṃ apaloketvā osāreti,**if she reinstates her after getting permission from the Sangha that did the procedure;*";
P_HTM[8941]="*gaṇassa chandaṃ jānitvā osāreti,**if she reinstates her with the consent of the group;*";
P_HTM[8942]="*vatte vattantiṃ osāreti,**if she reinstates one who is behaving properly;*";
P_HTM[8943]="*asante kammakārakasaṅghe osāreti,**if she reinstates her when the Sangha that did the procedure is unavailable;*";
P_HTM[8944]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[8945]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[8946]="*Catutthasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[8947]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[8948]="*5. Bhojanapaṭiggahaṇasikkhāpada**5. The training rule on receiving food*";
P_HTM[8949]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[8950]="*Tena kho pana samayena sundarīnandā bhikkhunī abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā.**At that time there was a beautiful nun called Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[8951]="*Manussā bhattagge sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ passitvā avassutā avassutāya sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā aggamaggāni bhojanāni denti.**When people saw her in the dining hall, they gave her the best food, both the donors and the recipient having lust.*";
P_HTM[8952]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī yāvadatthaṃ bhuñjati;**Sundarīnandā ate as much as she liked,*";
P_HTM[8953]="*aññā bhikkhuniyo na cittarūpaṃ labhanti.**but not so the other nuns.*";
P_HTM[8954]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[8955]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā sundarīnandā avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādissati bhuñjissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Sundarīnandā, being lustful, eat either fresh or cooked food after receiving it directly from a lustful man?” …*";
P_HTM[8956]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādati bhuñjatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Sundarīnandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[8957]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[8958]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[8959]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, sundarīnandā bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādissati bhuñjissati.**“How could Sundarīnandā, being lustful, eat either fresh or cooked food after receiving it directly from a lustful man?*";
P_HTM[8960]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[8961]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[8962]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī avassutā avassutassa purisapuggalassa hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a lustful nun eats fresh or cooked food after receiving it directly from a lustful man, then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[8963]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[8964]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[8965]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[8966]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[8967]="*Avassutā nāma**Lustful:*";
P_HTM[8968]="*sārattā apekkhavatī paṭibaddhacittā.**having lust, longing for, in love with.*";
P_HTM[8969]="*Avassuto nāma**Lustful:*";
P_HTM[8970]="*sāratto apekkhavā paṭibaddhacitto.**having lust, longing for, in love with.*";
P_HTM[8971]="*Purisapuggalo nāma**Man:*";
P_HTM[8972]="*manussapuriso, na yakkho na peto na tiracchānagato, viññū paṭibalo sārajjituṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of having lust.*";
P_HTM[8973]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[8974]="*pañca bhojanāni udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**apart from the five cooked foods, water, and tooth cleaners, the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[8975]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[8976]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[8977]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti thullaccayassa.**If she receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8978]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8979]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[8980]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[8981]="*Paṭhamāpattikanti**An immediate offense:*";
P_HTM[8982]="*saha vatthujjhācārā āpajjati asamanubhāsanāya.**there is an offense as soon as the misconduct is committed, and no pressing is required.*";
P_HTM[8983]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[8984]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[8985]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[8986]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[8987]="*Udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8988]="*Ekatoavassute “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If only the man has lust, and she receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8989]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti thullaccayassa.**For every mouthful, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8990]="*Udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8991]="*Ubhatoavassute yakkhassa vā petassa vā paṇḍakassa vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahassa vā hatthato “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If both of them have lust, and she receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it directly from a male spirit, a male ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a male animal in human form, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8992]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti thullaccayassa.**For every mouthful, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[8993]="*Udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8994]="*Ekatoavassute “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If only the male being has lust, and she receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8995]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8996]="*Udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[8997]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[8998]="*ubhatoanavassutā honti,**if both are without lust;*";
P_HTM[8999]="*“anavassuto”ti jānantī paṭiggaṇhāti,**if she receives, knowing that the man has no lust;*";
P_HTM[9000]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9001]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9002]="*Pañcamasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[9003]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[9004]="*6. Dutiyabhojanapaṭiggahaṇasikkhāpada**6. The second training rule on receiving food*";
P_HTM[9005]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9006]="*Tena kho pana samayena sundarīnandā bhikkhunī abhirūpā hoti dassanīyā pāsādikā.**At that time there was a beautiful nun called Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[9007]="*Manussā bhattagge sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ passitvā avassutā sundarīnandāya bhikkhuniyā aggamaggāni bhojanāni denti.**When people saw her in the dining hall, they were affected by lust, and they gave her the best food.*";
P_HTM[9008]="*Sundarīnandā bhikkhunī kukkuccāyantī na paṭiggaṇhāti.**Being afraid of wrongdoing, Sundarīnandā did not receive it.*";
P_HTM[9009]="*Anantarikā bhikkhunī sundarīnandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**The nun next to her said,*";
P_HTM[9010]="*“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, na paṭiggaṇhāsī”ti?**“Why didn’t you receive it, Venerable?”*";
P_HTM[9011]="*“Avassutā, ayye”ti.**“Because they have lust.”*";
P_HTM[9012]="*“Tvaṃ pana, ayye, avassutā”ti?**“But do you have lust?”*";
P_HTM[9013]="*“Nāhaṃ, ayye, avassutā”ti.**“No.”*";
P_HTM[9014]="*“Kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā.**“What can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, when you’re without it?*";
P_HTM[9015]="*Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā, bhuñja vā”ti.**Go on, Venerable, receive it with your own hands, and eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives you.”*";
P_HTM[9016]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9017]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could a nun say,*";
P_HTM[9018]="*‘kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā.**‘What can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, when you’re without it?*";
P_HTM[9019]="*Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā’”ti …pe…**Go on, Venerable, receive it with your own hands, and eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives you’?” …*";
P_HTM[9020]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī evaṃ vadeti—**“Is it true, monks, that a nun said this?”*";
P_HTM[9021]="*‘kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā yato tvaṃ anavassutā.* **";
P_HTM[9022]="*Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[9023]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9024]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9025]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could a nun say this?”*";
P_HTM[9026]="*‘kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā yato tvaṃ anavassutā;* **";
P_HTM[9027]="*iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9028]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9029]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9030]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī evaṃ vadeyya— ‘kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā’ti, ayampi bhikkhunī paṭhamāpattikaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**‘If a nun says, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it with your own hands and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives you,” then that nun too has committed an immediate offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[9031]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9032]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9033]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9034]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9035]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Says:*";
P_HTM[9036]="*“kiṃ te, ayye, eso purisapuggalo karissati avassuto vā anavassuto vā, yato tvaṃ anavassutā. Iṅgha, ayye, yaṃ te eso purisapuggalo deti khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā taṃ tvaṃ sahatthā paṭiggahetvā khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if she urges her on, saying, “Venerable, what can this man do to you, whether he has lust or not, if you’re without? Go on, Venerable, receive it with your own hands and then eat whatever fresh or cooked food he gives you,” then she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9037]="*Tassā vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, because of her statement, the other nun receives fresh or cooked food with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9038]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti thullaccayassa.**For every mouthful, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9039]="*Bhojanapariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**At the end of the meal, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9040]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[9041]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[9042]="*Paṭhamāpattikanti**An immediate offense:*";
P_HTM[9043]="*saha vatthujjhācārā āpajjati asamanubhāsanāya.**there is an offense as soon as the misconduct is committed, and no pressing is required.*";
P_HTM[9044]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[9045]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9046]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[9047]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9048]="*Udakadantaponaṃ “paṭiggaṇhā”ti uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she urges her on to receive water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9049]="*Tassā vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, because of her statement, the other nun receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9050]="*Ekatoavassute yakkhassa vā petassa vā paṇḍakassa vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahassa vā hatthato khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā “khāda vā bhuñja vā”ti uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, when only the male being has lust, she urges her on to eat fresh or cooked food received directly from a male spirit, a male ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a male animal in human form, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9051]="*Tassā vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, because of her statement, the other nun receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9052]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9053]="*Bhojanapariyosāne āpatti thullaccayassa.**At the end of the meal, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9054]="*Udakadantaponaṃ paṭiggaṇhāti uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she urges her on to receive water or a tooth cleaner, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9055]="*Tassā vacanena “khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, because of her statement, the other nun receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9056]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9057]="*“anavassuto”ti jānantī uyyojeti,**if she urges her on, knowing that he has no lust;*";
P_HTM[9058]="*“kupitā na paṭiggaṇhātī”ti uyyojeti,**if she urges her on, thinking that she is not receiving because of anger;*";
P_HTM[9059]="*“kulānuddayatāya na paṭiggaṇhātī”ti uyyojeti,**if she urges her on, thinking that she is not receiving because of compassion for the family;*";
P_HTM[9060]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9061]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9062]="*Chaṭṭhasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[9063]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[9064]="*10. Sikkhaṃpaccācikkhaṇasikkhāpada**10. The training rule on renouncing the training*";
P_HTM[9065]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[9066]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍitvā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**the nun Caṇḍakāḷī had argued with the nuns. In anger she said this:*";
P_HTM[9067]="*“buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi, dhammaṃ paccācikkhāmi, saṅghaṃ paccācikkhāmi, sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.**“I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training!*";
P_HTM[9068]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro, santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī”ti.**The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics. There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.”*";
P_HTM[9069]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9070]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā caṇḍakāḷī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could the nun Caṇḍakāḷī say this in anger?*";
P_HTM[9071]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.* **";
P_HTM[9072]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro, santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’”ti …pe…**…*";
P_HTM[9073]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Caṇḍakāḷī said this in anger?”*";
P_HTM[9074]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.* **";
P_HTM[9075]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro, santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[9076]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9077]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9078]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could the nun Caṇḍakāḷī say this in anger?*";
P_HTM[9079]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.* **";
P_HTM[9080]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro, santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9081]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9082]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9083]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeyya—**‘If a nun says in anger,*";
P_HTM[9084]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi, dhammaṃ paccācikkhāmi, saṅghaṃ paccācikkhāmi, sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi. Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro. Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’ti,**“I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training! The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics. There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them,”*";
P_HTM[9085]="*sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi evamassa vacanīyā—**then the nuns should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[9086]="*‘māyye, kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca— buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi, dhammaṃ paccācikkhāmi, saṅghaṃ paccācikkhāmi, sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi. Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro. Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmīti, abhiramāyye, svākkhāto dhammo; cara brahmacariyaṃ sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāyā’ti.**“Venerable, don’t say such things in anger, ‘I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training! The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics. There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.’ Take delight, Venerable; the Teaching is well proclaimed. Practice the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[9087]="*Evañca sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyya, sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If that nun continues as before, the nuns should press her up to three times to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9088]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsīyamānā taṃ paṭinissajjeyya iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she then stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9089]="*no ce paṭinissajjeyya, ayampi bhikkhunī yāvatatiyakaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**If she does not stop, then after the third announcement that nun too has committed an offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[9090]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9091]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9092]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9093]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9094]="*Kupitā anattamanāti**In anger:*";
P_HTM[9095]="*anabhiraddhā āhatacittā khilajātā.**discontent, having hatred, hostile.*";
P_HTM[9096]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Says:*";
P_HTM[9097]="*“buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi. Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro. Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī”ti.**“I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training! The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics. There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.”*";
P_HTM[9098]="*Sā bhikkhunīti**Her:*";
P_HTM[9099]="*yā sā evaṃvādinī bhikkhunī.**that nun who speaks thus.*";
P_HTM[9100]="*Bhikkhunīhīti**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[9101]="*aññāhi bhikkhunīhi. Yā passanti yā suṇanti tāhi vattabbā—**Other nuns who see it or hear about it. They should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[9102]="*“māyye, kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, don’t say such things in anger:*";
P_HTM[9103]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.**‘I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training!*";
P_HTM[9104]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro.**The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics.*";
P_HTM[9105]="*Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’ti.**There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.’*";
P_HTM[9106]="*Abhiramāyye, svākkhāto dhammo;**Take delight, Venerable; the Teaching is well proclaimed.*";
P_HTM[9107]="*cara brahmacariyaṃ sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāyā”ti.**Practice the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[9108]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**And they should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[9109]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9110]="*Sace paṭinissajjati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ,**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9111]="*no ce paṭinissajjati āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9112]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9113]="*Sā bhikkhunī saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—**That nun, even if she has to be pulled into the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[9114]="*“māyye, kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, don’t say such things in anger:*";
P_HTM[9115]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.**‘I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training!*";
P_HTM[9116]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro.**The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics.*";
P_HTM[9117]="*Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’ti.**There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.’*";
P_HTM[9118]="*Abhiramāyye, svākkhāto dhammo;**Take delight, Venerable; the Teaching is well proclaimed.*";
P_HTM[9119]="*cara brahmacariyaṃ sammā dukkhassa antakiriyāyā”ti.**Practice the spiritual life for the complete ending of suffering.”*";
P_HTM[9120]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**They should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[9121]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9122]="*Sace paṭinissajjati iccetaṃ kusalaṃ,**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9123]="*no ce paṭinissajjati āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9124]="*Sā bhikkhunī samanubhāsitabbā.**Should press her:*";
P_HTM[9125]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbā.**“And, monks, she should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[9126]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9127]="*“Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9128]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**The nun so-and-so says this in anger:*";
P_HTM[9129]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi, dhammaṃ paccācikkhāmi, saṅghaṃ paccācikkhāmi, sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.**“I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training!*";
P_HTM[9130]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro.**The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics.*";
P_HTM[9131]="*Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’ti.**There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.”*";
P_HTM[9132]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on saying it.*";
P_HTM[9133]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9134]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9135]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9136]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**The nun so-and-so says this in anger:*";
P_HTM[9137]="*‘buddhaṃ paccācikkhāmi …pe… sikkhaṃ paccācikkhāmi.**“I renounce the Buddha, I renounce the Teaching, I renounce the Sangha, I renounce the training!*";
P_HTM[9138]="*Kinnumāva samaṇiyo yā samaṇiyo sakyadhītaro.**The Sakyan daughters are not the only monastics.*";
P_HTM[9139]="*Santaññāpi samaṇiyo lajjiniyo kukkuccikā sikkhākāmā, tāsāhaṃ santike brahmacariyaṃ carissāmī’ti.**There are other monastics who have a sense of conscience, who are afraid of wrongdoing and fond of the training. I’ll practice the spiritual life with them.”*";
P_HTM[9140]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on saying it.*";
P_HTM[9141]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9142]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of pressing her to make her stop should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9143]="*yassā nakkhamati sā, bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9144]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9145]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9146]="*Samanubhaṭṭhā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha has pressed nun so-and-so to stop.*";
P_HTM[9147]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9148]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9149]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9150]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9151]="*Saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpajjantiyā ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ, dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā paṭippassambhanti.**For one who commits the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong conduct and the serious offenses are annulled.*";
P_HTM[9152]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[9153]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[9154]="*Yāvatatiyakanti**After the third announcement:*";
P_HTM[9155]="*yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya āpajjati, na saha vatthujjhācārā.**there is an offense when she has been pressed for the third time, not as soon as the misconduct has been committed.*";
P_HTM[9156]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[9157]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9158]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[9159]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9160]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9161]="*Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9162]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9163]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9164]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9165]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9166]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9167]="*asamanubhāsantiyā,**if she has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[9168]="*paṭinissajjantiyā,**if she stops;*";
P_HTM[9169]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9170]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9171]="*Sattamasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[9172]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[9173]="*11. Adhikaraṇakupitasikkhāpada**11. The training rule on being angry about a legal issue*";
P_HTM[9174]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9175]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**At that time the nun Caṇḍakāḷī was angry that a legal issue had been decided against her, saying,*";
P_HTM[9176]="*“chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, dosagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, mohagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo”ti.**“The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9177]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9178]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā caṇḍakāḷī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could Venerable Caṇḍakāḷī say such things just because she is angry that a legal issue has been decided against her?”*";
P_HTM[9179]="*‘chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo’”ti …pe…* **";
P_HTM[9180]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Caṇḍakāḷī said this because she was angry?”*";
P_HTM[9181]="*‘chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo’”ti?* **";
P_HTM[9182]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9183]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9184]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could Venerable Caṇḍakāḷī say such things just because she is angry that a legal issue has been decided against her?*";
P_HTM[9185]="*‘chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo’ti.* **";
P_HTM[9186]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9187]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9188]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeyya—**‘If a nun is angry because a legal issue has been decided against her, saying,*";
P_HTM[9189]="*‘chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, dosagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, mohagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo, bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo’ti,**“The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear,”*";
P_HTM[9190]="*sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi evamassa vacanīyā—**then the nuns should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[9191]="*‘māyye, kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, just because you’re angry that a legal issue has been decided against you, don’t say,*";
P_HTM[9192]="*chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo dosagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo mohagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyoti.**‘The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.’*";
P_HTM[9193]="*Ayyā kho chandāpi gaccheyya, dosāpi gaccheyya, mohāpi gaccheyya, bhayāpi gaccheyyā’ti.**Perhaps it’s you who are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9194]="*Evañca sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyya, sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If that nun continues as before, the nuns should press her up to three times to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9195]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsīyamānā taṃ paṭinissajjeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she then stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9196]="*no ce paṭinissajjeyya, ayampi bhikkhunī yāvatatiyakaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**If she does not stop, then after the third announcement that nun too has committed an offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[9197]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9198]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9199]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9200]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9201]="*Kismiñcideva adhikaraṇeti**A legal issue:*";
P_HTM[9202]="*adhikaraṇaṃ nāma cattāri adhikaraṇāni— vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**there are four kinds of legal issues: legal issues arising from disputes, legal issues arising from accusations, legal issues arising from offenses, legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[9203]="*Paccākatā nāma**Has been decided against her:*";
P_HTM[9204]="*parājitā vuccati.**what is meant is that she has lost.*";
P_HTM[9205]="*Kupitā anattamanāti**Angry:*";
P_HTM[9206]="*anabhiraddhā āhatacittā khilajātā.**discontent, having hatred, hostile.*";
P_HTM[9207]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Saying:*";
P_HTM[9208]="*“chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo”ti.**“The nuns are acting out of favoritism … and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9209]="*Sā bhikkhunīti**Her:*";
P_HTM[9210]="*yā sā evaṃvādinī bhikkhunī.**that nun who speaks thus.*";
P_HTM[9211]="*Bhikkhunīhīti**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[9212]="*aññāhi bhikkhunīhi. Yā passanti yā suṇanti tāhi vattabbā—**Other nuns who see it or hear about it. They should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[9213]="*“māyye, kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, just because you’re angry that a legal issue has been decided against you, don’t say,*";
P_HTM[9214]="*‘chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo’ti.**‘The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.’*";
P_HTM[9215]="*Ayyā kho chandāpi gaccheyya …pe… bhayāpi gaccheyyā”ti.**Perhaps it’s you who are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9216]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**And they should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[9217]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9218]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9219]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9220]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9221]="*Sā bhikkhunī saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—**That nun, even if she has to be pulled into the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[9222]="*“māyye, kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, just because you’re angry that a legal issue has been decided against you, don’t say,*";
P_HTM[9223]="*‘chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo’ti.**‘The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.’*";
P_HTM[9224]="*Ayyā kho chandāpi gaccheyya …pe… bhayāpi gaccheyyā”ti.**Perhaps it’s you who are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9225]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**They should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[9226]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9227]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9228]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9229]="*Sā bhikkhunī samanubhāsitabbā.**Should press her:*";
P_HTM[9230]="*“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbā.**“And, monks, she should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[9231]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9232]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho. Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen. The nun so-and-so, because she is angry that a legal issue has been decided against her, says this:*";
P_HTM[9233]="*“chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo… pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo”ti.**“The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9234]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on saying it.*";
P_HTM[9235]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9236]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9237]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9238]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī kismiñcideva adhikaraṇe paccākatā kupitā anattamanā evaṃ vadeti—**The nun so-and-so, because she is angry that a legal issue has been decided against her, says this:*";
P_HTM[9239]="*“chandagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo …pe… bhayagāminiyo ca bhikkhuniyo”ti.**“The nuns are acting out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, and fear.”*";
P_HTM[9240]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on saying it.*";
P_HTM[9241]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9242]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of pressing her to make her stop should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9243]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9244]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9245]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9246]="*Samanubhaṭṭhā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha has pressed nun so-and-so to stop.*";
P_HTM[9247]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9248]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9249]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9250]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9251]="*Saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpajjantiyā ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**For one who commits the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong conduct*";
P_HTM[9252]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā paṭippassambhanti.**and the serious offenses are annulled.*";
P_HTM[9253]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[9254]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[9255]="*Yāvatatiyakanti**After the third announcement:*";
P_HTM[9256]="*yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya āpajjati, na saha vatthujjhācārā.**there is an offense when she has been pressed for the third time, not as soon as the misconduct has been committed.*";
P_HTM[9257]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[9258]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9259]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[9260]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9261]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9262]="*Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9263]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9264]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9265]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9266]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9267]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9268]="*asamanubhāsantiyā,**if she has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[9269]="*paṭinissajjantiyā,**if she stops;*";
P_HTM[9270]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9271]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9272]="*Aṭṭhamasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eleventh offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[9273]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[9274]="*12. Pāpasamācārasikkhāpada**12. The training rule on bad behavior*";
P_HTM[9275]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9276]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā antevāsikā bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**At that time the nuns who were the pupils of the nun Thullanandā were socializing and behaving badly, had a bad reputation, and were harassing the Sangha of nuns and hiding each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9277]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9278]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā viharissanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā”ti …pe…**“How can nuns behave in this way?” …*";
P_HTM[9279]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns are behaving like this?”*";
P_HTM[9280]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9281]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[9282]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā viharissanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**“How can nuns behave in this way?*";
P_HTM[9283]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9284]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9285]="*“Bhikkhuniyo paneva saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**‘If nuns socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses,*";
P_HTM[9286]="*Tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīhi evamassu vacanīyā—**then the nuns should correct them like this:*";
P_HTM[9287]="*‘bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**“Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9288]="*Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī’ti.**Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[9289]="*Evañca tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyyuṃ, tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If those nuns still continue as before, the nuns should press them up to three times to make them stop.*";
P_HTM[9290]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsīyamānā taṃ paṭinissajjeyyuṃ, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If they then stop, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9291]="*no ce paṭinissajjeyyuṃ, imāpi bhikkhuniyo yāvatatiyakaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**If they do not stop, then after the third announcement those nuns too have committed an offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[9292]="*Bhikkhuniyo panevāti**Nuns:*";
P_HTM[9293]="*upasampannāyo vuccanti.**what is meant is that they are fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[9294]="*Saṃsaṭṭhā viharantīti**Socialize:*";
P_HTM[9295]="*saṃsaṭṭhā nāma ananulomikena kāyikavācasikena saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti.**they socialize with improper bodily and verbal action.*";
P_HTM[9296]="*Pāpācārāti**Behave badly:*";
P_HTM[9297]="*pāpakena ācārena samannāgatā.**having bad behavior.*";
P_HTM[9298]="*Pāpasaddāti**Have a bad reputation:*";
P_HTM[9299]="*pāpakena kittisaddena abbhuggatā.**a bad reputation has spread about them.*";
P_HTM[9300]="*Pāpasilokāti**Are notorious:*";
P_HTM[9301]="*pāpakena micchājīvena jīvitaṃ kappenti.**they make a living by means of a bad and wrong livelihood.*";
P_HTM[9302]="*Bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikāti**Harass the Sangha of nuns:*";
P_HTM[9303]="*aññamaññissā kamme karīyamāne paṭikkosanti.**they object on each other’s behalf when a legal procedure is being carried out against them.*";
P_HTM[9304]="*Aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikāti**Hide each other’s offenses:*";
P_HTM[9305]="*aññamaññaṃ vajjaṃ paṭicchādenti.**they hide one another’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9306]="*Tā bhikkhuniyoti**Them:*";
P_HTM[9307]="*yā tā saṃsaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo.**those nuns who socialize.*";
P_HTM[9308]="*Bhikkhunīhīti**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[9309]="*aññāhi bhikkhunīhi. Yā passanti yā suṇanti tāhi vattabbā—**Other nuns who see it or hear about it. They should correct them like this:*";
P_HTM[9310]="*“bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**“Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9311]="*Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[9312]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**And they should correct them a second*";
P_HTM[9313]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9314]="*Sace paṭinissajjanti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If they stop, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9315]="*no ce paṭinissajjanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they do not stop, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9316]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9317]="*Tā bhikkhuniyo saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—**Those nuns, even if they have to be pulled into the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[9318]="*“bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**“Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9319]="*Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[9320]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**They should correct them a second*";
P_HTM[9321]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9322]="*Sace paṭinissajjanti, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If they stop, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9323]="*no ce paṭinissajjanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they do not stop, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9324]="*Tā bhikkhuniyo samanubhāsitabbā.**Should press them:*";
P_HTM[9325]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbā.**“And, monks, they should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[9326]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9327]="*“Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9328]="*Itthannāmā ca itthannāmā ca bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**The nuns so-and-so and so-and-so socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9329]="*Tā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjanti.**And they keep on doing it.*";
P_HTM[9330]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhuniyo samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press them to make them stop.*";
P_HTM[9331]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9332]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9333]="*Itthannāmā ca itthannāmā ca bhikkhuniyo saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**The nuns so-and-so and so-and-so socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9334]="*Tā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjanti.**And they keep on doing it.*";
P_HTM[9335]="*Saṅgho itthannāmañca itthannāmañca bhikkhuniyo samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses them to make them stop.*";
P_HTM[9336]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya ca itthannāmāya ca bhikkhunīnaṃ samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of pressing them to make them stop should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9337]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9338]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9339]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9340]="*Samanubhaṭṭhā saṅghena, itthannāmā ca itthannāmā ca bhikkhuniyo tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha has pressed the nuns so-and-so and so-and-so to stop.*";
P_HTM[9341]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9342]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ,**After the motion, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9343]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā,**After each of the first two announcements, they commit a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9344]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When the last announcement is finished, they commit an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9345]="*Saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpajjantīnaṃ ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā paṭippassambhanti.**If they commit the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong conduct and the serious offenses are annulled.*";
P_HTM[9346]="*Dve tisso ekato samanubhāsitabbā. Tatuttari na samanubhāsitabbā.**Two or three may be pressed together, but not more than that.*";
P_HTM[9347]="*Imāpi bhikkhuniyoti**Those nuns too:*";
P_HTM[9348]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccanti.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[9349]="*Yāvatatiyakanti**After the third announcement:*";
P_HTM[9350]="*yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya āpajjanti, na saha vatthujjhācārā.**there is an offense when they have been pressed for the third time, not as soon as the misconduct has been committed.*";
P_HTM[9351]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[9352]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9353]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[9354]="*…pe… tenapi vuccati saṅghādisesoti.**… Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9355]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjanti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and they perceive it as such, and they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9356]="*Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭinissajjanti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but they are unsure of it, and they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9357]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjanti, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but they perceive it as illegitimate, and they do not stop, they commit an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9358]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but they perceive it as legitimate, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9359]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but they are unsure of it, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9360]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and they perceive it as such, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9361]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9362]="*asamanubhāsantīnaṃ,**if she has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[9363]="*paṭinissajjantīnaṃ,**if she stops;*";
P_HTM[9364]="*ummattikānaṃ,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9365]="*ādikammikānanti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9366]="*Navamasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The twelfth offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[9367]="*127. Saṅghādisesakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing suspension *";
P_HTM[9368]="*Saṅghādisesā 13: Dutiyapāpasamācārasikkhāpada**13. The second training rule on bad behavior*";
P_HTM[9369]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9370]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī saṅghena samanubhaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo evaṃ vadeti—**At that time the nun Thullanandā had been pressed by the Sangha. She then said to the nuns,*";
P_HTM[9371]="*“saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**“But, Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9372]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha.**There are other nuns in the Sangha who have such behavior, reputation, and notoriety,  and who harass the Sangha of nuns and hide each other’s offenses. The Sangha says nothing to them.*";
P_HTM[9373]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāya paribhavena akkhantiyā vebhassiyā dubbalyā evamāha— ‘bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī’”ti.**It’s because of disrespect, contempt, impatience, and slander, and because you are weak that the Sangha says to you, ‘Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses. Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.’”*";
P_HTM[9374]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9375]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā saṅghena samanubhaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could Venerable Thullanandā, after being pressed by the Sangha, say this to the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[9376]="*saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**…*";
P_HTM[9377]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo …pe…* **";
P_HTM[9378]="*viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetīti” …pe…* **";
P_HTM[9379]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī saṅghena samanubhaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo evaṃ vadeti—**“Is it true, monks, that after being pressed by the Sangha, the nun Thullanandā said this to the nuns?”*";
P_HTM[9380]="*saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.* **";
P_HTM[9381]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha.* **";
P_HTM[9382]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāya paribhavena akkhantiyā vebhassiyā dubbalyā evamāha— bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[9383]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9384]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9385]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī saṅghena samanubhaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo evaṃ vakkhati—**“How could the nun Thullanandā, after being pressed by the Sangha, say this to the nuns?*";
P_HTM[9386]="*saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.* **";
P_HTM[9387]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo …pe…* **";
P_HTM[9388]="*viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetīti.* **";
P_HTM[9389]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9390]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9391]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī evaṃ vadeyya—**‘If a nun says,*";
P_HTM[9392]="*‘saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**“Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9393]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha.**There are other nuns in the Sangha who have such behavior, reputation, and notoriety, and who harass the Sangha of nuns and hide each other’s offenses. The Sangha says nothing to them.*";
P_HTM[9394]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāya paribhavena akkhantiyā vebhassiyā dubbalyā evamāha— bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī’ti.**It’s because of disrespect, contempt, impatience, and slander, and because you are weak that the Sangha says to you, ‘Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses. Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters,’”*";
P_HTM[9395]="*Sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi evamassa vacanīyā—**then the nuns should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[9396]="*‘mā, ayye, evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, don’t say such things:*";
P_HTM[9397]="*saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**‘Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9398]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha.**There are other nuns in the Sangha who have such behavior, reputation, and notoriety, and who harass the Sangha of nuns and hide each other’s offenses. The Sangha says nothing to them.*";
P_HTM[9399]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāya paribhavena akkhantiyā vebhassiyā dubbalyā evamāha— bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī’ti.**It’s because of disrespect, contempt, impatience, and slander, and because you are weak that the Sangha says to you, “Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses. Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”’”*";
P_HTM[9400]="*Evañca sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyya, sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If that nun continues as before, the nuns should press her up to three times to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9401]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsīyamānā taṃ paṭinissajjeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she then stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9402]="*no ce paṭinissajjeyya, ayampi bhikkhunī yāvatatiyakaṃ dhammaṃ āpannā nissāraṇīyaṃ saṅghādisesan”ti.**If she does not stop, then after the third announcement that nun too has committed an offense entailing sending away and suspension.’”*";
P_HTM[9403]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9404]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9405]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9406]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9407]="*Evaṃ vadeyyāti—**Says:*";
P_HTM[9408]="*“saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**“Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9409]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā. Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha”.**There are other nuns in the Sangha who have such behavior, reputation, and notoriety, and who harass the Sangha of nuns and hide each other’s offenses. The Sangha says nothing to them.”*";
P_HTM[9410]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāyāti**It’s because of disrespect that the Sangha … to you:*";
P_HTM[9411]="*avaññāya.**because of despising.*";
P_HTM[9412]="*Paribhavenāti**Because of contempt:*";
P_HTM[9413]="*pāribhabyatā.**because of contemptuousness.*";
P_HTM[9414]="*Akkhantiyāti**Because of impatience:*";
P_HTM[9415]="*kopena.**because of irritation.*";
P_HTM[9416]="*Vebhassiyāti**Because of slander:*";
P_HTM[9417]="*vibhassīkatā.**Because of slandering.*";
P_HTM[9418]="*Dubbalyāti**Because … weak:*";
P_HTM[9419]="*apakkhatā.**Because of lack of supporters.*";
P_HTM[9420]="*Evamāha—**Says:*";
P_HTM[9421]="*“bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**“Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9422]="*Viciccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[9423]="*Sā bhikkhunīti**Her:*";
P_HTM[9424]="*yā sā evaṃvādinī bhikkhunī.**that nun who speaks thus.*";
P_HTM[9425]="*Bhikkhunīhīti**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[9426]="*aññāhi bhikkhunīhi. Yā passanti yā suṇanti tāhi vattabbā—**Other nuns who see it or hear about it. They should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[9427]="*“māyye, evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, don’t say such things:*";
P_HTM[9428]="*‘saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**‘Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9429]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo …pe…**There are other nuns in the Sangha …*";
P_HTM[9430]="*viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī’”ti.**“… Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”’”*";
P_HTM[9431]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**And they should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[9432]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9433]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9434]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9435]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9436]="*Sā bhikkhunī saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—**That nun, even if she has to be pulled into the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[9437]="*“māyye, evaṃ avaca—**“Venerable, don’t say such things:*";
P_HTM[9438]="*‘saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha. Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**‘Venerables, you should socialize. Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9439]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo …pe…**There are other nuns in the Sangha …*";
P_HTM[9440]="*viviccathāyye. Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī’”ti.**“… Be secluded, Venerables. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”’”*";
P_HTM[9441]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**They should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[9442]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[9443]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[9444]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9445]="*Sā bhikkhunī samanubhāsitabbā.**Should press her:*";
P_HTM[9446]="*“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbā.**“And, monks, she should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[9447]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9448]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9449]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī saṅghena samanubhaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo evaṃ vadeti—**The nun so-and-so, after being pressed by the Sangha, says this to the nuns,*";
P_HTM[9450]="*“saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha.**“Venerables, you should socialize.*";
P_HTM[9451]="*Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9452]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**There are other nuns in the Sangha who have such behavior, reputation, and notoriety, and who harass the Sangha of nuns and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9453]="*Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha.**The Sangha says nothing to them.*";
P_HTM[9454]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāya paribhavena akkhantiyā vebhassiyā dubbalyā evamāha—**It’s because of disrespect, contempt, impatience, and slander, and because you are weak that the Sangha says to you,*";
P_HTM[9455]="*bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**‘Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9456]="*Viviccathāyye.**Be secluded, Venerables.*";
P_HTM[9457]="*Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.’”*";
P_HTM[9458]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on saying it.*";
P_HTM[9459]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9460]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[9461]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9462]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī saṅghena samanubhaṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo evaṃ vadeti—**The nun so-and-so, after being pressed by the Sangha, says this to the nuns,*";
P_HTM[9463]="*“saṃsaṭṭhāva, ayye, tumhe viharatha.**“Venerables, you should socialize.*";
P_HTM[9464]="*Mā tumhe nānā viharittha.**Don’t live separately.*";
P_HTM[9465]="*Santi saṅghe aññāpi bhikkhuniyo evācārā evaṃsaddā evaṃsilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**There are other nuns in the Sangha who have such behavior, reputation, and notoriety, and who harass the Sangha of nuns and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9466]="*Tā saṅgho na kiñci āha.**The Sangha says nothing to them.*";
P_HTM[9467]="*Tumhaññeva saṅgho uññāya paribhavena akkhantiyā vebhassiyā dubbalyā evamāha—**It’s because of disrespect, contempt, impatience, and slander, and because you are weak that the Sangha says to you,*";
P_HTM[9468]="*bhaginiyo kho saṃsaṭṭhā viharanti pāpācārā pāpasaddā pāpasilokā, bhikkhunisaṅghassa vihesikā, aññamaññissā vajjappaṭicchādikā.**‘Sisters, you socialize, behave badly, have a bad reputation, are notorious, harass the Sangha of nuns, and hide each other’s offenses.*";
P_HTM[9469]="*Viviccathāyye.**Be secluded, Venerables.*";
P_HTM[9470]="*Vivekaññeva bhaginīnaṃ saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.’”*";
P_HTM[9471]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on saying it.*";
P_HTM[9472]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[9473]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of pressing her to make her stop should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[9474]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[9475]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9476]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[9477]="*Samanubhaṭṭhā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha has pressed nun so-and-so to stop.*";
P_HTM[9478]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[9479]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ,**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9480]="*dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā,**After each of the first two announcements, she commits a serious offense.*";
P_HTM[9481]="*kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**When the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9482]="*Saṅghādisesaṃ ajjhāpajjantiyā ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ, dvīhi kammavācāhi thullaccayā paṭippassambhanti.**For one who commits the offense entailing suspension, the offense of wrong conduct and the serious offenses are annulled.*";
P_HTM[9483]="*Ayampīti**That too:*";
P_HTM[9484]="*purimāyo upādāya vuccati.**this is said with reference to the preceding offenses.*";
P_HTM[9485]="*Yāvatatiyakanti**After the third announcement:*";
P_HTM[9486]="*yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsanāya āpajjati, na sahavatthujjhācārā.**there is an offense when she has been pressed for the third time, not as soon as the misconduct has been committed.*";
P_HTM[9487]="*Nissāraṇīyanti**Entailing sending away:*";
P_HTM[9488]="*saṅghamhā nissārīyati.**she is sent away from the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9489]="*Saṅghādisesoti**Suspension:*";
P_HTM[9490]="*saṅghova tassā āpattiyā mānattaṃ deti, mūlāya paṭikassati, abbheti, na sambahulā na ekā bhikkhunī. Tena vuccati “saṅghādiseso”ti.**only the Sangha gives the trial period for that offense, sends back to the beginning, and rehabilitates—not several nuns, not an individual nun. Therefore it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9491]="*Tasseva āpattinikāyassa nāmakammaṃ adhivacanaṃ, tenapi vuccati “saṅghādiseso”ti.**This is the name and designation of this class of offense. Therefore, too, it is called an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9492]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9493]="*Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9494]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti saṅghādisesassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing suspension.*";
P_HTM[9495]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9496]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9497]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9498]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9499]="*asamanubhāsantiyā,**if she has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[9500]="*paṭinissajjantiyā,**if she stops;*";
P_HTM[9501]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9502]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9503]="*Dasamasaṅghādisesasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The thirteenth offense entailing suspension is finished.*";
P_HTM[9504]="*Kuladūsakasikkhāpada* **";
P_HTM[9505]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, sattarasa saṅghādisesā dhammā—**“Venerables, the seventeen rules on suspension have been recited,*";
P_HTM[9506]="*nava paṭhamāpattikā, aṭṭha yāvatatiyakā.**nine being immediate offenses, eight after the third announcement.*";
P_HTM[9507]="*Yesaṃ bhikkhunī aññataraṃ vā aññataraṃ vā āpajjati, tāya bhikkhuniyā ubhatosaṅghe pakkhamānattaṃ caritabbaṃ.**If a nun commits any one of them, she must undertake a trial period for a half-month toward both Sanghas.*";
P_HTM[9508]="*Ciṇṇamānattā bhikkhunī yattha siyā vīsatigaṇo bhikkhunisaṅgho tattha sā bhikkhunī abbhetabbā.**When this is completed, she is to be rehabilitated wherever there is a sangha of at least twenty nuns.*";
P_HTM[9509]="*Ekāyapi ce ūno vīsatigaṇo bhikkhunisaṅgho taṃ bhikkhuniṃ abbheyya.**If that nun is rehabilitated by a sangha of nuns of even one less than twenty,*";
P_HTM[9510]="*Sā ca bhikkhunī anabbhitā, tā ca bhikkhuniyo gārayhā, ayaṃ tattha sāmīci.**then that nun is not rehabilitated and those nuns are at fault. This is proper procedure.*";
P_HTM[9511]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[9512]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[9513]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[9514]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[9515]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[9516]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[9517]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[9518]="*Sattarasakaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The group of seventeen is finished.*";
P_HTM[9519]="*Bhikkhunivibhaṅge saṅghādisesakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing suspension in the nuns’ analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[9520]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9521]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9522]="*1. Pattasannicayasikkhāpada**1. The training rule on collections of almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9523]="*Ime kho panāyyāyo tiṃsa nissaggiyā pācittiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these thirty rules on relinquishment and confession come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[9524]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9525]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo bahū patte sannicayaṃ karonti.**At that time the nuns from the group of six had collected a large number of almsbowls.*";
P_HTM[9526]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized those nuns,*";
P_HTM[9527]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo bahū patte sannicayaṃ karissanti, pattavāṇijjaṃ vā bhikkhuniyo karissanti, āmattikāpaṇaṃ vā pasāressantī”ti.**“How can the nuns collect a large number of bowls? Will they start up as bowl merchants or set up a bowl shop?”*";
P_HTM[9528]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[9529]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized those nuns,*";
P_HTM[9530]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo pattasannicayaṃ karissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six collect bowls?” …*";
P_HTM[9531]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo pattasannicayaṃ karontī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[9532]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9533]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[9534]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo pattasannicayaṃ karissanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six collect bowls?*";
P_HTM[9535]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9536]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9537]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī pattasannicayaṃ kareyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun collects almsbowls, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9538]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9539]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9540]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9541]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9542]="*Patto nāma**An almsbowl:*";
P_HTM[9543]="*dve pattā— ayopatto, mattikāpatto.**there are two kinds of bowls: the iron bowl and the ceramic bowl.*";
P_HTM[9544]="*Tayo pattassa vaṇṇā— ukkaṭṭho patto, majjhimo patto, omako patto.**And there are three grades of bowl: the large bowl, the medium bowl, and the small bowl.*";
P_HTM[9545]="*Ukkaṭṭho nāma patto**The large bowl:*";
P_HTM[9546]="*aḍḍhāḷhakodanaṃ gaṇhāti catubhāgaṃ khādanaṃ tadupiyaṃ byañjanaṃ.**it takes half an _āḷhaka_ measure of boiled rice, a fourth part of fresh food, and a suitable amount of curry.*";
P_HTM[9547]="*Majjhimo nāma patto**The medium bowl:*";
P_HTM[9548]="*nāḷikodanaṃ gaṇhāti catubhāgaṃ khādanaṃ tadupiyaṃ byañjanaṃ.**it takes a _nāḷika_ measure of boiled rice, a fourth part of fresh food, and a suitable amount of curry.*";
P_HTM[9549]="*Omako nāma patto**The small bowl:*";
P_HTM[9550]="*patthodanaṃ gaṇhāti catubhāgaṃ khādanaṃ tadupiyaṃ byañjanaṃ.**it takes a _pattha_ measure of boiled rice, a fourth part of fresh food, and a suitable amount of curry.*";
P_HTM[9551]="*Tato ukkaṭṭho apatto omako apatto.**Anything larger than this is not a bowl, nor anything smaller.*";
P_HTM[9552]="*Sannicayaṃ kareyyāti**Collects:*";
P_HTM[9553]="*anadhiṭṭhito avikappito.**almsbowls that have neither been determined nor transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[9554]="*Nissaggiyo hotīti**Entailing relinquishment:*";
P_HTM[9555]="*saha aruṇuggamanā nissaggiyo hoti.**entailing relinquishment at dawn.*";
P_HTM[9556]="*Nissajjitabbo saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**The bowl is to be relinquished to the Sangha, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9557]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbo.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9558]="*Tāya bhikkhuniyā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha, that nun should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[9559]="*“ayaṃ me, ayye, patto rattātikkanto nissaggiyo, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti.**‘Venerables, this almsbowl, which I have kept for more than one day, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’*";
P_HTM[9560]="*Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā.**After relinquishing it, she is to confess the offense.*";
P_HTM[9561]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya āpatti paṭiggahetabbā.**The confession should be received by a competent and capable nun.*";
P_HTM[9562]="*Nissaṭṭhapatto dātabbo—**The relinquished bowl is then to be given back:*";
P_HTM[9563]="*“Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[9564]="*Ayaṃ patto itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā nissaggiyo saṅghassa nissaṭṭho.**This almsbowl, which was to be relinquished by the nun so-and-so, has been relinquished to the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[9565]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho imaṃ pattaṃ itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dadeyyā”ti.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give this bowl back to nun so-and-so.’*";
P_HTM[9566]="*Tāya bhikkhuniyā sambahulā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassu vacanīyā—**After approaching several nuns, that nun should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[9567]="*“ayaṃ me, ayyāyo, patto rattātikkanto nissaggiyo, imāhaṃ ayyānaṃ nissajjāmī”ti.**‘Venerables, this almsbowl, which I have kept for more than one day, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the venerables.’*";
P_HTM[9568]="*Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā.**After relinquishing it, she is to confess the offense.*";
P_HTM[9569]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya āpatti paṭiggahetabbā.**The confession should be received by a competent and capable nun.*";
P_HTM[9570]="*Nissaṭṭhapatto dātabbo—**The relinquished bowl is then to be given back:*";
P_HTM[9571]="*“Suṇantu me, ayyāyo.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask you to listen.*";
P_HTM[9572]="*Ayaṃ patto itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā nissaggiyo ayyānaṃ nissaṭṭho.**This almsbowl, which was to be relinquished by the nun so-and-so, has been relinquished to you.*";
P_HTM[9573]="*Yadi ayyānaṃ pattakallaṃ, ayyāyo, imaṃ pattaṃ itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā dadeyyun”ti.**If it seems appropriate to you, you should give this bowl back to nun so-and-so.’*";
P_HTM[9574]="*Tāya bhikkhuniyā ekaṃ bhikkhuniṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyā—**After approaching a single nun, that nun should put her upper robe over one shoulder, squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[9575]="*“ayaṃ me, ayye, patto rattātikkanto nissaggiyo.**‘This almsbowl, which I have kept for more than one day, is to be relinquished.*";
P_HTM[9576]="*Imāhaṃ ayyāya nissajjāmī”ti.**I relinquish it to you.’*";
P_HTM[9577]="*Nissajjitvā āpatti desetabbā.**After relinquishing it, she is to confess the offense.*";
P_HTM[9578]="*Tāya bhikkhuniyā āpatti paṭiggahetabbā.**The confession should be received by that nun.*";
P_HTM[9579]="*Nissaṭṭhapatto dātabbo—**The relinquished bowl is then to be given back:*";
P_HTM[9580]="*“imaṃ pattaṃ ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this almsbowl back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9581]="*Rattātikkante atikkantasaññā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is more than one day and she perceives it as more, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9582]="*Rattātikkante vematikā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is more than one day, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9583]="*Rattātikkante anatikkantasaññā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is more than one day, but she perceives it as less, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9584]="*Anadhiṭṭhite adhiṭṭhitasaññā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it has not been determined, but she perceives that it has, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9585]="*Avikappite vikappitasaññā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it has not been transferred, but she perceives that it has, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9586]="*Avissajjite vissajjitasaññā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it has not been given away, but she perceives that it has, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9587]="*Anaṭṭhe naṭṭhasaññā …**If it is not lost, but she perceives that it is …*";
P_HTM[9588]="*avinaṭṭhe vinaṭṭhasaññā …**If it has not been ruined, but she perceives that it has …*";
P_HTM[9589]="*abhinne bhinnasaññā …**If it is not broken, but she perceives that it is …*";
P_HTM[9590]="*avilutte viluttasaññā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it has not been stolen, but she perceives that it has, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9591]="*Nissaggiyaṃ pattaṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she uses an almsbowl that should be relinquished without first relinquishing it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9592]="*Rattānatikkante atikkantasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than one day, but she perceives it as more, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9593]="*Rattānatikkante vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than one day, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9594]="*Rattānatikkante anatikkantasaññā anāpatti.**If it is less than one day and she perceives it as less, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9595]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9596]="*antoaruṇe adhiṭṭheti, vikappeti, vissajjeti, nassati, vinassati, bhijjati, acchinditvā gaṇhanti, vissāsaṃ gaṇhanti,**if, before dawn, it is determined, transferred to another, given away, lost, ruined, broken, stolen, or taken on trust;*";
P_HTM[9597]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9598]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9599]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo nissaṭṭhapattaṃ na denti.**Soon afterwards the nuns from the group of six did not give back a relinquished bowl.*";
P_HTM[9600]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[9601]="*“Na, bhikkhave, nissaṭṭhapatto na dātabbo.**“Monks, a relinquished almsbowl is to be given back.*";
P_HTM[9602]="*Yā na dadeyya, āpatti dukkaṭassā”ti.**If a nun doesn’t give it back, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.”*";
P_HTM[9603]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9604]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9605]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9606]="*2. Akālacīvarabhājanasikkhāpada**2. The training rule on the sharing out of out-of-season robe-cloth*";
P_HTM[9607]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9608]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo gāmakāvāse vassaṃvuṭṭhā sāvatthiṃ agamaṃsu vattasampannā iriyāpathasampannā duccoḷā lūkhacīvarā.**At that time, after completing the rainy-season residence in a village monastery, a number of nuns were traveling to Sāvatthī. They were perfect in conduct and deportment, but poorly dressed in shabby robes.*";
P_HTM[9609]="*Upāsakā tā bhikkhuniyo passitvā—**Some lay followers who saw them thought,*";
P_HTM[9610]="*“imā bhikkhuniyo vattasampannā iriyāpathasampannā duccoḷā lūkhacīvarā, imā bhikkhuniyo acchinnā bhavissantī”ti bhikkhunisaṅghassa akālacīvaraṃ adaṃsu.**“These nuns are perfect in conduct and deportment, but poorly dressed in shabby robes; they must’ve been robbed,” and they gave out-of-season robe-cloth to the Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[9611]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—**Because they had done the robe-making procedure, the nun Thullanandā*";
P_HTM[9612]="*“amhākaṃ kathinaṃ atthataṃ kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpesi.**determined it as in-season robe-cloth, and then shared it out.*";
P_HTM[9613]="*Upāsakā tā bhikkhuniyo passitvā etadavocuṃ—**The lay followers asked those nuns whether*";
P_HTM[9614]="*“apayyāhi cīvaraṃ laddhan”ti?**they had obtained any robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[9615]="*“Na mayaṃ, āvuso, cīvaraṃ labhāma.**They replied that they hadn’t*";
P_HTM[9616]="*Ayyā thullanandā—**and told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[9617]="*‘amhākaṃ kathinaṃ atthataṃ kālacīvaran’ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpesī”ti.* **";
P_HTM[9618]="*Upāsakā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**Those lay followers then complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9619]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā akālacīvaraṃ ‘kālacīvaran’ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā determine out-of-season robe-cloth as ‘in-season’, and then share it out?”*";
P_HTM[9620]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ upāsakānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those lay followers,*";
P_HTM[9621]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9622]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā akālacīvaraṃ ‘kālacīvaran’ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā do this?”*";
P_HTM[9623]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Those nuns then told the monks,*";
P_HTM[9624]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**who in turn told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[9625]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī akālacīvaraṃ ‘kālacīvaran’ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[9626]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9627]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9628]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī akālacīvaraṃ “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[9629]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9630]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9631]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī akālacīvaraṃ ‘kālacīvaran’ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun determines out-of-season robe-cloth as “in-season”, and then shares it out, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9632]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9633]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9634]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9635]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9636]="*Akālacīvaraṃ nāma**Out-of-season robe-cloth:*";
P_HTM[9637]="*anatthate kathine ekādasamāse uppannaṃ, atthate kathine sattamāse uppannaṃ, kālepi ādissa dinnaṃ, etaṃ akālacīvaraṃ nāma.**if the robe-making procedure has not been done, robe-cloth that is given during the eleven months. If the robe-making procedure has been done, robe-cloth that is given during the seven months. Also, if it is given in the robe season, but the cloth is designated, it is called “out-of-season robe-cloth”.*";
P_HTM[9638]="*Akālacīvaraṃ “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**If she shares it out, after determining out-of-season robe-cloth as “in-season”, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9639]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[9640]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**The robe-cloth is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9641]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9642]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[9643]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, akālacīvaraṃ ‘kālacīvaran’ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**… ‘Venerables, this out-of-season robe-cloth, which I shared out after determining it as “in-season”, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[9644]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[9645]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[9646]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9647]="*Akālacīvare akālacīvarasaññā “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is out-of-season robe-cloth and she perceives it as such, and she shares it out after determining it as “in-season”, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9648]="*Akālacīvare vematikā “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is out-of-season robe-cloth, but she is unsure of it, and she shares it out after determining it as “in-season”, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9649]="*Akālacīvare kālacīvarasaññā “kālacīvaran”ti adhiṭṭhahitvā bhājāpeti, anāpatti.**If it is out-of-season robe-cloth, but she perceives it as in-season robe-cloth, and she shares it out after determining it as “in-season”, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9650]="*Kālacīvare akālacīvarasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is in-season robe-cloth, but she perceives it as out-of-season robe-cloth, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9651]="*Kālacīvare vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is in-season robe-cloth, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9652]="*Kālacīvare kālacīvarasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is in-season robe-cloth and she perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9653]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9654]="*akālacīvaraṃ kālacīvarasaññā bhājāpeti,**if she shares out out-of-season robe-cloth that she perceives as in-season;*";
P_HTM[9655]="*kālacīvaraṃ kālacīvarasaññā bhājāpeti,**if she shares out in-season robe-cloth that she perceives as in-season;*";
P_HTM[9656]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9657]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9658]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9659]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9660]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9661]="*3. Cīvaraparivattanasikkhāpada**3. The training rule on swapping robes*";
P_HTM[9662]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9663]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī aññatarāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā paribhuñji.**At that time the nun Thullanandā was using a robe she had received after swapping with another nun.*";
P_HTM[9664]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ saṅgharitvā nikkhipi.**But the other nun folded up the robe she had received and put it aside.*";
P_HTM[9665]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**Thullanandā then said to her,*";
P_HTM[9666]="*“yaṃ te, ayye, mayā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattitaṃ, kahaṃ taṃ cīvaran”ti?**“Venerable, where’s that robe that I swapped with you?”*";
P_HTM[9667]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ nīharitvā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā dassesi.**She brought out the robe and showed it to her,*";
P_HTM[9668]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**and Thullanandā said,*";
P_HTM[9669]="*“handāyye, tuyhaṃ cīvaraṃ, āhara metaṃ cīvaraṃ, yaṃ tuyhaṃ tuyhamevetaṃ, yaṃ mayhaṃ mayhamevetaṃ, āhara metaṃ, sakaṃ paccāharā”ti acchindi.**“Here’s your robe and give me that robe of mine. That which is yours is yours and that which is mine is mine. Give me that and take back what’s yours.” And she just took it.*";
P_HTM[9670]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That nun then told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[9671]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9672]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindissatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā swap a robe with a nun and then take it back?”*";
P_HTM[9673]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Those nuns then told the monks,*";
P_HTM[9674]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**who in turn told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[9675]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[9676]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9677]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9678]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā swap a robe with a nun and then take it back?*";
P_HTM[9679]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9680]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9681]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ parivattetvā sā pacchā evaṃ vadeyya—‘handāyye, tuyhaṃ cīvaraṃ āhara, metaṃ cīvaraṃ, yaṃ tuyhaṃ tuyhamevetaṃ, yaṃ mayhaṃ mayhamevetaṃ, āhara metaṃ, sakaṃ paccāharā’ti acchindeyya vā acchindāpeyya vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun swaps robes with a nun and then says, “Here’s your robe; give me that robe of mine. That which is yours is yours, and that which is mine is mine. Give me that, and take back what’s yours;” and she just takes it or has it taken, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9682]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9683]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9684]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9685]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9686]="*Bhikkhuniyā saddhinti**With a nun:*";
P_HTM[9687]="*aññāya bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ.**with another nun.*";
P_HTM[9688]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**Robes:*";
P_HTM[9689]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ.**one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[9690]="*Parivattetvāti**Swaps:*";
P_HTM[9691]="*parittena vā vipulaṃ, vipulena vā parittaṃ.**much with little or little with much.*";
P_HTM[9692]="*Acchindeyyāti**Just takes it:*";
P_HTM[9693]="*sayaṃ acchindati nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**if she just takes it herself, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9694]="*Acchindāpeyyāti**Has it taken:*";
P_HTM[9695]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if she asks another, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9696]="*Sakiṃ āṇattā bahukampi acchindati, nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**If she only asks once, then even if the other takes back many, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[9697]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**The robe-cloth is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9698]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9699]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[9700]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, cīvaraṃ bhikkhuniyā saddhiṃ parivattetvā acchinnaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**… ‘Venerables, this robe-cloth, which I took back after swapping it with a nun, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[9701]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[9702]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[9703]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this robe-cloth back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9704]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If the other person is fully ordained and she perceives her as such, and after swapping robe-cloth with her she takes it back or has it taken back, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9705]="*Upasampannāya vematikā cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and after swapping robe-cloth with her she takes it back or has it taken back, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9706]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā cīvaraṃ parivattetvā acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive her as such, and after swapping robe-cloth with her she takes it back or has it taken back, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9707]="*Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ parivattetvā acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she swaps another requisite, and then takes it back or has it taken back, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9708]="*Anupasampannāya saddhiṃ cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ parivattetvā acchindati vā acchindāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she swaps robe-cloth or another requisite with someone who is not fully ordained, and then takes it back or has it taken back, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9709]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9710]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9711]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9712]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9713]="*sā vā deti,**if the other nun gives it back;*";
P_HTM[9714]="*tassā vā vissasantī gaṇhāti,**if she takes it on trust from her;*";
P_HTM[9715]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9716]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9717]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9718]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9719]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9720]="*4. Aññaviññāpanasikkhāpada**4. The training rule on asking for something else*";
P_HTM[9721]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[9722]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī gilānā hoti.**the nun Thullanandā was sick.*";
P_HTM[9723]="*Atha kho aññataro upāsako yena thullanandā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**A lay follower went to her and asked,*";
P_HTM[9724]="*“kiṃ te, ayye, aphāsu, kiṃ āharīyatū”ti?**“Venerable, what’s wrong with you? What may I get you?”*";
P_HTM[9725]="*“Sappinā me, āvuso, attho”ti.**“I need ghee.”*";
P_HTM[9726]="*Atha kho so upāsako aññatarassa āpaṇikassa gharā kahāpaṇassa sappiṃ āharitvā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā adāsi.**That lay follower then brought back from a shop a _kahāpaṇa_’s worth of ghee and gave it to Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[9727]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī evamāha—**Thullanandā said,*";
P_HTM[9728]="*“na me, āvuso, sappinā attho;**“I don’t need ghee;*";
P_HTM[9729]="*telena me attho”ti.**I need oil.”*";
P_HTM[9730]="*Atha kho so upāsako yena so āpaṇiko tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ āpaṇikaṃ etadavoca—**The lay follower returned to the shopkeeper and said,*";
P_HTM[9731]="*“na kirāyyo, ayyāya sappinā attho, telena attho.**“It seems the nun doesn’t need ghee, but oil.*";
P_HTM[9732]="*Handa te sappiṃ, telaṃ me dehī”ti.**Here’s your ghee; please give me oil.”*";
P_HTM[9733]="*“Sace mayaṃ, ayyo, vikkītaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ puna ādiyissāma, kadā amhākaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ vikkāyissati;**“Sir, if we were to take back goods that have been sold, when would our goods be sold?*";
P_HTM[9734]="*sappissa kayena sappi haṭaṃ, telassa kayaṃ āhara, telaṃ harissasī”ti.**When ghee is bought, ghee is taken away. Buying oil, you receive that, and you’ll take that away.”*";
P_HTM[9735]="*Atha kho so upāsako ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That lay follower then complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9736]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā aññaṃ viññāpetvā aññaṃ viññāpessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā ask for one thing and then for something else?”*";
P_HTM[9737]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tassa upāsakassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The nuns heard the complaints of that lay follower,*";
P_HTM[9738]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti …pe…**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9739]="*atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Those nuns then told the monks,*";
P_HTM[9740]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**who in turn told the Buddha. Soon afterwards he had the Sangha gathered and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[9741]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññaṃ viññāpetvā aññaṃ viññāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[9742]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9743]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9744]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññaṃ viññāpetvā aññaṃ viññāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā ask for one thing and then for something else?*";
P_HTM[9745]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9746]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9747]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī aññaṃ viññāpetvā aññaṃ viññāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun asks for one thing and then for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9748]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9749]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9750]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9751]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9752]="*Aññaṃ viññāpetvāti**Asks for one thing:*";
P_HTM[9753]="*yaṃ kiñci viññāpetvā.**whatever she asks for.*";
P_HTM[9754]="*Aññaṃ viññāpeyyāti**Then for something else:*";
P_HTM[9755]="*taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**apart from that thing, if she asks for something else, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9756]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[9757]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9758]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9759]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[9760]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, aññaṃ viññāpetvā aññaṃ viññāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**… ‘Venerables, this thing, which I asked for after asking for something else, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[9761]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[9762]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[9763]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9764]="*Aññe aññasaññā aññaṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is something else and she perceives it as such, and she asks for that, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9765]="*Aññe vematikā aññaṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is something else, but she is unsure of it, and she asks for that, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9766]="*Aññe anaññasaññā aññaṃ viññāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is something else, but she does not perceives it as such, and she asks for that, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9767]="*Anaññe aññasaññā anaññaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not something else, but she perceives it as such, and she asks for that, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9768]="*Anaññe vematikā anaññaṃ viññāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not something else, but she is unsure of it, and she asks for that, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9769]="*Anaññe anaññasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is not something else, and she does not perceives it as such, and she asks for that, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9770]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9771]="*taññeva viññāpeti, aññañca viññāpeti,**if she asks for both at the same time;*";
P_HTM[9772]="*ānisaṃsaṃ dassetvā viññāpeti,**if she demonstrates a benefit and then asks;*";
P_HTM[9773]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9774]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9775]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9776]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9777]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9778]="*5. Aññacetāpanasikkhāpada**5. The training rule on exchanging for something else*";
P_HTM[9779]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[9780]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī gilānā hoti.**the nun Thullanandā was sick.*";
P_HTM[9781]="*Atha kho aññataro upāsako yena thullanandā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**A lay follower went to her and asked,*";
P_HTM[9782]="*“kacci, ayye, khamanīyaṃ kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up, Venerable, I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[9783]="*“Na me, āvuso, khamanīyaṃ, na yāpanīyan”ti.**“I’m not bearing up, and I’m not getting better.”*";
P_HTM[9784]="*“Amukassa, ayye, āpaṇikassa ghare kahāpaṇaṃ nikkhipissāmi, tato yaṃ iccheyyāsi taṃ āharāpeyyāsī”ti.**“We’ll deposit a _kahāpaṇa_ coin in such-and-such a shop. Please get whatever you wish from there.”*";
P_HTM[9785]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī aññataraṃ sikkhamānaṃ āṇāpesi—**Thullanandā then said to a trainee nun,*";
P_HTM[9786]="*“gaccha, sikkhamāne, amukassa āpaṇikassa gharā kahāpaṇassa telaṃ āharā”ti.**“Go to such-and-such a shop and bring back a _kahāpaṇa_’s worth of oil.”*";
P_HTM[9787]="*Atha kho sā sikkhamānā tassa āpaṇikassa gharā kahāpaṇassa telaṃ āharitvā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā adāsi.**That trainee nun did just that and gave it to Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[9788]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī evamāha—**Thullanandā said,*";
P_HTM[9789]="*“na me, sikkhamāne, telena attho, sappinā me attho”ti.**“I don’t need oil; I need ghee.”*";
P_HTM[9790]="*Atha kho sā sikkhamānā yena so āpaṇiko tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ āpaṇikaṃ etadavoca—**The trainee nun returned to the shopkeeper and said,*";
P_HTM[9791]="*“na kira, āvuso, ayyāya telena attho, sappinā attho, handa te telaṃ, sappiṃ me dehī”ti.**“It seems the nun doesn’t need oil, but ghee. Here’s your oil; please give me ghee.”*";
P_HTM[9792]="*“Sace mayaṃ, ayye, vikkītaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ puna ādiyissāma, kadā amhākaṃ bhaṇḍaṃ vikkāyissati.**“Venerable, if we were to take back goods that have been sold, when would our goods be sold?*";
P_HTM[9793]="*Telassa kayena telaṃ haṭaṃ, sappissa kayaṃ āhara, sappiṃ harissasī”ti.**When oil is bought, oil is taken away. Buying ghee, you receive that, and you’ll take that away.”*";
P_HTM[9794]="*Atha kho sā sikkhamānā rodantī aṭṭhāsi.**The trainee nun started to cry.*";
P_HTM[9795]="*Bhikkhuniyo taṃ sikkhamānaṃ etadavocuṃ—**The nuns asked her*";
P_HTM[9796]="*“kissa tvaṃ, sikkhamāne, rodasī”ti?**why,*";
P_HTM[9797]="*Atha kho sā sikkhamānā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**and she told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[9798]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[9799]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā aññaṃ cetāpetvā aññaṃ cetāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā get one thing in exchange and then something else?” …*";
P_HTM[9800]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññaṃ cetāpetvā aññaṃ cetāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[9801]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9802]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[9803]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññaṃ cetāpetvā aññaṃ cetāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā get one thing in exchange and then something else?*";
P_HTM[9804]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9805]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9806]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī aññaṃ cetāpetvā aññaṃ cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gets one thing in exchange and then something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9807]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9808]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9809]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9810]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9811]="*Aññaṃ cetāpetvāti**Gets one thing in exchange:*";
P_HTM[9812]="*yaṃ kiñci cetāpetvā.**whatever she gets in exchange.*";
P_HTM[9813]="*Aññaṃ cetāpeyyāti**Then something else:*";
P_HTM[9814]="*taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**apart from that thing, if she gets something else in exchange, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9815]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[9816]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9817]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9818]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[9819]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, aññaṃ cetāpetvā aññaṃ cetāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**… ‘Venerables, this thing, which I got in exchange, having first got something else in exchange, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[9820]="*dadeyyāti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[9821]="*dadeyyunti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[9822]="*ayyāya dammīti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9823]="*Aññe aññasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is something else and she perceives it as such, and she gets that in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9824]="*Aññe vematikā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is something else, but she is unsure of it, and she gets that in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9825]="*Aññe anaññasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is something else, but she does not perceive it as such, and she gets that in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9826]="*Anaññe aññasaññā anaññaṃ cetāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not something else, but she perceives it as such, and she gets that in exchange, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9827]="*Anaññe vematikā anaññaṃ cetāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not something else, but she is unsure of it, and she gets that in exchange, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9828]="*Anaññe anaññasaññā anāpatti.**If it is not something else, and she does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9829]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9830]="*taññeva cetāpeti, aññañca cetāpeti,**if she gets both in exchange at the same time;*";
P_HTM[9831]="*ānisaṃsaṃ dassetvā cetāpeti,**if she demonstrates a benefit and then gets it in exchange;*";
P_HTM[9832]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9833]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9834]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9835]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9836]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9837]="*6. Saṅghikacetapanasikkhāpada**6. The training rule on exchanging what belongs to the Sangha*";
P_HTM[9838]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9839]="*Tena kho pana samayena upāsakā bhikkhunisaṅghassa cīvaratthāya chandakaṃ saṅgharitvā aññatarassa pāvārikassa ghare parikkhāraṃ nikkhipitvā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**At that time the lay followers collected voluntary contributions to supply the Sangha of nuns with robes. They stored the requisites in a cloth merchant’s shop, and then went to the nuns and said,*";
P_HTM[9840]="*“amukassa, ayye, pāvārikassa ghare cīvaratthāya parikkhāro nikkhitto, tato cīvaraṃ āharāpetvā bhājethā”ti.**“Venerables, requisites to be used for robes are stored in such-and-such a cloth merchant’s shop. Please have someone get cloth from that and share it out.”*";
P_HTM[9841]="*Bhikkhuniyo tena parikkhārena bhesajjaṃ cetāpetvā paribhuñjiṃsu.**But the nuns exchanged those requisites for tonics, which they then used.*";
P_HTM[9842]="*Upāsakā jānitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When the lay followers found out about this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9843]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpessantī”ti.**“When requisites belonging to the Sangha are designated for a specific purpose, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?”*";
P_HTM[9844]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ upāsakānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those lay followers,*";
P_HTM[9845]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9846]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpessantī”ti …pe…**“When requisites belonging to the Sangha are designated for a specific purpose, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?” …*";
P_HTM[9847]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[9848]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9849]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[9850]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpessanti.**“When requisites belonging to the Sangha are designated for a specific purpose, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?*";
P_HTM[9851]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9852]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9853]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘When a requisite belonging to the Sangha is designated for a specific purpose, if a nun exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9854]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9855]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9856]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9857]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9858]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikenāti**A requisite is designated for a specific purpose:*";
P_HTM[9859]="*aññassatthāya dinnena.**it was given for a specific purpose.*";
P_HTM[9860]="*Saṅghikenāti**Belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9861]="*saṅghassa, na gaṇassa, na ekabhikkhuniyā.**belonging to the Sangha, not to a group, not to an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9862]="*Aññaṃ cetāpeyyāti**Exchanges it for something else:*";
P_HTM[9863]="*yaṃatthāya dinnaṃ, taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if, apart from the purpose for which it was given, she exchanges it for something else, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9864]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[9865]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9866]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9867]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[9868]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena aññaṃ cetāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti.**‘Venerables, this thing, which I got in exchange for a requisite belonging to the Sangha that was designated for a specific purpose, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’*";
P_HTM[9869]="*…pe…**…*";
P_HTM[9870]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[9871]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[9872]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9873]="*Aññadatthike aññadatthikasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose and she perceives that it is, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9874]="*Aññadatthike vematikā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose, but she is unsure of it, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9875]="*Aññadatthike anaññadatthikasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose, but she does not perceive that it is, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9876]="*Nissaṭṭhaṃ paṭilabhitvā yathādāne upanetabbaṃ.**When she receives in return what had been relinquished, it is to be used in accordance with the intention of the donors.*";
P_HTM[9877]="*Anaññadatthike aññadatthikasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not for a specific purpose, but she perceives that it is, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9878]="*Anaññadatthike vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not for a specific purpose, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9879]="*Anaññadatthike anaññadatthikasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is not for a specific purpose, and she does not perceive that it is, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9880]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9881]="*sesakaṃ upaneti,**if she uses the remainder;*";
P_HTM[9882]="*sāmike apaloketvā upaneti,**if she uses it after getting permission from the owners;*";
P_HTM[9883]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[9884]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9885]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9886]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9887]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9888]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9889]="*7. Dutiyasaṅghikacetāpanasikkhāpada**7. The second training rule on exchanging what belongs to the Sangha*";
P_HTM[9890]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9891]="*Tena kho pana samayena upāsakā bhikkhunisaṅghassa cīvaratthāya chandakaṃ saṅgharitvā aññatarassa pāvārikassa ghare parikkhāraṃ nikkhipitvā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**At that time the lay followers collected voluntary contributions to supply the Sangha of nuns with robes. They stored the requisites in a cloth merchant’s shop, and then went to the nuns and said,*";
P_HTM[9892]="*“amukassa, ayye, pāvārikassa ghare cīvaratthāya parikkhāro nikkhitto, tato cīvaraṃ āharāpetvā bhājethā”ti.**“Venerables, requisites to be used for robes are stored in such-and-such a cloth merchant’s shop. Please have someone get cloth from that and share it out.”*";
P_HTM[9893]="*Bhikkhuniyo tena ca parikkhārena sayampi yācitvā bhesajjaṃ cetāpetvā paribhuñjiṃsu.**But even though they had asked for them, the nuns exchanged those requisites for tonics, which they then used.*";
P_HTM[9894]="*Upāsakā jānitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When the lay followers found out about this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9895]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpessantī”ti …pe…**“When requisites belonging to the Sangha are designated for a specific purpose and were asked for, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?” …*";
P_HTM[9896]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[9897]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9898]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[9899]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpessanti.**“When requisites belonging to the Sangha are designated for a specific purpose and were asked for, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?*";
P_HTM[9900]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9901]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9902]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘When a requisite belonging to the Sangha is designated for a specific purpose and was asked for, if a nun exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9903]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9904]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9905]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9906]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9907]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikenāti**A requisite is designated for a specific purpose:*";
P_HTM[9908]="*aññassatthāya dinnena.**it was given for a specific purpose.*";
P_HTM[9909]="*Saṅghikenāti**Belonging to the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[9910]="*saṅghassa, na gaṇassa, na ekabhikkhuniyā.**belonging to the Sangha, not to a group, not to an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9911]="*Saññācikenāti**Was asked for:*";
P_HTM[9912]="*sayaṃ yācitvā.**that she herself had asked for.*";
P_HTM[9913]="*Aññaṃ cetāpeyyāti**Exchanges it for something else:*";
P_HTM[9914]="*yaṃatthāya dinnaṃ taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if, apart from the purpose for which it was given, she exchanges it for something else, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9915]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[9916]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9917]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[9918]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[9919]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena saṅghikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**‘Venerables, this thing, which I got in exchange for a requisite belonging to the Sangha that was designated for a specific purpose and had been asked for, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[9920]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[9921]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[9922]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[9923]="*Aññadatthike aññadatthikasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose and she perceives that it is, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9924]="*Aññadatthike vematikā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose, but she is unsure of it, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9925]="*Aññadatthike anaññadatthikasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose, but she does not perceive that it is, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[9926]="*Nissaṭṭhaṃ paṭilabhitvā yathādāne upanetabbaṃ.**When she receives in return what had been relinquished, it is to be used in accordance with the intention of the donors.*";
P_HTM[9927]="*Anaññadatthike aññadatthikasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not for a specific purpose, but she perceives that it is, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9928]="*Anaññadatthike vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not for a specific purpose, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9929]="*Anaññadatthike anaññadatthikasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is not for a specific purpose, and she does not perceive that it is, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[9930]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[9931]="*sesakaṃ upaneti,**if she uses the remainder;*";
P_HTM[9932]="*sāmike apaloketvā upaneti,**if she uses it after getting permission from the owners;*";
P_HTM[9933]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[9934]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[9935]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[9936]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[9937]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[9938]="*Pattavagga**The sub-chapter on almsbowls*";
P_HTM[9939]="*8. Gaṇikacetāpanasikkhāpada**8. The training rule on exchanging what belongs to a group*";
P_HTM[9940]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[9941]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa pūgassa pariveṇavāsikā bhikkhuniyo yāguyā kilamanti.**At that time the nuns staying at the precincts belonging to a certain association were weak because of a lack of rice porridge.*";
P_HTM[9942]="*Atha kho so pūgo bhikkhunīnaṃ yāguatthāya chandakaṃ saṅgharitvā aññatarassa āpaṇikassa ghare parikkhāraṃ nikkhipitvā bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca—**Then, after collecting voluntary contributions to supply the nuns with rice porridge, that association stored the ingredients in a shop. They then went to the nuns and said,*";
P_HTM[9943]="*“amukassa, ayye, āpaṇikassa ghare yāguatthāya parikkhāro nikkhitto, tato taṇḍulaṃ āharāpetvā yāguṃ pacāpetvā paribhuñjathā”ti.**“Venerables, rice porridge ingredients are stored in such-and-such a shop. Please have someone get rice from that, have rice porridge cooked, and then eat it.”*";
P_HTM[9944]="*Bhikkhuniyo tena parikkhārena bhesajjaṃ cetāpetvā paribhuñjiṃsu.**But the nuns exchanged those ingredients for tonics, which they then used.*";
P_HTM[9945]="*So pūgo jānitvā ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**When that association found out about this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[9946]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena mahājanikena aññaṃ cetāpessantī”ti …pe…**“When collective ingredients are designated for a specific purpose, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?” …*";
P_HTM[9947]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena mahājanikena aññaṃ cetāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[9948]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[9949]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[9950]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena mahājanikena aññaṃ cetāpessanti.**“When collective ingredients are designated for a specific purpose, how could the nuns exchange them for something else?*";
P_HTM[9951]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[9952]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[9953]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena mahājanikena aññaṃ cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘When a collective requisite is designated for a specific purpose, if a nun exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[9954]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[9955]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[9956]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[9957]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[9958]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikenāti**A requisite is designated for a specific purpose:*";
P_HTM[9959]="*aññassatthāya dinnena.**it was given for a specific purpose.*";
P_HTM[9960]="*Mahājanikenāti**Collective:*";
P_HTM[9961]="*gaṇassa, na saṅghassa, na ekabhikkhuniyā.**belonging to a group, not to the Sangha, not to an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[9962]="*Aññaṃ cetāpeyyāti**Exchanges it for something else:*";
P_HTM[9963]="*yaṃatthāya dinnaṃ taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if, apart from the purpose for which it was given, she exchanges it for something else, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[9964]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
