P_HTM[10041]="*10. Puggalikacetāpanasikkhāpada**10. The training rule on exchanging what belongs to an individual*";
P_HTM[10042]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10043]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ.**At that time the nun Thullanandā was a learned reciter, and she was confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[10044]="*Bahū manussā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ payirupāsanti.**Many people visited her.*";
P_HTM[10045]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā pariveṇaṃ undriyati.**Just then the precincts of Thullanandā’s dwelling were falling apart.*";
P_HTM[10046]="*Manussā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—**People asked her why,*";
P_HTM[10047]="*“kissidaṃ te, ayye, pariveṇaṃ undriyatī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[10048]="*“Natthāvuso, dāyakā, natthi kārakā”ti.**and she replied, “I have neither a donor, nor a worker.”*";
P_HTM[10049]="*Atha kho te manussā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā pariveṇatthāya chandakaṃ saṅgharitvā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā parikkhāraṃ adaṃsu.**Then, after collecting voluntary contributions for the precincts of Thullanandā’s dwelling, the people gave the collected requisites to Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[10050]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī tena ca parikkhārena sayampi yācitvā bhesajjaṃ cetāpetvā paribhuñji.**But even though she had asked for them, Thullanandā exchanged those requisites for tonics, which she then used.*";
P_HTM[10051]="*Manussā jānitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When the people found out about this, they complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10052]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena puggalikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpessatī”ti …pe…**“When personal requisites are designated for a specific purpose and were asked for, how could the nun Thullanandā exchange them for something else?” …*";
P_HTM[10053]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena puggalikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[10054]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10055]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10056]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena puggalikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpessati.**“When personal requisites are designated for a specific purpose and were asked for, how could the nun Thullanandā exchange them for something else?*";
P_HTM[10057]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10058]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10059]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena puggalikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘When a personal requisite is designated for a specific purpose and was asked for, if a nun exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10060]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10061]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10062]="*bhikkhunīti …pe…**Nun :*";
P_HTM[10063]="*ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10064]="*Aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikenāti**A requisite is designated for a specific purpose:*";
P_HTM[10065]="*aññassatthāya dinnena.**it was given for a specific purpose.*";
P_HTM[10066]="*Puggalikenāti**Personal:*";
P_HTM[10067]="*ekāya bhikkhuniyā, na saṅghassa, na gaṇassa.**belonging to an individual nun, not to the Sangha, not to a group.*";
P_HTM[10068]="*Saññācikenāti**Was asked for:*";
P_HTM[10069]="*sayaṃ yācitvā.**that she herself had asked for.*";
P_HTM[10070]="*Aññaṃ cetāpeyyāti**Exchanges it for something else:*";
P_HTM[10071]="*yaṃatthāya dinnaṃ taṃ ṭhapetvā aññaṃ cetāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if, apart from the purpose for which it was given, she exchanges it for something else, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10072]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[10073]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[10074]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[10075]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[10076]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, aññadatthikena parikkhārena aññuddisikena puggalikena saññācikena aññaṃ cetāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**‘Venerables, this thing, which I got in exchange for a personal requisite that was designated for a specific purpose and had been asked for, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[10077]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[10078]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[10079]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[10080]="*Aññadatthike aññadatthikasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose and she perceives that it is, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10081]="*Aññadatthike vematikā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose, but she is unsure of it, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10082]="*Aññadatthike anaññadatthikasaññā aññaṃ cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is for a specific purpose, but she does not perceive that it is, and she exchanges it for something else, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10083]="*Nissaṭṭhaṃ paṭilabhitvā yathādāne upanetabbaṃ.**When she receives in return what had been relinquished, it is to be used in accordance with the intention of the donors.*";
P_HTM[10084]="*Anaññadatthike aññadatthikasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not for a specific purpose, but she perceives that it is, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10085]="*Anaññadatthike vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not for a specific purpose, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10086]="*Anaññadatthike anaññadatthikasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is not for a specific purpose, and she does not perceive that it is, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10087]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10088]="*sesakaṃ upaneti,**if she uses the remainder;*";
P_HTM[10089]="*sāmike apaloketvā upaneti,**if she uses it after getting permission from the owners;*";
P_HTM[10090]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[10091]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10092]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10093]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10094]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[10095]="*Cīvaravagga**The sub-chapter on robes*";
P_HTM[10096]="*11. Garupāvuraṇasikkhāpada**11. The training rule on heavy cloaks*";
P_HTM[10097]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10098]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ.**At that time the nun Thullanandā was a learned reciter, and she was confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[10099]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo sītakāle mahagghaṃ kambalaṃ pārupitvā yena thullanandā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**On one occasion when the weather was cold, king Pasenadi of Kosala dressed in an expensive woolen cloak and went to Thullanandā. He bowed and sat down.*";
P_HTM[10100]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ thullanandā bhikkhunī dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**And Thullanandā instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching.*";
P_HTM[10101]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**He then said,*";
P_HTM[10102]="*“vadeyyāsi, ayye, yena attho”ti?**“Venerable, please say what you need.”*";
P_HTM[10103]="*“Sace me tvaṃ, mahārāja, dātukāmosi, imaṃ kambalaṃ dehī”ti.**“Great king, if you wish to give me something, then give me this woolen cloak.”*";
P_HTM[10104]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā kambalaṃ datvā uṭṭhāyāsanā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**The king gave her his cloak. He then got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated her with his right side toward her, and left.*";
P_HTM[10105]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10106]="*“mahicchā imā bhikkhuniyo asantuṭṭhā.**“These nuns have great desires; they are not content.*";
P_HTM[10107]="*Kathañhi nāma rājānaṃ kambalaṃ viññāpessantī”ti.**How can they ask the king for his woolen cloak?”*";
P_HTM[10108]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[10109]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10110]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā rājānaṃ kambalaṃ viññāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā ask the king for his woolen cloak?” …*";
P_HTM[10111]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī rājānaṃ kambalaṃ viññāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā asked for this?”*";
P_HTM[10112]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10113]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10114]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī rājānaṃ kambalaṃ viññāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā ask the king for his woolen cloak?*";
P_HTM[10115]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10116]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10117]="*“Garupāvuraṇaṃ pana bhikkhuniyā cetāpentiyā catukkaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpetabbaṃ. Tato ce uttari cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun carries out an exchange to get a heavy cloak, it is to be worth at most four _kaṃsa_ coins. If she gets one in exchange that is worth more than that, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10118]="*Garupāvuraṇaṃ nāma**A heavy cloak:*";
P_HTM[10119]="*yaṃ kiñci sītakāle pāvuraṇaṃ.**whatever cloak is used in cold weather.*";
P_HTM[10120]="*Cetāpentiyāti**Carries out an exchange to get:*";
P_HTM[10121]="*viññāpentiyā.**asks for.*";
P_HTM[10122]="*Catukkaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpetabbanti**It is to be worth at most four _kaṃsa_ coins:*";
P_HTM[10123]="*soḷasakahāpaṇagghanakaṃ cetāpetabbaṃ.**it may be worth sixteen _kahāpaṇa_ coins.*";
P_HTM[10124]="*Tato ce uttari cetāpeyyāti**If she gets one in exchange that is worth more than that:*";
P_HTM[10125]="*tatuttari viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if she asks for one worth more than that, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10126]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[10127]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[10128]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[10129]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[10130]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, garupāvuraṇaṃ atirekacatukkaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**‘Venerables, this heavy cloak worth more than four _kaṃsa_ coins, which I got in exchange, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[10131]="*dadeyyāti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[10132]="*dadeyyunti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[10133]="*ayyāya dammīti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[10134]="*Atirekacatukkaṃse atirekasaññā cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is worth more than four _kaṃsa_ coins, and she perceives it as such, and she gets it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10135]="*Atirekacatukkaṃse vematikā cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is worth more than four _kaṃsa_ coins, but she is unsure of it, and she gets it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10136]="*Atirekacatukkaṃse ūnakasaññā cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is worth more than four _kaṃsa_ coins, but she perceives it as worth less, and she gets it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10137]="*Ūnakacatukkaṃse atirekasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is worth less than four _kaṃsa_ coins, but she perceives it as worth more, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10138]="*Ūnakacatukkaṃse vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is worth less than four _kaṃsa_ coins, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10139]="*Ūnakacatukkaṃse ūnakasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is worth less than four _kaṃsa_ coins, and she perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10140]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10141]="*catukkaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpeti,**if she carries out an exchange for one worth at most four _kaṃsa_ coins;*";
P_HTM[10142]="*ūnakacatukkaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpeti,**if she carries out an exchange for one worth less than four _kaṃsa_ coins;*";
P_HTM[10143]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[10144]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[10145]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[10146]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of her own property;*";
P_HTM[10147]="*mahagghaṃ cetāpetukāmassa appagghaṃ cetāpeti,**if she gets one in exchange that has little value from someone who wants to exchange one of great value;*";
P_HTM[10148]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10149]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10150]="*Ekādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eleventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10151]="*127. Nissaggiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on relinquishment *";
P_HTM[10152]="*12. Cīvaravagga**The sub-chapter on robes*";
P_HTM[10153]="*2. Lahupāvuraṇasikkhāpada**12. The training rule on light cloaks*";
P_HTM[10154]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10155]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ.**At that time the nun Thullanandā was a learned reciter, and she was confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[10156]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo uṇhakāle mahagghaṃ khomaṃ pārupitvā yena thullanandā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi.**On one occasion when the weather was warm, king Pasenadi of Kosala dressed in an expensive linen cloak and went to Thullanandā. He bowed and sat down.*";
P_HTM[10157]="*Ekamantaṃ nisinnaṃ kho rājānaṃ pasenadiṃ kosalaṃ thullanandā bhikkhunī dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**And Thullanandā instructed, inspired, and gladdened him with a teaching.*";
P_HTM[10158]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā dhammiyā kathāya sandassito samādapito samuttejito sampahaṃsito thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**He then said,*";
P_HTM[10159]="*“vadeyyāsi, ayye, yena attho”ti.**“Venerable, please say what you need.”*";
P_HTM[10160]="*“Sace me tvaṃ, mahārāja, dātukāmosi, imaṃ khomaṃ dehī”ti.**“Great king, if you wish to give me something, then give me this linen cloak.”*";
P_HTM[10161]="*Atha kho rājā pasenadi kosalo thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā khomaṃ datvā uṭṭhāyāsanā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**The king gave her his cloak. He then got up from his seat, bowed down, circumambulated her with his right side toward her, and left.*";
P_HTM[10162]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10163]="*“mahicchā imā bhikkhuniyo asantuṭṭhā.**“These nuns have great desires; they are not content.*";
P_HTM[10164]="*Kathañhi nāma rājānaṃ khomaṃ viññāpessantī”ti.**How can they ask the king for his linen cloak?”*";
P_HTM[10165]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[10166]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10167]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā rājānaṃ khomaṃ viññāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā ask the king for his linen cloak?” …*";
P_HTM[10168]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī rājānaṃ khomaṃ viññāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā asked for this?”*";
P_HTM[10169]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10170]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10171]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī rājānaṃ khomaṃ viññāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā ask the king for his linen cloak?*";
P_HTM[10172]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10173]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10174]="*“Lahupāvuraṇaṃ pana bhikkhuniyā cetāpentiyā aḍḍhateyyakaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpetabbaṃ. Tato ce uttari cetāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun carries out an exchange to get a light cloak, it is to be worth at most two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins. If she gets one in exchange that is worth more than that, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10175]="*Lahupāvuraṇaṃ nāma**A light cloak:*";
P_HTM[10176]="*yaṃ kiñci uṇhakāle pāvuraṇaṃ.**whatever cloak is used in warm weather.*";
P_HTM[10177]="*Cetāpentiyāti**Carries out an exchange to get:*";
P_HTM[10178]="*viññāpentiyā.**asks for.*";
P_HTM[10179]="*Aḍḍhateyyakaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpetabbanti**It is to be worth at most two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins:*";
P_HTM[10180]="*dasakahāpaṇagghanakaṃ cetāpetabbaṃ.**it may be worth ten _kahāpaṇa_ coins.*";
P_HTM[10181]="*Tato ce uttari cetāpeyyāti**If she gets one in exchange that is worth more than that:*";
P_HTM[10182]="*tatuttari viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if she asks for one worth more than that, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10183]="*Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti.**When she gets it, it becomes subject to relinquishment.*";
P_HTM[10184]="*Nissajjitabbaṃ saṅghassa vā gaṇassa vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā.**It is to be relinquished to the Sangha of nuns, a group, or an individual nun.*";
P_HTM[10185]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ.**“And, monks, it’s to be relinquished like this.*";
P_HTM[10186]="*…pe…**(To be expanded as in Nuns’ Relinquishment 1, [](pli-tv-bi-vb-np1:2.1.21--2.1.43), with appropriate substitutions.)*";
P_HTM[10187]="*“idaṃ me, ayye, lahupāvuraṇaṃ atirekaaḍḍhateyyakaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ, imāhaṃ saṅghassa nissajjāmī”ti …pe…**‘Venerables, this light cloak worth more than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, which I got in exchange, is to be relinquished. I relinquish it to the Sangha.’ …*";
P_HTM[10188]="*dadeyyā”ti …pe…**the Sangha should give …*";
P_HTM[10189]="*dadeyyun”ti …pe…**you should give …*";
P_HTM[10190]="*ayyāya dammī”ti.**‘I give this back to you.’”*";
P_HTM[10191]="*Atirekaaḍḍhateyyakaṃse atirekasaññā cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is worth more than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, and she perceives it as such, and she gets it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10192]="*Atirekaaḍḍhateyyakaṃse vematikā cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is worth more than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, but she is unsure of it, and she gets it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10193]="*Atirekaaḍḍhateyyakaṃse ūnakasaññā cetāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ.**If it is worth more than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, but she perceives it as worth less, and she gets it in exchange, she commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.*";
P_HTM[10194]="*Ūnakaaḍḍhateyyakaṃse atirekasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is worth less than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, but she perceives it as worth more, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10195]="*Ūnakaaḍḍhateyyakaṃse vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is worth less than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10196]="*Ūnakaaḍḍhateyyakaṃse ūnakasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is worth less than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins, and she perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10197]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10198]="*aḍḍhateyyakaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpeti,**if she carries out an exchange for one worth at most two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins;*";
P_HTM[10199]="*ūnakaaḍḍhateyyakaṃsaparamaṃ cetāpeti,**if she carries out an exchange for one worth less than two-and-a-half _kaṃsa_ coins;*";
P_HTM[10200]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[10201]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[10202]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[10203]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of her own property;*";
P_HTM[10204]="*mahagghaṃ cetāpetukāmassa appagghaṃ cetāpeti,**if she gets one in exchange that has little value from someone who wants to exchange one of great value;*";
P_HTM[10205]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10206]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10207]="*Dvādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The twelfth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10208]="*(Dutiya) Pattavagga* **";
P_HTM[10209]="*10 Pariṇatasikkhāpada***";
P_HTM[10210]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, tiṃsa nissaggiyā pācittiyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the thirty rules on relinquishment and confession have been recited.*";
P_HTM[10211]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[10212]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[10213]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[10214]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[10215]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[10216]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[10217]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[10218]="*Bhikkhunivibhaṅge nissaggiyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing relinquishment in the nuns’ analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[10219]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10220]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10221]="*1. Lasuṇasikkhāpada**1. The training rule on garlic*";
P_HTM[10222]="*Ime kho panāyyāyo chasaṭṭhisatā pācittiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these one hundred and sixty-six rules on offenses entailing confession come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[10223]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10224]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena upāsakena bhikkhunisaṅgho lasuṇena pavārito hoti—**At that time a lay follower had invited the Sangha of nuns to ask for garlic:*";
P_HTM[10225]="*“yāsaṃ ayyānaṃ lasuṇena attho, ahaṃ lasuṇenā”ti.**“If any of the nuns need garlic, I’ll supply it.”*";
P_HTM[10226]="*Khettapālo ca āṇatto hoti—**And he had told his field-keeper,*";
P_HTM[10227]="*“sace bhikkhuniyo āgacchanti, ekamekāya bhikkhuniyā dvetayo bhaṇḍike dehī”ti.**“If the nuns come, give two or three bulbs to each nun.”*";
P_HTM[10228]="*Tena kho pana samayena sāvatthiyaṃ ussavo hoti.**On that occasion they were holding a celebration in Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[10229]="*Yathābhataṃ lasuṇaṃ parikkhayaṃ agamāsi.**and the garlic was used up as soon as it arrived there.*";
P_HTM[10230]="*Bhikkhuniyo taṃ upāsakaṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ—**Just then the nuns went to that lay follower and said,*";
P_HTM[10231]="*“lasuṇena, āvuso, attho”ti.**“We need garlic.”*";
P_HTM[10232]="*“Natthāyye.**“Venerables, there isn’t any.*";
P_HTM[10233]="*Yathābhataṃ lasuṇaṃ parikkhīṇaṃ.**As soon as the garlic arrives, it’s used up.*";
P_HTM[10234]="*Khettaṃ gacchathā”ti.**Please go to the field.”*";
P_HTM[10235]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī khettaṃ gantvā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahuṃ lasuṇaṃ harāpesi.**The nun Thullanandā went to the field, and not having any sense of moderation she took a large amount of garlic.*";
P_HTM[10236]="*Khettapālo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**The field-keeper complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10237]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo na mattaṃ jānitvā bahuṃ lasuṇaṃ harāpessantī”ti.**“How can the nuns not have any sense of moderation and take a large amount of garlic?”*";
P_HTM[10238]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tassa khettapālassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The nuns heard the complaints of that field-keeper,*";
P_HTM[10239]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10240]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā na mattaṃ jānitvā bahuṃ lasuṇaṃ harāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā not have any sense of moderation and take a large amount of garlic?” …*";
P_HTM[10241]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī na mattaṃ jānitvā bahuṃ lasuṇaṃ harāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[10242]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10243]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10244]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī na mattaṃ jānitvā bahuṃ lasuṇaṃ harāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā not have any sense of moderation and take a large amount of garlic?*";
P_HTM[10245]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10246]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**and after giving a teaching he addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10247]="*“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa pajāpati ahosi.**“Once upon a time, monks, Thullanandā was the wife of a brahmin.*";
P_HTM[10248]="*Tisso ca dhītaro—**They had three daughters,*";
P_HTM[10249]="*nandā, nandavatī, sundarīnandā.**Nandā, Nandavatī, and Sundarīnandā.*";
P_HTM[10250]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, so brāhmaṇo kālaṃ katvā aññataraṃ haṃsayoniṃ upapajji.**When that brahmin eventually died, he was reborn as a goose,*";
P_HTM[10251]="*Tassa sabbasovaṇṇamayā pattā ahesuṃ.**whose feathers were all made of gold.*";
P_HTM[10252]="*So tāsaṃ ekekaṃ pattaṃ deti.**And he gave his former family members one feather at the time.*";
P_HTM[10253]="*Atha kho, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī ‘ayaṃ haṃso amhākaṃ ekekaṃ pattaṃ detī’ti taṃ haṃsarājaṃ gahetvā nippattaṃ akāsi.**Thullanandā considered this. She then grabbed hold of that king of geese and plucked him.*";
P_HTM[10254]="*Tassa puna jāyamānā pattā setā sampajjiṃsu.**But when his feathers regrew they were white.*";
P_HTM[10255]="*Tadāpi, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī atilobhena suvaṇṇā parihīnā.**At that time too, monks, Thullanandā lost her gold because she was too greedy.*";
P_HTM[10256]="*Idāni lasuṇā parihāyissatīti.**Now she will lose her garlic.”*";
P_HTM[10257]="*Yaṃ laddhaṃ tena tuṭṭhabbaṃ,**“One should be content with what one gets,*";
P_HTM[10258]="*Atilobho hi pāpako;**Because excessive greed is bad.*";
P_HTM[10259]="*Haṃsarājaṃ gahetvāna,**After grabbing hold of the king of geese,*";
P_HTM[10260]="*Suvaṇṇā parihāyathā”ti.**The gold came to an end.”*";
P_HTM[10261]="*Atha kho bhagavā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing the nun Thullanandā in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[10262]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10263]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī lasuṇaṃ khādeyya pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun eats garlic, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10264]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10265]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10266]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10267]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10268]="*Lasuṇaṃ nāma**Garlic:*";
P_HTM[10269]="*māgadhakaṃ vuccati.**from Magadha is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10270]="*“Khādissāmīti paṭiggaṇhā”ti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10271]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10272]="*Lasuṇe lasuṇasaññā khādati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is garlic and she perceives it as such, and she eats it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10273]="*Lasuṇe vematikā khādati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is garlic, but she is unsure of it, and she eats it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10274]="*Lasuṇe alasuṇasaññā khādati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is garlic, but she does not perceive it as such, and she eats it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10275]="*Alasuṇe lasuṇasaññā khādati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not garlic, but she perceives it as such, and she eats it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10276]="*Alasuṇe vematikā khādati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not garlic, but she is unsure of it, and she eats it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10277]="*Alasuṇe alasuṇasaññā khādati, anāpatti.**If it is not garlic and she does not perceive it as such, and she eats it, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10278]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10279]="*palaṇḍuke,**if it is an onion;*";
P_HTM[10280]="*bhañjanake,**if it is a shallot;*";
P_HTM[10281]="*harītake,**if it is chebulic myrobalan;*";
P_HTM[10282]="*cāpalasuṇe,**if it is a spring onion;*";
P_HTM[10283]="*sūpasampāke,**if it is cooked in a bean curry;*";
P_HTM[10284]="*maṃsasampāke,**if it is cooked with meat;*";
P_HTM[10285]="*telasampāke,**if it is cooked with oil;*";
P_HTM[10286]="*sāḷave,**if it is in sweets;*";
P_HTM[10287]="*uttaribhaṅge,**if it is a special curry;*";
P_HTM[10288]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10289]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10290]="*Lasuṇasikkhāpadaṃ paṭhamaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The training rule on garlic, the first, is finished.*";
P_HTM[10291]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10292]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10293]="*2. Sambādhalomasikkhāpada**2. The training rule on the hair of the private parts*";
P_HTM[10294]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10295]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpetvā aciravatiyā nadiyā vesiyāhi saddhiṃ naggā ekatitthe nahāyanti.**At that time the nuns from the group of six removed the hair from their private parts. They then bathed naked at a ford in the river Aciravatī together with sex workers.*";
P_HTM[10296]="*Vesiyā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The sex workers complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10297]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpessanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can the nuns remove the hair from their private parts? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[10298]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tāsaṃ vesiyānaṃ ujjhāyantīnaṃ khiyyantīnaṃ vipācentīnaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those sex workers,*";
P_HTM[10299]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10300]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six remove the hair from their private parts?” …*";
P_HTM[10301]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do that?”*";
P_HTM[10302]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10303]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10304]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpessanti.**“How can the nuns from the group do that?*";
P_HTM[10305]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10306]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10307]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī sambādhe lomaṃ saṃharāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun removes hair from her private parts, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10308]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10309]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10310]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10311]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10312]="*Sambādho nāma**The private parts:*";
P_HTM[10313]="*ubho upakacchakā, muttakaraṇaṃ.**both armpits and the groin.*";
P_HTM[10314]="*Saṃharāpeyyāti**Removes:*";
P_HTM[10315]="*ekampi lomaṃ saṃharāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she removes one hair, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10316]="*Bahukepi lome saṃharāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Even if she removes many hairs, she commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10317]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10318]="*ābādhapaccayā,**if she does it because she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10319]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10320]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10321]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10322]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10323]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10324]="*3. Talaghātakasikkhāpada**3. The training rule on slapping with the palm of the hand*";
P_HTM[10325]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[10326]="*Tena kho pana samayena dve bhikkhuniyo anabhiratiyā pīḷitā ovarakaṃ pavisitvā talaghātakaṃ karonti.**two nuns who were plagued by lust entered their room and slapped their genitals with the palm of their hands.*";
P_HTM[10327]="*Bhikkhuniyo tena saddena upadhāvitvā tā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**Hearing the sound, the nuns rushed to and asked them,*";
P_HTM[10328]="*“kissa tumhe, ayye, purisena saddhiṃ sampadussathā”ti?**“Venerables, are you having sex with a man?”*";
P_HTM[10329]="*“Na mayaṃ, ayye, purisena saddhiṃ sampadussāmā”ti bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**“No, we’re not,” and they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[10330]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10331]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo talaghātakaṃ karissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns slap their genitals with their hands?” …*";
P_HTM[10332]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo talaghātakaṃ karontī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did that?”*";
P_HTM[10333]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10334]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10335]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo talaghātakaṃ karissanti.**“How could nuns do that?*";
P_HTM[10336]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10337]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10338]="*“Talaghātake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun slaps her genitals with the palm of her hand, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10339]="*Talaghātakaṃ nāma**Slaps her genitals with the palm of her hand:*";
P_HTM[10340]="*samphassaṃ sādiyantī antamaso uppalapattenapi muttakaraṇe pahāraṃ deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, consenting to the contact, she hits her genitals, even with a lotus leaf, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10341]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10342]="*ābādhapaccayā,**if she does it because she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10343]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10344]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10345]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10346]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10347]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10348]="*4. Jatumaṭṭhakasikkhāpada**4. The training rule on dildos*";
P_HTM[10349]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10350]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā purāṇarājorodhā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti.**At that time a woman who had previously belonged to the king’s harem had gone forth as a nun.*";
P_HTM[10351]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī anabhiratiyā pīḷitā yena sā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**Another nun who was plagued by lust went to that nun and said,*";
P_HTM[10352]="*“rājā kho, ayye, tumhe cirāciraṃ gacchati.**“Venerable, the king only came to you at long intervals.*";
P_HTM[10353]="*Kathaṃ tumhe dhārethā”ti?**How did you cope?”*";
P_HTM[10354]="*“Jatumaṭṭhakena, ayye”ti.**“With a dildo.”*";
P_HTM[10355]="*“Kiṃ etaṃ, ayye, jatumaṭṭhakan”ti?**“What’s a dildo?”*";
P_HTM[10356]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī tassā bhikkhuniyā jatumaṭṭhakaṃ ācikkhi.**That nun described a dildo to her.*";
P_HTM[10357]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī jatumaṭṭhakaṃ ādiyitvā dhovituṃ vissaritvā ekamantaṃ chaḍḍesi.**The other nun then used a dildo. But she forgot to wash it before disposing of it in a certain place.*";
P_HTM[10358]="*Bhikkhuniyo makkhikāhi samparikiṇṇaṃ passitvā evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns saw it covered with flies, and they said,*";
P_HTM[10359]="*“kassidaṃ kamman”ti?**“Who did this?”*";
P_HTM[10360]="*Sā evamāha— “mayhidaṃ kamman”ti.**“I did it,” she replied.*";
P_HTM[10361]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10362]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī jatumaṭṭhakaṃ ādiyissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun use a dildo?” …*";
P_HTM[10363]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī jatumaṭṭhakaṃ ādiyatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[10364]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10365]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10366]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī jatumaṭṭhakaṃ ādiyissati.**“How could a nun use a dildo?*";
P_HTM[10367]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10368]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10369]="*“Jatumaṭṭhake pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun uses a dildo, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10370]="*Jatumaṭṭhakaṃ nāma**A dildo:*";
P_HTM[10371]="*jatumayaṃ kaṭṭhamayaṃ piṭṭhamayaṃ mattikāmayaṃ.**made of resin, made of wood, made of flour, made of clay.*";
P_HTM[10372]="*Ādiyeyyāti**Uses:*";
P_HTM[10373]="*samphassaṃ sādiyantī antamaso uppalapattampi muttakaraṇaṃ paveseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she consents to the contact and inserts it into her vagina, even if it is just a lotus leaf, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10374]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10375]="*ābādhapaccayā,**if she does it because she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10376]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10377]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10378]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10379]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10380]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10381]="*5. Udakasuddhikasikkhāpada**5. The training rule on cleaning with water*";
P_HTM[10382]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in the Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu,*";
P_HTM[10383]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā adhovāte aṭṭhāsi—**Mahāpajāpati Gotamī went to him and bowed. Standing downwind from him, she said,*";
P_HTM[10384]="*“duggandho, bhagavā, mātugāmo”ti.**“Venerable Sir, women smell.”*";
P_HTM[10385]="*Atha kho bhagavā—* **";
P_HTM[10386]="*“ādiyantu kho bhikkhuniyo udakasuddhikan”ti, mahāpajāpatiṃ gotamiṃ dhammiyā kathāya sandassesi samādapesi samuttejesi sampahaṃsesi.**“Well then, the nuns should clean themselves with water.” And the Buddha instructed, inspired, and gladdened her with a teaching,*";
P_HTM[10387]="*Atha kho mahāpajāpati gotamī bhagavatā dhammiyā kathāya sandassitā samādapitā samuttejitā sampahaṃsitā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā pakkāmi.**after which she bowed down, circumambulated him with her right side toward him, and left.*";
P_HTM[10388]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[10389]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ udakasuddhikan”ti.**“Monks, I allow the nuns to clean themselves with water.”*";
P_HTM[10390]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī—**Being aware that the Buddha had allowed cleaning with water,*";
P_HTM[10391]="*“bhagavatā udakasuddhikā anuññātā”ti atigambhīraṃ udakasuddhikaṃ ādiyantī muttakaraṇe vaṇaṃ akāsi.**a nun did it too deeply, causing a sore in her vagina.*";
P_HTM[10392]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ āroceti.**She told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[10393]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10394]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī atigambhīraṃ udakasuddhikaṃ ādiyissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun clean herself too deeply with water?” …*";
P_HTM[10395]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī atigambhīraṃ udakasuddhikaṃ ādiyatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[10396]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10397]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10398]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī atigambhīraṃ udakasuddhikaṃ ādiyissati.**“How could a nun clean herself too deeply with water?*";
P_HTM[10399]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10400]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10401]="*“Udakasuddhikaṃ pana bhikkhuniyā ādiyamānāya dvaṅgulapabbaparamaṃ ādātabbaṃ. Taṃ atikkāmentiyā pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun is cleaning herself with water, she may insert two finger joints at the most. If she goes beyond that, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10402]="*Udakasuddhikaṃ nāma**Is cleaning herself with water:*";
P_HTM[10403]="*muttakaraṇassa dhovanā vuccati.**washing the vagina is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10404]="*Ādiyamānāyāti**Cleaning:*";
P_HTM[10405]="*dhovantiyā.**washes.*";
P_HTM[10406]="*Dvaṅgulapabbaparamaṃ ādātabbanti**She may insert two finger joints at the most:*";
P_HTM[10407]="*dvīsu aṅgulesu dve pabbaparamā ādātabbā.**she may insert two joints of two fingers at the most.*";
P_HTM[10408]="*Taṃ atikkāmentiyāti**If she goes beyond that:*";
P_HTM[10409]="*samphassaṃ sādiyantī antamaso kesaggamattampi atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she consents to the contact and goes beyond even by a hair’s breadth, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10410]="*Atirekadvaṅgulapabbe atirekasaññā ādiyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two finger joints, and she perceives it as more, and she inserts them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10411]="*Atirekadvaṅgulapabbe vematikā ādiyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two finger joints, but she is unsure of it, and she inserts them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10412]="*Atirekadvaṅgulapabbe ūnakasaññā ādiyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than two finger joints, but she perceives it as less, and she inserts them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10413]="*Ūnakadvaṅgulapabbe atirekasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than two finger joints, but she perceives it as more, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10414]="*Ūnakadvaṅgulapabbe vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than two finger joints, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10415]="*Ūnakadvaṅgulapabbe ūnakasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is less than two finger joints, and she perceives it as less, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10416]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10417]="*dvaṅgulapabbaparamaṃ ādiyati,**if she inserts two finger joints;*";
P_HTM[10418]="*ūnakadvaṅgulapabbaparamaṃ ādiyati,**if she inserts less than two finger joints;*";
P_HTM[10419]="*ābādhapaccayā,**if she does it because she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10420]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10421]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10422]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10423]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
