P_HTM[10425]="*6. Upatiṭṭhanasikkhāpada**6. The training rule on attending on*";
P_HTM[10426]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[10427]="*Tena kho pana samayena ārohanto nāma mahāmatto bhikkhūsu pabbajito hoti.**a government official called Ārohanta became a monk*";
P_HTM[10428]="*Tassa purāṇadutiyikā bhikkhunīsu pabbajitā hoti.**and his ex-wife a nun.*";
P_HTM[10429]="*Tena kho pana samayena so bhikkhu tassā bhikkhuniyā santike bhattavissaggaṃ karoti.**On one occasion that monk was having his meal in the presence of that nun.*";
P_HTM[10430]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī tassa bhikkhuno bhuñjantassa pānīyena ca vidhūpanena ca upatiṭṭhitvā accāvadati.**While he was eating, she attended on him with drinking water and a fan, and she flirted with him.*";
P_HTM[10431]="*Atha kho so bhikkhu taṃ bhikkhuniṃ apasādeti—**But he dismissed her, saying,*";
P_HTM[10432]="*“mā, bhagini, evarūpaṃ akāsi.**“Don’t do that;*";
P_HTM[10433]="*Netaṃ kappatī”ti.**it’s not allowable.”*";
P_HTM[10434]="*“Pubbe maṃ tvaṃ evañca evañca karosi, idāni ettakaṃ na sahasī”ti—**“Before you did such and such to me, but now you can’t even take this much.”*";
P_HTM[10435]="*pānīyathālakaṃ matthake āsumbhitvā vidhūpanena pahāraṃ adāsi.**And she dropped the water vessel on its head and struck him with the fan.*";
P_HTM[10436]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10437]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī bhikkhussa pahāraṃ dassatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun hit a monk?” …*";
P_HTM[10438]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī bhikkhussa pahāraṃ adāsī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[10439]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10440]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10441]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī bhikkhussa pahāraṃ dassati.**“How could a nun hit a monk?*";
P_HTM[10442]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10443]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10444]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhussa bhuñjantassa pānīyena vā vidhūpanena vā upatiṭṭheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If, when a monk is eating, a nun attends on him with drinking water or a fan, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10445]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10446]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10447]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10448]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10449]="*Bhikkhussāti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[10450]="*upasampannassa.**fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[10451]="*Bhuñjantassāti**Is eating:*";
P_HTM[10452]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññataraṃ bhojanaṃ bhuñjantassa.**is eating any of the five cooked foods.*";
P_HTM[10453]="*Pānīyaṃ nāma**Drinking water:*";
P_HTM[10454]="*yaṃ kiñci pānīyaṃ.**any kind of drink.*";
P_HTM[10455]="*Vidhūpanaṃ nāma**A fan:*";
P_HTM[10456]="*yā kāci bījanī.**any kind of fan.*";
P_HTM[10457]="*Upatiṭṭheyyāti**Attends on:*";
P_HTM[10458]="*hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she stands within arm’s reach, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10459]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññā pānīyena vā vidhūpanena vā upatiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is fully ordained, and she perceives him as such, and she attends on him with drinking water or a fan, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10460]="*Upasampanne vematikā pānīyena vā vidhūpanena vā upatiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she attends on him with drinking water or a fan, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10461]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññā pānīyena vā vidhūpanena vā upatiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is fully ordained, but she does not perceive him as such, and she attends on him with drinking water or a fan, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10462]="*Hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā upatiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she attends on him from beyond arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10463]="*Khādanīyaṃ khādantassa upatiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she attends on him when he is eating fresh food, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10464]="*Anupasampannassa upatiṭṭhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she attends on one who is not fully ordained, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10465]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not fully ordained, but she perceives him as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10466]="*Anupasampanne vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10467]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive him as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10468]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10469]="*deti,**if she gives something;*";
P_HTM[10470]="*dāpeti,**if she has someone else give something;*";
P_HTM[10471]="*anupasampannaṃ āṇāpeti,**if she asks someone who is not fully ordained to do it;*";
P_HTM[10472]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10473]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10474]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10475]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10476]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10477]="*7. Āmakadhaññasikkhāpada**7. The training rule on raw grain*";
P_HTM[10478]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[10479]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo sassakāle āmakadhaññaṃ viññāpetvā nagaraṃ atiharanti dvāraṭṭhāne—**it was the harvest season. At that time the nuns had asked for raw grain, which they then carried to town. At the town gate they were detained and told,*";
P_HTM[10480]="*“dethāyye, bhāgan”ti.**“Venerables, give a share.”*";
P_HTM[10481]="*Palibundhetvā muñciṃsu.**After being released,*";
P_HTM[10482]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo upassayaṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**they went to the nuns’ dwelling place and told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[10483]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10484]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo āmakadhaññaṃ viññāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns ask for raw grain?” …*";
P_HTM[10485]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo āmakadhaññaṃ viññāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[10486]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10487]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10488]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo āmakadhaññaṃ viññāpessanti.**“How could nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[10489]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10490]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10491]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī āmakadhaññaṃ viññatvā vā viññāpetvā vā bhajjitvā vā bhajjāpetvā vā koṭṭetvā vā koṭṭāpetvā vā pacitvā vā pacāpetvā vā bhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun asks for or has someone else ask for raw grain, or she roasts it or has it roasted, or she pounds it or has it pounded, or she cooks it or has it cooked, and she then eats it, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10492]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10493]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10494]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10495]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10496]="*Āmakadhaññaṃ nāma**Raw grain:*";
P_HTM[10497]="*sāli vīhi yavo godhumo kaṅgu varako kudrusako.**rice, barley, wheat, millet, wild gram, kodo millet.*";
P_HTM[10498]="*Viññatvāti**Asks for:*";
P_HTM[10499]="*sayaṃ viññatvā.**she asks herself.*";
P_HTM[10500]="*Viññāpetvāti**Has someone ask for:*";
P_HTM[10501]="*aññaṃ viññāpetvā.**she gets another to ask.*";
P_HTM[10502]="*Bhajjitvāti**Roasts:*";
P_HTM[10503]="*sayaṃ bhajjitvā.**she roasts it herself.*";
P_HTM[10504]="*Bhajjāpetvāti**Has it roasted:*";
P_HTM[10505]="*aññaṃ bhajjāpetvā.**she gets someone else to roast it.*";
P_HTM[10506]="*Koṭṭetvāti**Pounds:*";
P_HTM[10507]="*sayaṃ koṭṭetvā.**she pounds it herself.*";
P_HTM[10508]="*Koṭṭāpetvāti**Has it pounded:*";
P_HTM[10509]="*aññaṃ koṭṭāpetvā.**she gets someone else to pound it.*";
P_HTM[10510]="*Pacitvāti**Cooks:*";
P_HTM[10511]="*sayaṃ pacitvā.**she cooks it herself.*";
P_HTM[10512]="*Pacāpetvāti**Has it cooked:*";
P_HTM[10513]="*aññaṃ pacāpetvā.**she gets someone else to cook it.*";
P_HTM[10514]="*“Bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she accepts it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10515]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10516]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10517]="*ābādhapaccayā,**if she does it because she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10518]="*aparaṇṇaṃ viññāpeti,**if she asks for vegetables;*";
P_HTM[10519]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10520]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10521]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10522]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10523]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10524]="*8. Uccārachaḍḍanasikkhāpada**8. The training rule on disposing of feces*";
P_HTM[10525]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[10526]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro brāhmaṇo nibbiṭṭharājabhaṭo “taññeva bhaṭapathaṃ yācissāmī”ti sīsaṃ nahāyitvā bhikkhunupassayaṃ nissāya rājakulaṃ gacchati.**a brahmin who had earned money by working for the king thought, “I’ll ask for my wages.” After washing his hair, he walked past the nuns’ dwelling place on his way to the king’s residence.*";
P_HTM[10527]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī kaṭāhe vaccaṃ katvā tirokuṭṭe chaḍḍentī tassa brāhmaṇassa matthake āsumbhi.**Just then, after defecating in a pot, a nun disposed of the feces over a wall, and it landed on the head of that brahmin.*";
P_HTM[10528]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**He complained and criticized the nuns,*";
P_HTM[10529]="*“assamaṇiyo imā muṇḍā bandhakiniyo.**“They’re not monastics these shaven-headed sluts!*";
P_HTM[10530]="*Kathañhi nāma gūthakaṭāhaṃ matthake āsumbhissanti.**How can they dump shit on my head?*";
P_HTM[10531]="*Imāsaṃ upassayaṃ jhāpessāmī”ti.**I’m gonna burn down their dwelling place!”*";
P_HTM[10532]="*Ummukaṃ gahetvā upassayaṃ pavisati.**And he got hold of a firebrand and entered their dwelling place.*";
P_HTM[10533]="*Aññataro upāsako upassayā nikkhamanto addasa taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ ummukaṃ gahetvā upassayaṃ pavisantaṃ.**Just then a lay follower who was coming out from the nuns’ dwelling place saw that brahmin with a firebrand on his way in,*";
P_HTM[10534]="*Disvāna taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca—**and he said to him,*";
P_HTM[10535]="*“kissa tvaṃ, bho, ummukaṃ gahetvā upassayaṃ pavisasī”ti?**“Sir, why are you entering the nuns’ dwelling place with a firebrand?”*";
P_HTM[10536]="*“Imā maṃ, bho, muṇḍā bandhakiniyo gūthakaṭāhaṃ matthake āsumbhiṃsu.**“These shaven-headed sluts dumped shit on my head.*";
P_HTM[10537]="*Imāsaṃ upassayaṃ jhāpessāmī”ti.**I’m gonna burn down their dwelling place!”*";
P_HTM[10538]="*“Gaccha, bho brāhmaṇa, maṅgalaṃ etaṃ.**“But this is auspicious, brahmin!*";
P_HTM[10539]="*Sahassaṃ lacchasi tañca bhaṭapathan”ti.**You’ll get your wages and a thousand coins in addition.”*";
P_HTM[10540]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo sīsaṃ nahāyitvā rājakulaṃ gantvā sahassaṃ alattha tañca bhaṭapathaṃ.**That brahmin then washed his hair, went to the king’s residence, and he got his wages and a thousand coins in addition.*";
P_HTM[10541]="*Atha kho so upāsako upassayaṃ pavisitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocetvā paribhāsi.**But that lay follower returned to the nuns’ dwelling place, told them what had happened, and then scolded them.*";
P_HTM[10542]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10543]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo uccāraṃ tirokuṭṭe chaḍḍessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns dispose of feces over a wall?” …*";
P_HTM[10544]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo uccāraṃ tirokuṭṭe chaḍḍentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[10545]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10546]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10547]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo uccāraṃ tirokuṭṭe chaḍḍessanti.**“How can nuns dispose of feces over a wall?*";
P_HTM[10548]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10549]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10550]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā saṅkāraṃ vā vighāsaṃ vā tirokuṭṭe vā tiropākāre vā chaḍḍeyya vā chaḍḍāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun disposes of feces or urine or trash or food scraps over a wall or over an encircling wall, or she has it disposed of in this way, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10551]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10552]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10553]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10554]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10555]="*Uccāro nāma**Feces:*";
P_HTM[10556]="*gūtho vuccati.**excrement is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10557]="*Passāvo nāma**Urine:*";
P_HTM[10558]="*muttaṃ vuccati.**pee is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10559]="*Saṅkāraṃ nāma**Trash:*";
P_HTM[10560]="*kacavaraṃ vuccati.**refuse is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10561]="*Vighāsaṃ nāma**Food scraps:*";
P_HTM[10562]="*calakāni vā aṭṭhikāni vā ucchiṭṭhodakaṃ vā.**food remnants or bones or used water.*";
P_HTM[10563]="*Kuṭṭo nāma**A wall:*";
P_HTM[10564]="*tayo kuṭṭā— iṭṭhakākuṭṭo, silākuṭṭo, dārukuṭṭo.**there are three kinds of walls: walls made of bricks, walls made of stone, walls made of wood.*";
P_HTM[10565]="*Pākāro nāma**An encircling wall:*";
P_HTM[10566]="*tayo pākārā— iṭṭhakāpākāro, silāpākāro, dārupākāro.**there are three kinds of encircling walls: encircling walls made of bricks, encircling walls made of stone, encircling walls made of wood.*";
P_HTM[10567]="*Tirokuṭṭeti**Over a wall:*";
P_HTM[10568]="*kuṭṭassa parato.**to the other side of the wall.*";
P_HTM[10569]="*Tiropākāreti**Over an encircling wall:*";
P_HTM[10570]="*pākārassa parato.**to the other side of the encircling wall.*";
P_HTM[10571]="*Chaḍḍeyyāti**Disposes of:*";
P_HTM[10572]="*sayaṃ chaḍḍeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she disposes of it herself, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10573]="*Chaḍḍāpeyyāti**Has it disposed of:*";
P_HTM[10574]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if she asks another, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10575]="*Sakiṃ āṇattā bahukampi chaḍḍeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she only asks once, then even if the other disposes of such things many times, she commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10576]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10577]="*oloketvā chaḍḍeti,**if she disposes of it after having looked;*";
P_HTM[10578]="*avaḷañje chaḍḍeti,**if she disposes of it at a place where no one passes by;*";
P_HTM[10579]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10580]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10581]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10582]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10583]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10584]="*9. Dutiyauccārachaḍḍanasikkhāpada**9. The second training rule on disposing of feces*";
P_HTM[10585]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10586]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa bhikkhunupassayaṃ nissāya yavakhettaṃ hoti.**At that time a brahmin had a barley field next to the nuns’ dwelling place.*";
P_HTM[10587]="*Bhikkhuniyo uccārampi passāvampi saṅkārampi vighāsampi khette chaḍḍenti.**The nuns disposed of feces, urine, trash, and food scraps in that field.*";
P_HTM[10588]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**The brahmin complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10589]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo amhākaṃ yavakhettaṃ dūsessantī”ti.**“How could the nuns spoil my barley field?”*";
P_HTM[10590]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tassa brāhmaṇassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The nuns heard the complaints of that brahmin,*";
P_HTM[10591]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10592]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo uccārampi passāvampi saṅkārampi vighāsampi harite chaḍḍessantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns dispose of feces, urine, trash, and food scraps on cultivated plants?” …*";
P_HTM[10593]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo uccārampi passāvampi saṅkārampi vighāsampi harite chaḍḍentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[10594]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10595]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10596]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo uccārampi passāvampi saṅkārampi vighāsampi harite chaḍḍessanti.**“How could nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[10597]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10598]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10599]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā saṅkāraṃ vā vighāsaṃ vā harite chaḍḍeyya vā chaḍḍāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun disposes of feces or urine or trash or food scraps on cultivated plants, or she has it disposed of in this way, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10600]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10601]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10602]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10603]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10604]="*Uccāro nāma**Feces:*";
P_HTM[10605]="*gūtho vuccati.**excrement is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10606]="*Passāvo nāma**Urine:*";
P_HTM[10607]="*muttaṃ vuccati.**pee is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10608]="*Saṅkāraṃ nāma**Trash:*";
P_HTM[10609]="*kacavaraṃ vuccati.**refuse is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10610]="*Vighāsaṃ nāma**Food scraps:*";
P_HTM[10611]="*calakāni vā aṭṭhikāni vā ucchiṭṭhodakaṃ vā.**food remnants or bones or used water.*";
P_HTM[10612]="*Haritaṃ nāma**Cultivated plants:*";
P_HTM[10613]="*pubbaṇṇaṃ aparaṇṇaṃ yaṃ manussānaṃ upabhogaparibhogaṃ ropimaṃ.**grain, vegetables, whatever cultivated plants people consider valuable or useful.*";
P_HTM[10614]="*Chaḍḍeyyāti**Disposes of:*";
P_HTM[10615]="*sayaṃ chaḍḍeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she disposes of it herself, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10616]="*Chaḍḍāpeyyāti**Has it disposed of:*";
P_HTM[10617]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if she asks another, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10618]="*Sakiṃ āṇattā bahukampi chaḍḍeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she only asks once, then even if the other disposes of such things many times, she commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10619]="*Harite haritasaññā chaḍḍeti vā chaḍḍāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they are cultivated plants, and she perceives them as such, and she disposes of it or has it disposed of, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10620]="*Harite vematikā chaḍḍeti vā chaḍḍāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they are cultivated plants, but she is unsure of it, and she disposes of it or has it disposed of, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10621]="*Harite aharitasaññā chaḍḍeti vā chaḍḍāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If they are cultivated plants, but she perceives them as uncultivated, and she disposes of it or has it disposed of, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10622]="*Aharite haritasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they are uncultivated plants, but she perceives them as cultivated, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10623]="*Aharite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If they are uncultivated plants, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10624]="*Aharite aharitasaññā, anāpatti.**If they are uncultivated plants, and she perceives them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10625]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10626]="*oloketvā chaḍḍeti,**if she disposes of it after having looked;*";
P_HTM[10627]="*khettamariyāde chaḍḍeti,**if she disposes of it at the edge of the field;*";
P_HTM[10628]="*sāmike āpucchitvā apaloketvā chaḍḍeti,**if she disposes of it after asking and getting permission from the owners;*";
P_HTM[10629]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10630]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10631]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10632]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10633]="*Lasuṇavagga**The sub-chapter on garlic*";
P_HTM[10634]="*10. Naccagītasikkhāpada**10. The training rule on dancing and singing*";
P_HTM[10635]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[10636]="*Tena kho pana samayena rājagahe giraggasamajjo hoti.**At that time in Rājagaha there was a hilltop fair,*";
P_HTM[10637]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo giraggasamajjaṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu.**and the nuns from the group of six went to see it.*";
P_HTM[10638]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10639]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo naccampi gītampi vāditampi dassanāya gacchissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns go to see dancing, singing, and music? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[10640]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[10641]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10642]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo naccampi gītampi vāditampi dassanāya gacchissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the nuns from the group of six go to see dancing, singing, and music?” …*";
P_HTM[10643]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo naccampi gītampi vāditampi dassanāya gacchantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns did that?”*";
P_HTM[10644]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10645]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10646]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo naccampi gītampi vāditampi dassanāya gacchissanti.**“How could the nuns from the group do this?*";
P_HTM[10647]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10648]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10649]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī naccaṃ vā gītaṃ vā vāditaṃ vā dassanāya gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun goes to see dancing or singing or music, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10650]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10651]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10652]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10653]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10654]="*Naccaṃ nāma**Dancing:*";
P_HTM[10655]="*yaṃ kiñci naccaṃ.**any kind of dancing.*";
P_HTM[10656]="*Gītaṃ nāma**Singing:*";
P_HTM[10657]="*yaṃ kiñci gītaṃ.**any kind of singing.*";
P_HTM[10658]="*Vāditaṃ nāma**Music:*";
P_HTM[10659]="*yaṃ kiñci vāditaṃ.**any kind of music.*";
P_HTM[10660]="*Dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is on her way to see it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10661]="*Yattha ṭhitā passati vā suṇāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever she stands to see it or hear it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10662]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati vā suṇāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time she moves beyond the range of sight and then sees it or hears it again, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10663]="*Ekamekaṃ dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is on her way to see any one of the three, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10664]="*Yattha ṭhitā passati vā suṇāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever she stands to see it or hear it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10665]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati vā suṇāti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time she moves beyond the range of sight and then sees it or hears it again, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10666]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10667]="*ārāme ṭhitā passati vā suṇāti vā,**if she sees it or hears it while remaining in the monastery;*";
P_HTM[10668]="*bhikkhuniyā ṭhitokāsaṃ vā nisinnokāsaṃ vā nipannokāsaṃ vā āgantvā naccanti vā gāyanti vā vādenti vā,**if the dancing, singing, or music comes to the place where the nun is standing, sitting, or lying down;*";
P_HTM[10669]="*paṭipathaṃ gacchantī passati vā suṇāti vā,**if she sees it or hears it while walking in the opposite direction;*";
P_HTM[10670]="*sati karaṇīye gantvā passati vā suṇāti vā,**if she goes there because there is something to be done and she then sees it or hears it;*";
P_HTM[10671]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[10672]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10673]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10674]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10675]="*Lasuṇavaggo paṭhamo.**The first sub-chapter on garlic is finished.*";
P_HTM[10676]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10677]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10678]="*11. Rattandhakārasikkhāpada**11. The training rule on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10679]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[10680]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhaddāya kāpilāniyā antevāsiniyā bhikkhuniyā ñātako puriso gāmakā sāvatthiṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**a male relative of a nun who was a pupil of Bhaddā Kāpilānī went from his own village to Sāvatthī on some business.*";
P_HTM[10681]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī tena purisena saddhiṃ rattandhakāre appadīpe ekenekā santiṭṭhatipi sallapatipi.**Then, in the dark of the night and without a lamp, that nun stood and talked alone with that man.*";
P_HTM[10682]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10683]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī rattandhakāre appadīpe purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhissatipi sallapissatipī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun do such a thing?” …*";
P_HTM[10684]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī rattandhakāre appadīpe purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhatipi sallapatipī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[10685]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10686]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10687]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī rattandhakāre appadīpe purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhissatipi sallapissatipi.**“How could a nun do such a thing?*";
P_HTM[10688]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10689]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10690]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī rattandhakāre appadīpe purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭheyya vā sallapeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If, in the dark of the night without a lamp, a nun stands or talks alone with a man, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10691]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10692]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10693]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10694]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10695]="*Rattandhakāreti**In the dark of the night:*";
P_HTM[10696]="*oggate sūriye.**when the sun has set.*";
P_HTM[10697]="*Appadīpeti**Without a lamp:*";
P_HTM[10698]="*anāloke.**without light.*";
P_HTM[10699]="*Puriso nāma**A man:*";
P_HTM[10700]="*manussapuriso na yakkho na peto na tiracchānagato viññū paṭibalo santiṭṭhituṃ sallapituṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of standing together and talking.*";
P_HTM[10701]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[10702]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[10703]="*Ekenekāti**Alone:*";
P_HTM[10704]="*puriso ceva hoti bhikkhunī ca.**just the man and the nun.*";
P_HTM[10705]="*Santiṭṭheyya vāti**Stands with:*";
P_HTM[10706]="*purisassa hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she stands within arm’s reach of the man, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10707]="*Sallapeyya vāti**Talks with:*";
P_HTM[10708]="*purisassa hatthapāse ṭhitā sallapati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she stands talking within arm’s reach of the man, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10709]="*Hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā santiṭṭhati vā sallapati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she stands or talks outside of arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10710]="*Yakkhena vā petena vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahena vā saddhiṃ santiṭṭhati vā sallapati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she stands or talks with a male spirit, a male ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a male animal in human form, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10711]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10712]="*yo koci viññū dutiyo hoti,**if she has a companion who understands;*";
P_HTM[10713]="*arahopekkhā,**if she is not seeking privacy;*";
P_HTM[10714]="*aññavihitā santiṭṭhati vā sallapati vā,**if she stands or talks thinking of something else;*";
P_HTM[10715]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10716]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10717]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10718]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10719]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10720]="*12. Paṭicchannokāsasikkhāpada**12. The training rule on concealed places*";
P_HTM[10721]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[10722]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhaddāya kāpilāniyā antevāsiniyā bhikkhuniyā ñātako puriso gāmakā sāvatthiṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**a male relative of a nun who was a pupil of Bhaddā Kāpilānī went from his own village to Sāvatthī on some business.*";
P_HTM[10723]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī—**Then,*";
P_HTM[10724]="*“bhagavatā paṭikkhittaṃ rattandhakāre appadīpe purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhituṃ sallapitun”ti teneva purisena saddhiṃ paṭicchanne okāse ekenekā santiṭṭhatipi sallapatipi.**knowing that the Buddha had prohibited standing or talking alone with a man in the dark of the night without a lamp, she instead stood and talked alone with that man in a concealed place.*";
P_HTM[10725]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10726]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī paṭicchanne okāse purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhissatipi sallapissatipī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun do such a thing?” …*";
P_HTM[10727]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī paṭicchanne okāse purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhatipi sallapatipī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[10728]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10729]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10730]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī paṭicchanne okāse purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhissatipi sallapissatipi.**“How could a nun do such a thing?*";
P_HTM[10731]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10732]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10733]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī paṭicchanne okāse purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭheyya vā sallapeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun stands or talks alone with a man in a concealed place, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10734]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10735]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10736]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10737]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10738]="*Paṭicchanno nāma**In a concealed place:*";
P_HTM[10739]="*okāso kuṭṭena vā kavāṭena vā kilañjena vā sāṇipākārena vā rukkhena vā thambhena vā kotthaḷiyā vā yena kenaci paṭicchanno hoti.**it is concealed by a wall, a door, a screen, a cloth screen, a tree, a pillar, a grain container, or anything else.*";
P_HTM[10740]="*Puriso nāma**A man:*";
P_HTM[10741]="*manussapuriso na yakkho na peto na tiracchānagato viññū paṭibalo santiṭṭhituṃ sallapituṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of standing together and talking.*";
P_HTM[10742]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[10743]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[10744]="*Ekenekāti**Alone:*";
P_HTM[10745]="*puriso ceva hoti bhikkhunī ca.**just the man and the nun.*";
