P_HTM[10800]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10801]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10802]="*14. Dutiyikauyyojanasikkhāpada**14. The training rule on dismissing a companion*";
P_HTM[10803]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10804]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī rathikāyapi byūhepi siṅghāṭakepi purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhatipi sallapatipi nikaṇṇikampi jappeti dutiyikampi bhikkhuniṃ uyyojeti.**At that time the nun Thullanandā stood and talked alone with men on streets, in cul-de-sacs, and at intersections, and she whispered in their ears and dismissed her companion nun.*";
P_HTM[10805]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10806]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā rathikāyapi byūhepi siṅghāṭakepi purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhissatipi sallapissatipi nikaṇṇikampi jappissati dutiyikampi bhikkhuniṃ uyyojessatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Thullanandā do such things?” …*";
P_HTM[10807]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī rathikāyapi byūhepi siṅghāṭakepi purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhatipi sallapatipi nikaṇṇikampi jappeti dutiyikampi bhikkhuniṃ uyyojetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā does this?”*";
P_HTM[10808]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10809]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10810]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī rathikāyapi byūhepi siṅghāṭakepi purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭhissatipi sallapissatipi nikaṇṇikampi jappissati dutiyikampi bhikkhuniṃ uyyojessati.**“How can the nun Thullanandā do such things?*";
P_HTM[10811]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10812]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10813]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī rathikāya vā byūhe vā siṅghāṭake vā purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā santiṭṭheyya vā sallapeyya vā nikaṇṇikaṃ vā jappeyya dutiyikaṃ vā bhikkhuniṃ uyyojeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun stands or talks alone with a man on a street or in a cul-de-sac or at an intersection, or she whispers in his ear or dismisses her companion nun, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10814]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10815]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10816]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10817]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10818]="*Rathikā nāma**A street:*";
P_HTM[10819]="*racchā vuccati.**a carriage road is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10820]="*Byūhaṃ nāma**A cul-de-sac:*";
P_HTM[10821]="*yeneva pavisanti teneva nikkhamanti.**one departs the same way one enters.*";
P_HTM[10822]="*Siṅghāṭako nāma**An intersection:*";
P_HTM[10823]="*caccaraṃ vuccati.**a crossroads is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10824]="*Puriso nāma**A man:*";
P_HTM[10825]="*manussapuriso na yakkho na peto na tiracchānagato viññū paṭibalo santiṭṭhituṃ sallapituṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of standing together and talking.*";
P_HTM[10826]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[10827]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[10828]="*Ekenekāti**Alone:*";
P_HTM[10829]="*puriso ceva hoti bhikkhunī ca.**just the man and the nun.*";
P_HTM[10830]="*Santiṭṭheyya vāti**Stands with:*";
P_HTM[10831]="*purisassa hatthapāse tiṭṭhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she stands within arm’s reach of the man, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10832]="*Sallapeyya vāti**Talks with:*";
P_HTM[10833]="*purisassa hatthapāse ṭhitā sallapati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she stands talking within arm’s reach of the man, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10834]="*Nikaṇṇikaṃ vā jappeyyāti**Whispers in his ear:*";
P_HTM[10835]="*purisassa upakaṇṇake āroceti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she speaks into the ear of a man, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10836]="*Dutiyikaṃ vā bhikkhuniṃ uyyojeyyāti**Dismisses her companion nun:*";
P_HTM[10837]="*anācāraṃ ācaritukāmā dutiyikampi bhikkhuniṃ uyyojeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**if, wanting to misbehave, she dismisses her companion nun, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10838]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vā savanūpacāraṃ vā vijahantiyā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the companion nun is in the process of going beyond the range of sight or the range of hearing, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10839]="*Vijahite āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the companion nun has gone beyond, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10840]="*Hatthapāsaṃ vijahitvā santiṭṭhati vā sallapati vā āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she stands or talks outside of arm’s reach, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10841]="*Yakkhena vā petena vā paṇḍakena vā tiracchānagatamanussaviggahena vā saddhiṃ santiṭṭhati vā sallapati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she stands or talks with a male spirit, a male ghost, a _paṇḍaka_, or a male animal in human form, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10842]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10843]="*yo koci viññū dutiyo hoti,**if she has a companion who understands;*";
P_HTM[10844]="*arahopekkhā,**if she is not seeking privacy;*";
P_HTM[10845]="*aññavihitā santiṭṭhati vā sallapati vā,**if she stands or talks thinking of something else;*";
P_HTM[10846]="*na anācāraṃ ācaritukāmā,**if she does not want to misbehave;*";
P_HTM[10847]="*sati karaṇīye dutiyikaṃ bhikkhuniṃ uyyojeti,**if she dismisses her companion nun when there is something to be done;*";
P_HTM[10848]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10849]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10850]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10851]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10852]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10853]="*15. Anāpucchāpakkamanasikkhāpada**15. The training rule on departing without taking leave*";
P_HTM[10854]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10855]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī aññatarassa kulassa kulūpikā hoti niccabhattikā.**At that time a certain nun was associating with a family from which she received a regular meal.*";
P_HTM[10856]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āsane nisīditvā sāmike anāpucchā pakkāmi.**Then, after robing up one morning, she took her bowl and robe and went to that family, where she sat down on a seat. She then departed without taking leave of the owners.*";
P_HTM[10857]="*Tassa kulassa dāsī gharaṃ sammajjantī taṃ āsanaṃ bhājanantarikāya pakkhipi.**Soon afterwards, a slave-woman who was sweeping the house put that seat in between some vessels.*";
P_HTM[10858]="*Manussā taṃ āsanaṃ apassantā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—**Not seeing the seat, the people there asked that nun,*";
P_HTM[10859]="*“kahaṃ taṃ, ayye, āsanan”ti?**“Venerable, where’s that seat?”*";
P_HTM[10860]="*“Nāhaṃ taṃ, āvuso, āsanaṃ passāmī”ti.**“I don’t know.”*";
P_HTM[10861]="*“Dethāyye, taṃ āsanan”ti paribhāsitvā niccabhattaṃ pacchindiṃsu.**“Give back the seat, Venerable.” And after scolding her, they made an end of her regular meal.*";
P_HTM[10862]="*Atha kho te manussā gharaṃ sodhentā taṃ āsanaṃ bhājanantarikāya passitvā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ khamāpetvā niccabhattaṃ paṭṭhapesuṃ.**Then, while those people were cleaning the house, they saw that seat in between those vessels. They asked that nun for forgiveness and restored her regular meal.*";
P_HTM[10863]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That nun then told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[10864]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10865]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī purebhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā āsane nisīditvā sāmike anāpucchā pakkamissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun visit a family before the meal, sit down on a seat, and then depart without taking leave of the owners?” …*";
P_HTM[10866]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī purebhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā āsane nisīditvā sāmike anāpucchā pakkamatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[10867]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10868]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10869]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave bhikkhunī purebhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā āsane nisīditvā sāmike anāpucchā pakkamissati.**“How could a nun act like this?*";
P_HTM[10870]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10871]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10872]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī purebhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā āsane nisīditvā sāmike anāpucchā pakkameyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun visits families before the meal, sits down on a seat, and then departs without taking leave of the owners, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10873]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10874]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10875]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10876]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10877]="*Purebhattaṃ nāma**Before the meal:*";
P_HTM[10878]="*aruṇuggamanaṃ upādāya yāva majjhanhikā.**from dawn until midday.*";
P_HTM[10879]="*Kulaṃ nāma**A family:*";
P_HTM[10880]="*cattāri kulāni— khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ.**there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[10881]="*Upasaṅkamitvāti**Visits:*";
P_HTM[10882]="*tattha gantvā.**goes there.*";
P_HTM[10883]="*Āsanaṃ nāma**A seat:*";
P_HTM[10884]="*pallaṅkassa okāso vuccati.**a place for sitting cross-legged is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10885]="*Nisīditvāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[10886]="*tasmiṃ nisīditvā.**sits down on that seat.*";
P_HTM[10887]="*Sāmike anāpucchā pakkameyyāti**Departs without taking leave of the owners:*";
P_HTM[10888]="*yo tasmiṃ kule manusso viññū taṃ anāpucchā anovassakaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, without taking leave of a person who understands in that family, she goes beyond the roof cover of that house, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10889]="*Ajjhokāse upacāraṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is out in the open and she goes beyond the vicinity of the seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10890]="*Anāpucchite anāpucchitasaññā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not taken leave, and she does not perceive that she has, and she departs, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10891]="*Anāpucchite vematikā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not taken leave, but she is unsure of it, and she departs, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10892]="*Anāpucchite āpucchitasaññā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not taken leave, but she perceives that she has, and she departs, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10893]="*Pallaṅkassa anokāse āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a place for sitting cross-legged, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10894]="*Āpucchite anāpucchitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has taken leave, but she does not perceive that she has, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10895]="*Āpucchite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has taken leave, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10896]="*Āpucchite āpucchitasaññā, anāpatti.**If she has taken leave, and she perceives that she has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10897]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10898]="*āpucchā gacchati,**if she departs after taking leave;*";
P_HTM[10899]="*asaṃhārime,**if the seat is not movable;*";
P_HTM[10900]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10901]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[10902]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10903]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10904]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10905]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10906]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10907]="*16. Anāpucchāabhinisīdanasikkhāpada**16. The training rule on sitting down without asking permission*";
P_HTM[10908]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10909]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane abhinisīdatipi abhinipajjatipi.**At that time the nun Thullanandā visited families after the meal, and she sat down and lay down on the seats without asking permission of the owners.*";
P_HTM[10910]="*Manussā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ hirīyamānā āsane neva abhinisīdanti na abhinipajjanti.**Because of Thullanandā, the people there had qualms,  neither sitting nor lying down.*";
P_HTM[10911]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**They then complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10912]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane abhinisīdissatipi abhinipajjissatipī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā visit families after the meal, and then sit down and lie down on the seats without asking the owners for permission?”*";
P_HTM[10913]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[10914]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[10915]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane abhinisīdissatipi abhinipajjissatipī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā act in this way?” …*";
P_HTM[10916]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane abhinisīdatipi abhinipajjatipī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[10917]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10918]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[10919]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane abhinisīdissatipi abhinipajjissatipi.**“How could the nun Thullanandā act in this way?*";
P_HTM[10920]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10921]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10922]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī pacchābhattaṃ kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā āsane abhinisīdeyya vā abhinipajjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun visits families after the meal, and then sits down or lies down on a seat without asking permission of the owners, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10923]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10924]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10925]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10926]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10927]="*Pacchābhattaṃ nāma**After the meal:*";
P_HTM[10928]="*majjhanhike vītivatte yāva atthaṅgate sūriye.**when the middle of the day has passed, until sunset.*";
P_HTM[10929]="*Kulaṃ nāma**A family:*";
P_HTM[10930]="*cattāri kulāni— khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ.**there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[10931]="*Upasaṅkamitvāti**Visits:*";
P_HTM[10932]="*tattha gantvā.**goes there.*";
P_HTM[10933]="*Sāmike anāpucchāti**Without asking permission of the owners:*";
P_HTM[10934]="*yo tasmiṃ kule manusso sāmiko dātuṃ, taṃ anāpucchā.**not having asked permission of a person in that family who is an owner and who has the authority to give.*";
P_HTM[10935]="*Āsanaṃ nāma**A seat:*";
P_HTM[10936]="*pallaṅkassa okāso vuccati.**a place for sitting cross-legged is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[10937]="*Abhinisīdeyyāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[10938]="*tasmiṃ abhinisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she sits down on that seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10939]="*Abhinipajjeyyāti**Lies down:*";
P_HTM[10940]="*tasmiṃ abhinipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she lies down on that seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10941]="*Anāpucchite anāpucchitasaññā āsane abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, and she does not perceive that she has, and she sits down or lies down on a seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10942]="*Anāpucchite vematikā āsane abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she is unsure of it, and she sits down or lies down on a seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10943]="*Anāpucchite āpucchitasaññā āsane abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she perceives that she has, and she sits down or lies down on a seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10944]="*Pallaṅkassa anokāse āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not a place for sitting cross-legged, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10945]="*Āpucchite anāpucchitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she does not perceive that she has, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10946]="*Āpucchite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[10947]="*Āpucchite āpucchitasaññā, anāpatti.**If she has asked permission, and she perceives that she has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[10948]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[10949]="*āpucchā āsane abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā,**if she sits down or lies down after asking permission;*";
P_HTM[10950]="*dhuvapaññatte,**if the seat is permanently put out for her;*";
P_HTM[10951]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[10952]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[10953]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[10954]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[10955]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[10956]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[10957]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[10958]="*17. Anāpucchāsantharaṇasikkhāpada**17. The training rule on spreading out without asking permission*";
P_HTM[10959]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[10960]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo kosalesu janapade sāvatthiṃ gacchantiyo sāyaṃ aññataraṃ gāmaṃ upagantvā aññataraṃ brāhmaṇakulaṃ upasaṅkamitvā okāsaṃ yāciṃsu.**At that time a number of nuns were traveling through the Kosalan country on their way to Sāvatthī, when one evening they arrived at a certain village. There they went to a brahmin family and asked for a place to stay.*";
P_HTM[10961]="*Atha kho sā brāhmaṇī tā bhikkhuniyo etadavoca—**The brahmin woman told them,*";
P_HTM[10962]="*“āgametha, ayye, yāva brāhmaṇo āgacchatī”ti.**“Please wait, Venerables, until my husband returns.”*";
P_HTM[10963]="*Bhikkhuniyo—* **";
P_HTM[10964]="*“yāva brāhmaṇo āgacchatī”ti seyyaṃ santharitvā ekaccā nisīdiṃsu ekaccā nipajjiṃsu.**While they were waiting, the nuns put out bedding, and some sat down on it while others lay down.*";
P_HTM[10965]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo rattiṃ āgantvā taṃ brāhmaṇiṃ etadavoca—**When the husband returned at night, he said to his wife,*";
P_HTM[10966]="*“kā imā”ti?**“Who are they?”*";
P_HTM[10967]="*“Bhikkhuniyo, ayyā”ti.**“They are nuns.”*";
P_HTM[10968]="*“Nikkaḍḍhatha imā muṇḍā bandhakiniyo”ti, gharato nikkaḍḍhāpesi.**“Throw out these shaven-headed sluts!”, and he had them thrown out of the house.*";
P_HTM[10969]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo sāvatthiṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**Those nuns then went to Sāvatthī, where they told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[10970]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[10971]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo vikāle kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā seyyaṃ santharitvā abhinisīdissantipi abhinipajjissantipī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns visit families at the wrong time, put out bedding without asking permission of the owners, and then sit down and lie down on it?” …*";
P_HTM[10972]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vikāle kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā seyyaṃ santharitvā abhinisīdantipi abhinipajjantipī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[10973]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[10974]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[10975]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vikāle kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā seyyaṃ santharitvā abhinisīdissantipi abhinipajjissantipi.**“How could nuns act like this?*";
P_HTM[10976]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[10977]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[10978]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī vikāle kulāni upasaṅkamitvā sāmike anāpucchā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā abhinisīdeyya vā abhinipajjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun visits families at the wrong time, puts out bedding without asking permission of the owners, or has it put out, and then sits down or lies down on it, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[10979]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[10980]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[10981]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[10982]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[10983]="*Vikālo nāma**The wrong time:*";
P_HTM[10984]="*atthaṅgate sūriye yāva aruṇuggamanā.**from sunset until dawn.*";
P_HTM[10985]="*Kulaṃ nāma**A family:*";
P_HTM[10986]="*cattāri kulāni— khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ suddakulaṃ.**there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[10987]="*Upasaṅkamitvāti**Visits:*";
P_HTM[10988]="*tattha gantvā.**goes there.*";
P_HTM[10989]="*Sāmike anāpucchāti**Without asking permission of the owners:*";
P_HTM[10990]="*yo tasmiṃ kule manusso sāmiko dātuṃ, taṃ anāpucchā.**not having asked permission of a person in that family who is an owner and who has the authority to give.*";
P_HTM[10991]="*Seyyaṃ nāma**Bedding:*";
P_HTM[10992]="*antamaso paṇṇasanthāropi.**even a spread of leaves.*";
P_HTM[10993]="*Santharitvāti**Puts out:*";
P_HTM[10994]="*sayaṃ santharitvā.**she puts it out herself.*";
P_HTM[10995]="*Santharāpetvāti**Has it put out:*";
P_HTM[10996]="*aññaṃ santharāpetvā.**she has someone else to put it out.*";
P_HTM[10997]="*Abhinisīdeyyāti**Sits down:*";
P_HTM[10998]="*tasmiṃ abhinisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she sits down on it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[10999]="*Abhinipajjeyyāti**Lies down:*";
P_HTM[11000]="*tasmiṃ abhinipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she lies down on it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11001]="*Anāpucchite anāpucchitasaññā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, and she does not perceive that she has, and she sits down or lies down on bedding after putting it out or having it put out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11002]="*Anāpucchite vematikā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she is unsure of it, and she sits down or lies down on bedding after putting it out or having it put out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11003]="*Anāpucchite āpucchitasaññā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she perceives that she has, and she sits down or lies down on bedding after putting it out or having it put out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11004]="*Āpucchite anāpucchitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she does not perceive that she has, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11005]="*Āpucchite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11006]="*Āpucchite āpucchitasaññā, anāpatti.**If she has asked permission, and she perceives that she has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11007]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11008]="*āpucchā seyyaṃ santharitvā vā santharāpetvā vā abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā,**if she first asks permission, and then, after putting out bedding or having it put out, sits down or lies down on it;*";
P_HTM[11009]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[11010]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11011]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11012]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11013]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11014]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11015]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[11016]="*18. Paraujjhāpanakasikkhāpada**18. The training rule on complaining about others*";
P_HTM[11017]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11018]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhaddāya kāpilāniyā antevāsinī bhikkhunī bhaddaṃ kāpilāniṃ sakkaccaṃ upaṭṭheti.**At that time a nun who was a pupil of Bhaddā Kāpilānī attended on her with care.*";
P_HTM[11019]="*Bhaddā kāpilānī bhikkhuniyo etadavoca—**Bhaddā Kāpilānī said to the nuns,*";
P_HTM[11020]="*“ayaṃ maṃ, ayye, bhikkhunī sakkaccaṃ upaṭṭheti, imissāhaṃ cīvaraṃ dassāmī”ti.**“Venerables, this nun is attending on me with care. I’ll give her a robe.”*";
P_HTM[11021]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī duggahitena dūpadhāritena paraṃ ujjhāpesi—**Then, because of misunderstanding and a lack of proper reflection, that nun complained about Bhaddā Kāpilānī,*";
P_HTM[11022]="*“ahaṃ kirāyye, ayyaṃ na sakkaccaṃ upaṭṭhemi, na kira me ayyā cīvaraṃ dassatī”ti.**“Venerables, if I didn’t attend on her with care, she wouldn’t give me a robe.”*";
P_HTM[11023]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11024]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī duggahitena dūpadhāritena paraṃ ujjhāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun complain about someone else because of misunderstanding and a lack of proper reflection?” …*";
P_HTM[11025]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī duggahitena dūpadhāritena paraṃ ujjhāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[11026]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11027]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11028]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī duggahitena dūpadhāritena paraṃ ujjhāpessati.**“How could a nun act in this way?*";
P_HTM[11029]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11030]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11031]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī duggahitena dūpadhāritena paraṃ ujjhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun complains about someone else because of misunderstanding and a lack of proper reflection, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11032]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11033]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11034]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11035]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11036]="*Duggahitenāti**Because of misunderstanding:*";
P_HTM[11037]="*aññathā gahitena.**because of wrong understanding.*";
P_HTM[11038]="*Dūpadhāritenāti**Because of a lack of proper reflection:*";
P_HTM[11039]="*aññathā upadhāritena.**because of wrong reflection.*";
P_HTM[11040]="*Paranti**Someone else:*";
P_HTM[11041]="*upasampannaṃ ujjhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she complains about one who is fully ordained, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11042]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā ujjhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives them as such, and she complains about them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11043]="*Upasampannāya vematikā ujjhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she complains about them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11044]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā ujjhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive them as such, and she complains about them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11045]="*Anupasampannaṃ ujjhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she complains about someone who is not fully ordained, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11046]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives them as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11047]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11048]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive them as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11049]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11050]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11051]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11052]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11053]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11054]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[11055]="*19. Paraabhisapanasikkhāpada**19. The training rule on cursing another*";
P_HTM[11056]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11057]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo attano bhaṇḍakaṃ apassantiyo caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—**some nuns were unable to find their possessions. They said to the nun Caṇḍakāḷī,*";
P_HTM[11058]="*“apāyye, amhākaṃ bhaṇḍakaṃ passeyyāsī”ti?**“Venerable, have you seen our things?”*";
P_HTM[11059]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**Caṇḍakāḷī complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11060]="*“ahameva nūna corī, ahameva nūna alajjinī, yā ayyāyo attano bhaṇḍakaṃ apassantiyo tā maṃ evamāhaṃsu—**“Why are you asking me if I’ve seen your things? Am I a thief? Am I shameless?*";
P_HTM[11061]="*‘apāyye, amhākaṃ bhaṇḍakaṃ passeyyāsī’ti?* **";
P_HTM[11062]="*Sacāhaṃ, ayye, tumhākaṃ bhaṇḍakaṃ gaṇhāmi, assamaṇī homi, brahmacariyā cavāmi, nirayaṃ upapajjāmi;**Venerables, if I took your things I wouldn’t be a monastic anymore. I would fall from the spiritual life and be reborn in hell.*";
P_HTM[11063]="*yā pana maṃ abhūtena evamāha sāpi assamaṇī hotu, brahmacariyā cavatu, nirayaṃ upapajjatū”ti.**May anyone who speaks such an untruth about me depart from monasticism, fall from the spiritual life, and be reborn in hell!”*";
P_HTM[11064]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11065]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā caṇḍakāḷī attānampi parampi nirayenapi brahmacariyenapi abhisapissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Caṇḍakāḷī invoke hell and the spiritual life to curse herself and others?” …*";
P_HTM[11066]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī attānampi parampi nirayenapi brahmacariyenapi abhisapatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Caṇḍakāḷī did this?”*";
P_HTM[11067]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11068]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11069]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī attānampi parampi nirayenapi brahmacariyenapi abhisapissati.**“How could the nun Caṇḍakāḷī act like this?*";
P_HTM[11070]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11071]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11072]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī attānaṃ vā paraṃ vā nirayena vā brahmacariyena vā abhisapeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun invokes hell or the spiritual life to curse herself or someone else, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11073]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11074]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11075]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11076]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11077]="*Attānanti**Herself:*";
P_HTM[11078]="*paccattaṃ.**oneself.*";
P_HTM[11079]="*Paranti**Someone else:*";
P_HTM[11080]="*upasampannaṃ.**one who is fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[11081]="*Nirayena vā brahmacariyena vā abhisapati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she invokes hell or the spiritual life as a curse, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11082]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā nirayena vā brahmacariyena vā abhisapati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives them as such, and she invokes hell or the spiritual life to curse them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11083]="*Upasampannāya vematikā nirayena vā brahmacariyena vā abhisapati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she invokes hell or the spiritual life to curse them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11084]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā nirayena vā brahmacariyena vā abhisapati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive them as such, and she invokes hell or the spiritual life to curse them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11085]="*Tiracchānayoniyā vā pettivisayena vā manussadobhaggena vā abhisapati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she invokes the animal realm, the ghost realm, or human misfortune as a curse, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11086]="*Anupasampannaṃ abhisapati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she curses someone who is not fully ordained, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11087]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives them as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11088]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11089]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive them as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11090]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11091]="*atthapurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at what is beneficial;*";
P_HTM[11092]="*dhammapurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at giving a teaching;*";
P_HTM[11093]="*anusāsanipurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at giving an instruction;*";
P_HTM[11094]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11095]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11096]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11097]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11098]="*Rattandhakāravagga**The sub-chapter on the dark of the night*";
P_HTM[11099]="*20. Rodanasikkhāpada**20. The training rule on crying*";
P_HTM[11100]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11101]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍitvā attānaṃ vadhitvā vadhitvā rodati.**the nun Caṇḍakāḷī quarreled with the nuns and then cried after repeatedly beating herself.*";
P_HTM[11102]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11103]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā caṇḍakāḷī attānaṃ vadhitvā vadhitvā rodissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Caṇḍakāḷī cry after repeatedly beating herself?” …*";
P_HTM[11104]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī attānaṃ vadhitvā vadhitvā rodatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Caṇḍakāḷī did this?”*";
P_HTM[11105]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11106]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11107]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī attānaṃ vadhitvā vadhitvā rodissati.**“How could the nun Caṇḍakāḷī act like this?*";
P_HTM[11108]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11109]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11110]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī attānaṃ vadhitvā vadhitvā rodeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun cries after repeatedly beating herself, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11111]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11112]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11113]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11114]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11115]="*Attānanti**Herself:*";
P_HTM[11116]="*paccattaṃ.**oneself.*";
P_HTM[11117]="*Vadhitvā vadhitvā rodati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she cries after repeatedly beating herself, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11118]="*Vadhati na rodati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she beats herself, but does not cry, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11119]="*Rodati na vadhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she cries, but does not beat herself, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11120]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11121]="*ñātibyasanena vā bhogabyasanena vā rogabyasanena vā phuṭṭhā rodati na vadhati,**if she cries, but does not beat herself, because of loss of relatives, loss of property, or loss of health;*";
P_HTM[11122]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11123]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11124]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11125]="*Andhakāravaggo dutiyo.**The second sub-chapter on darkness is finished.*";
P_HTM[11126]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11127]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11128]="*21. Naggasikkhāpada**21. The training rule on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11129]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11130]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo aciravatiyā nadiyā vesiyāhi saddhiṃ naggā ekatitthe nahāyanti.**a number of nuns were bathing naked at a ford in the river Aciravatī together with sex workers.*";
P_HTM[11131]="*Vesiyā tā bhikkhuniyo uppaṇḍesuṃ—**The sex workers teased the nuns,*";
P_HTM[11132]="*“kiṃ nu kho nāma tumhākaṃ, ayye, daharānaṃ brahmacariyaṃ ciṇṇena, nanu nāma kāmā paribhuñjitabbā.**“Venerables, why practice the spiritual life when you’re still young? Why not enjoy worldly pleasures?*";
P_HTM[11133]="*Yadā jiṇṇā bhavissatha tadā brahmacariyaṃ carissatha.**You can practice the spiritual life when you’re old.*";
P_HTM[11134]="*Evaṃ tumhākaṃ ubho atthā pariggahitā bhavissantī”ti.**In this way you’ll get the benefit of both.”*";
P_HTM[11135]="*Bhikkhuniyo vesiyāhi uppaṇḍiyamānā maṅkū ahesuṃ.**The nuns felt humiliated.*";
P_HTM[11136]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo upassayaṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They then went to the nuns’ dwelling place and told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[11137]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The nuns told the monks,*";
P_HTM[11138]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[11139]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11140]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the nuns for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[11141]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya …pe…**for the well-being of the Sangha …*";
P_HTM[11142]="*vinayānuggahāya.**for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[11143]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11144]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī naggā nahāyeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun bathes naked, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11145]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11146]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11147]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11148]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11149]="*Naggā nahāyeyyāti**Bathes naked:*";
P_HTM[11150]="*anivatthā vā apārutā vā nahāyati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if she bathes without wearing a sarong or an upper robe, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11151]="*Nahānapariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**At the end of the bath, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11152]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11153]="*acchinnacīvarikāya vā naṭṭhacīvarikāya vā,**if her robes have been stolen or ruined;*";
P_HTM[11154]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11155]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11156]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11157]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11158]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11159]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11160]="*22. Udakasāṭikasikkhāpada**22. The training rule on bathing robes*";
P_HTM[11161]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11162]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ udakasāṭikā anuññātā hoti.**At that time the Buddha had allowed bathing robes for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[11163]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo—* **";
P_HTM[11164]="*“bhagavatā udakasāṭikā anuññātā”ti appamāṇikāyo udakasāṭikāyo dhāresuṃ.**Knowing this, the nuns from the group of six wore bathing robes of inappropriate size.*";
P_HTM[11165]="*Puratopi pacchatopi ākaḍḍhantā āhiṇḍanti.**As they were walking about, they were dragging them along, both in front and behind.*";
P_HTM[11166]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11167]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo appamāṇikāyo udakasāṭikāyo dhāressantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six wear such bathing robes?” …*";
P_HTM[11168]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo appamāṇikāyo udakasāṭikāyo dhārentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns from the group of six do this?”*";
P_HTM[11169]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11170]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11171]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo appamāṇikāyo udakasāṭikāyo dhāressanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six wear such bathing robes?*";
P_HTM[11172]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11173]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11174]="*“Udakasāṭikaṃ pana bhikkhuniyā kārayamānāya pamāṇikā kāretabbā. Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ—dīghaso catasso vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ dve vidatthiyo. Taṃ atikkāmentiyā chedanakaṃ pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun is having a bathing robe made, it should be made the right size. This is the right size: four standard handspans long and two wide. If it exceeds that, it is to be cut down, and she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11175]="*Udakasāṭikā nāma**A bathing robe:*";
P_HTM[11176]="*yāya nivatthā nahāyati.**wearing it as a sarong, she bathes.*";
P_HTM[11177]="*Kārayamānāyāti**Is having made:*";
P_HTM[11178]="*karontiyā vā kārāpentiyā vā. Pamāṇikā kāretabbā.**making it herself or having someone else make it, it should be made the right size.*";
P_HTM[11179]="*Tatridaṃ pamāṇaṃ— dīghaso catasso vidatthiyo, sugatavidatthiyā; tiriyaṃ dve vidatthiyo.**This is the right size: four standard handspans long and two wide.*";
P_HTM[11180]="*Taṃ atikkāmetvā karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**If she makes one or has one made that exceeds that, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11181]="*Paṭilābhena chinditvā pācittiyaṃ desetabbaṃ.**When she gets it, it is to be cut down, and she is then to confess an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11182]="*Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she finishes what she began herself, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11183]="*Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has others finish what she began herself, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11184]="*Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she finishes herself what was begun by others, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11185]="*Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has others finish what was begun by others, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11186]="*Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she makes one or has one made for the benefit of someone else, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11187]="*Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she gets one that was made by someone else and then uses it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11188]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11189]="*pamāṇikaṃ karoti,**if she makes it the right size;*";
P_HTM[11190]="*ūnakaṃ karoti,**if she makes it smaller than the right size;*";
P_HTM[11191]="*aññena kataṃ pamāṇātikkantaṃ paṭilabhitvā chinditvā paribhuñjati,**if she gets one made by someone else that exceeds the right size and she cuts it down before using it;*";
P_HTM[11192]="*vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,**if she makes a canopy, a floor cover, a cloth screen, a mattress, or a pillow;*";
P_HTM[11193]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11194]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11195]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11196]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11197]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11198]="*23. Cīvarasibbanasikkhāpada**23. The training rule on sewing robes*";
P_HTM[11199]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11200]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarissā bhikkhuniyā mahagghe cīvaradusse cīvaraṃ dukkaṭaṃ hoti dussibbitaṃ.**At that time a robe belonging to a certain nun had been badly made and badly sewn from expensive robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[11201]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**The nun Thullanandā said to her,*";
P_HTM[11202]="*“sundaraṃ kho idaṃ te, ayye, cīvaradussaṃ;**“Venerable, this robe-cloth is beautiful,*";
P_HTM[11203]="*cīvarañca kho dukkaṭaṃ dussibbitan”ti.**but the robe has been badly made and badly sewn.”*";
P_HTM[11204]="*“Visibbemi, ayye, sibbissasī”ti?**“If I unstitch it, will you sew it back together?”*";
P_HTM[11205]="*“Āmāyye, sibbissāmī”ti.**“Sure.”*";
P_HTM[11206]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ visibbetvā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā adāsi.**Then that nun unstitched the robe and gave it to Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[11207]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—**Yet although Thullanandā*";
P_HTM[11208]="*“sibbissāmi sibbissāmī”ti neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti.**repeatedly said she would sew it, she neither sewed it herself nor did she make any effort to have someone else do it.*";
P_HTM[11209]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That nun then told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[11210]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized Thullanandā,*";
P_HTM[11211]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ visibbāpetvā neva sibbissati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā have a nun’s robe unstitched, and then neither sew it herself nor make any effort to have someone else do it?” …*";
P_HTM[11212]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ visibbāpetvā neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karotī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11213]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11214]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11215]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ visibbāpetvā neva sibbissati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā act like this?*";
P_HTM[11216]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11217]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11218]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva sibbeyya na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyya, aññatra catūhapañcāhā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun, after unstitching a nun’s robe or having it unstitched, neither sews it herself nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it, then, if there was no obstruction or it was no more than four or five days, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11219]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11220]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11221]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11222]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11223]="*Bhikkhuniyāti**A nun’s:*";
P_HTM[11224]="*aññāya bhikkhuniyā.**another nun’s.*";
P_HTM[11225]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**Robe:*";
P_HTM[11226]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ.**one of the six kinds of robes.*";
P_HTM[11227]="*Visibbetvāti**Unstitching:*";
P_HTM[11228]="*sayaṃ visibbetvā.**she unstitches it herself.*";
P_HTM[11229]="*Visibbāpetvāti**Having it unstitched:*";
P_HTM[11230]="*aññaṃ visibbāpetvā.**she has someone else unstitch it.*";
P_HTM[11231]="*Sā pacchā anantarāyikinīti**Then, if there was no obstruction:*";
P_HTM[11232]="*asati antarāye.**when there is no obstacle.*";
P_HTM[11233]="*Neva sibbeyyāti**She neither sews:*";
P_HTM[11234]="*na sayaṃ sibbeyya.**she does not sew it herself.*";
P_HTM[11235]="*Na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyyāti**Nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it:*";
P_HTM[11236]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya.**she does not ask anyone else.*";
P_HTM[11237]="*Aññatra catūhapañcāhāti**It was no more than four or five days:*";
P_HTM[11238]="*ṭhapetvā catūhapañcāhaṃ.**unless it was no more than four or five days.*";
P_HTM[11239]="*“Neva sibbissāmi na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I’ll neither sew it nor make any effort to have someone else sew it,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11240]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā cīvaraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti, aññatra catūhapañcāhā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives her as such, and she unstitches her robe or has it unstitched, and then neither sews it herself nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it, then, except if she was obstructed or it was no more than four or five days, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11241]="*Upasampannāya vematikā cīvaraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti, aññatra catūhapañcāhā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she unstitches her robe or has it unstitched, and then neither sews it herself nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it, then, except if she was obstructed or it was no more than four or five days, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11242]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā cīvaraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti, aññatra catūhapañcāhā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive her as such, and she unstitches her robe or has it unstitched, and then neither sews it herself nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it, then, except if she was obstructed or it was no more than four or five days, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11243]="*Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti, aññatra catūhapañcāhā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she unstitches another requisite or has it unstitched, and then neither sews it herself nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it, then, except if she was obstructed or it was no more than four or five days, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11244]="*Anupasampannāya cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ visibbetvā vā visibbāpetvā vā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva sibbati na sibbāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti, aññatra catūhapañcāhā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she unstitches her robe or another requisite, or has it unstitched, and then neither sews it herself nor makes any effort to have someone else sew it, then, except if she was obstructed or it was no more than four or five days, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11245]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11246]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11247]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11248]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11249]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[11250]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches for someone to sew, but does not find anyone;*";
P_HTM[11251]="*karontī catūhapañcāhaṃ atikkāmeti,**if she is doing it, but she goes beyond four or five days;*";
P_HTM[11252]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[11253]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11254]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11255]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11256]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11257]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11258]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11259]="*24. Saṅghāṭicārasikkhāpada**24. The training rule on moving the robes*";
P_HTM[11260]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11261]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamanti.**At that time the nuns stored one of their robes with other nuns and then left to wander the country in a sarong and an upper robe.*";
P_HTM[11262]="*Tāni cīvarāni ciraṃ nikkhittāni kaṇṇakitāni honti.**Because they were stored for a long time, the robes became moldy.*";
P_HTM[11263]="*Tāni bhikkhuniyo otāpenti.**When the nuns put them out to sun them,*";
P_HTM[11264]="*Bhikkhuniyo tā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**other nuns asked them,*";
P_HTM[11265]="*“kassimāni, ayye, cīvarāni kaṇṇakitānī”ti?**“Whose moldy robes are these?”*";
P_HTM[11266]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**And they told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[11267]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11268]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns store one of their robes with other nuns and then go wandering the country in a sarong and an upper robe?” …*";
P_HTM[11269]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[11270]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11271]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11272]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhunīnaṃ hatthe cīvaraṃ nikkhipitvā santaruttarena janapadacārikaṃ pakkamissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[11273]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11274]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11275]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī pañcāhikaṃ saṅghāṭicāraṃ atikkāmeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun does not move her robes for more than five days, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11276]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11277]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11278]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11279]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11280]="*Pañcāhikaṃ saṅghāṭicāraṃ atikkāmeyyāti**Does not move her robes for more than five days:*";
P_HTM[11281]="*pañcamaṃ divasaṃ pañca cīvarāni neva nivāseti na pārupati na otāpeti, pañcamaṃ divasaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she does not wear or sun her five robes on the fifth day, then, when the fifth day has passed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11282]="*Pañcāhātikkante atikkantasaññā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than five days, and she perceives it as more, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11283]="*Pañcāhātikkante vematikā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than five days, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11284]="*Pañcāhātikkante anatikkantasaññā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is more than five days, but she perceives it as less, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11285]="*Pañcāhānatikkante atikkantasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than five days, but she perceives it as more, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11286]="*Pañcāhānatikkante vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is less than five days, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11287]="*Pañcāhānatikkante anatikkantasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is less than five days and she perceives it as less, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11288]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11289]="*pañcamaṃ divasaṃ pañca cīvarāni nivāseti vā pārupati vā otāpeti vā,**if she wears or suns the five robes on the fifth day;*";
P_HTM[11290]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[11291]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11292]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11293]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11294]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11295]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11296]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11297]="*25. Cīvarasaṅkamanīyasikkhāpada**25. The training rule on borrowed robes*";
P_HTM[11298]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11299]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī piṇḍāya caritvā allacīvaraṃ pattharitvā vihāraṃ pāvisi.**there was a nun who, after walking for almsfood, spread out her moist robe and entered her dwelling.*";
P_HTM[11300]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī taṃ cīvaraṃ pārupitvā gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**A second nun put on that robe and entered the village for almsfood.*";
P_HTM[11301]="*Sā nikkhamitvā bhikkhuniyo pucchi—**Soon afterwards the first nun came out and asked the nuns,*";
P_HTM[11302]="*“apāyye, mayhaṃ cīvaraṃ passeyyāthā”ti?**“Venerables, have you seen my robe?”*";
P_HTM[11303]="*Bhikkhuniyo tassā bhikkhuniyā etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The nuns told her what had happened.*";
P_HTM[11304]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**She then complained and criticized the second nun,*";
P_HTM[11305]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī mayhaṃ cīvaraṃ anāpucchā pārupissatī”ti.**“How could a nun put on my robe without asking permission?”*";
P_HTM[11306]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**She told the nuns what had happened,*";
P_HTM[11307]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11308]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ anāpucchā pārupissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun put on another nun’s robe without asking permission?” …*";
P_HTM[11309]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ anāpucchā pārupatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[11310]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11311]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11312]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā cīvaraṃ anāpucchā pārupissati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[11313]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11314]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11315]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ dhāreyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun wears a robe taken on loan, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11316]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11317]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11318]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11319]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11320]="*Cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ nāma**A robe taken on loan:*";
P_HTM[11321]="*upasampannāya pañcannaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ tassā vā adinnaṃ taṃ vā anāpucchā nivāseti vā pārupati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she wears any of the five robes belonging to a fully ordained nun, and it has not been given to her, nor has she asked permission to use it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11322]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives her as such, and she takes on loan a robe belonging to her and then wears it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11323]="*Upasampannāya vematikā cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she takes on loan a robe belonging to her and then wears it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11324]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive her as such, and she takes on loan a robe belonging to her and then wears it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11325]="*Anupasampannāya cīvarasaṅkamanīyaṃ dhāreti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she takes on loan a robe belonging to her and then wears it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11326]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11327]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11328]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11329]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11330]="*sā vā deti,**if the robe has been given to her;*";
P_HTM[11331]="*taṃ vā āpucchā nivāseti vā pārupati vā,**if she wears it after asking permission;*";
P_HTM[11332]="*acchinnacīvarikāya,**if her own robe has been stolen;*";
P_HTM[11333]="*naṭṭhacīvarikāya,**if her own robe has been lost;*";
P_HTM[11334]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11335]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11336]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11337]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11338]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11339]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11340]="*26. Gaṇacīvarasikkhāpada**26. The training rule on robes for a group*";
P_HTM[11341]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11342]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā upaṭṭhākakulaṃ thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**a family that was supporting the nun Thullanandā said to her,*";
P_HTM[11343]="*“bhikkhunisaṅghassa, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassāmā”ti.**“Venerable, we’re going to give a robe to the Sangha of nuns.”*";
P_HTM[11344]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—**She replied,*";
P_HTM[11345]="*“tumhe bahukiccā bahukaraṇīyā”ti antarāyaṃ akāsi.**“You’re very busy,” and she created an obstacle for them.*";
P_HTM[11346]="*Tena kho pana samayena tassa kulassa gharaṃ ḍayhati.**Soon afterwards the house of that family burned down.*";
P_HTM[11347]="*Te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**They then complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11348]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā amhākaṃ deyyadhammaṃ antarāyaṃ karissati.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā create an obstacle for our gift?*";
P_HTM[11349]="*Ubhayenāmha paribāhirā bhogehi ca puññena cā”ti.**Now we have neither possessions nor merit.”*";
P_HTM[11350]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[11351]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11352]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā gaṇassa cīvaralābhaṃ antarāyaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā create an obstacle for a group to get a robe?” …*";
P_HTM[11353]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī gaṇassa cīvaralābhaṃ antarāyaṃ akāsī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11354]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11355]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11356]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī gaṇassa cīvaralābhaṃ antarāyaṃ karissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11357]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11358]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11359]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī gaṇassa cīvaralābhaṃ antarāyaṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun creates an obstacle for a group to get a robe, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11360]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11361]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11362]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11363]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11364]="*Gaṇo nāma**A group:*";
P_HTM[11365]="*bhikkhunisaṅgho vuccati.**the Sangha of nuns is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11366]="*Cīvaraṃ nāma**A robe:*";
P_HTM[11367]="*channaṃ cīvarānaṃ aññataraṃ cīvaraṃ vikappanupagaṃ pacchimaṃ.**one of the six kinds of robe-cloth, but not smaller than what can be transferred to another.*";
P_HTM[11368]="*Antarāyaṃ kareyyāti**Creates an obstacle:*";
P_HTM[11369]="*“kathaṃ ime cīvaraṃ na dadeyyun”ti antarāyaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she creates an obstacle with the thought, “What can be done so that these people don’t give robe-cloth?”, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11370]="*Aññaṃ parikkhāraṃ antarāyaṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she creates an obstacle for another requisite, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11371]="*Sambahulānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ vā ekabhikkhuniyā vā anupasampannāya vā cīvaraṃ vā aññaṃ vā parikkhāraṃ antarāyaṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she creates an obstacle for a number of nuns or for a single nun or for someone who is not fully ordained to get robe-cloth or another requisite, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11372]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11373]="*ānisaṃsaṃ dassetvā nivāreti,**if she obstructs them after demonstrating a benefit;*";
P_HTM[11374]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11375]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11376]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11377]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11378]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11379]="*27. Paṭibāhanasikkhāpada**27. The training rule on blocking*";
P_HTM[11380]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11381]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhunisaṅghassa akālacīvaraṃ uppannaṃ hoti.**At that time out-of-season robe-cloth had been given to the Sangha of nuns,*";
P_HTM[11382]="*Atha kho bhikkhunisaṅgho taṃ cīvaraṃ bhājetukāmo sannipati.**and the Sangha gathered to share it out.*";
P_HTM[11383]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā antevāsiniyo bhikkhuniyo pakkantā honti.**Just then the nuns who were pupils of the nun Thullanandā were away.*";
P_HTM[11384]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī tā bhikkhuniyo etadavoca—**Thullanandā said to the nuns:*";
P_HTM[11385]="*“ayye, bhikkhuniyo pakkantā, na tāva cīvaraṃ bhājīyissatī”ti.**“Venerables, there are nuns who are away. We cannot distribute the robe-cloth until they get back.”*";
P_HTM[11386]="*Cīvaravibhaṅgaṃ paṭibāhi.**And she blocked the distribution of robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[11387]="*Bhikkhuniyo na tāva cīvaraṃ bhājīyissatīti pakkamiṃsu.**Since the robe-cloth could not be distributed until those nuns returned, other nuns left.*";
P_HTM[11388]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī antevāsinīsu bhikkhunīsu āgatāsu taṃ cīvaraṃ bhājāpesi.**Then, when her pupils returned, Thullanandā had that robe-cloth distributed.*";
P_HTM[11389]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11390]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā dhammikaṃ cīvaravibhaṅgaṃ paṭibāhissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā block a legitimate distribution of robe-cloth?” …*";
P_HTM[11391]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dhammikaṃ cīvaravibhaṅgaṃ paṭibāhatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11392]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11393]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11394]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dhammikaṃ cīvaravibhaṅgaṃ paṭibāhissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11395]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11396]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11397]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī dhammikaṃ cīvaravibhaṅgaṃ paṭibāheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun blocks a legitimate distribution of robe-cloth, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11398]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11399]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11400]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11401]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11402]="*Dhammiko nāma cīvaravibhaṅgo**A legitimate distribution of robe-cloth:*";
P_HTM[11403]="*samaggo bhikkhunisaṅgho sannipatitvā bhājeti.**it is distributed by a unanimous Sangha of nuns.*";
P_HTM[11404]="*Paṭibāheyyāti**Blocks:*";
P_HTM[11405]="*kathaṃ imaṃ cīvaraṃ na bhājeyyāti paṭibāhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she blocks it with the thought, “What can be done so that this robe-cloth isn’t distributed?”, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11406]="*Dhammike dhammikasaññā paṭibāhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she blocks it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11407]="*Dhammike vematikā paṭibāhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she blocks it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11408]="*Dhammike adhammikasaññā paṭibāhati, anāpatti.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she blocks it, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11409]="*Adhammike dhammikasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11410]="*Adhammike vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11411]="*Adhammike adhammikasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11412]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11413]="*ānisaṃsaṃ dassetvā paṭibāhati,**if she blocks it after demonstrating a benefit;*";
P_HTM[11414]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11415]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11416]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11417]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11418]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11419]="*28. Cīvaradānasikkhāpada**28. The training rule on giving robes*";
P_HTM[11420]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11421]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī naṭānampi naṭakānampi laṅghakānampi sokajjhāyikānampi kumbhathūṇikānampi samaṇacīvaraṃ deti—**At that time the nun Thullanandā was giving monastic robes to actors, dancers, acrobats, magicians, and musicians, saying,*";
P_HTM[11422]="*“mayhaṃ parisati vaṇṇaṃ bhāsathā”ti.**“Please praise me in public.”*";
P_HTM[11423]="*Naṭāpi naṭakāpi laṅghakāpi sokajjhāyikāpi kumbhathūṇikāpi thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā parisati vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti—**And they did:*";
P_HTM[11424]="*“ayyā thullanandā bahussutā bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ;**“Venerable Thullanandā is a learned reciter; she’s confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[11425]="*detha ayyāya, karotha ayyāyā”ti.**Give to her; work for her!”*";
P_HTM[11426]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā … tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11427]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā agārikassa samaṇacīvaraṃ dassatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Thullanandā give monastic robes to householders?” …*";
P_HTM[11428]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī agārikassa samaṇacīvaraṃ detī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā does this?”*";
P_HTM[11429]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11430]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11431]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī agārikassa samaṇacīvaraṃ dassati.**“How can the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11432]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11433]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11434]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī agārikassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā samaṇacīvaraṃ dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives a monastic robe to a householder or a male wanderer or a female wanderer, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11435]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11436]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11437]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11438]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11439]="*Agāriko nāma**A householder:*";
P_HTM[11440]="*yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**anyone who lives at home.*";
P_HTM[11441]="*Paribbājako nāma**A male wanderer:*";
P_HTM[11442]="*bhikkhuñca sāmaṇerañca ṭhapetvā yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno.**any male wanderer apart from Buddhist monks and novice monks.*";
P_HTM[11443]="*Paribbājikā nāma**A female wanderer:*";
P_HTM[11444]="*bhikkhuniñca sikkhamānañca sāmaṇeriñca ṭhapetvā yā kāci paribbājikasamāpannā.**any female wanderer apart from Buddhist nuns, trainee nuns, and novice nuns.*";
P_HTM[11445]="*Samaṇacīvaraṃ nāma**A monastic robe:*";
P_HTM[11446]="*kappakataṃ vuccati.**a mark has been made is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11447]="*Deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she gives it away, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11448]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11449]="*mātāpitūnaṃ deti,**if she gives one to her mother or father;*";
P_HTM[11450]="*tāvakālikaṃ deti,**if she lends one out;*";
P_HTM[11451]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11452]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11453]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11454]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11455]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11456]="*29. Kālaatikkamanasikkhāpada**29. The training rule on letting the time expire*";
P_HTM[11457]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11458]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā upaṭṭhākakulaṃ thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**a family that was supporting the nun Thullanandā said to her,*";
P_HTM[11459]="*“sace mayaṃ, ayye, sakkoma, bhikkhunisaṅghassa cīvaraṃ dassāmā”ti.**“If we’re able, Venerable, we’ll give robe-cloth to the Sangha of nuns.”*";
P_HTM[11460]="*Tena kho pana samayena vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhuniyo cīvaraṃ bhājetukāmā sannipatiṃsu.**Just then the nuns who had completed the rainy-season residence had gathered to distribute robe-cloth.*";
P_HTM[11461]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī tā bhikkhuniyo etadavoca—**But Thullanandā said to them,*";
P_HTM[11462]="*“āgametha, ayye, atthi bhikkhunisaṅghassa cīvarapaccāsā”ti.**“Please wait, Venerables. The Sangha is expecting more cloth.”*";
P_HTM[11463]="*Bhikkhuniyo thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—**The nuns said to her,*";
P_HTM[11464]="*“gacchāyye, taṃ cīvaraṃ jānāhī”ti.**“Go and find out what’s happening.”*";
P_HTM[11465]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā te manusse etadavoca—**She then went to that family and said to them,*";
P_HTM[11466]="*“dethāvuso, bhikkhunisaṅghassa cīvaran”ti.**“Please give the robe-cloth to the Sangha of nuns.”*";
P_HTM[11467]="*“Na mayaṃ, ayye, sakkoma bhikkhunisaṅghassa cīvaraṃ dātun”ti.**“We’re sorry, but we’re not able to give robe-cloth to the Sangha.”*";
P_HTM[11468]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**Thullanandā told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[11469]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11470]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā dubbalacīvarapaccāsāya cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā allow the robe season to expire because of an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth?” …*";
P_HTM[11471]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dubbalacīvarapaccāsāya cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11472]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11473]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11474]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dubbalacīvarapaccāsāya cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11475]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11476]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11477]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī dubbalacīvarapaccāsāya cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun lets the robe season expire because of an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11478]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11479]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11480]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11481]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11482]="*Dubbalacīvarapaccāsā nāma**An uncertain expectation of robe-cloth:*";
P_HTM[11483]="*“sace mayaṃ sakkoma, dassāma karissāmā”ti vācā bhinnā hoti.**they have said, “If we’re able, then we’ll give, then we’ll act.”*";
P_HTM[11484]="*Cīvarakālasamayo nāma**Robe season:*";
P_HTM[11485]="*anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimo māso, atthate kathine pañca māsā.**for one who has not participated in the robe-making procedure, it is the last month of the rainy season; for one who has participated in the robe-making procedure, it is the five month period.*";
P_HTM[11486]="*Cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeyyāti**Lets the robe season expire:*";
P_HTM[11487]="*anatthate kathine vassānassa pacchimaṃ divasaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**for one who has not participated in the robe-making procedure, if she goes beyond the last day of the rainy season, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11488]="*Atthate kathine kathinuddhāradivasaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**For one who has participated in the robe-making procedure, if she goes beyond the day on which the robe-making season ends, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11489]="*Dubbalacīvare dubbalacīvarasaññā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, and she perceives it as such, and she lets the robe season expire, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11490]="*Dubbalacīvare vematikā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, but she is unsure of it, and she lets the robe season expire, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11491]="*Dubbalacīvare adubbalacīvarasaññā cīvarakālasamayaṃ atikkāmeti, anāpatti.**If it is an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, but she does not perceive it as such, and she lets the robe season expire, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11492]="*Adubbalacīvare dubbalacīvarasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, but she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11493]="*Adubbalacīvare vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is not an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11494]="*Adubbalacīvare adubbalacīvarasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is not an uncertain expectation of robe-cloth, and she does not perceive it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11495]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11496]="*ānisaṃsaṃ dassetvā nivāreti,**if she hinders it after demonstrating a benefit;*";
P_HTM[11497]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11498]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11499]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11500]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11501]="*Naggavagga**The sub-chapter on nakedness*";
P_HTM[11502]="*30. Kathinuddhārasikkhāpada**30. The training rule on the ending of the robe-making season*";
P_HTM[11503]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11504]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarena upāsakena saṅghaṃ uddissa vihāro kārāpito hoti.**At that time a lay follower had built a dwelling for the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[11505]="*So tassa vihārassa mahe ubhatosaṅghassa akālacīvaraṃ dātukāmo hoti.**He wanted to give out-of-season robe-cloth to both Sanghas at the presentation ceremony for that dwelling,*";
P_HTM[11506]="*Tena kho pana samayena ubhatosaṅghassa kathinaṃ atthataṃ hoti.**but both Sanghas had already done the robe-making procedure.*";
P_HTM[11507]="*Atha kho so upāsako saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā kathinuddhāraṃ yāci.**That lay follower then went to the Sangha and asked it to make an end of the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[11508]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[11509]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11510]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, kathinaṃ uddharituṃ.**“Monks, I allow you to end the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[11511]="*Evañca pana bhikkhave kathinaṃ uddharitabbaṃ.**And it should be done like this.*";
P_HTM[11512]="*Byattena bhikkhunā paṭibalena saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable monk should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[11513]="*‘Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[11514]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho kathinaṃ uddhareyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should end the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[11515]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[11516]="*Suṇātu me, bhante, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[11517]="*Saṅgho kathinaṃ uddharati.**The Sangha ends the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[11518]="*Yassāyasmato khamati kathinassa uddhāro, so tuṇhassa;**Any monk who approves of ending the robe-making season should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[11519]="*yassa nakkhamati, so bhāseyya.**Any monk who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[11520]="*Ubbhataṃ saṅghena kathinaṃ, khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha has made an end of the robe-making season. The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[11521]="*Atha kho so upāsako bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā kathinuddhāraṃ yāci.**That lay follower then went to the Sangha of nuns and asked them to end the robe-making season.*";
P_HTM[11522]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—* **";
P_HTM[11523]="*“cīvaraṃ amhākaṃ bhavissatī”ti kathinuddhāraṃ paṭibāhi.**But the nun Thullanandā, aiming to get robe-cloth for herself, blocked the Sangha from doing it.*";
P_HTM[11524]="*Atha kho so upāsako ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That lay follower complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11525]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo amhākaṃ kathinuddhāraṃ na dassantī”ti.**“How could the nuns not end the robe-making season for us?”*";
P_HTM[11526]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tassa upāsakassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The nuns heard the complaints of that lay follower.*";
P_HTM[11527]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11528]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā dhammikaṃ kathinuddhāraṃ paṭibāhissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā block a legitimate ending of the robe-making season?” …*";
P_HTM[11529]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dhammikaṃ kathinuddhāraṃ paṭibāhatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11530]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11531]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11532]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dhammikaṃ kathinuddhāraṃ paṭibāhissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11533]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11534]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11535]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī dhammikaṃ kathinuddhāraṃ paṭibāheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun blocks a legitimate ending of the robe-making season, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11536]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11537]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11538]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11539]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11540]="*Dhammiko nāma kathinuddhāro**A legitimate ending of the robe-making season:*";
P_HTM[11541]="*samaggo bhikkhunisaṅgho sannipatitvā uddharati.**a unanimous Sangha of nuns brings it to an end.*";
P_HTM[11542]="*Paṭibāheyyāti**Blocks:*";
P_HTM[11543]="*“kathaṃ idaṃ kathinaṃ na uddhareyyā”ti paṭibāhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she blocks it with the thought, “What can be done so that the robe-making season doesn’t end?”, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11544]="*Dhammike dhammikasaññā paṭibāhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she blocks it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11545]="*Dhammike vematikā paṭibāhati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she blocks it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11546]="*Dhammike adhammikasaññā paṭibāhati, anāpatti.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she blocks it, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11547]="*Adhammike dhammikasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11548]="*Adhammike vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11549]="*Adhammike adhammikasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11550]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11551]="*ānisaṃsaṃ dassetvā paṭibāhati,**if she blocks it after demonstrating a benefit;*";
P_HTM[11552]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11553]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11554]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11555]="*Naggavaggo tatiyo.**The third sub-chapter on nakedness is finished.*";
P_HTM[11556]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11557]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11558]="*31. Ekamañcatuvaṭṭanasikkhāpada**31. The training rule on lying down on the same bed*";
P_HTM[11559]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11560]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭenti.**two nuns were lying down on the same bed.*";
P_HTM[11561]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11562]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭessanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can two nuns lie down on the same bed? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[11563]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[11564]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11565]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns do this?” …*";
P_HTM[11566]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[11567]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11568]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11569]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[11570]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11571]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11572]="*“Yā pana bhikkhuniyo dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭeyyuṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If two nuns lie down on the same bed, they commit an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11573]="*Yā panāti**Two:*";
P_HTM[11574]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11575]="*bhikkhuniyoti**Nuns:*";
P_HTM[11576]="*upasampannāyo vuccanti.**fully ordained is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11577]="*Dve ekamañce tuvaṭṭeyyunti**If two lie down on the same bed:*";
P_HTM[11578]="*ekāya nipannāya aparā nipajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, when one is lying down, the other lies down, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11579]="*Ubho vā nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If both lie down together, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11580]="*Uṭṭhahitvā punappunaṃ nipajjanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time they get up and then lie down again, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11581]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11582]="*ekāya nipannāya aparā nisīdati,**if, when one is lying down, the other sits down;*";
P_HTM[11583]="*ubho vā nisīdanti,**if both sit down together;*";
P_HTM[11584]="*ummattikānaṃ,**if they are insane;*";
P_HTM[11585]="*ādikammikānanti.**if they are the first offenders.*";
P_HTM[11586]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11587]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11588]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11589]="*32. Ekattharaṇatuvaṭṭanasikkhāpada**32. The training rule on lying down on the same sheet*";
P_HTM[11590]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11591]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭenti.**two nuns were lying down on the same sheet and under the same cover.*";
P_HTM[11592]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11593]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭessanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can two nuns lie down on the same sheet and under the same cover? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[11594]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[11595]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11596]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns do this?” …*";
P_HTM[11597]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[11598]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11599]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11600]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[11601]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11602]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11603]="*“Yā pana bhikkhuniyo dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭeyyuṃ, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If two nuns lie down on the same sheet and under the same cover, they commit an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11604]="*Yā panāti**Two:*";
P_HTM[11605]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11606]="*bhikkhuniyoti**Nuns:*";
P_HTM[11607]="*upasampannāyo vuccanti.**fully ordained is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11608]="*Dve ekattharaṇapāvuraṇā tuvaṭṭeyyunti**If two lie down on the same sheet and under the same cover:*";
P_HTM[11609]="*taññeva attharitvā taññeva pārupanti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if they spread out just the one and cover themselves with just the one, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11610]="*Ekattharaṇapāvuraṇe ekattharaṇapāvuraṇasaññā tuvaṭṭenti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the same sheet and the same cover, and they perceive them as such, and they lie down, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11611]="*Ekattharaṇapāvuraṇe vematikā tuvaṭṭenti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the same sheet and the same cover, but they are unsure of it, and they lie down, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11612]="*Ekattharaṇapāvuraṇe nānattharaṇapāvuraṇasaññā tuvaṭṭenti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is the same sheet and the same cover, but they perceive them as different, and they lie down, they commit an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11613]="*Ekattharaṇe nānāpāvuraṇe, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is the same sheet but different covers, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11614]="*Nānattharaṇe ekapāvuraṇe, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is different sheets but the same cover, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11615]="*Nānattharaṇapāvuraṇe ekattharaṇapāvuraṇasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is different sheets and different covers, but they perceive them as the same, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11616]="*Nānattharaṇapāvuraṇe vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is different sheets and different covers, but they are unsure of it, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11617]="*Nānattharaṇapāvuraṇe nānattharaṇapāvuraṇasaññā, anāpatti.**If it is different sheets and different covers, and they perceive them as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[11618]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11619]="*vavatthānaṃ dassetvā nipajjanti,**if they make a partition and then lie down;*";
P_HTM[11620]="*ummattikānaṃ,**if they are insane;*";
P_HTM[11621]="*ādikammikānanti.**if they are the first offenders.*";
P_HTM[11622]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11623]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11624]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11625]="*33. Aphāsukaraṇasikkhāpada**33. The training rule on making ill at ease*";
P_HTM[11626]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11627]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ.**At that time the nun Thullanandā was a learned reciter, and she was confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[11628]="*Bhaddāpi kāpilānī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ uḷārasambhāvitā.**Bhaddā Kāpilānī, too, was a learned reciter who was confident and skilled at giving teachings, and she was respected for her excellence.*";
P_HTM[11629]="*Manussā—* **";
P_HTM[11630]="*“ayyā bhaddā kāpilānī bahussutā bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ uḷārasambhāvitā”ti bhaddaṃ kāpilāniṃ paṭhamaṃ payirupāsitvā, pacchā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ payirupāsanti.**Because of this, people visited Bhaddā Kāpilānī first and then Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[11631]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī issāpakatā—**Overcome by jealousy, Thullanandā thought,*";
P_HTM[11632]="*“imā kira appicchā santuṭṭhā pavivittā asaṃsaṭṭhā yā imā saññattibahulā viññattibahulā viharantī”ti bhaddāya kāpilāniyā purato caṅkamatipi tiṭṭhatipi nisīdatipi seyyampi kappeti uddisatipi uddisāpetipi sajjhāyampi karoti.**“These ones, who are supposedly contented and have few desires, who are supposedly secluded and not socializing, are always persuading and convincing people.” And in front of Bhaddā Kāpilānī, she walked back and forth, stood, sat down, and lay down, and she recited and had others recite, and she rehearsed.*";
P_HTM[11633]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11634]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā ayyāya bhaddāya kāpilāniyā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā intentionally make Bhaddā Kāpilānī ill at ease?” …*";
P_HTM[11635]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhaddāya kāpilāniyā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karotī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11636]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11637]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11638]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhaddāya kāpilāniyā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11639]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11640]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11641]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā sañcicca aphāsuṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun intentionally makes a nun ill at ease, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11642]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11643]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11644]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11645]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11646]="*Bhikkhuniyāti**A nun:*";
P_HTM[11647]="*aññāya bhikkhuniyā.**another nun.*";
P_HTM[11648]="*Sañciccāti**Intentionally:*";
P_HTM[11649]="*jānantī sañjānantī cecca abhivitaritvā vītikkamo.**knowing, perceiving, having intended, having decided, she transgresses.*";
P_HTM[11650]="*Aphāsuṃ kareyyāti—**Makes ill at ease:*";
P_HTM[11651]="*“iminā imissā aphāsu bhavissatī”ti anāpucchā purato caṅkamati vā tiṭṭhati vā nisīdati vā seyyaṃ vā kappeti uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā sajjhāyaṃ vā karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if, without asking permission, but thinking, “In this way she will be ill at ease,” she walks back and forth in front of her, or she stands, sits down, or lies down in front of her, or she recites, has others recite, or rehearses in front of her, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11652]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives her as such, and she intentionally makes her ill at ease, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11653]="*Upasampannāya vematikā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she intentionally makes her ill at ease, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11654]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā sañcicca aphāsuṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive her as such, and she intentionally makes her ill at ease, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11655]="*Anupasampannāya sañcicca aphāsuṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she intentionally makes her ill at ease, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11656]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11657]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11658]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11659]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11660]="*na aphāsuṃ kattukāmā āpucchā purato caṅkamati vā tiṭṭhati vā nisīdati vā seyyaṃ vā kappeti uddisati vā uddisāpeti vā sajjhāyaṃ vā karoti,**if, after asking permission and not desiring to make her ill at ease, she walks back and forth in front of her, or she stands, sits down, or lies down in front of her, or she recites, has others recite, or rehearses in front of her;*";
P_HTM[11661]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11662]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11663]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11664]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11665]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11666]="*34. Naupaṭṭhāpanasikkhāpada**34. The training rule on not having someone nursed*";
P_HTM[11667]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11668]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī dukkhitaṃ sahajīviniṃ neva upaṭṭheti na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti.**At that time a disciple of the nun Thullanandā was suffering, but Thullanandā neither nursed her nor made any effort to have someone else nurse her.*";
P_HTM[11669]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11670]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā dukkhitaṃ sahajīviniṃ neva upaṭṭhessati na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā not nurse a suffering disciple, nor make any effort to have someone else nurse her?” …*";
P_HTM[11671]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dukkhitaṃ sahajīviniṃ neva upaṭṭheti na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karotī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā didn’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[11672]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11673]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11674]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī dukkhitaṃ sahajīviniṃ neva upaṭṭhessati na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā not do this?*";
P_HTM[11675]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11676]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11677]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī dukkhitaṃ sahajīviniṃ neva upaṭṭheyya na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun neither nurses a suffering disciple, nor makes any effort to have someone else nurse her, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11678]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11679]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11680]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11681]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11682]="*Dukkhitā nāma**Suffering:*";
P_HTM[11683]="*gilānā vuccati.**sick is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11684]="*Sahajīvinī nāma**Disciple:*";
P_HTM[11685]="*saddhivihārinī vuccati.**a student is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11686]="*Neva upaṭṭheyyāti**Neither nurses:*";
P_HTM[11687]="*na sayaṃ upaṭṭheyya.**does not herself nurse her.*";
P_HTM[11688]="*Na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyyāti**Nor makes any effort to have someone else nurse her:*";
P_HTM[11689]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya.**she does not ask anyone else.*";
P_HTM[11690]="*“Neva upaṭṭhessāmi, na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I will neither nurse her nor make any effort to have someone else nurse her,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11691]="*Antevāsiniṃ vā anupasampannaṃ vā neva upaṭṭheti, na upaṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she neither nurses, nor makes any effort to have someone else nurse, a pupil or one who is not fully ordained, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11692]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11693]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[11694]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches but does not find a nurse;*";
P_HTM[11695]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[11696]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11697]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11698]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11699]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11700]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11701]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11702]="*35. Nikkaḍḍhanasikkhāpada**35. The training rule on throwing out*";
P_HTM[11703]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11704]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhaddā kāpilānī sākete vassaṃ upagatā hoti.**At that time Bhaddā Kāpilānī had entered the rainy-season residence at Sāketa.*";
P_HTM[11705]="*Sā kenacideva karaṇīyena ubbāḷhā thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā santike dūtaṃ pāhesi—**But because she was disturbed by a certain matter, she sent a message to the nun Thullanandā:*";
P_HTM[11706]="*“sace me ayyā thullanandā upassayaṃ dadeyya āgaccheyyāmahaṃ sāvatthin”ti.**“If you would give me a dwelling place, I would come to Sāvatthī.”*";
P_HTM[11707]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī evamāha—**Thullanandā replied,*";
P_HTM[11708]="*“āgacchatu, dassāmī”ti.**“Please come; I’ll give you one.”*";
P_HTM[11709]="*Atha kho bhaddā kāpilānī sāketā sāvatthiṃ agamāsi.**Bhaddā Kāpilānī then traveled from Sāketa to Sāvatthī,*";
P_HTM[11710]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī bhaddāya kāpilāniyā upassayaṃ adāsi.**and Thullanandā gave her a dwelling place.*";
P_HTM[11711]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ.**At that time Thullanandā was a learned reciter, and she was confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[11712]="*Bhaddāpi kāpilānī bahussutā hoti bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ uḷārasambhāvitā.**Bhaddā Kāpilānī, too, was a learned reciter who was confident and skilled at giving teachings, and she was respected for her excellence.*";
P_HTM[11713]="*Manussā—* **";
P_HTM[11714]="*“ayyā bhaddā kāpilānī bahussutā bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ uḷārasambhāvitā”ti bhaddaṃ kāpilāniṃ paṭhamaṃ payirupāsitvā pacchā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ payirupāsanti.**Because of this, people visited Bhaddā Kāpilānī first and then Thullanandā.*";
P_HTM[11715]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī issāpakatā—**Overcome by jealousy, Thullanandā thought,*";
P_HTM[11716]="*“imā kira appicchā santuṭṭhā pavivittā asaṃsaṭṭhā yā imā saññattibahulā viññattibahulā viharantī”ti kupitā anattamanā bhaddaṃ kāpilāniṃ upassayā nikkaḍḍhi.**“These ones, who are supposedly contented and have few desires, who are supposedly secluded and not socializing, are always persuading and convincing people.” And in anger she threw Bhaddā Kāpilānī out of that dwelling place.*";
P_HTM[11717]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11718]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā ayyāya bhaddāya kāpilāniyā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give a dwelling place to Venerable Bhaddā Kāpilānī and then throw her out in anger?” …*";
P_HTM[11719]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhaddāya kāpilāniyā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[11720]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11721]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11722]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhaddāya kāpilāniyā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[11723]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11724]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11725]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍheyya vā nikkaḍḍhāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives a dwelling place to a nun, and then, in anger, throws her out or has her thrown out, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11726]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11727]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11728]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11729]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11730]="*Bhikkhuniyāti**To a nun:*";
P_HTM[11731]="*aññāya bhikkhuniyā.**To another nun.*";
P_HTM[11732]="*Upassayo nāma**A dwelling place:*";
P_HTM[11733]="*kavāṭabaddho vuccati.**one that has a door is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[11734]="*Datvāti**Gives:*";
P_HTM[11735]="*sayaṃ datvā.**she gives it herself.*";
P_HTM[11736]="*Kupitā anattamanāti**In anger:*";
P_HTM[11737]="*anabhiraddhā āhatacittā khilajātā.**discontent, having hatred, hostile.*";
P_HTM[11738]="*Nikkaḍḍheyyāti**Throws out:*";
P_HTM[11739]="*gabbhe gahetvā pamukhaṃ nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she takes hold of her in a room and throws her out to the entryway, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11740]="*Pamukhe gahetvā bahi nikkaḍḍhati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she takes hold of her in the entryway and throws her outside, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11741]="*Ekena payogena bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Even if she makes her go through many doors with a single effort, she commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11742]="*Nikkaḍḍhāpeyyāti**Has thrown out:*";
P_HTM[11743]="*aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she asks another, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11744]="*Sakiṃ āṇattā bahukepi dvāre atikkāmeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she only asks once, then even if the other makes her go through many doors, she commits one offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11745]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives her as such, and she gives her a dwelling place, and she then throws her out in anger or has her thrown out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11746]="*Upasampannāya vematikā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she gives her a dwelling place, and she then throws her out in anger or has her thrown out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11747]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā upassayaṃ datvā kupitā anattamanā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive her as such, and she gives her a dwelling place, and she then throws her out in anger or has her thrown out, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11748]="*Tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she throws out one of her requisites, or she has it thrown out, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11749]="*Akavāṭabaddhā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she throws her out or has her thrown out from a dwelling place without a door, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11750]="*Tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she throws out one of her requisites from a dwelling place without a door, or she has it thrown out, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11751]="*Anupasampannaṃ kavāṭabaddhā vā akavāṭabaddhā vā nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she throws out one who is not fully ordained, or she has her thrown out, from a dwelling place with or without a door, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11752]="*Tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she throws out one of her requisites from that place, or she has it thrown out, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11753]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11754]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11755]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11756]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11757]="*alajjiniṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, one who is shameless;*";
P_HTM[11758]="*tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;*";
P_HTM[11759]="*ummattikaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, one who is insane;*";
P_HTM[11760]="*tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;*";
P_HTM[11761]="*bhaṇḍanakārikaṃ kalahakārikaṃ vivādakārikaṃ bhassakārikaṃ saṅghe adhikaraṇakārikaṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, one who is quarrelsome and argumentative, and who creates legal issues in the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[11762]="*tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;*";
P_HTM[11763]="*antevāsiniṃ vā saddhivihāriniṃ vā na sammā vattantiṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, a pupil or student who is not conducting herself properly;*";
P_HTM[11764]="*tassā parikkhāraṃ nikkaḍḍhati vā nikkaḍḍhāpeti vā,**if she throws out, or has thrown out, a requisite belonging to that person;*";
P_HTM[11765]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11766]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11767]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11768]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11769]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11770]="*36. Saṃsaṭṭhasikkhāpada**36. The training rule on socializing*";
P_HTM[11771]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11772]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī saṃsaṭṭhā viharati gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi.**the nun Caṇḍakāḷī was socializing with a householder and their child.*";
P_HTM[11773]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[11774]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā caṇḍakāḷī saṃsaṭṭhā viharissati gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Caṇḍakāḷī socialize with a householder and their child?” …*";
P_HTM[11775]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī saṃsaṭṭhā viharati gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Caṇḍakāḷī does this?”*";
P_HTM[11776]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11777]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[11778]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī saṃsaṭṭhā viharissati gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi.**“How can the nun Caṇḍakāḷī do this?*";
P_HTM[11779]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11780]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11781]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī saṃsaṭṭhā vihareyya gahapatinā vā gahapatiputtena vā sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi evamassa vacanīyā—**‘If a nun is socializing with a householder or a householder’s child, the nuns should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[11782]="*‘māyye, saṃsaṭṭhā vihari gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi. Viviccāyye; vivekaññeva bhaginiyā saṅgho vaṇṇetī’ti.**“Venerable, don’t socialize with householders or householders’ children. Be secluded, Venerable. The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[11783]="*Evañca sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi vuccamānā tatheva paggaṇheyya, sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīhi yāvatatiyaṃ samanubhāsitabbā tassa paṭinissaggāya.**If that nun continues as before, the nuns should press her up to three times to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[11784]="*Yāvatatiyañce samanubhāsīyamānā taṃ paṭinissajjeyya, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ; no ce paṭinissajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**If she then stops, all is well. If she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11785]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11786]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11787]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11788]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11789]="*Saṃsaṭṭhā nāma**Socializing:*";
P_HTM[11790]="*ananulomikena kāyikavācasikena saṃsaṭṭhā.**she socializes with improper bodily and verbal actions.*";
P_HTM[11791]="*Gahapati nāma**A householder:*";
P_HTM[11792]="*yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**whoever lives at home.*";
P_HTM[11793]="*Gahapatiputto nāma**A householder’s child:*";
P_HTM[11794]="*ye keci puttabhātaro.**whoever is a child or a sibling.*";
P_HTM[11795]="*Sā bhikkhunīti**Her:*";
P_HTM[11796]="*yā sā saṃsaṭṭhā bhikkhunī.**the nun who is socializing.*";
P_HTM[11797]="*Bhikkhunīhīti**The nuns:*";
P_HTM[11798]="*aññāhi bhikkhunīhi. Yā passanti yā suṇanti tāhi vattabbā—**Other nuns who see it or hear about it. They should correct her like this:*";
P_HTM[11799]="*“māyye, saṃsaṭṭhā vihari gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi.**“Venerable, don’t socialize with householders or householders’ children.*";
P_HTM[11800]="*Viviccāyye;**Be secluded, Venerable.*";
P_HTM[11801]="*vivekaññeva bhaginiyā saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[11802]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**And they should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[11803]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[11804]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[11805]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11806]="*Sutvā na vadanti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If those who heard about it do not say anything, they commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11807]="*Sā bhikkhunī saṅghamajjhampi ākaḍḍhitvā vattabbā—**That nun, even if she has to be pulled into the Sangha, should be corrected like this:*";
P_HTM[11808]="*“māyye, saṃsaṭṭhā vihari gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi.**“Venerable, don’t socialize with householders or householders’ children.*";
P_HTM[11809]="*Viviccāyye;**Be secluded, Venerable.*";
P_HTM[11810]="*vivekaññeva bhaginiyā saṅgho vaṇṇetī”ti.**The Sangha praises seclusion for the Sisters.”*";
P_HTM[11811]="*Dutiyampi vattabbā.**They should correct her a second*";
P_HTM[11812]="*Tatiyampi vattabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[11813]="*Sace paṭinissajjati, iccetaṃ kusalaṃ;**If she stops, all is well.*";
P_HTM[11814]="*no ce paṭinissajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not stop, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11815]="*Sā bhikkhunī samanubhāsitabbā.**Should press her:*";
P_HTM[11816]="*“Evañca pana, bhikkhave, samanubhāsitabbā.**“And, monks, she should be pressed like this.*";
P_HTM[11817]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[11818]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[11819]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī saṃsaṭṭhā viharati gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi.**The nun so-and-so is socializing with householders and householders’ children.*";
P_HTM[11820]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on doing it.*";
P_HTM[11821]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāseyya tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should press her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[11822]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[11823]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[11824]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā bhikkhunī saṃsaṭṭhā viharati gahapatināpi gahapatiputtenapi.**The nun so-and-so is socializing with householders and householders’ children.*";
P_HTM[11825]="*Sā taṃ vatthuṃ na paṭinissajjati.**And she keeps on doing it.*";
P_HTM[11826]="*Saṅgho itthannāmaṃ bhikkhuniṃ samanubhāsati tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya.**The Sangha presses her to make her stop.*";
P_HTM[11827]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya bhikkhuniyā samanubhāsanā tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of pressing her to make her stop should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[11828]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[11829]="*Dutiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe…**For the second time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[11830]="*tatiyampi etamatthaṃ vadāmi …pe….**For the third time I speak on this matter …*";
P_HTM[11831]="*Samanubhaṭṭhā saṅghena itthannāmā bhikkhunī tassa vatthussa paṭinissaggāya;**The Sangha has pressed nun so-and-so to stop.*";
P_HTM[11832]="*khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[11833]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11834]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11835]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11836]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11837]="*Dhammakamme vematikā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11838]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā na paṭinissajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she does not stop, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11839]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11840]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11841]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[11842]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11843]="*asamanubhāsantiyā,**if she has not been pressed;*";
P_HTM[11844]="*paṭinissajjantiyā,**if she stops;*";
P_HTM[11845]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11846]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11847]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11848]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11849]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11850]="*37. Antoraṭṭhasikkhāpada**37. The training rule on within their own country*";
P_HTM[11851]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11852]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo antoraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ caranti.**At that time the nuns went wandering without a group of travelers where it was considered risky and dangerous within their own country.*";
P_HTM[11853]="*Dhuttā dūsenti.**Scoundrels raped them.*";
P_HTM[11854]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11855]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo antoraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns go wandering without a group of travelers where it’s considered risky and dangerous within their own country?” …*";
P_HTM[11856]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo antoraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[11857]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11858]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11859]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo antoraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[11860]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11861]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11862]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī antoraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ careyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun goes wandering without a group of travelers where it is considered risky and dangerous within her own country, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11863]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11864]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11865]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11866]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11867]="*Antoraṭṭheti**Within her own country:*";
P_HTM[11868]="*yassa vijite viharati, tassa raṭṭhe.**in the country where she is living.*";
P_HTM[11869]="*Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma**Risky:*";
P_HTM[11870]="*tasmiṃ magge corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati.**a place has been seen along that road where criminals are camped, eating, standing, sitting, or lying down.*";
P_HTM[11871]="*Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma**Dangerous:*";
P_HTM[11872]="*tasmiṃ magge corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā dissanti.**criminals have been seen along that road, injuring, robbing, or beating people.*";
P_HTM[11873]="*Asatthikā nāma**Without a group of travelers:*";
P_HTM[11874]="*vinā satthena.**in the absence of a group of travelers.*";
P_HTM[11875]="*Cārikaṃ careyyāti**Goes wandering:*";
P_HTM[11876]="*kukkuṭasampāte gāme gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11877]="*Agāmake araññe addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11878]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11879]="*satthena saha gacchati,**if she travels with a group;*";
P_HTM[11880]="*kheme appaṭibhaye gacchati,**if she travels where it is safe and free from danger;*";
P_HTM[11881]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11882]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11883]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11884]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11885]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11886]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11887]="*38. Tiroraṭṭhasikkhāpada**38. The training rule on outside their own country*";
P_HTM[11888]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[11889]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo tiroraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ caranti.**At that time the nuns went wandering without a group of travelers where it was considered risky and dangerous outside their own country.*";
P_HTM[11890]="*Dhuttā dūsenti.**Scoundrels raped them.*";
P_HTM[11891]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11892]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo tiroraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns go wandering without a group of travelers where it’s considered risky and dangerous outside their own country?” …*";
P_HTM[11893]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo tiroraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[11894]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11895]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11896]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo tiroraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ carissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[11897]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11898]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11899]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī tiroraṭṭhe sāsaṅkasammate sappaṭibhaye asatthikā cārikaṃ careyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun goes wandering without a group of travelers where it is considered risky and dangerous outside her own country, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11900]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11901]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11902]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11903]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11904]="*Tiroraṭṭheti**Outside her own country:*";
P_HTM[11905]="*yassa vijite viharati, taṃ ṭhapetvā aññassa raṭṭhe.**in any country apart from the one where she is living.*";
P_HTM[11906]="*Sāsaṅkaṃ nāma**Risky:*";
P_HTM[11907]="*tasmiṃ magge corānaṃ niviṭṭhokāso dissati, bhuttokāso dissati, ṭhitokāso dissati, nisinnokāso dissati, nipannokāso dissati.**a place has been seen along that road where criminals are camped, eating, standing, sitting, or lying down.*";
P_HTM[11908]="*Sappaṭibhayaṃ nāma**Dangerous:*";
P_HTM[11909]="*tasmiṃ magge corehi manussā hatā dissanti, viluttā dissanti, ākoṭitā dissanti.**criminals have been seen along that road, injuring, robbing, or beating people.*";
P_HTM[11910]="*Asatthikā nāma**Without a group of travelers:*";
P_HTM[11911]="*vinā satthena.**in the absence of a group of travelers.*";
P_HTM[11912]="*Cārikaṃ careyyāti**Goes wandering:*";
P_HTM[11913]="*kukkuṭasampāte gāme gāmantare gāmantare, āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11914]="*Agāmake araññe addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11915]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11916]="*satthena saha gacchati,**if she travels with a group;*";
P_HTM[11917]="*kheme appaṭibhaye gacchati,**if she travels where it is safe and free from danger;*";
P_HTM[11918]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11919]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11920]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11921]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11922]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11923]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11924]="*39. Antovassasikkhāpada**39. The training rule on during the rainy season*";
P_HTM[11925]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary,*";
P_HTM[11926]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo antovassaṃ cārikaṃ caranti.**the nuns went wandering during the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[11927]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11928]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo antovassaṃ cārikaṃ carissanti haritāni tiṇāni ca sammaddantā, ekindriyaṃ jīvaṃ viheṭhentā, bahū khuddake pāṇe saṅghātaṃ āpādentā”ti.**“How can the nuns go wandering during the rainy season? They are trampling down the green grass, harming one-sensed life, and destroying many small beings.”*";
P_HTM[11929]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[11930]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11931]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo antovassaṃ cārikaṃ carissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns go wandering during the rainy season?” …*";
P_HTM[11932]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo antovassaṃ cārikaṃ carantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[11933]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[11934]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[11935]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo antovassaṃ cārikaṃ carissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[11936]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[11937]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11938]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī antovassaṃ cārikaṃ careyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun goes wandering during the rainy season, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11939]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11940]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11941]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11942]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11943]="*Antovassanti**During the rainy season:*";
P_HTM[11944]="*purimaṃ vā temāsaṃ pacchimaṃ vā temāsaṃ avasitvā.**not having stayed put for the first three or the last three months of the rainy season.*";
P_HTM[11945]="*Cārikaṃ careyyāti**Goes wandering:*";
P_HTM[11946]="*kukkuṭasampāte gāme gāmantare gāmantare āpatti pācittiyassa.**when the villages are a chicken’s flight apart, then for every next village she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11947]="*Agāmake araññe addhayojane addhayojane āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it is an uninhabited area, a wilderness, then for every six kilometers she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11948]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11949]="*sattāhakaraṇīyena gacchati,**if she goes on seven-day business;*";
P_HTM[11950]="*kenaci ubbāḷhā gacchati,**if she goes because something is disturbing her;*";
P_HTM[11951]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11952]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11953]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11954]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11955]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11956]="*Tuvaṭṭavagga**The sub-chapter on lying down*";
P_HTM[11957]="*40. Cārikanapakkamanasikkhāpada**40. The training rule on going wandering*";
P_HTM[11958]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Rājagaha in the Bamboo Grove, the squirrel sanctuary.*";
P_HTM[11959]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo tattheva rājagahe vassaṃ vasanti, tattha hemantaṃ, tattha gimhaṃ.**At that time the nuns were staying right there at Rājagaha for the rainy season, the cold season, and the hot season.*";
P_HTM[11960]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11961]="*“āhundarikā bhikkhunīnaṃ disā andhakārā, na imāsaṃ disā pakkhāyantī”ti.**“The nuns are leaving the districts in darkness and obscurity. They don’t brighten them up.”*";
P_HTM[11962]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[11963]="*Atha kho tā bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They then told the monks,*";
P_HTM[11964]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[11965]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**Soon afterwards the Buddha gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[11966]="*“tena hi, bhikkhave, bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññapessāmi dasa atthavase paṭicca—**“Well then, monks, I will lay down a training rule for the nuns for the following ten reasons:*";
P_HTM[11967]="*saṅghasuṭṭhutāya …pe…**for the well-being of the Sangha …*";
P_HTM[11968]="*saddhammaṭṭhitiyā vinayānuggahāya.**for the longevity of the true Teaching, and for supporting the training.*";
P_HTM[11969]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[11970]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī vassaṃvuṭṭhā cārikaṃ na pakkameyya antamaso chappañcayojanānipi, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun who has completed the rainy-season residence does not go wandering, even if only 65 to 80 kilometers, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[11971]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[11972]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[11973]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[11974]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[11975]="*Vassaṃvuṭṭhā nāma**Who has completed the rainy-season residence:*";
P_HTM[11976]="*purimaṃ vā temāsaṃ pacchimaṃ vā temāsaṃ vuṭṭhā.**who has completed the first three or the last three months of the rainy-season residence.*";
P_HTM[11977]="*“Cārikaṃ na pakkamissāmi antamaso chappañcayojanānipī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I won’t go wandering, not even 65 to 80 kilometers,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[11978]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[11979]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[11980]="*pariyesitvā dutiyikaṃ bhikkhuniṃ na labhati,**if she searches for a companion nun, but is unable to find one;*";
P_HTM[11981]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[11982]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[11983]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[11984]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[11985]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[11986]="*Tuvaṭṭavaggo catuttho.**The fourth sub-chapter on lying down is finished.*";
P_HTM[11987]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[11988]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[11989]="*41. Rājāgārasikkhāpada**41. The training rule on royal houses*";
P_HTM[11990]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[11991]="*Tena kho pana samayena rañño pasenadissa kosalassa uyyāne cittāgāre paṭibhānacittaṃ kataṃ hoti.**artwork had been installed in the pleasure house in King Pasenadi of Kosala’s park.*";
P_HTM[11992]="*Bahū manussā cittāgāraṃ dassanāya gacchanti.**Many people visited the pleasure house,*";
P_HTM[11993]="*Chabbaggiyāpi bhikkhuniyo cittāgāraṃ dassanāya agamaṃsu.**as did the nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[11994]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11995]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo cittāgāraṃ dassanāya gacchissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns visit a pleasure house? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[11996]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[11997]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[11998]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo cittāgāraṃ dassanāya gacchissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the nuns from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[11999]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo cittāgāraṃ dassanāya gacchantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[12000]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12001]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12002]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo cittāgāraṃ dassanāya gacchissanti.**“How could the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[12003]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12004]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12005]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī rājāgāraṃ vā cittāgāraṃ vā ārāmaṃ vā uyyānaṃ vā pokkharaṇiṃ vā dassanāya gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun visits a royal house or a pleasure house or a park or a garden or a lotus pond, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12006]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12007]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12008]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12009]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12010]="*Rājāgāraṃ nāma**A royal house:*";
P_HTM[12011]="*yattha katthaci rañño kīḷituṃ ramituṃ kataṃ hoti.**wherever one has been built for a king to entertain and enjoy himself.*";
P_HTM[12012]="*Cittāgāraṃ nāma**A pleasure house:*";
P_HTM[12013]="*yattha katthaci manussānaṃ kīḷituṃ ramituṃ kataṃ hoti.**wherever one has been built for a people to entertain and enjoy themselves.*";
P_HTM[12014]="*Ārāmo nāma**A park:*";
P_HTM[12015]="*yattha katthaci manussānaṃ kīḷituṃ ramituṃ kato hoti.**wherever one has been made for a people to entertain and enjoy themselves.*";
P_HTM[12016]="*Uyyānaṃ nāma**A garden:*";
P_HTM[12017]="*yattha katthaci manussānaṃ kīḷituṃ ramituṃ kataṃ hoti.**wherever one has been made for a people to entertain and enjoy themselves.*";
P_HTM[12018]="*Pokkharaṇī nāma**A lotus pond:*";
P_HTM[12019]="*yattha katthaci manussānaṃ kīḷituṃ ramituṃ katā hoti.**wherever one has been made for a people to entertain and enjoy themselves.*";
P_HTM[12020]="*Dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is on her way to visit them, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12021]="*Yattha ṭhitā passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever she stands to see them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12022]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time she moves outside the range of sight and then sees them again, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12023]="*Ekamekaṃ dassanāya gacchati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is on her way to visit any one of them, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12024]="*Yattha ṭhitā passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Wherever she stands to see it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12025]="*Dassanūpacāraṃ vijahitvā punappunaṃ passati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**Every time she moves outside the range of sight and then sees it again, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12026]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12027]="*ārāme ṭhitā passati,**if she sees it while remaining in a monastery;*";
P_HTM[12028]="*gacchantī vā āgacchantī vā passati,**if she sees it while coming or going;*";
P_HTM[12029]="*sati karaṇīye gantvā passati,**if she goes when there is something to be done and then sees it;*";
P_HTM[12030]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12031]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12032]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12033]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12034]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12035]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12036]="*42. Āsandiparibhuñjanasikkhāpada**42. The training rule on using high couches*";
P_HTM[12037]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12038]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo āsandimpi pallaṅkampi paribhuñjanti.**the nuns were using high and luxurious couches.*";
P_HTM[12039]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12040]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo āsandimpi pallaṅkampi paribhuñjissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns use high and luxurious couches? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[12041]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[12042]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12043]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo āsandimpi pallaṅkampi paribhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns do this?” …*";
P_HTM[12044]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo āsandimpi pallaṅkampi paribhuñjantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[12045]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12046]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12047]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo āsandimpi pallaṅkampi paribhuñjissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[12048]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12049]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12050]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī āsandiṃ vā pallaṅkaṃ vā paribhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun uses a high or luxurious couch, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12051]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12052]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12053]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12054]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12055]="*Āsandī nāma**A high couch:*";
P_HTM[12056]="*atikkantappamāṇā vuccati.**one that is oversize is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12057]="*Pallaṅko nāma**A luxurious couch:*";
P_HTM[12058]="*āharimehi vāḷehi kato hoti.**one decorated with images of predatory animals.*";
P_HTM[12059]="*Paribhuñjeyyāti**Uses:*";
P_HTM[12060]="*tasmiṃ abhinisīdati vā abhinipajjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she sits down or lies down on it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12061]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12062]="*āsandiyā pāde chinditvā paribhuñjati,**if she uses a high couch after cutting off the legs;*";
P_HTM[12063]="*pallaṅkassa vāḷe bhinditvā paribhuñjati,**if she uses a luxurious couch after removing the decorations with images of predatory animals;*";
P_HTM[12064]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12065]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12066]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12067]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12068]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12069]="*43. Suttakantanasikkhāpada**43. The training rule on spinning yarn*";
P_HTM[12070]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12071]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo suttaṃ kantanti.**the nuns from the group of six were spinning yarn.*";
P_HTM[12072]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12073]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo suttaṃ kantissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can the nuns spin yarn? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[12074]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[12075]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12076]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo suttaṃ kantissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six spin yarn?” …*";
P_HTM[12077]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo suttaṃ kantantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[12078]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12079]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12080]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo suttaṃ kantissanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[12081]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12082]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12083]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī suttaṃ kanteyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun spins yarn, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12084]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12085]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12086]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12087]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12088]="*Suttaṃ nāma**Yarn:*";
P_HTM[12089]="*cha suttāni—**there are six kinds of yarn:*";
P_HTM[12090]="*khomaṃ, kappāsikaṃ, koseyyaṃ, kambalaṃ, sāṇaṃ, bhaṅgaṃ.**linen, cotton, silk, wool, sunn hemp, and hemp.*";
P_HTM[12091]="*Kanteyyāti**Spins:*";
P_HTM[12092]="*sayaṃ kantati, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**if she spins it herself, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12093]="*Ujjavujjave āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every pull, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12094]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12095]="*kantitasuttaṃ kantati,**if she spins yarn that has already been spun;*";
P_HTM[12096]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12097]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12098]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12099]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12100]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12101]="*44. Gihiveyyāvaccasikkhāpada**44. The training rule on providing services for householders*";
P_HTM[12102]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12103]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo gihiveyyāvaccaṃ karonti.**the nuns were providing services for householders.*";
P_HTM[12104]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12105]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo gihiveyyāvaccaṃ karissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns provide services for householders?” …*";
P_HTM[12106]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo gihiveyyāvaccaṃ karontī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[12107]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12108]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12109]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo gihiveyyāvaccaṃ karissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[12110]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12111]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12112]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī gihiveyyāvaccaṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun provides services for a householder, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12113]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12114]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12115]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12116]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12117]="*Gihiveyyāvaccaṃ nāma**Services for a householder:*";
P_HTM[12118]="*agārikassa yāguṃ vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā pacati, sāṭakaṃ vā veṭhanaṃ vā dhovati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she cooks rice porridge, a meal, or fresh food for a householder, or she washes a wrap garment or a turban for them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12119]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12120]="*yāgupāne,**if it is a rice-porridge drink;*";
P_HTM[12121]="*saṅghabhatte,**if it is a meal for the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[12122]="*cetiyapūjāya,**if it is to venerate a shrine;*";
P_HTM[12123]="*attano veyyāvaccakarassa yāguṃ vā bhattaṃ vā khādanīyaṃ vā pacati, sāṭakaṃ vā veṭhanaṃ vā dhovati,**if she cooks rice porridge, a meal, or fresh food for her own service-provider, or she washes a wrap garment or a turban for them;*";
P_HTM[12124]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12125]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12126]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12127]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12128]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12129]="*45. Adhikaraṇasikkhāpada**45. The training rule on legal issues*";
P_HTM[12130]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12131]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca—**a certain nun went to the nun Thullanandā and said,*";
P_HTM[12132]="*“ehāyye, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehī”ti.**“Please come, Venerable, and resolve this legal issue.”*";
P_HTM[12133]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—**Thullanandā agreed,*";
P_HTM[12134]="*“sādhū”ti paṭissuṇitvā, neva vūpasameti na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karoti.**but then neither resolved it nor made any effort to do so.*";
P_HTM[12135]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That nun told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[12136]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12137]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā bhikkhuniyā—**“How could Venerable Thullanandā*";
P_HTM[12138]="*‘ehāyye, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehī’ti vuccamānā—* **";
P_HTM[12139]="*‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā, neva vūpasamessati na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**agree to resolve a legal issue, but then neither resolve it nor make any effort to do so?” …*";
P_HTM[12140]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā—**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[12141]="*‘ehāyye, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehī’ti vuccamānā—* **";
P_HTM[12142]="*‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā, neva vūpasameti na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[12143]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12144]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12145]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā—**“How could the nun Thullanandā act like this?*";
P_HTM[12146]="*‘ehāyye, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehī’ti vuccamānā—* **";
P_HTM[12147]="*‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā, neva vūpasamessati na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karissati.* **";
P_HTM[12148]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12149]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12150]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā—‘ehāyye, imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehī’ti vuccamānā—‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva vūpasameyya na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If, when asked by a nun, a nun consents to resolve a legal issue, but then neither resolves it nor makes any effort to resolve it, then, if there was no obstruction, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12151]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12152]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12153]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12154]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12155]="*Bhikkhuniyāti**By a nun:*";
P_HTM[12156]="*aññāya bhikkhuniyā.**by another nun.*";
P_HTM[12157]="*Adhikaraṇaṃ nāma**A legal issue:*";
P_HTM[12158]="*cattāri adhikaraṇāni— vivādādhikaraṇaṃ, anuvādādhikaraṇaṃ, āpattādhikaraṇaṃ, kiccādhikaraṇaṃ.**there are four kinds of legal issues: legal issues arising from disputes, legal issues arising from accusations, legal issues arising from offenses, legal issues arising from business.*";
P_HTM[12159]="*Ehāyye imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vūpasamehīti**To resolve a legal issue:*";
P_HTM[12160]="*ehāyye imaṃ adhikaraṇaṃ vinicchehi.**to decide a legal issue.*";
P_HTM[12161]="*Sā pacchā anantarāyikinīti**Then, if there was no obstruction:*";
P_HTM[12162]="*asati antarāye.**when there is no obstacle.*";
P_HTM[12163]="*Neva vūpasameyyāti**Neither resolves it:*";
P_HTM[12164]="*na sayaṃ vūpasameyya.**she does not resolve it herself.*";
P_HTM[12165]="*Na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ kareyyāti**Nor makes any effort to resolve it:*";
P_HTM[12166]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya.**she does not ask anyone else.*";
P_HTM[12167]="*“Neva vūpasamessāmi na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karissāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If, thinking, “I’ll neither resolve it nor make any effort to resolve it,” then, by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12168]="*Upasampannāya upasampannasaññā adhikaraṇaṃ neva vūpasameti na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, and she perceives her as such, and she neither resolves the legal issue nor makes any effort to resolve it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12169]="*Upasampannāya vematikā adhikaraṇaṃ neva vūpasameti, na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she neither resolves the legal issue nor makes any effort to resolve it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12170]="*Upasampannāya anupasampannasaññā adhikaraṇaṃ neva vūpasameti, na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karoti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the other person is fully ordained, but she does not perceive her as such, and she neither resolves the legal issue nor makes any effort to resolve it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12171]="*Anupasampannāya adhikaraṇaṃ neva vūpasameti, na vūpasamāya ussukkaṃ karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she neither resolves the legal issue nor makes any effort to resolve it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12172]="*Anupasampannāya upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12173]="*Anupasampannāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12174]="*Anupasampannāya anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the other person is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12175]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12176]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[12177]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches, but is unable to find anyone to settle it;*";
P_HTM[12178]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[12179]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12180]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12181]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12182]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12183]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12184]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12185]="*46. Bhojanadānasikkhāpada**46. The training rule on giving food*";
P_HTM[12186]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12187]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī naṭānampi naṭakānampi laṅghakānampi sokajjhāyikānampi kumbhathūṇikānampi sahatthā khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ deti—**At that time the nun Thullanandā was personally giving food to actors, dancers, acrobats, magicians, and musicians, saying,*";
P_HTM[12188]="*“mayhaṃ parisati vaṇṇaṃ bhāsathā”ti.**“Please praise me in public.”*";
P_HTM[12189]="*Naṭāpi naṭakāpi laṅghakāpi sokajjhāyikāpi kumbhathūṇikāpi thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā parisati vaṇṇaṃ bhāsanti—**And they did:*";
P_HTM[12190]="*“ayyā thullanandā bahussutā bhāṇikā visāradā paṭṭā dhammiṃ kathaṃ kātuṃ;**“Venerable Thullanandā is a learned reciter; she’s confident and skilled at giving teachings.*";
P_HTM[12191]="*detha ayyāya, karotha ayyāyā”ti.**Give to her; work for her!”*";
P_HTM[12192]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12193]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā agārikassa sahatthā khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ dassatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā personally give food to householders?” …*";
P_HTM[12194]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī agārikassa sahatthā khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ detī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā does this?”*";
P_HTM[12195]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12196]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12197]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī agārikassa sahatthā khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ dassati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[12198]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12199]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12200]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī agārikassa vā paribbājakassa vā paribbājikāya vā sahatthā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā dadeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun personally gives fresh or cooked food to a householder or a male wanderer or a female wanderer, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12201]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12202]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12203]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12204]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12205]="*Agāriko nāma**A householder:*";
P_HTM[12206]="*yo koci agāraṃ ajjhāvasati.**anyone who lives at home.*";
P_HTM[12207]="*Paribbājako nāma**A male wanderer:*";
P_HTM[12208]="*bhikkhuñca sāmaṇerañca ṭhapetvā yo koci paribbājakasamāpanno.**any male wanderer apart from Buddhist monks and novice monks.*";
P_HTM[12209]="*Paribbājikā nāma**A female wanderer:*";
P_HTM[12210]="*bhikkhuniñca sikkhamānañca sāmaṇeriñca ṭhapetvā yā kāci paribbājikasamāpannā.**any female wanderer apart from Buddhist nuns, trainee nuns, and novice nuns.*";
P_HTM[12211]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[12212]="*pañca bhojanāni—**apart from the five cooked foods*";
P_HTM[12213]="*udakadantaponaṃ ṭhapetvā avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**and water and tooth cleaners, the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[12214]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[12215]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[12216]="*Dadeyyāti**Gives:*";
P_HTM[12217]="*kāyena vā kāyapaṭibaddhena vā nissaggiyena vā deti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she gives by body or by what is connected to the body or by releasing, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12218]="*Udakadantaponaṃ deti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she gives water or tooth cleaners, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12219]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12220]="*dāpeti na deti,**if she does not give, but has it given;*";
P_HTM[12221]="*upanikkhipitvā deti,**if she gives by placing it near the person;*";
P_HTM[12222]="*bāhirālepaṃ deti,**if she gives ointments for external use;*";
P_HTM[12223]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12224]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12225]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12226]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12227]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12228]="*47. Āvasathacīvarasikkhāpada**47. The training rule on monastery robes*";
P_HTM[12229]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12230]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī āvasathacīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjati.**At that time the nun Thullanandā did not relinquish the monastery robe, but continued using it.*";
P_HTM[12231]="*Aññā utuniyo bhikkhuniyo na labhanti.**Other menstruating nuns did not get to use it.*";
P_HTM[12232]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12233]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā āvasathacīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā not relinquish the monastery robe, but continue using it?” …*";
P_HTM[12234]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī āvasathacīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[12235]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12236]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12237]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī āvasathacīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[12238]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12239]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12240]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī āvasathacīvaraṃ anissajjitvā paribhuñjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun does not relinquish a monastery robe, but continues to use it, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12241]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12242]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12243]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12244]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12245]="*Āvasathacīvaraṃ nāma**A monastery robe:*";
P_HTM[12246]="*“utuniyo bhikkhuniyo paribhuñjantū”ti dinnaṃ hoti.**it is given specifically for the use of menstruating nuns.*";
P_HTM[12247]="*Anissajjitvā paribhuñjeyyāti**Does not relinquish, but continues to use it:*";
P_HTM[12248]="*dvetisso rattiyo paribhuñjitvā catutthadivase dhovitvā bhikkhuniyā vā sikkhamānāya vā sāmaṇeriyā vā anissajjitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she uses it for two or three days, washes it on the fourth day, and then uses it again without relinquishing it to a nun or a trainee nun or a novice nun, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12249]="*Anissajjite anissajjitasaññā paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, and she perceives that it has not, and she uses it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12250]="*Anissajjite vematikā paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, but she is unsure of it, and she uses it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12251]="*Anissajjite nissajjitasaññā paribhuñjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, but she perceives that it has, and she uses it, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12252]="*Nissajjite anissajjitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been relinquished, but she perceives that it has not, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12253]="*Nissajjite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been relinquished, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12254]="*Nissajjite nissajjitasaññā anāpatti.**If it has been relinquished, and she perceives that it has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12255]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12256]="*nissajjitvā paribhuñjati,**if she relinquishes it and then uses it;*";
P_HTM[12257]="*puna pariyāyena paribhuñjati,**if she uses it again at the next turn;*";
P_HTM[12258]="*aññā utuniyo bhikkhuniyo na honti,**if there are no other menstruating nuns;*";
P_HTM[12259]="*acchinnacīvarikāya,**if her robe has been stolen;*";
P_HTM[12260]="*naṭṭhacīvarikāya,**if her robe has been lost;*";
P_HTM[12261]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12262]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12263]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12264]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12265]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12266]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12267]="*48. Āvasathavihārasikkhāpada**48. The training rule on lodgings*";
P_HTM[12268]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12269]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī āvasathaṃ anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkāmi.**the nun Thullanandā went wandering without first relinquishing her lodging.*";
P_HTM[12270]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā āvasatho ḍayhati.**Soon afterwards her lodging caught fire.*";
P_HTM[12271]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**Some nuns said,*";
P_HTM[12272]="*“handāyye, bhaṇḍakaṃ nīharāmā”ti.**“Come, Venerables, let’s remove her things.”*";
P_HTM[12273]="*Ekaccā evamāhaṃsu—**But others replied,*";
P_HTM[12274]="*“na mayaṃ, ayye, nīharissāma.**“No, let’s not.*";
P_HTM[12275]="*Yaṃ kiñci naṭṭhaṃ sabbaṃ amhe abhiyuñjissatī”ti.**She’ll just make us responsible for whatever is burnt.”*";
P_HTM[12276]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī punadeva taṃ āvasathaṃ paccāgantvā bhikkhuniyo pucchi—**When Thullanandā returned to her lodging, she asked the nuns,*";
P_HTM[12277]="*“apāyye, bhaṇḍakaṃ nīharitthā”ti?**“Venerables, I hope you removed my things?”*";
P_HTM[12278]="*“Na mayaṃ, ayye, nīharimhā”ti.**“No, we didn’t.”*";
P_HTM[12279]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**Thullanandā complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12280]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo āvasathe ḍayhamāne bhaṇḍakaṃ na nīharissantī”ti.**“How could the nuns not remove the contents when a lodging is burning?”*";
P_HTM[12281]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**But the nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12282]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā āvasathaṃ anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkamissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā go wandering without relinquishing her lodging?” …*";
P_HTM[12283]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī āvasathaṃ anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkamatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[12284]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12285]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12286]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī āvasathaṃ anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkamissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[12287]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12288]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12289]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī āvasathaṃ anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkameyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun goes wandering without relinquishing her lodging, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12290]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12291]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12292]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12293]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12294]="*Āvasatho nāma**Lodging:*";
P_HTM[12295]="*kavāṭabaddho vuccati.**one with a door is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12296]="*Anissajjitvā cārikaṃ pakkameyyāti**Goes wandering without relinquishing:*";
P_HTM[12297]="*bhikkhuniyā vā sikkhamānāya vā sāmaṇeriyā vā anissajjitvā parikkhittassa āvasathassa parikkhepaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she crosses the boundary of an enclosed lodging without first relinquishing it to a nun, a trainee nun, or a novice nun, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12298]="*Aparikkhittassa āvasathassa upacāraṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she goes beyond the vicinity of an unenclosed lodging, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12299]="*Anissajjite anissajjitasaññā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, and she perceives that it has not, and she goes, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12300]="*Anissajjite vematikā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, but she is unsure of it, and she goes, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12301]="*Anissajjite nissajjitasaññā pakkamati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it has not been relinquished, but she perceives that it has, and she goes, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12302]="*Akavāṭabaddhaṃ anissajjitvā pakkamati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she does not relinquish a lodging without a door, and then goes, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12303]="*Nissajjite anissajjitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been relinquished, but she perceives that it has not, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12304]="*Nissajjite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it has been relinquished, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12305]="*Nissajjite nissajjitasaññā, anāpatti.**If it has been relinquished, and she perceives that it has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12306]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12307]="*nissajjitvā pakkamati,**if she relinquishes it and then goes;*";
P_HTM[12308]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[12309]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches, but is unable to find anyone to relinquish it to;*";
P_HTM[12310]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[12311]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12312]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12313]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12314]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12315]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12316]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12317]="*49. Tiracchānavijjāpariyāpuṇanasikkhāpada**49. The training rule on learning pointless knowledge*";
P_HTM[12318]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12319]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇanti.**At that time the nuns from the group of six were learning pointless knowledge.*";
P_HTM[12320]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12321]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can the nuns learn pointless knowledge? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[12322]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[12323]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12324]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[12325]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[12326]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12327]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12328]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇissanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[12329]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12330]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12331]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī tiracchānavijjaṃ pariyāpuṇeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun learns pointless knowledge, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12332]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12333]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12334]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12335]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12336]="*Tiracchānavijjā nāma**Pointless knowledge:*";
P_HTM[12337]="*yaṃ kiñci bāhirakaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ.**whatever is external to the Buddha’s Teaching, not connected with the goal.*";
P_HTM[12338]="*Pariyāpuṇeyyāti**Learns:*";
P_HTM[12339]="*padena pariyāpuṇāti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she learns by the line, then for every line she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12340]="*Akkharāya pariyāpuṇāti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she learns by the syllable, then for every syllable she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12341]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12342]="*lekhaṃ pariyāpuṇāti,**if she learns writing;*";
P_HTM[12343]="*dhāraṇaṃ pariyāpuṇāti,**if she learns protective verses;*";
P_HTM[12344]="*guttatthāya parittaṃ pariyāpuṇāti,**if she learns verses for the purpose of protection;*";
P_HTM[12345]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12346]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12347]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12348]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12349]="*Cittāgāravagga**The sub-chapter on pleasure houses*";
P_HTM[12350]="*50. Tiracchānavijjāvācanasikkhāpada**50. The training rule on teaching pointless knowledge*";
P_HTM[12351]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12352]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ vācenti.**At that time the nuns from the group of six were teaching pointless knowledge.*";
P_HTM[12353]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12354]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ vācessanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can the nuns teach pointless knowledge? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[12355]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[12356]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12357]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ vācessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?” …*";
P_HTM[12358]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ vācentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[12359]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12360]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12361]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo tiracchānavijjaṃ vācessanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[12362]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12363]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12364]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī tiracchānavijjaṃ vāceyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun teaches pointless knowledge, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12365]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12366]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12367]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12368]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12369]="*Tiracchānavijjā nāma**Pointless knowledge:*";
P_HTM[12370]="*yaṃ kiñci bāhirakaṃ anatthasaṃhitaṃ.**whatever is external to the Buddha’s Teaching, not connected with the goal.*";
P_HTM[12371]="*Vāceyyāti**Teaches:*";
P_HTM[12372]="*padena vāceti, pade pade āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she teaches by the line, then for every line she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12373]="*Akkharāya vāceti, akkharakkharāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she teaches by the syllable, then for every syllable she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12374]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12375]="*lekhaṃ vāceti,**if she teaches writing;*";
P_HTM[12376]="*dhāraṇaṃ vāceti,**if she teaches protective verses;*";
P_HTM[12377]="*guttatthāya parittaṃ vāceti,**if she teaches verses for the purpose of protection;*";
P_HTM[12378]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12379]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12380]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12381]="*Cittāgāravaggo pañcamo.**The fifth sub-chapter on pleasure houses is finished.*";
P_HTM[12382]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12383]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12384]="*51. Ārāmapavisanasikkhāpada**51. The training rule on entering monasteries*";
P_HTM[12385]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12386]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhū gāmakāvāse ekacīvarā cīvarakammaṃ karonti.**a number of monks dressed only in a sarong were making robes in a certain village monastery.*";
P_HTM[12387]="*Bhikkhuniyo anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisitvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu.**Nuns entered that monastery without asking permission and approached those monks.*";
P_HTM[12388]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12389]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisissantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns enter a monastery without asking permission?” …*";
P_HTM[12390]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did that?”*";
P_HTM[12391]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12392]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12393]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisissanti.**“How could nuns do that?*";
P_HTM[12394]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12395]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12396]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī anāpucchā ārāmaṃ paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun enters a monastery without asking permission, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12397]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12398]="*Tena kho pana samayena te bhikkhū tamhā āvāsā pakkamiṃsu.**Soon afterwards those monks left that monastery.*";
P_HTM[12399]="*Bhikkhuniyo—“ayyā pakkantā”ti ārāmaṃ nāgamaṃsu.**But even though the nuns knew that the monks had left, they did not go there.*";
P_HTM[12400]="*Atha kho te bhikkhū punadeva taṃ āvāsaṃ paccāgacchiṃsu.**Soon the monks returned.*";
P_HTM[12401]="*Bhikkhuniyo—“ayyā āgatā”ti āpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisitvā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**When the nuns knew that this was the case, they asked permission and then entered that monastery.*";
P_HTM[12402]="*upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu.**They approached the monks and bowed down to them.*";
P_HTM[12403]="*Ekamantaṃ ṭhitā kho tā bhikkhuniyo te bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—“kissa tumhe, bhaginiyo, ārāmaṃ neva sammajjittha na pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhāpitthā”ti?**The monks then said to them, “Sisters, why didn’t you sweep the monastery, or put out water for drinking or water for washing?”*";
P_HTM[12404]="*“Bhagavatā, ayyā, sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—‘na anāpucchā ārāmo pavisitabbo’ti.**“The Buddha has laid down a training rule that we may not enter a monastery without asking permission.*";
P_HTM[12405]="*Tena mayaṃ na āgamimhā”ti.**That’s why we didn’t do it.”*";
P_HTM[12406]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12407]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisituṃ.**“Monks, when a monk is available, a nun should enter a monastery only after asking permission.*";
P_HTM[12408]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And so, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12409]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā ārāmaṃ paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun, when a monk is available, enters a monastery without asking permission, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12410]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[12411]="*Tena kho pana samayena te bhikkhū tamhā āvāsā pakkamitvā punadeva taṃ āvāsaṃ paccāgacchiṃsu.**Soon afterwards those monks left that monastery once more, before returning once again.*";
P_HTM[12412]="*Bhikkhuniyo—“ayyā pakkantā”ti anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisiṃsu.**Thinking that the monks were still away, the nuns entered the monastery without asking permission.*";
P_HTM[12413]="*Tāsaṃ kukkuccaṃ ahosi—“bhagavatā sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ—‘na santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā ārāmo pavisitabbo’ti.**The nuns became anxious, thinking,*";
P_HTM[12414]="*Mayañcamhā santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisimhā.**“We have entered a monastery without asking permission, even though a monk was available. And the Buddha has laid down a training rule against this.*";
P_HTM[12415]="*Kacci nu kho mayaṃ pācittiyaṃ āpattiṃ āpannā”ti …pe…**Could it be that we have committed an offense entailing confession?”*";
P_HTM[12416]="*bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**They told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[12417]="*Atha kho bhagavā etasmiṃ nidāne etasmiṃ pakaraṇe dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi …pe…**Soon afterwards he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12418]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And so, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12419]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī jānaṃ sabhikkhukaṃ ārāmaṃ anāpucchā paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun, knowing that there are monks in a monastery, enters it without asking permission, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12420]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12421]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12422]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12423]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12424]="*Jānāti nāma**Knowing:*";
P_HTM[12425]="*sāmaṃ vā jānāti, aññe vā tassā ārocenti, te vā ārocenti.**she knows it by herself or others have told her or they have told her.*";
P_HTM[12426]="*Sabhikkhuko nāma ārāmo**There are monks in a monastery:*";
P_HTM[12427]="*yattha bhikkhū rukkhamūlepi vasanti.**even where monks stay at the foot of a tree.*";
P_HTM[12428]="*Anāpucchā ārāmaṃ paviseyyāti**Enters it without asking permission:*";
P_HTM[12429]="*bhikkhuṃ vā sāmaṇeraṃ vā ārāmikaṃ vā anāpucchā parikkhittassa ārāmassa parikkhepaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she crosses the boundary of an enclosed monastery without asking permission of a monk or a novice monk or a monastery worker, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12430]="*Aparikkhittassa ārāmassa upacāraṃ okkamantiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she enters the vicinity of an unenclosed monastery, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12431]="*Sabhikkhuke sabhikkhukasaññā santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If there are monks in a monastery, and she perceives that there are, and she enters it without asking permission of an available monk, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12432]="*Sabhikkhuke vematikā santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there are monks in a monastery, but she is unsure of it, and she enters it without asking permission of an available monk, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12433]="*Sabhikkhuke abhikkhukasaññā santaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā ārāmaṃ pavisati, anāpatti.**If there are monks in a monastery, but she does not perceive that there are, and she enters it without asking permission of an available monk, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12434]="*Abhikkhuke sabhikkhukasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there are no monks in a monastery, but she perceives that there are, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12435]="*Abhikkhuke vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If there are no monks in a monastery, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12436]="*Abhikkhuke abhikkhukasaññā, anāpatti.**If there are no monks in a monastery, and she does not perceive that there are, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12437]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12438]="*santaṃ bhikkhuṃ āpucchā pavisati,**if she enters after asking permission of an available monk;*";
P_HTM[12439]="*asantaṃ bhikkhuṃ anāpucchā pavisati,**if, when there is no available monk, she enters without asking permission;*";
P_HTM[12440]="*sīsānulokikā gacchati,**if she goes while looking at the head of a nun in front of her;*";
P_HTM[12441]="*yattha bhikkhuniyo sannipatitā honti tattha gacchati,**if she is going to where the nuns have gathered;*";
P_HTM[12442]="*ārāmena maggo hoti,**if a path goes through the monastery;*";
P_HTM[12443]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[12444]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12445]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12446]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12447]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12448]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12449]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12450]="*52. Bhikkhuakkosanasikkhāpada**52. The training rule on abusing monks*";
P_HTM[12451]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā vesāliyaṃ viharati mahāvane kūṭāgārasālāyaṃ.**At one time when the Buddha was staying  in the hall with the peaked roof in the Great Wood near Vesālī,*";
P_HTM[12452]="*Tena kho pana samayena āyasmato upālissa upajjhāyo āyasmā kappitako susāne viharati.**Venerable Upāli’s preceptor, Venerable Kappita, was staying in a charnel ground.*";
P_HTM[12453]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ mahattarā bhikkhunī kālaṅkatā hoti.**At that time the leader of the nuns from the group of six had just died.*";
P_HTM[12454]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo taṃ bhikkhuniṃ nīharitvā āyasmato kappitakassa vihārassa avidūre jhāpetvā thūpaṃ katvā gantvā tasmiṃ thūpe rodanti.**They took her to that charnel ground, cremated her near Venerable Kappita’s dwelling, and made a stupa. They then went there to cry.*";
P_HTM[12455]="*Atha kho āyasmā kappitako tena saddena ubbāḷho taṃ thūpaṃ bhinditvā pakiresi.**Venerable Kappita was disturbed by the noise, and so he demolished the stupa and scattered the rubble.*";
P_HTM[12456]="*Chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo—**The nuns from the group of six thought,*";
P_HTM[12457]="*“iminā kappitakena amhākaṃ ayyāya thūpo bhinno, handa naṃ ghātemā”ti mantesuṃ.**“Kappita has demolished our Venerable’s stupa; let’s kill him,” and they laid a plan.*";
P_HTM[12458]="*Aññatarā bhikkhunī āyasmato upālissa etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**A certain nun told Venerable Upāli what was happening,*";
P_HTM[12459]="*Āyasmā upāli āyasmato kappitakassa etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**and he in turn told Venerable Kappita.*";
P_HTM[12460]="*Atha kho āyasmā kappitako vihārā nikkhamitvā nilīno acchi.**Venerable Kappita then left his dwelling and went into hiding.*";
P_HTM[12461]="*Atha kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo yenāyasmato kappitakassa vihāro tenupasaṅkamiṃsu;**Soon afterwards the nuns from the group of six went to his dwelling*";
P_HTM[12462]="*upasaṅkamitvā āyasmato kappitakassa vihāraṃ pāsāṇehi ca leḍḍūhi ca ottharāpetvā, “mato kappitako”ti pakkamiṃsu.**and crushed it with rocks and lumps of earth. When they thought he was dead, they left.*";
P_HTM[12463]="*Atha kho āyasmā kappitako tassā rattiyā accayena pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya vesāliṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**The following morning Venerable Kappita robed up, took his bowl and robe, and entered Vesālī for almsfood.*";
P_HTM[12464]="*Addasaṃsu kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo āyasmantaṃ kappitakaṃ piṇḍāya carantaṃ.**When the nuns from the group of six saw him,*";
P_HTM[12465]="*Disvāna evamāhaṃsu—**they said,*";
P_HTM[12466]="*“ayaṃ kappitako jīvati, ko nu kho amhākaṃ mantaṃ saṃharī”ti?**“Kappita is alive! Who foiled our plan?”*";
P_HTM[12467]="*Assosuṃ kho chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo—**When they heard*";
P_HTM[12468]="*“ayyena kira upālinā amhākaṃ manto saṃhaṭo”ti.**it was Venerable Upāli,*";
P_HTM[12469]="*Tā āyasmantaṃ upāliṃ akkosiṃsu—**they abused him,*";
P_HTM[12470]="*“kathañhi nāma ayaṃ kāsāvaṭo malamajjano nihīnajacco amhākaṃ mantaṃ saṃharissatī”ti.**“How could this barber, this dirt remover of inferior caste, foil our plan?”*";
P_HTM[12471]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12472]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ayyaṃ upāliṃ akkosissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the nuns from the group of six abuse Venerable Upāli?” …*";
P_HTM[12473]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo upāliṃ akkosantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[12474]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12475]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12476]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo upāliṃ akkosissanti.**“How could the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[12477]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12478]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12479]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuṃ akkoseyya vā paribhāseyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun abuses or reviles a monk, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12480]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12481]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12482]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12483]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12484]="*Bhikkhunti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[12485]="*upasampannaṃ.**one who is fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[12486]="*Akkoseyya vāti**Abuses:*";
P_HTM[12487]="*dasahi vā akkosavatthūhi akkosati etesaṃ vā aññatarena, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she abuses with the ten kinds of abuse or with any one of them, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12488]="*Paribhāseyya vāti**Reviles:*";
P_HTM[12489]="*bhayaṃ upadaṃseti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she induces fear, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12490]="*Upasampanne upasampannasaññā akkosati vā paribhāsati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is fully ordained, and she perceives him as such, and she abuses or reviles him, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12491]="*Upasampanne vematikā akkosati vā paribhāsati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, and she abuses or reviles him, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12492]="*Upasampanne anupasampannasaññā akkosati vā paribhāsati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If he is fully ordained, but she does not perceive him as such, and she abuses or reviles him, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12493]="*Anupasampannaṃ akkosati vā paribhāsati vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she abuses or reviles someone who is not fully ordained, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12494]="*Anupasampanne upasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not fully ordained, but she perceives him as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12495]="*Anupasampanne vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not fully ordained, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12496]="*Anupasampanne anupasampannasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If he is not fully ordained, and she does not perceive him as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12497]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12498]="*atthapurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at what is beneficial;*";
P_HTM[12499]="*dhammapurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at giving a teaching;*";
P_HTM[12500]="*anusāsanipurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at giving an instruction;*";
P_HTM[12501]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12502]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12503]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12504]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12505]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12506]="*53. Gaṇaparibhāsanasikkhāpada**53. The training rule on reviling a group*";
P_HTM[12507]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12508]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī bhaṇḍanakārikā hoti kalahakārikā vivādakārikā bhassakārikā saṅghe adhikaraṇakārikā.**At that time the nun Caṇḍakāḷī was quarrelsome and argumentative, and she created legal issues in the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[12509]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī tassā kamme karīyamāne paṭikkosati.**But when a legal procedure was being done against her, the nun Thullanandā objected.*";
P_HTM[12510]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī gāmakaṃ agamāsi kenacideva karaṇīyena.**Soon afterwards when Thullanandā went to a village on some business,*";
P_HTM[12511]="*Atha kho bhikkhunisaṅgho—**the Sangha of nuns*";
P_HTM[12512]="*“thullanandā bhikkhunī pakkantā”ti caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ āpattiyā adassane ukkhipi.**took the opportunity to eject Caṇḍakāḷī for not recognizing an offense.*";
P_HTM[12513]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī gāmake taṃ karaṇīyaṃ tīretvā punadeva sāvatthiṃ paccāgacchi.**When Thullanandā had finished her business, she returned to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[12514]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī thullanandāya bhikkhuniyā āgacchantiyā neva āsanaṃ paññapesi na pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakaṭhalikaṃ upanikkhipi;**As she was approaching, Caṇḍakāḷī neither prepared a seat for her, nor set out a foot stool, a foot scraper, or water for washing the feet;*";
P_HTM[12515]="*na paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesi na pānīyena āpucchi.**and she did not go out to meet her to receive her bowl and robe or to ask whether she wanted water to drink.*";
P_HTM[12516]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**Thullanandā asked her*";
P_HTM[12517]="*“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, mayi āgacchantiyā neva āsanaṃ paññapesi na pādodakaṃ pādapīṭhaṃ pādakaṭhalikaṃ upanikkhipi;**why she was acting like this.*";
P_HTM[12518]="*na paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesi na pānīyena āpucchī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[12519]="*“Evañhetaṃ, ayye, hoti yathā taṃ anāthāyā”ti.**She replied, “That’s how it is, Venerable, when one doesn’t have a protector.”*";
P_HTM[12520]="*“Kissa pana tvaṃ, ayye, anāthā”ti?**“But how is it, Venerable, that you don’t have a protector?”*";
P_HTM[12521]="*“Imā maṃ, ayye, bhikkhuniyo—**“When these nuns knew*";
P_HTM[12522]="*‘ayaṃ anāthā appaññātā, natthi imissā kāci pativattā’ti, āpattiyā adassane ukkhipiṃsū”ti.**that no one would speak up for me because I am not esteemed by them and I didn’t have a protector, they ejected me for not recognizing an offense.”*";
P_HTM[12523]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī—* **";
P_HTM[12524]="*“bālā etā abyattā etā netā jānanti kammaṃ vā kammadosaṃ vā kammavipattiṃ vā kammasampattiṃ vā”ti, caṇḍīkatā gaṇaṃ paribhāsi.**“They are incompetent fools! They don’t understand legal procedures, nor what makes them fail or succeed.” And in a rage she reviled the community.*";
P_HTM[12525]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12526]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā caṇḍīkatā gaṇaṃ paribhāsissatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā revile the community in a rage?” …*";
P_HTM[12527]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī caṇḍīkatā gaṇaṃ paribhāsatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[12528]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12529]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12530]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī caṇḍīkatā gaṇaṃ paribhāsissati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[12531]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12532]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12533]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī caṇḍīkatā gaṇaṃ paribhāseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If an enraged nun reviles a community, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12534]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12535]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12536]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12537]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12538]="*Caṇḍīkatā nāma**Enraged:*";
P_HTM[12539]="*kodhanā vuccati.**angry is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12540]="*Gaṇo nāma**A community:*";
P_HTM[12541]="*bhikkhunisaṅgho vuccati.**the Sangha of nuns is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12542]="*Paribhāseyyāti**Reviles:*";
P_HTM[12543]="*“bālā etā abyattā etā netā jānanti kammaṃ vā kammadosaṃ vā kammavipattiṃ vā kammasampattiṃ vā”ti paribhāsati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she reviles them, saying, “They are incompetent fools. They don’t understand legal procedures, nor what makes them fail or succeed,” she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12544]="*Sambahulā bhikkhuniyo vā ekaṃ bhikkhuniṃ vā anupasampannaṃ vā paribhāsati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she reviles several nuns, a single nun, or someone who is not fully ordained, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12545]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12546]="*atthapurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at what is beneficial;*";
P_HTM[12547]="*dhammapurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at giving a teaching;*";
P_HTM[12548]="*anusāsanipurekkhārāya,**if she is aiming at giving an instruction;*";
P_HTM[12549]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12550]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12551]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12552]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12553]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12554]="*54. Pavāritasikkhāpada**54. The training rule on inviting*";
P_HTM[12555]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12556]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññataro brāhmaṇo bhikkhuniyo nimantetvā bhojesi.**a certain brahmin had invited the nuns for a meal.*";
P_HTM[12557]="*Bhikkhuniyo bhuttāvī pavāritā ñātikulāni gantvā ekaccā bhuñjiṃsu ekaccā piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya agamaṃsu.**When the nuns had finished and refused an invitation to eat more, they went to their respective families, where some ate and others got almsfood and left.*";
P_HTM[12558]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo paṭivissake etadavoca—**Soon afterwards that brahmin said this to his neighbors,*";
P_HTM[12559]="*“bhikkhuniyo mayā, ayyā, santappitā, etha tumhepi santappessāmī”ti.**“I have satisfied the nuns. Come, and I’ll satisfy you, too.”*";
P_HTM[12560]="*Te evamāhaṃsu—* **";
P_HTM[12561]="*“kiṃ tvaṃ, ayyo, amhe santappessasi.**“How could you satisfy us?*";
P_HTM[12562]="*Yāpi tayā nimantitā tāpi amhākaṃ gharāni āgantvā ekaccā bhuñjiṃsu ekaccā piṇḍapātaṃ ādāya agamaṃsū”ti.**Those nuns who were invited by you came to our houses, where some ate and others got almsfood and left.”*";
P_HTM[12563]="*Atha kho so brāhmaṇo ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**That brahmin complained and criticized those nuns,*";
P_HTM[12564]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo amhākaṃ ghare bhuñjitvā aññatra bhuñjissanti, na cāhaṃ paṭibalo yāvadatthaṃ dātun”ti.**“How could they eat in our house and afterwards eat elsewhere? Am I not able to give them as much as they want?”*";
P_HTM[12565]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tassa brāhmaṇassa ujjhāyantassa khiyyantassa vipācentassa.**The nuns heard the complaints of that brahmin,*";
P_HTM[12566]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12567]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns finish their meal, refuse an invitation to eat more, and then eat elsewhere?” …*";
P_HTM[12568]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[12569]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12570]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12571]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhuttāvī pavāritā aññatra bhuñjissanti.**“How could nuns act in this way?*";
P_HTM[12572]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12573]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12574]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī nimantitā vā pavāritā vā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādeyya vā bhuñjeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun, who has been invited to a meal, refuses an invitation to eat more, and then eats fresh or cooked food, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12575]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12576]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12577]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12578]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12579]="*Nimantitā nāma**Refuses an offer to eat more:*";
P_HTM[12580]="*pañcannaṃ bhojanānaṃ aññatarena bhojanena nimantitā.**refuses an offer to eat any of the five cooked foods.*";
P_HTM[12581]="*Pavāritā nāma**Refuses an invitation to eat more:*";
P_HTM[12582]="*asanaṃ paññāyati, bhojanaṃ paññāyati, hatthapāse ṭhitā abhiharati, paṭikkhepo paññāyati.**eating is seen, cooked food is seen, it is offered by one standing within arm’s reach, a refusal is seen.*";
P_HTM[12583]="*Khādanīyaṃ nāma**Fresh food:*";
P_HTM[12584]="*pañca bhojanāni yāguṃ yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ ṭhapetvā**apart from the five cooked foods, rice porridge, the post-midday tonics, the seven-day tonics, and the lifetime tonics,*";
P_HTM[12585]="*avasesaṃ khādanīyaṃ nāma.**the rest is called “fresh food”.*";
P_HTM[12586]="*Bhojanīyaṃ nāma**Cooked food:*";
P_HTM[12587]="*pañca bhojanāni—odano, kummāso, sattu, maccho, maṃsaṃ.**there are five kinds of cooked food: cooked grain, porridge, flour products, fish, and meat.*";
P_HTM[12588]="*“Khādissāmi bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12589]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pācittiyassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12590]="*Nimantite nimantitasaññā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has refused an offer, and she perceives that she has, and she eats fresh or cooked food, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12591]="*Nimantite vematikā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has refused an offer, but she is unsure of it, and she eats fresh or cooked food, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12592]="*Nimantite animantitasaññā khādanīyaṃ vā bhojanīyaṃ vā khādati vā bhuñjati vā, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has refused an offer, but she does not perceive that she has, and she eats fresh or cooked food, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12593]="*Yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ āhāratthāya paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she receives post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics for the purpose of food, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12594]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti dukkaṭassa …pe….**For every mouthful, she commits an offense of wrong conduct. …*";
P_HTM[12595]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12596]="*nimantitā appavāritā,**if she has refused an offer to eat more, but not an invitation;*";
P_HTM[12597]="*yāguṃ pivati,**if she drinks rice porridge;*";
P_HTM[12598]="*sāmike apaloketvā bhuñjati,**if she eats more after getting permission from the person who invited her;*";
P_HTM[12599]="*yāmakālikaṃ sattāhakālikaṃ yāvajīvikaṃ sati paccaye paribhuñjati,**if, when there is a reason, she uses post-midday tonics, seven-day tonics, or lifetime tonics;*";
P_HTM[12600]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12601]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12602]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12603]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12604]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12605]="*55. Kulamaccharinīsikkhāpada**55. The training rule on being stingy with families*";
P_HTM[12606]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12607]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī sāvatthiyaṃ aññatarissā visikhāya piṇḍāya caramānā yena aññataraṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**a certain nun was walking for almsfood along a street in the same town. She then went to a certain family, where she sat down on the prepared seat.*";
P_HTM[12608]="*Atha kho te manussā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ bhojetvā etadavocuṃ—**The people there gave her a meal and said,*";
P_HTM[12609]="*“aññāpi, ayye, bhikkhuniyo āgacchantū”ti.**“Venerable, other nuns may come too.”*";
P_HTM[12610]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī—**Then that nun thought,*";
P_HTM[12611]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo nāgaccheyyun”ti, bhikkhuniyo upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca—**“What can I do so that other nuns don’t come?” And she went up to other nuns and said,*";
P_HTM[12612]="*“amukasmiṃ, ayye, okāse vāḷā sunakhā caṇḍo balibaddo cikkhallo okāso.**“Venerables, in such-and-such a place there are malicious dogs, a temperamental ox, and it’s muddy.*";
P_HTM[12613]="*Mā kho tattha agamitthā”ti.**Don’t go there.”*";
P_HTM[12614]="*Aññatarāpi bhikkhunī tassā visikhāya piṇḍāya caramānā yena taṃ kulaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi.**Another nun, too, went to that family while walking for almsfood along that street. She sat down on the prepared seat*";
P_HTM[12615]="*Atha kho te manussā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ bhojetvā etadavocuṃ—**and the people there gave her a meal. They then asked her,*";
P_HTM[12616]="*“kissa, ayye, bhikkhuniyo na āgacchantī”ti?**“Venerable, why don’t the nuns come here?”*";
P_HTM[12617]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī tesaṃ manussānaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And she told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[12618]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12619]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī kulaṃ maccharāyissatī”ti …pe…**“How can a nun be stingy with a family?” …*";
P_HTM[12620]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī kulaṃ maccharāyatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun acted like this?”*";
P_HTM[12621]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12622]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12623]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī kulaṃ maccharāyissati.**“How could a nun act like this?*";
P_HTM[12624]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12625]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12626]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī kulamaccharinī assa, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun is stingy with families, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12627]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12628]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12629]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12630]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12631]="*Kulaṃ nāma**A family:*";
P_HTM[12632]="*cattāri kulāni— khattiyakulaṃ, brāhmaṇakulaṃ, vessakulaṃ, suddakulaṃ.**there are four kinds of families: the aristocratic family, the brahmin family, the merchant family, the worker family.*";
P_HTM[12633]="*Maccharinī assāti**Is stingy:*";
P_HTM[12634]="*“kathaṃ bhikkhuniyo nāgaccheyyun”ti bhikkhunīnaṃ santike kulassa avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she thinks, “What can I do so that other nuns don’t come?” and she then speaks disparagingly of the family in the presence of nuns, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12635]="*Kulassa vā santike bhikkhunīnaṃ avaṇṇaṃ bhāsati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she speaks disparagingly of nuns in the presence of the family, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12636]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12637]="*kulaṃ na maccharāyantī santaṃyeva ādīnavaṃ ācikkhati,**if she is not being stingy with families, but describes the disadvantages as they are;*";
P_HTM[12638]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12639]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12640]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12641]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12642]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12643]="*56. Abhikkhukāvāsasikkhāpada**56. The training rule on monasteries without monks*";
P_HTM[12644]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12645]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo gāmakāvāse vassaṃvuṭṭhā sāvatthiṃ agamaṃsu.**At that time a number of nuns who had completed the rainy-season residence in a village monastery went to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[12646]="*Bhikkhuniyo tā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**The nuns there asked them,*";
P_HTM[12647]="*“katthāyyāyo vassaṃvuṭṭhā?**“Venerables, where did you spend the rains residence?*";
P_HTM[12648]="*Kacci ovādo iddho ahosī”ti?**We hope the instruction was effective?”*";
P_HTM[12649]="*“Natthayye, tattha bhikkhū;**“There were no monks there.*";
P_HTM[12650]="*kuto ovādo iddho bhavissatī”ti.**So how could the instruction be effective?”*";
P_HTM[12651]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12652]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasissantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns spend the rains residence in a monastery without monks?” …*";
P_HTM[12653]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[12654]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12655]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12656]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vasissanti.**“How could nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[12657]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12658]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12659]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī abhikkhuke āvāse vassaṃ vaseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun spends the rainy-season residence in a monastery without monks, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12660]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12661]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12662]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12663]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12664]="*Abhikkhuko nāma āvāso**A monastery without monks:*";
P_HTM[12665]="*na sakkā hoti ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā gantuṃ.**she is not able to go to the instruction or to formal meetings of the community.*";
P_HTM[12666]="*“Vassaṃ vasissāmī”ti senāsanaṃ paññapeti pānīyaṃ paribhojanīyaṃ upaṭṭhapeti pariveṇaṃ sammajjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she thinks, “I’ll stay here for the rainy-season residence,” and she prepares a dwelling, sets out water for drinking and water for washing, and sweeps the precincts, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12667]="*Saha aruṇuggamanā āpatti pācittiyassa.**At dawn, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12668]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12669]="*vassupagatā bhikkhū pakkantā vā honti vibbhantā vā kālaṅkatā vā pakkhasaṅkantā vā,**if the monks who entered the rainy-season residence there depart or disrobe or die or join another faction;*";
P_HTM[12670]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12671]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12672]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12673]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12674]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12675]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12676]="*57. Apavāraṇāsikkhāpada**57. The training rule on not inviting*";
P_HTM[12677]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12678]="*Tena kho pana samayena sambahulā bhikkhuniyo gāmakāvāse vassaṃvuṭṭhā sāvatthiṃ agamaṃsu.**At that time a number of nuns who had completed the rainy-season residence in a village monastery went to Sāvatthī.*";
P_HTM[12679]="*Bhikkhuniyo tā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**The nuns there asked them,*";
P_HTM[12680]="*“katthāyyāyo vassaṃvuṭṭhā;**“Venerables, where did you spend the rains residence?*";
P_HTM[12681]="*kattha bhikkhusaṅgho pavārito”ti?**Where did you invite the Sangha of monks for correction?”*";
P_HTM[12682]="*“Na mayaṃ, ayye, bhikkhusaṅghaṃ pavāremā”ti.**“We didn’t invite the Sangha of monks for correction.”*";
P_HTM[12683]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12684]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ na pavāressantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns who have completed the rains residence not invite the Sangha of monks for correction?” …*";
P_HTM[12685]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ na pavārentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns didn’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[12686]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12687]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12688]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vassaṃvuṭṭhā bhikkhusaṅghaṃ na pavāressanti.**“How could nuns not do this?*";
P_HTM[12689]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12690]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12691]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī vassaṃvuṭṭhā ubhatosaṅghe tīhi ṭhānehi na pavāreyya diṭṭhena vā sutena vā parisaṅkāya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun who has completed the rainy-season residence does not invite correction from both Sanghas in regard to three things—what has been seen, what has been heard, and what has been suspected—she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12692]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12693]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12694]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12695]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12696]="*Vassaṃvuṭṭhā nāma**Who has completed the rainy-season residence:*";
P_HTM[12697]="*purimaṃ vā temāsaṃ pacchimaṃ vā temāsaṃ vuṭṭhā.**who has completed the first three or the last three months of the rainy-season residence.*";
P_HTM[12698]="*Ubhatosaṅghe tīhi ṭhānehi na pavāressāmi diṭṭhena vā sutena vā parisaṅkāya vā”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I won’t invite correction from both Sanghas in regard to three things—what has been seen, heard, or suspected,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12699]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12700]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[12701]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches, but does not find anyone to invite for correction;*";
P_HTM[12702]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[12703]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12704]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12705]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12706]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12707]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12708]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12709]="*58. Ovādasikkhāpada**58. The training rule on the instruction*";
P_HTM[12710]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying in the Sakyan country in the Banyan Tree Monastery at Kapilavatthu,*";
P_HTM[12711]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū bhikkhunupassayaṃ upasaṅkamitvā chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovadanti.**the monks from the group of six went to the nuns’ dwelling place to instruct the nuns from the group of six.*";
P_HTM[12712]="*Bhikkhuniyo chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**Soon afterwards other nuns said to those nuns,*";
P_HTM[12713]="*“ethāyye, ovādaṃ gamissāmā”ti.**“Come, Venerables, let’s go to the instruction.”*";
P_HTM[12714]="*“Yampi mayaṃ, ayye, gaccheyyāma ovādassa kāraṇā, ayyā chabbaggiyā idheva āgantvā amhe ovadantī”ti.**“There’s no need. The monks from the group of six came and instructed us right here.”*";
P_HTM[12715]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12716]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ na gacchissantī”ti …pe…**“How could the nuns from the group of six not go to the instruction?” …*";
P_HTM[12717]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ na gacchantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns didn’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[12718]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12719]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12720]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo ovādaṃ na gacchissanti.**“How could the nuns from the group of six not do this?*";
P_HTM[12721]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12722]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12723]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā na gaccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun does not go to the instruction or take part in a formal meeting of the community, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12724]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12725]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12726]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12727]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12728]="*Ovādo nāma**The instruction:*";
P_HTM[12729]="*aṭṭha garudhammā.**the eight important principles.*";
P_HTM[12730]="*Saṃvāso nāma**The community:*";
P_HTM[12731]="*ekakammaṃ ekuddeso samasikkhatā.**joint legal procedures, a joint recitation, the same training.*";
P_HTM[12732]="*Ovādāya vā saṃvāsāya vā na gacchissāmīti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I won’t go to the instruction or take part in a formal meeting of the community,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12733]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12734]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[12735]="*pariyesitvā dutiyikaṃ bhikkhuniṃ na labhati,**if she searches for a companion nun, but does not find one;*";
P_HTM[12736]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[12737]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12738]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12739]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12740]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12741]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12742]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12743]="*59. Ovādūpasaṅkamanasikkhāpada**59. The training rule on going to the instruction*";
P_HTM[12744]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12745]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo uposathampi na pucchanti ovādampi na yācanti.**At that time the nuns did not enquire about the observance day nor ask for the instruction.*";
P_HTM[12746]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12747]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo uposathampi na pucchissanti ovādampi na yācissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns not enquire about the observance day nor ask for the instruction?” …*";
P_HTM[12748]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo uposathampi na pucchanti ovādampi na yācantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns don’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[12749]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12750]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12751]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo uposathampi na pucchissanti ovādampi na yācissanti.**“How can the nuns not do this?*";
P_HTM[12752]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12753]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12754]="*“Anvaddhamāsaṃ bhikkhuniyā bhikkhusaṅghato dve dhammā paccāsīsitabbā—uposathapucchakañca ovādūpasaṅkamanañca. Taṃ atikkāmentiyā pācittiyan”ti.**‘Every half-month a nun should seek two things from the Sangha of monks: asking it about the observance day and going to it for the instruction. If she goes beyond a half-month, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12755]="*Anvaddhamāsanti**Every half-month:*";
P_HTM[12756]="*anuposathikaṃ.**every observance day.*";
P_HTM[12757]="*Uposatho nāma**The observance day:*";
P_HTM[12758]="*dve uposathā— cātuddasiko ca pannarasiko ca.**there are two observance days: the fourteenth and the fifteenth.*";
P_HTM[12759]="*Ovādo nāma**The instruction:*";
P_HTM[12760]="*aṭṭha garudhammā.**the eight important principles.*";
P_HTM[12761]="*“Uposathampi na pucchissāmi ovādampi na yācissāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I won’t enquire about the observance day, nor ask for the instruction,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12762]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12763]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[12764]="*pariyesitvā dutiyikaṃ bhikkhuniṃ na labhati,**if she searches for a companion nun, but does not find one;*";
P_HTM[12765]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[12766]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[12767]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12768]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12769]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12770]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12771]="*Ārāmavagga**The sub-chapter on monasteries*";
P_HTM[12772]="*60. Pasākhejātasikkhāpada**60. The training rule on what is growing on the lower part of the body*";
P_HTM[12773]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12774]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī pasākhe jātaṃ gaṇḍaṃ purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā bhedāpesi.**a certain nun was alone with a man, when she had him rupture an abscess growing on the lower part of her body.*";
P_HTM[12775]="*Atha kho so puriso taṃ bhikkhuniṃ dūsetuṃ upakkami.**When he tried to rape her,*";
P_HTM[12776]="*Sā vissaramakāsi.**she cried out.*";
P_HTM[12777]="*Bhikkhuniyo upadhāvitvā taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavocuṃ—**The nuns came rushing to and asked her why.*";
P_HTM[12778]="*“kissa tvaṃ, ayye, vissaramakāsī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[12779]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**And she told them what had happened.*";
P_HTM[12780]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[12781]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī pasākhe jātaṃ gaṇḍaṃ purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā bhedāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun be alone with a man and have him rupture an abscess growing on the lower part of her body?” …*";
P_HTM[12782]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī pasākhe jātaṃ gaṇḍaṃ purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā bhedāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[12783]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12784]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[12785]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī pasākhe jātaṃ gaṇḍaṃ purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā bhedāpessati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[12786]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12787]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12788]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī pasākhe jātaṃ gaṇḍaṃ vā rudhitaṃ vā anapaloketvā saṅghaṃ vā gaṇaṃ vā purisena saddhiṃ ekenekā bhedāpeyya vā phālāpeyya vā dhovāpeyya vā ālimpāpeyya vā bandhāpeyya vā mocāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun, alone with a man, without getting permission from the Sangha or a group, has an abscess or a wound situated on the lower part of her body ruptured by him, or split open, washed, anointed, bandaged, or unwrapped by him, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12789]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12790]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12791]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12792]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12793]="*Pasākhaṃ nāma**The lower part of the body:*";
P_HTM[12794]="*adhonābhi ubbhajāṇumaṇḍalaṃ.**below the navel and above the knees.*";
P_HTM[12795]="*Jātanti**Situated:*";
P_HTM[12796]="*tattha jātaṃ.**situated there.*";
P_HTM[12797]="*Gaṇḍo nāma**An abscess:*";
P_HTM[12798]="*yo koci gaṇḍo.**any kind of abscess.*";
P_HTM[12799]="*Rudhitaṃ nāma**A wound:*";
P_HTM[12800]="*yaṃ kiñci vaṇaṃ.**any kind of sore.*";
P_HTM[12801]="*Anapaloketvāti**Without getting permission:*";
P_HTM[12802]="*anāpucchā.**without having asked permission.*";
P_HTM[12803]="*Saṅgho nāma**The Sangha:*";
P_HTM[12804]="*bhikkhunisaṅgho vuccati.**the Sangha of nuns is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12805]="*Gaṇo nāma**A group:*";
P_HTM[12806]="*sambahulā bhikkhuniyo vuccanti.**several nuns is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12807]="*Puriso nāma**A man:*";
P_HTM[12808]="*manussapuriso, na yakkho, na peto, na tiracchānagato, viññū paṭibalo dūsetuṃ.**a human male, not a male spirit, not a male ghost, not a male animal. He understands and is capable of raping.*";
P_HTM[12809]="*Saddhinti**With:*";
P_HTM[12810]="*ekato.**together.*";
P_HTM[12811]="*Ekenekāti**Alone:*";
P_HTM[12812]="*puriso ceva hoti bhikkhunī ca.**just the man and the nun.*";
P_HTM[12813]="*“Bhindā”ti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells him, “Rupture it,” she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12814]="*Bhinne āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it has been ruptured, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12815]="*“Phālehī”ti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells him, “Split it open,” she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12816]="*Phālite āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it has been split open, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12817]="*“Dhovā”ti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells him, “Wash it,” she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12818]="*Dhovite āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it has been washed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12819]="*“Ālimpā”ti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells him, “Anoint it,” she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12820]="*Litte āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it has been anointed, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12821]="*“Bandhāhī”ti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells him, “Bandage it,” she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12822]="*Baddhe āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it has been bandaged, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12823]="*“Mocehī”ti āṇāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she tells him, “Unwrap it,” she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12824]="*Mutte āpatti pācittiyassa.**When it has been unwrapped, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12825]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12826]="*apaloketvā bhedāpeti vā phālāpeti vā dhovāpeti vā ālimpāpeti vā bandhāpeti vā mocāpeti vā,**if she gets permission and then has it ruptured, split open, washed, anointed, bandaged, or unwrapped;*";
P_HTM[12827]="*yā kāci viññū dutiyikā hoti,**if she has a female companion who understands;*";
P_HTM[12828]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12829]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12830]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12831]="*Ārāmavaggo chaṭṭho.**The sixth sub-chapter on monasteries is finished.*";
P_HTM[12832]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12833]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[12834]="*61. Gabbhinisikkhāpada**61. The training rule on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[12835]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12836]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**the nuns gave the full admission to a pregnant woman.*";
P_HTM[12837]="*Sā piṇḍāya carati.**When she walked for alms,*";
P_HTM[12838]="*Manussā evamāhaṃsu—**people said,*";
P_HTM[12839]="*“dethāyyāya bhikkhaṃ, garubhārā ayyā”ti.**“Give almsfood to the Venerable. She’s carrying a heavy burden.”*";
P_HTM[12840]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12841]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti.**“How can the nuns give the full admission to a pregnant woman?”*";
P_HTM[12842]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[12843]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12844]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns do this?” …*";
P_HTM[12845]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[12846]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12847]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12848]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How could nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[12849]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12850]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12851]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī gabbhiniṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a pregnant woman, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12852]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12853]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12854]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12855]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12856]="*Gabbhinī nāma**A pregnant woman:*";
P_HTM[12857]="*āpannasattā vuccati.**a woman with child is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[12858]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[12859]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[12860]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12861]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12862]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12863]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[12864]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12865]="*Gabbhiniyā gabbhinisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is pregnant, and she perceives her as such, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12866]="*Gabbhiniyā vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is pregnant, but she is unsure of it, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12867]="*Gabbhiniyā agabbhinisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, anāpatti.**If she is pregnant, but she does not perceive her as such, and she gives her the full admission, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12868]="*Agabbhiniyā gabbhinisaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not pregnant, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12869]="*Agabbhiniyā vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not pregnant, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12870]="*Agabbhiniyā agabbhinisaññā, anāpatti.**If she is not pregnant, and she does not perceive her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12871]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12872]="*gabbhiniṃ agabbhinisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she is pregnant, but she does not perceive her as such, and she gives her the full admission;*";
P_HTM[12873]="*agabbhiniṃ agabbhinisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she is not pregnant, and she does not perceive her as such, and she gives her the full admission;*";
P_HTM[12874]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12875]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12876]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12877]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12878]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[12879]="*62. Pāyantisikkhāpada**62. The training rule on women who are breastfeeding*";
P_HTM[12880]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[12881]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**the nuns gave the full admission to a woman who was breastfeeding.*";
P_HTM[12882]="*Sā piṇḍāya carati.**When she walked for alms,*";
P_HTM[12883]="*Manussā evamāhaṃsu—**people said,*";
P_HTM[12884]="*“dethāyyāya bhikkhaṃ, sadutiyikā ayyā”ti.**“Give almsfood to the Venerable. She has a companion.”*";
P_HTM[12885]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12886]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti.**“How can the nuns give the full admission to a woman who is breastfeeding?”*";
P_HTM[12887]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people*";
P_HTM[12888]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12889]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How could nuns do this?” …*";
P_HTM[12890]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns did this?”*";
P_HTM[12891]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12892]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12893]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How could nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[12894]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12895]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12896]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī pāyantiṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a woman who is breastfeeding, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12897]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12898]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12899]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12900]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12901]="*Pāyantī nāma**A woman who is breastfeeding:*";
P_HTM[12902]="*mātā vā hoti dhāti vā.**she is a mother or a wet-nurse.*";
P_HTM[12903]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[12904]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[12905]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12906]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12907]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12908]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[12909]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12910]="*Pāyantiyā pāyantisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is breastfeeding, and she perceives her as such, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12911]="*Pāyantiyā vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is breastfeeding, but she is unsure of it, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12912]="*Pāyantiyā apāyantisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, anāpatti.**If she is breastfeeding, but she does not perceive her as such, and she gives her the full admission, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12913]="*Apāyantiyā pāyantisaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not breastfeeding, but she perceives her as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12914]="*Apāyantiyā vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is not breastfeeding, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12915]="*Apāyantiyā apāyantisaññā, anāpatti.**If she is not breastfeeding, and she does not perceive her as such, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[12916]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12917]="*pāyantiṃ apāyantisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a woman who is breastfeeding, but she does not perceive her as such;*";
P_HTM[12918]="*apāyantiṃ apāyantisaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a woman who is not breastfeeding, and she does not perceive her as such;*";
P_HTM[12919]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12920]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12921]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12922]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12923]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[12924]="*63. Sikkhamānasikkhāpada**63. The training rule on trainee nuns*";
P_HTM[12925]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12926]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to trainee nuns who had not trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[12927]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**They were ignorant and incompetent, and did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[12928]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[12929]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to trainee nuns who haven’t trained for two years in the six rules?” …*";
P_HTM[12930]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[12931]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[12932]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[12933]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[12934]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[12935]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[12936]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[12937]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, sikkhamānāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval is required for a trainee nun to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[12938]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[12939]="*Tāya sikkhamānāya saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that trainee nun should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[12940]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya sikkhamānā.**‘Venerables, I, so-and-so, am a trainee nun under Venerable so-and-so.*";
P_HTM[12941]="*Saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**I ask the Sangha for approval to train for two years in the six rules.’*";
P_HTM[12942]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[12943]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[12944]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[12945]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12946]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya sikkhamānā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācati.**So-and-so, who is a trainee nun under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[12947]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ saṅgho itthannāmāya sikkhamānāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval to trainee nun so-and-so to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[12948]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[12949]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[12950]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya sikkhamānā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācati.**So-and-so, who is a trainee nun under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[12951]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya sikkhamānāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval to trainee nun so-and-so to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[12952]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya sikkhamānāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval to trainee nun so-and-so to train in the six rules for two years should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[12953]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[12954]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya sikkhamānāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammuti.**The Sangha has given approval to trainee nun so-and-so to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[12955]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[12956]="*Sā sikkhamānā “evaṃ vadehī”ti vattabbā—**That trainee nun should then be told to say this:*";
P_HTM[12957]="*“pāṇātipātā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi.**‘I undertake to abstain from killing living beings for two years without transgression.*";
P_HTM[12958]="*Adinnādānā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi.**I undertake to abstain from stealing for two years without transgression.*";
P_HTM[12959]="*Abrahmacariyā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi.**I undertake to abstain from sexual activity for two years without transgression.*";
P_HTM[12960]="*Musāvādā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi.**I undertake to abstain from lying for two years without transgression.*";
P_HTM[12961]="*Surāmerayamajjappamādaṭṭhānā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi.**I undertake to abstain from alcohol, which causes heedlessness, for two years without transgression.*";
P_HTM[12962]="*Vikālabhojanā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmī”ti.**I undertake to abstain from eating at the wrong time for two years without transgression.’”*";
P_HTM[12963]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[12964]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[12965]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a trainee nun who has not trained in the six rules for two years, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[12966]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[12967]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[12968]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[12969]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[12970]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[12971]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[12972]="*Asikkhitasikkhā nāma**Who has not trained:*";
P_HTM[12973]="*sikkhā vā na dinnā hoti, dinnā vā sikkhā kupitā.**the training has not been given to her, or the training has been given to her, but she has failed in it.*";
P_HTM[12974]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[12975]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[12976]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12977]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12978]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12979]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[12980]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12981]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12982]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12983]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[12984]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12985]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12986]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[12987]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[12988]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years;*";
P_HTM[12989]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[12990]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[12991]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[12992]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[12993]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[12994]="*64. Dutiyasikkhamānasikkhāpada**64. The second training rule on trainee nuns*";
P_HTM[12995]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[12996]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to trainee nuns who had trained in the six rules for two years, but who had not been approved by the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[12997]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns said,*";
P_HTM[12998]="*“etha, sikkhamānā, imaṃ jānātha, imaṃ detha, imaṃ āharatha, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karothā”ti.**“Come, trainee nuns, find out about this,” “Give this,” “Bring this,” “There’s need for this,” or “Make this allowable.”*";
P_HTM[12999]="*Tā evamāhaṃsu—**But they replied,*";
P_HTM[13000]="*“na mayaṃ, ayye, sikkhamānā, bhikkhuniyo mayan”ti.**“Venerables, we’re not trainee nuns. We’re nuns.”*";
P_HTM[13001]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13002]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to trainee nuns who have trained for two years in the six rules, but who haven’t been approved by the Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[13003]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13004]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13005]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13006]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13007]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13008]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[13009]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13010]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval is required for the full admission of a trainee nun who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13011]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13012]="*Tāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that trainee nun should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say:*";
P_HTM[13013]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā sikkhamānā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, I, the trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, ask the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.’*";
P_HTM[13014]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[13015]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[13016]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13017]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13018]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā sikkhamānā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācati.**This trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained under Venerable so-and-so for two years in the six rules, is asking the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13019]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval for the trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained for two years in the six rules, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13020]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13021]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13022]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā sikkhamānā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācati.**This trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained under Venerable so-and-so for two years in the six rules, is asking the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13023]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval for the trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained for two years in the six rules, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13024]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya vuṭṭhānasammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval for the trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained for two years in the six rules, to be fully admitted should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13025]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13026]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya sikkhamānāya vuṭṭhānasammuti;**The Sangha has given approval for the trainee nun so-and-so, who has trained for two years in the six rules, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13027]="*khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13028]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[13029]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13030]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years, but who has not been approved by the Sangha, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13031]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13032]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13033]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13034]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13035]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13036]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13037]="*Sikkhitasikkhā nāma**Who has trained:*";
P_HTM[13038]="*chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**who has trained in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13039]="*Asammatā nāma**Who has not been approved:*";
P_HTM[13040]="*ñattidutiyena kammena vuṭṭhānasammuti na dinnā hoti.**approval to be fully admitted has not been given though a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement.*";
P_HTM[13041]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13042]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13043]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13044]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13045]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13046]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13047]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13048]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13049]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13050]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13051]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13052]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13053]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13054]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13055]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ sikkhamānaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a trainee nun who has trained in the six rules for two years and who has been approved by the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[13056]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13057]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13058]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13059]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13060]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[13061]="*65. Gihigatasikkhāpada**65. The training rule on married girls*";
P_HTM[13062]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[13063]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**the nuns were giving the full admission to married girls less than twelve years old.*";
P_HTM[13064]="*Tā akkhamā honti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ.**They were unable to endure cold and heat; hunger and thirst; contact with horseflies, mosquitoes, wind, the burning sun, and creeping animals and insects; rude and unwelcome speech;*";
P_HTM[13065]="*Uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātikā honti.**and they were unable to bear up with bodily feelings that are painful, severe, sharp, and destructive of life.*";
P_HTM[13066]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13067]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to married girls less than twelve years old?” …*";
P_HTM[13068]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13069]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13070]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13071]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13072]="*Ūnadvādasavassā, bhikkhave, gihigatā akkhamā hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ.**A married girl less than twelve years old is unable to endure cold and heat; hunger and thirst; contact with horseflies, mosquitoes, wind, the burning sun, and creeping animals and insects; rude and unwelcome speech;*";
P_HTM[13073]="*Uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātikā hoti.**and she’s unable to bear up with bodily feelings that are painful, severe, sharp, and destructive of life.*";
P_HTM[13074]="*Dvādasavassāva kho, bhikkhave, gihigatā khamā hoti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ.**But a married girl who is twelve years old is able to endure these things.*";
P_HTM[13075]="*Uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātikā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[13076]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13077]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13078]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ūnadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a married girl who is less than twelve years old, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13079]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13080]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13081]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13082]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13083]="*Ūnadvādasavassā nāma**Who is less than twelve years old:*";
P_HTM[13084]="*appattadvādasavassā.**who has not reached twelve years of age.*";
P_HTM[13085]="*Gihigatā nāma**A married girl:*";
P_HTM[13086]="*purisantaragatā vuccati.**one who has gone to the place of a man is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13087]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13088]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13089]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13090]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13091]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13092]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13093]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13094]="*Ūnadvādasavassāya ūnadvādasavassasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the girl is less than twelve years old, and she perceives her as less, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13095]="*Ūnadvādasavassāya vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the girl is less than twelve years old, but she is unsure of it, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13096]="*Ūnadvādasavassāya paripuṇṇasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, anāpatti.**If the girl is less than twelve years old, but she perceives her as more, and she gives her the full admission, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[13097]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya ūnadvādasavassasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the girl is more than twelve years old, but she perceives her as less, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13098]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the girl is more than twelve years old, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13099]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya paripuṇṇasaññā, anāpatti.**If the girl is more than twelve years old, and she perceives her as more, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[13100]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13101]="*ūnadvādasavassaṃ paripuṇṇasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a girl less than twelve years old, but she perceives her as more;*";
P_HTM[13102]="*paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ paripuṇṇasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a girl more than twelve years old, and she perceives her as more;*";
P_HTM[13103]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13104]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13105]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13106]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13107]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[13108]="*66. Dutiyagihigatasikkhāpada**66. The second training rule on married girls*";
P_HTM[13109]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13110]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to married girls who were more than twelve years old, but who had not trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13111]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**They were ignorant and incompetent, and they did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13112]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13113]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to married girls who are more than twelve years old, but who haven’t trained for two years in the six rules?” …*";
P_HTM[13114]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13115]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13116]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13117]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13118]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13119]="*vigarahitvā dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**and after criticizing them … he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13120]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval is required for a married girl who is more than twelve years old to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13121]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And the approval is to be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13122]="*Tāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that married girl who is more than twelve years old should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[13123]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, I, so-and-so, a married girl who is more than twelve years old, am training under Venerable so-and-so. I ask the Sangha for approval to train for two years in the six rules.’*";
P_HTM[13124]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[13125]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[13126]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13127]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13128]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācati.**The married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and training under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13129]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval to the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old, to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13130]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13131]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13132]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācati.**The married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and training under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13133]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval to the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old, to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13134]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval to the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old, to train in the six rules for two years should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13135]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13136]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammuti.**The Sangha has given approval to the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old, to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13137]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[13138]="*Sā paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā evaṃ vadehīti vattabbā—**That married girl, who is more than twelve years old, should be told to say this:*";
P_HTM[13139]="*“pāṇātipātā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi …pe…**‘I undertake to abstain from killing living beings for two years without transgression. …*";
P_HTM[13140]="*vikālabhojanā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmī”ti.**I undertake to abstain from eating at the wrong time for two years without transgression.’”*";
P_HTM[13141]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[13142]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13143]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a married girl who is more than twelve years old, but who has not trained in the six rules for two years, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13144]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13145]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13146]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13147]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13148]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassā nāma**Who is more than twelve years old:*";
P_HTM[13149]="*pattadvādasavassā.**who has reached twelve years of age.*";
P_HTM[13150]="*Gihigatā nāma**A married girl:*";
P_HTM[13151]="*purisantaragatā vuccati.**one who has gone to the place of a man is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13152]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13153]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13154]="*Asikkhitasikkhā nāma**Who has not trained:*";
P_HTM[13155]="*sikkhā vā na dinnā hoti, dinnā vā sikkhā kupitā.**the training has not been given to her, or the training has been given to her, but she has failed in it.*";
P_HTM[13156]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13157]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13158]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13159]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13160]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13161]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13162]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13163]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13164]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13165]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13166]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13167]="*Adhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13168]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13169]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13170]="*paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a married girl who is more than twelve years old and who has trained in the six rules for two years;*";
P_HTM[13171]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13172]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13173]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13174]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13175]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[13176]="*67. Tatiyagihigatasikkhāpada**67. The third training rule on married girls*";
P_HTM[13177]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13178]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to married girls who were more than twelve years old and who had trained in the six rules for two years, but who had not been approved by the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[13179]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns said,*";
P_HTM[13180]="*“etha, sikkhamānā, imaṃ jānātha, imaṃ detha, imaṃ āharatha, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karothā”ti.**“Come, trainee nuns, find out about this,” “Give this,” “Bring this,” “There’s need for this,” or “Make this allowable.”*";
P_HTM[13181]="*Tā evamāhaṃsu—**But they replied,*";
P_HTM[13182]="*“na mayaṃ, ayye, sikkhamānā, bhikkhuniyo mayan”ti.**“Venerables, we’re not trainee nuns. We’re nuns.”*";
P_HTM[13183]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13184]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to married girls who are more than twelve years old and who have trained for two years in the six rules, but who haven’t been approved by the Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[13185]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13186]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13187]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13188]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13189]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13190]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[13191]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13192]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval should be given for the full admission of a married girl who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13193]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it should be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13194]="*Tāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that married girl who is more than twelve years old should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[13195]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā, saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, I, the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, ask the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.’*";
P_HTM[13196]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[13197]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[13198]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo.**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13199]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13200]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācati.**This married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13201]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval for the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13202]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13203]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13204]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassā gihigatā dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācati.**This married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13205]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval for the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13206]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval for the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13207]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13208]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya gihigatāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammuti.**The Sangha has given approval for the married girl so-and-so, who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13209]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13210]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[13211]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13212]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a married girl who is more than twelve years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules, but who has not been approved by the Sangha, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13213]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13214]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13215]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13216]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13217]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassā nāma**Who is more than twelve years old:*";
P_HTM[13218]="*pattadvādasavassā.**who has reached twelve years of age.*";
P_HTM[13219]="*Gihigatā nāma**A married girl:*";
P_HTM[13220]="*purisantaragatā vuccati.**one who has gone to the place of a man is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13221]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13222]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13223]="*Sikkhitasikkhā nāma**Who has trained:*";
P_HTM[13224]="*chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**who has trained in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13225]="*Asammatā nāma**Who has not been approved:*";
P_HTM[13226]="*ñattidutiyena kammena vuṭṭhānasammuti na dinnā hoti.**approval to be fully admitted has not been given though a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement.*";
P_HTM[13227]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13228]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13229]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13230]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13231]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13232]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13233]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13234]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13235]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13236]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13237]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13238]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13239]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13240]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13241]="*paripuṇṇadvādasavassaṃ gihigataṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a married girl who is more than twelve years old and who has trained in the six rules for two years and who has been approved by the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[13242]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13243]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13244]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13245]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13246]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[13247]="*68. Sahajīvinīsikkhāpada**68. The training rule on disciples*";
P_HTM[13248]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13249]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā dve vassāni neva anuggaṇhāti na anuggaṇhāpeti.**At that time the nun Thullanandā gave the full admission to her disciples, but then, for the next two years, neither guided them nor had them guided.*";
P_HTM[13250]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā;**They were ignorant and incompetent,*";
P_HTM[13251]="*na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**and they did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13252]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13253]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā dve vassāni neva anuggaṇhissati na anuggaṇhāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How can Venerable Thullanandā give the full admission to her disciples, and then neither guide them nor have them guided for two years?” …*";
P_HTM[13254]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā dve vassāni neva anuggaṇhāti na anuggaṇhāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā does this?”*";
P_HTM[13255]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13256]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13257]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā dve vassāni neva anuggaṇhissati na anuggaṇhāpessati.**“How can the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[13258]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13259]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13260]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā dve vassāni neva anuggaṇheyya na anuggaṇhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to her disciple, and then, for the next two years, neither guides her nor has her guided, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13261]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13262]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13263]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13264]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13265]="*Sahajīvinī nāma**Disciple:*";
P_HTM[13266]="*saddhivihārinī vuccati.**student is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13267]="*Vuṭṭhāpetvāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13268]="*upasampādetvā.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13269]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13270]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13271]="*Neva anuggaṇheyyāti**Neither guides her:*";
P_HTM[13272]="*na sayaṃ anuggaṇheyya uddesena paripucchāya ovādena anusāsaniyā.**she does not herself guide her—through recitation, through questioning, through instruction, though teaching.*";
P_HTM[13273]="*Na anuggaṇhāpeyyāti**Nor has her guided:*";
P_HTM[13274]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya**she does not ask anyone else.*";
P_HTM[13275]="*“dve vassāni neva anuggaṇhissāmi na anuggaṇhāpessāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I’ll neither guide her nor have her guided for two years,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13276]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13277]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[13278]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches for someone to guide her, but cannot find anyone;*";
P_HTM[13279]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[13280]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[13281]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13282]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13283]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13284]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13285]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[13286]="*69. Pavattinīnānubandhanasikkhāpada**69. The training rule on not following one’s mentor*";
P_HTM[13287]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13288]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo vuṭṭhāpitaṃ pavattiniṃ dve vassāni nānubandhanti.**At that time nuns who had received the full admission did not follow their mentor for two years.*";
P_HTM[13289]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā;**They were ignorant and incompetent,*";
P_HTM[13290]="*na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**and they did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13291]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13292]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo vuṭṭhāpitaṃ pavattiniṃ dve vassāni nānubandhissantī”ti …pe…**“How can those nuns receive the full admission and then not follow their mentor for two years?” …*";
P_HTM[13293]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vuṭṭhāpitaṃ pavattiniṃ dve vassāni nānubandhantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns don’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[13294]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13295]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13296]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo vuṭṭhāpitaṃ pavattiniṃ dve vassāni nānubandhissanti.**“How can nuns not do this?*";
P_HTM[13297]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13298]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13299]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī vuṭṭhāpitaṃ pavattiniṃ dve vassāni nānubandheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun does not follow the mentor who gave her the full admission for two years, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13300]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13301]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13302]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13303]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13304]="*Vuṭṭhāpitanti**Who gave her the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13305]="*upasampāditaṃ.**who gave her the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13306]="*Pavattinī nāma**The mentor:*";
P_HTM[13307]="*upajjhāyā vuccati.**the preceptor is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13308]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13309]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13310]="*Nānubandheyyāti**Does not follow:*";
P_HTM[13311]="*na sayaṃ upaṭṭhaheyya.**does not herself attend on her.*";
P_HTM[13312]="*Dve vassāni nānubandhissāmīti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I won’t follow her for two years,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13313]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13314]="*upajjhāyā bālā vā hoti alajjinī vā,**if the preceptor is ignorant or shameless;*";
P_HTM[13315]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[13316]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[13317]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13318]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13319]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13320]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13321]="*Gabbhinivagga**The sub-chapter on pregnant women*";
P_HTM[13322]="*70. Dutiyasahajīvinīsikkhāpada**70. The second training rule on disciples*";
P_HTM[13323]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13324]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā neva vūpakāseti na vūpakāsāpeti.**At that time the nun Thullanandā gave the full admission to a disciple, but neither took her away nor had her taken away.*";
P_HTM[13325]="*Sāmiko aggahesi.**And so her husband got hold of her.*";
P_HTM[13326]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13327]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā neva vūpakāsessati na vūpakāsāpessati, sāmiko aggahesi.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give the full admission to a disciple, and then neither take her away nor have her taken away?*";
P_HTM[13328]="*Sacāyaṃ bhikkhunī pakkantā assa, na ca sāmiko gaṇheyyā”ti …pe…**If this nun had gone away, her husband would not have gotten hold of her.” …*";
P_HTM[13329]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā neva vūpakāseti na vūpakāsāpeti, sāmiko aggahesī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā didn’t do this?”*";
P_HTM[13330]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13331]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13332]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā neva vūpakāsessati na vūpakāsāpessati, sāmiko aggahesi.**“How could the nun Thullanandā not do this?*";
P_HTM[13333]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13334]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13335]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī sahajīviniṃ vuṭṭhāpetvā neva vūpakāseyya na vūpakāsāpeyya antamaso chappañcayojanānipi, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to her disciple, and then neither takes her away nor has her taken away, even if just 65 to 80 kilometers, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13336]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13337]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13338]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13339]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13340]="*Sahajīvinī nāma**Disciple:*";
P_HTM[13341]="*saddhivihārinī vuccati.**student is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13342]="*Vuṭṭhāpetvāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13343]="*upasampādetvā.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13344]="*Neva vūpakāseyyāti**Neither takes her away:*";
P_HTM[13345]="*na sayaṃ vūpakāseyya.**she does not herself take her away.*";
P_HTM[13346]="*Na vūpakāsāpeyyāti**Nor has her taken away:*";
P_HTM[13347]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya.**she does not ask anyone else to take her away.*";
P_HTM[13348]="*“Neva vūpakāsessāmi na vūpakāsāpessāmi antamaso chappañcayojanānipī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I’ll neither take her away nor have her taken away, even just 65 to 80 kilometers,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13349]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13350]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[13351]="*pariyesitvā dutiyikaṃ bhikkhuniṃ na labhati,**if she searches for a companion nun for her, but cannot find anyone;*";
P_HTM[13352]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[13353]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[13354]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13355]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13356]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13357]="*Gabbhinivaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on pregnant women is finished.*";
P_HTM[13358]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13359]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13360]="*71. Kumāribhūtasikkhāpada**71. The training rule on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13361]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13362]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo ūnavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to unmarried girls less than twenty years old.*";
P_HTM[13363]="*Tā akkhamā honti sītassa uṇhassa jighacchāya pipāsāya ḍaṃsamakasavātātapasarīsapasamphassānaṃ duruttānaṃ durāgatānaṃ vacanapathānaṃ.**They were unable to endure cold and heat; hunger and thirst; contact with horseflies, mosquitoes, wind, the burning sun, and creeping animals and insects; rude and unwelcome speech;*";
P_HTM[13364]="*Uppannānaṃ sārīrikānaṃ vedanānaṃ dukkhānaṃ tibbānaṃ kharānaṃ kaṭukānaṃ asātānaṃ amanāpānaṃ pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātikā honti.**and they were unable to bear up with bodily feelings that are painful, severe, sharp, and destructive of life.*";
P_HTM[13365]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13366]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo ūnavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to unmarried girls less than twelve years old?” …*";
P_HTM[13367]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ūnavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13368]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13369]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13370]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ūnavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13371]="*Ūnavīsativassā, bhikkhave, kumāribhūtā akkhamā hoti sītassa uṇhassa …pe…**An unmarried girl less than twenty years old is unable to endure cold and heat; hunger and thirst; contact with horseflies, mosquitoes, wind, the burning sun, and creeping animals and insects; rude and unwelcome speech;*";
P_HTM[13372]="*pāṇaharānaṃ anadhivāsakajātikā hoti.**and she’s unable to bear up with bodily feelings that are painful, severe, sharp, and destructive of life.*";
P_HTM[13373]="*Vīsativassāva kho, bhikkhave, kumāribhūtā khamā hoti sītassa uṇhassa …pe…**But an unmarried girl who is twenty years old is able to endure these things.*";
P_HTM[13374]="*pāṇaharānaṃ adhivāsakajātikā hoti.* **";
P_HTM[13375]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13376]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13377]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ūnavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to an unmarried girl who is less than twenty years old, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13378]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13379]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13380]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13381]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13382]="*Ūnavīsativassā nāma**Who is less than twenty years old:*";
P_HTM[13383]="*appattavīsativassā.**who has not reached twenty years of age.*";
P_HTM[13384]="*Kumāribhūtā nāma**An unmarried girl:*";
P_HTM[13385]="*sāmaṇerī vuccati.**a novice nun is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13386]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13387]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13388]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13389]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13390]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13391]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13392]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13393]="*Ūnavīsativassāya ūnavīsativassasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If the girl is less than twenty years old, and she perceives her as less, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13394]="*Ūnavīsativassāya vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the girl is less than twenty years old, but she is unsure of it, and she gives her the full admission, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13395]="*Ūnavīsativassāya paripuṇṇasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, anāpatti.**If the girl is less than twenty years old, but she perceives her as more, and she gives her the full admission, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[13396]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassāya ūnavīsativassasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the girl is more than twenty years old, but she perceives her as less, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13397]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassāya vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If the girl is more than twenty years old, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13398]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassāya paripuṇṇasaññā, anāpatti.**If the girl is more than twenty years old, and she perceives her as more, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[13399]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13400]="*ūnavīsativassaṃ paripuṇṇasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a girl less than twenty years old, but she perceives her as more;*";
P_HTM[13401]="*paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ paripuṇṇasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to a girl more than twenty years old, and she perceives her as more;*";
P_HTM[13402]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13403]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13404]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13405]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13406]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13407]="*72. Dutiyakumāribhūtasikkhāpada**72. The second training rule on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13408]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13409]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to unmarried girls who were more than twenty years old, but who had not trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13410]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā;**They were ignorant and incompetent,*";
P_HTM[13411]="*na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**and they did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13412]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13413]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to unmarried girls who are more than twenty years old, but who haven’t trained for two years in the six rules?” …*";
P_HTM[13414]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13415]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13416]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13417]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13418]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13419]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[13420]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13421]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, aṭṭhārasavassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval is required for an unmarried girl who is eighteen years old to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13422]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And the approval is to be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13423]="*Tāya aṭṭhārasavassāya kumāribhūtāya saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that unmarried girl who is eighteen years old should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[13424]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya aṭṭhārasavassā kumāribhūtā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, I, so-and-so, an unmarried girl who is eighteen years old, am training under Venerable so-and-so. I ask the Sangha for approval to train for two years in the six rules.’*";
P_HTM[13425]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[13426]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[13427]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13428]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13429]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya aṭṭhārasavassā kumāribhūtā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācati.**This unmarried girl so-and-so, who is eighteen years old and training under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13430]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmāya aṭṭhārasavassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval to the unmarried girl so-and-so who is eighteen years old to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13431]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13432]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13433]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya aṭṭhārasavassā kumāribhūtā saṅghaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ yācati.**This unmarried girl so-and-so, who is eighteen years old and training under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13434]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya aṭṭhārasavassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval to the unmarried girl so-and-so who is eighteen years old to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13435]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya aṭṭhārasavassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval to the unmarried girl so-and-so who is eighteen years old to train in the six rules for two years should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13436]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13437]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya aṭṭhārasavassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhāsammuti.**The Sangha has given approval to the unmarried girl so-and-so who is eighteen years old to train in the six rules for two years.*";
P_HTM[13438]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’*";
P_HTM[13439]="*Sā aṭṭhārasavassā kumāribhūtā evaṃ vadehīti vattabbā—**That unmarried girl who is eighteen years old should be told to say this:*";
P_HTM[13440]="*“pāṇātipātā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmi …pe…**‘I undertake to abstain from killing living beings for two years without transgression. …*";
P_HTM[13441]="*vikālabhojanā veramaṇiṃ dve vassāni avītikkamma samādānaṃ samādiyāmī”ti.**I undertake to abstain from eating at the wrong time for two years without transgression.’”*";
P_HTM[13442]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[13443]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13444]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu asikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old, but who has not trained in the six rules for two years, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13445]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13446]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13447]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13448]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13449]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassā nāma**Who is more than twenty years old:*";
P_HTM[13450]="*pattavīsativassā.**who has reached twenty years of age.*";
P_HTM[13451]="*Kumāribhūtā nāma**An unmarried girl:*";
P_HTM[13452]="*sāmaṇerī vuccati.**a novice nun is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13453]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13454]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13455]="*Asikkhitasikkhā nāma**Who has not trained:*";
P_HTM[13456]="*sikkhā vā na dinnā hoti, dinnā vā sikkhā kupitā.**the training has not been given to her, or the training has been given to her, but she has failed in it.*";
P_HTM[13457]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13458]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13459]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13460]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13461]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13462]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13463]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13464]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13465]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13466]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13467]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13468]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13469]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13470]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13471]="*paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old, and who has trained in the six rules for two years;*";
P_HTM[13472]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13473]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13474]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13475]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13476]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13477]="*73. Tatiyakumāribhūtasikkhāpada**73. The third training rule on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13478]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13479]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to unmarried girls who were more than twenty years old and who had trained in the six rules for two years, but who had not been approved by the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[13480]="*Bhikkhuniyo evamāhaṃsu—**The nuns said this:*";
P_HTM[13481]="*“etha, sikkhamānā, imaṃ jānātha, imaṃ detha, imaṃ āharatha, iminā attho, imaṃ kappiyaṃ karothā”ti.**“Come, trainee nuns, find out about this,” “Give this,” “Bring this,” “There’s need for this,” or “Make this allowable.”*";
P_HTM[13482]="*Tā evamāhaṃsu—**But they replied,*";
P_HTM[13483]="*“na mayaṃ, ayye, sikkhamānā, bhikkhuniyo mayan”ti.**“Venerables, we’re not trainee nuns. We’re nuns.”*";
P_HTM[13484]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13485]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to unmarried girls who are more than twenty years old and who have trained for two years in the six rules, but who haven’t been approved by the Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[13486]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13487]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13488]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13489]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13490]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13491]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[13492]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13493]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paripuṇṇavīsativassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval is required for the full admission of an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13494]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And the approval is to be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13495]="*Tāya paripuṇṇavīsativassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[13496]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇavīsativassā kumāribhūtā dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, I, the unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, ask the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.’*";
P_HTM[13497]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[13498]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[13499]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should then inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13500]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13501]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇavīsativassā kumāribhūtā dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācati.**This unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13502]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇavīsativassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval for the unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13503]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13504]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13505]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā itthannāmāya ayyāya paripuṇṇavīsativassā kumāribhūtā dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ yācati.**This unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, is asking the Sangha for approval to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13506]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇavīsativassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval for the unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13507]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya paripuṇṇavīsativassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval for the unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13508]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13509]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya paripuṇṇavīsativassāya kumāribhūtāya dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhāya vuṭṭhānasammuti.**The Sangha has given approval for the unmarried girl so-and-so, who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules under Venerable so-and-so, to be fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13510]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13511]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[13512]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13513]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena asammataṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old and who has trained for two years in the six rules, but who has not been approved by the Sangha, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13514]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13515]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13516]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13517]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13518]="*Paripuṇṇavīsativassā nāma**Who is more than twenty years old:*";
P_HTM[13519]="*pattavīsativassā.**who has reached twenty years of age.*";
P_HTM[13520]="*Kumāribhūtā nāma**An unmarried girl:*";
P_HTM[13521]="*sāmaṇerī vuccati.**a novice nun is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13522]="*Dve vassānīti**Two years:*";
P_HTM[13523]="*dve saṃvaccharāni.**two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13524]="*Sikkhitasikkhā nāma**Who has trained:*";
P_HTM[13525]="*chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**who has trained in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13526]="*Asammatā nāma**Who has not been approved:*";
P_HTM[13527]="*ñattidutiyena kammena vuṭṭhānasammuti na dinnā hoti.**approval to be fully admitted has not been given though a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement.*";
P_HTM[13528]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13529]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13530]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13531]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13532]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13533]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13534]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13535]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13536]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13537]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13538]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13539]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13540]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13541]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13542]="*paripuṇṇavīsativassaṃ kumāribhūtaṃ dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhaṃ saṅghena sammataṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to an unmarried girl who is more than twenty years old, who has trained in the six rules for two years, and who has been approved by the Sangha;*";
P_HTM[13543]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13544]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13545]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13546]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13547]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13548]="*74. Ūnadvādasavassasikkhāpada**74. The training rule on less than twelve years*";
P_HTM[13549]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13550]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time nuns who had less than twelve years of seniority were giving the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13551]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**They were ignorant and incompetent, and they did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13552]="*Saddhivihāriniyopi bālā honti abyattā;**And their students too were ignorant and incompetent,*";
P_HTM[13553]="*na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**and they too did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13554]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13555]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns who have less than twelve years of seniority give the full admission?” …*";
P_HTM[13556]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13557]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13558]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13559]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ūnadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13560]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13561]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13562]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ūnadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun who has less than twelve years of seniority gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13563]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13564]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13565]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13566]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13567]="*Ūnadvādasavassā nāma**Who has less than twelve years of seniority:*";
P_HTM[13568]="*appattadvādasavassā.**who has not reached twelve years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[13569]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13570]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13571]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13572]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13573]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13574]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13575]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13576]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13577]="*paripuṇṇadvādasavassā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if one who has twelve years of seniority gives the full admission;*";
P_HTM[13578]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13579]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13580]="*Catutthasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fourth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13581]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13582]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13583]="*75. Paripuṇṇadvādasavassasikkhāpada**75. The training rule on twelve years of seniority*";
P_HTM[13584]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13585]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena asammatā vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time nuns who had twelve years of seniority were giving the full admission without being approved by the Sangha.*";
P_HTM[13586]="*Tā bālā honti abyattā;**They were ignorant and incompetent,*";
P_HTM[13587]="*na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**and they did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13588]="*Saddhivihāriniyopi bālā honti abyattā;**And their students too were ignorant and incompetent,*";
P_HTM[13589]="*na jānanti kappiyaṃ vā akappiyaṃ vā.**and they too did not know what was allowable and what was not.*";
P_HTM[13590]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13591]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena asammatā vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns who have twelve years of seniority give the full admission without being approved by the Sangha?” …*";
P_HTM[13592]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena asammatā vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13593]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13594]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13595]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena asammatā vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13596]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13597]="*vigarahitvā …pe…**and after criticizing them …*";
P_HTM[13598]="*dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—**he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13599]="*“anujānāmi, bhikkhave, paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya bhikkhuniyā vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ dātuṃ.**“Monks, approval is required for a nun who has twelve years of seniority to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13600]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And the approval is to be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13601]="*Tāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya bhikkhuniyā saṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā vuḍḍhānaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ pāde vanditvā ukkuṭikaṃ nisīditvā añjaliṃ paggahetvā evamassa vacanīyo—**After approaching the Sangha of nuns, that nun who has twelve years of seniority should put her upper robe over one shoulder and pay respect at the feet of the senior nuns. She should then squat on her heels, raise her joined palms, and say,*";
P_HTM[13602]="*‘ahaṃ, ayye, itthannāmā paripuṇṇadvādasavassā bhikkhunī saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ yācāmī’ti.**‘Venerables, I, the nun so-and-so who has twelve years of seniority, ask the Sangha for approval to give the full admission.’*";
P_HTM[13603]="*Dutiyampi yācitabbā.**And she should ask a second*";
P_HTM[13604]="*Tatiyampi yācitabbā.**and a third time.*";
P_HTM[13605]="*Sā bhikkhunī saṅghena paricchinditabbā— ‘byattāyaṃ bhikkhunī lajjinī’ti.**The Sangha should then decide whether that nun is competent and has a sense of conscience.*";
P_HTM[13606]="*Sace bālā ca hoti alajjinī ca, na dātabbā.**If she is ignorant and shameless, approval should not be given.*";
P_HTM[13607]="*Sace bālā hoti lajjinī, na dātabbā.**If she is ignorant but has a sense of conscience, approval should not be given.*";
P_HTM[13608]="*Sace byattā hoti alajjinī, na dātabbā.**If she is competent but shameless, approval should not be given.*";
P_HTM[13609]="*Sace byattā ca hoti lajjinī ca, dātabbā.**If she is competent and has a sense of conscience, approval should be given.*";
P_HTM[13610]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, dātabbā.**And it is to be given like this.*";
P_HTM[13611]="*Byattāya bhikkhuniyā paṭibalāya saṅgho ñāpetabbo—**A competent and capable nun should inform the Sangha:*";
P_HTM[13612]="*‘Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**‘Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13613]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā paripuṇṇadvādasavassā bhikkhunī saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ yācati.**The nun so-and-so, who has twelve years of seniority, is asking the Sangha for approval to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13614]="*Yadi saṅghassa pattakallaṃ, saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya bhikkhuniyā vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ dadeyya.**If it seems appropriate to the Sangha, the Sangha should give approval to nun so-and-so, who has twelve years of seniority, to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13615]="*Esā ñatti.**This is the motion.*";
P_HTM[13616]="*Suṇātu me, ayye, saṅgho.**Please, Venerables, I ask the Sangha to listen.*";
P_HTM[13617]="*Ayaṃ itthannāmā paripuṇṇadvādasavassā bhikkhunī saṅghaṃ vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ yācati.**The nun so-and-so, who has twelve years of seniority, is asking the Sangha for approval to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13618]="*Saṅgho itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya bhikkhuniyā vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ deti.**The Sangha gives approval to nun so-and-so, who has twelve years of seniority, to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13619]="*Yassā ayyāya khamati itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya bhikkhuniyā vuṭṭhāpanasammutiyā dānaṃ, sā tuṇhassa;**Any nun who approves of giving approval to nun so-and-so, who has twelve years of seniority, to give the full admission should remain silent.*";
P_HTM[13620]="*yassā nakkhamati, sā bhāseyya.**Any nun who does not approve should speak up.*";
P_HTM[13621]="*Dinnā saṅghena itthannāmāya paripuṇṇadvādasavassāya bhikkhuniyā vuṭṭhāpanasammuti.**The Sangha has given approval to nun so-and-so, who has twelve years of seniority, to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13622]="*Khamati saṅghassa, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmī’”ti.**The Sangha approves and is therefore silent. I will remember it thus.’”*";
P_HTM[13623]="*Atha kho bhagavā tā bhikkhuniyo anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā dubbharatāya …pe…**Then, after criticizing those nuns in many ways, the Buddha spoke in dispraise of being difficult to support …*";
P_HTM[13624]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13625]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena asammatā vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun who has twelve years of seniority gives the full admission without approval from the Sangha, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13626]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13627]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13628]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13629]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13630]="*Paripuṇṇadvādasavassā nāma**Who has twelve years of seniority:*";
P_HTM[13631]="*pattadvādasavassā.**who has reached twelve years of seniority.*";
P_HTM[13632]="*Asammatā nāma**Without approval:*";
P_HTM[13633]="*ñattidutiyena kammena vuṭṭhāpanasammuti na dinnā hoti.**approval to give the full admission has not been given though a legal procedure consisting of one motion and one announcement.*";
P_HTM[13634]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13635]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13636]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13637]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13638]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13639]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13640]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13641]="*Dhammakamme dhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13642]="*Dhammakamme vematikā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13643]="*Dhammakamme adhammakammasaññā vuṭṭhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If it is a legitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as illegitimate, and she gives the full admission, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13644]="*Adhammakamme dhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she perceives it as legitimate, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13645]="*Adhammakamme vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13646]="*Adhammakamme adhammakammasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If it is an illegitimate legal procedure, and she perceives it as such, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13647]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13648]="*paripuṇṇadvādasavassā saṅghena sammatā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she has twelve years of seniority, has been approved by the Sangha, and then gives the full admission;*";
P_HTM[13649]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13650]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13651]="*Pañcamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13652]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13653]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13654]="*76. Khīyanadhammasikkhāpada**76. The training rule on criticizing*";
P_HTM[13655]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[13656]="*Tena kho pana samayena caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī bhikkhunisaṅghaṃ upasaṅkamitvā vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ yācati.**the nun Caṇḍakāḷī approached the Sangha of nuns and asked for approval to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13657]="*Atha kho bhikkhunisaṅgho caṇḍakāḷiṃ bhikkhuniṃ paricchinditvā—**The Sangha of nuns*";
P_HTM[13658]="*“alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenā”ti, vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ na adāsi.**decided that she should not,*";
P_HTM[13659]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī “sādhū”ti paṭissuṇi.**and Caṇḍakāḷī consented.*";
P_HTM[13660]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhunisaṅgho aññāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ deti.**Soon afterwards the Sangha of nuns gave approval to other nuns to give the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13661]="*Caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī ujjhāyati khiyyati vipāceti—**Caṇḍakāḷī complained and criticized it,*";
P_HTM[13662]="*“ahameva nūna bālā, ahameva nūna alajjinī;**“So it seems I’m ignorant and shameless,*";
P_HTM[13663]="*yaṃ saṅgho aññāsaṃ bhikkhunīnaṃ vuṭṭhāpanasammutiṃ deti, mayhameva na detī”ti.**since the Sangha gives approval to other nuns, but not to me.”*";
P_HTM[13664]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13665]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā caṇḍakāḷī—**“How could Venerable Caṇḍakāḷī*";
P_HTM[13666]="*‘alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenā’ti vuccamānā ‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissatī”ti …pe…**consent to not being approved to give the full admission, and then criticize it afterwards?” …*";
P_HTM[13667]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī ‘alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenā’ti vuccamānā ‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjatī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Caṇḍakāḷī did this?”*";
P_HTM[13668]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13669]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13670]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, caṇḍakāḷī bhikkhunī—**“How could the nun Caṇḍakāḷī*";
P_HTM[13671]="*‘alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenā’ti vuccamānā ‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjissati.**do this?*";
P_HTM[13672]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13673]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13674]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī—‘alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenā’ti vuccamānā ‘sādhū’ti paṭissuṇitvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun is told, “Venerable, you have given enough full admissions for now,” and she consents, saying, “Fine,” but then criticizes it afterwards, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13675]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13676]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13677]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13678]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13679]="*Alaṃ tāva te, ayye, vuṭṭhāpitenāti**Venerable, you have given enough full admissions for now:*";
P_HTM[13680]="*alaṃ tāva te, ayye, upasampāditena.**Venerable, you have given enough full ordinations for now.*";
P_HTM[13681]="*“Sādhū”ti paṭissuṇitvā pacchā khīyanadhammaṃ āpajjati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she consents, saying, “Fine,” but then criticizes it afterwards, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13682]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13683]="*pakatiyā chandā dosā mohā bhayā karontaṃ khiyyati,**if she criticizes one who regularly acts out of favoritism, ill will, confusion, or fear;*";
P_HTM[13684]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13685]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13686]="*Chaṭṭhasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The sixth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13687]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13688]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13689]="*77. Sikkhamāna-navuṭṭhāpanasikkhāpada**77. The training rule on not giving the full admission to trainee nuns*";
P_HTM[13690]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[13691]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā sikkhamānā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ upasaṅkamitvā upasampadaṃ yāci.**a trainee nun went to the nun Thullanandā and asked her for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13692]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī taṃ sikkhamānaṃ—**Thullanandā told her,*";
P_HTM[13693]="*“sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpeti na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti.**“If you give me a robe, Venerable, I’ll give you the full admission.” But she neither gave her the full admission nor made any effort to have her fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13694]="*Atha kho sā sikkhamānā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That trainee nun told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[13695]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13696]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā sikkhamānaṃ—**“How could Venerable Thullanandā say this to a trainee nun,*";
P_HTM[13697]="*‘sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpessati na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**but then neither give her the full admission nor make any effort to have her fully admitted?” …*";
P_HTM[13698]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sikkhamānaṃ—**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[13699]="*‘sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpeti na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[13700]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13701]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13702]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sikkhamānaṃ—**“How could the nun Thullanandā act in this way?*";
P_HTM[13703]="*‘sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpessati na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissati.* **";
P_HTM[13704]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …”*";
P_HTM[13705]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13706]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī sikkhamānaṃ—‘sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi, evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva vuṭṭhāpeyya na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun tells a trainee nun, “If you give me a robe, Venerable, I’ll give you the full admission,” but she then neither gives her the full admission nor makes any effort to have her fully admitted, then, if there was no obstruction, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13707]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13708]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13709]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13710]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13711]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[13712]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13713]="*Sace me tvaṃ, ayye, cīvaraṃ dassasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmīti**If you give me a robe, Venerable, I’ll give you the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13714]="*evāhaṃ taṃ upasampādessāmi.**I’ll give you the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13715]="*Sā pacchā anantarāyikinīti**Then, if there was no obstruction:*";
P_HTM[13716]="*asati antarāye.**when there is no obstacle.*";
P_HTM[13717]="*Neva vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**She neither gives her the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13718]="*na sayaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya.**does not herself give her the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13719]="*Na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyyāti**Nor makes any effort to have her fully admitted:*";
P_HTM[13720]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya.**does not ask anyone else to give her the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13721]="*“Neva vuṭṭhāpessāmi na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I’ll neither give her the full admission nor make any effort to have her fully admitted,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13722]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13723]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[13724]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches for someone to give her the full ordination, but is unable to find anyone;*";
P_HTM[13725]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[13726]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[13727]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13728]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13729]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13730]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13731]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13732]="*78. Dutiyasikkhamāna-navuṭṭhāpanasikkhāpada**78. The second training rule on not giving the full admission to trainee nuns*";
P_HTM[13733]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[13734]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā sikkhamānā thullanandaṃ bhikkhuniṃ upasaṅkamitvā upasampadaṃ yāci.**a trainee nun went to the nun Thullanandā and asked for the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13735]="*Thullanandā bhikkhunī taṃ sikkhamānaṃ “sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpeti na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karoti.**Thullanandā told her, “If you follow me for two years, Venerable, I’ll give you the full admission.” But she neither gave her the full admission nor made any effort to have her fully admitted.*";
P_HTM[13736]="*Atha kho sā sikkhamānā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**That trainee nun told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[13737]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13738]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā sikkhamānaṃ—**“How could Venerable Thullanandā say this to a trainee nun,*";
P_HTM[13739]="*‘sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpessati na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissatī”ti …pe…**but then neither give her the full admission nor make any effort to have her fully admitted?” …*";
P_HTM[13740]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sikkhamānaṃ—**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[13741]="*‘sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpeti na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karotī”ti?* **";
P_HTM[13742]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13743]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13744]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī sikkhamānaṃ—**“How could the nun Thullanandā act in this way?*";
P_HTM[13745]="*‘sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, neva vuṭṭhāpessati na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissati.* **";
P_HTM[13746]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13747]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13748]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī sikkhamānaṃ— ‘sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasi evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī’ti vatvā, sā pacchā anantarāyikinī neva vuṭṭhāpeyya na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun tells a trainee nun, “If you follow me for two years, Venerable, I’ll give you the full admission,” but she then neither gives her the full admission nor makes any effort to have her fully admitted, then, if there was no obstruction, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13749]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13750]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13751]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13752]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13753]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[13754]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13755]="*Sace maṃ tvaṃ, ayye, dve vassāni anubandhissasīti**“If you follow me for two years, Venerable”:*";
P_HTM[13756]="*dve saṃvaccharāni upaṭṭhahissasi.**if you attend on me for two twelve-month periods.*";
P_HTM[13757]="*Evāhaṃ taṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmīti**“I’ll give you the full admission”:*";
P_HTM[13758]="*evāhaṃ taṃ upasampādessāmi.**I’ll give you the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13759]="*Sā pacchā anantarāyikinīti**Then, if there was no obstruction:*";
P_HTM[13760]="*asati antarāye.**when there is no obstacle.*";
P_HTM[13761]="*Neva vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**She neither gives her the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13762]="*na sayaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya.**she does not herself give her the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13763]="*Na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ kareyyāti**Nor makes any effort to have her fully admitted:*";
P_HTM[13764]="*na aññaṃ āṇāpeyya.**she does not ask anyone else to give her the full admission.*";
P_HTM[13765]="*“Neva vuṭṭhāpessāmi na vuṭṭhāpanāya ussukkaṃ karissāmī”ti dhuraṃ nikkhittamatte āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she thinks, “I’ll neither give her the full admission nor make any effort to have her fully admitted,” then by the mere fact of giving up her duty, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[13766]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13767]="*sati antarāye,**if there is an obstacle;*";
P_HTM[13768]="*pariyesitvā na labhati,**if she searches for someone to give her the full ordination, but is unable to find anyone;*";
P_HTM[13769]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[13770]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[13771]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13772]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13773]="*Aṭṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eighth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13774]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13775]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13776]="*79. Sokāvāsasikkhāpada**79. The training rule on one who is difficult to live with*";
P_HTM[13777]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13778]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī purisasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ kumārakasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ caṇḍiṃ sokāvāsaṃ caṇḍakāḷiṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti.**At that time the nun Thullanandā gave the full admission to the trainee nun Caṇḍakāḷī, who was socializing with men and boys, and who was temperamental and difficult to live with.*";
P_HTM[13779]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13780]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā purisasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ kumārakasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ caṇḍiṃ sokāvāsaṃ caṇḍakāḷiṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give the full admission to the trainee nun Caṇḍakāḷī, who is socializing with men and boys, and who is temperamental and difficult to live with?” …*";
P_HTM[13781]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī purisasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ kumārakasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ caṇḍiṃ sokāvāsaṃ caṇḍakāḷiṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[13782]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13783]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13784]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī purisasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ kumārakasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ caṇḍiṃ sokāvāsaṃ caṇḍakāḷiṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[13785]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13786]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13787]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī purisasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ kumārakasaṃsaṭṭhaṃ caṇḍiṃ sokāvāsaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a trainee nun who is socializing with men and boys and who is temperamental and difficult to live with, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13788]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13789]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13790]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13791]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13792]="*Puriso nāma**Men:*";
P_HTM[13793]="*pattavīsativasso.**those who have reached twenty years of age.*";
P_HTM[13794]="*Kumārako nāma**Boys:*";
P_HTM[13795]="*appattavīsativasso.**those who have not reached twenty years of age.*";
P_HTM[13796]="*Saṃsaṭṭhā nāma**Socializing:*";
P_HTM[13797]="*ananulomikena kāyikavācasikena saṃsaṭṭhā.**she socializes with improper bodily and verbal actions.*";
P_HTM[13798]="*Caṇḍī nāma**Temperamental:*";
P_HTM[13799]="*kodhanā vuccati.**angry is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13800]="*Sokāvāsā nāma**Difficult to live with:*";
P_HTM[13801]="*paresaṃ dukkhaṃ uppādeti, sokaṃ āvisati.**she causes suffering to others, and grieves herself.*";
P_HTM[13802]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[13803]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13804]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13805]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13806]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13807]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13808]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13809]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa;**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13810]="*gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13811]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13812]="*ajānantī vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission without knowing what she is like;*";
P_HTM[13813]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13814]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13815]="*Navamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The ninth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13816]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13817]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13818]="*80. Ananuññātasikkhāpada**80. The training rule on lack of permission*";
P_HTM[13819]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13820]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī mātāpitūhipi sāmikenapi ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti.**At that time the nun Thullanandā gave the full admission to a trainee nun who had not been given permission by her parents and her husband.*";
P_HTM[13821]="*Mātāpitaropi sāmikopi ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**They complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13822]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā amhehi ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessatī”ti.**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give the full admission to that trainee nun without our permission?”*";
P_HTM[13823]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo mātāpitūnampi sāmikassapi ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of the parents and the husband.*";
P_HTM[13824]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13825]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā mātāpitūhipi sāmikenapi ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give the full admission to a trainee nun who doesn’t have permission from her parents and her husband?” …*";
P_HTM[13826]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī, mātāpitūhipi sāmikenapi ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[13827]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13828]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13829]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī mātāpitūhipi sāmikenapi ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[13830]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13831]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13832]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī mātāpitūhi vā sāmikena vā ananuññātaṃ sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to a trainee nun who has not been given permission by her parents or her husband, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13833]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13834]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13835]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13836]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13837]="*Mātāpitaro nāma**Parents:*";
P_HTM[13838]="*janakā vuccanti.**the biological parents is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[13839]="*Sāmiko nāma**Husband:*";
P_HTM[13840]="*yena pariggahitā hoti.**he who possesses her.*";
P_HTM[13841]="*Ananuññātāti**Who has not been given permission:*";
P_HTM[13842]="*anāpucchā.**who has not asked permission.*";
P_HTM[13843]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[13844]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13845]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13846]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13847]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13848]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13849]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13850]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13851]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13852]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13853]="*ajānantī vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission without knowing;*";
P_HTM[13854]="*apaloketvā vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission after getting permission;*";
P_HTM[13855]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13856]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13857]="*Dasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13858]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13859]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13860]="*81. Pārivāsikasikkhāpada**81. The training rule on what is expired*";
P_HTM[13861]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā rājagahe viharati veḷuvane kalandakanivāpe.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[13862]="*Tena kho pana samayena thullanandā bhikkhunī—**the nun Thullanandā*";
P_HTM[13863]="*“sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti there bhikkhū sannipātetvā pahūtaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ passitvā—**had gathered a group of senior monks, intending to give the full admission to a trainee nun. But after seeing much fresh and cooked food, she dismissed the senior monks, saying,*";
P_HTM[13864]="*“na tāvāhaṃ, ayyā, sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti there bhikkhū uyyojetvā devadattaṃ kokālikaṃ kaṭamodakatissakaṃ khaṇḍadeviyā puttaṃ samuddadattaṃ sannipātetvā sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpesi.**“Venerables, I won’t give the full admission to the trainee nun just yet.” She then gathered Devadatta, Kokālika, Kaṭamodakatissaka, Khaṇḍadeviyāputta, and Samuddadatta, and gave the full admission to that trainee nun.*";
P_HTM[13865]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[13866]="*“kathañhi nāma ayyā thullanandā pārivāsikachandadānena sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessatī”ti …pe…**“How could Venerable Thullanandā give the full admission to a trainee nun, when the given consent had expired?” …*";
P_HTM[13867]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī pārivāsikachandadānena sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpetī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nun Thullanandā did this?”*";
P_HTM[13868]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13869]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[13870]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, thullanandā bhikkhunī pārivāsikachandadānena sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpessati.**“How could the nun Thullanandā do this?*";
P_HTM[13871]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13872]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13873]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī pārivāsikachandadānena sikkhamānaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If, when any given consent has expired, a nun gives the full admission to a trainee nun, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13874]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13875]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13876]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13877]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13878]="*Pārivāsikachandadānenāti**When any given consent has expired:*";
P_HTM[13879]="*vuṭṭhitāya parisāya.**when the gathering has left.*";
P_HTM[13880]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[13881]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[13882]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission:*";
P_HTM[13883]="*upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13884]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13885]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13886]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13887]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13888]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13889]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13890]="*avuṭṭhitāya parisāya vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives her the full admission while the gathering has not yet left;*";
P_HTM[13891]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13892]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13893]="*Ekādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eleventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13894]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13895]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13896]="*82. Anuvassasikkhāpada**82. The training rule on every year*";
P_HTM[13897]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13898]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpenti, upassayo na sammati.**At that time the nuns were giving full admission every year, and the nuns’ dwelling place did not have sufficient capacity.*";
P_HTM[13899]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13900]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti, upassayo na sammatī”ti.**“How can the nuns give full admission every year, when the nuns’ dwelling place doesn’t have sufficient capacity?”*";
P_HTM[13901]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[13902]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13903]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns give full admission every year?” …*";
P_HTM[13904]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13905]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13906]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13907]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can the nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13908]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13909]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13910]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī anuvassaṃ vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives full admission every year, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13911]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13912]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13913]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13914]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13915]="*Anuvassanti**Every year:*";
P_HTM[13916]="*anusaṃvaccharaṃ.**every twelve-month period.*";
P_HTM[13917]="*Vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives full admission:*";
P_HTM[13918]="*upasampādeyya.**gives full ordination.*";
P_HTM[13919]="*“Vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give full admission, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13920]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13921]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13922]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13923]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13924]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13925]="*ekantarikaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives full admission every other year;*";
P_HTM[13926]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13927]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13928]="*Dvādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The twelfth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13929]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13930]="*Kumāribhūtavagga**The sub-chapter on unmarried girls*";
P_HTM[13931]="*83. Ekavassasikkhāpada**83. The training rule on one year*";
P_HTM[13932]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery.*";
P_HTM[13933]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpenti.**At that time the nuns were giving the full admission to two women per year,*";
P_HTM[13934]="*Upassayo tatheva na sammati.**and the nuns’ dwelling place still did not have sufficient capacity.*";
P_HTM[13935]="*Manussā tatheva ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13936]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can the nuns give the full admission to two women per year,*";
P_HTM[13937]="*Upassayo tatheva na sammatī”ti.**when the nuns’ dwelling place still doesn’t have sufficient capacity?”*";
P_HTM[13938]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[13939]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13940]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpessantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns give the full admission to two women per year?” …*";
P_HTM[13941]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13942]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13943]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13944]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpessanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[13945]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13946]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13947]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī ekaṃ vassaṃ dve vuṭṭhāpeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun gives the full admission to two women in one year, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13948]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13949]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13950]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13951]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13952]="*Ekaṃ vassanti**In one year:*";
P_HTM[13953]="*ekaṃ saṃvaccharaṃ.**in one twelve-month period.*";
P_HTM[13954]="*Dve vuṭṭhāpeyyāti**Gives the full admission to two women:*";
P_HTM[13955]="*dve upasampādeyya.**gives the full ordination to two women.*";
P_HTM[13956]="*“Dve vuṭṭhāpessāmī”ti gaṇaṃ vā ācariniṃ vā pattaṃ vā cīvaraṃ vā pariyesati, sīmaṃ vā sammannati, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, intending to give the full admission to two women, she searches for a group, a teacher, a bowl, or a robe, or she establishes a monastic boundary, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13957]="*Ñattiyā dukkaṭaṃ.**After the motion, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13958]="*Dvīhi kammavācāhi dukkaṭā.**After each of the first two announcements, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13959]="*Kammavācāpariyosāne upajjhāyāya āpatti pācittiyassa.**When the last announcement is finished, the preceptor commits an offense entailing confession,*";
P_HTM[13960]="*Gaṇassa ca ācariniyā ca āpatti dukkaṭassa.**and the group and the teacher commit an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[13961]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[13962]="*ekantarikaṃ ekaṃ vuṭṭhāpeti,**if she gives the full admission to one woman every other year;*";
P_HTM[13963]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[13964]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[13965]="*Terasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The thirteenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[13966]="*Kumāribhūtavaggo aṭṭhamo.**The eighth sub-chapter on unmarried girls is finished.*";
P_HTM[13967]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[13968]="*Chattupāhanavagga**The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[13969]="*84. Chattupāhanasikkhāpada**84. The training rule on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[13970]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[13971]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo chattupāhanaṃ dhārenti.**the nuns from the group of six used sunshades and sandals.*";
P_HTM[13972]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13973]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo chattupāhanaṃ dhāressanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns use sunshades and sandals? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[13974]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[13975]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[13976]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo chattupāhanaṃ dhāressantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six use sunshades and sandals?” …*";
P_HTM[13977]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo chattupāhanaṃ dhārentī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[13978]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[13979]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[13980]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo chattupāhanaṃ dhāressanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[13981]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[13982]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13983]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī chattupāhanaṃ dhāreyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun uses a sunshade and sandals, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13984]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[13985]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī gilānā hoti.**Soon afterwards there was a sick nun*";
P_HTM[13986]="*Tassā vinā chattupāhanaṃ na phāsu hoti …pe…**who was not comfortable without sandals and a sunshade. …*";
P_HTM[13987]="*bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. The Buddha then had the Sangha gathered and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[13988]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānāya bhikkhuniyā chattupāhanaṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick nun to use a sunshade and sandals.*";
P_HTM[13989]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And so, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[13990]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī agilānā chattupāhanaṃ dhāreyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun who is not sick uses a sunshade and sandals, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[13991]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[13992]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[13993]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[13994]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[13995]="*Agilānā nāma**Who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[13996]="*yassā vinā chattupāhanaṃ phāsu hoti.**who is comfortable without a sunshade and sandals.*";
P_HTM[13997]="*Gilānā nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[13998]="*yassā vinā chattupāhanaṃ na phāsu hoti.**who is not comfortable without a sunshade and sandals.*";
P_HTM[13999]="*Chattaṃ nāma**A sunshade:*";
P_HTM[14000]="*tīṇi chattāni— setacchattaṃ, kilañjacchattaṃ, paṇṇacchattaṃ maṇḍalabaddhaṃ salākabaddhaṃ.**there are three kinds of sunshades: the white sunshade, the reed sunshade, the leaf sunshade. They are bound at the rim and bound at the ribs.*";
P_HTM[14001]="*Dhāreyyāti**Uses:*";
P_HTM[14002]="*sakimpi dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she uses it even once, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14003]="*Agilānā agilānasaññā chattupāhanaṃ dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is not sick, and she does not perceive herself as sick, and she uses a sunshade and sandals, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14004]="*Agilānā vematikā chattupāhanaṃ dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is not sick, but she is unsure of it, and she uses a sunshade and sandals, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14005]="*Agilānā gilānasaññā chattupāhanaṃ dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is not sick, but she perceives herself as sick, and she uses a sunshade and sandals, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14006]="*Chattaṃ dhāreti na upāhanaṃ, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she uses a sunshade, but not sandals, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14007]="*Upāhanaṃ dhāreti na chattaṃ, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she uses sandals, but not a sunshade, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14008]="*Gilānā agilānasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is sick, but she does not perceive herself as sick, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14009]="*Gilānā vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is sick, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14010]="*Gilānā gilānasaññā, anāpatti.**If she is sick, and she perceives herself as sick, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[14011]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14012]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14013]="*ārāme ārāmūpacāre dhāreti,**if she uses them in a monastery or in the vicinity of a monastery;*";
P_HTM[14014]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14015]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14016]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14017]="*Paṭhamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14018]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[14019]="*Chattupāhanavagga**The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[14020]="*85. Yānasikkhāpada**85. The training rule on vehicles*";
P_HTM[14021]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14022]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo yānena yāyanti.**the nuns from the group of six were traveling in vehicles.*";
P_HTM[14023]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14024]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo yānena yāyissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can the nuns travel in a vehicle? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[14025]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[14026]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14027]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo yānena yāyissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six travel in a vehicle?” …*";
P_HTM[14028]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo yānena yāyantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14029]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14030]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14031]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo yānena yāyissanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[14032]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14033]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14034]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī yānena yāyeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun travels in a vehicle, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14035]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[14036]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī gilānā hoti, na sakkoti padasā gantuṃ …pe…**Soon afterwards there was a sick nun who was not able to travel on foot. …*";
P_HTM[14037]="*bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. The Buddha then had the Sangha gathered and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[14038]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānāya bhikkhuniyā yānaṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick nun to use a vehicle.*";
P_HTM[14039]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And so, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14040]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī agilānā yānena yāyeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun who is not sick travels in a vehicle, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14041]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14042]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14043]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14044]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14045]="*Agilānā nāma**Who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[14046]="*sakkoti padasā gantuṃ.**who is able to travel on foot.*";
P_HTM[14047]="*Gilānā nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[14048]="*na sakkoti padasā gantuṃ.**who is unable to travel on foot.*";
P_HTM[14049]="*Yānaṃ nāma**A vehicle:*";
P_HTM[14050]="*vayhaṃ ratho sakaṭaṃ sandamānikā sivikā pāṭaṅkī.**a wagon, a carriage, a cart, a chariot, a palanquin, a litter.*";
P_HTM[14051]="*Yāyeyyāti**Travels:*";
P_HTM[14052]="*sakimpi yānena yāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she travels in a vehicle even once, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14053]="*Agilānā agilānasaññā yānena yāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is not sick, and she does not perceive herself as sick, and she travels in a vehicle, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14054]="*Agilānā vematikā yānena yāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is not sick, but she is unsure of it, and she travels in a vehicle, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14055]="*Agilānā gilānasaññā yānena yāyati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she is not sick, but she perceives herself as sick, and she travels in a vehicle, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14056]="*Gilānā agilānasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is sick, but she does not perceive herself as sick, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14057]="*Gilānā vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is sick, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14058]="*Gilānā gilānasaññā, anāpatti.**If she is sick, and she perceives herself as sick, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[14059]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14060]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14061]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14062]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14063]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14064]="*Dutiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The second training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14065]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[14066]="*Chattupāhanavagga**The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[14067]="*86. Saṅghāṇisikkhāpada**86. The training rule on ornamentations of the hip*";
P_HTM[14068]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14069]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī aññatarissā itthiyā kulūpikā hoti.**there was a nun was associating with the family of a certain woman.*";
P_HTM[14070]="*Atha kho sā itthī taṃ bhikkhuniṃ etadavoca—**That woman said to that nun,*";
P_HTM[14071]="*“handāyye, imaṃ saṅghāṇiṃ amukāya nāma itthiyā dehī”ti.**“Venerable, please give this hip ornament to such-and-such a woman.”*";
P_HTM[14072]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī—**The nun thought,*";
P_HTM[14073]="*“sacāhaṃ pattena ādāya gacchāmi vissaro me bhavissatī”ti paṭimuñcitvā agamāsi.**“If I carry it in my almsbowl, I’ll get into trouble,” and so she put it on and then left.*";
P_HTM[14074]="*Tassā rathikāya suttake chinne vippakiriyiṃsu.**While she was walking along a street the threads snapped and were scattered all over.*";
P_HTM[14075]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[14076]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo saṅghāṇiṃ dhāressanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns wear hip ornaments? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[14077]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[14078]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[14079]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī saṅghāṇiṃ dhāressatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun wear a hip ornament?” …*";
P_HTM[14080]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī saṅghāṇiṃ dhāretī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[14081]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14082]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[14083]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī saṅghāṇiṃ dhāressati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[14084]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14085]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14086]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī saṅghāṇiṃ dhāreyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun wears a hip ornament, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14087]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14088]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14089]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14090]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14091]="*Saṅghāṇi nāma**A hip ornament:*";
P_HTM[14092]="*yā kāci kaṭūpagā.**whatever goes on the hip.*";
P_HTM[14093]="*Dhāreyyāti**Wears:*";
P_HTM[14094]="*sakimpi dhāreti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she wears it even once, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14095]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14096]="*ābādhappaccayā,**if she wears it because she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14097]="*kaṭisuttakaṃ dhāreti,**if she wears a girdle;*";
P_HTM[14098]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14099]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14100]="*Tatiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The third training rule is finished.*";
