P_HTM[14198]="*90. Bhikkhuniummaddāpanasikkhāpada**90. The training rule on having nuns massage*";
P_HTM[14199]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14200]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpentipi parimaddāpentipi.**the nuns were having other nuns massage and rub them.*";
P_HTM[14201]="*Manussā vihāracārikaṃ āhiṇḍantā passitvā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**When people walking about the dwellings saw this, they complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14202]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpessantipi parimaddāpessantipi, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns get other nuns to massage and rub them? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[14203]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[14204]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14205]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpessantipi parimaddāpessantipī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns get other nuns to massage and rub them?” …*";
P_HTM[14206]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpentipi parimaddāpentipī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14207]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14208]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14209]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpessantipi parimaddāpessantipi.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[14210]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14211]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14212]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhuniyā ummaddāpeyya vā parimaddāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun has a nun massage her or rub her, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14213]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14214]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14215]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14216]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14217]="*Bhikkhuniyāti**A nun:*";
P_HTM[14218]="*aññāya bhikkhuniyā.**another nun.*";
P_HTM[14219]="*Ummaddāpeyya vāti**If she has a nun massage her:*";
P_HTM[14220]="*ummaddāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she gets her to massage her, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14221]="*Parimaddāpeyya vāti**Or if she has a nun rub her:*";
P_HTM[14222]="*sambāhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she gets her to rub her, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14223]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14224]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14225]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14226]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14227]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14228]="*Sattamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The seventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14229]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
