P_HTM[14237]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo gihiniyā ummaddāpessantipi parimaddāpessantipi, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can the nuns get female householders to massage and rub them? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[14238]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[14239]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe…  tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14240]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo gihiniyā ummaddāpessantipi parimaddāpessantipī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns get female householders to massage and rub them?”*";
P_HTM[14241]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo gihiniyā ummaddāpentipi parimaddāpentipī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that the nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14242]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14243]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14244]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo gihiniyā ummaddāpessantipi parimaddāpessantipi.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[14245]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14246]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14247]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī (sikkhamānāya …pe…  sāmaṇeriyā …pe… ) gihiniyā ummaddāpeyya vā parimaddāpeyya vā, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun has (a trainee nun … a novice nun …) a female householder massage her or rub her, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14248]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14249]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14250]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14251]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14252]="*Sikkhamānā nāma**A trainee nun:*";
P_HTM[14253]="*dve vassāni chasu dhammesu sikkhitasikkhā.**one who has trained for two years in the six rules.*";
P_HTM[14254]="*Sāmaṇerī nāma**A novice nun:*";
P_HTM[14255]="*dasasikkhāpadikā.**a female training in the ten training rules.*";
P_HTM[14256]="*Gihinī nāma**A female householder:*";
P_HTM[14257]="*agārinī vuccati.**a female who lives in a house is what is meant.*";
P_HTM[14258]="*Ummaddāpeyya vāti**If she has her massage her:*";
P_HTM[14259]="*ummaddāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she gets her to massage her, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14260]="*Parimaddāpeyya vāti**If she has her rub her:*";
P_HTM[14261]="*sambāhāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she gets her to rub her, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14262]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14263]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14264]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14265]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14266]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14267]="*Aṭṭhama-navama-dasamasikkhāpadāni niṭṭhitāni.**The tenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14268]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[14269]="*Chattupāhanavagga**The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[14270]="*94. Anāpucchāsikkhāpada**94. The training rule on not asking permission*";
P_HTM[14271]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14272]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo bhikkhussa purato anāpucchā āsane nisīdanti.**nuns sat down on seats in front of a monk without asking permission.*";
P_HTM[14273]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14274]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo bhikkhussa purato anāpucchā āsane nisīdissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns sit down on seats in front of a monk without asking permission?” …*";
P_HTM[14275]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhussa purato anāpucchā āsane nisīdantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14276]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14277]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14278]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo bhikkhussa purato anāpucchā āsane nisīdissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[14279]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14280]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14281]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī bhikkhussa purato anāpucchā āsane nisīdeyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun sits down on a seat in front of a monk without asking permission, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14282]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14283]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14284]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14285]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14286]="*Bhikkhussa puratoti**In front of a monk:*";
P_HTM[14287]="*upasampannassa purato.**in front of one who is fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[14288]="*Anāpucchāti**Without asking permission:*";
P_HTM[14289]="*anapaloketvā.**without getting permission.*";
P_HTM[14290]="*Āsane nisīdeyyāti**Sits down on a seat:*";
P_HTM[14291]="*antamaso chamāyapi nisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**even if she sits down on the ground, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14292]="*Anāpucchite anāpucchitasaññā āsane nisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, and she does not perceive that she has, and she sits down on a seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14293]="*Anāpucchite vematikā āsane nisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she is unsure of it, and she sits down on a seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14294]="*Anāpucchite āpucchitasaññā āsane nisīdati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she perceives that she has, and she sits down on a seat, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14295]="*Āpucchite anāpucchitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she does not perceive that she has, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14296]="*Āpucchite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14297]="*Āpucchite āpucchitasaññā, anāpatti.**If she has asked permission, and she perceives that she has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[14298]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14299]="*āpucchā āsane nisīdati,**if she sits down on the seat after asking permission;*";
P_HTM[14300]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14301]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14302]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14303]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14304]="*Ekādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The eleventh training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14305]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[14306]="*Chattupāhanavagga**The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[14307]="*95. Pañhāpucchanasikkhāpada**95. The training rule on asking questions*";
P_HTM[14308]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14309]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo anokāsakataṃ bhikkhuṃ pañhaṃ pucchanti.**the nuns asked questions of a monk who had not given permission.*";
P_HTM[14310]="*Bhikkhū ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The monks complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14311]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo anokāsakataṃ bhikkhuṃ pañhaṃ pucchissantī”ti …pe…**“How can nuns ask questions of a monk who hasn’t given permission?” …*";
P_HTM[14312]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo anokāsakataṃ bhikkhuṃ pañhaṃ pucchantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14313]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14314]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14315]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo anokāsakataṃ bhikkhuṃ pañhaṃ pucchissanti.**“How can nuns do this?*";
P_HTM[14316]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14317]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14318]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī anokāsakataṃ bhikkhuṃ pañhaṃ puccheyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun asks a question of a monk who has not given permission, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14319]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14320]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14321]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14322]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14323]="*Anokāsakatanti**Who has not given permission:*";
P_HTM[14324]="*anāpucchā.**without asking permission.*";
P_HTM[14325]="*Bhikkhunti**A monk:*";
P_HTM[14326]="*upasampannaṃ.**one who is fully ordained.*";
P_HTM[14327]="*Pañhaṃ puccheyyāti**Asks a question:*";
P_HTM[14328]="*suttante okāsaṃ kārāpetvā vinayaṃ vā abhidhammaṃ vā pucchati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she gets permission to ask about the discourses, but she asks about the Monastic Law or philosophy, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14329]="*Vinaye okāsaṃ kārāpetvā suttantaṃ vā abhidhammaṃ vā pucchati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she gets permission to ask about the Monastic Law, but she asks about the discourses or philosophy, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14330]="*Abhidhamme okāsaṃ kārāpetvā suttantaṃ vā vinayaṃ vā pucchati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she gets permission to ask about philosophy, but she asks about the discourses or the Monastic Law, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14331]="*Anāpucchite anāpucchitasaññā pañhaṃ pucchati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, and she does not perceive that she has, and she asks a question, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14332]="*Anāpucchite vematikā pañhaṃ pucchati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she is unsure of it, and she asks a question, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14333]="*Anāpucchite āpucchitasaññā pañhaṃ pucchati, āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she has not asked permission, but she perceives that she has, and she asks a question, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14334]="*Āpucchite anāpucchitasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she does not perceive that she has, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14335]="*Āpucchite vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she has asked permission, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14336]="*Āpucchite āpucchitasaññā, anāpatti.**If she has asked permission, and she perceives that she has, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[14337]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14338]="*okāsaṃ kārāpetvā pucchati,**if she asks after getting permission;*";
P_HTM[14339]="*anodissa okāsaṃ kārāpetvā yattha katthaci pucchati,**if she gets permission, but not in regard to a specific subject, and she then asks about any subject;*";
P_HTM[14340]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14341]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14342]="*Dvādasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The twelfth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14343]="*127. Pācittiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing confession *";
P_HTM[14344]="*Chattupāhanavagga**The sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals*";
P_HTM[14345]="*96. Asaṅkaccikasikkhāpada**96. The training rule on not wearing a chest wrap*";
P_HTM[14346]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14347]="*Tena kho pana samayena aññatarā bhikkhunī asaṅkaccikā gāmaṃ piṇḍāya pāvisi.**a nun had entered a village for almsfood without wearing her chest wrap.*";
P_HTM[14348]="*Tassā rathikāya vātamaṇḍalikā saṅghāṭiyo ukkhipiṃsu.**While she was walking along a street, a whirlwind lifted up her upper robes.*";
P_HTM[14349]="*Manussā ukkuṭṭhiṃ akaṃsu—**People shouted out,*";
P_HTM[14350]="*“sundarā ayyāya thanudarā”ti.**“She has beautiful breasts and stomach!”*";
P_HTM[14351]="*Sā bhikkhunī tehi manussehi uppaṇḍiyamānā maṅku ahosi.**Because she was teased by those people, she felt humiliated.*";
P_HTM[14352]="*Atha kho sā bhikkhunī upassayaṃ gantvā bhikkhunīnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesi.**After returning to the nuns’ dwelling place, she told the nuns what had happened.*";
P_HTM[14353]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized her,*";
P_HTM[14354]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhunī asaṅkaccikā gāmaṃ pavisissatī”ti …pe…**“How could a nun enter an inhabited area without wearing her chest wrap?” …*";
P_HTM[14355]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī asaṅkaccikā gāmaṃ pāvisī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that a nun did this?”*";
P_HTM[14356]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14357]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized her …*";
P_HTM[14358]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, bhikkhunī asaṅkaccikā gāmaṃ pavisissati.**“How could a nun do this?*";
P_HTM[14359]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14360]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14361]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī asaṅkaccikā gāmaṃ paviseyya, pācittiyan”ti.**‘If a nun enters an inhabited area without wearing her chest wrap, she commits an offense entailing confession.’”*";
P_HTM[14362]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14363]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14364]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14365]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14366]="*Asaṅkaccikāti**Without wearing her chest wrap:*";
P_HTM[14367]="*vinā saṅkaccikaṃ.**not wearing her chest wrap.*";
P_HTM[14368]="*Saṅkaccikaṃ nāma**Chest wrap:*";
P_HTM[14369]="*adhakkhakaṃ ubbhanābhi, tassa paṭicchādanatthāya.**it is for the purpose of concealing the body below the collar bone and above the navel.*";
P_HTM[14370]="*Gāmaṃ paviseyyāti**Enters an inhabited area:*";
P_HTM[14371]="*parikkhittassa gāmassa parikkhepaṃ atikkāmentiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**if she crosses the boundary of an enclosed inhabited area, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14372]="*Aparikkhittassa gāmassa upacāraṃ okkamantiyā āpatti pācittiyassa.**If she enters the vicinity of an unenclosed inhabited area, she commits an offense entailing confession.*";
P_HTM[14373]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14374]="*acchinnacīvarikāya,**if her robe is stolen;*";
P_HTM[14375]="*naṭṭhacīvarikāya,**if her robe is lost;*";
P_HTM[14376]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14377]="*assatiyā,**if she is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[14378]="*ajānantiyā,**if she does not know;*";
P_HTM[14379]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14380]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14381]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14382]="*Terasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The thirteenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14383]="*Chattupāhanavaggo navamo.**The ninth sub-chapter on sunshades and sandals is finished.*";
P_HTM[14384]="*Dhammikavagga* **";
P_HTM[14385]="*Nandasikkhāpada* **";
P_HTM[14386]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, chasaṭṭhisatā pācittiyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the one hundred and sixty-six rules on confession have been recited.*";
P_HTM[14387]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[14388]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14389]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14390]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14391]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14392]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14393]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[14394]="*Khuddakaṃ samattaṃ.**The section on minor rules has been completed.*";
P_HTM[14395]="*Bhikkhunivibhaṅge pācittiyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing confession in the nuns’ analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[14396]="*(…)* **";
P_HTM[14397]="*127. Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment *";
P_HTM[14398]="*1. Sappiviññāpanasikkhāpada**1. The training rule on asking for ghee*";
P_HTM[14399]="*Ime kho panāyyāyo aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these eight rules on acknowledgment come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[14400]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14401]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**the nuns from the group of six were eating ghee that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14402]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14403]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can nuns eat ghee that they have asked for?*";
P_HTM[14404]="*Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti.**Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t prefer tasty food?”*";
P_HTM[14405]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[14406]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā …pe… tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14407]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjissantī”ti …pe…**“How can the nuns from the group of six eat ghee that they have asked for?” …*";
P_HTM[14408]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā, bhikkhuniyo sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjantī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14409]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14410]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14411]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[14412]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14413]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**“And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14414]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjeyya, paṭidesetabbaṃ tāya bhikkhuniyā—**‘If a nun asks for ghee and then eats it, she must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[14415]="*‘gārayhaṃ, ayye, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ, taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[14416]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[14417]="*Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhuniyo gilānā honti.**Soon afterwards a number of nuns were sick.*";
P_HTM[14418]="*Gilānapucchikā bhikkhuniyo gilānā bhikkhuniyo etadavocuṃ—**The nuns who were looking after them asked,*";
P_HTM[14419]="*“kacci, ayye, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?**“I hope you’re bearing up? I hope you’re getting better?”*";
P_HTM[14420]="*“Pubbe mayaṃ, ayye, sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjāma, tena no phāsu hoti;**“Previously we ate ghee that we had asked for, and then we were comfortable.*";
P_HTM[14421]="*idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na viññāpema, tena no na phāsu hotī”ti …pe…**But now that the Buddha has prohibited this, we don’t ask because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. And because of that we’re not comfortable.” …*";
P_HTM[14422]="*bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[14423]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānāya bhikkhuniyā sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjituṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick nun to eat ghee that she has asked for.*";
P_HTM[14424]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And so, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14425]="*“Yā pana bhikkhunī agilānā sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjeyya, paṭidesetabbaṃ tāya bhikkhuniyā—**‘If a nun who is not sick asks for ghee and then eats it, she must acknowledge it:*";
P_HTM[14426]="*‘gārayhaṃ, ayye, dhammaṃ āpajjiṃ asappāyaṃ pāṭidesanīyaṃ taṃ paṭidesemī’”ti.**“I have done a blameworthy and unsuitable thing that is to be acknowledged. I acknowledge it.”’”*";
P_HTM[14427]="*Yā panāti**A:*";
P_HTM[14428]="*yā yādisā …pe…**whoever …*";
P_HTM[14429]="*bhikkhunīti**Nun:*";
P_HTM[14430]="*…pe… ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippetā bhikkhunīti.**… The nun who has been given the full ordination in unanimity by both Sanghas through a legal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is irreversible and fit to stand—this sort of nun is meant in this case.*";
P_HTM[14431]="*Agilānā nāma**who is not sick:*";
P_HTM[14432]="*yassā vinā sappinā phāsu hoti.**who is comfortable without ghee.*";
P_HTM[14433]="*Gilānā nāma**Who is sick:*";
P_HTM[14434]="*yassā vinā sappinā na phāsu hoti.**who is not comfortable without ghee.*";
P_HTM[14435]="*Sappi nāma**Ghee:*";
P_HTM[14436]="*gosappi vā ajikāsappi vā mahiṃsasappi vā. Yesaṃ maṃsaṃ kappati tesaṃ sappi.**ghee from cows, ghee from goats, ghee from buffaloes, or ghee from whatever animal whose meat is allowable.*";
P_HTM[14437]="*Agilānā attano atthāya viññāpeti, payoge dukkaṭaṃ.**If she is not sick and she asks for herself, then for the effort there is an act of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14438]="*Paṭilābhena “bhuñjissāmī”ti paṭiggaṇhāti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**When she receives it with the intention of eating it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14439]="*Ajjhohāre ajjhohāre āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**For every mouthful, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[14440]="*Agilānā agilānasaññā sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is not sick, and she does not perceive herself as sick, and she eats ghee that she has asked for, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[14441]="*Agilānā vematikā sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is not sick, but she is unsure of it, and she eats ghee that she has asked for, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[14442]="*Agilānā gilānasaññā sappiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjati, āpatti pāṭidesanīyassa.**If she is not sick, but she perceives herself as sick, and she eats ghee that she has asked for, she commits an offense entailing acknowledgment.*";
P_HTM[14443]="*Gilānā agilānasaññā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is sick, but she does not perceive herself as sick, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14444]="*Gilānā vematikā, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If she is sick, but she is unsure of it, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14445]="*Gilānā gilānasaññā, anāpatti.**If she is sick, and she perceives herself as sick, there is no offense.*";
P_HTM[14446]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14447]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14448]="*gilānā hutvā viññāpetvā agilānā bhuñjati,**if she asked for it when she was sick, but eats it when she is no longer sick;*";
P_HTM[14449]="*gilānāya sesakaṃ bhuñjati,**if she eats the leftovers from one who is sick;*";
P_HTM[14450]="*ñātakānaṃ,**if it is from relatives;*";
P_HTM[14451]="*pavāritānaṃ,**if it is from those who have given an invitation;*";
P_HTM[14452]="*aññassatthāya,**if it is for the benefit of someone else;*";
P_HTM[14453]="*attano dhanena,**if it is by means of her own property;*";
P_HTM[14454]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14455]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14456]="*Paṭhamapāṭidesanīyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The first training rule on acknowledgment is finished.*";
P_HTM[14457]="*127. 2.5 Pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment *";
P_HTM[14458]="*2.5.2–8 Tela-madhu-phāṇita-maccha-maṃsa-khīra-dadhiviññāpanasikkhāpada**2–8. The training rules on asking for oil … honey … syrup … fish … meat … milk … curd*";
P_HTM[14459]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14460]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo telaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**the nuns from the group of six were eating oil that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14461]="*…pe… madhuṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**… were eating honey that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14462]="*…pe… phāṇitaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**… were eating syrup that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14463]="*…pe… macchaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**… were eating fish that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14464]="*…pe… maṃsaṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**… were eating meat that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14465]="*…pe… khīraṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**… were drinking milk that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14466]="*…pe… dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjanti.**… were eating curd that they had asked for.*";
P_HTM[14467]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14468]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo dadhiṃ viññāpetvā bhuñjissanti.**“How can nuns eat curd that they have asked for?*";
P_HTM[14469]="*Kassa sampannaṃ na manāpaṃ, kassa sāduṃ na ruccatī”ti.**Who doesn’t like nice food? Who doesn’t prefer tasty food?”*";
P_HTM[14470]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people.*";
P_HTM[14471]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā … pe … tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**The nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
