P_HTM[14540]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the eight rules on acknowledgment have been recited.*";
P_HTM[14541]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[14542]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14543]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14544]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14545]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14546]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14547]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[14548]="*Bhikkhunivibhaṅge pāṭidesanīyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on offenses entailing acknowledgment in the nuns’ analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[14549]="*127. Sekhiyakaṇḍa **127.  The chapter on training *";
P_HTM[14550]="*Parimaṇḍalavagga**The sub-chapter on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[14551]="*1. Parimaṇḍalasikkhāpada**1. The training rule on evenly all around*";
P_HTM[14552]="*Ime kho panāyyāyo sekhiyā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these rules to be trained in come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[14553]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14554]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo puratopi pacchatopi olambentī nivāsenti.**the nuns from the group of six wore their sarongs hanging down in front and behind.*";
