P_HTM[14563]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo puratopi pacchatopi olambentī nivāsessanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[14564]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14565]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14566]="*“Parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsessāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will wear my sarong evenly all around,” this is how you should train.’*";
P_HTM[14567]="*Parimaṇḍalaṃ nivāsetabbaṃ nābhimaṇḍalaṃ jāṇumaṇḍalaṃ paṭicchādentiyā.**One should wear one’s sarong evenly all around, covering the navel and the knees.*";
P_HTM[14568]="*Yā anādariyaṃ paṭicca purato vā pacchato vā olambentī nivāseti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If a nun, out of disrespect, wears her sarong hanging down in front or behind, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14569]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14570]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[14571]="*assatiyā,**if she is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[14572]="*ajānantiyā,**if she does not know;*";
P_HTM[14573]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14574]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14575]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14576]="*ādikammikāyāti …pe…**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14577]="*(Saṅkhittaṃ.)**(Contracted.)*";
P_HTM[14578]="*7. Pādukavagga**The sub-chapter on shoes*";
P_HTM[14579]="*7.15 Udakeuccārasikkhāpada**75. the training rule on defecating in water*";
P_HTM[14580]="*Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme.**At one time when the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery,*";
P_HTM[14581]="*Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karonti.**the nuns from the group of six were defecating, urinating, and spitting in water.*";
P_HTM[14582]="*Manussā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**People complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14583]="*“kathañhi nāma bhikkhuniyo udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karissanti, seyyathāpi gihiniyo kāmabhoginiyo”ti.**“How can nuns defecate, urinate, and spit in water? They are just like householders who indulge in worldly pleasures!”*";
P_HTM[14584]="*Assosuṃ kho bhikkhuniyo tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ.**The nuns heard the complaints of those people,*";
P_HTM[14585]="*Yā tā bhikkhuniyo appicchā, tā ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—**and the nuns of few desires complained and criticized them,*";
P_HTM[14586]="*“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karissantī”ti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six defecate, urinate, and spit in water?”*";
P_HTM[14587]="*Atha kho bhikkhuniyo bhikkhūnaṃ etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**The nuns told the monks,*";
P_HTM[14588]="*Bhikkhū bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ.**who in turn told the Buddha.*";
P_HTM[14589]="*Atha kho bhagavā …pe…**Soon afterwards the Buddha had the Sangha gathered*";
P_HTM[14590]="*bhikkhū paṭipucchi—**and questioned the monks:*";
P_HTM[14591]="*“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karontī”ti?**“Is it true, monks, that those nuns do this?”*";
P_HTM[14592]="*“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti.**“It’s true, Sir.”*";
P_HTM[14593]="*Vigarahi buddho bhagavā …pe…**The Buddha criticized them …*";
P_HTM[14594]="*kathañhi nāma, bhikkhave, chabbaggiyā bhikkhuniyo udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi karissanti.**“How can the nuns from the group of six do this?*";
P_HTM[14595]="*Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya …pe…**This will affect people’s confidence …” …*";
P_HTM[14596]="*evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14597]="*“Na udake uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“I will not defecate, urinate, or spit in water,” this is how you should train.’*";
P_HTM[14598]="*Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhunīnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti.**In this way the Buddha laid down this training rule for the nuns.*";
P_HTM[14599]="*Tena kho pana samayena gilānā bhikkhuniyo udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi kātuṃ kukkuccāyanti.**Soon afterwards, being afraid of wrongdoing, sick nuns did not defecate, urinate, or spit in water.*";
P_HTM[14600]="*Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ …pe…**They told the Buddha. He then had the Sangha gathered and addressed the monks:*";
P_HTM[14601]="*anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānāya bhikkhuniyā udake uccārampi passāvampi kheḷampi kātuṃ.**“Monks, I allow a sick nun to defecate, urinate, and spit in water.*";
P_HTM[14602]="*Evañca pana, bhikkhave, bhikkhuniyo imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddisantu—**And so, monks, the nuns should recite this training rule like this:*";
P_HTM[14603]="*“Na udake agilānā uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karissāmīti sikkhā karaṇīyā”ti.**‘“When not sick, I will not defecate, urinate, or spit in water,” this is how you should train.’*";
P_HTM[14604]="*Na udake agilānāya uccāro vā passāvo vā kheḷo vā kātabbo.**If one is not sick, one should not defecate, urinate, or spit in water.*";
P_HTM[14605]="*Yā anādariyaṃ paṭicca udake agilānā uccāraṃ vā passāvaṃ vā kheḷaṃ vā karoti, āpatti dukkaṭassa.**If, out of disrespect, a nun who is not sick defecates, urinates, or spits in water, she commits an offense of wrong conduct.*";
P_HTM[14606]="*Anāpatti—**There is no offense:*";
P_HTM[14607]="*asañcicca,**if it is unintentional;*";
P_HTM[14608]="*assatiyā,**if she is not mindful;*";
P_HTM[14609]="*ajānantiyā,**if she does not know;*";
P_HTM[14610]="*gilānāya,**if she is sick;*";
P_HTM[14611]="*thale kato udakaṃ ottharati,**if she does it on dry ground, but it then spreads to water;*";
P_HTM[14612]="*āpadāsu,**if there are dangers;*";
P_HTM[14613]="*ummattikāya,**if she is insane;*";
P_HTM[14614]="*khittacittāya,**if she is deranged;*";
P_HTM[14615]="*vedanāṭṭāya,**if she is overwhelmed by pain;*";
P_HTM[14616]="*ādikammikāyāti.**if she is the first offender.*";
P_HTM[14617]="*Pannarasamasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The fifteenth training rule is finished.*";
P_HTM[14618]="*Pādukavaggo sattamo.**The seventh sub-chapter on shoes is finished.*";
P_HTM[14619]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, sekhiyā dhammā.**“Venerables, the rules to be trained in have been recited.*";
P_HTM[14620]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[14621]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14622]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14623]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14624]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14625]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14626]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[14627]="*Sekhiyakaṇḍaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ.**The chapter on training is finished.*";
P_HTM[14628]="*127. Adhikaraṇasamatha **127.  The settling of legal issues *";
P_HTM[14629]="*Ime kho panāyyāyo satta adhikaraṇasamathā dhammā uddesaṃ āgacchanti.**Venerables, these seven principles for the settling of legal issues come up for recitation.*";
P_HTM[14630]="*Uppannuppannānaṃ adhikaraṇānaṃ samathāya vūpasamāya**“For the settling and resolving of legal issues whenever they arise there is:*";
P_HTM[14631]="*sammukhāvinayo dātabbo,**Resolution face-to-face to be applied;*";
P_HTM[14632]="*sativinayo dātabbo,**Resolution through recollection to be granted;*";
P_HTM[14633]="*amūḷhavinayo dātabbo,**Resolution because of past insanity to be granted;*";
P_HTM[14634]="*paṭiññāya kāretabbaṃ,**Acting according to what has been admitted;*";
P_HTM[14635]="*yebhuyyasikā,**Majority decision;*";
P_HTM[14636]="*tassapāpiyasikā,**Further penalty;*";
P_HTM[14637]="*tiṇavatthārakoti.**Covering over as if with grass.*";
P_HTM[14638]="*Uddiṭṭhā kho, ayyāyo, satta adhikaraṇasamathā dhammā.**Venerables, the seven principles for the settling of legal issues have been recited.*";
P_HTM[14639]="*Tatthāyyāyo pucchāmi—**In regard to this I ask you,*";
P_HTM[14640]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14641]="*Dutiyampi pucchāmi—**A second time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14642]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14643]="*Tatiyampi pucchāmi—**A third time I ask,*";
P_HTM[14644]="*“kaccittha parisuddhā”?**‘Are you pure in this?’*";
P_HTM[14645]="*Parisuddhetthāyyāyo, tasmā tuṇhī, evametaṃ dhārayāmīti.**You are pure in this and therefore silent. I will remember it thus.”*";
P_HTM[14646]="*Adhikaraṇasamathā niṭṭhitā.**The seven principles for the settling of legal issues are finished.*";
P_HTM[14647]="*Uddiṭṭhaṃ kho, ayyāyo, nidānaṃ.**“Venerables, the introduction has been recited;*";
P_HTM[14648]="*Uddiṭṭhā aṭṭha pārājikā dhammā.**the eight rules on expulsion have been recited;*";
P_HTM[14649]="*Uddiṭṭhā sattarasa saṅghādisesā dhammā.**the seventeen rules on suspension have been recited;*";
P_HTM[14650]="*Uddiṭṭhā tiṃsa nissaggiyā pācittiyā dhammā.**the thirty rules on relinquishment and confession have been recited;*";
P_HTM[14651]="*Uddiṭṭhā chasaṭṭhisatā pācittiyā dhammā.**the one hundred and sixty-six rules on confession have been recited;*";
P_HTM[14652]="*Uddiṭṭhā aṭṭha pāṭidesanīyā dhammā.**the eight rules on acknowledgment have been recited;*";
P_HTM[14653]="*Uddiṭṭhā sekhiyā dhammā.**the rules to be trained in have been recited;*";
P_HTM[14654]="*Uddiṭṭhā satta adhikaraṇasamathā dhammā.**the seven principles for the settling of legal issues have been recited.*";
P_HTM[14655]="*Ettakaṃ tassa bhagavato suttāgataṃ suttapariyāpannaṃ anvaddhamāsaṃ uddesaṃ āgacchati.**This much has come down and is included in the Monastic Code of the Buddha and comes up for recitation every half-month.*";
P_HTM[14656]="*Tattha sabbāheva samaggāhi sammodamānāhi avivadamānāhi sikkhitabbanti.**In regard to this everyone should train in unity, in concord, without dispute.”*";
P_HTM[14657]="*Bhikkhunivibhaṅgo niṭṭhito.**The nuns’ rules and their analysis is finished.*";
P_HTM[14658]="*Pācittiyapāḷi niṭṭhitā.**The canonical text beginning with offenses entailing confession is finished.*";
